INSERT INTO `hotels` VALUES (1,NULL,1,NULL,'','','','','hotela name','',NULL,'','',NULL,'',NULL,0,1,0,'2014-08-21 22:25:11','2014-08-21 22:25:11',NULL),(2,NULL,1,NULL,'','','','','','',NULL,'','',NULL,'',NULL,0,1,0,'2014-08-21 22:27:25','2014-08-21 22:27:25',NULL),(3,NULL,1,NULL,'','','','','','',NULL,'','',NULL,'',NULL,0,1,0,'2014-08-21 22:28:17','2014-08-21 22:28:17',NULL),(4,NULL,1,NULL,'','','','','','',NULL,'','',NULL,'',NULL,0,1,0,'2014-08-21 22:29:06','2014-08-21 22:29:06',NULL),(5,NULL,1,NULL,'','','','','','',NULL,'','',NULL,'',NULL,0,1,0,'2014-08-21 22:29:41','2014-08-21 22:29:41',NULL),(20,NULL,2,13,'','','','asdasdasd','Hotel MAradonio','asda asd asda','','','','','<h2>Description</h2>\r\n\r\n<p>Undoubtedly one of Arequipa&rsquo;s finest hotels, this former 18th century Mint House (now a historic monument) has been lovingly restored and boasts the original manor house as well as an adjacent modern complex, plus 2 spacious colonial courtyards.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Careful restor<strong>ation in 2008 helped unveil the building&rsquo;s rich history by exposing previously hidden frescoes, gold-leaf murals, and an exquisite chapel. Elegant d&eacute;cor and furnishings help to further transport guests back to colonial times, yet now with all the com</strong>forts of the modern era.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Just steps away from the gorgeous Santa Catalina Convent, and only a few blocks from other attractions in the historic center, Casa Andina Private Collection Arequipa is the perfect place to relax and enjoy the stately beauty of Arequipa. The hotel&rsquo;s fourth floor terrace opens up to unrivaled views of El Misti, a volcano that towers in the city&rsquo;s backdrop. This is a great place for guests to bask in the sunshine. On the ground level, accessible from the main sunlit courtyard, is a small mint museum exhibiting the manor&rsquo;s past, a sleek bar, and the hotel&rsquo;s on-site gourmet restaurant serving Novoandina cuisine.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>The 2 rooms of the elegant Alma restaurant open onto the splendid courtyard and entice guests to take a moment to sit back and contemplate the tranquility of the setting over creative regional and national cuisine such as grilled ostrich, crayfish chowder, and stuffed rocoto peppers. The rich colors of the stone walls and hardwood floors are attractively contrasted with light green trimmings and crisp white tablecloths. All meals are served here; breakfasts are also served out under the covered section of the courtyard.</p>\r\n\r\n<h2>Room Amenities</h2>\r\n\r\n<p>The Casa Andina Private Collection Arequipa Hotel offers 41 immaculate guestrooms, 3 of which are housed within the original manor house while the others are located within the newer 4-story building, just off the second courtyard. All guestrooms are spacious and comfortable, but 3 senior suites and a single imperial suite contain the most colonial characteristics.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>The stone walls and vaulted ceilings reflect a long gone era, and as the sun filters in from wrought iron windows, it is easy to lose oneself in the charm of what was once colonial Peru. The coveted Imperial Suite features this and more: a private entrance, huge original wooden balcony, and large Jacuzzi overlooking the principal interior patio.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>All rooms include a bathtub, telephone, hair dryer, air conditioning and heating, free high-speed wireless Internet, cable TV with LCD screen, safe deposit box, coffeemaker and coffee supplies, and soundproof double-pane windows for total privacy.</p>\r\n\r\n<h2>Hotel Services &amp; Facilities</h2>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Restaurant</li>\r\n	<li>Colonial-style bar</li>\r\n	<li>Internet centers with free high-speed Internet</li>\r\n	<li>Conference room</li>\r\n	<li>Room service (6 a.m. - 11 p.m.)</li>\r\n	<li>Gift shop</li>\r\n	<li>Laundry service</li>\r\n	<li>Medical assistance</li>\r\n	<li>ATM machine</li>\r\n	<li>24-hour front desk service</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n',NULL,1,0,0,'2014-08-29 17:56:08','2014-08-28 22:20:50',NULL),(35,NULL,1,4,'Aranwa Cusco Boutique Hotel Info & Photos | Cusco Hotels | Peru For Less','Stay at a the high quality Aranwa Cusco hotel on your Peruvian adventure organized by the value-oriented team of travel experts at Peru For Less.','Cusco hotels, Cusco accommodations, Aranwa Cusco Boutique Hotel, Peru travel, Peru tours, Peru vacations','hotels-cusco','Machu Picchu Pueblo Hotel','The Inkaterra Machu Picchu Pueblo Hotel is a naturalist’s haven. Conveniently nestled in the verdant Andean cloud forest, this lovely hotel is the perfect place to catch a glimpse of the astonishing flora and fauna of the region. The eco-friendly hotel resembles an Andean village and is comprised of charming white-washed cottages decorated with modern indigenous art as well as authentic pre-Columbian artifacts. With a commitment to indulging the whims of its guests, this luxury hotel expertly combines nature and comfort to create a one-of-a-kind Machu Picchu experience. Try some regional dishes at the excellent restaurant overlooking the Urubamba River.','img\\icon-aranwa.jpg','Details about the Aranwa Boutique Hotel','Get more details on the Aranwa Cusco Boutique Hotel','Kilometer 110 Via Ferrea, Aguas Calientes','<h2>Description</h2>\r\n\r\n<p>The Machu Picchu Pueblo Hotel is split into a main building and bungalows, emulating a small Andean town. The architecture is Spanish colonial in style with stone archways and red tiled roofs. White walls, red tiles, high windows flanked by exposed beams, and a private veranda, all contribute to make this the perfect place to enjoy your stay at Machu Picchu. Guests can sit on their verandas or walk leisurely along garden paths.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>The Pueblo is home to 372 species of orchids, 100 species of birds, and 250 species of butterflies. Even if you don&#39;t stay at the Machu Picchu Pueblo Hotel it is well worth a visit. Spend some time wandering the paths or take one of their orchid or bird tours. The hotel offers a wide range of ecotourism activities that promote contact with nature and the local culture. It is also involved in a project to rehabilitate spectacled bears and eventually to release them into the wild.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>For your hungry needs, the Machu Picchu Pueblo Hotel has three fabulous options:</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Mikhuna Wasi, which means &ldquo;house of food&rdquo; in the Quechua language, is a comfortable, spacious area built as a large glass house with an exceptional view of the Urubamba River and the green mountains. The restaurant is the perfect place to enjoy the breakfast buffet or a delectable variety of international and Peruvian cuisine for lunch or dinner.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Caf&eacute; Inkaterra&nbsp;is located just a few meters from the Aguas Calientes train station. This buffet-style restaurant offers regional and international cuisine served in a spacious dining room.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Hiram Bingham Bar&nbsp;offers a comfortable atmosphere with a large selection of drinks, light snacks, and board games. The bar is an experience for the senses as it combines the aromas of extravagant humid forest flowers, soft coffee, the unmistakable Peruvian lemon constantly cut for the famous Pisco sour, and a hint of honey from the wax of the rough beams.</p>\r\n\r\n<h2>Room Amenities</h2>\r\n\r\n<p>86 secluded rooms, all with different pitched-roof bungalows, are connected to each other by winding stone paths. There&#39;s a definite home-like atmosphere about the hotel, with colorful handcrafted furnishings and spacious rooms filled by plenty of natural light.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>The Machu Picchu Pueblo Hotel has large, comfortable single and double rooms in standard and superior grades, along with junior suites and suites for the guest who requires greater comfort and luxury. Triple rooms are available only in some superior rooms and junior suites.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Some suites are equipped with wireless Internet, flat screen TVs and DVD players, slippers and bathrobes, and separate sitting areas. The Inkaterra Suite, the hotel&rsquo;s most luxurious room comes with a private garden, pool, iPod dock, and minibar.</p>\r\n\r\n<h2>Hotel Services &amp; Facilities</h2>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Unu Spa</li>\r\n	<li>Caf&eacute; Inkaterra</li>\r\n	<li>Dining room &amp; bar</li>\r\n	<li>Inkaterra gallery</li>\r\n	<li>Ceremonies</li>\r\n	<li>Private interpreter</li>\r\n	<li>Children explorer kit</li>\r\n	<li>Early check-in &amp; late check-out</li>\r\n	<li>Laundry service</li>\r\n	<li>Transportation</li>\r\n	<li>Vow renewal service</li>\r\n	<li>VIP services</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n',5,1,1,0,'2014-09-08 16:31:51','2014-09-01 20:49:08',NULL),(36,NULL,1,2,'','','','aranwa-boutique-hotel','Aranwa Boutique Hotel','The brand new Aranwa Boutique Hotel, opened in October 2010, is operated by Aranwa Hotels Resorts & Spas, one of the most luxurious hotel chains in Peru, known for their careful attention to their clients’ well-being. Probably the best value luxury accommodation in Cusco, this elegant 5-star hotel is housed in a converted 16th century mansion and is decorated with colonial era furniture, impressive paintings from the Cusco school, and colonial gold-leaf plated carvings and sculptures. This boutique hotel is conveniently located right behind Plaza San Francisco, a new upscale neighborhood away from the hustle and bustle of Cusco’s main square. With each room boasting an oxygen system and a variety of soothing spa treatments available, this just may be the best place to acclimatize to the high altitude in Cusco in a most comfortable setting.','','','','','<h2>Description</h2>\r\n\r\n<p>The Aranwa Cusco Boutique Hotel is operated by Aranwa Hotels Resorts &amp; Spas, one of the most luxurious hotel chains in Peru. Housed in a converted 16th century mansion, this elegant 5-star hotel is decorated with colonial-era furniture, impressive paintings from the Cusco school, and colonial gold leaf-plated carvings and sculptures.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Declared a National Historic Landmark, the former mansion once belonged to the Dean of the Cusco Cathedral, Alonso P&eacute;rez de Villarejo, and has one of the best-preserved fa&ccedil;ades in Cusco. Architectural enthusiasts will delight in the stunning baroque elements such as Corinthian columns typically found on the edifices of convents and churches. In the midst of this historic ambience, guests will enjoy the ultimate in comfort and attentive, personalized service.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Guests can also take advantage of the wellness spa which offers a variety of treatments combining European and Inca methods. On-site is a hair salon, steam room, dry sauna, and massage space. This focus on health and wellness is incorporated into every aspect of the hotel, including the d&eacute;cor. Common areas are warm and inviting with soothing elements like color therapy, aromatherapy, and music therapy into the design to keep guests relaxed. It is easy to understand why this hotel chain was named the most innovative company in the Cusco region by the Cusco Chamber of Commerce in 2010.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Not least, serving a delicious combination of Peruvian and Andean cuisine with a modern twist is the excellent multicultural Mishti restaurant. The chef pays special attention to both flavor and presentation to create a fine dining experience that is specially made for the international city of Cusco. As well, the understated yet chic Khasikay Bar has an innovative menu serving Andean-style tapas in addition to both national and international cuisine.</p>\r\n\r\n<h2>Room Amenities</h2>\r\n\r\n<p>The Aranwa Boutique Hotel has 43 rooms and suites decorated in the traditional style of a 16th century mansion. Suites are elegantly decorated with tasteful artwork and feature a separate living room and balcony. The marble-floored bathrooms have large Jacuzzi-style baths, a Scottish shower, and heated floors to keep you warm on cold Andean nights. You can also indulge with the complementary organic bath products, bathrobes and slippers, and room climate control. As well, take advantage of the wireless Internet, satellite TV, telephone (national and international), iPod dock/CD player, minibar, electronic safe deposit box, hair dryer, and iron and ironing board in each room.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Each of the rooms is equipped with an intelligent oxygen system to help alleviate any stress on the body caused by the high altitude.</p>\r\n\r\n<h2>Hotel Services &amp; Facilities</h2>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Restaurant</li>\r\n	<li>Bar</li>\r\n	<li>Breakfast buffet</li>\r\n	<li>Currency exchange</li>\r\n	<li>Concierge</li>\r\n	<li>Laundry service</li>\r\n	<li>Transfer service</li>\r\n	<li>Guided city tours</li>\r\n	<li>Room service</li>\r\n	<li>Business center</li>\r\n	<li>Spa</li>\r\n	<li>Beauty salon</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n',5,0,1,0,'2014-09-08 20:44:54','2014-09-08 16:29:17',NULL),(37,NULL,1,2,'','','','hotel-monasterio','Hotel Monasterio','A restored 16th century seminary on the site of an ancient Inca palace, Hotel Monasterio was recently designated as the Best Hotel in South America by Condé Nast Traveler Awards. Along with a rich history, this five-star establishment offers a successful blend of modernity and tradition. Simple and elegant, each room is unique in shape and decoration, and many provide beautiful views of the city and the surrounding courtyard. With every luxury imaginable at your disposal, you are certain to experience contemporary comfort in this historical atmosphere.','','','','','<h2>Description</h2>\r\n\r\n<p>A stay at the Monasterio will allow you to discover the charms of this hallowed colonial San Antonio Abad seminary built more than 300 years ago. The seminary is an excellent example of 17th century Andean Baroque architecture and offers a unique atmosphere.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>The Monasterio hotel holds 4 lovely and well-maintained courtyards surrounded by colonial arcades and beautiful gardens and fountains which will transport you back to historic times while providing the comforts and quality of a modern 5-star hotel.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>As much a museum as a hotel, it has its own opulent gilded chapel and 18th century Escuela Cusque&ntilde;a art collection. The Chapel, dating from colonial times, has been restored and contains an altar and &ldquo;retables&rdquo; covered in gold leaf and paintings from the Cusque&ntilde;an School. The past is overwhelmingly present in this hotel even while you are pampered with every luxury and modern comfort. At night, the view of the stars from the Monasterio&rsquo;s courtyard, soft lighting, and sounds from the fountain are truly serene.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>There are 2 restaurants in the Monasterio hotel offering a delicious taste of the excellent Peruvian gastronomy. With its view of the main patio and intimate ambience, Restaurant Illariy never fails to charm. Its unique atmosphere and distinctive Andino-Nikkei cuisine, created by Chef Mariano Takinami, have been huge successes since inception. Restaurant El Tupay serves a delicious buffet breakfast from 5:00 a.m. to 10:00 a.m. in the antique refectory.</p>\r\n\r\n<h2>Room Amenities</h2>\r\n\r\n<p>Rooms are impeccably decorated with an elegant combination of colonial and modern styles. Each room is exclusive varying in size and design, and many offer charming views of the colorful rooftops of Cusco or of the wonderful main courtyard. The accommodations off the first courtyard are more traditionally designed with an authentic feel. For a special treat, consider one of the two-story suites. There are 91 Deluxe Rooms, 12 Junior Suites, 3 Presidential Suites, and 2 Royal Suites. The decorations and furnishings are a tasteful combination of colonial and modern styles.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>The original architecture and design of the Monasterio have not been significantly altered, and thus the rooms reflect their origins as a home for Jesuit seminarians. The hotel has also alleviated many guests&rsquo; altitude sickness with its oxygen enrichment systems found in most of the rooms. Wireless Internet, a telephone, safe deposit box, and TV complete this hotel&rsquo;s modern amenities.</p>\r\n\r\n<h2>Hotel Services &amp; Facilities</h2>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Lobby bar</li>\r\n	<li>Restaurant</li>\r\n	<li>Relaxation massages</li>\r\n	<li>Excursions &amp; extra activities in Cusco</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n',5,1,1,0,'2014-09-08 20:44:45','2014-09-08 16:30:35',NULL),(38,NULL,1,4,'','','','sumaq-machu-picchu-hotel','Sumaq Machu Picchu Hotel','This exclusive and elegant hotel is located in the village of Aguas Calientes at the foot of Machu Picchu. It has ample and luxurious rooms decorated in an original and very cozy Andean style. With some of the best views of the surrounding landscape and a brand new design this hotel really is a great place to relax and enjoy a little bit of luxury after a long day of exploring the Machu Picchu citadel. Boasting an Andean health spa, sauna, massage, steam room, Thai massage, and Jacuzzi, the Sumaq Hotel will make you feel like royalty while you enjoy this stunning part of the world.','','','','','<h2>Description</h2>\r\n\r\n<p>The literal translation of Sumaq&mdash;&ldquo;a great stay&rdquo; in the indigenous Quechua language&mdash;does not begin to describe the excellence of this hotel. Comfort, relaxation, and elegance are the mainstays of this establishment. The design of the building reflects the masterful architecture of Machu Picchu, imitating the world-famous citadel through beautiful hotel d&eacute;cor and spectacular architecture. The hotel also prides itself in protecting the natural and social environment of the Cusco and Machu Picchu region.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Guests who wish to relax after an exciting day of visiting the citadel of Machu Picchu may spend time in the hotel&rsquo;s opulent Aqlla Spa. Aqlla, which in Quechua means &ldquo;chosen one,&rdquo; is an appropriate name for this luxurious center where guests can indulge in a relaxing massage, take advantage of the top-notch Andean-style sauna, and be pampered with salon services such as a manicure or pedicure.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>The hotel also provides unique activities that guests can enjoy during their Machu Picchu vacation. For example, join a shaman (traditional spiritual healer) during a ceremony that pays homage and makes offerings to the Pachamama (Mother Earth). Or if you wish to partake in an unforgettable culinary experience, ask for a cooking lesson from a resident chef who will show you how to prepare Peru&rsquo;s most famous dish, ceviche (lime-marinated fish, seasoned with aji pepper and cilantro).</p>\r\n\r\n<p>The Qunuq restaurant welcomes guests to an intimate atmosphere where they can savor delicious meals prepared by one of Peru&rsquo;s top chefs, Rafael Piqueras. The highly-respected culinary master brings a 5-star modern flair to traditional Peruvian dishes. This elegant and exclusively-designed dining hall features an incredible view of the Urubamba River.</p>\r\n\r\n<h2>Room Amenities</h2>\r\n\r\n<p>The Sumaq Machu Picchu Hotel features 46 superior deluxe rooms, 11 junior suites, and 3 Sumaq suites. As can be expected, all rooms are incredibly spacious and equipped with all modern amenities, providing for a peaceful and comfortable space to relax after a long day of sightseeing. These include cable TV, a direct-dial telephone, electronic safe deposit box, minibar, and hair dryer.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Suites have amenities such as hydro-massage bathtubs and DVD player/mp3 radios. But for a truly excellent Machu Picchu hotel experience, stay at the Sumaq Suite, the hotel&rsquo;s largest accommodation which features a fireplace, an LCD flat-screen TV, and a plush king-sized bed covered with the softest high-thread-count cotton sheets. Guests staying in these sumptuous Sumaq Suite rooms may also rent a laptop during their stay.</p>\r\n\r\n<h2>Hotel Services &amp; Facilities</h2>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Aqlla Spa</li>\r\n	<li>Cooking lessons</li>\r\n	<li>Qunuq Restaurant</li>\r\n	<li>Suquy Caf&eacute; Bar</li>\r\n	<li>Nuna Boutique</li>\r\n	<li>Laundry service</li>\r\n	<li>Infirmary</li>\r\n	<li>Luggage transfer</li>\r\n	<li>Guest service</li>\r\n	<li>Wake-up call</li>\r\n	<li>Room service</li>\r\n	<li>Wireless Internet</li>\r\n	<li>Currency exchange</li>\r\n	<li>Mail &amp; fax service</li>\r\n	<li>Post service</li>\r\n	<li>Accommodations for disabled guests</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n',5,0,1,0,'2014-09-08 16:33:27','2014-09-08 16:33:01',NULL),(39,NULL,1,2,'','','','andean-wings-boutique-hotel','Andean Wings Boutique Hotel','Located in a magnificent colonial house that dates back to over 300 years ago, this charming boutique hotel offers excellent services in a luxurious atmosphere. The Andean Wings Boutique Hotel strives to provide guests with an intimate setting as well as the highest quality amenities in the heart of magical Cusco. The rooms are extremely well appointed and inviting; the restaurant offers original and delicious dishes in the hotel’s interior patio; and the spa’s amazing services are assured to keep guests relaxed. The small size of the hotel, with only 18 rooms, allows for personalized attention to each and every guest.','','','',NULL,'',4,1,0,0,'2014-09-08 17:56:45','2014-09-08 17:56:45',NULL),(40,NULL,1,2,'','','','casa-andina-private-collection-cusco','Casa Andina Private Collection Cusco','The Casa Andina Private Collection Cusco is the most recent addition to the renowned Casa Andina Hotels. Built in a large colonial house dating back to the 18th century, the hotel is ideally located in the center of Cusco, just a few blocks from the main square in the direction of Koricancha. Relax in the beautiful courtyard with its gurgling stone fountain, one of Cusco’s emblematic colonial sights, and get lost in the intriguing maze of corridors that lead you to the various patios. Casa Andina’s first upscale hotel in Cusco features 94 heated rooms with private bathrooms, cable television, telephones, hairdryers, and in-room safes. The hotel is equipped with a gourmet restaurant, a bar, 3 courtyards, and offers room service as well as many other excellent amenities. Discover the magic of this beautiful city while staying at Casa Andina Private Collection Cusco, where you will enjoy the warm atmosphere and the outstanding service from the very hospitable and highly qualified staff.','','','','','',3,1,0,0,'2014-09-08 20:04:21','2014-09-08 20:00:23',NULL),(41,NULL,1,9,'','','','hotel-libertador-paracas','Hotel Libertador Paracas','Soak up the luxury and splendor of the lavish Hotel Libertador in Paracas, one of the first “It” hotels on the glittering Peruvian coast. Leave your bags with the porter and your cares at the door. Inside the plush, aquatic-hued Libertador, a soothing, slowed-down world of total relaxation awaits. Ideally located on the Paracas Bay in front of the Natural Reserve of Paracas, Hotel Libertador Paracas is one of the Peruvian coast’s most spectacular deluxe hotels. Five-star amenities and highly personalized service are combined to make this resort-spa a blissful haven of sensual delight.','','','','','',5,1,0,0,'2014-09-08 20:21:11','2014-09-08 20:20:31',NULL),(42,NULL,1,9,'','','','doubletree-hilton-paracas','Doubletree Hilton Paracas','The Doubletree Paracas Resort by Hilton Peru, which opened in March 2009, is a luxury resort that allows visitors to take advantage of comfortable and relaxing accommodations surrounded by stunning views while they explore the natural splendor and archaeological wonders of Paracas Bay. The spacious suites are spread throughout the 2-story hotel and feature private terraces with views of the bay or the hotel’s gardens. The 2-room suites offer a variety of amenities for those accustomed to the best international hotels. On your Peru vacation, let yourself be enchanted by the magnificent service and 8,000-square-foot swimming pool with views of Paracas Bay.','','','',NULL,'',4,1,0,0,'2014-09-08 20:21:50','2014-09-08 20:21:50',NULL),(43,NULL,1,9,'','','','la-hacienda-bahia-paracas','La Hacienda Bahia Paracas','This understated hotel offers comfortable accommodations in the spectacular seaside setting of Paracas, a town just a few short hours from Lima and on the way to the Nazca Lines. Spacious guestrooms, suites, and bungalows are all tastefully decorated in a minimalist style combining the earthy tones of polished wood and brick tiling with white-washed walls and contemporary furniture. Each room has a bathtub and a private terrace, while the hotel’s grounds boast a luxurious spa, swimming pool, bar, and restaurant. Recently added to the hotel\'s alluring charm is an exclusive museum displaying a private collection of 250 artifacts from prominent pre-Hispanic Peruvian civilizations.','','','',NULL,'',4,0,0,0,'2014-09-08 20:22:36','2014-09-08 20:22:36',NULL),(44,NULL,2,18,'','','','hotel-emperador','Hotel Emperador','The Hotel Emperador is similar to its sister institution, the Hotel Emperador Madrid. Located in the center of Buenos Aires, it offers a personalized service to maximize your comfort. Its rooms are modern in design, but feature classic details such as fine, exotic, crafted furniture. It offers cars with drivers, concierge service, 24 hour room service, 24 hour medical emergency service, laundry service, fully stocked business center, free indoor pool, fitness center, sauna, solarium and massage center, and a restaurant and bar.','','','','','',5,1,0,0,'2014-09-08 20:52:06','2014-09-08 20:51:21',NULL);
