INSERT INTO `testimonies` VALUES (1,1,'Hi Bernard,','<p>Yes we arrived back in Sydney on Monday at the same time as many from Bali so that was memorable in itself.</p>\r\n<p>Anyway, we had a great time and enjoyed the experience very much. </p>\r\n<p>The Andean Apartments in Cusco was OK and Caesar was very hospitable. </p>\r\n<p>I\'ll tell Edwina to send you a message. Generally everything went well, the altitude didn\'t affect us too much and back home safely with lots of wonderful photos. We should have asked you to arrange a hotel in Lima for the one night on return trip as we had to rely on the advice at the airport and ended up in El Chalan (I think) in Miraflores and I certainly wouldn\'t reccommend it to anyone else! </p>\r\n<p>Thank you for all your assistance and organisation. </p>\r\n<p>Cheers.</p>','Heather,<br />Australia.','','','',8,0,0,NULL,NULL,NULL),(2,1,'Hi Bernard,','<p>Thanks again for all that you did for us. Love Peru and wish I was there this minute. Maybe Iâ??ll catch the wrong plane and show up on the door step around 2:00 a.m.</p>','Carolyn,<br />Colorado Springs, USA.','','','',9,0,0,NULL,NULL,NULL),(3,1,'Hi Bernard,','<p>I\'m glad you liked the book - if you ever get to this area (when it\'s Ã¢â?¬ÂsafeÃ¢â?¬Â) please give us a call! They both really did have a great time - and yes, they had some good stories!&nbsp;We\'ve gotten the pictures developed (they each lost a roll of film :( It\'s so beautiful - I\'m even tempted (by train, of course:)&nbsp;I know Kevin would love to go back again - he really enjoyed the people he met &amp; especially the guide on the trail.&nbsp;Several people told him how much they liked Arequipa - so he\'s ready to try that next &amp; of course more hiking, he just loved it. Kevin\'s already off on his next adventure - he\'s visiting one of his sisters in St. Louis &amp; then on to hike the Appalachian Trail for a few months. Larry\'s taking it easy - getting ready for his marathon on Sunday. </p>\r\n<p>I know they both enjoyed having dinner with you and thank you for the Pisco - I can\'t believe they never tried it.&nbsp;You can be sure I will (I\'ll try your recipe first:) </p>\r\n<p>Anyway, the trip was a huge success. </p>\r\n<p>Thanks once again for all your help &amp; putting up with all my e-mails - I had fun, but I could NEVER be a travel agent! </p>\r\n<p>Take care &amp; call us if you\'re in the DC area.</p>','Peggy,<br />USA','','','',10,0,0,NULL,NULL,NULL),(4,1,'Hi Bernard,','<p>We\'re fine thanks.&nbsp;Peru was great - had a fantastic time and loved the \r\nColca Canyon (thanks for the rec), Nazca and (of course) Macchu Picchu.</p>\r\n<p>Shame we did not get to meet you.</p>\r\n<p>Regards, </p>','Dhirendra (Dennis),<br />United Kingdom.','','','',14,0,0,NULL,NULL,NULL),(6,1,'Bernard,','<p>Well, we successfully finished the Inca Trail, though we do have some sore muscles. It was great. Wilfredo Surco, our guide, and his entire crew were the best. The explainations of the Trail, the ruins, Inca and Peru history were a real plus in understanding exactly what we were viewing and experiencing.</p>','Harold,<br />USA','','','',15,0,0,NULL,NULL,NULL),(7,1,'Dear Ale,','<p>I just wanted to drop you an email to say how much I appreciated the great work you did on my trip.&nbsp; The trek to Choquekirao was very special.&nbsp; There aren\'t many adventures like that left to have in the world.&nbsp; I fell in love with the Incan stonework and my guide (and now friend) Richard Castillo helped me develop an appreciation for Incan culture and spirituality.&nbsp; The guy even took me shopping! </p>\r\n<p>Thank you also for setting me up with Marc.&nbsp; He is quite a guy who, like you, seems really into his work.&nbsp; It means a lot to me that you guys were really on top of things.&nbsp; He also tells me you are expanding and will have trips throughout South America .&nbsp; I look forward to taking another adventure with you soon.&nbsp; There is a lot more to explore!</p>\r\n<p>Thanks again, </p>','John,<br />USA. ','','','',17,0,0,NULL,NULL,NULL),(8,1,'Bernard,','<p>Thanks for following up. Peru is quite an extraordinary country. There are so \r\nmany things to see and we only sampled the 2 among them, Inca trail &amp; Manu. \r\nThese were both awesome for me. The town of Cusco, the snow peaks of the Andes, \r\nthe high rainforest, the mystical Inca ruins, the Peru people, the magical city \r\nof Machu Picchu, the ruggedness and beauty of the jungle all made for an \r\nunforgettable adventure. Some of the girls were a little overwhelmed by the \r\ninsects in Manu, but c\'est le vie. </p>\r\n<p>By the way, the Inca trail tour and the Jungle Tour companies were good.</p>\r\n<p>I will certainly be returning to Peru at some point. Possibly another Inca \r\ntrail trek (with a stay in Sancturay Lodge for night viewing of Machu Picchu \r\nunder a full moon), at least 2 days at the Peublo Hotel (really nice place, \r\n&amp; Aguas Calientes is a unique town), Lake Titicaca, Galapagos, etc. I\'m up \r\nfor an Ayawaska journey in the jungle as well.</p>','Micheal,<br />New York - USA','','','',16,0,0,NULL,NULL,NULL),(9,1,'Dear Peru For Less','<p>We had a great trip to Peru. Thanks for all of your help in setting things \r\nup. The best place we stayed was the hotel in Cusco. Great tour guides and \r\ndrivers were well worth the extra money. I am sending some photos in another \r\nemail.</p>\r\n<p>Thanks for everything, </p>','The Riggs,<br />USA.','','','',22,0,0,NULL,NULL,NULL),(10,1,'Bernard,','<p>We had a great trip to Peru. Everything that you set up worked well. We had a little mountain sickness the first night in Cusco, but after that, we all felt fine. The Inca ruins at Machu Picchu were amazing. We were there the day they discovered the three skeletons in the gravesite. It was pretty astounding. The Picoaga Hotel is quite nice, has a good location and the people are quite friendly and accommodating. Dena was very nice. All the tours picked us up within the time that they said they would. </p>\r\n\r\n<p>Wagner, the guide at Machu Picchu, was excellent. You should use him whenever possible. The el Pueblo hotel was quite fun. I was hoping that they would have a better swimming pool, but otherwise, the facility was very nice. There was an electrical blackout while we were there, but it was fun. The hotel brought out candles and kerosene lanterns and we just carried on. </p>\r\n\r\n<p>When we got back to Lima, the people at Manhattan Inn sent us to Plaza San Migel. That is a very nice shopping area. All of our flights seemed to go OK. </p>\r\n\r\n<p>I really enjoyed having lunch with you and friends. Glad to hear that your ankle is returning to normal.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Thanks for all your help with our trip. We will keep you in mind for future travel. </p>\r\n\r\n','Bob,<br />USA.','','','',18,0,0,NULL,NULL,NULL),(11,1,'Hi Ale,','<p>Thx for everything. Machu Picchu was great - particularly Wayna Picchu! Everything went smoothly, the pick up, the hotel (great service by the hotel staff), the guides were GOOD. If any of my friends talk about going to Machu Picchu I will MOST certainly recommend you guys! And this is not just something I say. We ordered late, made changes, and changes to the changes - but you made it work.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>THANK YOU!.</p>\r\n','Ola and Dag,<br />Norway. ','','','',21,1,0,NULL,'2014-09-10 20:25:33',NULL),(12,1,'Dear Peru For Less','<p>Thank you so much for an amazing trip. Our travels through Peru were perfectly orchestrated, and your people along the way were always delightful, punctual, and helpful. Unfortunately, the Angelique - our boat for the Galapagos trip - had a broken propeller, but the owners managed to make arrangements for us each day and refunded half of our payment. </p>\r\n<p>We will definitely recommend you to our friends.</p>\r\n','Cheryl and Lon,<br />USA.','','','',19,0,0,NULL,NULL,NULL),(13,1,'Dear Peru For Less','<p>We had great time in Peru !!! Such a wonderful experience !!!! </p>\r\n<p>Thanks a lot for you attention.</p>','Mila,<br />USA.','','','',23,0,0,NULL,NULL,NULL),(14,1,'Hi Diego,','<p>The trip was wonderful! Maria and Carlos were great as well as our tour \r\nguides. No complaints!&nbsp; We loved Peru and the people.</p>','Vicky,<br />Seattle, WA. ','','','',24,0,0,NULL,NULL,NULL),(15,1,'Diego my friend,','<p>I want to \r\nthank you and all the staff at Peru For Less.&nbsp;Let it be clear that I have \r\nenjoyed very much the people of your country.&nbsp;All are&nbsp;kind and the \r\nchildren&nbsp;have much character.&nbsp;We have visited many of the childrenâ??s \r\nschools here and have told them beautiful stories of trees.&nbsp;One childâ??s \r\nwords, which I can not forget:&nbsp; he said,&nbsp;Â¨I will plant a tree&nbsp;on \r\nthe first day of the year for the rest of my life.Â¨&nbsp; You know I could not \r\nfind the strength in me to resist some tears forming in&nbsp;my eyes.</p>\r\n<p>Thank you again Diego,</p>','Your friend Rafeal<br />California, USA.','','','',26,0,0,NULL,NULL,NULL),(16,1,'Dear Peru For Less','<p>My husband and I had an excellent time in Peru , and would gladly and \r\nwholeheartedly recommend PFL as an agent for anyone else traveling there. Marc \r\nwas extremely conscientious in following up on any concerns or queries that we \r\nhad, and all the local agents in each place we visited were also extremely \r\nattentive and helpful (to the extent that the local representative in Cusco \r\nactually lent me her own jacket to wear on the Inca trail - service well above \r\nand beyond what I had expected). All our hotels were clean and comfortable and \r\ngenerally better than we had expected, given that we had chosen PFL partly for \r\nreasons of budget, on which I would also say that their prices seemed very \r\ncompetitive to us. PFL hotel/agents/guides etc struck us generally as being \r\ncomfortably mid-range - not luxury five star, but certainly well above \r\nbackpacker standard. Finally - the food is absolutely fabulous! Go ahead with \r\nPFL and have a wonderful time.</p>','Alexandra and Daniel,<br />Maryland, USA.','','','',41,0,0,NULL,NULL,NULL),(17,1,'Hi Bernard,','<p>The trip to Peru was great! It was well organized and we were welcomed. It \r\nwas great experience. I really appreciate your help. I will definitely recommend \r\nPeru for Less.</p>\r\n<p>Best,</p>','Junghwa,<br />USA. ','','','',28,0,0,NULL,NULL,NULL),(18,1,'Hello Diego,','<p>Thanks for checking in.&nbsp;We had a grand time and all associated with Peru for Less was great.</p>\r\n<p>Thanks,</p>','Lynn,<br />Salt Lake City, UT.','','','',32,0,0,NULL,NULL,NULL),(19,1,'Dear Ale,','<p>Carolyn and I had a wonderful time. We were very impressed by the punctuality, kindness and consideration of everyone&nbsp;connected with Peru for Less, especially Maria and Rosie in Cusco.</p>\r\n<p>The highlight of the trip was Machu Piccu and we loved Cusco where we discovered Pisco Sours and shopped for our baby - alpaca gifts. I hope to return to Peru some day and explore some different areas of this beautiful country. </p>\r\n<p>We want to thank you and Claudia for all your help in making this a very memorable trip.</p>','Joan and Carolyn,<br />USA.','','','',33,0,0,NULL,NULL,NULL),(20,1,'Dear Peru For Less','<p>Sorry I haven\'t gotten back to your earlier.&nbsp; The trip was excellent. \r\nEverything was very well organized, transfers/trips were always on time, hotels \r\nvery good, trips interesing.&nbsp; I should have probably spent one more day in \r\nCusco , this is really beautiful city. </p>\r\n<p>I\'m glad I decided to take the train to Puno - somebody should tell Lonely \r\nPlanet not to discourage travellers :) The Bolivian part was also good, La Paz \r\nlooks very nice, it\'s very hard to believe that just 5 months ago they had all \r\nthose riots in the city. </p>\r\n<p>Anyway, thanks for organizing everything so well, I will definitelly \r\nrecommend you guys if I have a chance. </p>','Bogdan,<br />Portland.','','','',40,0,0,NULL,NULL,NULL),(21,1,'Dear Bernard,','<p>Peru was a very good trip. the land and the people are fantastic, we had no rain!!! Arequipa and Puno were great. Bus trip Puno-Cusco was very good, not only with the landsacpes we were able to see, but allowed us to rest. Hacienda Incatambo hotel was delightful, since we were the only guests. we were given a suite!! and the service was fantastic.</p>\r\n<p>All in all, a fun trip. thanks for your help. We will recommend you to our friends.</p>\r\n<p>sincerely.</p>','Cheryl and Jim,<br />USA.','','','',44,0,0,NULL,NULL,NULL),(22,1,'Dear Wenche,','<p>I appreciate very much if you will send my best regards to Ximena in Peru for less. The way she has organized and planned the Peru trip for us was just perfect. The timing and all the guiding to the most exciting places in Peru will be a memory for life for both of us. The Jungle, Machu Picchu and the stay at the Titicaca Island were the most exciting places. All the personal guides where very well educated and had good knowledge about the area that we where visiting. All in all the days in Peru will be good memories for life thanks to Ximena and her Ã¢â?¬ÂCrewÃ¢â?¬Â.</p>','Tom and Sos,<br />Norway. ','','','',42,0,0,NULL,NULL,NULL),(23,1,'Hi Bernard,','<p>Happy New Year! Envious you were in Cusco for the event...trust it was a \r\ngreat one! </p>\r\n<p>The Peruvian trip was one of the most amazing trips we\'ve done, and MP/Inca \r\ntrail was unbelievable - highly recommended. I\'m glad we did it, and am grateful \r\nfor your help on this.</p>\r\n<p>The stay in the Sacred Valley overnight was EXCELLENT - very worthwhile and \r\nrecommended. It was great to be away from everyone &amp; everything in such a \r\nbeautiful surrounds.</p>\r\n<p>Cheers, </p>','Paul,<br />USA.','','','',43,0,0,NULL,NULL,NULL),(24,1,'Dear Bernard,','<p>Thank you for asking. We really enjoyed the trip. I would like to go back \r\nmaybe next year and would definitely go through you again. </p>\r\n<p>Anyway thanks for everything. If you would like to use me for a US reference \r\nI would give you a good referral. </p>','Emily,<br />USA.','','','',25,0,0,NULL,NULL,NULL),(25,1,'Dear Bernard,','<p>Peru was a very good trip. the land and the people are fantastic, we had no \r\nrain!!! Arequipa and Puno were great. Bus trip Puno-Cusco was very good, not \r\nonly with the landsacpes we were able to see, but allowed us to rest. Hacienda \r\nIncatambo hotel was delightful, since we were the only guests. we were given a \r\nsuite!! and the service was fantastic.</p>\r\n<p>All in all, a fun trip. thanks for your help. We will recommend you to our \r\nfriends.</p>\r\n<p>sincerely</p>','Dr. Ahmed,<br />USA.','','','',45,0,0,NULL,NULL,NULL),(26,1,'Hi Bernard,','<p>Peru was wonderful! Regret we did not spend more time there, although it \r\nwould have taken us months, maybe, to visit the whole country. </p>\r\n<p>I have no complaints; everything was wonderfully organised. I particularly \r\nloved the Andean Apartments (we had the attic/loft room).</p>\r\n<p>With Christmas around the corner, everyone is pretty busy here. I\'m the \r\nCatholic one... will write u again.</p>\r\n<p>Regards </p>','Jeanie,<br />Malaysia.','','','',46,0,0,NULL,NULL,NULL),(27,1,'Dear Peru For Less','<p>Our trip to Peru was amazing.&nbsp;My mom and I loved the trip. Peru For Less was wonderful.I would highly recommend them to anyone travelling to Peru or South America</p>\r\n<p>Thanks again,</p>','Sarah, <br />Unionville, Ontario ','','','',47,0,0,NULL,NULL,NULL),(28,1,'Dear Peru For Less','<p>Thank you so much for your emails and phone calls. The South American trip was one of \r\nthe most memorable and fun trips I have ever taken and I must thank your travel \r\noutfit for making it possible. I have been raving about my trip since I came \r\nback and I have put a good word with friends and acquaintances.</p>\r\n<p>Sincerely,</p>','Ingrid, <br />Lafayette, CA.','','','',48,0,0,NULL,NULL,NULL),(29,1,'Dear Peru For Less','<p>We just want to tell you that we had a great trip to Peru. Everything worked out \r\nperfectly. People were waiting for us with big signs with our name on them when \r\nwe came to a new place. We were also always picked up at our hotel at time. You \r\nhad found some great hotels for us; especially the one at Puno, Casa Andina \r\nPrivate, was fantastic. The guides were fine and told us a lot about Peru. \r\nAgain, thank you for planning a great trip for us.</p>\r\n<p>Kind regards,</p>','Niels and Lise,<br />Texas, USA.','','','',55,0,0,NULL,NULL,NULL),(30,1,'Hi Diego,','<p>Yes I am back after a really enjoyable visit to Peru. The visit to Manu was \r\nvery special and the service from Peru for Less well worth recommending. We had \r\nan extremely good guide - his precise knowledge of the fauna and flora was \r\nimpressive. The food was good- even too much!&nbsp; The drivers and helpers were \r\nprofessional and friendly. </p>\r\n<p>Many thanks,</p>','Antonie,<br />Aussenkehr, Namibia.','','','',50,0,0,NULL,NULL,NULL),(31,1,'Dear Richard,','<p>We, David and Ursula Chappell, are back from an absolutely wonderful trip to Peru and want to thank you very, very much for arranging this trip on rather short notice. It could not have been better! Every little detail, and there were plenty of them, went like clock work. Since I work in the tourist industry here in Hawaii myself, I know how many things can go wrong, but nothing did, we were in awe! You work with fantastic, reliable, polite, thoughtful, helpful people and agencies in Peru, we can\'t thank them enough. We also liked all the hotels you had chosen for us. We\'ll definitely recommend Peru and Peru For Less to our friends. </p>\r\n<p>Thank you again!! </p>','Ursula and David.','','','',51,0,0,NULL,NULL,NULL),(32,1,'Greetings Bernard,','<p>I really liked the people that I met, all were so friendly and helpful. The \r\nentire trip through PeruForLess, including the Inca Trail guide and all of the \r\nporters, and the Hotel in Cusco and in Aguas Calientes were all fantastic. I \r\nwould recommend your company to anyone who asks. The people treated us very \r\nwell, were extremely helpful and as a matter of fact, I have exchanged emails \r\nwith many of them, including a few folks at Hotel Presidente, some new aikido \r\nbuddies, the Inca Trail guide, Humberto, and of course I will stay in touch with \r\nyou. I cannot say enough about the incredible helpful porters and their \r\nincredibly hard-working and professional manner. I plan on coming back to your \r\ncountry, again and again, if I can manage it. Next time, I hope to bring some \r\nother friends. Not once in my whole entire time in Peru, did I have a bad \r\nexperience! Cusco is a beautiful city. Machu Picchu is amazing. Your country is \r\nbeautiful, the land and the people. Patient and kind. I don\'t really prefer big \r\ncities, so Lima is not where I\'d spend my time in Peru. However, the \r\ncountrysides, the smaller towns and the natural wonders are more my cup of tea. \r\nI realize that this is a rambling email, but wanted to write down as much as I \r\ncould now, so that you are aware that you have done a wonderful job of taking \r\ncare of us.</p>\r\n<p>Muchas gracias. I will stay in touch! </p>','Candice,<br />London, Canada.','','','',52,0,0,NULL,NULL,NULL),(33,1,'Dear Peru For Less','<p>I really enjoyed South America! The wine tour and folk festival in Chile was wonderful. Tour Guide Maria was so great.  We all loved her. Argentina is my next best favorite place to travel now. Buenos Aires is fabulous. Great shopping bargains! The Claridge hotel was right-on too.I have been to Rio 3 times, but I am falling in love with Sao Paulo. Next time I will visit the sea coast. The Gaucho tour and samba show will forever be in my memories. Wow! I have to mention how wonderful Anna was on our Gaucho tour. We were going a lot on tours and getting on planes a lot and we probably needed more time. However we got a good feel for the places we visited. The food was great too! I will definitely plan on a South America trip in 2008. You\'ll be hearing from me! Thanks for making everything work so smoothly.</p>\r\n<p>Best Regards,</p>','Robert,<br />Orlando, FL.','','','',49,0,0,NULL,NULL,NULL),(35,1,'Hello Bernard,','<p>We are back in NY and wanted to say that we had a wonderful time in Peru. \r\nEverything was well organized and as per schedule, including all transfers. We \r\nwere amazed at the efficiency of the Peruvians. The Inca trail hike was \r\nspectacular and we really recommend Lucio, the our guide, and M. A. travels for \r\nmaking our experience there unforgettable. </p>\r\n<p>Thank you. </p>','Jugmohan,<br />USA.','','','',56,0,0,NULL,NULL,NULL),(36,1,'Bernard,','<p>Hey! Yvette and I are back from our honeymoon trip in Peru. Everything went well, Cusco was great, Machu Picchu was tough but the scenery and guides were great and the Amazon was great too. Everything on your end went off without a hitch. </p>\r\n<p>The trip was great though and we would totally recommend you to anyone who is going to Peru.</p>\r\n<p>Thanks, </p>','Will and Yvette,<br />USA.','','','',57,0,0,NULL,NULL,NULL),(37,1,'Dear Diego and Peru For Less,','<p>Thanks for the most amazing holiday us girls have ever had. Peru is now definitely the most recommended place I will tell everyone to go. With Peru For Less the Guides were always helpful and on time. Being 3 young girls we needed all the help we could get! Everyone with Peru For Less were always friendly, and courteous. We had the most amazing vacation of our lives. Special mention to our Machu Picchu guide Fabricio. He was amazing and his attention to detail and knowledge of the area made it all the more entertaining. The hotel and its staff at Cusco were perfect, the location and the rooms were very nice and comfortable, we couldn\'t have asked for more. Thanks Diego for answering all our questions and making the trip a truly wonderful experience we will never forget! Thanks again for everything.</p>\r\n<p>Cheers,</p>','Laura,Clarissa, and Joanna,<br />Sydney, Australia. ','','','',58,0,0,NULL,NULL,NULL),(38,1,'Dear Peru For Less','<p>Thank you for inquiring about our trip to Peru. The trip was a complete success, all of your people were helpful, polite, and on time, every step of the way. The bookings for the flights, trains, hotels in Lima and Cusco, the dinner show in Cusco, as well as breakfast each morning, were perfect and their staffs were very helpful in every way. We enjoyed Peru very much and wish to return again.</p>\r\n<p>Thank you,</p>','Doug and Theâ??<br />California, USA. ','','','',59,0,0,NULL,NULL,NULL),(39,1,'Dear Peru For Less','<p>My trip to Peru was wonderful! Thank you for all of your help. Everything went \r\nsmoothly, and everything was well organized. We also met 2 men who you had \r\nhelped with arrangements, and they were having a great trip as well! I will \r\nnever forget my Peru experience, thank you again! I will definitely be \r\nrecommending Peru For Less to others.</p>','Jennifer,<br />Los Angeles, CA.','','','',60,0,0,NULL,NULL,NULL),(40,1,'Dear Mr. Garcia,','<p>Our trip in Peru was fabulous and very memorable. All the arrangements went smoothly. Your colleagues in Cuzco and Aguas Calientes took excellent care of us and went out of their way to be helpful. We will certainly tell anyone who asks about our positive experience with Peru For Less and the excellent staff. </p>\r\n<p>With regards,</p>','Karlene<br />Arlington, VA.','','','',61,0,0,NULL,NULL,NULL),(41,1,'Dear Peru For Less','<p>After researching numerous tour operators we choose Peru For Less. What \r\na great trip we had at a reasonable price.&nbsp;The guides were all there at the \r\nappropriate times, they were very friendly and informative. Everything went \r\nvery smoothly. We didn\'t have any problems with any of our transfers \r\nthroughout Peru. We really enjoyed our trip in Peru, and can\'t wait to go \r\nback again.&nbsp;I have recommended Peru For Less to all my friends.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>Muchas Gracias. </p>','Paul,<br />Jacksonville, Florida.','','','',66,0,0,NULL,NULL,NULL),(42,1,'Dear Peru For Less','<p>Thank you for our wonderful trip to Peru; this is a trip we will always \r\nremember.&nbsp;A special thanks to Ale for organizing our trip so perfectly, and \r\nalso a special thank you to Rossie our representative in Cusco who helped us \r\ntrack down our luggage and also made sure all of our excursions went well.&nbsp; \r\n<br />We very much&nbsp;enjoyed our horseback riding trip to the Tipon \r\nruins.&nbsp;We&nbsp;rode through the mountains amongst local farms, llama, \r\ncattle, sheep, chickens, beautiful flowers, and birds.&nbsp;We felt very safe \r\nand secure on these well trained horses.&nbsp; <br />We were also amazed at hiking \r\nthe Inka Trail, what a beautiful way to see the country.&nbsp;This was a very \r\ndifficult trail but it was made very enjoyable by our guide Santiago, our \r\nwonderful cook, and all of the very courteous and friendly porters.&nbsp;On the \r\nthird evening of the trail we were able to enjoy the hot springs in Aguas \r\nCalenties; that was a real pleasure for the aching muscles.<br />Rafting the \r\nUrabamba River was a pleasure. You have a whole different view of the country \r\nwhile riding the river through the valley. We had one level 3 rapids which were \r\nvery exciting for our first time rafting, and we all managed to stay in the \r\nraft- a special thank you to Allen our guide in our raft.<br />I also have to \r\nmention the absolutely amazing staff at Los Apus Hotel. Every one of the staff \r\nmembers at this hotel was always very friendly and helpful to us. They sent a \r\nbottle of champagne to our room for our Wedding Anniversary with a card signed \r\nby all of the staff.&nbsp;Our waiter even invited us to his home to meet his \r\nfamily.&nbsp;They made this trip very memorable.</p>\r\n<p>Thank you again for all of your assistance in planning this trip and making \r\nthis a very special memory for us.</p>','Mike &amp; Cindy. ','','','',67,0,0,NULL,NULL,NULL),(43,1,'Dear Bernard,','<p>We just had a wonderful trip to Peru! Your arrangements were really good. We had great time.We thoroughly enjoyed Lima, Cusco ,Macchu-Picchu and especially Posada Amazonas. Staying in Jungle lodge was quite an experience. We enjoyed every minute of it. All guides were very knowledgable and courtious. Overall people are very courteous in Peru. We had very good experience. Kaushik(my husband),Deepak and boys went to Hwayna picchu also.(excuse the spelling). Marcella was very helpful on last day. She could even spend couple of hours with us. We went to Indian market, Barranco, jockey club mall. Barranco was a very good area. We had fun. We also enjoyed ollyante Tambo and Pisac Indian Market. If any of our other friends wants to visit Peru,I will recommend your company. All the arrangements were good. You planned a perfect 10 day vacation for us with different highlights.Thank You.......................AdiosÃ¢â?¬Â...........</p>','Kalpana,<br />Boston, USA. ','','','',68,0,0,NULL,NULL,NULL),(44,1,'Dear Peru For Less','<p>Iâ??m just writing to say thank you for the most amazing experience Iâ??ve ever \r\nhad! I decided to take my mum to Peru for her 50th birthday, and we are both so \r\nglad we chose to go with Peru for Less. </p>\r\n<p>We went to so many different places in a short time, and were always met on \r\ntime and really welcomed by our guides. Every accommodation we had was amazing. \r\nWe were also very happy about how helpful and efficient Peru for Less was when \r\nwe phoned up with some last minute additions to our trip.</p>\r\n<p>The days we spent in Puerto Maldonadoâ??s rainforest were better than I could \r\nhave imagined. We were in a small group with a couple who told us that they had \r\npaid a lot more than we did with a different agency for exactly the same tour, \r\nso Peru for Less defiantly is a value for your money.</P>\r\n<P>The whole trip was perfect. For us coming all the way from Iceland, it was \r\nalmost like a fairytale, but we did have such high expectations, I didnâ??t really \r\nthink the trip itself could live up to them- it was even better! </p>\r\n<p>In a way, I think the floating islands of Lake Titicaca were the highlight \r\nfor me- completely unique, and the people were so lovely. In fact we were blown \r\naway by how nice the Peruvians are. I donâ??t think weâ??ve ever met friendlier \r\npeople.</p>\r\n<p>I just wanted to write a few words to say thanks to Claudia, Bernard, and \r\neveryone at Peru for Less. You guys really made this perfect for us, and my mum \r\ntold me it was the best birthday she had ever had.</p>','Sunna,<br />Iceland.','','','',69,0,0,NULL,NULL,NULL),(45,1,'Dear Peru For Less','<p>We thoroughly enjoyed our time in Peru . The accommodations were great, and it \r\nwas really helpful to have people meeting us at every destination and coming to \r\nour hotel to take us to that day\'s event. Going through Peru for less allowed us \r\nto customize our trip yet still have the security of knowing everything was \r\ntaken care of. The co-operating local tour companies were all helpful. \r\nInformative and accommodating.</p>','Robbie and Jean,<br />Portland, Oregon.','','','',70,0,0,NULL,NULL,NULL),(46,1,'Dear Diego,','<p>My trip was a dream come true! From the very beginning everything worked like clockwork. The bottom line is that I would recommend you and your company to anyone that wants to see Peru in a safe, classy, affordable, hassle-free way. On the way back from the Nazca fly over, when leaving the airport I was asked to pay 10.00 soles each for airport use, which I gladly did, a few minutes later our driver apologized for the error and got us our money back. I thought that was commendable since he could have easily pocketed the money for himself, (of course I tipped him well!). Thanks so much for everything you did; you did a great job all the way, from the minute I was lucky enough to get you in the phone. I will be calling you soon since I have a couple of friends that want to tour Machu Picchu and they think since I am from Peru, I know my way around (if they will only know!). Thanks Diego for making my trip a great experience and for the memories that will stay in my heart forever!</p>','Ana,<br />Canoga Park, CA.','','','',71,0,0,NULL,NULL,NULL),(47,1,'Dear Bernard,','<p>It is hard to put in words what an amazing experience I had in Peru.&nbsp;As \r\nan independent female traveler, your company gave me the personal attention and \r\ndetailed information necessary to truly have an extraordinary \r\nadventure.&nbsp;From your hotel recommendations to your selection of smart and \r\nsavvy tour guides, I only had a positive experience while traveling throughout \r\nyour beautiful country. Thank you for making my holiday one to remember forever! \r\n</p>\r\n<p>Please let me know if I can provide any of your future clients with a more in \r\ndepth point of view about Peru and/or your valued and highly professional \r\nservices.</p>\r\n<p>Kindest regards,</p>','Lori,<br />USA.','','','',72,0,0,NULL,NULL,NULL),(48,1,'Dear Ms. Kraus,','<P>We recently had the good pleasure of making arrangements for a trip to Peru. We had the good fortune of being assisted by Juan Pablo Salcedo. This young man is not only helpful, he is very articulate and professional. In spite of several difficulties in travel (unrelated to Peru For Lessâ?? arrangements), he made arrangements and salvaged our vacation. We have traveled in many places in the world; however, Dufray and I can unequivocally state that this was our best vacation ever. Upon our arrival in Cusco, Wilda met us at the airport. She was extremely helpful. She gave us her cell telephone number and offered to assist us in any way she could. When we missed our flight from Cusco to Puerto Maldonado, Loly Luz came to our assistance. She did not leave our side until we were safely on our trip from Cuzco to Puerto Maldonado. We believe that the high point of our trip was our visit to Machu Picchu. Fabricio is an exceptional guide. Our trip to Machu Picchu was not only enlightening, it proved to be a spiritual event. His knowledge of the Inca culture is exceptional. His presentation of Machu Picchu to us was very personal and emotional. We will forever be grateful to this young man. We understand you have many other people working behind the scenes. Our contact with your representatives was nothing short of exceptional. Again, this was one of our most exciting vacations ever. Thank you very much.</P>\r\n<P>Sincerely,</P>','Lionel &amp; Dufray <br />Edinburg, TX. ','','','',73,0,0,NULL,NULL,NULL),(49,1,'Dear Richard,','<p>We had a wonderful time and were very pleased with all your travel services. Everyone seemed to really enjoy what they were doing, were very knowledgeable and really cared about how we were enjoying ourselves. Hotels were great. </p>\r\n<p>Have tons of photos that we are enjoying.<br />Hope you are over your pneumonia and feeling much better. </p>\r\n<p>Thanks again</p>','Kevin,<br />USA.','kevin.jpg','Kevin at Machu Picchu','',424,0,0,NULL,NULL,NULL),(53,1,'Hi Ale,','<p>Peru was simply great!!! It was our first time to South America and we loved it!!! <br />The hotels we stayed in were consistant with our expectations of tourist class hotels....in particular we felt hotel Mariel and Corihausi deserved particular praise. The transfers all happened seamlessly and the tour guides were all of a good standard...overall, our impression of this tour was very very good. </p>\r\n<p>We left Peru with a ton of photos and lots of shopping and wonderful memories....one week is definitely not enough and I hope one day I will have the opportunity, time and money to go back to spend more time in your beautiful country!! </p>\r\n<p>Once again, thank you!!! </p>','Ben,<br />Singapore. ','goh.jpg','Ben at Machu Picchu, Cusco','',426,0,0,NULL,NULL,NULL),(54,1,'Hello Bernard,','<p>The trip went very well. It was definitely worthwhile despite my initial self imposed problems. All your contacts were very reliable keeping in touch and making sure we got to the right places at the right times. The several days in Lima were also nice. Had a chance to get to know the place a little. </p>\r\n<p>It was a great introduction to Peru. I\'d like to go back sometime and explore more in depth, maybe do the Inca trail etc.</p>\r\n<p>Appreciate all your efforts through the confusion. Hope things are going well with you. Let\'s keep in touch.</p>','Tom,<br />USA.','Spitzer.jpg','Tom in the Andes, Peru','',432,0,0,NULL,NULL,NULL),(55,1,'Hi Ximena,','<p>Did mean to get back to you sooner but have been suffering from post holiday \r\ndepression! We just wanted to say thanks again for all your work in booking our \r\ntrip- everything went really well, we even got upgraded to first class on the \r\nflight out from Madrid to Lima, which was very nice: how the other half live! \r\n<br />All the pick-ups were on time, in hindsight I should have booked the \r\ntransfers to and from the hotel with you on our return from Cusco to Lima, as it \r\nwas always good to see someone there with a board waiting for you. It makes \r\nthings really easy. <br />Weather was good, even got some sunshine in Lima, which \r\nwas quite rare by all accounts! And yes, it was hot up at Machu Picchu, but what \r\na place! It didnâ??t fill up with visitors either. We loved the market at Pisaq, \r\nreally could have blown the whole budget there, but had to remember that we had \r\nto carry it all with us. <br />We have enclosed a photo we took at the National \r\nStadium in Lima, as we went up to have a look. The taxi driver took his life in \r\nhis hands for this picture, as he stood in the middle of the road. Thatâ??s why \r\nI\'m looking at the traffic- someone slapped him on the bum as he drove past! But \r\nhe didnâ??t seem to mind! Anyway, just a big thanks again for a wonderful \r\ntrip.</p>','Roy and Jacqui, <br />Scotland. ','Roy.jpg','Roy and Jacqui at the National Stadium, Lima','',433,0,0,NULL,NULL,NULL),(56,1,'Dear Peru For Less','<p>The trip with my mother to PERU is an experience I will never forget. Even if \r\nyou\'ve read a thousand books and talked to a million people about PERU, you \r\nwon\'t have the same experience of taking just are step and taking in the air, \r\nisn\'t the same.</p>\r\n<p>Not only did I learn about the ruins from the tour guides, I learned the \r\nphilosophy, and the INCA culture, and some jokes to make the tour more FUN!. \r\n</p>\r\n<p>I will always remember the grocery store owner that spoke to my Mother and I \r\nabout the QUECHUA Language for 2 hours at store, it was the greatest lecture \r\never! </p>\r\n<p>My Mother and I will never forget the BICYCLE-TAXI ride (That speeeeeeeeed is \r\nsuch an adventure!) we took back to the hotel in PUNO from a dinner and live \r\nperformance, my Mother screamed the whole BICYCLE-TAXI ride. Oh! MAMALLAY (Madre \r\nmia!:in Quechua) </p>\r\n<p>I felt jealous to see some of the Island people of Lake TITIKAKA, never saw a \r\ncar before and never heard the car alarm go off all night because of a car \r\nthief, which always happens around New York City where we live. </p>\r\n<p>I hope PERU stays the same forever!!. <br />Thank you JP.and all of the Peru \r\nfor Less staff! </p>','Hana,<br />New York, USA. ','hana.jpg','Hana at Machu Picchu, Cuzco','',434,0,0,NULL,NULL,NULL),(58,1,'Dear Peru For Less','<p>Our trip was more than we ever expected.&nbsp;All of the travel arrangements \r\nwere perfect, and everyone was so friendly and accommodating. The weather \r\nwas very nice (we expected a lot of rain, but we only had a few hours of rain in \r\nthe jungle). Our trip&nbsp;was great. </p>\r\n<p>I think the highlight of our trip was Machu Picchu. It was incredible to see \r\nthe ruins, and it was so beautiful.&nbsp;We also loved Cusco, and the Jungle \r\nTrip was also incredible.&nbsp; We saw a family of giant river&nbsp;otters on \r\nLake Sandoval, two caimans, red howler monkeys, bats, and many birds. We \r\nalso&nbsp;saw a capybara&nbsp;on the Madre de Dios. We loved everything about \r\nPeru and would love to return. An added bonus that we did not plan was the \r\nFestival of the Virgin of Candelaria, in Puno. The parade was spectacular.</p>\r\n<p>Thanks again for all of your help.&nbsp; We hope to visit Peru again soon, \r\nand we will certainly recommend Peru for Less to our friends.</p>\r\n<p>Sincerely, </p>','Bob &amp; Mary,<br />Salt Lake City, Utah.','bob.jpg','Bob and Mary at Ollantaytambo, Cusco','',436,0,0,NULL,NULL,NULL),(59,1,'Hi Richard,','<p>We had a wonderful trip. Thank you for all the help. Everything \r\nwent smoothly.&nbsp; Great guides and transfers were always there waiting for \r\nus. We highly recommend the trekking. Our group was just four and we were able \r\nto go at our own pace. We carried on after Huarmihuanusqa&nbsp; pass and \r\nstopped at&nbsp; Chaqui Cocha.&nbsp; So our second day was really big, but we \r\nwere so happy we went on.&nbsp;Pacaymayo was crowded and muddy because of the \r\nrain. The Hotels you arranged were wonderful.&nbsp;We will always remember our \r\ntrip to Peru . What a wonderful experience.</p>\r\n<p>Thanks again, </p>','Carolyn, Phillip, Thomas, and Jennifer,<br />USA.','gilbertson-kohlhardt.jpg','Carolyn, Phillip, Thomas, and Jennifer in the Ande','',437,0,0,NULL,NULL,NULL),(60,1,'Dear Mark and Claudia,','<p>Jim and I had a fabulous time in Peru thanks to all the hard work you all put \r\nforth coordinating our trip in April to this most fascinating and beautiful \r\nland.<br />Obliviously, it is the people who make it so very worthwhile, and we \r\nwant to express our most sincere gratitude to all those who made it very \r\ncomfortable and pleasurable for us. <br />Peru, its people, culture and beauty \r\nwill remain forever in our hearts as a very special place, and we do hope to \r\nreturn one day in the future.</p>\r\n<p>With Sincerest Gratitude, </p>','Pat and Jim,<br />USA.','pat-jim.jpg','Pat and Jim in the Sacred Valley, Cusco','',441,0,0,NULL,NULL,NULL),(61,1,'Dear Marcos,','<p>We had a fabulous time! The personnel were helpful, friendly and very \r\nknowledgeable. We thoroughly enjoyed all aspects of the adventure. We fell in \r\nlove with Peru and are eager to return. Our very best salutations to you and \r\nyour great crew!</p>','Joel and Rhea. ','Rhea.jpg','Joel and Rhea at Machu Picchu, Cusco','',442,0,0,NULL,NULL,NULL),(62,1,'Dear Bernard,','<p>Thanks for your nice note, yes we enjoyed our trip to Peru very much.</p\r\n<p>We will keep you in mind for our next south-american adventure, and any of our friends will be reffered to you too.</p>\r\n<p>The book you sent us is beautiful, it is sitting on our table, in the living room, constant reminder of how beautiful and interesting Peru is.</p> \r\n<p>With best wishes.</p>\r\n<p>Yours Truly,</p>','Naomi and Rafael,<br />New Jersey, USA.','Rafael.jpg','Naomi and Rafael in Peru','',448,0,0,NULL,NULL,NULL),(63,1,'Dear Peru For Less','<p>I don\'t think I have ever visited another country where I felt so welcomed and cared for. I can\'t say enough about the personal and efficient service we received from your folks.<strong> Laura, Rosie, Maria, Umberto, the friendly drivers and the folks at the Archeologo were always a step ahead of us, so we had absolutely no worries about when, how or where.</strong> Probably our favorite adventure was the fabulous rafting day provided by Willie; he was full of enthusiasm as well as knowledge about everything we saw.</p>\r\n<p>Steve and Josh were totally comfortable with the Inca Trail hike, thanks to Norma and Maria; I understand their encouragement and fun wafted the hikers up the trail with only a little huffing and puffing! In fact, the \"boys\" went on to climb Huayna Picchu the next day! As for me,<strong> I must say that Darwin, at Machu Picchu, is absolutely the best tour guide I have ever experienced in many, many years of travel.</strong></p>\r\n<p>Best regards, JP</p>\r\n','Carol (Palm Beach, Florida)<br/>\r\nTraveled to: Cusco, Sacred Valley, Machu Picchu\r\n','elder.jpg','Carol at Machu Picchu, Cusco','\"I can\'t say enough about the personal and efficient service we received from your folks.\"',100034,0,0,NULL,'2014-09-10 22:55:10',NULL),(64,1,'Dear Ximena,','<p>We were very satisfied with the 3 weeks trip to Peru, and with your \r\nOrganization. For all the amazing work and committed assistance you put into \r\npreparing our trip, we thank you again Ximena! You created something that fitted \r\nour interests perfectly and allowed us to have an unforgettable vacation in \r\nSouth America.</p>\r\n<p>We\'ll always remember the incredible experience we had in Peru.<br />We\'ll be \r\nhappy to recommend Peru For Less to anyone in Italy interested in taking a trip \r\nto Peru. Thank you and see you soon!!</p>','Alberto and Anna,<br />Turin, Italy.','Castagneri.jpg','Alberto and Anna in Peru','',450,0,0,NULL,NULL,NULL),(65,1,'Dear Peru For Less','<p>I cannot believe it has been nearly 2 months since I was in Peru. What a wonderful and unforgettable experience. I loved the beauty of Cusco and the gem of the Inca ruin, Machu-Pichu. I regret that I didn?t spent much time in there. </p>\r\n<p>I wish I could have stayed and seen more places in Peru. Your representative, Rossie, gave me good advice; she was nice and punctual. And drivers for the pick up service were also punctual and friendly every time. </p>\r\n<p>Overall, I had great pleasure in Peru. And I would like to say thank you for serving nice tour to Peru for Less. I\'m sorry for this late reply. I hope this review might help your next customer.</p>\r\n<p>Yours Sincerely,</p>','Junko,<br />Minneapolis, Minnesota.','junko.jpg','Junko in Cusco','',451,0,0,NULL,NULL,NULL),(66,1,'Dear Peru For Less','<p>My wife and I had originally planned to visit Peru in September of \'03, but \r\ndropped the idea after the agency we were working through couldn\'t get things \r\ntogether. Although disappointed at the time, it turned out to be a great move, \r\nas it enabled us to try again a year later through Peru for Less. Most \r\nespecially, we were able to take full advantage of the patience and diligence of \r\nMarc Harrison, who worked with us for weeks to put together the perfect \r\nitinerary. </p>\r\n<p>Thanks to Marcos and the Peru for Less team, we ended up with one of the \r\nbest trips we have ever taken. Our two weeks in Peru were extraordinary, and \r\nevery day was a new and exciting adventure. We were especially pleased when we \r\nwere able to hook up with Marcos in Cusco and personally thank him for putting \r\ntogether such a remarkable trip. We would enthusiastically recommend Peru for \r\nLess to all travelers who want the best experience and value for their vacation \r\ndollar. </p>','James and Diana,<br />Rockville, Maryland.','Galfund.jpg','James and Diana at Machu Picchu, Cusco','',452,0,0,NULL,NULL,NULL),(67,1,'Dear Bernard,','<p>We would like to thank you for arranging such a wonderful Peru trip. One thing for sure, a trip to Peru is a memorable and exciting adventure. We found the people to be colorful, charming, and ever willing to share their beautiful country with strangers. Now back in Colorado, we think back to all the sights, sounds and tastes we enjoyed.</p>\n<p>One of our fondest memories was our meal with you at Tanta Restaurant. We have never tasted such wonderful fish prepared in so many different ways. Thank you for taking the time out of your busy schedule to meet with us and introduce us to Peru.</p>\n<p>The jungle segment at Posada Amazonas was terrific--the Ese\'ejas people and Rainforest Expeditions were gracious hosts. The Posada lodge was wonderful, but there is no way we could have prepared for the intensity and lush vegetation of the jungle. We loved the wildlife at Posada, and found the sights and sounds of the jungle exhilarating.</p>\n<p>We loved the Nazca adventure, and seeing the geo-glyphs from the six-seater Cessna was great. As was the boat ride to see all the marine and bird life at Ballestas Islands. The Uros and Taquile communities on Lake Titicaca were also so interesting to visit, and the residents there were such a delight.</p>\n<p><strong>Cusco and Machu Picchu were certainly the highlights of our trip. Even though we read books and have seen documentaries of the Inca Ruins, nothing prepared us for the immensity, lushness, and location of the ruin. Seeing the ruin as the morning mist cleared was so memorable.</strong></p>\n<p>We felt fortunate that our Sacred Valley tour was on a Sunday, as both the Pisac and Chinceros Indian Markets were in full swing. We loved the textiles, alpaca sweaters, and crafts. Additionally, the ruins of Sacsayhuaman and Ollantaytambo are not to be missed.</p>\n<p>PeruRail provided excellent service, and the trains were well maintained and comfortable. The scenery along both the Machu Picchu and Cusco to Puno routes was outstanding--following along the rush and roar of the Urubamba River as we descended toward Machu Picchu from Cusco was great, as well as the views of the Andes with large flocks of llama and alpaca en route to Puno.</p>\n<p>Again, <strong>thank you for assisting us while in Peru, and for making the arrangements necessary for a memorable trip.</strong> All of the agents and guides were knowledgeable, courteous, and very helpful. We would be most pleased to recommend your company and services to other Peru travelers and look forward to sharing pictures of Peru with friends and family.</p>\n<p>Yours Truly,</p>\n','Dave and Blanche (Colorado, USA)<br/>\r\nTraveled to: Nazca Lines, Ballestas Islands, Cusco, Sacred Valley, Machu Picchu, Lake Titicaca, Puerto Maldonado\r\n','Roberts.jpg','Dave and Blanche in Peru','\"One of our fondest memories was our meal with you at Tanta Restaurant.. Thank you for taking the time out of your busy schedule to meet with us and introduce us to Peru.\"',100054,0,0,NULL,'2014-09-10 23:08:24',NULL),(68,1,'Dear Richard,','<p>We really enjoyed our vacation to Peru. Everything went smoothly. There was \r\nalways someone to meet us at the airport and take us to our hotel. All of the \r\naccommodations were very nice and a couple of them had great views out the \r\nwindow. Machu Picchu was spectacular.</p>\r\n<p>We enjoyed our stay with the family on Amantani Island. Prior to leaving for \r\nthe island, the tour guide suggested we take something to the family we would be \r\nstaying with. He said is was optional. He recommended canned milk, sugar, pasta, \r\nor rice. We bought coloring books, and small matchbox trucks in the United \r\nStates to take to the&nbsp;children. </p>\r\n<p>Thank you so much for all you did to make our trip a trip&nbsp;to remember. I \r\nwould certainly recommend Peru For Less to all my friends.</p>','Tom,<br />Florida, USA.','Spradlin.jpg','Tom in Peru','',455,0,0,NULL,NULL,NULL),(69,1,'Dear Ximena,','<p>We had a fantastic time. All of the arrangements you made were perfect from \r\nthe hotel in Cusco to our fantastic guide on the Inca Trail, Norma Flores.</p>\r\n<p>Thank You.</p>','Jonathan,<br />Virginia, USA.','jonathan.jpg','Jonathan in the Andes, Peru','',456,0,0,NULL,NULL,NULL),(70,1,'Dear Bernard,','<p>We very much enjoyed our trip to Peru. We were amazed by the variety of climate, topography, landscapes, archeology, and culture in your country. And we were impressed by the efficiency of the transportation systems --- whether by air, rail, water, or highway. Contacts, tours, and transfers were all as scheduled. <strong>The trip exceeded our expectations. There were many memorable moments, among them going to dinner with you to Tanta\'s in Lima, a most amazing seafood restaurant. Perhaps the most unusual, if not the best seafood we have ever tasted.</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>We would highly recommend your Travel Agency to friends and relatives. <strong>We were favorably impressed by the tour guides on all of our mini-tours. They were knowledgeable, friendly, and spoke very good English, for those of us who don\'t understand Spanish.</strong> And they were most helpful in answering our many questions, especially when it came to giving advice on good places to shop, and excellent restaurants. We fell in love with the Alpaca wool sweaters and multi colored table cloths.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>We think that what makes your agency exceptional is the personal, 24-hour service you provide, your ease of accessibility throughout Peru, and your prompt, courteous, and competent attention to our needs.<strong> There will always be glitches in any trip, no matter how well planned. And we had our share over 20 days. However, you and your team always responded in a timely and more-than-satisfactory fashion.</strong> Case in point --- when our flight from Puno to Arequipa was cancelled one morning, resulting in the cancellation of a scheduled afternoon tour of Arequipa, at no expense to us, you rescheduled our flight to Arequipa, as well as the city tour and return flight to Lima on our last day in country. This actually turned out to be a more convenient itinerary for us in the long run, with no loss of planned sight-seeing.</p>\r\n<p>Thank you again for the attention you and your staff gave to us during our delightful and adventurous stay in your beautiful country!</p>\r\n<p>Sincerely,</p>\r\n','Jeff and Dolly (USA)<br/>\r\nTraveled to: Lima, Machu Picchu, Puno, Arequipa\r\n','Heywood.jpg','Jeff and Dolly in Peru','\"What makes your agency exceptional is the personal, 24-hour service you provide, your ease of accessibility throughout Peru, and your prompt, courteous, and competent attention to our needs.\"',100044,0,0,NULL,'2014-09-10 22:55:09',NULL),(71,1,'Richard,','<p>We\'re back in the US and wanted to thank you for all your help and \r\nsuggestions. The trip was arranged in just the right order of Cusco first and \r\nLima last, and the assistance we received from your agents in Cusco was \r\nexceptional. We particularly want to thank Carlos who unfortunately we did not \r\nget to see our last day. He and the entire Cusco group were there to help us \r\ntransition and really enjoy the trip.<br />Again, many thanks!</p>\r\n<p>Thanks again, </p>','David,<br />Atlanta, GA.','Davidatlanta.jpg','David at Machu Picchu, Cusco','',459,0,0,NULL,NULL,NULL),(72,1,'Dear Ale,','<p>What a pleasant surprise to have your two e-mails waiting when we returned \r\nfrom South America; and yes, the trip was FANTASTIC!!  Although our plane \r\nwas almost two hours late arriving into Lima, we were met by a host and driver \r\nwho took us directly to the Marriott in Miraflores and verified the scheduled \r\nitinerary during our stay. We had a beautiful room overlooking the Pacific Ocean \r\non the 25th floor, and access to the Executive Club with its amenities \r\n(breakfast buffet and evening snacks).</p>\r\n<p>Yes, we did eat at Astrid&nbsp;y Gaston (scallops and lamb washed down with a \r\nnice sauvignon blanc), as well as the Rosa Nautica (pisco sours, ceviche \r\nand another fine wine). They were the two&nbsp;most memorable restaurants \r\nbecause of their ambiance and unique locations. </p>\r\n<p>Speaking of memorable;&nbsp;the Monasterio hotel and the Plaza de Armas in \r\nCuzco, the train ride to Machu Picchu (we saw two Andean condors soaring above \r\nthe train en-route to Aguas Calientes), the Pueblo Hotel where we met Oscar \r\nMedina, the author of, \"The Enigma of Machu Picchu\" which he was pleased to \r\nautograph for us, magnificent Machu Picchu (unbelievable stone construction \r\nhanging on a mountain side&nbsp;most readily accessible by those condors), \r\nOllataytambo (Penne and I climbed all the way to the top - whew!) the Andean \r\nExplorer train ride across the Altiplano to Puno, Lake Titicaca, the Uros \r\nIndians and their floating islands, reed houses and boats, and last but not \r\nleast, Isla Taquile and the knitted goods of the men and women (another arduous \r\nclimb to the top of the island - extremely difficult to breathe). </p>\r\n<p>Yes, we enjoyed Peru; its beautiful, friendly, and cheerful people, its \r\nhistory and culture, its mysterious ruins, and its special charm (enhanced by \r\nPisco sours and mate de coca).<br />Would we consider returning, and are we \r\nrecommending the trip to our friends? YOU BET! It will be interesting to see \r\nwhether my ex-work associate contacts you before we do; we are anxious to return \r\nto your fascinating country, but have to wait for awhile until family \r\ncommitments are met. When we do decide on a date, we\'ll definitely be contacting \r\nPeru For Less, and hopefully working with you again, since you know our \r\npreferences for hotel and travel accommodations.</p>\r\n<p>Ale, thank you so much for arranging and coordinating such a perfectly \r\ndelightful adventure. Before we left the U.S., I would have considered it a \r\nonce-in-a-lifetime experience. Now we are already planning a return!</p>\r\n<p>Take care!. </p>','John and Penne,<br />New Mexico, USA.','john.jpg','John in Peru','',461,0,0,NULL,NULL,NULL),(74,1,'Dear Peru For Less','<p>Thanks again for arranging such an amazing trip for Jessica and myself to Peru this past June. I know how annoying all of my pre-trip questions and itinerary changes must have been <strong>and I want to thank you for always being responsive and professional in working with me to make sure I was comfortable and satisfied.</strong></p>\r\n\r\n\r\n<p>If that wasn\'t enough, I was absolutely blown away with the 5-Star service we received once we arrived in Peru. The PFL staff and the Peruvian people treated us like royalty. I will NEVER forget how Laura went out of her way to retrieve my brand new camera that I left on the airplane in Cusco ...and this was after it had departed and landed in Puerto Maldonado! She really pulled the rabbit out of the hat on that one.</p>\r\n<p>Thanks, too, for taking the time to meet us back in Lima on our last night in Peru at the Astrid y Gaston restaurant.  We thoroughly enjoyed the meal, the food, the wine and the company.  What a great way to end an already perfect experience!</p>\r\n\r\n\r\n<p>I look forward to a return trip and want to <strong>thank you again for all you did to make Jessica\'s \"senior trip\" one that neither she nor I will ever forget.</p>\r\n<p>You and the PFL staff are incredible.</strong></p>\r\n','Craig and Jessica (Baton Rouge, Louisiana)<br/>\r\nTraveled to: Lima, Cusco, Machu Picchu, Puerto Maldonado\r\n','Craig.jpg','Craig and Jessica in the Andes, Peru','\"I was absolutely blown away with the 5 - star service we received once we arrived in Peru. The PFL staff and the Peruvian people treated us like royalty.\"',100036,0,0,NULL,'2014-09-10 23:08:30',NULL),(75,1,'Dear Ximena,','<p>Thanks for following up with us. The trip was excellent, and your suggestions \r\nregarding accommodations and places to see were admired by many fellow \r\ntravelers. Thank you very much for your efforts to make our trip enjoyable. We \r\nhad a great time, and we really didn\'t want to come home. Vanessa and I have not \r\ntraveled through an agency before, and we were not disappointed by how efficient \r\nand reliable the entire process was.</p>\r\n<p>Thanks again for exceeding our expectations. We would gladly recommend Peru \r\nfor Less to anyone considering travel to South America.</P>\r\n<p>Sincerely, </p>','<br />Phillip and Vanessa,<br />California, USA. ','Phillip.jpg','Philip and Vanessa in Lima, Peru','',463,0,0,NULL,NULL,NULL),(76,1,'Hello Richard,','<p>We are writing to thank you and the Peruforless staff for the first class \r\norganisation of our recent holiday in Peru.&nbsp; All agencies used were \r\nfantastic.&nbsp; Most of our hotels exceeded our expectations,&nbsp;the tours \r\narranged were interesting and varied and the guides were all well informed and \r\ninteresting. </p>\r\n<p>We loved the whole experience. </p>','George and Jean,<br />The United Kingdom.','lane.jpg','George and Jean at Machu Picchu, Cusco','',464,0,0,NULL,NULL,NULL),(77,1,'Dear Ale,','<p>Thank you for the email inquiring about our trip. Yes we did have a great \r\ntime and we wish we were still there. The Hotels... Generally we thought the \r\nstandard was good to very good. The staffs in all the hotels were friendly and \r\nhelpful. Transport... We had no problems, pickups and transfers were always on \r\ntime. Your reps... Very warm, friendly people, always there if needed. </p>\r\n<p><strong>The places we visited:</strong></p>\r\n<p>Cuscoâ?¦ One of our favorite places, glad we spent a few days there. Thursday \r\nwas the highlight, watched England WIN a football match in the morning and then \r\nwatched the Corpus Christi parade in the afternoon (from the Cross Keys, a bar \r\nin the main square, balcony) so we had a great view.</p>\r\n<p>The Sacred Valleyâ?¦ We enjoyed the Pisaq market, and bought a few momentos. \r\nOllyantaytambo is a picturesque town with interesting Inca ruins. Our spare \r\nday&nbsp;in the sacred&nbsp;valley turned out to be an unexpected highlight. We \r\nwalked to Urubamba, not a tourist town, but very interesting. We \r\nwandered around the town visiting the market, witnessed a wedding, and in \r\nthe afternoon we followed the crowds and got to the Bullring. We watched several \r\nMatadors with the bulls, and young men trying to ride bareback on wild \r\nhorses. We used the local Tricycle-Taxis back to the hotel: an unusual ride that \r\ncost 2 soles. We saw a little bit of real Peru in this area. That night a brass \r\nband visited our hotel, and a party took place. We also had our first Pisco Sour \r\nhere... we liked this drink, and had several more during our travels.</p>\r\n<p>Machu Pichu. The ruins and the setting were breathtaking. You need \r\nlonger than the 2 hour guided tour to fully appreciate them and we are glad we \r\ncould stay longer. We walked to the Sun Gate (the place were people who have \r\ndone the Inca Trail first see Machu Pichu). It really is worth it as the view \r\nfrom here is the best you will ever see.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>The Colca Canyon trip was very enjoyable. The party of 13 was made up of \r\nAmericans, Mexicans, Spaniards, Australians, a couple from Equador and us from \r\nEngland. The tour guide, did a wonderful job explaining everything in 2 \r\nlanguages and got the whole group joining in everything. The scenery on the trip \r\nwas different from what we had seen in other parts of Peru and was well \r\nexplained by the guide. We picked a good day to visit the canyon, within 10 \r\nminutes of arriving we saw our first Condor, in the next hour we had 15 /20 \r\nsightings and twice a Condor flew over our heads only a few feet above us.</p>\r\n<p>We should end by thanking you for your efforts in helping us plan the trip. \r\nThe extra night in the Sacred Valley was a stroke of genius or luck, either way, \r\nwe loved that hotel and the day in Urubamba was one of those days that just \r\nhappen, you canâ??t plan them! Cusco is a beautiful city and from talking to other \r\ntravelers it is everyoneâ??s favorite place. The extra days we had there gave us a \r\nrest from traveling and we had a chance to just wander at our own pace.</p>\r\n<p>We would happily recommend Peru for Less to anyone. Will we come back again? \r\nWe hope soâ?¦..we have got a taste for South America, wish we were 21 years old \r\nand could join the backpackers spending several months thereâ?¦.we will be back \r\none day. </p>\r\n<p>Thank You, </p>','Cedric and Denise,<br />West Yorks, England.','Cedric.jpg','Cedric and Denise at Machu Picchu, Cusco','',465,0,0,NULL,NULL,NULL),(78,1,'Hi Ximena,','<p>I have to thank you again for the wonderful trip you organized for me Ximena. \r\nAfter all of the changes I came up with over the months of planning, which you \r\nmanaged to work in, the trip came together wonderfully well, and I\'ll have no \r\nhesitation in recommending Peru For Less to anybody wanting to see Machu Picchu \r\n(and I\'ll encourage them to go for all of the side trips too). </p>\r\n<p>Apart from seeing Giant Otters on Lake Sandoval on my birthday (what a \r\npresent!), I will treasure magical memories of Machu Picchu forever. Given that \r\nI was traveling on my own, I really appreciated being met and transported \r\nbetween airports and hotels, so I didn\'t have to worry about any arrangements. \r\nThere were no problems with any of the hotels either. The guides on the \r\ntours I went on were very considerate, and really helped to make my holiday \r\ngreat. </p>\r\n<p>I think Peru is somewhere everybody should have on their list of places to go \r\nbefore they die - it is a truly amazing place, with such diversity, and I only \r\njust skimmed the surface. Thanks for your help. </p>\r\n<p>Many thanks again,</p>','Gillian,<br />Darlington, UK.','Gillian.jpg','Gillian at Machu Picchu, Cusco','',466,0,0,NULL,NULL,NULL),(79,1,'Dear Peru For Less','<p>Our trip was great; everything went according to plan.&nbsp; We had a wonderful \r\ntrip, thanks to you and your agents on the ground in Peru and Ecuador. We have \r\nrecommended \'Peru For Less\' to several friends who are interested in a wonderful \r\nexperience! Thanks for all your help!</p>','Mike and Janice,<br />Alliston, Ontario, Canada.','Mike.jpg','Mike and Janice at Amantani Island, Lake Titicaca','',477,0,0,NULL,NULL,NULL),(80,1,'Hola Ximena,','<p>Our honeymoon was absolutely fantastic. Thanks for organizing it so well and letting people know it was a special holiday. We had a huge 4 poster bed in the Archeologo; flowers displaying ?congratulations? on our bed on arrival to the Eco Inn in Puno; and the most touching of all, the porters carried a cake and bottle of champagne all the way to the first camp on the Inca Trail for us to celebrate. I would have loved to see more of Peru ? we will have to come back some day for a trek in Huascaran! We really enjoyed our holiday and you definitely did a very good job. </p>\r\n<p>Many thanks to Marcos too, he was very helpful on arrival, and managed to get the hotel staff to buy me some medicine I?d forgotten in the UK! Best wishes to yourself and the whole Peru for Less team.</p>\r\n<p>Thanks again. </p>','Michael and Karen,<br />Quebec, Canada.','Michael.jpg','Michael and Karen at Machu Picchu, Cuzco','',478,0,0,NULL,NULL,NULL),(81,1,'Hello,','<p>I would like to thank the Peru For Less team, and more particularly Ale, for \r\nthe wonderful 2 weeks I just spent in Peru. Everything was as planned as \r\nexpected, and even betterâ?¦ The guides were very knowledgeable, friendly, and \r\nfunny; and the pick-ups to the different sites were always on time. I did Cuzco, \r\nthe Valle Sagrado, the Camino Inca to Macchu Pichu, and finished with Lago \r\nTiticaca. An amazing experience.</p>\r\n<p>Sincerely, </p>','Christophe,<br />Montreal, Quebec.','Christophe.jpg','Christophe in the Andes, Peru','',479,0,0,NULL,NULL,NULL),(82,1,'Hi Ximena,','<p>My wife and I would like to thank you and your company for an outstanding job on \r\nour vacation in Peru. Our hotel in Cusco &nbsp;had lots of character and \r\ncharm and the staff went out of their way to make us feel right at home. Your \r\nreps were always in touch with us to outline the next days activities and they \r\nwere just a cell phone call away if we needed any assistance. Our dinner at the \r\nrestaurant was outstanding and the show with the local musicians ended&nbsp;the \r\nnight perfectly. I recommend to anyone going to Macchu Picchu to select the \r\nPrivate Guide that was provided in our package....he was excellent and we had a \r\ngreat time as he walked through Macchu Picchu. Buying a tour book doesn\'t even \r\ncome close to the knowledge provided by the guide. Our stay in Lima was also \r\nvery enjoyable, and the hotel was again very charming. We can\'t thank you enough \r\nfor the great holiday that we had, your company is first class. Thanks again \r\nXimena on an outstanding job!!!</p>','Murray and Sandy,<br />Langely BC, Canada.','murray.jpg','Murray and Sandy at Machu Picchu, Cuzco','',480,0,0,NULL,NULL,NULL),(85,1,'Dear Ale,','<p>Thank you so much for helping plan our trip to Cusco and Machu Picchu ! You \r\nwere so helpful with advice and plans and your emails describing Peru and \r\nanswering my many questions were great. I found your website on the Fodors web \r\nsite and it is true, PFL is an excellent resource. Your organization has an \r\nincredible depth of knowledge about Peru , which we did not have. You folks have \r\nreally been to all of the places on your web site and you know all of the \r\nins-and-outs about Peru travel. I have told many friends about how great you \r\nare!</p>','Catherine,<br />Massachusetts, USA. ','smith.jpg','Catherine in Cuzco','',481,0,0,NULL,NULL,NULL),(86,1,'Dear Peru For Less','<p>Thank you so much for everything! Everything about the trip was PERFECT! \r\nEverything went smoothly at Machu Picchu . Rossie from CAT Cusco was excellent!! \r\nShe gave us her cell phone numbers just in case anything came up and I felt \r\nconfident that even if there were to be more landslides she would have helped us \r\nto get up to or back from Machu Picchu somehow.</p>\r\n<p>All the transfers went smoothly. All the hotels were nice and their staff \r\nwere all very friendly and helpful. The entire trip was just one amazing day \r\nafter another. Thank you for all your work in arranging everything and for being \r\navailable to answer all my questions, even once we were in Peru. My wife and I \r\ncan\'t wait to visit South America again. When we do we will definitely be \r\ncalling Peru for Less again. As soon as we got back I started looking at your \r\nwebsite again to see all the other places you have tours in!!.</p>\r\n<p>Thanks again, </p>','Andy and Mary,<br />California, USA. ','sanchez.jpg','Andy and Mary in Lima','',482,0,0,NULL,NULL,NULL),(87,1,'Hola Ximena,','<p>Juleen and I had a wonderful time in Peru. Thanks so much to you and \r\nPeruforless. The personal touches that were provided by you and the staff at \r\nPeruforless were remarkable. We really enjoyed meeting with you and your \r\nwonderful parents in Lima. Cucsco, MachuPicchu, and the surrounding area were \r\nbreathtaking and inspiring. We are grateful to all the staff members for making \r\nour trip productive and worry free. Special thanks to Louise, Carlos, and Maria. \r\nOur Guides Darwin Comacho Pederes and Sylvia were passionate and informative, \r\nand gave us an excellent insight to the history and beauty of Peru and the \r\npeople. I would highly recommend you and the services provided by Peruforless to \r\nothers, and plan to use them again myself.<br />Thanks so much for making this \r\ntrip a vacation of a lifetime for Juleen and I.</p>\r\n<p>Best wishes until we see you again. </p>','Dave and Juleen,<br />Minnesota.','dave.jpg','Dave and Juleen in Peru','',483,0,0,NULL,NULL,NULL),(88,1,'Bernard,','<p>I have only just checked my e-mails today on arriving back at work. Yes, we \r\nwere in Cusco. It\'s a shame that I hadn\'t realised earlier as we could have met \r\nup. We spent the night in Cross Keys before going into the square which as you \r\nknow was wild. We have never seen a party like it !</p>\r\n<p>As for the trip as a whole we were extremely impressed and I would recommend \r\nyou to anyone.</p>\r\n<p>The hotels were better than I was expecting and the transfers were always \r\npunctual and very friendly.</p>\r\n<p>We had some great seats at the very front of the train back from Machu Pichu \r\n(literally the front two) and the train down to Puno was also something else \r\n(more like the Orient Express).</p>\r\n<p>Four days in the jungle was just right time wise but brilliant as we saw so \r\nmany animals and birds. Again the people were very informative and friendly.</p>\r\n<p>I could write and tell you about each stop we made but basically we couldn\'t \r\nhave asked for much more.</p>\r\n<p>We also got engaged on New Years Day at Machu Pichu so the itinerary worked \r\nout perfect for me to propose.</p>\r\n<p>So, thanks for a great trip, it was good to meet you and if we come to South \r\nAmerica again we will get you to arrange it.</p>\r\n<p>Best wishes <br />Andrew</p>\r\n<p>PS I\'m going to get a recipe for Pisco Sour and get stuck into the bottle you \r\ngave us. </p>','Andrew,<br />United Kingdom.','perchard.jpg','Andrew on Lake Titicaca','',484,0,0,NULL,NULL,NULL),(89,1,'Dear Peru For Less','<p>I just wanted to send you a belated thank you for a fantastic trip? We thought the quality of the hotels was excellent (they surpassed our expectations). As for the trail itself, the food, accommodation and guide were superb. Speaking to other people that did the Inca trail with other companies, we seemed to have the best experience of them all. Thanks again, and keep up the good work! We will be sure to recommend you to others.</p>\r\n<p>Regards</p>','Dave,<br />UK.','cook.jpg','Dave at Machu Picchu, Cuzco','',488,0,0,NULL,NULL,NULL),(90,1,'Hello Bernard,','<p>We were absolutely delighted with the smoothness of the arrangements youmade. \r\nAll our connections were there and everyone was helpful and friendly.This was a \r\nmajor benefit for us as we were first-time travelers, not only to Peru, but to \r\nSouth America. We loved the hotels in Arequipa, Aguas Calientes and the final \r\none in Cusco. We also were very happy with the hotel in Lima. </p>\r\n<p><strong>These are the things we enjoyed the most (not in any order of \r\npreference):</strong></p>\r\n<p>1) Machu Picchu - we really needed the extra day there, and could have stayed \r\nlonger. It is every bit as wonderful as the pictures show.</p>\r\n<p>2) The scenery and countryside - Peru is beautiful and we have only seen the \r\nsouth. Our photographs show how lovely it is.</p>\r\n<p>3) The people - a big one this - your tour guides are outstanding and \r\neveryone we met was incredibly friendly. It may be that my small amount of \r\nSpanish helped - I found people most anxious to talk to me when they knew I \r\ncould understand them and respond in their language.</p>\r\n<p>4) The food!!! How does everyone eat three super meals a day and stay so fit? \r\nThe food at Posada Amazonas was particularly outstanding.</p>\r\n<p>5) The buildings and ruins - how impressive! We felt that we were seeing a \r\nsurfeit of riches on our tour of the Sacred Valley.</p>\r\n<p>6) The cities - each one has its own character. We thought Aguas Calientes \r\nwas a blast! I loved Arequipa.</p>\r\n<p>7) Your internal transportation is outstanding - very professional, very \r\nefficient - and the fashion show on the return trip from Machu Picchu to Cusco \r\nwas really fun.</p>\r\n<p>8) The organization of the tour - because it was so very smooth, it gave us \r\nmore time and opportunity to enjoy our trip. We had confidence that people would \r\nbe were you said they would be and everyone worked with us to make this a great \r\nvacation.</p>\r\n<p>I\'m sure there are many more highlights that I cannot think of right now - \r\nyou can tell what a wonderful trip we had. We would not hesitate to recommend \r\nyour agency to anyone who is interested in traveling to Peru and you are welcome \r\nto use us as a reference!</p>\r\n<p>Now that we have visited Peru, we will be very interested and concerned about \r\nwhat happens in the future. Your lovely country\'s biggest asset is its people, \r\nwho work very hard, especially physically, in the countryside.</p>\r\n<p>All good wishes, especially for the New Year! </p>','Corrinne and Michael,<br />USA.','Corrinne.jpg','Corrinne at Machu Picchu, Cuzco','',489,0,0,NULL,NULL,NULL),(91,1,'Hello Bernard,','<p>My trip was really great. Everything that we had planned ran so smoothly. All \r\nof my transfers were on time and the staff was very helpful. The horseback \r\nriding and rafting days were great. The bus tours were thorough and I met some \r\nnice people along the way.</p>\r\n<p>I\'m really glad I spent the night in Aguas Caliente. That gave me the \r\nopportunity to do some serious hiking on Huayna Picchu. It was spectacular! I \r\nwas also happy with both of my hotels, which were nicer than I expected for a \r\n\"budget\" tour. Thanks for making my trip so fun and easy! I will definitely \r\nrecommend Peru for Less to anyone I know taking a trip to Peru.</p>','Tracy,<br />USA.','larson.jpg','Tracy in Cuzco','',490,0,0,NULL,NULL,NULL),(92,1,'Hi Bernard,','<p>Just wanted to say THANKS to you for ANOTHER job well done. Last year you did a wonderful job on planning our Peru trip and this year it was the Galapagos. Both well done. <strong>Sudha, I and the kids just returned from the Galapagos and what a time we had. As usual, you delivered on everything you promised.</strong> The trip, one that we will fondly remember for years to come, was enjoyable as well as educational. And as always, it was a pleasure working with you during the planning.</p>\r\n<p>As for our ship, The Legend, it\'s a ship that you can feel very comfortable in recommending to your other clients. Yvette Hauser and her crew took great care of us, paying attention to every detail and ensuring we were comfortable and well attended to. <strong>As for our naturalist/guide, Jorge, we loved having him as our guide.</strong> In addition to showing us the sights, he also provided detailed explanations of why things are the way they are in the Galapagos.<strong> Given our science backgrounds and keen interest in this subject, we enjoyed and learned much from his talks. Between us, we now refer to him as \"Professor Jorge\". :)</strong> As for the ship itself, it has the amenities and comforts of a large ship and yet the number of passengers on it is small enough to make it a more \"intimate\" experience.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Well, that\'s all for now. I just wanted to say THANKS to you for all that you do.<strong> Clearly, when we travel again to South America, you\'ll be sure to hear from us.</strong></p>\r\n','Vinay and Sudha (Virginia US)<br/>\r\nTraveled to: Galapagos Islands\r\n','Kumar.jpg','Vinay and Sudha at the Galapagos Islands','\"[We] just returned from the Galapagos and what a time we had. As usual, you delivered on everything you promised.\"',100051,0,0,NULL,'2014-09-10 22:55:09',NULL),(93,1,'Dear Peru For Less','<p>We just returned home from Peru and wanted to let you know what a wonderful \r\ntime we had. Peru For Less exceeded our expectations for a tour company and made \r\nsure we had a safe, exciting, and informative trip. </p>\r\n<p>The contacts and transport people were where they were supposed to be when \r\nthey were supposed to be there and guided us through every step of the journey. \r\nThey were knowledgeable, friendly, and accommodating. We very much appreciated \r\nyour phone call to check on us as well. I don\'t think we could have messed up \r\nthe trip if we had tried. </p>\r\n<p>We hope to return to Peru someday, and, when we do, it will be with Peru For \r\nLess. Nobody does it better. </p>\r\n<p>Pam and I gave each other this trip for Christmas. It was the best gift we \r\nhave given or received. Thanks for a wonderful holiday! </p>\r\n<p>Sincerely, </p>','Jim and Pam,<br />Fort Collins, Colorado.','Jordan.jpg','Jim and Pam in Cuzco','',492,0,0,NULL,NULL,NULL),(94,1,'Hi there Bernard,','<p>We are doing just fine, and yes, we miss Peru - the sunshine and the lovely \r\npeople! </p>\r\n<p>We would like to thank you for making our trip to Peru so memorable. \r\nEverything seemed to run smoothly and we were very impressed at each stagewith \r\nthe handovers and transfers. All the hotels we were in, were clean \r\nandcomfortable. We would gladly recommend \"Peru for Less\" to all our friends and \r\ncolleagues.As mentioned to you, we were initially impressed with the speed of \r\nyour return E mails, and your knowledge, gave us every confidence. </p>\r\n<p>We loved our trip to Lake Titicaca (had a little altitude sickness only) and \r\nof course Machu Picchu was most impressive, a dream come true! We had a \r\nwonderful flight over the Nazca lines, and the Ballestas islands were an utter \r\ndelight. <br />We would love to visit Peru again, and maybe visit Ecuador too. We \r\nwill most certainly contact you when we do so.</p>\r\n<p>Once again, thank you for all your help.</p>\r\n<p>Regards</p>','Linda and Geoff,<br />England.','linda.jpg','Linda on the Floating Islands of the Uros, Lake Ti','',493,0,0,NULL,NULL,NULL),(95,1,'Dear Bernard,','<p>Our trip to Peru was fascinating. The detailed program that you so \r\nefficiently customized for us worked out beautifully. All your representatives \r\nwere right on time to pick us up at airports and trainstations providing all \r\nkinds of information for the following day. This made us feel very confortable \r\nat all times. Rene in Miami was most helpful.&nbsp;The hotels were very \r\ngood. Bernard , you were wonderful. You customized the itinerary to \r\nourliking, responded to all our e-mails promptly and worked with us in aone to \r\none personal way in spite of being very busy as owner and chief leader of the \r\nCompany.</p>\r\n<p>All in all it was a great experience. Thank you very much.</p>\r\n<p>Sincerely, </p>','Mario and Pat,<br />USA.','mariomesa.jpg','Mario in Cusco','',495,0,0,NULL,NULL,NULL),(96,1,'Dear Peru For Less','<p>The trip was FANTASTIC!&nbsp; We thank you and your local colleagues very \r\nmuch for being so coordinated and punctual.</p>\r\n<p>Christian had left the travel documents for us by the time we landed in Lima \r\nand called us twice to make sure we understood what the documents meant, if we \r\nhad any questions, etc. Carlos met us at the airport in Cusco with signs \r\nand all, and Rosie briefed us afterwards at the hotel. Our tours were \r\nsplendid -- both Janet and Darwin were very well-informed, energetic, and \r\npatient with our groups;we couldn\'t have asked for better guides. And the \r\nbus pick-ups and deliveries were always punctual (I am a great fan of \r\npunctuality). Both Carlos and Maria were at the train station as promised \r\nwhen we returned tired and weary from Machu Picchu.</p>\r\n<p>Thank you again very much for a terrific trip -- you even arranged for the \r\nweather to be perfect! We are recommending you to all our friends and will \r\ndefinitely keep you in mind if we have plans to travel elsewhere in South \r\nAmerica.</p>\r\n<p>Kind Regards and much continued success to your group!</p>','Andrea and George,<br />Scotch Plains, New Jersey.','Merenyi.jpg','Andrea in Cuzco','',497,0,0,NULL,NULL,NULL),(98,1,'Dear Peru For Less','<p>We had a great time, overall. The guides and transfers were great... \r\nChristian in Lima, Maria and Rossie in Cusco, Vilma at Macchu Picchu, and \r\nWilliam and Jorge at Posada Amazonas. I missed the Sacred Valley Tour (I got \r\nsick one night in Cuzco) but Matt and the kids really enjoyed it. \r\nWe&nbsp;especially enjoyed the private tours, Machu Picchu, and the jungle. I \r\nthink for the kids the only tour they did not really enjoy was the day trip \r\nwithin the city of Cuzco. </p>\r\n<p>We enjoyed the people, the country, the scenery, and the culture. Peru for \r\nLess made a busy and fast paced trip possible with great people and timely \r\nservice. We could not have done as much as we did, nor, with such ease, on our \r\nown. We had been hesitant to use a tour company in the past, but we were very \r\nhappy with your company. </p>\r\n<p>Also, Lan airlines is awesome! Matt and I went to Costa Rica five years ago \r\nand we had to fly very small planes to get around the country. We were very \r\nimpressed with Lan and it made us feel secure when flying with our children \r\nwithin Peru. </p>\r\n<p>Overall, we felt very secure and safe in Peru, and having such nice people to \r\nwelcome us and guide us was a lot of fun! Our son says he is going back to Peru \r\nfor a month when he is older, and will stay in the jungle the whole time. Only \r\nin the jungle could we have gotten him up at 4:30 am to go on a hike to a clay \r\nlick! He was in heaven. The kids also caught Piranha fish in the oxbow lake, and \r\nafterwards the guides took them back to the kitchen and they cooked them for the \r\nkids for lunch. They loved them! </p>\r\n<p>Our last night, we took a taxi to Miraflores and had a great dinner at one of \r\nthe restaurants overlooking the ocean. We put our bags in storage at the \r\nairport. It was a nice way to end the trip. Overall, Peru was great and thanks \r\nfor all your time and coordination!</p>\r\n<p>We tell everyone if they ever go to Peru - you are definitely the people to \r\ncontact. </p>\r\n<p>Take care,<br />Beth.</p>\r\n<p><em>PS. We are thinking of another South American destination for next year. \r\nYou\'ll have to give me some of your destinations.</em></P>','Beth,<br />Glen Ellyn, Illinois USA. ','Beth.jpg','Beth and family in the Amazon, Peru','',500,0,0,NULL,NULL,NULL),(99,1,'Dear Bernard,','<p>I want to thank you wholeheartedly for arranging such a wonderful trip for \r\nour family. Your company has identified all the appropriate channels to ensure a \r\nsuccessful trip at every level. At all times we felt welcomed, safe and \r\ninformed. Your people came through in the most professional manner from the \r\nmoment we arrived in Lima. On the Incan trail itself, the care provided was at \r\nall times excellent. From porters, cooks and guide all we recieved were \r\nkindnesses and care. Quality of food was truly wonderful and unbelievable that \r\nit could be prepared so well and with such care, on the Incan Trail.</p>\r\n<p>Our family will never forget Peru, The Incan trail, nor you. Thank you again \r\nfor coming through on every detail promised and therefore providing us with a \r\nsafe and beautiful experience. We recommend you and if you have a client that \r\nwould care to contact us, we are available. </p>\r\n<p>It\'s heartwarming to meet a young man that is so committed and responsible. \r\nWe wish you much success on every future endeavor.</p>\r\n<p>Most sincerely, </p>\r\n<p>P.S. &#161 Viva los Ciencianos!</p>','The five Menkes from Maryland,<br />USA.','Menkes.jpg','The Menkes on the Inca Trail, Cuzco','',506,0,0,NULL,NULL,NULL),(100,1,'Hi Peru For Less,','<p>I can\'t thank you enough for all of your excellent recommendations, \r\nadvice and attention. You helped to ensure our trip to Peru was everything \r\nand more than we imagined and hoped it would be. From our arrival \r\nin Lima, the 3 wonderful nights at the truly beautiful Miraflores \r\nHotel, followed by our Cusco stay at the incredible Monestario, we fell in \r\nlove with Peru. After we left you in Lima,&nbsp;everything continued to go \r\nsmoothly. <br />We will never forget Peru. The stunning beauty of Macchu \r\nPicchu, the Sacred Valley, and the&nbsp;beautiful and kind people all made the \r\ntrip extraordinary. Thank you for organizing this wonderful experience for us. \r\nWe look forward to booking a trip with you when your company launches the \r\nArgentina trips.</p>\r\n<p>Wishing you all the very best,</p>','Sharon and Terry,<br />British Columbia, Canada.','McKenzie.jpg','Sharon and Terry at Machu Picchu, Cusco','',507,0,0,NULL,NULL,NULL),(101,1,'Dear Peru For Less','<p>We had a really fantastic time in Peru. We couldn\'t have asked for a more \r\norganised holiday and even when plans got changed at the last minute there was \r\nalways someone there to meet us and it took all the hassle out of it. The tours \r\nwere excellent and the hotels were clean, comfortable with friendly, helpful \r\nstaff and in great locations. Duncan needed to see a dentist whilst we were \r\nthere so we asked our guide (Adriel) to recommend a good one and not only did he \r\ndo this but he took us there and translated for us so that the holiday wasn\'t \r\nruined by tooth ache! We have wonderful memories and are telling all our friends \r\nabout you, so thank-you again, we really hope to visit again in the future.</p>','Kelly and Duncan,<br />United Kingdom. ','jones.jpg','Kelly and Duncan at Machu Picchu, Cuzco','',508,0,0,NULL,NULL,NULL),(102,1,'Dear Ale and all the other fantastic people at PFL,','<p>We want to thank you for making our trip to Peru unforgettable. We had \r\nzero problems the whole trip. Starting with Ale who helped us to book the \r\ntrip, to the people who met us at the airports, train stations and \r\nhotels to the tour guides, everybody was perfect. PFL is incredibly \r\nwell organized and bent over backwards to make sure we had everything we \r\nneeded. Rosey, for example, in Cuzco, gave us her cell phone # and \r\ninsisted we call day or night if we had any questions or problems.</p>\r\n<p>We hope to get back to Peru in the not too distant future and will definitely \r\nuse PFL again. </p>','Marc and Laura,<br />Charlotte, North Carolina, USA.','marc-lewin.jpg','Marc and Laura at Machu Picchu, Cusco','',510,0,0,NULL,NULL,NULL),(103,1,'Hi Bernard,','<p>I had fun after you left me at the Gold Museum. Thanks again for the \r\nfantastic lunch! What a great restaurant. I\'ve never had an variety of quality \r\nfood, unique menu, and beautiful presentation like it. You were so right. And \r\nthe drinks were good too! And of course, I loved riding in your Audi. I sure \r\nhope I get to buy it later this year or early next year.</p>\r\n<p>Peru for Less really exceeded my expectations for my Peru vacation. My \r\ncustomized itinerary was followed beautifully, and the tour descriptions given \r\nto me by Bernard matched exactly what I experienced on every level. The \r\nwonderful people who greeted me for all of my transfers throughout Lima, Cusco, \r\nand Machu Picchu were on-time, friendly, and accommodating, especially Laura \r\nRodriguez. The tour guide services were excellent for every tour on my \r\nitinerary, since they were relaxed, friendly and knowledgable. This was easily \r\nthe best vacation I had ever experienced, and I can\'t imagine it being done any \r\nbetter than the good people at Peru for Less.</p>\r\n<p>Thanks for everything. I\'ll have wonderful memories forever! </p>','Kim,<br />USA.','Kim-McClure.jpg','Kim in Cuzco','',511,0,0,NULL,NULL,NULL),(104,1,'Dear Peru For Less','<p>Our trip was incredible. For one, we love Mesoamerican culture and history, so staying in Cusco, and being able to see the Spanish architecture built upon the ancient Inca foundations was absolutely amazing. Every moment in Peru was simply one gasping moment after another, and it really seemed like every place we went, from the Sacred Valley to Machu Picchu, was more amazing than the last!</p>\n<p><strong>Your company did a fantastic job, from helping us to plan our trip, to saving our lives at the airport in Juliaca.</strong> We don\'t even want to imagine the hell we would have gone through had we not been able to get on that plane. Anytime you need help in a tight spot, you know who to call. <strong>What we think makes your company stand out however is your customer service and dedication.</strong> At each one of our hotels, there was a message waiting for us in the evening, with the time of when we would be picked up the next day. The people in Peru were very considerate, and took to great lengths to guarantee that we were comfortable and knew what was going on in every situation.</p>\n<p>There wasn\'t a single point during the entire trip that we felt lost or abandoned; on the contrary, you showed more concern for our well-being than even some of our own family would show, and we want to tell you, it was greatly appreciated.</p>\n<p>Anyways, <strong>in a nutshell, you rock, Peru for Less is awesome, and the second we have enough money to visit Argentina for a month, we\'ll be in touch.</strong> Thanks again, and we\'ll hopefully see you in the future!</p>\n','Nick and Kit (Atlanta, Georgia)<br/>\r\nTraveled to: Cusco, Sacred Valley, Machu Picchu, Puno\r\n','nick.jpg','Nick and Kit in Cuzco','\"What we think makes your company stand out is your customer service and dedication.\"',100059,0,0,NULL,'2014-09-10 23:13:26',NULL),(105,1,'Dear Ale,','<p>We want to thank you for making our trip to Peru unforgettable. Peru For Less \r\nreally exceeded our expectations for our Peruvian vacation. The wonderful people \r\nwho greeted us during all of our transfers throughout Lima, Cusco, and Machu \r\nPicchu were on time, friendly, and accommodating. We were amazed by the variety \r\nof climate, topography, landscapes, archeology, and culture in your country. \r\nWe\'ll be happy to recommend Peru For Less to anyone that is planning a trip to \r\nPeru. We felt that Peru For Less did a really fabulous job for what we feel is a \r\nvery fair price. We loved our trip to Lake Titicaca, and of course Machu Picchu \r\nwas incredible! We had a wonderful flight over the Nazca lines. Thank you so \r\nmuch for arranging the tour for us in Peru. We really enjoyed the adventure!</p>','Barbara &amp; Jim,<br />Topeka, Kansas.','Barbara.jpg','Barbara and Jim at Machu Picchu, Cusco','',518,0,0,NULL,NULL,NULL),(106,1,'Dear Peru For Less','<p>While I realize that we had the opportunity to thank you in person, I wanted to \r\nthank you one more time, for your great assistance in planning our trip. Your \r\naccessibility and attention to detail are wonderful attributes and richly \r\nappreciated by those making their first trip to Peru . As importantly, we were \r\nvery pleased with you efforts to individualize our trip to our more specific \r\nneeds and interests. We had a fabulous week that appealed to each and every \r\nmember of our 3 generation family (ages 10 to 70). The highlights would be many, \r\nbut at a minimum would certainly include: the kindness of the Peruvian people, \r\nthe Pisac market, a great rafting adventure, the Machu Picchu Pueblo Hotel and \r\nits surrounding wildlife, and of course Machu Picchu itself. Thanks for \r\neverything, I hope to stay in touch for our next South of the Border adventure!</p>','Debbie, Blake, Bryce, Brooke, and Mary,<br />Tampa Bay, \r\nFlorida.','Bonsack.jpg','Debbie, Blake, Bryce, Brooke, and Mary in the Sacr','',524,0,0,NULL,NULL,NULL),(107,1,'Dear Peru For Less','<p><strong>The best part of our journey in Peru was . . . Rossie, Lourdes , Elfer, Juan, Maria, Simon . . . in short-the Peruvian people we met. But, wait, it was Peru for Less that picked those great tour guides, drivers, and friends for us!</strong> It was Peru for Less that chose those charming and accommodating hotels for us. It was Peru For Less that recommended the itinerary and chose the transportation that moved us along from one beautiful place to the next.<strong> It was Peru For Less that took all the work and worry out of our first visit to South America.</strong> We\'ve been to Asia and Africa and Europe and always arranged everything ourselves to ensure we got precisely what we wanted when we wanted it. With Peru For Less we got it all and didn\'t have to do any of the work. They sold us a package, but they delivered a personalized experience.</p>','Debra and Ramesh (Washington, D.C)<br/>\r\nTraveled to: Lima, Cusco, Machu Picchu\r\n','Lewin.jpg','Debra and Ramesh at Machu Picchu, Cuzco','\"With Peru For Less we got it all and didn\'t have to do any of the work. They sold us a package, but they delivered a personalized experience.\"',100032,0,0,NULL,'2014-09-10 22:55:10',NULL),(108,1,'Dear Peru For Less','<p>Dear PFL - just wanted to thank you for creating the perfect trip for my buddy \r\nand I. Peru for Less (PfL) made this once in a lifetime trip a truly \r\nunforgettable experience. In addition to being the most cost effective of all \r\nthe sources we researched, PfL\'s level of service was a big surprise. You really \r\nwent above and beyond what we could have expected and created a tailored and \r\nunique trip based on our personal preferences and time available for our trip. \r\nEverywhere we went, a PfL representative was waiting to bring us to our next \r\ndestination or just to make sure we were doing OK. We were able to experience \r\nPeru in an \"off-the-beaten-path\" kind of way while feeling secure that we were \r\nlooked after. Given we only had 2 weeks for our trip, PfL did an exceptional job \r\nof bringing the local culture and scenic beauty of Peru to us. The fact that PfL \r\ncaters solely to Peru really shows in the attention to detail and the intimate \r\nknowledge of every aspect of the our trip, from the mere logistics of getting \r\naround the country to being able to explain the different areas of the country \r\neven in the planning stages of the trip. PfL really took the time and had the \r\npatience to help us plan the perfect trip. Maybe you will expand your services \r\nto other parts of the world! What a pleasant surprise to find a discount travel \r\nprovider with no discount to the service it provides.</p>','Lars,<br />Charlotte, North Carolina.','Gedenbord.jpg','Lars at Machu Picchu, Cuzco','',526,0,0,NULL,NULL,NULL),(109,1,'To the whole team at Peru For Less,','<p>THANKS for an Amazing Vacation. Everything in every city was fantastic. The \r\nGuides were on time, friendly, and courteous.&nbsp; We had the most amazing \r\nvacation of our lives. It was due 100% to the expert planning and resources \r\nthrough Peru for Less. Everyone was on time and in the designated \r\nlocation. The tours were perfect, the hotels as pictured. The staff gave \r\nit\'s time fully to answer all questions.&nbsp;Even prior to the trip every \r\nquestion was answered with expertise and focus on our needs. Thanks again \r\nto everyone at PFL.</p>','Ron and Glenn,<br />Pompano Beach, Florida.','Ron.jpg','Ron and Glenn in the Andes, Peru','',528,0,0,NULL,NULL,NULL),(110,1,'Dear Ale,','<p>Perhaps the true test of a great travel agent is when things go \r\nwrong. Many thanks for all you and your associates did to minimize the \r\ndamage to our trip due to&nbsp;our traveling companion\'s&nbsp;lost passport. We \r\nfeel you all definitely went above and beyond the call of duty in this case, and \r\nwe are most appreciative of that. In spite of that problem, the itinerary that \r\nyou worked out for us gave us many very memorable moments. Our tour guides \r\nwere excellent, knowledgeable, and enthusiastic; and their love of their country \r\nwas contagious. Though Machu Picchu was magnificent, the \r\nhydrofoil&nbsp;tour of Lake Titicaca was definitely a surprise highlight of the \r\ntrip. The floating islands and the peoples who inhabit them were amazing to \r\nlearn about. The restaurant you recommended in Cusco was excellent, and the tour \r\nof the Sacred Valley with Pachamama as our tour guide was delightful. Thanks \r\nfor a well-planned trip and all your extra help along the way?</p>\r\n<p>We tell everyone if they ever go to Peru - you are definitely the people to \r\ncontact. </p>','Judy and Dave,<br />Phoenix, AZ, USA.','Davis.jpg','Judy and Dave at Lake Titicaca, Puno','',529,0,0,NULL,NULL,NULL),(111,1,'Dear Ximena and Peru For Less,','<p>I\'m a pretty picky guy and the situation was one where I got uncomfortable \r\nreally easy, and Ximena held our hands real tight on the phone with emails and \r\nreally took care of us. I can\'t say enough about the tour guides we had. They \r\nall gave 100 percent and more. We really got a lot of information about where we \r\nwereÃ¢â?¬â?more than we ever would have expected. Peru For Less did a really fabulous \r\njob for what we feel is a very fair price. I\'d use them again in a minute, and \r\nwish them the best of success!</p>\r\n<p>Happy holidays and deepest thanks for taking care of things! </p>','Bruce &amp; Louise,<br />California, USA.','Bow.jpg','Bruce and Louise at Machu Picchu, Cuzco','',531,0,0,NULL,NULL,NULL),(112,1,'Hello Bernard,','<p>As promised, I am finally getting back in touch with you, in regards to our travel experience in Peru as well as in working with you.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>As for working with you, I can\'t say enough positive things Bernard. What a wonderful experience it was. This was our first time planning a trip on-line. At first, we were somewhat nervous, since we didn\'t know if your firm was legitimate, or anything like that. But you were always responsive, caring, and warm, answered our many many questions patiently and thoroughly, provided us with good guidance and helped us plan our trip. Everything you promised, you delivered. The guides were knowledgeable and with good communication skills. And the places you selected for us were comfortable and nice to stay at. <strong>The trip was totally hassle free, safe, enjoyable, and a memorable experience, one that we will cherish and remember fondly for many years to come.</strong></p>\r\n\r\n\r\n<p>As for Peru, what a beautiful country it is. It\'s clean. The people are so very warm and friendly. And we found it to be totally safe, something we were concerned about prior to leaving for Peru. To me, Peru felt so much like home. In fact so much so that we are now missing it very much and one day, we would love to come there again. And when we do, we\'ll definitely be contacting you.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Needless to say, we are 100+% satisfied with the trip to Peru and in working with you.</strong> Bernard, anytime any one asks for a reference on you and your firm, you can feel free to give them our name and contact information and we will be glad to speak with them. Also, feel free to use this letter in any way that you wish. And next time you are in DC area, please do stay with me and my family. We would love to have you stay with you. It\'ll be our pleasure.</p>\r\n<p>Well, that\'s all for now. Please do stay in touch. And similar to your kind and generous offer to us, I like to extend the same to you. If you ever need anything from here, please do not hesitate to let me know. It\'ll be my pleasure in sending it to you.</p>\r\n<p>Warm Regards!</p>\r\n','Vinay and Sudha (Virginia, USA)<br/>\r\nTraveled to: Lima, Cusco, Machu Picchu\r\n','Kumar2.jpg','Vinay and Sudha in the Andes, Peru','\"This was our first time planning a trip on- line. At first, we were somewhat nervous. But you were always responsive, caring, and warm.. Everything you promised, you delivered.2',100038,0,0,NULL,'2014-09-10 23:08:30',NULL),(113,1,'Dear Rory,','<p>The trip including the hike to Machhu Picchu was enchanting! Peru for Less \r\nprovided me with personal attention and exceptional service from customized \r\nitinerary, booking the tickets to help in figuring out the contents of the back \r\npack, visa information and many small details that made the trip a lifetime \r\nmemory. No request was too big for the energetic staff to accommodate. This \r\ntruly is a gem in the otherwise cluttered Peru tourism. As far as the hike is \r\nconcerned, just go already!</p>\r\n<p>Say Rory, do you know anything about the Mt</p>\r\n<p>Kilimanjaro hike?</p>\r\n<p>Happy holidays and deepest thanks for taking care of things! </p>','Sumeet,<br />USA.','sumeet.jpg','Sumeet in the Andes, Peru','',533,0,0,NULL,NULL,NULL),(114,1,'Dear Peru For Less','<p>Peru is a wonderful place to visit with some fantastic scenery, culture, cuisine and friendly, honest people. As a country relying on tourism, everyone seems to be helpful to make you enjoy everything they have to offer. Peru is a paradise to buy locally made clothing and gifts at inexpensive prices. The itinerary developed with Peru For Less via the internet ensured that we made it to all the relevant sites with our time schedule.</p>\r\n<p>Many thanks,</p>','Dave and Pauline, <br />Derby, UK.','Cartwright.jpg','Dave and Pauline at Machu Picchu','',414,0,0,NULL,NULL,NULL),(115,1,'Dear Peru For Less','<p>We were delighted with all your companyâ??s performance. Once again thanks to all guides and staff at Peru For Less.</p>\r\n<p>Kindest Regards,</p>','Max and Helen,<br />NSW, Australia. ','Brundson.jpg','Max and Helen at Machu Picchu','',418,0,0,NULL,NULL,NULL),(116,1,'Dear Peru For Less','<p>First of all I want to thank you and everybody on the Peru For Less staff, and Wilda and Janette for making my trip to Peru a very memorable \r\nexperience. Me and my friend were so amazed by the breathtaking beauty of \r\nPeru, its history, and its people. We also enjoyed shopping for handicrafts \r\nand we like the Peruvian cuisine so much. We surely miss Peru and we hope we \r\ncan come back next year to explore the rest of the country since we spent \r\nonly 5 days, but I have tons of  pictures and memories that I share here with \r\nmy friends. We highly recommend Peru for Less! </p>','Joan and Judy,<br />San Francisco, CA. ','Uy.jpg','Joan and Judy at Machu Picchu','',419,0,0,NULL,NULL,NULL),(117,1,'Dear Peru For Less','<p>The trip was excellent, the two day trail was just enough for the limited \r\ntime we had in Peru. Having the guide just to ourselves and without other people \r\nwas excellent and Silvia mentioned you guys keep the group numbers low. \r\n<br />Thanks,</p>','Zara and Oliver,<br />Sao Paulo, Brazil. ','Potts.jpg','Zara and Oliver in the Sacred Valley','',420,0,0,NULL,NULL,NULL),(118,1,'Dear Peru For Less','<p>Thanks for the e-mail. We had an amazing trip. Peru is trully \r\nbeautiful. We were very happy we did the 4 day trek. Our guide Sylvia was \r\namazing. The porters were so helpful and the food was very good. I would \r\ndefinitely reccomend this trip for anyone who is ready for an adventure. Lynn \r\nand I also really enjoyed the two day tours that we took in Cusco and felt that \r\nthey were very well organized.</p>\r\n<p>Thanks again!</p>','Annie,<br />Los Angeles, CA.','Goshert.jpg','Annie and Lynn at Macchu Piccchu','',421,0,0,NULL,NULL,NULL),(119,1,'Dear Peru For Less','<p>I just want to let you know that my husband and I enjoyed our trip to Peru very \r\nmuch. We have been telling our friends about Peru and your excellent service. \r\nSome of my friends are planning to go Peru this year, and we are hoping to go \r\nback to Peru and other countries of South America in the future. We really \r\nappreciate what you have done for us. We want to thank Fabricio, our excellent \r\nguide at Machu Picchu. We will keep telling our friends about our tip to Peru, \r\nwe and are hoping to visit Peru and other countries like Brazil, Argentina and \r\nChile.</p>\r\n<p>Thank you so much!!</p>','Noriko and Matt, <br />Huntington Beach, CA.','Matsumoto.jpg','Noriko and Matt at Machu Picchu','',422,0,0,NULL,NULL,NULL),(120,1,'Hi Richard,','<p>We had a very nice holiday and thank you for all the arrangements. Your \r\ncontacts and services were great. Our favorites were Cuzco, Machu Picchu, and \r\nthe Iguazu Falls.&nbsp; We also really enjoyed Lima- wish we would have spent an \r\nextra day there, especially at the Second Home boutique hotel. Should we visit \r\nyour Country again we will certainly contact you for further arrangements.</p>\r\n<p>All the best, </p>','Jane &amp; Bob,<br />Wymbolwood Beach, Ontario.','Lippert.jpg','Jane and Bob at the Iguazu Falls','',423,0,0,NULL,NULL,NULL),(121,1,'Dear Peru For Less','<p>Our trip to Peru was excellent! Everything was so well organizedâ?? we didnâ??t \r\nhave to worry about a thingâ?? and the hotels and guides were excellent. Machu \r\nPicchu was of course the highlight and the Inkaterra Pueblo Hotel in Aguas \r\nCalientes was one of our favorites (their food was fabulous too!). My favorite \r\nguide was on the trip to the Colca Canyon.&nbsp; Not only was he a very \r\nknowledgeable guide; he took great care of us all. We had a wonderful time, and \r\nare already thinking about going back. For the next visit, we would plan to \r\nspend more time in Lima, in Cusco and in Aguas Calientes, then add a few days in \r\nthe Amazon or something similar. Thanks again for all of your help with this \r\ntrip. We loved it!</p>','Allyson,<br />Toronto, Canada. ','Newburg.jpg','Allyson and her Husband in the Mountains','',446,0,0,NULL,NULL,NULL),(122,1,'Dear Peru For Less','<p>We thoroughly enjoyed our trip to Peru, but are totally exhausted from all \r\nthe walking and climbing. It was worth every step!! Our stay at El Pueblo was \r\nfantastic. We went on the early morning bird-watching walk, and the nature and \r\norchid walk. Both were amazing. I\'m so thankful that we were able to stay there. \r\nAll of your agents and guides were pleasant, helpful, and informative. Thank you \r\nfor your help in planning and completing our trip!</p>','Barbara,<br />New Jersey, USA. ','Engler.jpg','Barbara and company at Machu Picchu','',447,0,0,NULL,NULL,NULL),(123,1,'Dear Peru For Less','<p>We had an absolutely amazing trip! Your country is beautiful and everyone we met \r\nwas friendly and welcoming. We hope to be able to return another time and visit \r\ndifferent areas. We were always met on schedule and our transfers went smoothly. \r\nWe really enjoyed our Colca Valley tour- luckily the group that we were with was \r\nvery congenial and a lot of fun. Our guide was super. Watching the condors glide \r\nand soar was such a treat! Visiting Machu Picchu was the highlight of our trip. \r\nAfter seeing pictures of it for years, actually being there was truly a thrill. \r\nOn our second day, we took the first bus up to the site at 5:30 AM. It was \r\ncloudy that day, so we didn\'t get to see the sun rise, but it was so peaceful \r\nand quiet that we just sat and appreciated the beauty all around us. We ate at \r\nseveral restaurants recommended by various Peru for Less staffers, and one in \r\nparticular really stood out--Granja Heidi. We had the best meal of the trip \r\nthere- in fact, one of the best meals we\'ve ever had anywhere. The Nelson \r\nMandela Cake is totally unlike anything we\'ve ever had before, and absolutely \r\ndelicious! Service was excellent, and the price was unbelievably reasonable. I \r\nfound your website to be very comprehensive, and you were very quick to respond \r\nto all of my questions and requests. Thank you for helping us to have a very \r\nmemorable vacation.</p>','Paula,<br />Yarmouth, ME.','Richardson.jpg','Skip and Paula at Machu Picchu','',454,0,0,NULL,NULL,NULL),(124,1,'Dear Peru For Less','<p>We had a wonderful time and, on the whole, everything went very smoothly. All \r\nof the Peru for Less and affiliated representatives and guides were fantastic. \r\nRosie in Cuzco was one of the best - she was so informative and we felt like we \r\nlearned so much from her during the day and a half we were with her. We also had \r\na great time on the Colca Canyon tour. Everything was fantastic! We also had a \r\ngreat time at Machu Picchu.<br />So thank you very much to you and all your team \r\nfor all your wonderful work. All of our family and friends have been interested \r\nto hear about how we planned our trip so we have spread the word about your \r\ncompany and in the future if we hear of anyone going to Peru, we will most \r\ndefinitely send them your link.</p>\r\n<p>Thank you again!</p>','Rachel and Nick,<br />New York City, NY. ','Sinden.jpg','Rachel and Nick feeding the Alpacas','',460,0,0,NULL,NULL,NULL),(125,1,'Dear Peru For Less','<p>As promised, here are some comments about our recent trip to Peru.<br />\r\nWe were met at each point of transfer without any problems and this made the travel end of the trip very care free. Our first hotel, Melia, near the Lima airport was convenient, the buffet breakfast excellent. The hotel in Cuzco, the Arqueologo, was a real treat.  We felt right at home there and everyone on the staff was friendly and helpful. They had drinkable water available to fill our water bottles. The had light meals in the evening at the bar of which we took advantage of the first and last nights we were there. The Sacred Valley tour was very interesting. The Inka Trail was extrodinairy. Our guide met every need and was a delight to spend time with. We had a small group, a total of 7 people, and three different languages spoken, English, Spainish and German. Our porters worked endlessly and deserve much more credit than anyone. The train ride from Aguas Calientes was very entertaining. They had a fashion show and dancer on board. Actually, the nicest Alpacca we saw was featured on the train. Our day spent in Lima was also very nice. We had a wonderful meal at Punta Sol that was reccommended by our driver. The location of the Marriot in Miraflores was perfect for us to walk along the water front, do last minute shopping and have a lite meal before heading to the airport. Hope this information is helpful. We would reccomend Peru For Less to everyone.</p>\r\n','Cheryl and Elise,<br />San Francisco, CA.','Minivielle.jpg','Cheryl and Elise on the Inca Trail','',486,0,0,NULL,NULL,NULL),(126,1,'Dear Peru For Less','<p>Thank you for following up on our trip!&nbsp; We had an absolutely marvelous \r\ntime!! All the arrangements you made for us turned out just perfectly. Our hotel \r\nin Santiago was a lot nicer than we expected- we had a beautiful suite (even if \r\njust for one night)! Our time in Cusco was quite memorable. We had a nice hotel, \r\nnot far from the Plaza de Armas, and within walking distance of all the good \r\nrestaurants and shopping. The day we spent in Sacred Valley was awesome, and \r\nJose, our guide, did a nice job of leading us through that adventure. However, \r\nwe cannot begin to tell you about the Awesomeness of GOD that we witnessed as we \r\ndrove through the Andes- especially on our way up to Machu Picchu! To top it \r\noff, our wonderful guide, Fabricio, made Machu Picchu remarkable!! He guided us \r\nto the edge of the cliff; when we got there (with our eyes closed) and we opened \r\nthem to see for the first time a view that we had only vaguely imagined it was a \r\nvery emotional moment. We are most appreciative of you and your staff that made \r\nthese experiences a memorable one for us. We hope, one day, to be able to return \r\nto Cusco, as it was truly the highlight of our 23 day adventure.</p>\r\n<p>Thank you, and may our Lord and Savior, Christ Jesus, bless you richly!!</p>','Mel and Mary, <br />USA.','Sutton.jpg','Mel and Mary at Machu Picchu','',487,0,0,NULL,NULL,NULL),(127,1,'Dear Peru For Less','<p>I just wanted to take a moment and share with you my experience in Mendoza, \r\nArgentina. I had a wonderful time. Although my trip was short it was filled with \r\nsome great experiences and wonderful memories. I want to thank you for all the \r\ncare you put into my trip and the quick turn around in the short time I gave you \r\nto prepare everything. The vineyards we visited were very nice and all of the \r\npeople involved in all of our tours were very well informed and very pleasant to \r\nbe around. My trip to the mountains of Mendoza was amazing. Although the weather \r\nwas not to our favor, this will always be a trip that I will hold close to my \r\nheart. On our last night in Mendoza my boyfriend of 3 yrs asked me to marry him. \r\nSo you see Mendoza brought me: great wine, wonderful memories, and a lot of \r\nlove. The extra attention of an interpreter for my boyfriend was a great \r\nsurprise. Ivana was her name, and she was a great addition to all of this \r\npleasure. Thank you once again. I wish you and your team great success in all of \r\nyour future endeavors.</p>\r\n<p>Sincerely,</p>','Katherine,<br />New Jersey, USA.','Lima.jpg','Katherine in Argentina','',494,0,0,NULL,NULL,NULL),(128,1,'Dear Peru For Less','<p>Many thanks to you and your team for your help in our trip to Peru! You have \r\nprovided us with lots of flexibility in the travel organisation as well as all \r\nthe information needed! Once arrived and despite our chaotic schedule with \r\npeople arriving the day before and a lot of customization, everything went \r\nreally well! The representative in Arequipa was extremely friendly and helpful, \r\nas well as the guide we had for the tour of the city! His English was perfect \r\nand he was really knowledgeable, customizing the tour for us, providing us an \r\nexcellent service. We then headed towards the Colca Canyon and Chivay for a few \r\ndays. Our guide Milagros was fantastic as well as the whole landscape and the \r\nmountain experience. We really enjoyed our stay and the people from Peru for \r\nLess made it happen! You definitely WOW your customers!</p>\r\n<p>A thousand thanks,</p>','Alicia, Romain and Leo,<br />UK and Switzerland. ','Perego.jpg','Alicia Romain and Leo at Machu Picchu','',498,0,0,NULL,NULL,NULL),(129,1,'Dear Peru For Less','<p>Jeff and I very much enjoyed our trip to Peru and have recommended you and Peru \r\nFor Less to my friend who will be travelling with you. We were very happy with \r\nour arrangements. People were invariably warm and friendly. As we walked through \r\nvillages every single person we passed greeted us with a \"Buenos dias\" or \r\n\"Buenas tardes.\" We don\'t get that here in the US very often. It goes without \r\nsaying that the ruins were breathtaking and didn\'t disappoint, either. Our \r\nthanks again to our guides: Sylvia in Cuzco, Mary in the Sacred Valley, and \r\nFabricio at Machu Picchu. Also to Jenny, who helped with arrangements, Wilda \r\nin Cuzco, and Carlos, our driver. The whole staff was very friendly and \r\nhelpful and we were pleasantly surprised to have private tours in the Sacred \r\nValley and Machu Picchu. All the tranfers and pick-ups were on time and every \r\nhotel was comfortable, clean and charming. Thanks again to everyone at Peru For \r\nLess! We were very happy with the service and had a wonderful \r\nvacation!</p>\r\n<p>Sincerely,</p>','Debbie and Jeff,<br />Aldie, VA.','Moore.jpg','Debbie and Jeff at Machu Picchu','',499,0,0,NULL,NULL,NULL),(130,1,'Dear Peru For Less','<p>The trip was absolutely great. Your service was excellent. As a traveler who \r\noften makes his own arrangements, it was a great relief to have all this taken \r\ncare of for me. The itinerary was excellent. I would highly recommend your \r\nservices to any potential clients. I certainly would like to return for a more \r\nextensive tour of your country.</p>','Paul,<br />California, USA. ','Nigro.jpg','Paul at Machu Picchu','',501,0,0,NULL,NULL,NULL),(131,1,'Hello Diego,','<p>We had a great trip to Peru and would like to thank you and Peru for \r\nLess for putting together a great package. We spent 3 months traveling around \r\nSouth America and did a lot of it on our own. With not being able to speak much \r\nSpanish it made our trip so much easier and enjoyable to travel with Peru For \r\nLess and know that someone would be waiting for us at the airport and train \r\nstation to take us to our hotel and then pick us up and take us to our next \r\ndestination. It was like traveling on our own but someone else had done all the \r\norganization for us. The standard of the hotels were great. We had a rough idea \r\nof where we wanted to go but you bought it all together and offered great advice \r\nin terms of transport options and other tours. Machu Picchu is what everyone \r\ngoes to Peru to see, and we were not disappointed. We enjoyed it so much that we \r\nreturned there the second day and did the walk to the top of Huayna Picchu. It \r\nwas the scariest thing I have ever done, but I am so glad that I made it to the \r\ntop. It was worth the early start. The other highlights of the trip were the \r\nisland stay with a local family on Lake Titicaca and the Maras Moray Salt Mine \r\ntour. We did the tour with just a guide and driver but Maras is amazing to see. \r\nThere are lots of ruins in Peru but Maras is something different. It is amazing \r\nwhat the Inca people achieved. We would also recommend doing the train trip from \r\nPuno to Cuzco (first class). It was very enjoyable and well worth the money.<br />\r\nThank you very much for all you help and advice. </p>','Sharlene and Mark, <br />Newcastle, Australia.','Sharlene.jpg','Sharlene at Lake Titicaca','',502,0,0,NULL,NULL,NULL),(132,1,'Dear Peru For Less','<p>We have great memories of our trip, thank you! We wish we were still in Peru! \r\nThank you to you and everyone at Peru for Less. We were looked after \r\nbrilliantly, and due to your perfect organisation we were able to see so much of \r\nPeru within our two weeks. We loved seeing the condors at Colca Canyon and the \r\nanimals on the jungle treks, but really, everything we saw was breathtaking and \r\neveryone we met so friendly. Definately thinking of visiting again next year! \r\nThanks again.</p>\r\n<p>Warm Regards,</p>','Fran &amp; James,<br />London, UK.','Brown.jpg','Frances and James at Machu Picchu','',503,0,0,NULL,NULL,NULL),(133,1,'Dear Peru For Less','<p>We spent 12 wonderful days in Peru. The entire trip was perfectly planned, down \r\nto the last detail, by Peru For Less. The hotels were all very conveniently \r\nlocated and comfortable. We were especially impressed by all the local guides \r\nwho were always on time and courteous. They were all very well informed and \r\nenthusiastic to talk about their country. The beauty of Machu Picchu cannot be \r\ndescribed and a visit is a life time experience! Thank you very much for the \r\nsuperb organization of a truly unforgettable trip!</p>','Sylvia and Karl,<br />San Diego, CA.','Sun.jpg','Sylvia and Karl at Machu Picchu','',504,0,0,NULL,NULL,NULL),(134,1,'Dear Peru For Less','<p>We had a fantastic time! Peru is such a wonderful place and our experience was \r\nvery good. Peru for Less was a great pick for us to use. We had no problems with \r\nany of our connections, hotels, tours, it all worked out wonderfully. Our \r\nexperience on the Inca Trail was great, what a beautiful place. Thanks again for \r\nall the effort to make our visit an enjoyable one; it was the trip of a life \r\ntime. You guys did a great job.</p>\r\n<p>Thanks again JP,</p> ','Keith,<br />Stanton, CA.','Brush.jpg','Keith and the Gang in the Sacred Valley','',505,0,0,NULL,NULL,NULL),(135,1,'Ms. Alegre,','<p>My trip to Peru was WONDERFUL. Thanks to you and your associates for doing \r\nsuch a great job planning the trip. Besides the spectacular scenery and \r\narcheological sites, I must say the most memorable part of my trip was visiting \r\nwith the people of Peru. Quite seriously, having traveled around the world (over \r\n30 countries), I found the Peruvians to be the most polite, warm, and friendly \r\npeople I have ever visited with. After discussing my trip with friends and \r\nfamily, you may have some additional business in the future.&nbsp; Everybody \r\nwants to visit Peru. Again, thank you and your associates (including Mr. Jan) \r\nfor your assistance.</p>\r\n<p>Regards,</p>','Carlton,<br />Georgia, USA. ','Fitzpatrick.jpg','Carlton and Rachel at Machu Picchu','',509,0,0,NULL,NULL,NULL),(136,1,'Dear Diego,','<p>Just a note to tell you how much we enjoyed our trip to Peru - and how \r\nimpressed we were with Peru for Less. Everything was just perfect! Machu Picchu \r\nwas spectacular and every step of the hike was breathtaking. Peru for Less (and \r\nespecially Diego) handled absolutely everything, allowing us to enjoy our trip. \r\nEverything was personalized. We were greeted promptly at every step of the way \r\nby our transports, even when our flights were delayed! Our tents were clean and \r\nthe food on the hike was some of the best we enjoyed in Peru. As for Cuzco, the \r\ntown was adorable and our hotel was gorgeous (the Hotel Libertador) - we \r\ncouldn\'t have picked a better one ourselves. We have done a lot of international \r\ntravel, but had never been to South America - we will definitely be back in the \r\nnear future, and we will definitely be using Peru for Less! Thanks so much again \r\nfor all the help and for an unforgettable trip!</p>','Alexis and Jake,<br />Philadelphia, PA. ','Straus.jpg','Alexis and Jake in Cuzco','',512,0,0,NULL,NULL,NULL),(137,1,'Dear Peru For Less','<p>Our trip to Peru truly exceeded all our expectations. I organized the trip on \r\nbehalf of the rest of my group and I was very happy with choosing your company. \r\nThe best part was being able to focus on the trip and the amazingly kind and \r\nwelcoming people of Peru. Our vacation ran smoothly from beginning to end. At \r\nevery destination, we immediately found a Peru For Less representative waiting \r\nfor us. You didn\'t let us down at any time. Since my first call to Peru For \r\nLess, and even until after the end of our trip, we received very specialized \r\nattention. I liaised mostly with JP, I am truly thankful to him and also to all \r\nhis colleagues who made it possible.</p>\r\n<p>Muchas Gracias!</p> ','Jimena, Renee, and Susan,<br />New York City, NY.','Teijeiro.jpg','Jimena Renee and Susan at Machu Picchu','',514,0,0,NULL,NULL,NULL),(138,1,'Dear Peru For Less','<p>The trip was WONDERFUL, and both Joanne and I are certain that Peru for Less was \r\na big part of the great time we had. We\'ll recommend you to anyone. You took all \r\nthe work out of it and left only the fun. There was someone to meet us right on \r\ntime every time - good people who were fun to be with and knew Peru very well. \r\nWe especially enjoyed Rosa in Lima, the fellow (missed his name) who conducted \r\nthe Cusco city tour, and Fabricio in Machu Picchu. Again, thanks for organizing \r\nsuch a great time.</p>','Jim &amp; Joanne,<br />Belmont, CA.','Callan.jpg','Jim and Joanne at Machu Picchu','',517,0,0,NULL,NULL,NULL),(139,1,'Dear Peru For Less','<p>As a globetrotter, I have always traveled on my own without the help of an agency. I always thought it was the best way to go- cheaper, less hassle, no time commitments. However, I wanted to just relax on my trip to Peru. I wanted everything to be taken care of without needing to find places to stay, booking transportation, worrying about cabs and the other aspects that come along with \'roughing it.\' Skeptical, I decided to call Peru for Less. I worried that the upfront cost would be a waste and I would regret ever contacting them. <strong>The moment I landed at the airport in Peru, guides were waiting with plenty of useful information to put my anxiety to rest. On the many guided tours, I learned more than ever from the knowledgeable tour guides.</strong> Transportation was waiting at every stop. <strong>The unique hotels rivaled that of the U.S. because they were quaint, eclectic, and catered to our every need. The sites recommended were phenomenal and the extra trips we took were unforgettable.</strong> I realize now how helpful a tourist agency can be. If I had to plan the trip again, I would call Peru For Less. On my next trip to South America I plan to call Peru For Less.</p>','Joshua (Coldwater, Mississippi)<br/>\r\nTraveled to: Lima, Cusco, Machu Picchu\r\n','Savage.jpg','Josh at Machu Picchu','\"I realize now how helpful a tourist agency can be. If I had to plan the trip again, I would call Peru For Less.\"',100033,0,0,NULL,'2014-09-10 22:55:10',NULL),(140,1,'Diego,','<p>Peru For Less did an outstanding job arranging an itinerary that accommodated \r\nmy last minute requests and the fact I was traveling alone. Each of the airport \r\ntransfers was smooth and friendly, and the tours were exactly what I had hoped. \r\nI\'ve traveled throughout Asia and this was my first vacation to South America. \r\nPeru For Less was easily on par if not better than most of the Asian tours I\'ve \r\ntaken. Peru For Less even called to follow-up and ensure things were going \r\nsmoothly while I was in the middle of the tour. That\'s a sign they truly \r\nunderstand customer service. Kudos to Peru For Less and I wish them great \r\nsuccess in the future.</p>\r\n<p>Many thanks,</p>','Marcus,<br />Highland, UT. ','Daly.jpg','Marcus at Machu Picchu','',522,0,0,NULL,NULL,NULL),(141,1,'Dear Peru For Less','<p>We are very happy with our trip to Peru - you arranged everything to perfection. \r\nAll the Peru For Less representatives were on hand at the right times and in the \r\nright places, plus they were very courteous and a pleasure to deal with. The \r\nguides on our various tours and excursions were all very good and added \r\nimmeasurably to our experiences. The hotels you arranged were all as described, \r\nvery clean and pleasant. We saw so many outstanding things in Peru that it\'s \r\nhard to single out any particular experiences. Lima, the Pisco area, the Nazca \r\nlines, Machu Picchu, Cusco, the Sacred Valley, Lake Titicaca, Arequipa, the \r\nColca Canyon (to name just a few) were all unique and unforgettable experiences. \r\nThe jungle foliage, wildlife, drenching rains, and excellent guides made the \r\nAmazon experience absolutely unforgettable. The horseback ride to the salt mines \r\nand Maras Moray, and the trek to Chacan were a lot of fun and provided \r\ninformation and close ups of areas we would not have otherwise seen. All in all, \r\nthe Peru experience was outstanding. Thanks to you and to everyone at Peru For \r\nLess for arranging such an amazing trip.</p>','Ray and Bob,<br />USA.','Baker.jpg','Ray and Bob having lunch on the horseback ride to','',523,0,0,NULL,NULL,NULL),(142,1,'Hi Diego,','<p>We thought our trip was carefully planned and carried-out. Your staff was \r\nfriendly, knowledgeable, and did their best to accommodate our special \r\ninterests. Even when we made a slight adjustment to the itinerary, your local \r\ncontact was able to accommodate the change, which was very helpful. You \r\ndelivered a high quality experience at a reasonable price. Good job and we would \r\ncertainly recommend your service.</p>\r\n<p>Thanks again,</p>','Warren,<br />Lincoln University, PA.','Miller.jpg','Warren at Machu Picchu','',527,0,0,NULL,NULL,NULL),(143,1,'Dear Peru For Less','<p>Many thanks to you and the folks at Peru for Less for making my dream come true.</p> \r\n<p>After 30+ years I was able to go to Peru, despite my doctor saying I should stay off of my foot, just one week before the trip.<p>\r\n<p><strong>I so appreciate all of your effort to make the trip possible, to make accommodations and your infinite patience with all of my anxieties and needs. </strong></p>\r\n<p>Our time in the jungle was magical and we had the most charming, and knowledgeable guide, Richard, who shared many amazing secrets of the jungle, the birds, monkeys and insects. He is a fine naturalist and we felt fortunate to have him guide us. Every need and whim of the guests was anticipated. I would recommend Posada Amazonas to anyone who loves nature.<strong> Representatives from Peru for Less met us at airports, train stations, and hotels and provided transfers, vouchers, and information in a most professional, prompt, and helpful manner.</strong> In Machu Picchu I was delighted when Fabricio said to me, \"With a little help, anything is possible.\" He took my arm and led me up the path to the temple of the Sun. He was right; there I was exploring Machu Picchu in a walking cast. In Cuzco, lovely Marie and a driver took us to the nearby ruins and to the peoples market for a private, slower paced excursion.  <strong>We were very pleased that we could have so much time for exploration on our own as well as just the right amount of guidance when we could most enjoy it. We are so grateful for your kindness, knowledge, ability to help create a perfect vacation.</strong></p>\r\n<p>Warmly</p>\r\n','Cheryl and Nelly (Portland, OR)<br/>\r\nTraveled to: Lima, Cusco, Machu Picchu, Puerto Maldonado\r\n','Wilton.jpg','Cheryl and Nelly in the Amazon','\"Many thanks to you and the folks at Peru for Less for making my dream come true.\"',100043,0,0,NULL,'2014-09-10 23:08:30',NULL),(144,1,'Dear Peru For Less','<p>My husband Geoff and I traveled through Chile, Peru, Argentina, and Brazil \r\nfor five weeks and it was due to the thorough planning and bookings that you did \r\nfor us that enabled us to have had one of the best holidays we have ever had. \r\nThe entire itinerary was perfect, the suggestions and help you gave us, JP, as \r\nto where to go and what to do were really great and the professionalism of you \r\nand your team made the holiday so enjoyable. I had searched the internet for \r\nmany hours before coming across your web site. I went with your company because \r\nit had so many different choices of tours to suit all ages and budgets- we were \r\nnot disappointed. We could not find a flaw in any of the arrangements, and all \r\nthe agents were very prompt, courteous, and most helpful. When booking from \r\nAustralia there is a lot of trust involved and we are pleased to say everything \r\nwent according to plan. We have gladly recommended you and your company to many \r\nother travelers and will continue to do so.</p>\r\n<p>Thank you all very much,</p>','Jean and Geoff, <br />Perth, Australia. ','Parker.jpg','Jean and Geoff at Machu Picchu','',535,0,0,NULL,NULL,NULL),(145,1,'Dear Peru For Less','<p>Thank you for following up with us.  My husband (John) and I had a wonderful time. Due to problems with our flights to Peru (which were arranged by us, not by Peru For Less), we did not get off to a great start. Half of our group (2 people) made it to Peru on schedule. The other two were 24 hours behind. Janjoris was very helpful in rescheduling our flight from Lima to Cusco, our hotels, and our train to Machu Picchu. Peru For Less handled our problem well and managed two separate itineraries for a few days until those of us arriving late caught up to the other two three days later. <strong>This was a true test for how well a travel agency can be the difference in a having a good or bad vacation. Without Peru For Less, this may have turned out to be a bad vacation for us!</strong></p> \r\n<p>The Peru for Less staff and other tour guides were great. Fabricio (Machu Picchu) was very knowledgeable and made the experience perfect. Juan Carlos was so nice and really took good care of us in Cusco. I have to say that Machu Picchu was the highlight of the trip. That is something we had wanted to see for awhile and it did not disappoint.<strong>We really enjoyed our entire stay in Peru. All the people we met were so nice and the food was fantastic. We already know we\'d like to go back to Peru on a future vacation.</strong> We plan to recommend Peru For Less to our friends and family, as we had a wonderful experience.</p>\r\n<p>Gracias!</p>\r\n','Karen & John (Michigan, USA)<br/>\r\nTraveled to: Lima, Cusco, Machu Picchu\r\n','Eagle.jpg','Karen and John at Machu Picchu','\"Peru For Less handled our problem well.. a true test for how well a travel agency can be the difference in a having a good or bad vacation.\"',100047,0,0,NULL,'2014-09-10 22:55:09',NULL),(146,1,'Dear Peru For Less','<p>We had a great trip. Thanks for everything you did!!!</p>','Samantha and Ali,<br />Brookline, MA.','','','',1,0,0,NULL,NULL,NULL),(147,1,'Dear Peru For Less','<p>Thank you so much for making the arrangements for my trip. I totally enjoyed my vacation \r\nin Cusco, Machu Picchu and Nazca. The Peruvian people were very friendly to me. I strongly hope \r\nI can come to Peru again. Thank you again for your assistance.</p>\r\n<p>Sincerely,</p>','Itaru,<br />New York.','','','',7,0,0,NULL,NULL,NULL),(148,1,'Hi Jenny and Ximena,','<p>Thanks for setting up our tour to Arequipa, it was fabulous! At El Balcon where we stayed they treated us well and we had some great food there!! I would recommend them to anyone that is going to Arequipa. Our tour guide Guido was informative and funny and made us laugh a lot. The one thing we regret is not having gone to the Colca Canyon. I guess that may have to be another trip.</p>\r\n<p>Take care and thanks again,</p>','Myrna,<br />St. Helena, CA.','','','',2,0,0,NULL,NULL,NULL),(149,1,'Ximena,','<p>Thanks much for the email. The trip went very well with no preventable problems. I have recommended Peru For Less to other volunteers. Peru For Less did a great job of customizing arrangements for reasonable prices. Everything worked.</p>\r\n<p>Stay well and enjoy the holidays,</p>','Helen,<br />Elburn, IL.','','','',3,0,0,NULL,NULL,NULL),(150,1,'Hi Richard,','<p>We got back from our trip a few days ago and had a great time! Thanks for all your help coordinating it. The Peru For Less representatives in Peru were all great.</p>\r\n<p>Take care,</p>','Liam,<br />Oakland, CA.','','','',4,0,0,NULL,NULL,NULL),(151,1,'Dear Ximena,','<p>I just wanted to say thank you for all your efforts and planning. I had a wonderful trip through Peru. Everyone was so nice and helpful. The hotels were wonderful, and I was able to enjoy being with my son and the Peruvian people that he loves. Thank you so much for all your help!</p>\r\n<p>Muchas gracias,</p>','Nancy,<br />Santa Clara, CA.','','','',5,0,0,NULL,NULL,NULL),(152,1,'Thanks Richard,','<p>Enjoyed the trip! Your crew was awesome, on time, and knowledgeable. You made my trip very comfortable by not having to negotiate my way around by myself. Sorry I didn\'t get to meet you.</p>\r\n<p>Thanks again,</p>','Carol,<br />USA.','','','',6,0,0,NULL,NULL,NULL),(153,1,'Hi Ximena,','<p>I did finally end up seeing Machu Picchu which is definitely awe-inspiring and worth the trip. My guide was great and really informative. It was an amazing experience. Also, I just want to thank you for making all the arrangements for Cusco and Lima. Both towns were beautiful in their own way. Cusco is like a golden jewel at night.  The people were nice. The hotel staff at Plaza de Armas was great-very informative and helpful. The hotel staffs at all the other places were great. Lima on the other hand was very metropolitan which was a nice change from the small town of Cusco. And I particularly loved the beach there in Miraflores. Great job from you for setting up my hotel stay in Miraflores (the hotel staff was excellent- warm, informative and the accommodations were very modern, clean, and comfortable). All in all, I enjoyed my trip. I hope to go back to Peru again. The people and culture and land were something I\'ll never forget.</p>\r\n<p>Thank you,</p>','Aimee,<br />Santa Cruz, CA.','','','',11,0,0,NULL,NULL,NULL),(154,1,'Hi Ximena,','<p>Where to begin...? Highlights: Arequipa- Hotel Casa del Melgar, walking tour of the city, our fabulous tour guides, the drive to Colca Canyon, coca leaves, coca tea? the views at 16,000 feet were breathtaking, Pozo Del Cielo Hotel in the Colca Canyon. Cusco- everything, especially the Sacred Valley tour, and I loved Ollantaytambo Hotel Arqueologo, the Inca Trail was unreal. Machu Picchu- well, words cannot express my wonder and delight at all of the history and ruins throughout our journey. I could go on and on....our adventure was more than we imagined. Every transfer was seamless. Thanks for everything. Your patience and professionalism were stellar.</p>\r\n','Kim,<br />Glen Arm, MD.','','','',12,0,0,NULL,NULL,NULL),(155,1,'Hi Richard,','<p>PERU- I enjoyed every moment, you guys are truly well organised. The only thing was it was very rushed. If I had to do it again, I would take more time in certain areas.The hotels and guides were great. So l can carry on and on praising. When I tell anyone about Peru I say they should visit now cause in a couple of years it will be the next best tourist destination. I got this months news letter and I have to go back and do the north of Peru.It looks great. Now I will tell you the real purpose of my trip. The Celestine Prophesy.I read it many years ago and I knew I had to go.I returned to Machu Picchu the next day after the tour and sat on the rock In the Sun Temple for over an hour in the rain. That experience is etched deep in my heart. No photo will ever do justice to such an amazing place. Michelle is wanting to go work in the jungle,she is totally in love with forest and the lodge. Richard this is just a quick summary but Thank You from the bottom of my heart.</p>\r\n<p>Take care,</p>','Lynn,<br />South Africa.','','','',13,0,0,NULL,NULL,NULL),(156,1,'Dear Ximena,','<p>We had a wonderful trip and certainly appreciate what you did to pull it all \r\ntogether. Maria and Carlos were great transporting us to and from the airport \r\nand the train station. Rosie did a good job making sure we knew what time we\'d \r\nbe picked up and taking us on the Sacred Valley tour. Staying at the Sanctuary \r\nLodge was certainly a highlight of the trip. Although I note that their prices \r\nare high, I encourage anyone who can possibly afford it to stay there. It was \r\nwonderful to be able to just walk back and forth to the preserve. We liked the \r\nNovotel Cusco and thought their staff was very accommodating. I enjoyed having \r\ndinner with you on Tuesday evening. It was very nice to be able to meet the \r\nperson with whom I had corresponded so many times. We would certainly use Peru \r\nFor Less again should we plan another trip to Peru. Your company does an \r\nexcellent job. Best wishes for a wonderful holiday season. When you come to DC, \r\nplease give us a call.</p>\r\n<p>Thanks again,</p>','Kate<br />Washington D.C. ','','','',34,0,0,NULL,NULL,NULL),(157,1,'Hi Richard,','<p>Phyllis and I had a wonderful vacation in Peru.  It was fantastic. A truly beautiful country with great people. First of all, we were very impressed with the tour companies and how they met us at every hotel, bus station, train station and airport. It was one of those small things that allowed us to be totally relaxed and enjoy everything else. We truely appreciated the Peruvian people and how friendly they are. We had great meals, some at restaurants you recommended: Astrid y Gaston in Lima, and a couple in Cusco that I can\'t remember the names. Also, the hotels were all charming and well staffed. The tours were also very good. We enjoyed the Lima city tour, the tour out of Pisco (Ballestas Islands), and of course the Sacred Valley was beautiful. We tended to think that Sacsayhuaman was more interesting than Macchu Pichu because of the stone work, however, Macchu Pichu was spectacular in its\' setting, especially after the crowds left. Ollantaytambo was also amazing. Your company did an excellent job and we certainly would ask you to plan our next South American trip in a few years. We have discussed a Buenos Aires to Patagonia to Santiago trip; maybe in 2008. Thank you again for a wonderful vacation.</p>\r\n<p>Regards,</p>','Patrick, <br />Mountain View, CA.','','','',35,0,0,NULL,NULL,NULL),(158,1,'Hi Ximena,','<p>The trip was spectacular and everything went perfect. Everyone was on time for pick-ups and all our tickets and accommodations were in line. All the hotels were very nice. All the tours we went on and museums were great as well. Lucky for us, the weather was perfect, too. Thanks so much for everything....we had a great time and your company did a great job. We were very pleased and would definitely recommend you to anyone.</p>\r\n<p>Take care,</p>','Moira,<br />Fernandina Beach, FL.','','','',36,0,0,NULL,NULL,NULL),(159,1,'Dear Peru For Less','<p>Our trip was wonderful. We enjoyed everything we did and saw. It would be hard to pick a favorite activity or location. Everything was so different at each place that we just loved all of them. As for the guides, again they were great. They were always on time and all were knowledgeable about the areas we visited. Anytime we have traveled, we have never considered going back to that location, but there was still so much more to see and do in Peru that we have considered at some point going back and we just got home!  My son just loved the horseback ride to Maras Morey Salt mines, and my husband is ready to ride the train again that we took to Puno. He is a huge train fan. As for me, I would like to head back to Ollantaytambo. Our trip there was not long enough and our only regret was not staying the night there in that town. There is just so much to explore in that area and the day tours don\'t give enough time for that. Without a doubt, we will highly recommend your tour group to all of our friends. I can\'t imagine anyone doing a better job than your entire crew did. Thanks for doing such a good job and making this the best and most memorable trip we have ever taken!.</p>','Kelly, James and Joshua,<br />Illinois, USA.','','','',37,0,0,NULL,NULL,NULL),(160,1,'Hi Jenny,','<p>Our trip to Peru in November was great, thanks to your arrangements and the local folks who took care of us. All of the accomodations, transportation and site visits went very smoothly. The Inca sites are truly amazing and we were happy to visit now because I\'m sure that access to these sites will be restricted in the future for their preservation. Wilda and Frabricio and their associates were terrific. Since it was election season in Peru, it was fun to talk with them about politics and the election. We appreciated their willingness to engage us in conversation about life in Peru in addition to the typical tourism conversations. From restaurant recommendations to hotel room selection, our guides were helpful and knowledgeable. Thanks so much for a memorable trip. I\'ve recommended you to others.</p>\r\n<p>Cheers,</p>','Linda and Vince,<br />Madison, WI.','','','',38,0,0,NULL,NULL,NULL),(161,1,'Hi Ximena and Jenny,','<p>Thanks to you and your staff, we had a great visit to Peru, Chile and \r\nArgentina (&amp; 3 hours worth of Brazil!). We especially want to mention Wilda, \r\nFabricio, and Mary in Cuzco/Machu Picchu, Abelardo in Santiago, Eduardo in \r\nBuenos Aires, and Marta in Barriloche. We marveled at the scenery, antiquities, \r\nthe Tango, and the distances. We found the people friendly and helpful. Although \r\n2 and 1/2 weeks was not nearly enough time to spend in South America, we enjoyed \r\nit all, and hope to return in the future. We wish you a joyous Christmas season \r\nand a happy, healthy New Year.</p>\r\n<p>Warm regards,</p>','Nancy and Alan,<br />Lafayette, CA. ','','','',39,0,0,NULL,NULL,NULL),(162,1,'Dear Richard,','<p>It\'s been 2 weeks since I came back from Peru and reality has not hit me quite yet. What can I say about Peru that has not been said. This was a long awaited dream of mine and I want to thank you and Peru for less for making it real. The accommodations were excellent. All the guides were extremely helpful, but truly every Peruvian I was in contact with was welcoming. As a woman, I felt very safe everywhere. Again thank you for a great trip and I will definitely recommend Peru For Less to anybody planning a trip in South America.</p>','Mathilde,<br />Westlake Village, CA.','','','',53,0,0,NULL,NULL,NULL),(163,1,'Hi Diego,','<p>I\'m back from our wonderful time in Peru. All guides were EXCELLENT. They could not have been more kind, concerned, caring, and informative. One week is close to an insult, however. So, I\'ll be back again....and when I do, I shall be contacting you! What a magnificent country your Peru is.</p>\r\n<p>Thanks Diego,</p>','Nancy,<br />Sylvania, OH.','','','',54,0,0,NULL,NULL,NULL),(164,1,'Hola Ximena,','<p>So nice to hear from you. I have been meaning to write sooner so was delighted that you prompted me. We had a wonderful time and I can\'t thank you enough for your efforts to make it so. I can\'t tell you how much fun we had in Huacachina. I could not get over the terrain. I had never associated Peru with those incredible windswept dunes. We indeed all went sand-boarding and I had the bruises and aches to prove it! Our accommodations were lovely throughout the trip. I would particularly want to mention our tour guide in Machu Picchu, Fabricio. He truly made our visit a mystical and most memorable experience. In addition he came to our rescue when we missed our train back to Cuzco. (Sorry about that!) Everyone we met associated with Peru For Less could not have been nicer. I have several friends that are hoping to visit Peru so you can be certain that I will be touting your name. Thanks again and remember I expect to see you in Nova Scotia one of these days.</p>','Jane,<br />Nova Scotia, Canada.','','','',62,0,0,NULL,NULL,NULL),(165,1,'Richard,','<p>I had a great trip. The itinerary you put together for me was just what I wanted and at every stop I was met by very pleasant and professional people. I had a call from Jenny to check up on me, which was a nice touch and an unexpected private tour of Machu Picchu with Fabricio, who was a dedicated and knowledgeable guide. The hotels were all comfortable and even the bus drivers drove carefully. I will certainly recommend your service to any of my friends who might want to see some of the wonderful sights of Peru. Once again, thanks for a great trip.</p>\r\n<p>Many thanks and best regards,</p>','Sven.','','','',63,0,0,NULL,NULL,NULL),(166,1,'Dear Peru For Less','<p>I have just returned from my business trip to Lima and wanted to write and thank you and your entire team for the fantastic job you did in organizing the Ã¢â?¬ÂvacationÃ¢â?¬Â portion of my time in Peru. As promised,  I was met at each airport and train station and trasferred to great hotels. All of the drivers (especially Carlos and Mary on my Sacred Valley tour) were professional and extremely knowledgeable, on top of being very interesting people in their own right. All the arrangements for the Cusco / Machu Picchu portion went extremely well and Christina in Cusco was unbelieveably efficient and gracious. The food, the people, and the places were lovely and my days of vacation were totally stress free thanks to your great organization. Thanks again and I\'ll contact you within the year to organize a small group tour for friends and family!</p>\r\n<p>All the best,</p>','Barbara,<br />Victoria, Canada.','','','',64,0,0,NULL,NULL,NULL),(167,1,'Hi Ximena,','<p>First of all, I was very impressed by how prompt the representatives were in Peru (your company has done a great job with making me feel comfortable). They were extremely reliable. Hotels- I loved the old colonial Spanish style of the hotels. They were very quaint and comfortable. The food was excellent!!! The City tour was excellent- our guide was very knowledgeable. There was a significant amount of interesting information provided to us during the tour. The all day tour of the Sacred Valley was absolutely wonderful. I was totally amazed at how large their fruits and vegetables are. I loved Pisaq Market and did a lot of shopping. That guide was even more knowledgeable. She had a wonderful personality as well. I didn\'t realize that the tour guides had to go to school for so long to enter into their fields (makes sense- they know so much about the culture and history). The bus ride was very comfortable and the scenery picture perfect. The trek itself was difficult, only because I was not in the type of shape I thought I was in. I was happy that I took heed to the thorough and informative tips that you provided (i.e. personal items to take- sleeping bag, etc.) because they definitely came in handy. The evenings were cold, thankfully the tents provided good shelter. The cooks were very, very good- the food (all three meals in the day) were always very delicious. I was impressed by the meals, the little tubs of hot water and towels they provided for us morning and evening for washing up; the portable restrooms and the solution they used to sanitize the portable toilet, and most of all their kindness and patience. At one point, when I could no longer walk up the trek, they provided me with a horse to ride. Machu Picchu was absolutely breathtaking. I could definitely see why so many people refer to Machu Picchu as spiritual. There is so much to share about the trip... but I\'ll end it here with? I had an absolutely wonderful journey</p>\r\n<p>Thanks so much,</p>','Val,<br />Fonatna, CA.','','','',65,0,0,NULL,NULL,NULL),(168,1,'Dear Cristina,','<p>Our Peruvian adventure became quite frightening when my husband became gravely ill (it was completely unrelated to our trip to Peru) and required an immediate return to the United States. After one call to our travel agent, Cristina, we were at the airport in less than four hours. Dr Postigo (arranged for by Peru for Less) gave IV fluids and IV antibiotics to my husband, Steve, to help prepare him for the trip home. Special thanks to our guide in Arequipa who waited in the hotel lobby with me for Dr. Postigo to arrive and helped me navigate the pharmacy. He was very professional and never once let on that he knew I was about to lose it. Cristina even contacted our son with our flight information and he was at the Miami airport to pick us up and take us to the ER. Thankfully, Steve has recovered and we are both well. We couldn\'t have been treated with more kindness and concern and I can\'t thank you enough! When we go back to Peru, it will be with Peru for Less.</p>','Debby,<br />Fort Pierce, FL.','','','',74,0,0,NULL,NULL,NULL),(169,1,'Dear Richard,','<p>Overall, our trip to Peru was a fantastic experience! It was a pleasure having Peru for Less coordinate our travel arrangements. Your representatives were always on time and very courteous and accommodating. A few things stand out that I would like to share with you. Upon arriving at the Tupac Yupanqui hotel in Cusco, I noticed that there was a curb that blocked entry for my wheelchair into the hotel. The hotel employees immediately made accommodations by lifting me, along with my chair, over the curb and into the lobby. Upon returning to the hotel later in the day from a tour of the Sacred Valley, to my surprise a ramp had been constructed making my entry into the hotel much easier. Two days later after going up to Machu Picchu, we returned once again to the Tupac Yupanqui hotel in Cusco only to discover that another two ramps had been built, one to provide access from the sidewalk, the other for access up the street curb. As a result, I had independent wheelchair access into the hotel. The train ride was an enjoyable experience. As I arrived to board the train For Machu Picchu, it became apparent that there was no wheelchair access directly onto the train. The employees of Peru Rail immediately offered their services to help me board. Fortunately I was able to hold onto handrails and climb up the stairs as my wheelchair was lifted in behind me. Once inside the train car, a young lady Ã¢â?¬ÂstewardessÃ¢â?¬Â named Cristina greeted us and provided her assistance. Throughout the trip, she went out of her way to accommodate my friends and me, and to make our trip most comfortable and memorable. Soon after we arrived at Aguas Calientes, your representative introduced me to a man who offered to assist me in navigating the trails of Machu Picchu.  Another man (a policeman) also offered to help out. As a result, my wheelchair and I were maneuvered up and down the steps and along the paths throughout the ruins. When my traveling companions met up with me, they said that I saw nearly as much of Machu Picchu as they did on their tour. What an adventure that was. After returning to Cusco from Machu Picchu, I discovered that some parts from my wheelchair were missing. We phoned your company asking for your driver to look for them in the van. To my surprise he found them and promptly returned the parts to me at our hotel. For this kind act, I am very grateful. Once again thank you for your assistance in planning our wonderful trip to Peru.</p>','John, <br />Oakland, CA.','','','',75,0,0,NULL,NULL,NULL),(170,1,'Dear Richard,','<p>The trip could not have been better; it was the best organized trip we have ever been on and we have done our fair share of traveling. It started out with a mishap: Delta did not leave Atlanta on time and consequently, we arrived in Lima three and a half hours late, at 2:00 in the morning instead of 10:30 at night. Yet your representative and driver were there waiting for us (I must say I was very pleasantly surprised). That set the tone for the entire trip- no matter what delays we ran into, the representatives were there awaiting us. As we found out when talking to other travellers who had booked with different companies, this is not a given; many of them were not picked up when their arrival was delayed. All the representatives were very courteous and helpful and went out of their way to make our trip pleasant. The guides were superb; every single one of them showed a passion for their work: they wanted us to get to know Peru and to appreciate its rich heritage and culture. And they were all very well informed and loved to share their knowledge. The whole itinerary was great, just the right balance between sightseeing and some free time. I particularly liked the idea that we were able to customize- I think that is a really great plus of your program. Again, many other companies do not offer that service as we learned from talking with others. Also, the ability to choose the hotels is a great service. I have to say that in most cases the websites do not do them justice. So, thanks again for making this trip a dream trip. I have nothing but praise for your company and have recommended it to anyone who will hear about it (and even to those who rather not!).</p>\r\n<p>Best regards</p>','Ella and Michael,<br />Alexandria, VA.','','','',76,0,0,NULL,NULL,NULL),(171,1,'Dear Peru For Less','<p>After a dicey arrival in Peru due to American Airlines, it was a great pleasure to finally see some of Peru . Thank you for all efforts to accommodate late arrivals. Especially, Laura, Maria, and Carlos. The tour guides were superb. </p>\r\n<p>We are glad that we spent the extra night in Aguas Calientes to see two mornings of sunrise in the grandest ruin we ever encountered and traveling to ruins is our specialty. Cusco was warm and spectacular; the colonial architecture and paintings a unique legacy.</p>\r\n<p>I realize that I would be happy to spend 3 weeks in Sacred Valley , Picchu, and Cusco alone but unforntunately had to return to reality.</p>\r\n<p>Best regards,</p>','John, <br />New York, NY.','','','',20,0,0,NULL,NULL,NULL),(172,1,'Dear Peru For Less','<p>Just thought I should let you know that all went well on our itinerary: we \r\nenjoyed the visit immensely. </p>\r\n<p>The accommodation was fine and convenient; the private day trip was most \r\nenjoyable and personally I feel preferable to an organised bus tour as it was \r\nmuch more relaxed. The stay at MP was well worthwhile even though I did suffer \r\nvertigo on one of the walks! An excellent experience. Sincere thanks for your \r\nassistance in organising the itinerary.</p>\r\n<p>best regards, </p>','Brian,<br />Australia. ','','','',27,0,0,NULL,NULL,NULL),(173,1,'Dear Ale','<p>I was glad to find out that you could arrange a sidetrip for me to northern \r\nPeru, even though it\'s not on Peru For Less\'s list of tours. I wanted to see the \r\ncity of Trujillo and visit some of the nearby ruins of the Moche and Chimu \r\ncultures, and you were able to come up with several interesting tours for \r\nme.</p>\r\n<p>Now I\'m already thinking about another trip to Peru, maybe further north to \r\nChiclayo this time, to visit the excellent new museum there and the ruins of \r\nSipan....What do you think, Ale?.</p>','Bill,<br />San Francisco, California. ','howe.jpg','Bill in Peru','',425,0,0,NULL,NULL,NULL),(174,1,'Dear Ale,','<p>Our trip to Peru was just wonderful, thanks to you and your staff. The \r\naltitude was a little difficult in the \"highlands\" and we appreciated the oxygen \r\nwhen we returned to Lima. However, Cuzco is just magical. This was our favorite \r\nplace, and a place we\'d love to return to. We loved Machu Picchu, the Sacred \r\nValley, and the many other sites in this area. All of our accommodations were \r\nperfect, and our tour guides were informative and fun. We found rural Peru quite \r\nenticing, simple yet wholesome. All in all, a perfect vacation, and we\'d \r\nrecommend Peru to anyone, assuming they don\'t mind the altitude and are able to \r\nclimb. There were quite a few people in our groups who were \"huffing and \r\npuffing\", but the exercise and thin air really didn\'t slow us down much. Thanks \r\nagain for all of your help. Perhaps our paths will cross one day.</p>','Judy,<br />Quebec, Canada. ','Judy.jpg','Judy on the Floating Islands of the Uros, Lake Tit','',435,0,0,NULL,NULL,NULL),(175,1,'Hello there Ximena,','<p>You are the BEST thing about Peru For Less, along with the wonderful guide we \r\nhad for Machu Picchu, he was absolutely super! It was a wonderful time.</p>\r\n<p>Many thanks,</p>','Mary,<br />New York City, NY. ','Mary-Ann.jpg','Mary Ann at Machu Picchu','',415,0,0,NULL,NULL,NULL),(177,1,'Ximena,','<p>We\'re still raving about our holiday to everyone and the fabulous job you and \r\nJenny did in arranging, coordinating, and babysitting. Have a safe, happy \r\nholiday and pass along same to Jenny.</p>','Renota and Ton,<br />Netherland, Antilles. ','Renota-Tom.jpg','Ton and Renota on the Train','',413,0,0,NULL,NULL,NULL),(178,1,'Dear Ximena,','<p>Thanks for checking on our trip. We had a wonderful experience; everything \r\nwent very well. Our guide Jovana was very friendly, knowledgeable, and helpful. \r\nWe were met on time for all transfers. Both hotels were very good. I will \r\nrecommend you to all who ask.</p>\r\n<p>Best regards,</p>','Bill,<br />San Jose, CA. ','Bill-sanjose.jpg','Bill at Machu Picchu','',416,0,0,NULL,NULL,NULL),(179,1,'Hello Diego,','<p>The trip to Peru was beautiful, we had a great time!!!! Loved itâ?¦would do it all over againâ?¦we are thinking about going next year to visit the Nazca lines, and to visit other beautiful places in my lovely Country.</p>\r\n<p>Thank you for everything,</p>\r\n','Candy,<br />Miami, FL.\r\n','Candy.jpg','Candy, Dave and Family in Peru','',417,0,0,NULL,NULL,NULL),(180,1,'Hi Richard,','<p>The Sacred Valley trip was awesome; we learned a lot and saw some very nice \r\nthings. It was not as great as Machu Picchu, but close. Thank you again for \r\nhelping me with all the endless questions I had. All our guides were wonderful. \r\nFred in Pisco and then later in Nazca was wonderful. He was very helpful and \r\nknowledgeable. We had a wonderful time and would recommend your company to \r\nanyone and in fact have mentioned your name several times to different people. \r\nThe memories will be with us for a lifetime.</p>\r\n<p>Thanks and God bless,</p>','Sandra,<br />Stanwood, WA. ','Sandra-stanwood.jpg','Sarah, Gary, and Matthew in the Sacred Valley','',438,0,0,NULL,NULL,NULL),(181,1,'Dear Peru For Less','<p>We had a fantastic time in Peru. PFL\'s service was excellent. All your guides \r\nwere very knowledgeable, kind, and punctual. For the guides that spent more than \r\none day with us, it was hard to say goodbye as we became very attached to them: \r\nValeria, Carola, Javi, Cristina, and Mauge. The food at all our lodgings was \r\nsuperb, especially at Refugio Amazonas and El Pueblo. El Pueblo had the added \r\nbenefit of onsite bird guide and many exotic birds right on the premises. The \r\nColca Lodge had beautiful breathtaking surroundings and we would have stayed \r\nlonger if it had been possible. The Inti Raymi festival was fine, however, it \r\nseemed geared to the tourists. We all concurred that the dances of the various \r\ngroups at the Plaza in Cusco exceeded entertainment value of the IntiRaymi. We \r\nwill recommend PFL to our friends and family and we hope to call on PFL when we \r\nreturn to Peru.</p>\r\n<p>Sincerely,</p>','Mirtha and Family,<br />Oakland, CA. ','Mirtha-oakland.jpg','Mirtha and Family at Machu Picchu','',439,0,0,NULL,NULL,NULL),(182,1,'Hi Ximena,','<p>I had a wonderful time in Peru and loved all the places I visited. My guides and contacts through Peru For Less were excellent. I suffered with altitude sickness but my guide going to the Colca Canyon got me some medicine and I felt better. I was impressed with the cleanliness and high standard of the hotels and food. Cusco was my favorite town and hotel and I wish that I had spent a bit more time there. Machu Picchu was of course magnificent and I liked it in the rain and mist.<br />\r\nPeru will be a very happy memory for me always, thank you very much for making it all possible.</p>\r\n<p>Regards,</p>\r\n','Dorothy,<br />Holmbridge, Yorkshire, England.\r\n','Dorothy-holmbridge.jpg','Dorothy in the Amazon','',440,0,0,NULL,NULL,NULL),(183,1,'Hi Ale,','<p>Thanks for all your patience and careful advice preparing our fantastic holiday in Peru. Every day was special. Pass our details to anyone who wants some re assurance. You can trust Peru For Less. They deliver the goods. They provide a great semi-independent way to explore that works. We shalln\'t hesitate to contact them again for our next South American venture.</p>\r\n<p>Cheers,</p>\r\n','Janet and Rowan,<br />Sheffield, UK.\r\n','Janet-sheffield.jpg','Janet and Rowan in the Andes Mountains','',443,0,0,NULL,NULL,NULL),(184,1,'Richard,','<p>Thanks for following up! We had a great time! All the rooms were beautiful; we really felt we were living in luxury during each night of our stay in Peru. The hotel locations were so convenient to the Plaza de Armas in Cusco. We went to most of the restaurants that were recommended in each city and they were all served delicious meals! Each PFL representative came to pick us up on time, or met us the night before, and was able to answer all of our questions. So we never felt like we didn\'t know what we were doing. The guides were all so knowledgeable and welcoming. Please thank Fabricio again for giving us a great tour of Machu Picchu! I think we really enjoyed Rosie as our guide to the Sacred Valley too! I would definitely recommend others to go through Peru For Less, and this experience will definitely encourage me to visit Peru again!</p>','Maureen,<br />USA.\r\n','Maureen-USA.jpg','At Machu Picchu','',444,0,0,NULL,NULL,NULL),(185,1,'Hi Ximena,','<p>Thank you so much for all the travel arrangements to Peru! Traveling to another country can be complicated at times, and you did a great job answering our questions and making sure we had all the information we would need to make it a memorable trip. Your attention to detail added a personal touch, which we greatly appreciated. There was no part of the trip where we felt that we had wasted our time or money! The operations team did a great job in ensuring that pick-ups were on time and things ran like clockwork! All four of us had a great time and maybe we\'ll be back someday!</p>\r\n<p>Best wishes,</p>\r\n','Arun, Gaurav, Prashant, Rahul.','Arun.jpg','Arun, Gaurav, Prashant, Rahul in Peru','',445,0,0,NULL,NULL,NULL),(186,1,'Hi Ximena!','<p>Thank you for your email. Our trip was wonderful! We had a great time! We \r\nespecially liked the laid back atmosphere in Posada Amazonas, plus, the \r\none-on-one tours with our guide during those 4 days. That made it a lot of fun, \r\nand we got to learn a lot about the area. Also, we loved Machu Picchu. That has \r\nto be one of the most glorious places imaginable! The extra day was definitely \r\nworth it! Peru was fabulous! The people were wonderful, the country was \r\nbeautiful, and the prices were reasonable throughout the trip! Plus, I\'ve \r\nalready shown many pictures to my friends and family and they all want to take a \r\ntrip there as well! Thanks again for a wonderful time!</p>','Kimberly and Ernie,<br />Colorado Springs, CO. ','Kimberly-colorado.jpg','Kimberly and Ernie at Machu Picchu','',458,0,0,NULL,NULL,NULL),(187,1,'Dear Ximena,','<p>I recently took a tour to Peru with the assistance of Peru For Less. I wanted to thank you Ximena and the Peru For Less team who met me in every: train station, bus station, airport, hotel, and city tour. Everyone in person and not in person was very attentive with my tour and cared about my well being, as I was traveling alone. Everything turned out to be organized and in a timely manner. I had such a fantastic time being in Peru! I saw more than I expected and learned what I would have never imagined. Peru is a beautiful country that is a must not only to explore its mysteries, but to see its beauties in person too. I wish I could have spent more than 14 days in Peru. However, I hope to go back to Peru some day and not only walk the Inca Trail ,but see other places that I did not have the opportunity to visit. I once again wanted to thank the Peru for less team for being so kind and hardworking.</p>\r\n<p>MUCHAS GRACIAS!</p>\r\n','Nancy,<br /> Culver City, CA.\r\n','Nancy-culver.jpg','Nancy and her Llama buddy at Machu Picchu','',471,0,0,NULL,NULL,NULL),(188,1,'Dear Richard,','<p>We are back in Malta! We would like to thank you and your team for a most enjoyable vacation. Considering the many countries (Peru, Chile, Argentina, and Brazil) we visited, and the 14 flights we took, all went well. Hotels were of a good standard with the \'Emperador\' in Buenos Aires being exceptional value. We were always met on time by extremely competent guides. Transport used was always clean and comfortable. Once again, thank you for a great vacation and I will certainly recommend Peru For Less to those who would like a stress free holiday in South America.</p>','Oliver,<br />Malta. ','Oliver-malta.jpg','Oliver and Company on Vacation','',472,0,0,NULL,NULL,NULL),(189,1,'Dear Peru For Less','<p>My husband and I had a wonderful time in Peru and were very pleased by the services provided by PFL. Our questions were answered, promises were kept, and we appreciated the personal touch. We felt very well taken care of and were able to fully enjoy our time in Peru. The Inca Trail was quite an adventure and, even though we (I) found it challenging, we loved our tour guides (especially Miguel) and found the whole experience to be incredible. The scenery was amazing and Machu Picchu was breathtaking. We\'ll never forget the morning light on that beautiful place. On the trail, the food was plentiful and delicious and we again felt well taken care of thanks to the caring nature of both guides and porters. We consider our trip to be a success and are highly recommending both PFL and Machu Picchu to our friends and family. Should we ever decide to revisit South America, we\'ll certainly use PFL\'s services again. Thanks again for all your help.</p>','Valerie, <br />Castro Valley, CA.\r\n','Valerie-castro.jpg','Valerie and Husband at Machu Picchu','',473,0,0,NULL,NULL,NULL),(190,1,'Hi Richard,','<p>The trip was a great success. All of the PFL (Peru for Less) staff was great. The private tour guides and the accommodations were the best. We highly recommend this tour and PFL. The PFL staff was able to accommodate our late arrival into Lima by booking an extra night room and transportation for the continuation to Cusco the next day. Finding that our return flight was very late, PFL was able to book the Lima city tour including the Archeological museum. I highly recommend this as it helps fill in the whole history of the region. There were four in our little group and the transportation and tours worked out perfect. We really got to experience the Peruvian culture and understand a little bit better the history of the Incas and their predecessors.</p>','Earl, Sharon, Dan, and Gwen, <br />ValparaÃ­so, IN and Grand Marais, MI.\r\n','Earl-valparaiso.jpg','Earl, Sharon, Dan, and Gwen','',474,0,0,NULL,NULL,NULL),(191,1,'Hi Richard and Pauline,','<p>We had a wonderful time in Peru. Most of all, we immensely enjoyed the \r\nSalcantay hike (Thanks to Richard for suggesting it to us!). All our pick-ups \r\nand drop-offs were on time, and the briefings were good and covered all the \r\nimportant things we needed to know. Weâ??d like to mention that Christina did an \r\nawesome job on making sure we got on our Cusco tour (as LAN messed up our flight \r\nreservations), and she gave us good tips on shopping and dining. Claudia from \r\nthe Lima office was also very helpful and gave us a great briefing.<br />Last, but \r\nnot the least, weâ??ve like to mention that Maria and Derik made our Salcantay \r\nhike a great experience. Overall weâ??ve bought back some great memories from \r\nPeru! So, thank you all once again!</p>','Amitha, <br />Santa Clara, CA. ','Amitha-santaclara.jpg','Amitha, Ramesh, Gautham, Prashant, and Amit on the','',475,0,0,NULL,NULL,NULL),(192,1,'Hi Richard,','<p>Our trip was outstanding. We all had a great time. Every time we sit and talk about it it is hard to say what we enjoyed the most. I would like you all to know we will all remember this trip as one of our best. The quality of tour guides you employ is truly world class. I don\'t remember all the names but they all did a great job. The white water rafting showed the Valley from a diffrent view then we had seen the day before. The tour guide we had for Machu Pichu was outstanding. Everything was great- we do not have a bad comment. The Hotel Novel was our favorite. Local artists, music, and food was great. Your organization should be proud of the whole team in Peru. \r\nRichard, I would also like to thank you for making the last minute arangments for us in Lima. It was well worth the money. We loved the Gold Musium exibit. It showed us there was so much more before the Incas. Thanks again for creating memories of a life time with us.</p>','Doug, <br />Lisbon, Iowa.\r\n','Doug-lisbon.jpg','Doug and the Guys at Machu Picchu','',476,0,0,NULL,NULL,NULL),(193,1,'Dear Peru For Less','<p>The trip was really wonderful!!  I was very pleased at how smoothly everything went. Every airport pickup and drop off was right on time and very efficient. Everyone was very, very nice with good English skills. All of the hotels were great. The Salcantay team was excellent. In particular, our guide, Cesar Medina, was wonderful. He was excellent. The food on the trek was also very good- tasty and safely prepared. I would like to return to Peru and see Nazca, Ica, Lake Titicaca, and the Amazon (plus Machu Picchu) in a few years when my children are older so that they can appreciate and remember their experience. Thank you so much once again- YOU were wonderful and very patient with me.</p> \r\n<p>All the best,</p> \r\n','Rob,<br />California, USA.\r\n','Rob-california.jpg','Rob and Andrew at Machu Picchu','',485,0,0,NULL,NULL,NULL),(194,1,'Dear Peru For Less','<p>We just got back from a trip of a lifetime to Peru that we booked with with your company. From the minute we got off the plane until we got back on a plane to go home again almost three weeks later, we were impressed daily at the attitude and work ethic of the Peru for Less staff. Everything that was promised was delivered-on time and reliably. Since we were travelling with our two sons (ages 4 and 7), we really depended on you to help us out in these strange new places. I can\'t thank you enough for your quality service and we will be recommending you to our friends and family!</p>\r\n<p>Thanks again JP,</p>\r\n','Robert and Family,<br />Guayaquil, Ecuador.\r\n','Robert-guayaquil.jpg','Robert and Family at Machu Picchu','',513,0,0,NULL,NULL,NULL),(195,1,'Dear Diego,','<p>Many thanks for a seamless, flawless vacation. Your attention to detail and flexibility in the planning process were very much appreciated. I considered many times during our travels that the anxieties of visiting another country were very much reduced by the coordinated efforts made by Peru For Less.  There was also an ideal balance of planned tours and free time, which we appreciated because it allowed us to explore and get out on our own while still having the ability to be guided through the regions that we visited. We couldn\'t have been more pleased with the trip. Thanks again, maybe we\'ll be back in the future to visit the Amazon.</p>\r\n<p>Best Wishes,</p>\r\n','Alex and Chrissy,<br />Pittsburgh, PA.\r\n','Alex-pittsburgh.jpg','Alex and Chrissy at Machu Picchu','',516,0,0,NULL,NULL,NULL),(196,1,'Hi Richard,','<p>I can\'t recommend you guys at Peru For Less highly enough. Ale coordinated most of our trip and after a few weeks of emails and suggestions from Ale and changed itineraries we finalized our plans. <strong>We had planned to do all the bookings ourselves to save money as we have done this in other continents such as Europe and Asia without problems. But, we soon learned that South America is very different and we worked out that it was going to be a lot less stressful and most probably cheaper to book it through your services. This certainly turned out to be true.</strong> In Chile & Bolivia we had made our own direct bookings. However, flights were cancelled, taxis were very expensive, and roads were blocked. This meant a lot of uncertainly and wasted time, with organizing new flights and rearranging hotel bookings etc. We had enough adventure by the time we arrived in Peru. It was such a relief knowing that everything had been organized by this time. </p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Our whole trip in Peru was fantastic.</strong> It is such a diverse place and it was hard to say what impressed us the most - it was a combination of the scenery, history, culture, and the food!! On the whole, we like to do our own thing so your service was ideal for us. <strong>With just over three week\'s holiday, it was so good to arrive at a place knowing we would be picked up and taken to our hotel which was already booked.</strong> Not having to waste so much time finding suitable accommodation or haggle prices with the hotels or taxis, meant we had heaps of extra time to just relax and explore. We would be picked up from the bus or train and taken to our hotel where all our tickets were waiting for us. We had pre-arranged mini-tours and were then left to our own devices for a day or so, depending on where we were. The longer tours were very small in number which was great. You were not stuck with the same group for a traditional tour. If there were any changes to the itinerary we were called at the hotel or messages were left for us to advise of any time changes. At every place, we were allocated a person to whom we could call for any problems. Also, there was an emergency contact if something went astray. </p>\r\n\r\n<p>Highlights of the Peru trip were of course Machu Picchu, Colca Canyon, Lake Titicaca, and Paracas/Nazca. The whole trip was incredible, but probably<strong> our most special memory was staying in the Sacred Valley at Ollantaytambo for three days at Hotel Sauce. What a magical place this was.</strong> We hired a motorbike and toured the region also. Overall, it was hard to say what was the best and everywhere the guides were so good. <strong>Fabricio went out of his way to make our first view of Machu Picchu incredibly special.</strong> Your website is fantastic to go and check out the suggested itineraries and look at the hotels. We had a rough plan of what we wanted to do and this made it so much easier to add a day here or there, and work out suitable transport, which was all organized for us. Again, thank you for helping to make our trip so special. Your service would have to be the best value for money for such a quality service.</p>\r\n','Kind regards,<br/>\r\nKris and David (Byron Bay, Australia)<br/>\r\nTraveled to: Lima, Cusco, Sacred Valley, Machu Picchu, Lake Titicaca, Nazca & Paracas\r\n','Kris-byron.jpg','Kris and David at Machu Picchu','\"Thank you for helping to make our trip so special. Your service would have to be the best value for money for such a quality service.\"',100049,0,0,NULL,'2014-09-10 22:55:09',NULL),(197,1,'Hola! Richard, my friend,','<p>As you know, I have just returned (with your help) from your great country. Peru for Less was everything you promised....and more. I was always picked up on time and the drivers and guides were always friendly, knowledgeable, efficient, and helpful. All the hotels were basic but clean and located well. <strong>Thank you so much for all your help. You always answered my emails containing many questions. I came to trust you and my trust was well placed. </strong>Thanks to you and Pauline for arranging our \'escape\' from Peru during the strike. You arranged a private van with driver and got us safely from Puno to Arequipa! Thanks to PFL we were able to keep our original flight schedule back to the USA. No small miracle under the circumstances!! I have already recommended PFL to several people and will continue to do so. To any readers.....believe me, you can trust Peru for Less and I would recommend this company and its staff to you without reservation.</p>','Best regards,<br/>\r\nBen (USA)<br/>\r\nTraveled to: Lima, Cusco, Machu Picchu, Puno, Arequipa\r\n','Ben-USA.jpg','Ben at Machu Picchu','\"Peru For Less was everything you promised.. and more.\"',100042,0,0,NULL,'2014-09-10 23:08:30',NULL),(198,1,'Dear Peru For Less','<p>We can\'t say enough about how wonderful the entire trip was. It began with our flight being delayed (imagine that). As we stood in the immigration line and eventually retrieved our luggage and as our energy\r\nlevel rapidly drained away from us, we entered the sea of humanity outside the baggage claim with the barrage of taxi, taxi cat calls, it then dawned upon us that it was the middle of the night and we were in a foreign country.  It seemed like a hopeless situation and thoughts of despair hit us and then like a ray of sunshine, we saw the Peru for Less agent holding a sign with our name on it. Everything from that point became the adventure of a lifetime. The highlight was of course Machu Picchu. It was as advertised and even more. The entire journey was a feast of spectacular sights, tastes, and cultural enlightment.  This was a trip like no other we\'ve ever taken. The people of Peru were warm and hospitable and that made the entire journey even more pecial. I would highly recommend Peru for Less for anyone who ever plans on visiting Peru. The staff was very curteous and professional and they exceeded all of our expectations. They were very detail oriented and made us feel very secure and safe throughout the entire trip. Thank you for making a this trip a trip of a lifetime.</p>\r\n','Portia and George,<br />Las Vegas, NV.\r\n','Portia-lasvegas.jpg','Portia and George at Machu Picchu','',534,0,0,NULL,NULL,NULL),(199,1,'Dear Peru For Less','<p>Our trip to Peru was thoroughly enjoyable!  What a wonderfully diverse country! All reservations PFL made for us (transfers, tours, hotels, flights, etc.) were in place and efficiently handled. At one point we needed to call PFL (I believe on a Sunday) over concern that we had only one voucher (for 1 person/1 seat) for two of the Cruz del Sur bus trips. After explaining the situation to Jan, he said Ã¢â?¬ÂI\'ll take care of itÃ¢â?¬Â. Shortly thereafter, we received new vouchers for BOTH of us. The jungle lodge Reserva Amazonica was great! Our accommodations were superlative (I think we had a suite!) and the excursions were interesting.  The entire complex is beautifully laid out. Other hotels we really liked: Casa Andina (Sacred Valley), Sanctuary Lodge (Machu Picchu) and Colca Lodge. The best tour guide was Ã¢â?¬ÂJohnny.Ã¢â?¬Â  He guided our group to the Colca Canyon. He was informative, knowledgeable, had an outgoing personality, and was fluent in English, French, and Spanish. Again, we had a fabulous time and want to thank all of you for making the arrangements and helping us with some of the decision making.</p>','Barbara and Terry,<br />Pennsilvania.\r\n','','','',29,0,0,NULL,NULL,NULL),(200,1,'Diego,','<p>Machu Picchu was awesome. For 25 years I have had my poster of Machu Picchu hanging in my classroom. Its mysteriousness has always beckoned to me. At last, I got to see it and was not disappointed. Our guide was very knowledgeable. She obviously loved her people and her country and enjoyed sharing her knowledge with others. She was also patient with the slower climbers. She left some time for the adventurous one to explore a bit on their own. I loved being able to walk a piece of the Inca Trail. My day in Machu Picchu was a dream come true. Everything else we got to see was just frosting on the cake. In my Spanish textbook there is a three sentence blurb about the Inti Raymi celebration. After being there, I now have a lot more information to share with my students. I\'m certain they will be a lot more students interested in the Incas when I show them the video and other information I got at the Inti Raymi celebration. Our seats were great! I got wonderful photos and videos! You gave good advice about pacing our tours so we would have something interesting to see every day but not so much that we would get too tired to enjoy things or have no free time for shopping.</p>','Christine,<br />Toledo, OH.\r\n','','','',30,0,0,NULL,NULL,NULL),(201,1,'Dear Peru For Less','<p>We had a fantastic time in Peru. Our trip to Machu Picchu was great. From the moment we were picked up in Cusco to our return. Our guide was great and made our trip very memorable. We even had other tourists joining our group as his English was so good and he was so enthusiastic about his job!!<br />\r\nSo thank you and Peru for Less.</p>\r\n<p>Kind regards,</p>\r\n','Laura, <br />Dublin, Ireland.\r\n','','','',31,0,0,NULL,NULL,NULL),(202,1,'Dear Peru For Less','<p>Our family appreciates all the excellent travel assistance you have provided us on our Peru vacation. All of the places we visited (Lima, Arequipa, the Coca Valley, Lake Titicaca, Cusco, Sacred Valley, and of course Machu Picchu) were utterly fascinating and the guides were excellent. When our flight leaving Arequipa was cancelled, Jan promptly rearranged our tour at Lake Titicaca. My family will continue to remember the amazing people and places we visited in Peru. In the future if we visit South America again, we will definitely contact Peru for Less.</p>\r\n<p>Thank You,</p>','Vernon and Family, <br />Thousand Oaks, California.\r\n','Vernon-Thousand.jpg','Vernon and Family at Machu Picchu','',431,0,0,NULL,NULL,NULL),(203,1,'Dear Janjoris,','<p>We, a Dutch family of 12 persons, had a fantastic time in Peru thanks to the program that you arranged for us. Everything was very well arranged from the start at the airport in Lima to the end at the same location. Everywhere drivers/guides were waiting for us and brought us to our hotels. The tour that you had chosen for us was very diversified and spectacular. Starting with the Islas Ballestas, then the famous Nazca Lines, the floating Islands at the Titicaca Lake, the cultural centre of Cuzco, the Lares trekking in the Andes Mountains and finally the famous Machu Picchu. What attracted us especially was the combination of nature (the Andes) and culture (the Incas). This is unique. But we could enjoy these that much, thanks to the perfect organization of our journey. Everywhere enthusiastic local guides were showing us the most interesting places en giving us relevant information. People in the hotels were very friendly, as the people in Peru in general are, and made our stay unforgettable.</p>\r\n<p>Many, many thanks for your efforts,</p> ','Sjaak, <br />Holland.','Sjaak-Holland.jpg','Sjaak and Family in Peru','',430,0,0,NULL,NULL,NULL),(204,1,'Hello again Richard,','<p>I want to send heartfelt thanks from all of us for the exceptional job Peru For Less did on our trip.<strong> With such a long and complicated itinerary, we fully expected a few hitches, but no, it all went like clockwork.</strong> We were highly impressed with your country, your people, your scenery, and above all by the courteous and friendly people we met along the way. <strong>Special praise must go to the guides Javier in Arequipa and Juan Carlos on Cuzco. They were knowledgeable and super friendly and helpful.</strong> Each area we traveled to was so different from the one before and we are glad we made an effort to do it all. The planes, buses, and 1st Class train to Machu Picchu were surprisingly modern and safe, with good service. One of the highlights of the trip was on the 1st Class Train when the waiters put on a fashion show of Alpaca goods and did a Peruvian dance up and down the aisle! Between all of us, we have an incredible amount of photographs to look at now for the rest of our lives, to remind us of the trip of a lifetime. You spoiled us, as we will never find another place to compare with Peru. Thanks again. <strong>All of you at Peru For Less are doing a 5 star job, for 3 star rates.</strong></p>','Many, many regards,<br/>\r\nMaggie and her Group (Rhodes, Greece)<br/>\r\nTraveled to: Lima, Arequipa, Cusco, Machu Picchu\r\n','Maggie-Rhodes.jpg','Maggie and Friends at Machu Picchu','\"We have an incredible amount of photographs.. to remind us of the trip of a lifetime. You spoiled us, as we will never find another place to compare with Peru.\"',100045,0,0,NULL,'2014-09-10 22:55:09',NULL),(205,1,'Dear Peru For Less','<p>I just wanted to write to thank Peru For Less for helping organize our trip to Paracas. Everything went smoothly, even when our driver had to change a tire on the drive back into Lima (a big thank you for that one!). Thanks again for helping us with the tour and transport.</p>','Carl.','Carl.jpg','Carl at Paracas','',428,0,0,NULL,NULL,NULL),(206,1,'Dear Diego,','<p>Javier (Arequipa-Colca), Juan Carlos (Cuzco), and Fabricio (Machu Picchu) were our favorite guides! Thanks, Diego, for your part in making our trip fabulous!</p>','Bill, Laura, Rose, and Tom, <br />Oakland, CA.\r\n','Bill-Oakland.jpg','Javier, Rose and Tom on the Colca Canyon Tour','',427,0,0,NULL,NULL,NULL),(207,1,'Diego,','<p>It is nice to have everything planned out for us. Juan Carlos was \r\nparticularly amazing taking care of the little extras to make the trip special \r\nsuch as dinner reservations and ordering a birthday cake at the hotel for our \r\nnewly minted teenager and going the extra yard on several occasions to insure we \r\naligned on our expectations. Itâ??s not often that tour personnel provide their \r\npersonal cell phone number. The team was particularly helpful as we extended our \r\nvacation one night. Within an hour, we had our hotel room and full \r\ntransportation to the airport. That is comfort that you cannot receive through \r\nan online agency. Thanks to Diego, Juan Carlos and the rest of the Peru for Less \r\nteam!</p><br />','Toby, Karen, Leslie, Allison, and Rachel,<br />Colleyville, TX. ','Toby-Colleyville.jpg','Toby and Family in Cuzco','',470,0,0,NULL,NULL,NULL),(208,1,'Hi Diego,','<p>Everything was wonderful. Machu Picchu was amazing! Thank you for helping us plan this trip. Christina was very helpful and made sure everything was taken care of. She recommended some very good restaurants. She was also very helpful in getting us to Puno after our train was cancelled. Fabracio our guide at Machu Picchu was very knowledgeable and passionate about his job. We especially liked the personalized tour. Josuelo, our driver to Puno is very hard working. We encountered many road blocks on the way but he did not have any trouble getting us to Puno safely. Bruno also was a good guide on our island tours. Thanks for a wonderful vacation!!!</p>','Jetal,<br />Peoria, AZ.','Jetal-Peoria.jpg','Jetal at Machu Picchu','',469,0,0,NULL,NULL,NULL),(210,1,'Dear Wonderful Friends at Peru For Less,','<p>We selected Peru For Less because of your willingness to individualize our trip to Cuzco and Machu Picchu for a great price. Little did we realize just how wise a decision this would turn out to be. Our PFL schedule was based on the arrival of our cruise ship in Lima, but the cruise line cancelled the trip one week out. We quickly rebooked on another cruise originating in Lima and contacted Diego at PFL on Friday. By Monday afternoon, he and his associates had rebooked everything (hotel, tours, air, etc.) for a nominal change fee. <strong>As others have testified, words cannot adequately describe the superb attention and wonderful service we received by the PFL staff in Peru, they exceeded every expectation time and again! </strong>\r\nCuzco: Juan Carlos masterfully coordinated multiple transfers during our time in Cuzco and even met us on his morning off to ensure we hailed a \"safe\" taxi to return us to our hotel. Lalo expertly chauffeured us to/from the airport/train station at all hours of the day and night, shyly offering guided commentary in his limited English. And when there was a change in a tour meeting time, at least four staff members of the Hotel Arqueologo informed us of the new time.</p> \r\n<p><strong>Machu Picchu: Our guide Fabricio was a wonderfully kind and knowledgeable man who enabled us both to enjoy this magnificent wonder.</strong> He was so encouraging and thoughtful as he helped a 60 something woman trek though the ruins. Because he focused on her safety and enjoyment, it allowed her younger companion to thoroughly enjoy the ruins at her own pace. Just as amazing to us was the friendly welcome and assistance we received from the people of Peru who were not associated with PFL: the staff of the left luggage office at the Lima airport; the vendors in the craft markets; the proprietress of the corner store where we purchased bottled water; the waiters at the restaurants; and many, many others. </p>\r\n<p>We cannot thank you enough for our amazing adventure in Peru!! We have already recommended Peru For Less to everyone who has asked us about our vacation. And we will be contacting you soon to arrange a tour in conjunction with a business trip to Chile.</p>\r\n','Janet and Karlene (Texas and Virginia, USA)<br/>\r\nTraveled to: Cusco, Machu Picchu\r\n','Janet-Texas.jpg','Janet and Karlene at Machu Picchu','\"We cannot thank you enough for our amazing adventure in Peru!! We have already recommended Peru For Less to everyone who has asked us about our vacation.\"',100050,0,0,NULL,'2014-09-10 22:55:09',NULL),(211,1,'Dear Peru For Less','<p>Can\'t imagine traveling to South America without all the V.I.P. assistance rendered to my wife and I in making the complicated itinerary actually work, with amazingly smooth connections. Too many things could go wrong as we tall Americans stand out so easily in just dealing with security just as a starter and having a multitude of staff representatives meeting us at airports and train stations, supervising next day\'s tours with special planning meetings and in hosting us with private drivers daily along with private tour guides who all spoke English fluently. All of our friends were particularly scared to death that we were going to San Paulo and Rio de Janeiro, Brazil. But your Rio de Janeiro representative quickly settled that issue ten minutes after checking in at the hotel. He succinctly gave us specific do\'s and don\'ts and we were completely safe during all of our free time as we freely walked, eat (never got sick) and shopped all over both day and night as the fashions in Rio are trend setting. And above all, Peru for Less gave us the best customization possible in making the itinerary so dynamic and fulfilling and all within a minimum amount of visitation time in each city and country. Our trip was incredibly successful in three different countries: Chile, Brazil and Peru. And in every instance, the coordination of details and execution were impeccably accurate regardless of the country visited. Success at every stage was achieved regardless of location, the weather, the country and/or the time of day or night we traveled and were sight-seeing. In summary, my wife and I are veteran international travelers to four continents and we will never travel to South America without Peru For Less for the many reasons cited above.</p>','John,<br />Golden, CO.','John-Golden.jpg','In Rio de Janeiro','',467,0,0,NULL,NULL,NULL),(212,1,'Dear Friends at Peru for Less,','<p>We found Peru For Less thanks to a wonderful recommendation by some Peruvian friends. From the first contact we made with Janjoris van Diepen, we were convinced that we had found the correct destination and the correct people. You instantly understood what we wanted to do, and you came up with a package specially designed to meet our interests and budget! You also were very concerned with preventing any inconveniences throughout our journey. The organization of the trip, hotels, and excursions was impeccable. As soon as we returned to Argentina we started recommending Peru For Less to many friends who are interested in seeing the natural and archaeological wonders of Peru. Thank you Janjoris, thank you Jenny, and thanks to the rest of the Peru For Less team for being so kind. Congratulations on the professionalism and efficiency of your company! We will be seeing you again very soon!</p>','Fernanda and Miguel,<br />Argentina.\r\n','Fernanda-Argentina.jpg','Fernanda and Miguel at Paracas','',496,0,0,NULL,NULL,NULL),(215,1,'Dear Peru For Less','<p>I\'m writing to say a big thank you to you both for organising what turned out to be a fantastic journey !</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Everything went like clock work from transfers and excursions to flights and hotels, the guides and the people we met were great, and the sights we have seen will stay with us for a long time, we tell everyone who asks what a great place Peru is to visit.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>I had made a promise to myself when I was 18 that I would see Machu Picchu before I was 40 and at 6.30 am on my 40th birthday I saw it, thanks to you.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>So again many thanks, and apologies for changing my mind on what must have seemed a daily basis.</p>\r\n','Best Regards<br />Lee','','','',82,0,0,NULL,NULL,NULL),(216,1,'Dear Peru For Less','<p>I just wanted to drop you an email to say thanks very much for the excellent service on our trip to Peru. I\'m extremely impressed with the high quality support we got from Peru for Less from the moment we got off the plane to the moment we arrived the USA. Your representatives were always waiting to meet us on time and with a smile. They were all very professional and ready to help with any problems or questions.  I\'ve never had such an easy time traveling overseas.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Posada Amazones was amazing and Lucho, (our guide), made it a great experience. He constantly went over and above what was expected by organizing extra activities for us and making sure we were taken care of.  I would thoroughly recommend this lodge and all its staff.\r\nThe Inca trail was incredible. Probably the hardest thing I\'ve ever done, but extremely rewarding.  The guide and the porters were amazing and both of my sons and I felt like we\'d achieved something incredible by the end. All of the flight check-ins and train tickets were waiting for us when we needed them. I really can\'t believe how well organized everything was. Thanks again to you and Gavin Breeze for a WONDERFUL holiday!</p>\r\n','Albert','','','',81,0,0,NULL,NULL,NULL),(217,1,'Dear Peru For Less','<p>We had a wonderful time. Your tour guides to the Sacred Valley and Machu Picchu were outstanding. We not only got great views, pictures and experiences but we also came back with a rich history and culture we did not expect to receive. Thank you so much for handling our adventure.  We do plan on coming back to challenge the Inca Trail soon. We would highly recommend Peru for Less to anyone and have already shown pictures to family and friends. Thanks again and we would also like to extend our personal thanks to the tour guides and coordinators.</p>','Doyle &amp; Mary','','','',80,0,0,NULL,NULL,NULL),(218,1,'Dear Peru For Less','<p>Thank you for setting up a fantastic trip for me that included everything I asked to see and do.  I really appreciated the promptness of all pick-ups and drop offs, the quality of the hotels where we stayed, the great tours, the complete Galapagos package and fantastic crew on the Guantanamera yacht, the home stay on Lake Titikaka, the enthusiasm of all the people we came in contact with on the trip and the efficiency of all the people with whom I worked on planning this 24-day trip.  This was a 50 year dream come true for me.  All in all I will go through your company again when I revisit South America.  I will, and have, referred people to your company. Thanks again for all the work that was put into arranging my trip.</p>','Sincerely, <br />Dona\r\n','','','',79,0,0,NULL,NULL,NULL),(220,1,'Dear Peru For Less','<p>Cheryl and I were very satisfied with your service, the accommodations and our tours.  We found our contact in Cusco (Kristina) helpful, hardworking, chock full of useful recommendations and punctual.  She certainly made sure that everything happened for us the way it was supposed to.  The visit to Macu Pichu was incredible and our tour was excellent.  We were part of a small, well matched group and our guide (Janni) was knowledgeable and enthusiastic about his culture. We were impressed that you managed to meet our tight schedule with such a limited notice.  Everything ran seamlessly and we will recommend you to our friends.</p>','Best regards,<br />Phil','','','',77,0,0,NULL,NULL,NULL),(221,1,'Dear Peru For Less','<p>We want to thank you so much for making our trip to Peru one of the most memorable of our lives. We had a wonderful time in each place and had unforgettable experiences in all of them. </p>\r\n\r\n<p>The trip was planned so well. We felt comfortable in all the places we traveled. All the representatives in each place made us feel welcomed and safe. If we had any questions or needs they were there for us. All the guides were passionate about Peru and made us want to learn more about this special country. All of our accommodations were great and we wished we had more time to enjoy some of them at our leisure. We plan to tell everyone who is considering visiting Peru to use Peru for Less to plan their special vacation. Congratulations on a job well done and thank you again for making our trip so special.</p>\r\n','Thank you all for everything.<br />Jim and Dawna','jim-dawna.jpg','','',537,0,0,NULL,NULL,NULL),(222,1,'Dear Peru For Less','<p>I want to start by saying that we had an absolute awesome time!! It was definitely the best trip I\'ve been on, and Machu Picchu is truly the coolest thing I\'ve ever seen! And, I wanted to let you know what a gem Javier was. He was absolutely awesome! When I lost my wallet he went above and beyond to assist me in getting it back (which I did, with everything still in it!). He was friendly, knowledgeable and always available to answer our questions. </p>\r\n \r\n<p>Thank you for all your assistance and hard work in arranging this trip for us and for always being so quick to answer my questions. I really appreciate it, and I know your responsiveness and service made our trip being a huge success. </p>\r\n','Thank you,<br />Shawna &amp; Kris','shawna-kris.jpg','','',538,0,0,NULL,NULL,NULL),(223,1,'Dear Peru For Less','<p>Thank you for making our travels in Peru an exceptional experience.  When we first decided to travel and booked our trip in August, Peru had a large earthquake that made us very nervous - especially since part of our tour was near the earthquake zone.  Your company reacted quickly to find us a suitable alternative for our accommodations and still ensure that we were still able to travel to all the destinations in our tour.  We really appreciated your patience in answering our numerous questions and rearranging our tour to meet our needs.  It was very comforting to see the Peru for Less sign at all our destinations. The accommodations were terrific, the sites and tours well planned and picked and the entire trip was wonderful. </p>\r\n \r\n<p>Finally, we appreciated meeting you, Christina and Javier for lunch - a personal touch we won\'t forget.  We could not believe that Javier would also \"follow us\" to Cusco to check on us midway through the tour.  That level of service goes beyond anyone\'s expectations!  Great Job; we will definitely recommend your company and services to anyone thinking of traveling to Peru!</p>\r\n','Joni &amp; Gwen','joni-gwen.jpg','','',539,0,0,NULL,NULL,NULL),(224,1,'Dear Peru For Less','<p>Let me begin by saying THANK YOU!!!</p>\r\n<p>Though I have traveled around the world with my sons (over 27 countries), this was the first trip when it was just the 3 of us, so it was a very special trip, indeed. My experience with Peru For Less was enjoyable from the onset. <strong>Not only were you and Diego prompt and precise in your email communications with me, your company worked effortlessly with me to customize this very special trip.</p>\r\n<p>Your prices are more than reasonable and your methods of payment were simple, as well as assured.</strong> As a traveler, I am more than aware of how even the most experienced traveler can get ripped off. And though I had researched your company, I admit I still harbored a fear that things may not turn out the way I had planned them with your company. After arriving in Peru, those fears were put to rest time and time again.</p>\r\n<p>Cristina was amazing! To see her smiling face greet us in Cuzco was a welcome sight. The driver, Carlos, was professional, pleasant, prompt and a safe driver. Cristina was enjoyable, personable, and completely in control of each event. Maria (our guide for the Sacred Valley) and our driver were also prompt in pick-up services and very personable and flexible, as well as enjoyable during our full-day excursion through the Sacred Valley which included the buffet lunch. Lunch, by the way, was amazing. Not just the food, but the restaurant! Wow! What an experience!</p>\r\n<p>We were then picked up for our train ride to Machu Picchu with no problems. I can\'t tell you how important that was. Such an early pick-up, yet there we were, at the station and on our way.<strong> Fabricio, our guide in Machu Picchu, was amazing!</strong> Like the rest of your people, he too was prompt and provided another unforgettable experience. We really enjoyed him.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Cristina was, again, a delight to see when she and Carlos took us back to the airport when we had to leave Cuzco to head back for Lima. She escorted us as far as she could until she knew we were okay to continue on with our flight. She then made sure our ride was ready for us back in Lima to take us to the hotel you arranged for us. Then, to our final satisfaction, your driver delivered us to the international airport the next morning to return us back to the States.</p>\r\n<p>Without Peru For Less, I am convinced that this very special trip would not have been NEARLY as wonderful as it was. Thank you for making this a truly unforgettable experience for my sons and for me. Your services were so exemplary; I have already referred you to at least two of my friends who were waiting to see how it worked out for me.</p>\r\n<p>Thank you, thank you, thank you! This trip will stand out as a favorite because of you!</p>\r\n<p>With much appreciation,</p>\r\n','Vetha<br/>\r\nTraveled to: Cusco, Sacred Valley, Machu Picchu\r\n','vetha-pierce.jpg','','\"Without Peru For Less, I am convinced that this very special trip would not have been NEARLY as wonderful as it was. Thank you for making this a truly unforgettable experience..\"',100041,0,0,NULL,'2014-09-10 23:08:30',NULL),(225,1,'Dear Peru For Less','<p>Five weeks in South America and we joke that we received \"more for less.\" Our first online contact was with Gavin Breeze who patiently answered innumerable questions and helped us organize our \"own detailed and unique itinerary\" to meet our interests, pace and budget to suit our group of five people, all in their sixties. We selected our accommodations (based on our price range) from an electronic shortlist provided by Peru for Less. The hotel names were linked to websites so we could actually see the possibilities ahead of time. Our accommodations turned out to be excellent throughout the trip. From hotels, to flight purchases, and to arrangements for the local tours, Gavin\'s insights gave us good advice and choices. Our questions were always promptly and thoroughly answered. This service was SO much better than buying a packaged tour!!!</p>\r\n\r\n<p>We also appreciated the ground staff arranged by Peru for Less in the five different countries (Brazil, Argentina, Chile, Peru, and Ecuador) we visited, who, without fail, arranged for us to meet and depart on eleven separate flights at all hours of the day. Having personal transfers from airports to hotels (and vice versa) and to be picked up and delivered at our hotels before and after tours took so much of the stress and uncertainty out of the trip. This service allowed us to really enjoy the sights and not worry about the logistics of getting here and there. We were provided with often exceptional guides for specified tours that always met or exceeded expectations. We had a good balance of tours on our own and those when we were merged with larger groups. We always appreciated the flexibility and personal touch, AND all at reasonable price. We highly recommend Peru for Less and plaudits to Gavin who easily earned his beer when we met up with him in Lima.\" </p>\r\n','Diane and Jim<br /> Victoria, BC Canada','diane-jimanderson.jpg','','',541,0,0,NULL,NULL,NULL),(226,1,'Dear Peru For Less','<p>Yes, I loved Peru! Your airlines and trains put the United States to shame. They were professional, polite, and they even served food- something that seldom happens on transportation in the US. People were friendly and proud to show us their beautiful country. I lost my passport before even leaving the Lima airport but thanks to the lady that picked us up I got it back - she remembered seeing another travel agent find it, and due to her alertness, our trip did not turn into a disaster. Our guides were great- not a single problem. We\'re talking about going back next year and will certainly book through Peru for Less. Your services could not have been better.</p>','Barbara<br />Tallahassee, FL','barbara-tallahassee.jpg','','',542,0,0,NULL,NULL,NULL),(227,1,'Dear Peru For Less','<p>What an incredible time we had! One of our best trips ever! It even exceeded our expectations. The trip went so smoothly, thanks to Peru For Less. We will highly recommend you to others. We are already thinking about our next trip to South America and hope you will help us again. Please thank Juan Pablo in Lima and Cristina in Cuzco for us, too. </p>','Most Sincerely,<br />Robyn','robyn.jpg','','',543,0,0,NULL,NULL,NULL),(228,1,'Dear Peru For Less','<p>Thanks for all of the arrangements.  I had a wonderful time in Peru, I wished the trip was 6 months not 3 weeks.  The highlight was definitely the Inca Trail hike and the amazing scenery along the way.  The group was a lot of fun and the guide was really cool and energetic.  </p>\r\n \r\n<p>I would definitely do it a little more leisurely next time, cramming in the sightseeing around Cusco and then the Inca Trail immediately after was pretty exhausting, but glad I did it.  Andrea was very helpful as well in Cusco.  I really wasn\'t looking for a guided tour of everything but my lack of Spanish skills definitely required that I do so for some of it, so I think it worked out well- combination of guides with enough time spent on my own. </p>\r\n \r\n<p>Anyway, you have a beautiful country full of wonderful people and should be very proud.  Thanks for everything.  I would definitely like to visit again sometime.</p>\r\n','Vinay','vinay.jpg','','',544,0,0,NULL,NULL,NULL),(229,1,'Dear Peru For Less','<p>We want to thank you for making our trip to Peru a wonderful experience.  Your recommendations for tours were exactly what we hoped they would be.  Christina was the best!  She had every detail taken care of and we were met on time, every time, by people who made our tours come to life with information and personal insight into local customs and lifestyles as well as the history of the area.</p>\r\n \r\n<p>We\'ll share our pictures and memories with family and friends, along with our recommendation that anyone who visits the area should definitely contact Peru for Less to make their trip a spectacular one.</p>\r\n','Rich and Cathy <br />Colorado, USA','rich-cathy.jpg','','',545,0,0,NULL,NULL,NULL),(230,1,'Dear Peru For Less','<p>Our recent trip to Peru was magical, challenging, and fun. We stayed for \r\nten days in your beautiful country and had a wonderful experience \r\nmeeting people, enjoying excellent food, hiking the Inca Trail, and \r\nsucceeding in the mental and physical challenge of reaching the \r\nmagnificent Machu Picchu. </p>\r\n\r\n<p>Along the way, we received a warm welcome from everyone we met, and \r\nyour excellent arrangements made us feel safe, relaxed, and continually \r\nintrigued by your amazing history and culture. As Turkish and Egyptian \r\ntravelers, we come from equally rich and magical civilizations, but the \r\nsplendor of Peru is a testament to the beauty of your land and its \r\npeople.</p>\r\n','Sherine and Esin<br />Atlanta, GA','sherine-esin.jpg','','',546,0,0,NULL,NULL,NULL),(231,1,'Dear Peru For Less','<p>Thank you so much for an amazing, memorable trip... I can\'t say enough about how great it was and how helpful the agents were in arranging everything. Even after a delayed flight that resulted in my late arrival, Peru For Less worked hard to rearrange everything at the last moment to make sure I got to see everything I wanted. The country is beautiful, and the tours were interesting and informative (my favorite was Machu Picchu)!  I\'m only sorry I couldn\'t stay longer, but this gives me all the more reason to come back, so don\'t be surprised if you see me booking another trip with you!  </p>','Thanks so much again, <br />Cheryl,<br />New York, USA','','','',85,0,0,NULL,NULL,NULL),(232,1,'Dear Rylee,','<p>Yes I am back from the trip and I have high praise for the service I received. The schedule and service provided by Peru For Less made the trip very enjoyable and stress free. The coordinators communicated well and everything was provided as stated. I would certainly use Peru for Less again should I find the opportunity. I did love Cuzco and the ruins were spectacular. The Sacred Valley tour and education about the agriculture and how people live in the area was what most interested me.</p>','Regards,<br />JoAnn,<br />Washington, USA','','','',84,0,0,NULL,NULL,NULL),(233,1,'Hi Rylee','<p>We had a wonderful day rafting on an upper tributary to the Urubamba River on March 24. Our guide, Aaron, was terrific! He skillfully maneuvered us through class 3 rapids (very exciting!), speaks excellent English, and has a wonderful sense of humor. Also, the lunch at the end of our 2-hour rafting trip was excellent. All went well and we would strongly recommend Peru For Less to anyone seeking a safe, economical and well-organized adventure in Peru. Overall, our two weeks in Peru went well enough to entice us back someday. </p>\r\n<p>Thank you for setting up a great day on the river!</p>','Bill &amp; Polly,<br />Montana, USA','','','',83,0,0,NULL,NULL,NULL),(234,1,'Hi to all in Peru For Less,','<p>Coming from Singapore, after flying for more than 34 hours, I am very grateful that I have chosen the correct travel agent for my 15-day Peru trip.</p>\r\n<p><strong>The itinerary had given my dad and I ample time to rest and acclimatize to the high altitude. The tours were evenly spread out, with sufficient free time for us to explore all the gorgeous cities on our own.</strong> We met a number of tourists on the way, and heard their complaints on canceled tours due to delay as their package was very tight. A British couple was very envious of our itinerary when I showed it to them, and they blamed themselves for not doing enough homework. It reminded me of a friend who signed up with a prestigious travel agent last year with her hubby and paid a huge sum to tour Peru and Chile. They had her name wrong on all internal flights within Peru which caused unnecessary delays, and they had tour guides that either did not appear on time or totally forgot about them. She spent quite a sum to call the travel agent numerous times to resolve the issues encountered on her way. I am fortunate that all these never happened to me. The local guides were always there on time, if not, earlier.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Honestly, <strong>the arrangement done by Peru For Less far exceeded my expectation, including the mode of transportation. This shows how thoughtful you were in deriving the itinerary for your clients.</strong> I appreciate all your help beginning with the day I contacted you, and after a reply from Juan, the rest is history.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>The local travel guides were fabulous and professional.</strong> There are a few which I would like to commend specifically. Both the tour guide and driver which brought us to Colca Canyon (2 days) were very helpful and attentive, and we had great fun along the way. The local/tour guide and driver in Lima were simply wonderful and entertaining. The guide, Edgar, explained very clearly the history of Lima, and he did not hesitate to explain again if necessary, a very patient person indeed. The driver in Lima, despite having communication difficulties, is the most hardworking and helpful guy I had ever seen, and I am very impressed by his passion and work attitude.</p>\r\n<p>Not forgetting Juan and Carolina for their patience and help in the initial stage, especially Juan for his quick response to my ever-changing requests.</p>\r\n<p>Overall, the experience was awesome and memorable, and I am very pleased with the arrangement done by Peru For Less. <strong>I will definitely encourage my friends here in South East Asia to sign up with Peru For Less if they were to travel to South America.</strong> Now, my next question is, when should I sign up with you again for my trip to Argentina or Chile?</p>\r\n<p>Once again, thanks for everything!</p>\r\n','Soon Yoong (Singapore)<br/>\r\nTraveled to: Lima, Arequipa, Cusco, Machu Picchu\r\n','soon-yoong-kit.jpg','','\"The experience was awesome and memorable, and I am very pleased with the arrangement done by Peru For Less.\"',100035,0,0,NULL,'2014-09-10 22:55:10',NULL),(235,1,'Dear Peru For Less','<p>We had a great time in Peru and thanks very much for all the help we got from PFL. \r\nIt requires a lot of trust when booking holiday travels with someone on the other side of the world over the Internet. You and Liz always responded to my questions very quickly and with a lot of information. \r\nWhile we were in Peru, everything was well organized. The pick-ups were always on time, the people from PFL were always polite and very friendly. \r\nI can\'t believe you actually sent someone to pick us up from the train station and walked us to the bus station at Machu Picchu - It was just a 1 or 2 minute walk. But this arrangement helped us avoid the crowd arriving with us on the same train and we got on the first bus without queuing at all. \r\nWe really enjoyed the service provided by PFL, you were very flexible and attentive to details. \r\nAgain, thanks very much and I am looking forward to book my next holiday in South America again with you. </p>\r\n','Regards,<br />Deng &amp; Xin','deng-xin.jpg','','',554,0,0,NULL,NULL,NULL),(236,1,'Dear Peru For Less','<p>Thank you for all of your help in planning our adventure in Peru!  </p>\r\n\r\n<p>Having a guide to interpret the ruins and point out local flora and fauna is invaluable and adds so much value to the tour!  Our guide, Sylvia, was wonderful on the hike to Machu Picchu and during the tour to the ruins the second day.  </p>\r\n\r\n<p>Maria and Juan Carlos were great guides on the Sacred Valley tour and the stop at Awana Kancha Living Museum was certainly a pleasant surprise for us!  </p>\r\n\r\n<p>The hostel rooms in Cusco were comfortable and clean, but we were impressed with the Rumi Wasi at Aguas Calientes - it surpassed our expectations!  After a hot and difficult day climbing Machu Picchu, it was nice to have such a comfortable place to rest!</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Again, thank you for helping us plan a once in a lifetime memory!  Friends here at home are jealous of our experience and we are recommending your services to everyone.</p>\r\n','Vince and Bob<br />Orlando, FL','vince-bob.jpg','','',553,0,0,NULL,NULL,NULL),(237,1,'Dear Peru For Less','<p>We can\'t thank you enough for the wonderful four days in Peru you organized for us. We were a little nervous leaving our cruise ship and casting ourselves adrift in an unknown country but the staff at Peru For Less were extremely competent. The hotel you chose for us in Cusco was the best hotel I have ever stayed in, (Libertador) Cusco is a lovely fascinating place and our guide was excellent. We felt we were being looked after by a true Inca! </p>\r\n\r\n<p>I wish we could have stayed longer. The train ride to Aguas Calientes is unforgettable and Machu Picchu of course is just amazing, how did they build it? I don\'t believe we could do it even now with all our technology. Our guide at the Inca town was excellent and very knowledgeable. Again, another day there would have been good but we had to catch up with our ship. Cusco is a lovely fascinating place and our guide was excellent. We felt we were being looked after by a true Inca! </p>\r\n\r\n\r\n<p>We will recommend Peru For Less to all our friends.</p>\r\n','Thanks again,<br />Graham and Joan, Derby UK','graham-joan.jpg','','',552,0,0,NULL,NULL,NULL),(238,1,'Dear Peru For Less','<p>Thanks a million for arranging the Peru trip for my friend and I. The schedule was spotless. And your price is the best one we can get amongst all of the travel agencies on the internet. Thanks to Liz Boyd - Our Travel Coordinator, who made sure that we got first class treatments in every place we visited. I would recommend your service to anyone who is interested in visiting Peru. </p>','Zhi','zhi.jpg','','',551,0,0,NULL,NULL,NULL),(239,1,'Dear Peru For Less','<p>Thank you for making our travels in Peru an exceptional experience.  When we first decided to travel and booked our trip, Peru had just had a large earthquake that made us very nervous - especially since part of our tour was near the earthquake zone.  Your company reacted quickly to find us a suitable alternative for our accommodations and ensure that we were still able to travel to all the destinations in our tour.  We really appreciated your patience in answering our numerous questions and rearranging our tour to meet our needs.  It was very comforting to see the Peru for Less sign at all our destinations. The accommodations were terrific, the sites and tours well planned and picked and the entire trip was wonderful. </p>\r\n \r\n<p>Finally, we appreciated meeting you in Lima , and Christina and Javier for lunch in Cusco - a personal touch we won\'t forget.  We could not believe that Javier would even \"follow us\" to Cusco to check on us midway through the tour.  That level of service goes beyond anyone\'s expectations!</p>\r\n \r\n<p>Great Job; we will definitely recommend your company and services to anyone thinking of traveling to Peru!</p>\r\n','Gwen <br />Canada','gwen-will.jpg','','',550,0,0,NULL,NULL,NULL),(240,1,'Dear Peru For Less',' <p>Wanted to take this moment to specially thank Andrea Martinez in Cuzco for all of her hard work in making my trip go so smoothly. I was in Cuzco for the Machu Pichu tour and unfortunately the massive Inca Strike occurred which pretty much shut down the whole area. However, Andrea and her crew worked so hard and diligently to make alternative arrangements to get me to Machu Pichu. Had it not been for them, I would have never gotten to Machu Pichu and my trip would have been ruined. But it turned out to be one of the most awesome travel experiences I\'ve ever had. Thank you sooooooo much!</p>','Al','Al.jpg','','',549,0,0,NULL,NULL,NULL),(241,1,'Dear Peru For Less','<p>Thank you very much for your excellent job!  We were really surprised with the quality of your service. All our tour guides were superb. \r\nSpecial thanks to Christina from Cuzco for her help and smiling face. Our tour included Lima, Nazca, Colca Canyon, Areguipa, Cuzco and Machu Picchu.\r\nAll our hotels were great. We choose 3 star hotels with the exception of Arequipa where we stayed in the centrally located Sonesta Posada. On our way back we booked a hotel in Lima for \"day use\" which helped us stretch our legs before the long flight back home. We used long distance bus twice (from Lima to Nazca and from Nazca to Arequipa) and were surprised with the level of comfort and service.\r\nPeru is a wonderful country and with your help we were ably to fully enjoy it. </p>\r\n\r\n<p>Thanks again and we hope to see you soon.</p>\r\n','Ewa and Barbara<br />Poland/USA','ewa-barbara.jpg','','',548,0,0,NULL,NULL,NULL),(242,1,'Dear Peru For Less','<p>Everything was perfect. We can\'t really find the right words. It was an enormous experience for us. Norway is a rich country with all kind of regulations. Peru is for us something quite different from what we meet in Europe. All the historic sites and the nature, we have never seen anything like it. Our guide in Cusco, Juan Carlos, was an amazing person with enormous knowledge.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Thank you very much for all Peru For Less did for us.</p>\r\n','Reidunn and Geir,<br />Norway','reidunn-geir.jpg','','',547,0,0,NULL,NULL,NULL),(243,1,'Dear Peru For Less','<p>We had a great trip. First we enjoyed the country, the people, and the places we visited. \r\nWe wish we had more time to spend there. We were truly impressed by the punctuality of the pick-ups, \r\nthe cleanliness and good organization in the hotels, and generally with everything. The guides were \r\nhelpful, friendly and knowledgeable. We enjoyed the local food, and chicha morada. Lake Titicaca was \r\ntruly spectacular. The Salcantay Trail was well organized, the food was good, and campsites were good,\r\n and the cooks and the guide took good care of all of us. Thanks for the great trip.</p>','Regards,<br />Armin <br />Hong Kong.','','','',86,0,0,NULL,NULL,NULL),(244,1,'Dear Peru For Less','<p>We got back to New York today. Overall the trip was great, and we must thank you for all your help.\r\n Everything planned by you has been great and overall all the locations were beautiful. We loved the \r\nManu trip change you made; it went through without any hiccups. Most of the guides were good, and I \r\nmust highlight that Maria, our guide for Sacred Valley was outstanding.</p>','Thank you,<br />Ritvik<br />NY, USA.','','','',87,0,0,NULL,NULL,NULL),(245,1,'Richard,','<p>I can honestly tell you that we had the most wonderful honeymoon in history thanks to you and \r\nPeru For Less!  It\'s no wonder you couldn\'t get a hold of us because we were constantly on a new \r\nadventure. The Amazon jungle was nothing short of amazing and I would very much like to go back \r\nthere again. Cristina in Cuzco was wonderful and took good care of us. I was worried for nothing \r\nbecause the trip went off without a hitch.  All transfers were there right on time, we loved our hotels \r\nand we have gained so many memories that I had to write them down just to be able to remember \r\nthem all!  Kate & Gerry are world travelers and said that this was the best vacation that they had ever \r\nhad..</p>\r\n<p>THANK YOU PERU FOR LESS - RICHARD, CAROLINA, LIZ AND NICOLA!!!</p>\r\n<p>We will definitely recommend this company and their outstanding staff to anyone who will listen!</p>','Laurie, David, Kate &amp; Gerry<br />Phoenix, AZ.','','','',88,0,0,NULL,NULL,NULL),(246,1,'Dear Peru For Less','<p>Our trip was awesome!!! Suzi and I were impressed by all the representatives of Peru For Less. \r\nEveryone was professional, friendly and on time. Our hotels were great. The guides were so \r\nknowledgeable. I have already recommended your company to some co-workers who are thinking \r\nabout doing a trip to Peru. If I go again, I will arrange the trip with you. Thanks for making the \r\nexperience a memorable one</p>','Sincerely, <br />Jan<br />USA.','','','',89,0,0,NULL,NULL,NULL),(247,1,'Dear Peru For Less','<p>Everything went well. The tour was very well organized. I am amazed at the personalized care \r\nyour group provided us, especially the Machu Picchu hike and tour. Having a personal guide made \r\nall the difference. Marco was simply great. The way everyone took care of things when we almost \r\nmissed our flight from Arequipa to Cuzco was excellent. We were able to make last minute changes \r\nin the itinerary at a couple of places. I have already recommended Peru For Less to most of my \r\ncolleagues at work. I am sure you will hear soon from them</p>','Once again thanks for everything,<br />Ritu <br />California, USA.','','','',90,0,0,NULL,NULL,NULL),(248,1,'Dear Peru For Less','<p>My husband, Jan, and I returned late Saturday night from a wonderful trip to Cuzco, Machu Picchu, \r\nand Lake Sandoval Lodge.</p>\r\n<p>Everything went smoothly and the Peru For Less staff was always there to transfer us to our next \r\ndestination----as well as being very courteous and helpful.  We were very pleased and impressed, \r\nespecially when we wanted to change plans for our final day in Lima.  Edgar was planning to give us a \r\ncity and museum tour, but we were \"out of gas\" and wanted something more casual and relaxing.  He \r\nwas fantastic about making sure we spent the time doing what we wanted, which was to go to a \r\nwetlands area south of town to see some birds.  Then we just wanted to relax in some nice place for \r\ndrinks and dinner.  The restaurant he recommended along the coast couldn\'t have been more \r\nperfect!  Muchas gracias for all of that!</p>\r\n<p>Again, we thank you and your staff for a wonderful trip. We will highly recommend your company \r\nto our friends.</p>\r\n<p>Fondly,</p>','Sincerely, <br />Patti <br />Everett, WA.','','','',91,0,0,NULL,NULL,NULL),(249,1,'Dear Peru For Less','<p>We had a blast.  In fact, just today I gave your name and e-mail to friends who are interested in \r\na similar trip next year.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>We loved Peru.  We were especially pleased with our guide, Chris.  He was experienced, capable, \r\nfriendly, helpful, professional and kind.  We love him!  The trail was spectacular - I wasn\'t prepared for \r\nthe sheer beauty of your country.  We live in the Rocky Mountains, but your mountains are even more \r\nbeautiful.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>We loved Cusco.  What a vibrant, beautiful, friendly and historic city.  The city tour was very \r\neducational and just the perfect thing to do on our first day there.  The Sacred Valley tour was a lot \r\nof fun and we enjoyed all the climbing around.</p>\r\n\r\n\r\n<p>Finally, Lake Titicaca was breathtaking.  The floating islands are so unusual and we really enjoyed \r\nvisiting them. Taquile is one of the prettiest places I have ever seen.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>We found Peruvians to be helpful, friendly, and very proud of their country (as they should be).</p>\r\n\r\n<p>We were always met on time and all the arrangements were perfect.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>I have nothing but compliments for you and Peru for Less.  I would highly recommend your \r\nservices to anyone.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Thank you for helping us with our trip of a lifetime!</p>\r\n','Leslie, <br />Denver, CO.','','','',92,0,0,NULL,NULL,NULL),(250,1,'Dear Peru For Less','<p>We had a wonderful time.  Thank you for your efforts in making our trip stress free.  \r\nWe were very impressed with our tour guides and probably would not have had such a good time \r\nwithout them.  Our whitewater rafting trip was great and our guide was truly entertaining.  The lunch \r\nprovided was also delicious.  Our guide to Sacred Valley (Juan Carlos) was incredibly knowledgeable \r\nabout Incan culture and made the experience not only exciting but very educational.  \r\nOur two day trek on the Inca trail was amazing.  The hike was strenuous but the Andes Mountains \r\nwere breathtaking. When we finally reached Machu Picchu, we were overwhelmed by its beauty and \r\ncould not have imagined a better way to reach it than by making the trek along the Inca trail. \r\nOur trip to Peru was perhaps one of the best vacations of our lives.  Thank you again for making it \r\nsuch a successful trip.</p>','All the best,<br />Elizabeth <br />NY, USA.','eliza-gonza.jpg','Elizabeth at Machu Picchu','',556,0,0,NULL,NULL,NULL),(251,1,'Dear Peru For Less','<p>The personalized service was unbelievable!  The day we went to Machu Picchu, we were picked \r\nup from our hotel and taken to the bus station, where Rachel and I were the only guests on the ride \r\nto the train station.  We were escorted to the train station and were immediately greeted when we \r\ngot off the train by another guide, who escorted us from the train station to the bus station.  \r\nWe were again immediately greeted by a guide when we arrived at Machu Picchu.  \r\nWe were completely surprised and thrilled to learn the two of us had a private guide, who was \r\nincredibly knowledgeable!  We were blown away by Andrea\'s professionalism and organization \r\nthroughout our stay in Peru and everyone we met was friendly and professional.</p>','Thanks again for arranging an amazing trip!<br />Janet and Rachel <br />Minneapolis, MN.','janet-paulson.jpg','Janet Paulson and Rachel DeHaan at Machu Picchu','',557,0,0,NULL,NULL,NULL),(252,1,'Dear PFL,','<p>We just returned from our trip to Peru and I wanted to write while the memories are still fresh. \r\nPFL was great, punctual, efficient and very helpful. Andrea laid out the plans and answered all our \r\nquestions.<br />The guides, Juan Carlos, Mary and Fabricio were all excellent and provided \r\nwonderful insight. The Picoaga was very nice, well located and good rooms. The El Pueblo in Agua \r\nCalientes was truly outstanding and it was a joy to stay there. Everything worked out beautifully \r\nand we had two glorious sunny days at Machu Picchu. You exceeded our expectations in every way \r\nand I would not hesitate to recommend your company to anyone traveling to Peru.</p>','Thanks again,<br />Jeff <br />Ann Arbor, MI.','jeff-stross.jpg','Jeff Stross at Machu Picchu','',558,0,0,NULL,NULL,NULL),(253,1,'Dear Ric,','<p>Peru for Less was so helpful in coordinating many aspects of our latest trip Chile and Peru that \r\nwe plan to use them again when we take 2 groups down to Chile on a mission trip. They can find good \r\ndeals, routes, and make traveling easy. THANKS SO MUCH. Service is the key and PFL took care of \r\neverything.</p>','Denny <br />USA.','denny-nooner.jpg','Denny Nooner at Machu Picchu','',559,0,0,NULL,NULL,NULL),(254,1,'Dear Peru For Less','<p>All went well. The young lady, from Romania, in Cusco was excellent. Fabricio in Machu Picchu \r\nwas very good. We enjoyed the trip very much.</p>','Thanks,<br />Bob<br />California, USA.','bob-california.jpg','Bob at Machu Picchu','',560,0,0,NULL,NULL,NULL),(255,1,'Dear Peru For Less','<p>Our Peru For Less trip was incredible and we can\'t stop talking about it. It was so nice to have \r\nall of the little details taken care of and I have to honestly say that there are so many elements that \r\nwe would not have been able to arrange ourselves. It would have taken months to plan this trip had \r\nwe tried to do it ourselves. We loved all of our guides; their passion for their country as well as their \r\nhistory is very apparent. We enjoyed the amounts of scheduled tours, but had ample free time to \r\nshop or explore on our own. Thank you again for what was a once in a lifetime trip! We will definitely \r\nplan another trip through Peru for Less.</p>','Thanks,<br />Kathy, Mary, and Joseph <br />Dallas, TX.','kathy-stevenson.jpg','Kathy Stevenson, Mary Stevenson, and Joseph Norman','',561,0,0,NULL,NULL,NULL),(256,1,'Dear PFL,','<p>Thank you Peru for Less for an impeccable organization on our trip to Cuzco as well as our trip \r\nto Argentina and Uruguay last year!</p>','Martha and Arnaldo <br />Lima, Peru.','arnaldo-leon.jpg','Martha and Arnaldo Leon at Machu Picchu','',562,0,0,NULL,NULL,NULL),(257,1,'Dear Peru For Less','<p>Thank you so much for an incredible trip to Peru. We got off to a rough start because of airline cancellations which got us in almost a full day later than originally planned, but thank goodness we were able to call you to put our minds at ease and reorganize our itinerary. <strong>I don\'t know what we would have done had we tried to book everything on our own.</strong> It was such a relief to finally get to Peru because there was someone to meet us everywhere we went and everyone was perfectly on time. Andrea from your Cusco office was so friendly and she even had our boarding passes printed out for us for our return flight to Lima.<strong> The guided trips were great because the groups were very small and we were able to get to know the guides as if we were on a private tour.</strong> Of course the country itself is beautiful and the people are super friendly. Machu Picchu and the Sacred Valley are just incredible and we learned so much from our guides.<strong> We definitely plan to come back someday and we would highly recommend Peru For Less to anybody planning on making the trip!</strong></p>\r\n<p>Thanks again!</p>\r\n','Brett and Ashley (Houston, TX)<br/>\r\nTraveled to: Cusco, Sacred Valley, Machu Picchu\r\n','brett-ashley.jpg','Brett and Ashley at Machu Picchu','\"We got off to a rough start because of airline cancellations which got us in almost a full day later than originally planned, but thank goodness we were able to call you to put our minds at ease and reorganize our itinerary.\"',100031,0,0,NULL,'2014-09-10 22:55:10',NULL),(258,1,'Dear Peru For Less','<p>Our trip was great! Thanks again for helping us set everything up. The tour guides were \r\namazingly informative and Andrea was very helpful. Cuzco and the surrounding area were so \r\nbeautiful and the weather was perfect! We will definitely recommend Peru For Less to anyone we \r\nknow traveling to Peru.</p>','Evy <br />Nipomo, CA.','evy-godwin.jpg','Evy Godwin at Machu Picchu','',564,0,0,NULL,NULL,NULL),(259,1,'Dear Peru For Less','<p>We are back from our trip I have to say the Special 8: World Wonder trip was truly amazing; \r\nI would do it over again.  I would like to thank you and the team at Argentina For Less and \r\nPeru For Less for making our vacation so perfect. In each city someone was at the airport waiting \r\nfor us with a smile and was excited to make sure that we were in good hands. We did not run into \r\nany problems at all! I will recommend you and use you for another tour in the future.</p>','Thanks again,<br />Barbara and Diego <br />Miami, FL.','barbara-diego-beltran.jpg','Barbara and Diego Beltran al Cuzco','',565,0,0,NULL,NULL,NULL),(260,1,'Dear Peru For Less','<p>Our trip to Peru was by far the best foreign travel experience I\'ve ever had! To begin, Aimee was \r\nan angel to help plan the two week trip...she carefully considered our style, dreams, and goals for the \r\ntrip...and it all manifested in our extensive personal itinerary. From the moment we arrived in Lima \r\nuntil we left for home, Peru For Less handled every detail of our journey. It was the most stress-free \r\nforeign travel possible. Transfers to and from hotels, tours, planes, and trains were fantastic...always \r\nin the best vehicles on the road and with excellent drivers. Above all, we were delighted with our \r\nknowledgeable guides - especially Marlene on our Sacred Valley private tour, Juan Carlos on our \r\nCusco City & Ruins tour, and Omar on our Pachacamac private tour. Their understanding and ability \r\nto communicate the fullness of the Incan civilization was phenomenal. I\'m recommending \r\nPeru For Less to everyone I know!</p>','Anne <br />Kerrville, TX.','anne-schneider.jpg','Anne Schneider at Lake Titicaca','',566,0,0,NULL,NULL,NULL),(261,1,'Dear Peru For Less','<p>First off I would like to say our encounter with the Peru For Less was excellent from the very beginning. I had a great number of questions and concerns that you always answered promptly and with the right amount of detail.</p>\r\n<p>I was very pleased with the itinerary we worked out together to include all the elements we were keen on-it meant getting a little creative but you were always game and cooperative. <strong>I was very impressed with the pricing of the whole package. I had done my homework and thought your program was going to provide me with the best value and after the trip was over I was even more certain of it.</strong></p>\r\n\r\n\r\n<p>After we had made our initial reservations with you, we were assigned an operations specialist to make all the bookings and confirm all the tours. We had the great pleasure of having logistics handled by Carolina and then Liz. Their professionalism and follow through was fantastic.<strong> Any question - and I had plenty - was answered promptly and courteously.</strong></p>\r\n\r\n\r\n<p>We felt like every detail was handled. We were met at every destination and the details for that day were explained. We loved that we had a driver plus an English speaking guide. Private tours really enhanced our trip, it enabled us to ask a lot of questions and really focus on our areas of interest. Javier was great; he made sure we knew what was planned every step of the way. We especially loved having Juan Carlos as a guide for Sacred Valley. We learned so much from him, it was incredible.</p>\r\n\r\n\r\n<p>Marialuz did a great job explaining all the history of Cuzco, Sacsayhuaman and Koricancha. One of the things we liked best was the learning about the Cuzco School of Art - seeing the Andean influences in artwork at the cathedral.</p>\r\n<p>Machu Picchu was beyond words. So majestic and awe inspiring seeing it in person. Gilbert was a very congenial guide.</p>\r\n<p>Edgar was great when we toured Lima with him-he went way above and beyond what we expected, we learned so much.</p>\r\n<p>The tours were all fantastic. Your staff is so knowledgeable; the education and backgrounds of our guides was fantastic. We were treated so well.</p>\r\n<p><strong>The Peru For Less personnel were great! From the drivers to the coordinators we felt like we were being welcomed into their homes.</strong></p>\r\n<p>The food included at the hotels was beyond our expectations. I was so impressed that they had these lavish spreads ready in time for all our early morning departures. It was excellent.</p>\r\n<p>The staff at each hotel was very accommodating, they were empowered to handle situations; they were helpful, polite, kind and attentive. The service was great in the restaurants at all the hotels as well.</p>\r\n<p>In fact, everyone we met in Peru was wonderful. Everyone was extremely friendly, courteous, sweet-natured and so proud of their country.</p>\r\n<p>I will be recommending your company to anyone I know who plans to travel to Peru. We were very happy with everything!.</p>\r\n<p>Best regards,</p>\r\n','Roberta and Fred (Rancho Santa Fe, CA)<br/>\r\nTraveled to: Cusco, Sacred Valley, Machu Picchu\r\n','roberta-halliburton.jpg','Roberta Halliburton and Fred Pfeifer at Machu Picc','\"I was very pleased with the itinerary we worked out together to include all the elements we were keen on - it meant getting a little creative but you were always game and cooperative.\"',100039,0,0,NULL,'2014-09-10 23:13:20',NULL),(262,1,'Hi Everyone!','<p>I just wanted to let you know that Raye and I made it back to the USA without a hitch and THOROUGHLY enjoyed our trip to Peru. Many thanks to all of you for making it such a wonderful trip, we couldn\'t ask for more. All of you were so helpful, knowledgeable, and friendly that we feel we got a real taste of Peru and its interesting history (but not a taste of cuy or alpaca). We only wish we had more time to spend in Peru, but there is plenty to come back to see. Thanks especially to Cristina for helping us in Cuzco and getting us to MP, Fabricio for a great tour of the site, Maria for showing us Ollantaytambo and the Sacred Valley, and Edgar for showing us as much of Lima as we could see in the short time we had--all of you were great and really made the trip for us.  Thanks also to Aimee and to Liz for helping us pull all of this together on such short notice. Thanks again! </p>','John and Raye <br/>\r\nVentura, CA. <br/>\r\nCuzco, Machu Picchu\r\n','lamerdin.jpg','John and Raye Lamerdin in Cuzco','',576,0,0,NULL,NULL,NULL),(263,1,'Dear Peru For Less','<p>We had a terrific time in Peru. Peru For Less did a fabulous job with our transfers from the airport/train station and the hotels. The pick-ups were always on time and easy to find. Andrea, who met us at the Cuzco airport, was very organized and helpful with getting us oriented with the city. She made sure we had everything: hotel vouchers, train tickets, Machu Picchu passes, coca tea, etc. My husband loved Casa San Blas; it was very quaint.</p>\r\n<p>Our Sacred Valley tour with Mariela was awesome. She was very attentive and personable. We loved her suggestion to visit the llama and alpaca museum/farm. Now I know the difference between a llama, alpaca, vicuna, and guanaco. She guided us through the Pisac market and church. We enjoyed our personalized tour of Ollantaytambo and our relaxing evening at Kyuchi Rumi.</p>\r\n<p>When we arrived in Aguas Calientes, we were immediately greeted by the tour agent and the bellboy, just as Andrea had said. <strong>Staying at the Sanctuary Lodge was definitely a splurge, but the best decision we made. We left our bags with concierge and went straight to explore the Macchu Picchu site. We took fabulous pictures.</strong> We hiked all the way up to the Inca Bridge. We finally settled into our room at the Sanctuary Lodge, the view from the window was glorious.</p>\r\n<p>The train ride from Aguas Calientes to Poroy was sprinkled with entertainment. The Peru Rail cabin hostess and host had a fashion show, modeling alpaca-wear. There was music and a mini-dance performance. Even though the train arrived in Poroy late, we were greeted by our transfer agent and made it back to Casa San Blas in Cuzco. Andrea met us the next morning and we were so glad she had printed our boarding passes for our return flight. What a huge relief! My only regret is that we didn\'t spend one more day in Cuzco.</p>\r\n<p>Thank you Peru For Less for a memorable vacation. We are very satisfied and would recommend your services to our friends and family. We have amazing pictures to show for it.</p>\r\n','Sincerely, Shirley and Anil (Malvern, PA) <br/>\r\nTraveled to: Cuzco, Sacred Valley, Machu Picchu\r\n\r\n','fung-sharma.jpg','Shirley Fung and Anil Sharma in Cuzco','\"Andrea was very organized and helpful.. She made sure we had everything: hotel vouchers, train tickets, Machu Picchu passes, coca tea, etc.\"',100048,0,0,NULL,'2014-09-10 22:55:09',NULL),(264,1,'Dear Peru For Less','<p>Thanks for arranging such a great trip to Peru for us. You were able to get us everywhere we wanted to go even with our time constraints and we had time to spare as well. Cristina helped us use that spare time with her suggestions and last minute tour of the Sacred Valley. We had a wonderful trip and are very thankful that we found your company on the internet. All of the guides and transport people were helpful, friendly and knowledgeable. </p>','Paul, Vicki and Andrew <br/>\r\nVermont, Virginia. <br/>\r\nLima, Cuzco, Machu Picchu, Nazca','simons.jpg','Paul, Vicki and Andrew Simons Cuzco','',574,0,0,NULL,NULL,NULL),(265,1,'Dear Peru For Less','<p>The trip was wonderful. Everything went very smoothly, we were met everywhere by efficient and helpful guides. They were all good; I think particularly of Cristina in Cuzco and Fabricio in Machu Picchu. Cristina was punctual, energetic, friendly, informative, helpful and speaks excellent English. While we were in Cuzco the Inti Raymi festival was taking place so the town was very crowded and she got us everywhere on time and helped us navigate the people and streets without a problem. She had a lot of work to do but gave us all the assistance we needed and we felt we were in good hands. Thanks so much Cristina! </p>\r\n\r\n<p>Seeing the Cruz del Condor was fantastic, I didn\'t expect to see them so clearly. Machu Picchu was amazing, we climbed Huayna Picchu which was really worth all the effort and the jungle was beautiful. We saw over 50 species of birds! Everything went without a hitch and a lot of that is due to your good organization, thank you very much for a memorable trip!</p>\r\n','Rosalind and Lynne <br/>\r\nSacramento, CA. <br/>\r\nLima, Arequipa, Colca Canyon, Cuzco, Machu Picchu, Puerto Maldonado','becker.jpg','Rosalind Becker and Lynne Blake Arequipa Cuzco','',575,0,0,NULL,NULL,NULL),(266,1,'Hi Rylee,','<p>My mom and I had a terrific time visiting Peru. The transfers, hotels, tours, and your service was outstanding. Everything went according to plan and schedule; I enjoyed my trip without having to worry about the details. Pedro made our horseback riding trip to Moray and the salt mines of Maras an unforgettable experience for us. Also, visiting Machu Picchu was a once in a lifetime dream of mine that now I can say I have accomplished. I highly recommend your services, and will definitely be calling you once I am ready to visit Argentina and Brazil.  </p>','Thanks so much,\r\nJorge <br/>\r\nCharlotte, NC. <br/>\r\nCuzco, Sacred Valley, Machu Picchu and Lima','martinez.jpg','Jorge Martinez Machu Picchu and Lima','',572,0,0,NULL,NULL,NULL),(267,1,'Dear Peru For Less','<p>Overall, we saw and experienced many wonderful things. You truly did put together a lovely itinerary. My favorite things, other than Machu Picchu, would have to be the serenity of the jungle and Sandoval Lake at dawn each day. Also, I really enjoyed flying over the Nazca Lines in that little airplane. </p>\r\n\r\n<p>Thank you for your efforts. Our guides were fantastic and the hotels were outstanding. Included is a photo I took of a little Peruvian boy in traditional garb that I was so pleased with.</p>\r\n','Regards,\r\nSandy <br/>\r\nDelray Beach, Florida. <br/>\r\nLima, Arequipa, Cuzco, Puno, Amazon, Nazca Lines','davidson.jpg','Jorge Martinez Puno Lima','',573,0,0,NULL,NULL,NULL),(268,1,'Dear Peru For Less','<p>Thanks for making my first trip to South America a wonderful experience.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>The guides were very informative, interesting, flexible and patient. As we are not used to walking up and down stairs, sometimes it took a while to follow but our guides were always waiting and ready to take pictures of us with all our cameras.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>I think we were able to enjoy our trip so much because our itinerary was so organized.\r\nI have been e-mailing family and friends about our trip with pictures. I think I have convinced many of them to visit Peru. I will definitely recommend Peru For Less to them.</p>\r\n','Tomoko <br/>\r\nLos Angeles, USA. <br/>\r\nCuzco, Sacred Valley, Machu Picchu, Puno','tomoko.jpg','Tomoko Horie in Cuzco','',570,0,0,NULL,NULL,NULL),(269,1,'Dear Peru For Less','<p>The trip was great. Edgar was a great guide in Lima and very knowledgeable on the history of Lima as well as some history of Cuzco. </p>\r\n\r\n<p>Machu Picchu was breathtaking and I enjoyed every minute there. My brother wants to visit Peru with his family. I will definitely tell them what a great job you did for me. My itinerary was all that it said, and any changes were explained to me right away by Andrea. </p>\r\n\r\n<p>The tour guides were good. I didn\'t know that I would like the city of Cuzco so much. I will definitely go back and spend a free day just walking around and enjoying the city. Thanks for all of your help and for your prompt answers to all my questions. Peru was a great experience and I can\'t wait to go back.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>If any of you come to Los Angeles, California I will try to help you in any way I can to make your visit enjoyable as a token of my gratitude for helping me have a good time in Peru. Do not hesitate to write me anytime. I know I will be writing you when I return to Peru.</p>\r\n','Best Wishes, \r\nNick\r\nLos Angeles, CA. <br/>\r\nLima, Cuzco, Machu Picchu ','nick-la.jpg','Nick Cuzco','',571,0,0,NULL,NULL,NULL),(270,1,'Dear Peru For Less','<p>Thank you, our trip was wonderful, amazing, stunning. We will never forget Peru.\r\nService provided during the tour was really good, specially our guide Juan Carlos. The hotel in Cuzco was really great.</p>','Kulik <br/>\r\nPoland. <br/>\r\nCuzco, Machu Picchu','arkadiusz.jpg','Kulik Arkadiusz Machu Picchu','',568,0,0,NULL,NULL,NULL),(271,1,'Dear Peru For Less','<p>I have had a few days to get back into the swing of things, and it\'s amazing how many things you have to rethink. It is fun to think about all the little things that were different in Peru and in the US. Jenny and I did have a fabulous time. </p>\r\n \r\n<p>Our favorite part of the trip was the Rainforest. We had a wonderful guide, Manuel, and the other members of our group were just as excited to be there as we were. Cuzco was also a lovely town. We also loved Uros Island as I\'m sure most people do. It was a wonderful event for us to do just after our long drive to Puno. We were grateful you found us a private driver to take us all the way to Puno. </p>\r\n\r\n<p>Arequipa was another bright spot in the trip. We loved that it was a private city tour.  Gladys did a great job. She took us to the monastery, found us an excellent guide, and then provided a nice mixture of informative material and shopping experiences. She was very friendly and she knew a lot about her city. It was a really nice time. The hotel was exceptional too. We stayed at Casa Arequipa, and they provided wonderful information and service. After our favorite spot (the jungle), our three favorite hotels were Casa Arequipa, Arqueologo (Cuzco), and the Casa Bella (Lima).  Each staff member was kind and they tried to help us in any way they could. They all provided free internet access too! During this time we also went to Colca Canyon.  I loved seeing the condors in flight. Our guide, Edwin, did a great job of stopping along the way to point out the interesting things.  </p>\r\n  \r\n<p>Flying the Nazca lines was wonderful. We enjoyed all the sites and particularly enjoyed the guide provided there--Paul.  He\'s also the guy that took us to the Ballestas Islands.  He had a great personality and provided accurate details. The Ballestas Islands were great too. Seeing all those animals was certainly fun. I had a Wildlife Guide, and everywhere I went guides helped me to mark the wildlife I saw. It was nice to know I had a good book, but it was even nicer that all the people helped me to identify animals.</p>\r\n \r\n<p>We enjoyed our day in Lima too. Edgar did a great job of taking us to places that were important to us. For example, I was trying to find a particular book for my nephew.  Edgar took me to several places until we found the book, I really appreciated it.  Orlando was also a wonderful perk to the trip. He was the owner of La Casa Bella.  The services provided on our last night/day almost made us want to stay longer.</p>\r\n \r\n<p>I loved the country, I loved the experience, and I was certainly happy with your company. I hope the thoughts I\'ve shared in this letter convey that. We do appreciate the security traveling with Peru For Less gave us. Should we travel to Peru again, we will certainly contact you again.</p>\r\n','Thanks for everything,\r\nRebecca \r\nMissouri, USA. <br/>\r\nLima, Puerto Maldonado, Cuzco, Machu Picchu, Puno, Arequipa, Colca Canyon, Nazca, Ica','rebecca.jpg','','',569,0,0,NULL,NULL,NULL),(272,1,'To Whom It May Concern:','<p>I have now worked with Peru For Less on several large tours and they have always come through for me. I have large groups and odd requests, such as dawn visits to archaeological sites, which they always accommodate. Their people, both in the booking office and on the ground, are helpful, friendly, and knowledgeable. Even when I needed help booking things in Bolivia, they went out of their way to help me. Their prices are fair, their services are superior, and their response times are almost immediate.  During all of my tours, Peru For Less representatives were available 24 hours a day. Whether you are traveling alone or organizing a trip for a big group, I highly recommend Peru For Less.</p>','Dr. Edwin <br/>\r\nDirector, Maya Exploration Center\r\nAustin, TX. <br/>\r\nCuzco, Sacred Valley, Lake Titicaca, Puno, La Paz, Copacabana','','','',108,0,0,NULL,NULL,NULL),(273,1,'Dear Peru For Less','<p>My wife and I just returned home from a fabulous vacation in Peru to celebrate 30 years being married. We feel very fortunate that we chose Peru For Less to organize and oversee our trip. You gave us numerous hotels to choose from, with extensive pictures of the facilities and they were accurate. We were always met at the airport/train station by a friendly and knowledgeable guide, and escorted to our hotel/destination. We never experienced any difficulty with transportation or accommodations (unlike several travelers that we met along our venture). Our guides were the best...informative and fun.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>By having a set itinerary we were able to save time, and relax more, knowing that everything was already in place and taken care of.  The stress level was nonexistent. I could spend my time on more important issues like where we were going to eat next. Ah food....a very important part of Peruvian culture. I must say the food is incredible. For the first time in my life I ate alpaca, ostrich, and the traditional guinea pig - fabulous!  All of it was excellent and I recommend it highly, not to mention all the other fruits, vegetables, soups and desserts. What a treat. The people were very friendly, appreciative, and helpful. Our trip truly was a vacation of a lifetime. Machu Picchu and the Sacred Valley were magic, no other way to describe it.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Oh yeah, and be sure to tell everyone to include the Amazon, that\'s a part they won\'t want to miss. Seeing black caimans, giant otters, monkeys, and macaws up close and personal was beyond our wildest expectations.\r\nSo to Peru For Less we tip our hat and say \"Well done and thank you!\"</p>\r\n','Best regards,\r\nRick & Cheryl <br/>\r\nGridley, California. <br/>\r\nArequipa, Cuzco, Machu Picchu, Puno, the Amazon','','','',96,0,0,NULL,NULL,NULL),(274,1,'Dear Peru For Less','<p>Rob and I had a wonderful trip through Peru, thank you. We had a huge time, saw some wonderful sights and met some great travelling companions.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>The services and tours were all spot on and ran like clockwork. The Peru for Less staff did a great job and the pick-ups and transfers from airports, hotels, bus stations, etc. were all on time and superbly organised. It made traveling a pleasure, knowing that there was always going to be someone waiting at the next destination. The three-star hotels were all more than adequate and in most cases, exceeded our expectations.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>The Salkantay Trail and Machu Picchu were definitely the highlights of the trip. We even managed to be part of the group allowed to climb Waynu Picchu, from which the views were spectacular. </p>\r\n\r\n<p>Once again, thank you very much for putting together such a wonderful, exciting and seamless trip. You and the staff at Peru for Less couldn\'t have done a better job to make our trip a very special experience.</p>\r\n','Kind regards, \r\nJacob <br/>\r\nHamilton, New Zealand. <br/>\r\nLima, Amazon, Cuzco, Salkantay Trail, Machu Picchu, Puno, Arequipa, Colca Canyon','','','',95,0,0,NULL,NULL,NULL),(275,1,'Dear Peru For Less','<p>Our trip was wonderful. I think I loved Peru more than I could have imagined. It is such a fascinating place with a beautiful culture, and scenery to match -- all very awe-inspiring and thought-provoking. We toured the Sacred Valley with a private driver and guide; both were absolutely terrific, smart, well informed, and a delight to spend the day with. </p>\r\n\r\n<p>The tours were great, the guides kind, funny, and knowledgeable. Peru proved to be most amazing place and we would like to return. I want to thank you for your planning, patience and time. We will absolutely recommend you to our friends who travel frequently.</p>\r\n','Take care and stay well.\r\nJudy & Douglas <br/>\r\nWashington DC, USA. <br/>\r\nCuzco, Sacred Valley, Machu Picchu, Puno, Arequipa','','','',94,0,0,NULL,NULL,NULL),(276,1,'Dear Peru For Less','<p>The trip was great.  We really loved the Casona Yucay Hotel in the Sacred Valley.  We are glad that we took the Vista Dome class to Machu Picchu.  The Casa Andina Catedral Hotel was in a great location. Everyone at Peru for Less was very helpful and things went smoothly. Thanks.</p>','Best Regards,\r\nBrad\r\nMontecito, California. <br/>\r\nCuzco, Sacred Valley, Machu Picchu','','','',93,0,0,NULL,NULL,NULL),(277,1,'Dear Peru For Less','<p>The trip to Peru was a remarkable experience. It was our first time to South America and we did not know what to expect. The trip far surpassed my expectations. In fact, I was somewhat concerned prior to departing as I did not know how \'dangerous\' this trip was going to be. I am very glad to report that we did not experience any incidents where we were in any way concerned about our security.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>I am very glad that we chose Peru as our first visit as it is a country so rich in history and with such diverse and stunning scenery. We found the people to be very friendly and helpful and so proud of their heritage. Machu Picchu was an awesome experience, but so were many other places. The Nazca lines took my breath away.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>I am also of the opinion that this holiday would not have been as enjoyable without the assistance of Peru For Less. All your arrangements were perfect and we were looked after very well. I would definitely recommend your company to anyone planning a visit to Peru.   </p>\r\n\r\n<p>Thank you once again for the great service - keep up the good work.      </p>\r\n','Jeannette and Annegret <br/>\r\nSouth Africa. <br/>\r\nLima, Nazca, Amazon, Cuzco, Lake Titicaca, Rio de Janeiro\r\n','kitshoff.jpg','Jeannette van Zyl and Annegret Kitshoff','',578,0,0,NULL,NULL,NULL),(278,1,'Dear Peru For Less','<p>We wish we had discovered Peru For Less sooner!  Chad and I went to the Galapagos with another travel agency, spent too much money, and came out of the experience disappointed and feeling cheated.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Our experience with Peru For Less was wonderful and hassle-free.  Everything happened as planned; no changes in itineraries.  Heck, our guides actually knew what our itinerary was each day (with the other travel agency, no one seemed to know our scheduled activities, and the only thing that saved us was the itinerary that I had printed out ahead of time)!!  We were greeted in every city and had smooth transports (Andrea in Cusco was especially great).  All of our guides were knowledgeable and helpful.  We especially appreciate the advice from Andrea and our guide in Machu Picchu to go early and get the tickets to hike Wynapicchu (we hadn\'t even heard of it!)--it is one of the best memories of our trip.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Peru is an amazing and beautiful country; it is one of the best trips we\'ve ever taken. We thank Peru For Less for the great service.  We will definitely go with Peru For Less for future trips to South America.</p>\r\n','Chad &amp; Amanda <br/>\r\nAtlanta, GA. <br/>\r\nLima, Arequipa, Colca Canyon, Cuzco, Machu Picchu, Puno\r\n','hoover.jpg','Chad &amp; Amanda Hoover','',579,0,0,NULL,NULL,NULL),(279,1,'Dear Peru For Less','<p>The trip was great. We loved Edgar (our tour guide in Lima). He was extremely knowledgeable and pleasant.  The Sol De Oro Hotel was the best out of all of the places that we stayed.  Overall, our pickups went off without any problems- our drivers were always easily found and helpful.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Fabricio, our tour guide at Machu Picchu and Alison (Cuzco) were great.  I always felt like I had reliable contacts and knew what the plan would be.  </p>\r\n \r\n<p>I am really looking forward to visiting Peru again and would definitely use Peru For Less a second time. We were both very happy with our trip!  Thanks for helping us have a safe and relaxing time in Peru!  </p>\r\n \r\n<p>PS: You have been wonderful too- thank you!</p>\r\n','Jeanne <br/>\r\nNew Jersey, USA. <br/>\r\nLima, Nazca, Cuzco\r\n','arnold.jpg','Jeanne Arnold','',580,0,0,NULL,NULL,NULL),(280,1,'Dear Peru For Less','<p>I want to thank you for our excellent vacation! We had a wonderful experience in Peru! I have to say that Andrea was so professional and friendly, and helped us to feel well cared for from the moment we arrived at the airport! We also loved Fabricio, who gave us our Machu Picchu tour with such an incredible story-telling style! Every person was where they promised to be at every turn, and we only had to think about enjoying ourselves!</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Many thanks, and we will definitely recommend Peru For Less to our friends!</p>\r\n','Susan <br/>\r\nLongwood, FL. <br/>\r\nCuzco, Machu Picchu\r\n','bourgoin.jpg','Susan Bourgoin','',581,0,0,NULL,NULL,NULL),(281,1,'Dear Peru For Less','<p>THANK YOU for planning an AWESOME trip!! My sister and I had a great time. The Sacred Valley private tour with Abad was wonderful. He did a fantastic job. Machu Picchu was breathtaking and many photos were taken.  Andrea was a lifesaver as our flight from Cusco was cancelled. She stayed with us for two hours until all arrangements were made. We cannot thank her and praise her enough. Your company was already getting glowing remarks for all the arrangements, but Andrea set you above and beyond. I would highly recommend your travel company to anyone traveling to Peru. Do you make arrangements to other countries as well?</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Thanks again, Gavin and Liz, for all you did to make our travel to Peru so enjoyable and carefree. </p>\r\n','Mary &amp; Karen <br/>\r\nIowa, USA. <br/>\r\nCuzco, Sacred Valley, Machu Picchu\r\n','gregg-greiss.jpg','Mary Gregg &amp; Karen Greis','',582,0,0,NULL,NULL,NULL),(282,1,'Dear Peru For Less','<p>WHAT A FABULOUS ADVENTURE!  THANKS A MILLION AIMEE!</p>\r\n \r\n<p>Elaine and I had just a marvelous time traveling through Peru.  The sites were spectacular, the people were wonderful, and the food was exceptional.  It really was a \"gastronomical extravaganza.\"</p>\r\n \r\n<p>Thank you for all your hard work, travel suggestions, and organization.  I met a number of other travellers who simply raved about \"Peru for Less\" and the itinerary that your company had put together for them.  They were pleased with the service they received.  Elaine and I have travelled with many companies over the years and we were extremely satisfied, highly impressed, and thankful that we had booked through you, Aimee.  You were also absolutely wonderful to work with and we both appreciated your efforts in helping us to plan our trip to Peru.</p>\r\n  \r\n<p>We were always picked up promptly and on time. Our guides and tours were excellent throughout our trip.  They all did a super job of guiding us through Peru.  We were more than happy to tip accordingly.</p>\r\n \r\n<p>Please pass on our sincere regards to Nicola as well for her fine communication, positive comments to my bad jokes and supporting our trip.</p>\r\n \r\n<p>What a wonderful experience!</p>\r\n \r\n<p>THANKS AGAIN!</p>\r\n','Elaine and Bill <br/>\r\nAlberta, Canada. <br/>\r\nCuzco, Sacred Valley, Machu Picchu, Puno, Arequipa, Colca, Nazca, Ica, Lima\r\n','kidd-bill.jpg','Elaine and Bill Kidd','',595,0,0,NULL,NULL,NULL),(283,1,'Dear Peru For Less','<p>I apologize for not getting back to you sooner, but its been a bit hectic readjusting after such a great trip to Peru!  Everything was fantastic while we were there, and the people with Peru for Less could not have been more helpful.  Alison took care of all of our needs while we were in Cusco, Machu Picchu and elsewhere.  I would be more than happy to write a testimonial for you as well as send a picture, so here it goes:</p>\r\n\r\n<p>I must say that for two non-Spanish speaking guys, Peru for Less was fantastic!  Anything and everything we needed was taken care of, and any problems along the way were remedied with extreme professionalism and courtesy.  For such a quick trip with the last minute planning, it could not have worked out better.  Lima-Cusco-Mach Picchu in six days was a great experience, and all those working behind the scenes made it effortless.  </p>\r\n\r\n<p>Alison, our Cusco home-base, was there to answer our questions and give us guidance...even when we were in Aguas Calientes!  Every guide gave us a different perspective, while stressing that it was their own personal views since there is no one accepted version yet.  We would use Per for Less again in a heartbeat, and highly recommend it for anyone interested in a trip to Peru with no worries!</p>\r\n','Andy <br/>\r\nWashington, DC. <br/>\r\nLima, Cusco, Machu Pichu\r\n','rein.jpg','Andy Rein','',594,0,0,NULL,NULL,NULL),(284,1,'Rylee,','<p>Our family enjoyed our Peru For Less Trip immensely. The weaver\'s cooperative was a high point for me, although the whole trip was amazing &#45; one spectacular tour after another, with wonderful, inexpensive food in between. The Huchuyqosqo trek was amazing.  I really enjoyed the trip, knowing that I\'d be at a good hotel, that I\'d get a guide, and that all transport was taken care of. The largest tour group we were in was 13, and we were often &#45; even at Machu Picchu &#45; in our own group of four. I would highly recommend spending an extra day at Machu Picchu.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>There is so much to see of Peru, and Peru for Less helped us to see as much and as deeply as we could, in our 18 days. The Peruvian people are warm, friendly and helpful; pre-Columbian ruins are all over, and the food is wonderfully good and inexpensive. Our trip to Trujillo and Chiclayo was amazing. There we saw huge sites that are not well known. Peru for Less helped us see beyond Machu Picchu, and made our trip smooth. I highly recommend Peru For Less.</p>\r\n','Kay <br/>\r\nMaplewood, MN. <br/>\r\nLima, Nazca, Arequipa &amp; Colca Canyon, Cuzco &amp; Machu Picchu, Trujillo &amp; Chiclayo\r\n','hatlestad.jpg','Kay Hatlestad','',593,0,0,NULL,NULL,NULL),(285,1,'Dear Peru For Less','<p>Thank you for arranging a fantastic trip for us to Peru.  We TRUELY enjoyed it!  We are looking forward to another trip to South America - maybe Argentina, Chile or Brazil - perhaps using YOUR outstanding service if possible! I was very impressed with what your group had done for us. Being an independent traveller in most of my other world-wide trips, I was very very very happy that I had asked for your service on this journey to South America.  And I am definitely referring your service to all my friends.</p>\r\n \r\n<p>The staff and guides were extremely helpful and knowledgeable.  The transfers in and out of city were seamless.  The drivers made our journey safe.  I wanted to say again, THANK YOU, for everything.</p>\r\n \r\n<p>Our special thanks go out to Cristina in Cuzco (who was thorough and organized) and the lady who helped us in Arequipa - I know special arrangement needed to be made for the Juanita Mummy tour.  Marcial was an excellent guide for Colca canyon who made sure we saw all the wildlife out there - vicunas, aplacas, candor, and many others.  Maria Elena in Cuzco was an \"above and beyond\" guide, who not only was knowledgeable, caring, sensitive to our needs, but an excellent photographer as well!  The Lake Titikaka tour was culturally and scenically eye-opening.  And the guide was very pleasant.  Finally, Omar from Lima city tour was definitely a humorous guide, who was able to explain the history of Peru and the Inca Empire, with a very interesting perspective.  </p>\r\n \r\n<p>Again, I wanted to say that our trip to Peru was fabulous thanks to you.  Do you also help people arrange for Argentina or Chile?  Please take care!</p>\r\n','Irene <br/>\r\nSunnyvale, CA. <br/>\r\nArequipa, Puno, Cuzco &amp; Machu Picchu\r\n','chen.jpg','Irene Chen','',592,0,0,NULL,NULL,NULL),(286,1,'Dear Peru For Less','<p>I was visiting Peru with my friend and her daughter in August and greatly appreciated the help and attention we received from all your staff. Everyone was professional,  \r\nEfficient, ready to assist us and told us much about the culture  \r\nand history of Peru. Christina was very helpful when we were  \r\ndelayed arriving in Cuzco by bringing us to the tour already in  \r\nprogress. She also programmed her cell phone number into my cell phone  \r\nso I could contact her easily if I had any problems! Jimmy and  \r\nFabricio were most kind and helped me navigate the terrain-I have  \r\narthritis and sometimes have difficulty with steep inclines. I could  \r\nnot have climbed as high as I did without the support. We always felt  \r\nwe were given personal attention instead of just another person in a  \r\nlarge group.  I would not hesitate to refer my friends to your tour  \r\ncompany should they visit Peru and when and if I return to Peru I  \r\nwill call your company again! You made a special vacation even more  \r\nspecial! Thank you all for your help and for making history come alive  \r\nfor us! </p>\r\n','Karin <br/>\r\nNorth Andover MA. <br/>\r\nCuzco &amp; Machu Picchu\r\n','seiller.jpg','Karin Seiller','',591,0,0,NULL,NULL,NULL),(287,1,'Dear Peru For Less','<p>The trip was great; thanks for all your help in planning it and making it a success.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>While there are probably cheaper and/or more adventurous ways to see Peru, I\'m pretty sure there isn\'t an easier way.  I literally did no planning and got to see everything I wanted to in and around Cuzco in just 2 and a half days.  Left to my own devices I\'m sure I would have missed something (maybe even Machu Picchu since the train was sold out) and since I was traveling solo, the group tours were an excellent choice. The other tourists in the group were easy to get along with and the guides were knowledgeable and entertaining.  </p>\r\n\r\n<p>If you\'re like me and like to let someone else handle all the details, Peru for Less is the way to go.  I have already recommended you to my parents, who after seeing the Machu Picchu pictures and are interested in going.  Good work PFL!</p>\r\n','Nick <br/>\r\nLivermore, CA. <br/>\r\nCuzco &amp; Machu Picchu\r\n','loper.jpg','Nick Loper','',590,0,0,NULL,NULL,NULL),(288,1,'Dear Peru For Less','<p>We had a blast! The trip was amazing and the guides were awesome! Our tour guide in the Amazon showed us both an amazing time. Thank you so much for all your work to make our Peru trip a success. </p>\r\n\r\n<p>Machu Picchu was the most beautiful place I\'ve ever been and the people in Peru were also great. I\'ve been ranting and raving about the trip since coming back. I will be sure to recommend your company to anyone planning a trip to Peru.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Y\'all did a great job setting it all up.</p>\r\n','Thanks!\r\nVincent &amp; Derek <br/>\r\nVirgina, USA. <br/>\r\nCuzco, Machu Picchu, Puerto Maldonado\r\n','hansen-derek.jpg','Vincent &amp; Derek Hansen','',589,0,0,NULL,NULL,NULL),(289,1,'Dear Peru For Less','<p>I would like to thank you, Liz and everyone at Peru for Less for making our trip to Peru such a wonderful experience.  The tours you scheduled were so interesting and informative.  Your tour guides were always on time and fully explained our itinerary for each day ahead of time, which made preparation very easy.  The guides were all personable, professional and came across as really enjoying their jobs and sharing Peru\'s history with us.  My son and I both enjoyed Cusco and the Sacred Valley but Machu Picchu was beyond belief and awe inspiring. The Hotel Andena Private was a great place to stay and the staff was wonderful.  Breakfast was welcomed each morning as a good way to get started.  We enjoyed Cusco at night with its many restaurants and beautiful plazza with the old style street lights.  All in all we would definitely refer any of our friends to you and your company.  Once again thank you for a wonderful vacation.</p>','Carl and Yuri <br/>\r\nHenderson, NV. <br/>\r\nCuzco &amp; Machu Picchu\r\n','graves-yuri.jpg','Carl and Yuri Graves','',588,0,0,NULL,NULL,NULL),(290,1,'Hola amigos!','<p>We are back from Peru - an amazing country if you ever get to go. Now that the Shining Path terrorists are out of the country everyone\'s so darn friendly! We told JP from Peru for Less what we wanted to see &amp; he arranged the perfect trip for us. We\'re definitely going back one more time to hit things we missed that we have to see. Some of the cool stuff we saw/did:\r\nSpotting tons of birds (inc. penguins), sea lions &amp; dolphins at the Ballestas Islands.\r\nTaking a dune buggy &amp; sandboarding at the sand dunes around Ica. We don\'t know what sand dunes are in this country - these things were thousands of feet tall. Our hotel was in an oasis surrounded by sand dunes - gorgeous!\r\nFlying over the Nazca Lines - we got lucky &amp; had perfect weather. \r\nVisiting TONS (literally) of ruins including, of course, the amazing Machu Picchu. \r\nJust a wonderful country.\r\nCan\'t say we\'re glad to be back, but it will be nice to see you guys again.</p>\r\n','Sandi <br/>\r\nNewton, NJ. <br/>\r\nParacas, Nazca, Cusco &amp; Machu Picchu\r\n','morrow.jpg','Sandi Morrow','',587,0,0,NULL,NULL,NULL),(291,1,'Dear Peru For Less','<p>We had a truly great time on our trip.  The arrangements were virtually flawless.  The only variation we encountered was no problem at all, and a phone call confirmed that an alternative transportation arrangement had been made.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>All of the guides we had were exceptionally knowledgeable, and all transportation/connections were punctual.  </p>\r\n\r\n<p>Thanks again to you and Liz Boyd for all of your help in formulating and executing the itinerary.  We are extremely satisfied with your services and would recommend them highly.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Best regards,</p>\r\n','Marc and Scott <br/>\r\nNew Jersey, USA. <br/>\r\nLima, Cuzco, Machu Picchu, Puno\r\n','crowley-smith.jpg','Marc Crowley and Scott Smith','',586,0,0,NULL,NULL,NULL),(292,1,'Dear Rylee,','<p>I want to THANK YOU, THANK YOU, THANK YOU, for one exciting and amazing trip.  Your efforts and planning allowed for my friends and I to enjoy Peru and all of its cultural wonders.  From the get go, we were greeted and taken care of.  Transfers between Cusco/Machu Picchu, Puno/Lake Titicaca and Arequipa/Colca Canyon were basically flawless.  It was great that we  can enjoy this trip, without having to worry about the details.  The coordinators were really on top of everything.  Our guides were very knowledgeable about the areas we\'ve visited.  I\'ve learned so much!  I cannot say enough to express my gratitude on all the help and effort you put into helping our two groups (both Kyle\'s and mine) get together, to make this all work. I will definitely recommend both you and Peru for Less, to anyone and everyone!   Again, thank you very much!</p>','Sincerely,\r\nRianne <br/>\r\nChula Vista, CA. <br/>\r\nCuzco, Machu Picchu, Puno, Arequipa\r\n','decena.jpg','Rianne Decena','',585,0,0,NULL,NULL,NULL),(293,1,'Rylee,','<p>All of the Peru For Less staff who helped us with our Peru vacation was absolutely wonderful. They were all honest, prompt, kind, and followed through with their promises. The price couldn\'t be beat and we were well taken care of during our vacation! </p>\r\n \r\n<p>Very good service! Every single one of the guides for our tours was wonderfully helpful and good at their job. We especially liked the river rafting guide Romuelo. </p>\r\n','Thanks!!\r\nMelissa &amp; Chris <br/>\r\nWichita, KS. <br/>\r\nCuzco, Machu Picchu, Lima\r\n','harrington.jpg','Melissa &amp; Chris Harrington','',584,0,0,NULL,NULL,NULL),(294,1,'Dear Peru For Less','<p>Everything was very good. The hotels, Peru for Less employees, and freelancers (drivers/cars) were quite good.</p>','Thank you and my best wishes.\r\nCamille\r\n','gedeon.jpg','Thank you and my best wishes.\r\nCamille Gedeon\r\n','',583,0,0,NULL,NULL,NULL),(295,1,'Dear Peru For Less','<p>Our time in Peru was completely amazing! It\'s so sad to write it in the past tense; it\'s so sad to realize our trip is over! We had so much fun and learned so much and saw so many beautiful people and places. We heard beautiful music and wonderful stories. We heard stories of tragedy (the Spanish conquest of the Incas) and survival and triumph. We were greeted warmly everywhere we went!\r\nBeing in Puno was fine (the Eco Inn hotel was the most spacious we stayed in for the entire trip and we really enjoyed it!), the tour of the Uros Islands was great. Our representative in Puno was very kind and friendly. Also, our guide of the Sillustani funerary towers and the ride to the airport was very kind, friendly, and eager to help. I speak a bit of Spanish, so it was nice to put my broken Spanish together with their (very good) English and come up with a conversation we were all interested in.\r\nWe had never been to South America and we were resistant to having someone else plan things for us. We were mildly nervous about the language and customs barrier and weren\'t sure we\'d be able to get around. Boy, were we pleasantly surprised! PFL took care of us from airports to hotels to tours back to hotels and airports. Muchas gracias to Abby and everyone at PFL for making our (first!) trip to Peru memorable and fun!\r\nThank you so much for everything you and the team at PFL did to make our trip memorable. We are currently searching Phoenix for a Peruvian restaurant because my husband is craving Lomo Saltado :-) </p>\r\n','Muchas gracias!\r\nMargi &amp; Jon <br/>\r\nChandler, AZ. <br/>\r\nCuzco, Inca Trail, Puno\r\n','','','',107,0,0,NULL,NULL,NULL),(296,1,'Dear Peru For Less','<p>We just wanted to let you know that my daughter, Gabriela, my friend, \r\nKarin, and I, just thoroughly enjoyed our recent trip to Cusco and \r\nMachu Picchu, and the services of all of the Peru for Less staff were \r\nsensational. We were met by Christina in Cusco very efficiently, even \r\nthough some of us missed our connections and arrived later than \r\nexpected on a different flight, making her work harder to connect with \r\nus all.  Christina made sure that we met up with our tour and missed \r\nvery little, which we appreciate tremendously.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Christina worked very hard to try to iron out plane reservation \r\ncomplications, and all the staff in Cusco was friendly, knowledgeable \r\nand efficient.  We were met promptly, all the details of our \r\narrangements were seamless, and our hotel, the Del Prado Inn, was \r\ndelightful. Our guides, Mary and Jimmy, were able to help us appreciate \r\nall the sites in Cusco and the Sacred Valley. Our transportation to \r\nsites outside the city was very modern and comfortable.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Our ride to and from Machu Picchu on the backpack train went off \r\nwithout a hitch, and our tickets and arrangements were perfectly \r\norganized for us. We were met promptly by Rebecca, who had all of our \r\nhotel and luggage info, as well as bus tickets and passes to Machu Picchu \r\nready and waiting. Our tour guide Fabricio was very warm and friendly, \r\nand helpful to those in our party who needed an extra hand with the \r\nrigorous climb up and down the inclines of Machu Picchu.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Fabricio was able to arrange an escort for my daughter to climb \r\nWaynapicchu, which made her very happy, and was a great relief to me. \r\nGabriela was especially delighted to be the first in line for the 7 AM \r\nclimb, thanks to the advocacy and dedication of both Fabricio and Mary, \r\nin Agua Calientes and on the mountain. The Wayna Picchu staff marked her \r\nticket with a number 1, which is a great souvenir.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>I have to say that before meeting the staff, I had my concerns about  \r\narranging for a tour online without any direct contact beforehand. Once \r\nthe trip began, however, it was apparent that Peru for Less has a real \r\ndedication to making sure that travelers experience a worry free and \r\npleasant trip. Every transfer, arrangement, contact and tour was \r\nhandled professionally, efficiently, and with great communication. We \r\nalways had an emergency phone number to contact Christina in Cusco if \r\nwe ran into trouble or needed something, and at all times felt well \r\ncared for and  secure.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>I will definitely recommend Peru for Less to everyone I know who is \r\nconsidering a trip to Peru, and I will begin planning my next Peru for \r\nLess expedition as soon as possible!! Thanks to J.P. and all the on \r\nsite staff in Cusco and Machu Picchu who helped to make this a very \r\nmemorable vacation!!</p>\r\n','Fran <br/>\r\nMassachusetts, USA. <br/>\r\nCuzco, Machu Picchu\r\n','','','',106,0,0,NULL,NULL,NULL),(297,1,'Dear Peru For Less','<p>We all thought Machu Picchu was amazing.  We were able to get there first thing on the second day so that we could hike up Wyna Picchu.  I think we all really enjoyed that.  The views were incredible, although the hike definitely wore us out.  We also had a lot of fun hanging out in Cusco and went to quite a few good restaurants.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>The Jungle was also really nice.  It was a pretty good way to end the trip since there was so much downtime between hikes/canoe rides, we had plenty of time to lounge around and relax.  We saw quite a few tarantulas, caimans, various birds, monkeys, and even a couple snakes.  We also saw the river otters from a distance, but they were far enough away, that we couldn\'t really get a good look. </p>\r\n\r\n<p>As far as the guides, we were happy with all of them.  They were all very knowledgeable and friendly. </p>\r\n\r\n<p>Overall, we had a great trip and were happy with the way everything turned out.</p>\r\n','Thanks for everything,\r\nJim <br/>\r\nChicago, IL. <br/>\r\nCuzco, Machu Picchu, Puerto Maldonado, Puno \r\n','','','',105,0,0,NULL,NULL,NULL),(298,1,'Hi Rylee,','<p>We have just returned from South America and thoroughly enjoyed our trip to Peru and the Galapagos Islands which you kindly helped us organise.</p>\r\n \r\n<p>We were very happy with the scheduled tours and the overall trip. In particular, we were impressed with the professional service, friendly and honest advice we received from you. Your comments and input helped us with the planning of our trip. Thank you so much for all your help. </p>\r\n\r\n<p>With kind regards,</p>\r\n','David and Patricia <br/>\r\nMunich, Germany. <br/>\r\nCuzco, Machu Picchu and Galapagos\r\n','','','',104,0,0,NULL,NULL,NULL),(299,1,'Dear Peru For Less','<p>I wanted to drop a quick note saying all was great!!!!\r\nSanctuary Lodge worth every penny. My husband who rarely travels with me loved this trip. </p>\r\n','Cheers, \r\nBarbara <br/> \r\nSan Jose, CA. <br/>\r\nCuzco &amp; Machu Picchu\r\n','','','',103,0,0,NULL,NULL,NULL),(300,1,'Rylee!','<p>Our trip to Peru was magnificent! Your personnel were all very professional, knowledgeable, friendly, and very positive. We had such a blast and will definitely recommend Peru for Less to our friends and family.\r\nThank you for all your help!</p>\r\n','Dorothy and Eric <br/>\r\nLewes, DE. <br/>\r\nCuzco, Machu Picchu and Puno\r\n','','','',102,0,0,NULL,NULL,NULL),(301,1,'Hi Rylee,','<p>We just got home from our trip to Peru. I enjoyed the trip very much. All the hotels were great and so were the tour guides. All in all it was a wonderful trip we met a lot of interesting people from all over the world!\r\nThank you for arranging it!</p>\r\n','Ellen <br/>\r\nWayzata, MN. <br/>\r\nLima, Cuzco &amp; Machu Picchu, Puno &amp; Lake Titicaca and Nazca\r\n','','','',101,0,0,NULL,NULL,NULL),(302,1,'Rylee,','<p>The trip was amazing. Thank you for helping me plan the whole thing. Everything went well. I would love to go on other trips with Peru for less and I will recommend it to everyone.\r\nThank you very much for your expertise, professionalism, the whole companyâ??s staff and individual support and services. </p>\r\n \r\n<p>I do plan on using Peru for less again. </p>\r\n','Estelle <br/> \r\nMalden, MA. <br/>\r\nCuzco, Machu Picchu and Puerto Maldonado\r\n','','','',100,0,0,NULL,NULL,NULL),(303,1,'Rylee,','<p>Thank you for following up!  I really did enjoy your services and the tour.  You are an exceptional agent and you were excellent at helping us plan our trip.  \r\nI loved all 3 places.  Our tour guides were highly knowledgeable and I really learned a lot about the local culture on this trip. It was all really amazing.  I will be more than happy to submit a testimonial. =)   Again, I appreciate all your efforts in assisting us in coordinating this trip.  I will recommend Peru for Less (and you, if that\'s okay), to other friends who may travel to Peru or South America, in the future.</p>\r\n','Sincerely,\r\nMarianne <br/>\r\nChula Vista, CA. <br/>\r\nCuzco, Machu Picchu and Puno and Arequipa\r\n','','','',99,0,0,NULL,NULL,NULL),(304,1,'Dear Peru For Less','<p>I just wanted to drop you a note to let you know we had a fabulous trip to Peru, and all accommodations and reservations were in perfect order and perfectly arranged.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Thank you so much â?? we had a wonderful time!</p>\r\n','Julie &amp; Kevin <br/> \r\nChicago, IL. <br/>\r\nCuzco, Puerto Maldonado, Lima \r\n','','','',98,0,0,NULL,NULL,NULL),(305,1,'Rylee,','<p>Thank you so much Rylee for putting together a great trip!</p>\r\n\r\n<p>We got back late afternoon yesterday, it was amazing and fun. Iguazu was unbelievable and the wineries in Chile were beautiful and had so much history. The guides were great and so were the tours. We will definitely be recommending you guys to friends and family.</p>\r\n \r\n<p>What other countries in the world can we do this for through you guys?\r\nThanks again for everything and as soon as we get our pictures together I will send some in!</p>\r\n','Cheers, \r\nNiloofar and Koorosh <br/>\r\nWoodland Hills, CA. <br/>\r\nBuenos Aires, Iguazu, Santiago\r\n','','','',97,0,0,NULL,NULL,NULL),(306,1,'Dear Peru For Less','<p>Our trip was great. It wasn\'t actually our honeymoon; it was more of a trip just for fun. All of the guides we had on each part of our trip were fantastic. Everyone was very friendly and knowledgable. Overall I guess that the hotels were what someone should expect for a 3 star hotel. The woman we had contact with in Cuzco was great, I can\'t seem to remember her name at the moment.</p> \r\n\r\n<p>Here are some things I would recommend to others traveling to Peru: \r\nIn hindsight I think that we would have done things just a little differently, such as having 1 extra day in either Cuzco or Aguas Calientes just to unwind a little bit. Also I think we would have done the 5 day trek because we heard really good things about it (not that we didn\'t enjoy the Lares trek). Another thing I think I would recommend to other travelers is when making your way back from Aguas Calientes to Cuzco, get off at the Ollyantambo train station and take a van back to Cuzco. </p>\r\n','Ben. \r\nMinneapolis, USA <br/>\r\nLares Trek and Amazon\r\n','ben.jpg','ben','',596,0,0,NULL,NULL,NULL),(307,1,'Hello Rylee,','<p>Peru was very fine.</p> \r\n \r\n<p>Our pick- ups from train station or the airport were always on schedule. In Cuzco, we stayed at a very nice hotel, the Arquelogo. It had a very nice staff and was very clean. We had a beautiful experience. We had a nice hotel and a very good guide just for the two of us. This is excellent because, because chasing monkeys with 20 people is a lot more difficult. The macaws and all the other animals were an experience we will never forget. </p>\r\n \r\n<p>For our Sacred Valley tour, we thought that Ollantaytambo is very impressive and the market of Pisac is nice. \r\nThe Lares trek was very nice. We liked every part of it. We had a very good guide, a good cook and a good tent (even after the hail storm).</p>\r\n\r\n<p>So to conclude, we had a very nice experience and we saw a lot of beautiful things (I think we don\'t yet realise half of it). \r\nThank you for organising everything, </p>\r\n','Sarah and Bart\r\nOostende, Belgium <br/>\r\nLares Trek, Cuzco, Machu Picchu and Lake Sandoval in Puerto Maldonado \r\n','sarah-bart.jpg','Sarah and Bart','',597,0,0,NULL,NULL,NULL),(308,1,'Dear Peru For Less','<p>Yes our trip was a \"once in a lifetime experience\" Machu Picchu was on my \"Bucket List\" as a place to visit before I die. It certainly was not a let down. Allison took care of our needs in Cuzco and I would like to make sure that her supervisor is aware how much she helped us and took care of our needs. Please pass this on to her supervisor. Everyone along the way that represented Peru for Less did a fine job. Our tours were well planned and our guides did a fine job. I would have to say that Jan and I were very impressed with our over all experience and would certainly recommend Peru for Less to anyone. </p>','Richard <br/>\r\nMichigan, USA <br/>\r\nLima, Cusco and Machu Picchu\r\n','folk-richard.jpg','Richard Folk','',598,0,0,NULL,NULL,NULL),(309,1,'Dear Peru For Less','<p>At the outset, I should say that I was fortunate to team up with you. The success of our trip was mainly due to the planning that we made together. Without your assistance and advice, it would have been completely a different experience. The hotels we picked were very good and in most cases surpassed our expectations. Not only were they comfortable, the people were very hospitable and courteous.</p>\r\n \r\n<p>LIMA - We had a very comfortable stay in Lima. Our guide in Lima, a young man named Miguel, was very knowledgeable and friendly. Not only did he show us the sights in Lima, he also gave us suggestions for shopping and suggested a good dinner restaurant  called \"Junius\". At Junius, we enjoyed an elegant meal and were entertained with a live band and show where we were treated to Peruvian dances and music.</p>\r\n \r\n<p>CUZCO - Our flight to Cuzco was delayed by weather. This was the hardest day of our entire trip. We left the hotel at 3.30am. Our hotel staff at Lima, woke us up in time and graciously provided us breakfast before we left. However our 6.00 am flight was cancelled because of the weather in Cuzco. We did not leave Lima until 2.45 pm, reaching Cuzco just before sunset. Ms. Pamela picked us and dropped us off at the airport.\r\nAfter arrival, we were told of the strike situation in Cuzco and realized that we would have another delay in getting to Ollantaytambo. Ms. Christine in Cuzco was very efficient and concerned to make sure we got to our destination safely. We left Cuzco for Ollantaytambo around 8 pm presuming that the strike was over and it was safe to go. However, on the way we encountered one obstacle after another in a never-ending series that made our 2 hr journey to Sacred Valley into a 6 hr ordeal, finally arriving there at 2 am. Dealing with an angry mob and not knowing what lay ahead kept us in constant worry about our safety. Our driver Mr. Mario deserves more than what we can describe in words. He went above and beyond his duty in order to keep us safe and out of harms way. Mario took us into a safe side street until the violence of the mob subsided, and then ventured cautiously ahead.\r\nBoth he and Christine kept in close touch till the wee hours of the morning in making sure that we were safe and got to our destination unscathed.  </p>\r\n\r\n<p>OLLANTAYTAMBO/MACHU PICCHU - Our hotel in Ollantaytambo was very picturesque, nestled in the valley and beautifully landscaped. Unfortunately, we did not have time to savor its beauty as we were taking the early morning train to Machu Picchu. Machu Picchu was breathtaking, and our hotel \"Inkaterra Pueblo Hotel\" was the highlight of our stay in Peru. Although a bit expensive, I\'d recommend that hotel to anyone who would like to just relax and enjoy splendor and beauty of their property. The hotel offers activities like nature walks, bird watching, orchid garden tour and other educational tours included, at no extra charge. Their food was beyond excellent with Breakfast, Lunch, High Tea and Dinner. Their service was impeccable. We had a wonderful time there we feel our stay there was memorable and well worth it. The Inkaterra  Hotel is in a class by itself.\r\nOur train ride back to Cuzco was leisurely and we enjoyed the scenic beauty of the Valley and the Urubamba River.</p>\r\n \r\n<p>CUZCO/SACRED VALLEY - After a restful night, we met our Guide - Maria Elena Amanca Flores. By far, Maria gets the distinction of being the BEST GUIDE on our PERU/ECUADOR trip. She is not only very knowledgeable about the history and culture of the Peruvian people, she is also a very kind hearted person. She was always attentive to our needs, and treated us like her own family member. We do not think of her as a guide, but more as a good friend. We would welcome another trip to Cuzco and spend more time in this wonderful city as our present stay was very short. I am sure Maria would make it enjoyable for us the next time and we will look forward to it. Once again I have to thank you and Peru for less for arranging the Sacred Valley tour and the sights around Cuzco tours, together. Ordinarily we would have missed the tour due to the strike.  It was a long day for all of us, but very enjoyable, and we had a great time.</p>\r\n\r\n \r\n<p>QUITO - Our trip from Cuzco - Lima - Quito was good. The hotel and food in Quito was good. Quito is a great city. Our guide at the Equatorial monument was a young lady who was also very pleasant. Our Quito guide was a young man who was knowledgeable and helpful. He is also an avid trekker.</p>\r\n \r\n<p>GALAPAGOS - We enjoyed our five days cruising around the Galapagos Islands. Our yacht \"Estrella del Mar\" was a comfortable boat. Fortunately, the waters were not too choppy. The Captain and crew were very nice and always there to help and assist the passengers. Food was great and adequate and no food was wasted. I have to make a special mention of their soups. They were wonderful and out of this world.\r\nOur guide Naturalist guide Estebhan Chavez was excellent.  As we are not swimmers, we did miss out the natural beauty that comes with snorkeling and diving. My husband was happily taking all the pictures and videos he could in this natural oasis. I have not yet checked them out.\r\nOur last day on land, in the Galapagos was leisurely and helped us unwind. We flew back to Quito to return back to the US, happy to be home and yet nostalgic with wonderful memories of the past 2 weeks to carry us through.</p>\r\n \r\n<p>All in all, we had a great time. Our holiday was enjoyable beyond our expectations. We enjoyed Peru much more than Ecuador/Galapagos. We would love to visit this beautiful country Peru again. Not only is the natural scenery exquisite, the Inca history and its civilization has enamored us. But most of all, our memories are cherished by the warmth of the people, their simplicity, honesty, good nature and hard work. \r\nI thank you once again for all the coordination and hard work to put everything in order for us. I can categorically state that it is with your help Chris, and the assistance of the others who work with \'Peru for Less \' our trip was so incredibly enjoyable. You certainly helped a lot in coordinating before and during our trip as unforeseen circumstances required changes that became necessary. We would love to repeat the experience again to visit other places in Peru and South America. </p>\r\n\r\n<p>I enjoyed working with you and will happily recommend you and \"Peru for Less\" to my friends and associates for their future travel to South America.</p>\r\n','Thanks once again.\r\n\r\nSincerely,\r\nShirley &amp; Noel <br/>\r\nCuzco, Machu Picchu, Gal&aacute;pagos\r\n','dias-shirley.jpg','Shirley &amp; Noel Dias','',599,0,0,NULL,NULL,NULL),(310,1,'Dear Peru For Less','<p>Forgive us for not having communicated with you earlier. We have thought about you a lot during our trip to your beautiful country. Everything worked out perfectly and exactly how we had planed. Thank Goodness!   Both air and ground transportation was in perfect order and precision. We are very thankful for all Peru for Less guides\' and drivers\' attention. The excursions were all a resounding success. We were so impressed with the historical knowledge that the tourist guides had. They are walking encyclopedias!</p>','Angel and Ana\r\nFlorida, USA <br/>\r\nPeru Special #1 and Lima\r\n','ana-angel.jpg','Angel and Ana','',600,0,0,NULL,NULL,NULL),(311,1,'Dear Peru For Less','<p>Abby, our trip was fabulous!  Truly an extraordinary vacation!  Special thanks for our Machu Picchu tour guide - Fabrizio was outstanding - we would highly recommend him for all of your tour groups!  </p>','Regards,\r\n\r\nPam <br/>\r\nChicago, IL, USA <br/>\r\nMachu Picchu\r\n','oshea.jpg','Pam OShea','',601,0,0,NULL,NULL,NULL),(312,1,'Dear Su,','<p>Our trip to Peru was even more incredible than we could have imagined!  Every piece of the trip was planned out perfectly.  We were so grateful for the support that we received before we left and while we were in Peru. Whether in the area of the Amazon, Cuzco, Machu Picchu, or Lake Titcaca, we were thrilled with our accommodations. Thank you for making our trip such a memorable experience. </p>Sincerely,','\r\nDebra and Marc <br/>\r\nNew York, NY, USA <br/>\r\nAmazon, Cuzco, Lake Titicaca\r\n','bennet.jpg','Debra and Marc Bennet','',602,0,0,NULL,NULL,NULL),(313,1,'Dear Peru For Less','<p>Our trip to Peru was magnificent! It was so nice to have everything planned ahead of time. You and Nicola did a great job arranging our itinerary, answering our pre-trip questions, and helping with some questions on our first day in Lima. Every place on our itinerary added to the experience of enjoying the friendly and helpful people, sites, and culture: the historical sites in Lima with its crazy traffic, the tranquil oasis of Huacachina, the amazing wildlife of the Ballestas Islands, the flight over the Nazca lines, the beautiful city of Arequipa, the amazing Colca Canyon with its awesome condors, the grand city of Cusco, and the absolutely incredible Machu Picchu.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Miguel met us at the Lima airport and his excitement about the country only added to our anticipation. We appreciated his tips for our stay as well as his recommendations of food specialties to try (the shrimp soup in Arequipa was excellent). Paul with Alegria Tours was especially helpful in Ica and on our Ballestas Islands tour. Allison was most helpful in Cusco. Not only did she meet us on our arrival, but she personally escorted us to the train station for our trip to Aguas Calientes and then to the Cusco airport at the end of our stay. Fabricio\'s knowledge of the Incan civilization and his creative ability to communicate it made the tour of Machu Picchu exceptional.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>All of our accommodations were great. However, Orlando and his staff at Casa Bella in Lima and David at the Hotel Arqueologo in Cusco were especially helpful.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Thanks to Peru for Less and all of your business partners for making our visit to Peru an amazing experience. We will definitely recommend PFL to everyone.</p>\r\n','Best regards,\r\nRuss and Mary <br/>\r\nCleveland, OH <br/>\r\nLima, Ica, Nazca, Arequipa, Colca Canyon, Cuzco, Machu Picchu\r\n','russ-mary.jpg','Russ and Mary Toye','',603,0,0,NULL,NULL,NULL),(314,1,'Dear Peru For Less','<p>Hello. Sorry, it took so long for us to get back to you. We would love to leave a testimonial and submit pictures of our trip to Peru.</p>\r\n \r\n<p>We had an absolutely fabulous time. Peru For Less was amazing in being there for us every step of the way. We love Pamela (would like her mailing address to send her something). Everything went smoothly and without any complications. The Manhattan Inn was a good hotel real close to the airport it\'s a great stopover point. </p>\r\n \r\n<p>Cuzco was wonderful. We love Cuzco. We love the city, the people, the culture, the atmosphere. I would have loved to have spent a few more days there. Our hotel, Suenos Del Inka was great. The hotel took really good care of us. Giving us coca tea twice a day helped us tremendously in settling in. We had a great view of Cuzco. It was so beautiful. I would highly recommend this hotel for Cuzco. We loved the Sacred Valley tour. The landscaping was breathtaking. Wished we could have shopped a little more.</p>\r\n \r\n<p>The train ride to Aguas Calientes was incredible. It was relaxing, beautiful and peaceful. We met fellow travelers and made some new friends. </p>\r\n \r\n<p>Machu Picchu was everything we had imagined. The history, the culture, archaeologically ruins were amazing. What an incredible view of life there once was there. We\'re forever grateful for being able to experience one of the Wonders of the World.</p>\r\n \r\n<p>Machu Picchu overall, is a city still growing up to the mountains which surround it. Don\'t look at what you see, but the people that live there and bring the city to life. </p>\r\n \r\n<p>We changed our stop on our train trip coming back from Aguas Calientes. We gave Peru For Less advance notice and Peru For Less was there to greet us. We guys are awesome.</p>\r\n \r\n<p>Overall, Peru For Less was great. The personal service was impeccable. We were basically waited on hand and foot. The comfort of knowing they were always around made our trip even more relaxing and enjoyable. </p>\r\n \r\n<p>We would highly, highly recommend Peru For Less to anyone. We look forward to using Peru For Less again on our future travel adventures.</p>\r\n \r\n<p>Aimee, thanks so much for all your help. </p>\r\n','Teresa <br/>\r\nRobert  Sloan\r\nEl Cerrito, CA, USA <br/>\r\nLima, Cuzco, Machu Picchu\r\n','valdivia-teresa.jpg','Teresa Valdivia','',604,0,0,NULL,NULL,NULL),(315,1,'Dear Peru For Less','<p>Our trip was wonderful, all the guides, drivers and people who helped during the trip were great. I would recommend your company to anyone who is traveling to South America. \r\nThanks for a great trip\r\n</p>','Brian\r\nHouston, TX, USA <br/>\r\nCuzco and Machu Picchu \r\n','','','',109,0,0,NULL,NULL,NULL),(316,1,'Hi Rylee,','<p>Thank you for your email. We are back in the freezing cold of England! Peru was incredible; I hope to return in next couple of years. The trip to Machu Picchu was amazing, it was really well organized. Thank you very much for all your hard work.\r\nThanks for all your help over the past few months.\r\n</p>','Tim <br/>\r\nSomerset, UK <br/>\r\nCuzco, Machu Picchu, \r\n','','','',110,0,0,NULL,NULL,NULL),(317,1,'Hi Rylee,','<p>We had a wonderful time. Thank you very much for helping me plan this awesome trip. Thank you so much for being so quick and so helpful. You have been great! Everyone from the drivers to the tour guides was great! </p>\r\n\r\n<p>I would highly recommend your company.</p>\r\n','Mariana\r\nNapa, CA <br/>\r\nCuzco, Machu Picchu, Lake Titicaca\r\n','','','',111,0,0,NULL,NULL,NULL),(318,1,'Dear Peru For Less','<p>We\'re back and fine. An interesting experience! No location, or event anywhere, can compare to Machu Picchu.</p>\r\n<p>GUIDES\r\nWe enjoyed your guides. Loved Edgar (in Lima), interesting and knowledgeable. Armando (in the Amazon), knowledgeable and really worked hard. Julio (in Chiclayo), was the best, -- great sense of humor. Everyone was very kind and accommodating.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>We liked Chiclayo and Trujillo, but no one includes it probably because itâ??s not adventuresome.\r\nMy older sister wasnâ??t interested, but found the area and contrast with the rest of Peru interesting. The people today, in general, are not museum people; they just want to be wowed! They do not want to read or learn anything.</p>\r\n','Thank you for all your help.\r\nJean\r\nUSA <br/>\r\nIquitos, Cuzco, Machu Picchu, Chiclayo, Trujillo & Lima\r\n','','','',113,0,0,NULL,NULL,NULL),(319,1,'Dear Peru For Less','<p>We had a wonderful trip to Peru. We enjoyed the Hotel Arqueologoâ?? small, quaint, clean, friendly. Lares Trek was amazing!  Enjoyed it a lotâ?¦..however, near the highest points we did have to take it slowâ?¦.became out of breath easily, but no sickness. Guide, porters, cooks â?? very nice.</p>','Ruth <br/>\r\nTennessee, USA <br/>\r\nCuzco and Lares Trek\r\n','','','',115,0,0,NULL,NULL,NULL),(320,1,'Dear Peru For Less','<p>When we prepared to take this holiday in Peru and South America, many people warned us of dangers, of theft etc. While on one level we paid heed to such warnings, we also endeavored to make our own judgments. We actually felt so very safe everywhere we went, the people were an absolute delight.  Peru for Less had a lot to do with our feeling secure and from them we learnt how to continue our journey safely through Bolivia Argentina and Chile.</p>\r\n \r\n<p>We told Peru for Less what we wanted to do and see and they helped us put the first 20 or so days together. From the minute we stepped off the plane, someone from the company was there to meet us, to take us to our hotel and give us the information as to pick time next day for the tour they had planned for us. These tour operators in each destination made sure we understood the details of the tours etc and were very helpful. They would also leave us a contact number in case we needed further information or help. </p>\r\n \r\n<p>Rather than chose our own basic 3 star hotel we asked Peru for Less to choose for us as they would know from experience, which were the nicer hotels, and we were right. We often had the very best views of a snowy mountain top or a mountain stream rushing over rocks.  Each hotel supplied a good buffet breakfast; the only thing we missed was being able to make our own cuppa in our own way!!! Itâ??s not easy to find a good takeaway shop in Peru or anywhere in South America, (we are very spoilt in Australia).</p>\r\n \r\n<p>If you want to see the best of Peru and have it all organised for you, leave it to Peru for Less to make your plans for you and you will be glad you did!   </p>\r\n','Leonie and Joyce\r\nBrisbane, Queensland. Australia <br/>\r\nLima/ Ica/ Nazca/ Arequipa/ Colca Canyon/ Cuzco/ Machu Picchu/ Amazon\r\n','','','',117,0,0,NULL,NULL,NULL),(321,1,'Hi Rylee,','<p>Sorry, I didn\'t initiate the contact earlier. We have been busy catching up with work and everything. I was just talking to one of my friend about our trip and how amazing Machu Picchu was.</p>\r\n \r\n<p>More than that how you guys made our trip easier and worry free. We do a lot of traveling and some of it is easy enough to make our own arrangements. But I knew this wasn\'t going to be one of them. Boy, was I glad that we found you. Before we got to Cusco and found out there might be train strike, you guys already made an arrangement so that  in case there was one, we wouldn\'t miss Machu Picchu. And Machu Picchu was the top reason we went all the way to Peru. Needless to say because you might have heard again and again, you were so organized and every thing was well planed out.  Your restaurant and hotel suggestions were outstanding. </p>\r\n \r\n<p>We really enjoyed our train trip to Machu Picchu from Cusco and to Puno from Cuzco.</p>\r\n \r\n<p>All of the tour guides were wonderful. They were very knowledgeable and friendly. We appreciate your patience with us when we first tried to plan this trip. We started out only with Lima and Machu Picchu. Every time I called you, we ended revising it several times. It became a custom made trip with lean budget. Thanks again.</p>\r\n \r\n<p>I also give special thanks to Cristina at Cusco working so hard to make sure the schedule went smooth.</p>\r\n \r\n<p>Good luck to you with Peru for Less and I will keep in touch.</p>\r\n \r\n<p>We won\'t hesitate to contact you next time we are planning another trip.   </p>\r\n','Thanks,\r\nYasmine\r\n','','','',121,0,0,NULL,NULL,NULL),(322,1,'Dear Peru For Less','<p>Thank you so much for organizing our resent cruise in the Galapagos on the M/V Evolution.  We loved the boat. The crew was friendly, the food was outstanding, the guide was very knowledgeable; and the wildlife was spectacular.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Definitely one of the best trips we have taken.</p>\r\n','Kind regards\r\nMike &amp; Liz <br/>\r\nUSA <br/>\r\nGalapagos Cruise \r\n','','','',118,0,0,NULL,NULL,NULL),(323,1,'Dear Peru For Less','<p>At the outset, I should say that I was fortunate to team up with you. The success of our trip was mainly due to the planning that we made together. Without your assistance and advice, it would have been completely a different experience. The hotels we picked were very good and in most cases surpassed our expectations. Not only were they comfortable, the people were very hospitable and courteous.</p>\r\n \r\n<p>LIMA - We had a very comfortable stay in Lima. Our guide in Lima, a young man named Miguel, was very knowledgeable and friendly. Not only did he show us the sights in Lima, he also gave us suggestions for shopping and suggested a good dinner restaurant  called Junius. At Junius, we enjoyed an elegant meal and were entertained with a live band and show where we were treated to Peruvian dances and music.</p>\r\n \r\n<p>CUZCO - Our flight to Cuzco was delayed by weather. This was the hardest day of our entire trip. We left the hotel at 3.30am. Our hotel staff at Lima, woke us up in time and graciously provided us breakfast before we left. However our 6.00 am flight was cancelled because of the weather in Cuzco. We did not leave Lima until 2.45 pm, reaching Cuzco just before sunset. Ms. Pamela picked us and dropped us off at the airport.\r\nAfter arrival, we were told of the strike situation in Cuzco and realized that we would have another delay in getting to Ollantaytambo. Ms. Cristine in Cuzco was very efficient and concerned to make sure we got to our destination safely. We left Cuzco for Ollantaytambo around 8 pm presuming that the strike was over and it was safe to go. However, on the way we encountered one obstacle after another in a never-ending series that made our 2 hr journey to Sacred Valley into a 6 hr ordeal, finally arriving there at 2 am. Dealing with an angry mob and not knowing what lay ahead kept us in constant worry about our safety. Our driver Mr. Mario deserves more than what we can describe in words. He went above and beyond his duty in order to keep us safe and out of harms way. Mario took us into a safe side street until the violence of the mob subsided, and then ventured cautiously ahead.\r\nBoth he and Christine kept in close touch till the wee hours of the morning in making sure that we were safe and got to our destination unscathed.  </p>\r\n\r\n<p>OLLANTAYTAMBO/MACHU PICCHU - Our hotel in Ollantaytambo was very picturesque, nestled in the valley and beautifully landscaped. Unfortunately, we did not have time to savor its beauty as we were taking the early morning train to Machu Picchu. Machu Picchu was breathtaking, and our hotel \"Inkaterra Pueblo Hotel\" was the highlight of our stay in Peru. Although a bit expensive, I\'d recommend that hotel to anyone who would like to just relax and enjoy splendor and beauty of their property. The hotel offers activities like nature walks, bird watching, orchid garden tour and other educational tours included, at no extra charge. Their food was beyond excellent with Breakfast, Lunch, High Tea and Dinner. Their service was impeccable. We had a wonderful time there we feel our stay there was memorable and well worth it. The Inkaterra  Hotel is in a class by itself.\r\nOur train ride back to Cuzco was leisurely and we enjoyed the scenic beauty of the Valley and the Urubamba River.</p>\r\n \r\n<p>CUZCO/SACRED VALLEY - After a restful night, we met our Guide - Maria Elena Amanca Flores. By far, Maria gets the distinction of being the BEST GUIDE on our PERU/ECUADOR trip. She is not only very knowledgeable about the history and culture of the Peruvian people, she is also a very kind hearted person. She was always attentive to our needs, and treated us like her own family member. We do not think of her as a guide, but more as a good friend. We would welcome another trip to Cuzco and spend more time in this wonderful city as our present stay was very short. I am sure Maria would make it enjoyable for us the next time and we will look forward to it. Once again I have to thank you and Peru for less for arranging the Sacred Valley tour and the sights around Cuzco tours, together. Ordinarily we would have missed the tour due to the strike.  It was a long day for all of us, but very enjoyable, and we had a great time.</p>\r\n\r\n \r\n<p>QUITO - Our trip from Cuzco - Lima - Quito was good. The hotel and food in Quito was good. Quito is a great city. Our guide at the Equatorial monument was a young lady who was also very pleasant. Our Quito guide was a young man who was knowledgeable and helpful. He is also an avid trekker.</p>\r\n \r\n<p>GALAPAGOS - We enjoyed our five days cruising around the Galapagos Islands. Our yacht \"Estrella del Mar\" was a comfortable boat. Fortunately, the waters were not too choppy. The Captain and crew were very nice and always there to help and assist the passengers. Food was great and adequate and no food was wasted. I have to make a special mention of their soups. They were wonderful and out of this world.\r\nOur guide Naturalist guide Estebhan Chavez was excellent.  As we are not swimmers, we did miss out the natural beauty that comes with snorkeling and diving. My husband was happily taking all the pictures and videos he could in this natural oasis. I have not yet checked them out.\r\nOur last day on land, in the Galapagos was leisurely and helped us unwind. We flew back to Quito to return back to the US, happy to be home and yet nostalgic with wonderful memories of the past 2 weeks to carry us through.</p>\r\n \r\n<p>All in all, we had a great time. Our holiday was enjoyable beyond our expectations. We enjoyed Peru much more than Ecuador/Galapagos. We would love to visit this beautiful country Peru again. Not only is the natural scenery exquisite, the Inca history and its civilization has enamored us. But most of all, our memories are cherished by the warmth of the people, their simplicity, honesty, good nature and hard work. \r\nI thank you once again for all the coordination and hard work to put everything in order for us. I can categorically state that it is with your help Chris, and the assistance of the others who work with \'Peru for Less \' our trip was so incredibly enjoyable. You certainly helped a lot in coordinating before and during our trip as unforeseen circumstances required changes that became necessary. We would love to repeat the experience again to visit other places in Peru and South America. <p>\r\n\r\n<p>I enjoyed working with you and will happily recommend you and \"Peru for Less\" to my friends and associates for their future travel to South America.</p>\r\n','Thanks once again.\r\n \r\nSincerely,\r\nShirley &amp; Noel <br/>\r\nSaint Joseph, Missouri <br/>\r\nCuzco, Machu Picchu, Galapagos \r\n','','','',119,0,0,NULL,NULL,NULL),(324,1,'Dear Peru For Less','<p>Hi Aimee...This trip really was a once in a lifetime experience. We enjoyed every minute of it!</p>\r\n  \r\n<p>We just loved the hotel in Cusco - the Casa San Blas. It was so cute and cozy and everyone was so nice and helpful. We just had a short walk downhill to reach the main plaza and shopping and restaurants.</p>\r\n \r\n<p>Our drivers were all great. All the people from Peru For Less were wonderful - especially Veronica in Puno and Christina in Cusco. I think Christina deserves a medal and time off for all the time she put in over the problems due to the strike. I hope that you will pass along to her office how great we thought she was. Our guides were just as wonderful - Bruno in Puno, Rosa in Lima, Fabrizio in Machu Picchu, Antonio and Juan Carlos in Cusco. They were all very knowledgeable and easy to get along with.</p>\r\n \r\n<p>The bus ride from Lima to Nazca was way better than we had hoped. I have never been on a bus where you could lay the seat back and nap if you wanted (not that we wanted to nap - too much to see!!!!) - or where you were served meals by a bus attendant. The ride went by so quickly! The flight over the Nazca Lines was phenomenal and we really enjoyed it.</p>\r\n \r\n<p>In Puno I was affected by the altitude on the first evening and early the next morning but by the time we were out visiting the floating islands in Uros, I was doing much better. I just kept drinking coca tea and eating coca candies. Denis luckily wasn\'t affected at all. I didn\'t realize that I was going to be walking uphill for so far on the island of Taquile to get to the top for lunch, but I\'m proud to say that I made it and also survived the walk down the other side of the hill. It was another great day - we felt we were in the midst of a National Geographic special.</p>\r\n \r\n<p>The city of Cuzco was my favorite place and I\'m glad we got to spend a few days there. Unfortunately it rained most of the time that we were up at Machu Pichhu but that really didn\'t make a difference. It was still a magical place. Apart from the ruins, being in the midst of the jungle-covered Andes was so impressive to me. I couldn\'t stop looking up at the mountains. We were glad we had the chance to take the van back to Cuzco from Ollantaytambo instead of the train because it was such a scenic trip by van up to the top of a mountain and then back down into the valley. I know the strike caused you and your co-workers more work than you needed but for us everything ran so smoothly.</p>\r\n  \r\n<p>Our final tour along the Sacred Valley was also a beautiful trip. We scrambled to the top of the ruins at Ollantaytambo and trooped through the market at Pisac and enjoyed every minute of it.</p>\r\n \r\n<p>The food was delicious everywhere we went and we tried to taste a lot of the Peruvian specials. I am hooked on Pisco Sours and we brought home 2 bottles of Pisco so we can make some here.</p>\r\n \r\n<p>All in all, we can\'t say enough good things about all our drivers, aides, guides and tours. We took over 650 pictures so we\'ll never forget a minute of the trip.</p>\r\n \r\n<p>As a home-based travel agent myself I know I will definitely come back to Peru For Less if I have customers who want to travel to Peru. It\'s nice to know that there is such a reliable travel company out there, as we did hear a few horror stories from other travellers about the companies they were dealing with.\r\n \r\n<p>Again, thank you for all the help and the super-enjoyable holiday. We both fell in love with Peru and the people there.\r\n','Margaret &amp; Denis\r\nWinnipeg, Canada <br/>\r\nLima, Nazca, Puno, Cuzco and Machu Picchu\r\n','margaret-denis.jpg','Margaret &amp; Denis','',611,0,0,NULL,NULL,NULL),(325,1,'Dear Peru For Less','<p>We just wanted to express our gratitude to you and everyone at Peru For Less for making our trip one of the most memorable experiences we\'ve ever had. We truly appreciate the effort your entire team put forth in taking care of all of our requests especially since everything was so last minute. We especially want to thank you personally for taking the time to meet us in Lima and show us around town on our free day. By the way, your restaurant suggestions were superb. Everything you arranged for us was spot on. The hotels, transportation and tours were even more than we expected!</p>\r\n\r\n<p>We were really impressed with the personal attention that we got at each city we visited. All of your representatives (Miguel - Lima, Christina - Cusco, Fabricio - Macchu Pichu, and David-Puno), really went out of their way to make sure that this was truly a trip of a lifetime. A special thanks to Christina and Fabricio for all of their special help at Macchu Pichu.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Usually we don\'t go for \"guided tour\" packages, but I have to say that all of our experiences were fantastic. And your suggestion to go to the rainforest was one of the most memorable. </p>\r\n\r\n<p>All of the guides we had were extremely knowledgeable, and very entertaining.  And all of the tours were amazing. The Uros islands of Lake Titicaca were unbelievable!</p>\r\n\r\n<p>This was one of the greatest trips ever, and thanks to everyone at Peru for Less for making it happen!  We\'re telling everyone we know that they have to visit Peru and to call you when they\'re ready.</p>\r\nSincerely,','\r\nJoe and Sarah <br/>\r\nLas Vegas, Nevada <br/>\r\nLima, Puerto Maldonado, Cuzco, Machu Picchu \r\n','messina.jpg','Joe and Sarah Beck-Messina','',610,0,0,NULL,NULL,NULL),(326,1,'Dear Matt,','<p>I haven\'t been able to stop telling all of my friends what an amazing time Adria and I had in Peru. Trying to cover three destinations -- Lima, Cusco (&amp; Macchu Picchu) and Puerto Maldonado (&amp; the rainforest) in six days could have been a disaster, but thanks to your expert assistance every step of the way, it was a fantastic trip!</p> \r\n \r\n<p>From planning the trip beforehand to all the logistics in Peru, everything worked out so smoothly and effortlessly. You were so accommodating working on a tight timeline as we only booked our trip a month before, and made sure every detail was taken care of before we even stepped on the plane. Not having to worry about the logistics of our trip allowed Adria and me to enjoy every moment we had there!</p>\r\n \r\n<p>As for the itinerary that you crafted for us, we couldn\'t have asked for anything better! The two-day trek to Machu Picchu was a great way to get a taste of the area and the site while still allowing us to see other parts of Peru. We felt well taken care of and more importantly, very safe, every step of the way from getting to the train station in Cusco to the actual trek. Our tour guide, Pavel, could not have been better suited to Adria and me--he was young, knowledgeable, and fun. The suggestion for staying in the jungle was perfect too. The lodge was very comfortable and the guides were fantastic!</p>   \r\n \r\n<p>It was so nice of you to make time to meet Adria and me during our short time in Lima. What otherwise could have been dead time was instead a real spark for the rest of our trip. It was great to meet you, put a face to a voice and and hear firsthand about your experiences in Peru after many phone calls and emails.</p>\r\n','Thanks again!  \r\nCindy\r\nSan Francisco, California, USA <br/>\r\nLima, Machu Picchu, Puerto Maldonado\r\n','cindy.jpg','Cindy','',609,0,0,NULL,NULL,NULL),(327,1,'Hey Rylee!','<p>Thanks again so much for taking such good care of me out there! Things have been pretty hectic since I got back here - but it\'s all good.</p>\n<p>Ok here\'s my glowing review of your fine services!</p>\n<p>When I set my itinerary for travel in Peru I had a very clear vision of exactly what kind of trip I wanted: an active adventure immersed in nature and culture. With this vision driving my actions and <strong>24 hours before I flew to my South American destination- I emailed Peru for Less with a slightly frantic message- \"Please help me plan my entire 2 week trip to Peru within the next hour and a half. Thanks.\" Within minutes I had a reply from Rylee,</strong> a salesgirl from Peru for Less. <strong>She quickly became my little guardian travel angel, reading my mind and sending itineraries tailored to my exact desires.</strong> She went well beyond the call of duty, answering all my questions and even taking her computer home with her so she could work after hours to answer any more of my questions and finalize my last minute itinerary. Rylee called me at the airport the next morning to assure me that a representative from Peru for Less would be at the airport in Lima to greet me upon my arrival and I got on the plane feeling confident that all my travel needs would be taken care of. <strong>Peru was incredible, everything I needed it to be. Thank you Peru For Less and Rylee for making my last minute adventure such a smashing success!</strong> Call me if you come to Los Angeles and I\'ll show you around my town!</p>\n<p>Thanks a lot! Parvati </p>\n','Survivor: Cook Islands - 6th Place Survivor: Micronesia- Winner Los Angeles, CA, USA <br/>\r\nTraveled to: Iquitos, Amazon, Lima, Cuzco, Lares Trek and Machu Picchu\r\n','parvati.jpg','Parvati Shallow','\"Thank you Peru For Less and Rylee for making my last minute adventure such a smashing success!\"',100057,0,0,NULL,'2014-09-10 23:08:09',NULL),(328,1,'Dear Peru For Less','<p>Abby - I have been meaning to email you and Nicola.</p>\r\n \r\n<p>The trip was absolutely perfect, no problems and your tour guides were excellent. Everything was well organized and everyone was there when they should have been. They were even nice enough to come into the airports with us when we had flights to catch and steered us in the right direction. This was so helpful to us, being in a foreign country\'s airport can be confusing. We do have pictures, we have to sort them out and I will then email them to you. Machu Picchu was incredible and we loved Fabricio. He did a great two hours and we learned a lot about the history of the ruins, Allison was also wonderful as well as Miguel in Lima. They both did a very good job for us.</p>\r\n \r\n<p>Yes, we will highly recommend you; I\'ll be back in touch with you soon with some pictures. Please forward my email to Allison and Miguel as I do not have their email addresses, only Fabricio\'s.</p>\r\n \r\n<p>Thank you so much for everything, you made our trip a pleasure.</p> \r\n\r\n','Carole &amp; Bill \r\nBoca Raton, FL, USA <br/>\r\nLima, Cuzco, Sacred Valley and Machu Picchu \r\n','carole-bill.jpg','Carole &amp; Bill','',607,0,0,NULL,NULL,NULL),(329,1,'Dear Rylee,','<p>This was my first time using a travel company and my first time traveling by myself outside the United States to South America. I want to thank Rylee for her knowledge and expertise with customizing my quick weekend getaway to Machu Picchu in between business locations prior to my departure from the US. Cristina was assigned as my local contact and she was always on time and very professional with my weekend itinerary. She provided answers to all my questions and made an excellent dinner recommendation at Don Tomas in Cuzco. She is an awesome part of the Peru for Less team and had great answers and tips for all of my questions. I was nervous and had my doubts about going on this adventure by myself, but Peru for Less and their team delivered exactly what was discussed in the itinerary and the transportation arrangements were flawless. The trip to Machu Picchu was an amazing experience and completely breathtaking. I made my personal pilgrimages to one of the high points in the ruins to overlook the city with the mountain peak in the background. </p>Sincerely, ','\r\nAndrew <br/>\r\nMesa, AZ. <br/>\r\nCuzco and Machu Picchu\r\n','Kristich.jpg','Andrew Kristich','',606,0,0,NULL,NULL,NULL),(330,1,'Dear Peru For Less','<p>Peru is a fantastic Country. The things to see and do are extraordinary. We chose Peru as a vacation destination mostly because we wanted to see Machu Picchu. I contacted Peru for Less to help us with this leg of our itinerary. They were able to procure our train tickets, book our hotel (Machu Picchu Pueblo is amazing!) and organize a private guided tour for us. The trip would not have gone as smoothly if not for Peru for Less.</p>\r\n<p>Making travel plans in a foreign country can be challenging. It was so nice and easy to have a contact like Peru for Less to help us along. </p>\r\nSincerely,','\r\nEleanor <br/>   \r\nVirgina, USA &amp; France <br/>\r\nMachu Picchu\r\n','wachter.jpg','Eleanor Wachter','',605,0,0,NULL,NULL,NULL),(331,1,'Hi Rylee,','<p>My wife, children and I just got back from a trip to Peru booked through Peruforless, and it was wonderful!  Everyone was very helpful and friendly, and the weather was beautiful.  Rylee, thanks for your work in helping us get it together. </p>\r\n<p>The company did an excellent job of taking care of all the small arrangements necessary to enjoy seeing the country.  From the moment we stepped off the plane, Peruforless made sure everything went exactly as we wanted it to - they were even accommodating when we wanted to change our itinerary in Machu Picchu at the last minute.  I would definitely book through them again if we return to the area.</p>','Dan <br/>\r\nFort Riley, KS, USA.\r\nCuzco and Machu Picchu','dan-pace.jpg','Dan Pace','',612,0,0,NULL,NULL,NULL),(332,1,'Dear Peru For Less','<p>Please accept my apologies for not replying sooner.  We had an excellent time in Peru, thanks to you and the staff of Peru For Less.  The hotels were comfortable with professional staff (especially Casa Andina in Cuzco) and the tours were well done.  We appreciated being part of a small group.  Best of all was having a \"handler\" to take care of us on our arrivals and departures.  With Cristina\'s help, our transport to and from airports and train stations went very smoothly. </p>','Thank you for organizing our itinerary - it was perfect.  We have already recommended Peru For Less to our friends.\r\nRicha <br/>\r\nUSA\r\nCuzco, Machu Picchu and Puerto Maldonado','richa-wilson.jpg','Richa Wilson','',613,0,0,NULL,NULL,NULL),(333,1,'Dear Peru For Less','<p>We could not imagine a better tour than our trip to Peru.  The guides anticipated our needs, and they knew what we wanted better than we thought we did. We are so happy we were not in one of the big groups that struggled around us, and there is nothing we would change about our trip.   Peru for Less is less cost (you could pay more but not get any better service) and less hassle, but certainly more freedom, choice, and cultural knowledge. Every connection was on-time, and it was so comforting to arrive in an airport and see our name on a placard.</p>','With much appreciation,\r\n\r\nShanon <br/>\r\nSan Francisco, CA, USA.\r\nLima, Arequipa, Cuzco and Machu Picchu','shanon-sedivy.jpg','Shanon Sedivy','',614,0,0,NULL,NULL,NULL),(334,1,'Dear Peru For Less','<p>We had asked Peru for Less for a local country experience with an emphasis on many archeological sites and visits to locations, as well as accommodations in lesser traveled areas. We got what we asked for and really \"had it our way\". All four hotels where we stayed were great, with excellent breakfast buffets and were wonderfully situated. The staff was friendly and helpful despite our very limited local language skills. The first hotel (Yucay) had beautiful gardens and architecture; the second (Ollantaytambo) a birds-eye view of the ruins; the third (Aqua Calientes near Machu Picchu) had a Jacuzzi and river view; and the forth (Cuzco) had a view of the famous Cathedral. Peru for Less did a great job with transfers, arranging our (mostly private) tours, calling us with updated information, fixing any minor difficulties we might have, and doing everything on time. They picked up and stored luggage transferred to us many times and did a great job moving us from place to place. The tours were fabulous, especially seeing the Pisac ruins with an archeologist describing the sites. He also explained special sites to look for at the future ruins we would be touring. We highly recommend traveling with Peru for Less and will travel again with them if the occasion arises.</p>\r\n<p>Hope this finds you well,</p>','Don &amp; Ann <br/>\r\nWaterloo, New York, USA <br/>\r\nSacred Valley, Machu Picchu, Cuzco\r\n','cobb.jpg','cobb','',615,0,0,NULL,NULL,NULL),(335,1,'Dear Peru For Less','<p>We had a wonderful trip in Peru. Almost everything went well. Every time we came out off the bus, train or plane, someone was waiting for us. We never had to wait. Also, when we had a tour the guide, they came on time. The people we met were all very kind and explained everything. When something wasn\'t clear, they phoned the office to confirm. The hotels were all very good, especially in Cuzco where we had lovely rooms. However, we liked the others very much too!</p>\r\n<p>In Arequipa we had a \"reality tour\". We heard that there weren\'t many people who booked this tour, but we can highly recommend it!</p>\r\n<p>The four of us had a lovely time in Peru. Our daughter and her boyfriend stayed there for a longer time. We had to get back to go to work again.</p>\r\n<p>Thank you for all the good things!</p>','Johan <br/>\r\nNetherlands <br/>\r\nCuzco, Machu Picchu \r\n','johan-blind.jpg','johan-blind','',616,0,0,NULL,NULL,NULL),(336,1,'Dear Peru For Less','<p>I wanted to send you a note to thank you for helping me arrange the most fantastic vacation of my life. My trip to Peru was amazing and I thank you and Peru for Less for making it an unforgettable experience. </p>\r\n<p>I was very satisfied with the services, care and attention I was given by everyone I encountered in Peru; from the tour guides, to the pick up agents, to the drivers! Everyone was very professional, respectful and knowledgeable of the many hidden gems and rich Peruvian culture. As you know, I was traveling alone and never once felt unsafe. The representatives of Peru for Less were always waiting for me when I landed at all my destinations and gave me the best advice for all the places I visited. Peruvian people are very hospitable, caring and beautiful and your team sure fits that description. Attached is a photo of Uros Island on Lake Titicaca which was the highlight of my trip. Visiting Lake Titicaca and staying on Amantani Island was a very surreal experience that I highly recommend. </p>\r\n<p>Given that I had such a great experience with Peru for Less, I will definitely use your services again when I travel to Brazil!</p>\r\n<p>Thanks for making my vacation so awesome!</p>\r\n<p>P.S. Thanks to Sandra and the people in Operations in Cuzco!</p>','Patria <br/>\r\nSeattle, Washington, USA <br/>\r\nTravel Destination/Package: Lima, Puno, Cuzco, Machu Picchu, Arequipa\r\n','cabral.jpg','cabral','',617,0,0,NULL,NULL,NULL),(337,1,'Dear Peru For Less','<p>Firstly, I must again thank you for the offer of dinner and a show in Lima, for our last night in Peru.  However, after a very long drive back from Nazca, we were all very happy to have drinks and dinner in the Las Americas Hotel in Lima.  We did have two shows of folkloric music, both on the train to Machu Picchu and the Hiram Bingham train back to Cuzco.  </p>\r\n\r\n<p>The hotels were all excellent. The food at the restaurants was always very good, and, coupled with the wines we selected for dinner, a very good value!  We especially enjoyed our dinner in Lima at the Las Americas hotel.  Also, the lunch of Avocado Reina at lunch, en route to and from Nazca, was fabulous.  This hotel had particularly clean washrooms, as well.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>The time it took to get to and from Nazca was long, for a short 30 minute flight.  But, it could not have been missed.  Everyone enjoyed the flight, and no one threw up! In Nazca, we enjoyed the rustic, but interesting Hotel Majoro with its beautiful grounds.  We had drinks outside, which was quite wonderful.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Machu Picchu was breathtaking.  Our guide was knowledgeable and his two hour tour was interesting and enjoyable.  He took the photo that I am sending with this message. The tour of the Sacred Valley was also very interesting.  The guide, once again was very knowledgeable and paced the walking, giving us ample time for photographs.  The starting times were not too early (except of course when we had a plane to catch!).</p>\r\n\r\n<p>The drivers were all very good - we were especially impressed with the driver in and around Cuzco.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>As for a testimonial, we all agreed that we received good value for our dollars.  The tours were all professionally handled, and the timing and pace of the tours were very appropriate.  Meals, on our own, were all excellent.  Thank you for the suggestions.  In Cuzco, we especially enjoyed the Inca Grill, Cicciolina, and Incanto (our favorite, went twice!).</p>\r\n\r\n<p>We will definitely recommend Peru-for-Less to anyone who wants a hand-crafted personalized tour.  Having someone to meet us with a sign was very comforting when arriving in a new city.  And, we never could have done all of the organization of transfers between airports, hotels, sites, and train stations on our own.  Thanks again to those who re-organized the trip to Machu Picchu the next day, as a result of the roads being covered with rubble - apparently a strike.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Thanks to everyone on your team who made our trip to Peru so memorable.  It truly was \"a trip of a lifetime!\"</p>\r\n','James, Phyllis, Roger, Louise, Robin, Beverly, Lorne, Sheila <br/>\r\nBritish Columbia, Canada <br/>\r\nCuzco, Puno, Nazca, Lima, Quito\r\n','stich.jpg','stich','',618,0,0,NULL,NULL,NULL),(338,1,'Hello Rylee,','<p>How was the Peru trip? It was fantastic, great and well-organized. Thank you very much, we had a super time.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>After we arrived in Lima at 10:30PM Oscar was there greeting us, giving us all the vouchers, explaining all the details and got us to the hotel before midnight. After a short night we took off early for Puerto Maldonado by plane, where Jhinn (our super guide for the rainforest) picked us up for the boat ride to Refugio Amazonas. We spent four great days there. The lodge is something we never experienced before: relaxing, good food, nice bar, candlelight dinners, hammock in room to relax and the jungle right outside without a wall in between. Jhinn was always there to guide us. Our time in Cuzco was great. Casa Andina was a great place to stay and get used to the high altitude. Coca tea also really helped. The in-house restaurant was splendid. We are now settled in again at home and will re-live the trip to Peru through our pictures, videos and memories. </p>\r\n\r\n<p>Thanks to you we had the time of our life with no worries, only new discoveries and adventures every day. Everything was organized to perfection. We enjoyed all the hotels, especially Casa Andina Private in Cuzco, Hotel Las Dunas Resort in Ica and lastly the mind bogglingly home of Victor Delfin, The Second Home in Barranco, Lima.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Your ground transportation on all the wonderful sightseeing tours was great and all the drivers and guides were very professional and courteous. Special mention to all the organizers and guides, starting with Oscar at the Lima airport there to greet us; Jhinn who kept us in good spirits in the rain forest; Maria who knew all the history of the ruins and temples in Cuzco; the Sacred Valley guide Fabricio, who knew more than the books about Machu Picchu; Liliane who took us to Colca Canyon, the hot springs and a great folklore show; and all the others.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>We will definitely recommend you and your company to everyone going to Peru.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>So thanks again,</p>\r\n','Peter &amp; Monika <br/>\r\nMalibu, California, USA <br/>\r\nPuerto Maldonado, Cuzco, Machu Picchu, Lake Titicaca, Arequipa and Colca Canyon, Nazca, Ica and Lima\r\n','monica-fuzz.jog','monica-fuzz','',619,0,0,NULL,NULL,NULL),(339,1,'Doniece,','<p>Just a quick note to let you know that our trip was fabulous! We would go again to South America. The Peru for Less group was terrific - always there to pick us up, friendly and efficient. Our hotels were great, food great and our favorite town was Aqua Calientes. Our hotel room there was literally on the river which showed a beautiful, sunny day in Machu Picchu. We all loved the whole experience!</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Thanks for your help in arranging this and we will refer you to any of our friends and family who might need help with a trip.</p>\r\n\r\n','Sharon <br/>\r\nTexas, USA\r\nPeru \r\n','','','',129,0,0,NULL,NULL,NULL),(340,1,'Dear Peru For Less','<p>Yes, we had a great time and thank you very much for helping us organize the trip and putting up with our lots of questions and requests. Machu Picchu was such a breathtaking experience and we all enjoyed it very much. Inkaterra was also great! Wish we could spend an extra night there.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>My brother, Masaya, is now thinking about visiting Peru. I told him your e-mail address. He might contact you shortly. Hope you can help him out his trip as well.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Thank you so much!</p>\r\n','Best,\r\n\r\nTomoko <br/>\r\nTokyo, Japan <br/>\r\nLima, Cuzco, Machu Picchu \r\n','','','',128,0,0,NULL,NULL,NULL),(341,1,'Hey Rylee,','<p>The trip was great and all things went well with your company and guides. Our guides were great and everything was well organized and quality. You have already been recommended to a friend traveling out there later this year.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Thanks,</p>\r\n','Tristan <br/>\r\nNew York, New York, USA <br/>\r\nCuzco and Machu Picchu','','','',134,0,0,NULL,NULL,NULL),(342,1,'Dear Juan,','<p>We had a fabulous trip in Peru and will recommend Peru for less anytime. Christina, Carlos and Fabrizio could not have been more helpful and really made our stay a treat. Thanks for making our stay wonderful.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Regards,</p>\r\n','Ann <br/>\r\nLondon, UK <br/>\r\nCuzco, Machu Picchu\r\n','','','',125,0,0,NULL,NULL,NULL),(343,1,'Rylee,','<p>The trip was a total success and Peru for less was all-around great. The guides were awesome and so were all the drivers.  When our flight home from Lima was delayed I called the 24 hour number and our pick up time was changed quickly and without any hassle.  </p>\r\n \r\n<p>Everyone was awesome. Next time if your still there, we can make coffee happen. :)</p>\r\n','Omar <br/>\r\nChicago, Illinois, USA <br/>\r\nLima, Cuzco and Machu Picchu\r\n','','','',123,0,0,NULL,NULL,NULL),(344,1,'Dear Peru For Less','<p>How are you? We had a wonderful time in Peru...very prompt and great service! My children really had a great time! I am glad I found you guys!</p>','Rani <br/>\r\nTexas, USA\r\nCusco, Machu Picchu','kodali.jpg','kodali ','',620,0,0,NULL,NULL,NULL),(345,1,'Hi Rylee','<p>All home now. Thanks so much as everything! The trip was great and everything was well organized! Zig zag served great dinner in Arequipa. Thanks for the recommendation</p>\r\n \r\n<p>It was OUR joy to meet you and Garzo. Hopefully my little one Shannon can hook up with you guys sometime in the future especially if you head to Huaraz or if Garzo is playing music in Lima.</p>\r\n \r\n<p>Go check out trip advisor forum where I keep mentioning you. Also you can use me as a customer reference whenever you have a client that is not sure of doing a tour with you</p>\r\n \r\n<p>Thanks for all your help!</p>\r\n','David <br/>\r\nLima, Arequipa, Puno, Cuzco and Machu Picchu\r\n','doran.jpg','doran','',621,0,0,NULL,NULL,NULL),(346,1,'Hi Rylee, ','<p>We are still in Peru... We did a few days in Puno, Lake Titicaca, and now back in Cusco after we finished Machu Picchu.... The trip and experience were great... The tour guide Jose and Wayki Trek were great.  The hotel was nice, and Allison was helpful in picking us up and answering our questions... We leave for home tonight and arrive in New York tomorrow morning....We have had a wonderful time. </p>\r\n\r\n<p>Thanks again,</p>\r\n','Robert <br/>\r\nFlushing, New York, USA\r\nCusco and the Salkantay Trek to Machu Picchu','petrocelli.jog','petrocelli','',641,0,0,NULL,NULL,NULL),(347,1,'Howdy Rylee,','<p>We had an absolutely amazing trip - it really was perfect.  My father and I had such a great trip and I thank you so much for setting it all up. Everyone was great.  Early this week I will spend some time to go over and formulate a detailed response.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>It was perfect! We\'ll chat soon. </p>\r\n','Courtney <br/>\r\nDallas, TX, USA\r\nLima, Cuzco, Machu Picchu, Puerto Maldonado','corley.jpg','corley','',622,0,0,NULL,NULL,NULL),(348,1,'Dear Rylee,','<p>The trip was awesome! We truly enjoyed every part of it. All of the tours were very informative and the guides very patient even when we always seemed to be the last ones back on the tour bus. Our favorite was the guide we had while in Cuzco. I believe his name was Juan Carlos. He truly gave us insightful information about Inca life and was hilarious! The hotels were beautiful and our Peru for Less representative was very helpful in any of the changes we needed to be done.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>We appreciate all the effort put into the trip. Thank you!</p>\r\n','Nadia <br/>\r\nWest Covina, CA, USA\r\nCusco and Machu Picchu','alvarez.jpg','alvarez','',623,0,0,NULL,NULL,NULL),(349,1,'Dear Peru For Less','<p>The trip was fantastic. I think you guys did very good job at arranging the local support for us. Tours guides started on time and information such as pickup time was provided in advance, which definitely made it even more relaxing. </p>\r\n\r\n<p>Your local staff was great. Alison was very help for me when I forgot to pack my staff before leaving for the hike, to which I was very grateful. Also like the hiking company, small enough to know all the people in the hiking group. </p>\r\n\r\n<p>I think the best part of the trip is that I met really good people on the tours and remained friends with them. </p>\r\n\r\n<p>I will definitely recommend you to other friends. </p>\r\n','Thanks, \r\n\r\nJennifer <br/>\r\nNew York, USA\r\nLima, Cusco, Inca Trail','huang.jpg','huang','',625,0,0,NULL,NULL,NULL),(350,1,'Dear Peru For Less','<p>All the people - guides, boat operators, lodge management and personnel were extremely affable, pleasant and kind.  I found this to be the case throughout our contact with Peruvians everywhere.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>The boat ride from Puerto Maldonado to Refugio Amazonas took about 2 1/2 hours.  We had around a dozen people on board.  They prepared a unique lunch wrapped in banana leaves.  It was some rice based concoction and very good.  The boat ride to Tambopata took about 4 hours including 2 stops at ranger stations as we entered the refuge.  The boats were handled professionally and safely.  All locals on the boat were good people.  We were surprised at how shallow the river is.  They had to poll in certain areas on the way from Refugio Amazonas to Tambopata.  This was not the rainy season.  </p>\r\n\r\n<p>Our specific guide - \"William\" - was on time, very pleasant, hard working, knowledgeable and fun.  He was incredibly patient and helpful as well.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>The biggest surprise was the \"clay lick\".  We got up at 4:30am to get to the hillside across from what is touted as the world\'s largest clay lick for macaws and parrots of every variety.  Little by little, the parrots flew to different perches as dawn approached.  You could hear the sounds of dozens of parrots more than you could see them.  About the time the sun was barely on the horizon - what we call magic time in the film business - it was like someone pulled a lever and the sky exploded with parrots.  I have never seen anything like it.  The sun was shining on their underbellies reflecting the incredible colors of their feathers.  Parrots were flocking in large numbers coming out of everywhere.  The sound was almost deafening.  This explosion of birds went on for at least 45 minutes.  You have to understand that in all my travels to tropical places, I have never seen more than 2 macaws in one place and they were not in the wild.  I wish I could have gotten a closer look at the flocks but they were moving so fast it was hard to keep them in the lens finder.  It was truly a mind blowing morning.   </p>\r\n\r\n<p>I found Peru For Less to be exemplary in their administration, communication and planning.  </p>\r\n','Good work.\r\n\r\nJohn <br/>\r\nAustin, TX\r\nTambopata Research Center','bernardoni.jpg','bernardoni','',626,0,0,NULL,NULL,NULL),(351,1,'Dear Peru For Less','<p>Am just writing to let you know that my friends and I had a marvelous time in Peru! Maria Elena and Fabricio were outstanding guides - can\'t thank them enough. There were no problems with logistics either - Cristina took good care of us. </p>\r\n \r\n<p>In addition, the various sites and food were excellent. We did have a blast! For me, Machu Picchu and the hike up to Huayna Picchu were incredible. I am certainly glad you offered hotels such as the Inkaterra Pueblo as part of your list, because the stay there was more than we could have hoped for. In hindsight, we should have stayed there longer!</p>\r\n \r\n<p>Also I wanted to thank you for setting up this itinerary (in spite of my multiple questions and revisions). Once again, our sincerest thanks to all your staff who made this stay so enjoyable.</p>\r\n','Tellis <br/>\r\nNew York, USA\r\nLima, Cuzco, Machu Picchu','party.jpg','party','',627,0,0,NULL,NULL,NULL),(352,1,'Hello Rylee,','<p>You made planning our trip easy by always replying quickly and giving us the information we needed. We appreciated the flexibility in choosing the tours and hotels.\r\nAll the arrangements for planes, trains, buses, hotels and tours worked out like clockwork. It was so nice to be greeted by friendly people on arrival in a new place and not to have to worry about hotels. We also appreciated to have the phone numbers of the different people who looked after us, just in case. We never needed them!\r\nThe tours were in small groups. The tour guides were extremely knowledgeable and proud of their country. We learned a lot about history, plants, animals and customs. The tours offered by Peru for Less are well chosen to explore different climates, geography and cultures of the country.\r\nAlexander, our guide from Puno, was also superb. He took us to an Uros Island further from Puno, so there were no other tours there. On Amantani he made sure everybody was comfortable with their host family. At Taquile he landed in a non touristy spot, took us through farmers fields to the ridge on the island and we ended up at a secluded sandy beach, where some of us played ball with local youth. We had an introduction to soap making from a herb and the significance of the belts that the men wear. We finished with a most delicious trout meal. We really appreciated that Alexander knew how to bring us away from touristy places and closer to the people.\r\nThe highlights for us were Machu Picchu, the home stay at Amantani Island and the days in the jungle.</p>\r\n','Thanks again for always being there for us.\r\n\r\nVerena and Bill\r\nOttawa, Canada\r\nLima, Puerto Maldonado, Cuzco, Puno, Arequipa, Nazca, and Ica','verena.jpg','verena','',628,0,0,NULL,NULL,NULL),(353,1,'Dear Peru For Less','<p>As an experienced single traveler, I usually make my own travel arrangements including local tours.  However, Peru seemed a bit challenging as it would involve three cities, five different hotel stays, travel by planes, trains, taxis and buses, and tours desired at each location. Based on what was offered on their WEB site, I selected Peru for Less and was very glad I did. The entire trip went off without a single hitch. There was someone to meet me with a sign stating my name at all the airports, and train stations. Before each departure a Peru for Less representative waited with me for the local tour operator to pick me up.  The tour agents in Lima , Juan Pablo and Daniel Smith set up the entire tour flawlessly.  Their field representative in Cusco was a very personable and likeable young lady named Kari. She was simply amazing. I was continually impressed by her intrinsic enthusiasm and commitment to my having the easiest and best trip ever. Kari even printed out my plane boarding passes, walked me through the tax and ticket lines and carried one of my bags. You can\'t beat that for service. The hotel in Cusco, Picoaga was a former mansion with an inner courtyard complete with fountain. The rooms were immaculate, quiet and furnished in a Peruvian colonial style but with all the modern amenities. Unless you want to pay a small fortune, there are on very few hotels in Las Aguas Calientes also known as the Machu Picchu town that are up to American standards. I stayed at the Orquideas Hotel. The price was reasonable by Las Aguas Calientes prices and although it was simple, it was clean and quiet with a staff that would consistently go out of its way to ensure that your stay was an pleasant one. The tours \r\n(Cusco, Sacred Valley and Machu Picchu) were very enjoyable with informed, English speaking guides. I am returning to South America next year and Peru for Less would be my Travel Agency of choice. I am thinking of a trip to Iguazu Falls via Argentina or a Buenos Aires, Rio combination trip.</p>\r\n','Tom <br/>\r\nMassachusetts, USA\r\nCusco, Machu Picchu, Puno','gribbons.jpg','gribbons','',629,0,0,NULL,NULL,NULL),(355,1,'Kristina,','<p>Our trip to Peru, Cuzco, and Machu Picchu was great. Peru For Less did everything they said they would and always on time.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>During the planning phase, I e-mailed and talked to Kristina many times. Each time, she answered my questions and followed up later whenever she said she would. She made suggestions for hotels (Ramada in Lima) and (Del Prado Inn in Cuzco) which I accepted and with which we were fully satisfied. She listened to me when I outlined what we wanted to do and how much time we had. Our time was short at my son\'s request as he had to get back to his job. She responded with a custom tour with certain options. Within a day or two, we worked out the details and finalized things. When she said she would reply back with an answer or an option within one day, she did just that. When I am hiring someone, I expect good service and Kristina delivered every time. There were no surprises when we arrived. I am totally pleased with Kristina\'s service.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Allison met us at the airport upon our arrival in Cuzco and was very friendly and courteous. She picked us up the next morning for Machu Picchu and again the final morning to go to the airport. Each time she provided very complete answers to our questions and even put up with my poor Spanish. Upon arrival at out hotel, she escorted us in and told the hotel worker who we were and helped get us initially settled. At the airport, she went in with us and took us through baggage check and the airport tax counter. She had also printed our boarding passes for this Cuzco-Lima flight. The morning of the train ride to Machu Picchu, she escorted us into the train station and made sure we had all our tickets for the train and for Machu Picchu. She left only when we assured her we knew where the line was for the train. Escorting us in these situations reduced the stress of guessing things or figuring them out as we went along. A nice touch. My main concern after arrival was that one of our transfers would be late or not show up at all. You know what that would do to our trip. Every time, we depended on Peru For Less, Allison was there ON TIME and WITH GOOD SERVICE. And with a smile.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>I made a good choice hiring Peru For Less. Everything was done professionally. Thank you.</p>\r\n','Sincerely,\r\n\r\nTed &amp; Bryan <br/>\r\nArizona, USA \r\nCusco and Machu Picchu','stanton.jpg','stanton','',631,0,0,NULL,NULL,NULL),(356,1,'Dear Peru For Less','<p>I would say that <strong>it was a truly fantastic holiday and Peru is simply awesome</strong> (us Brits don\'t often use that word but it is the only one that covers it!).</p>\r\n<p>I have been recommending Peru for Less to colleagues and friends like a newly converted missionary!</p>\r\n<p>What I think was so helpful is that<strong> all the drudge of organizing trips or pick-up\'s and hotels etc was simply removed and we could maximize our time in Peru actually enjoying it.</strong> We were never let down and we always had a friendly face to meet us and sort us out.</p>\r\n<p>What\'s more you go out of your way to help - our baggage failed to show up in Lima and Miguel rang to make sure it was on the next flight. He also took us for our tour to the Gold Museum and we were there too early but this was great because we said we liked to bird-watch and he and the driver took us to places to do this until it was time to go to the museum - fantastic! Christina (the tornado!) in Cusco helped to sort out a visit to the Amano Museum in Lima on our last day because Juan Carlos (our guide for the Cusco City trip) had recommended it as an amazing place for historical textiles - a passion of mine - it was incredible and really rounded off our visit perfectly - so big thanks to both of them too!</p>\r\n<p><strong>Peru was a staggering list of highlights; Machu Picchu, condors, the Jungle, antiquity, the Ballestas Islands, the food, the people, textiles and the landscape and it is going to take some time to process and will never leave</strong> us and it was made all the better by the excellent organization of Peru for Less - we met other people with other companies not anywhere near as pleased and I think this comes down to you being on the ground and knowing your business inside out.</p>\r\n<p>Hotels: We were especially pleased with the upgraded accommodation at Casa San Blas in Cusco - what a very special place and staff team! Casa Andina was excellent and it was nice to have that continuity of provision.</p>\r\n<p>So once again thank you and all the teams; fixers, drivers, guides and hotels that looked after us so well. <strong>we really felt at home in Peru - and we know how hard you all work so we can play!</strong></p>\r\n','Cheers,<br/>\r\nEmma and Paul (London, UK) <br/>\r\nTraveled to: Lima, Puerto Maldonado, Cuzco, Puno, Arequipa, Nazca, Ica\r\n','emma-paul.jpg','emma-paul','\"Thank you.. We really felt at home in Peru - and we know how hard you all work so we can play!\"',100052,0,0,NULL,'2014-09-10 22:55:09',NULL),(357,1,'Dear Peru For Less','<p>Our tour in Peru was very well organized. The hotels were either very good or excellent (for example, the Colca Lodge). Special thanks to Christina who helped us a lot in Cuzco. We enjoyed the tour immensely. You did a very good job.</p>','Regards,\r\n\r\nDan <br/>\r\nFlorida, USA\r\nArequipa, Cuzco, Machu Picchu and Puno','marinescu.jpg','Dan Marinescu','',633,0,0,NULL,NULL,NULL),(358,1,'Hi Rylee,','<p>Overall, we had a very nice trip. The guides who helped us were very well informed and friendly.  The Inti Raymi festival was quite impressive. After a great tour of Machu Picchu, we loved the train ride from Aguas Calientes to Ollantaytambo. I\'ve never seen a train with armchairs - very nice. All of our transfers went smoothly and any questions we had were answered. Thank you Rylee, it was a memorable trip for us.</p>','Carol <br/>\r\nMiles City, MT, USA\r\nCuzco and Machu Picchu','stoltz-carol.jpg','Carol Stoltz','',634,0,0,NULL,NULL,NULL),(359,1,'Dear Cristina and Tracy,','<p>Thank you so much for all of your efforts toward making my recent trip to Peru an adventure beyond my expectations! Your support and attention to detail allowed me to relax, feel secure and enjoy the travel experience completely. The hotels you selected for me were great and the itinerary made excellent use of my brief travel time. A special thanks is due for your willingness to accommodate my last minute request for an itinerary change which turned out perfectly. I am already planning a return trip through Peru for Less in 2010. You\'re the best!!</p>','Faith <br/>\r\nAmherst, NY, USA\r\nLima, Cuzco, Sacred Valley and Machu Picchu','hoffman-faith.jpg','Faith Hoffman','',636,0,0,NULL,NULL,NULL),(360,1,'Dear Peru For Less','<p>We are acclimatizing back to California and wanted to let you know how amazing our trip was. All the contacts were so organized and took VERY good care of us - from meeting us at airports, to checking us in to hotels, to helping with rearrangements when the local strikes made changes in plans necessary. All the tour guides - Maria Elena in Cuzco, Fabrizio in Machu Picchu, and Angel in Lake Titicaca - were fantastic. They were extremely knowledgeable, and also full of stories of history, legend and culture.\r\nMuchas Gracias for helping make this trip to Peru an unforgettable experience,</p>\r\n','Jim and Karen <br/>\r\nCalifornia, USA\r\nCuzco, Machu Picchu and Puno','malin-chi.jpg','Jim and Karen Malin','',637,0,0,NULL,NULL,NULL),(361,1,'Hi Jennifer!','<p>Thank you for planning a WONDERFUL trip to Peru for us.  My dad and I will remember our trip for the rest of our lives.  Once you were responsible for our itinerary everything seemed to go smoothly and once we were in Peru someone was always there to greet us and make all our transfers simple and easy.  We always had all our paperwork on time and everything was well planned (thank you to Allison as well).  I would also like to mention the excellent team we had with us when hiking the Inca Trail.  David and Jose were awesome!  They were very knowledgeable and always there to help if we needed it.  The porters were exceptional as well and deserve significant tips for the jobs that they do.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Thank you for everything... a job well done!</p>\r\n\r\nBest, \r\n','Lauren <br/>\r\nUSA\r\nCuzco, Inca Trail, Machu Picchu and Puno\r\n','howes-lauren.jpg','Lauren Howes','',638,0,0,NULL,NULL,NULL),(362,1,'Dear Kelly,','<p>My trip was problem-free and magical! All transfers were on time and a detailed explanation of the next day\'s weather, clothes, times and tips decreased any anxiety for traveling alone.</p>\r\n \r\n<p>This is my first trip to Peru and my first trip traveling alone, but I will return with the family after such a positive experience.</p>\r\n \r\nThanks, \r\n','Angelica <br/>\r\nMiami, FL, USA<br/>\r\nAyacucho, Cuzco and Machu Picchu','jimenez-angelica.jpg','Angelica Jimenez','',639,0,0,NULL,NULL,NULL),(363,1,'Dear Peru For Less','<p>We had a super trip, and would use Peru For Less again.</p>\r\n\r\nTHANKS!\r\n','Lori <br/>\r\nCalifornia, USA\r\nCuzco, Inca Trail and Machu Picchu','','','',112,0,0,NULL,NULL,NULL),(364,1,'Dear Peru For Less','<p>Yes, the trip went perfectly. Thanks for al the arrangements. It was a great experience! I will recommend Peru For Less to others that may want to visit Peru.</p>\r\n\r\nThanks,\r\n','Rohit <br/>\r\nPittsburg, PA, USA\r\nCuzco and Machu Picchu','','','',114,0,0,NULL,NULL,NULL),(365,1,'Dear Deanna,','<p>We had a great trip. The Hotel in Ica was very nice and the fossil tour to the desert was awesome. We actually found a fossilized spine and rib cage from an unknown animal. It was so cool dusting the sand away and finding the pieces. </p>\r\n\r\n<p>Nazca was even better than expected. Our guide was very nice and helpful. The trip to the lines was awesome along with Palpa. The Casa Andina Hotel was clean and everyone was helpful. </p>\r\n\r\n<p>We had a wonderful time. I was sorry it was so short: we should have stayed longer.</p>\r\n','Steve <br/>\r\nCoral Springs, FL, USA\r\nIca and Nazca','','','',116,0,0,NULL,NULL,NULL),(366,1,'Hi Rylee,','<p>Our trip was really great and your local representatives were all wonderful as well!  Thank you so much for all of your help. </p>\r\n\r\n<p>Regards,</p>\r\n','Ayaka <br/>\r\nNew York, NY, USA\r\nCuzco and Machu Picchu','','','',130,0,0,NULL,NULL,NULL),(367,1,'Dear Peru For Less','<p>I want to thank you and \"Peru for Less\" for helping me and my daughter have a once-in-a-lifetime experience in Cuzco and Machu Picchu. We will recommend your services to anyone else we know who might be visiting South America.</p>\r\n<p>We\'re now back in the US now but are looking at our pictures with great memories of our time in Peru. </p>\r\n\r\nThanks again! \r\n','Brian <br/>\r\nIllinois, USA\r\nCuzco and Machu Picchu','','','',131,0,0,NULL,NULL,NULL),(368,1,'Susan,','<p>Thank you, we did enjoy our trip and the hotels were fine. The guide for the Lord of Sipan area (Maria) was great, and she did full tours. Peru is wonderful, and hopefully more people will travel to the north. The Wayki Tour trek to Macchu Picchu was fantastic! Their staff were very friendly and helpful, the food was gourmet and the guide was terrific! I hope you will recommend them to other clients.</p>\r\n\r\nThanks again, \r\n','Kathy <br/>\r\nMichigan, USA\r\nLima, Trujillo, Chiclayo, Cuzco, Inca Trail and Machu Picchu','','','',132,0,0,NULL,NULL,NULL),(369,1,'Jennifer,','<p>The trip was wonderful, and we had no real issues or concerns to speak of. The list of recommended restaurants in Cuzco was great and the food was terrific in each location! River rafting was also fun. </p>\r\n<p>ALL our contacts and guides were friendly, knowledgeable and expressed genuine concern for us. I will gladly pass on Peru For Less to anyone who asks for my recommendation.</p>\r\n\r\nThanks for your assistance,\r\n','Doug <br/>\r\nUSA\r\nArequipa, Cuzco, Machu Picchu and Puno','','','',133,0,0,NULL,NULL,NULL),(370,1,'Dear Peru For Less','<p>We just wanted to let you know that we had a very good time in Peru! We enjoyed all the different cities that we went to. Tell Miguel (who gave us the Lima City tour, that he was the best tour guide that we had the whole trip). \r\nWhen talking to other people thinking about going down to Central or South America we definitely recommend Latin America For Less.\r\nMy wife and I would like to be kept on any distribution email lists that you have for any specials or promotional deals that your company may run. We are thinking about possibly going back to South America or Central America next summer.</p>\r\n\r\nThank you for working with us to help plan a great trip.\r\n','Dan <br/>\r\nWashington DC, USA\r\nLima, Arequipa, Machu Picchu and Puerto Maldonado','','','',135,0,0,NULL,NULL,NULL),(371,1,'Dear Kristina,','<p>I am writing to thank you for such an amazing experience my girlfriend and I had on the Salkantay trek in Cuzco.\r\nI was so impressed with the enthusiasm and knowledge of our guide Jose. The food was delicious and very hearty - we felt stuffed the whole time!\r\nIt was great to arrive at our campsite and have our tent and a hot drink waiting for us. It was rejuvenating to soak our tired legs in the natural hot springs on third night as well - what a bonus! \r\nAfter traveling around the world for 9 months this trek to Machu Picchu has been the most memorable and enjoyable to date. Your ongoing help and advice during the booking process was very professional and made me feel confident to use Peru For Less - it was worth every penny!</p>\r\n\r\nThank you,\r\n','Jamie &amp; Cristy <br/>\r\nCanada\r\nCuzco, Salcantay and Machu Picchu','','','',136,0,0,NULL,NULL,NULL),(372,1,'Hi Rylee,','<p>I hope you are doing well.  We returned on Tuesday evening from our wonderful trip.  Thanks for all the help in planning it and all the decisions you helped us make.  The guides you arranged were wonderful, especially Rodrigo in Quito and Ronnie for the Sacred Valley.  Ronnie was really good, informative, had a great sense of humor and very knowledgeable.  Miguel in Lima was also good and very helpful!\r\nIn Ecuador, our boat the Galapagos Legend was great, very well managed and organized and we were constantly in awe of what we saw and the experiences we had.</p>\r\n<p>Machu Picchu was SO amazing, even with all the pictures we had seen, we were not prepared for the sheer wonder of it all. \r\nYou and Peru for Less did a great job for us.  Everything went like clock work, all was very well planned and organized, and great choices were made by you for us.  Everyone was lovely, kind and very helpful! In fact, everyone we met was wonderful, eager to help, tell us about their country and make us feel at home.</p>\r\n<p>It was a wonderful, once in a life time trip. Thank you so much!</p>','Robin <br/>\r\nSanta Monica, CA, USA\r\nCuzco, Machu Picchu and Galapagos Islands','','','',137,0,0,NULL,NULL,NULL),(373,1,'Jennifer,','<p>Yes - back home safe, and sound.  A summary of the trip would have to be that it was just wonderful.  I can\'t tell you how impressed we were about how smoothly everything went and what an incredible standard of care we received from the Peru for Less employees and agents in each town.  I would say that the trip and all the transport went off without a single hitch and the whole experience was so much more than we had even dared to hope.  A big thank you to you and the team for such a great experience.</p>\r\n \r\n<p>Our tour in Lima was good: the guide was knowledgeable and spoke very good English.</p>\r\n \r\n<p>In Ica someone was waiting for us at the bus station, even though were over an hour late.  The Mossone Hotel in Haucachina is amazing - the whole building was lovely. We had a fun day on the dune buggies and went sandboarding.  We ran into Omar, who had collected us from the airport and was with another tour group - when we came to collect our luggage he had left some chocolates for us with the hotel!  Please thank him for his kindness and tell him they were delicious.</p>\r\n \r\n<p>The Hotel Oro Viejo in Nazca was also extremely nice.  The staff was very accommodating; we didn\'t leave until 9:30pm and they were very happy for us to wander in and out and use the very nice pool and common area all day, even after we had checked out.  The Nazca Lines overflight was very good - we went in the morning and as there was no wind it was smooth.</p>\r\n \r\n<p>The night bus to Arequipa was amazing, just like first class air travel.  Casa Andina is nice and provided very good breakfast.  The tour was good and the highlight was the Santa Catalina Monastery, which was beautiful.  The Colca Canyon Tour was was a magical experience.  We saw vicunas on the way, which we were very pleased about.  We also visited the hot springs, which we enjoyed very much. </p>\r\n \r\n<p>When we arrived in Cuzco we were picked up at the airport by Christina, who was just amazing.  She gave us such a lot of information it was almost overwhelming. She drew maps, recommended places to eat and things to see, and gave us tips on visiting Machu Picchu. We did the tour of the city with Juan Carlos, who was just an incredible guide - very knowledgeable and full of interesting insight.  We also did the Sacred Valley tour with him the next day and were very impressed with him.  We took the bus to visit Pisac were very impressed by the ruins. By going on our own we got to spend as much time as we wanted there and really explore and the bus trip was an adventure.</p>\r\n  \r\n<p>When we were in Machu Picchu it was great fun hiking up all the steps of Wayna Picchu in the dark with lots of little flashlights bobbing.  We did the 7am hike up the mountain and it was very quiet as we stayed ahead of most of the crowds.  It was amazing and totally worth the early start. </p>\r\n \r\n<p>We had no problems at all and a great trip in general. I\'m sure we will be back to Peru at some stage - we have yet to see the Amazon.</p>\r\n \r\n<p>Thanks again to you and all your team,</p>\r\n','Jon &amp; Catherine <br/>\r\nUnited Kingdom\r\nLima, Ica, Nazca, Arequipa, Cuzco and Machu Picchu','','','',138,0,0,NULL,NULL,NULL),(374,1,'Hi Rylee,','<p>We had a grand time in Peru last week. First, I want to mention that Tracy in Cuzco provided wonderful customer service, and if there is any way you can recognize her excellent service internally, please do so. </p>\r\n<p>We loved the place we stayed at in Cuzco: comfortable rooms and the guy at the front desk was very friendly and helpful. I would strongly recommend this hotel to anyone who\'s heading to Cuzco. Tours there were also nice and well arranged.\r\nI want to thank you for making it so easy to arrange this trip to begin with. It was relatively painless to set this up and you were very flexible in customizing the itinerary on the fly. It is not always this easy to make a trip fit into the schedule we can afford. I would definitely recommend Peru For Less to friends. </p>\r\n\r\n<p>All in all: beautiful scenery, nice friendly people and great food. We had great time in Peru and enjoyed every bit of it.  </p>\r\n\r\nThanks again, ','Yayoi <br/>\r\nSan Jose, CA, USA\r\nLima, Cuzco and Machu Picchu','yayoi.jpg','Yayoi Land','',635,0,0,NULL,NULL,NULL),(375,1,'Rylee,','<p>We thank you for our fabulous honeymoon to Peru! We had so much fun, and really enjoyed having the flexibility to customize our own tour. We liked having smaller group tours, and loved having private tours as well. Everything went very smoothly, which allowed for the most stress-free vacation possible. We really enjoyed having David and Fabricio as our tours guides in Cuzco and Machu Picchu. Pedro was also an amazing ecotourism guide. He knew so much about the Amazon rainforest. All of our guides were so friendly, spoke English very well, and loved their jobs. They were all very knowledgeable and had a strong passion for their country. We loved all of our accommodations, especially Casa De Campo in Cuzco.\r\nPeru is such an amazing country with so many hidden jewels, and Peru For Less did an amazing job of uncovering those for us and allowing us to see so many amazing sights. We can not wait till we go back so we can discover even more of Peru.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Thank you so much and we look forward to visiting Peru again very shortly. </p>\r\n','Ryan and Trisha <br/>\r\nDallas, TX, USA <br/>\r\nLima, Ica, Paracas, Cuzco, Machu Picchu and Puerto Maldonado\r\n','carlile-trisha.jpg','Ryan and Trisha Carlile ','',640,0,0,NULL,NULL,NULL),(376,1,'Dear Rylee,','<p>Our trip to Cuzco, Machu Picchu and surrounding areas was incredible!! Thank you for helping us plan this fantastic 10 day trip in June.  My wife, daughter and I had a wonderful experience on the 4 day Inca Trail hike thanks to Peru For Less and our guide Bryan and all the services which were provided.  It was an amazing experience and the memories will last a life time. Our hotel The Arque&oacute;logo in Cuzco was wonderful!  The staff was great, very helpful and they went out of their way to accommodate all of our early departures.  Our room was very clean and comfortable.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>The Inti Raymi Festival was an enriching experience that helped us further appreciate the culture of the indigenous people of Peru.  All our guides were very knowledgeable and ensured our safe arrival and departure to the many Inca sites we visited.  The transportation provided was very comfortable and convenient.  The Sacred Valley and Pisac Market tour were great experiences as well.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Thanks again to Peru For Less for giving us more than we could have imagined.\r\nOur only regret is that we could not stay longer!</p>\r\n\r\nSincerely,\r\n','Louie, Lisa and Angelina <br/>\r\nSan Jose, CA, USA\r\nCuzco, Inca Trail and Machu Picchu\r\n','rocha-louie.jpg','Louie, Lisa and Angelina Rocha','',624,0,0,NULL,NULL,NULL),(377,1,'Hi Rylee,','<p>The trip was wonderful! Peru is a spectacularly beautiful country and all the people we met always the way were kind and friendly and wonderful.  All our hotels were beautiful and our excursions very enjoyable. The pickups and transferred were perfect, in general.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>We really appreciated everyone\'s assistance through the strike.  Because of everyone\'s diligent work, the inconveniences were minimal.\r\nAs for the many, many people that took care of us along the way, they were all excellent!!!!!!! Kind, friendly, knowledgeable, on time, helpful...the list of adjectives can go on and on.  I appreciate each and every one of them.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Thank you for all that you did to make our trip a wonderful success. We truly appreciated it.</p>\r\n\r\nPeace,\r\n','Lourdes <br/> \r\nStaten Island, NY, USA\r\nLima, Ica, Nazca, Arequipa, Puno, Cuzco and Machu Picchu\r\n','','Lourdes Ferrer','',120,0,0,NULL,NULL,NULL),(378,1,'Hello Rylee,','<p>I just wanted to let you know that all of our tours worked out great.  Our tour guides were very competent, especially Mary in Cuzco (for the City Tour) and Fabricio in Machu Picchu. Tracy was also very punctual and helpful. I will certainly recommend PFL to my friends that want to go to Peru.</p>\r\n\r\nThanks again,\r\n','Maria <br/> \r\nItaly\r\nLima, Arequipa, Puno, Cuzco and Machu Picchu\r\n','','Maria Cirulli','',122,0,0,NULL,NULL,NULL),(379,1,'Rylee,','<p>Our trip, although short, was excellent. We were met by a Peru for Less representative at every transfer location, which gave us a great sense of security.  Machu Picchu was beyond expectation and our guide, Fabricio, was outstanding. We gained a much deeper appreciation of the Ruins with his tour.  When we return to Peru for a \"vacation\" rather than work, we will definitely make plans with Peru for Less.</p>\r\n\r\nThank you again for all your help,\r\n','Kim <br/> \r\nHornell, NY, USA\r\nCuzco and Machu Picchu\r\n\r\n','','Kim Meacham','',124,0,0,NULL,NULL,NULL),(380,1,'Hi Rylee,','<p>We loved the time we spent in Cuzco. The guides were excellent, and unbelievably knowledgeable. The last nightâ??s meal and musical performers were outstanding.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Thank you for all of your help.<(p>\r\n\r\nBlessings,\r\n','Hank <br/>\r\nWichita, KS, USA\r\nCuzco and Machu Picchu\r\n','','Hank Volden','',126,0,0,NULL,NULL,NULL),(381,1,'Hi Rylee, ','We had a wonderful time and cannot thank you enough for all you did for us! Everything went VERY smoothly and it was almost surreal to not have to \"think\" about anything because everything was taken care of for us  thank you, thank you!','Marisa Robisch \r\nSan Francisco, CA, USA\r\nJune/July 2009\r\nLima, Cuzco and Machu Picchu\r\n','','Marisa Robisch ','',127,0,0,NULL,NULL,NULL),(382,1,'Dear Peru For Less','<meta http-equiv=\"Content-Type\" content=\"text/html; charset=utf-8\"><meta name=\"ProgId\" content=\"Word.Document\"><meta name=\"Generator\" content=\"Microsoft Word 11\"><meta name=\"Originator\" content=\"Microsoft Word 11\"><link rel=\"File-List\" href=\"file:///C:%5CDOCUME%7E1%5CADMINI%7E1%5CCONFIG%7E1%5CTemp%5Cmsohtml1%5C03%5Cclip_filelist.xml\"><o:smarttagtype namespaceuri=\"urn:schemas-microsoft-com:office:smarttags\" name=\"country-region\" downloadurl=\"http://www.5iantlavalamp.com/\"></o:smarttagtype><o:smarttagtype namespaceuri=\"urn:schemas-microsoft-com:office:smarttags\" name=\"place\" downloadurl=\"http://www.5iantlavalamp.com/\"></o:smarttagtype><o:smarttagtype namespaceuri=\"urn:schemas-microsoft-com:office:smarttags\" name=\"City\" downloadurl=\"http://www.5iamas-microsoft-com:office:smarttags\"></o:smarttagtype><o:smarttagtype namespaceuri=\"urn:schemas-microsoft-com:office:smarttags\" name=\"PlaceName\" downloadurl=\"http://www.5iantlavalamp.com/\"></o:smarttagtype><o:smarttagtype namespaceuri=\"urn:schemas-microsoft-com:office:smarttags\" name=\"PlaceType\" downloadurl=\"http://www.5iantlavalamp.com/\"></o:smarttagtype><o:smarttagtype namespaceuri=\"urn:schemas-microsoft-com:office:smarttags\" name=\"address\"></o:smarttagtype><o:smarttagtype namespaceuri=\"urn:schemas-microsoft-com:office:smarttags\" name=\"Street\"></o:smarttagtype><!--[if gte mso 9]><xml>\r\n <w:WordDocument>\r\n  <w:View>Normal</w:View>\r\n  <w:Zoom>0</w:Zoom>\r\n  <w:HyphenationZone>21</w:HyphenationZone>\r\n  <w:PunctuationKerning/>\r\n  <w:ValidateAgainstSchemas/>\r\n  <w:SaveIfXMLInvalid>false</w:SaveIfXMLInvalid>\r\n  <w:IgnoreMixedContent>false</w:IgnoreMixedContent>\r\n  <w:AlwaysShowPlaceholderText>false</w:AlwaysShowPlaceholderText>\r\n  <w:Compatibility>\r\n   <w:BreakWrappedTables/>\r\n   <w:SnapToGridInCell/>\r\n   <w:WrapTextWithPunct/>\r\n   <w:UseAsianBreakRules/>\r\n   <w:DontGrowAutofit/>\r\n  </w:Compatibility>\r\n  <w:BrowserLevel>MicrosoftInternetExplorer4</w:BrowserLevel>\r\n </w:WordDocument>\r\n</xml><![endif]--><!--[if gte mso 9]><xml>\r\n <w:LatentStyles DefLockedState=\"false\" LatentStyleCount=\"156\">\r\n </w:LatentStyles>\r\n</xml><![endif]--><!--[if !mso]><object\r\n classid=\"clsid:38481807-CA0E-42D2-BF39-B33AF135CC4D\" id=ieooui></object>\r\n<style>\r\nst1\\:*{behavior:url(#ieooui) }\r\n</style>\r\n<![endif]--><style>\r\n<!--\r\n /* Font Definitions */\r\n @font-face\r\n	{font-family:Verdana;\r\n	panose-1:2 11 6 4 3 5 4 4 2 4;\r\n	mso-font-charset:0;\r\n	mso-generic-font-family:swiss;\r\n	mso-font-pitch:variable;\r\n	mso-font-signature:536871559 0 0 0 415 0;}\r\n /* Style Definitions */\r\n p.MsoNormal, li.MsoNormal, div.MsoNormal\r\n	{mso-style-parent:\"\";\r\n	margin:0cm;\r\n	margin-bottom:.0001pt;\r\n	mso-pagination:widow-orphan;\r\n	font-size:12.0pt;\r\n	font-family:\"Times New Roman\";\r\n	mso-fareast-font-family:\"Times New Roman\";}\r\n@page Section1\r\n	{size:612.0pt 792.0pt;\r\n	margin:70.85pt 3.0cm 70.85pt 3.0cm;\r\n	mso-header-margin:36.0pt;\r\n	mso-footer-margin:36.0pt;\r\n	mso-paper-source:0;}\r\ndiv.Section1\r\n	{page:Section1;}\r\n-->\r\n</style><!--[if gte mso 10]>\r\n<style>\r\n /* Style Definitions */\r\n table.MsoNormalTable\r\n	{mso-style-name:\"Tabla normal\";\r\n	mso-tstyle-rowband-size:0;\r\n	mso-tstyle-colband-size:0;\r\n	mso-style-noshow:yes;\r\n	mso-style-parent:\"\";\r\n	mso-padding-alt:0cm 5.4pt 0cm 5.4pt;\r\n	mso-para-margin:0cm;\r\n	mso-para-margin-bottom:.0001pt;\r\n	mso-pagination:widow-orphan;\r\n	font-size:10.0pt;\r\n	font-family:\"Times New Roman\";\r\n	mso-ansi-language:#0400;\r\n	mso-fareast-language:#0400;\r\n	mso-bidi-language:#0400;}\r\n</style>\r\n<![endif]-->\r\n\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-size: 8.5pt; font-family: Verdana;\" lang=\"EN-GB\">I wanted to\r\nthank you for all you did in putting together a phenomenal trip to <st1:country-region w:st=\"on\"><st1:place w:st=\"on\">Peru</st1:place></st1:country-region>!&nbsp;\r\nEach of our stops along the way was a destination in itself, and my wife, our\r\nteenage kids, and I thoroughly enjoyed each place.&nbsp; It was an incredible\r\ntrip that we will not soon forget...my youngest son even thinks it was on par\r\nwith our safari trip to the Serengeti.<o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-size: 8.5pt; font-family: Verdana;\" lang=\"EN-GB\"><br>\r\nI also want to thank you for coordinating the personal tours throughout our\r\ntrip.&nbsp; It was unexpected to have it all set up that way, but it was an\r\nexceptional treat for me and my family (who thoroughly loved it that way).<o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-size: 8.5pt; font-family: Verdana;\" lang=\"EN-GB\"><br>\r\nIn <st1:city w:st=\"on\"><st1:place w:st=\"on\">Arequipa</st1:place></st1:city> we\r\nwere greeted by your representative, who was friendly and cheerful and gave\r\nseveral restaurant suggestions. Casa Andina was a good hotel, located not too\r\nfar from the center of town.&nbsp; Management was helpful and hospitable,\r\nbreakfast was good, and the rooms were clean and comfortable.<o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-size: 8.5pt; font-family: Verdana;\" lang=\"EN-GB\"><br>\r\nGuillermo was our guide in the <st1:place w:st=\"on\"><st1:placename w:st=\"on\">Colca</st1:placename>\r\n <st1:placetype w:st=\"on\">Canyon</st1:placetype></st1:place>, with Isidro as\r\nthe driver.&nbsp; Guillermo was enthusiastic, entertaining, and very\r\nhumorous.&nbsp; He was a wealth of knowledge about the people of the canyon,\r\nthe economy, politics, geography, and many other topics.&nbsp; He engaged each\r\nof the kids in conversation, and shared many of his deep, personal experiences\r\n(including his brush with death).&nbsp;&nbsp; Stories about how his grandmother\r\nused herbal medicines to help him overcome his injuries, as well as stories\r\nabout her wisdom on many aspects of the <st1:place w:st=\"on\"><st1:placename w:st=\"on\">Colca</st1:placename> <st1:placetype w:st=\"on\">Canyon</st1:placetype></st1:place>\r\nway of life, really brought the experience to a new level.&nbsp; Seeing the\r\ncondors was a thrill, but seeing the people, understanding their life,\r\ninteracting with them (our daughter was dressed in a traditional outfit with\r\nthe help of a roadside vendor, and we all practiced using an Incan slingshot\r\nslinging rocks into the canyon) was just as interesting to me.&nbsp; Guillermo\r\nis an incredible guide...I honestly could not envision experiencing the canyon\r\nas deeply as we did with another guide.&nbsp; Factually, others guides may be\r\nas accurate about the canyon, but the personal stories make Guillermo a stellar\r\nguide.&nbsp; We could not recommend him any more highly to anyone.<o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-size: 8.5pt; font-family: Verdana;\" lang=\"EN-GB\"><br>\r\nPozo del Cielo was a good choice for us.&nbsp; The rooms are rustic charming,\r\nand the hotel staff could not have been more welcoming.&nbsp; The restaurant is\r\nalso excellent.&nbsp; We also ate at two other good buffet lunch restaurants in\r\nChivay: Puerto Notales and a family run restaurant in the center of town about\r\n2 blocks from the market and <st1:street w:st=\"on\"><st1:address w:st=\"on\">Main\r\n  Square</st1:address></st1:street>.&nbsp; The preparation of the <i style=\"\">cuy</i> was a bit rugged for us.... quartered,\r\nwith skin and a bit of fur still on!&nbsp; But it was fun and the other food\r\nwas excellent.&nbsp;Just makes for good stories...<o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-size: 8.5pt; font-family: Verdana;\" lang=\"EN-GB\"><br>\r\nIn <st1:city w:st=\"on\"><st1:place w:st=\"on\">Cuzco</st1:place></st1:city>, Alison\r\nour coordinator was bright, cheery, and friendly.&nbsp; She welcomed us warmly\r\nto <st1:city w:st=\"on\"><st1:place w:st=\"on\">Cuzco</st1:place></st1:city> and\r\nanswered many questions we had.&nbsp; She was prompt in contacting the hotel\r\neach night, letting us know the schedule for the next day and the time that\r\nsomeone would be by to pick us up.&nbsp; This was a great little comfort.<o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-size: 8.5pt; font-family: Verdana;\" lang=\"EN-GB\"><br>\r\nMary Luz was our guide in <st1:city w:st=\"on\">Cuzco</st1:city> and the <st1:place w:st=\"on\"><st1:placename w:st=\"on\">Sacred</st1:placename> <st1:placetype w:st=\"on\">Valley</st1:placetype></st1:place>.&nbsp;\r\nShe was very friendly and informative.&nbsp; Though she did not have the gift\r\nof storytelling of Guillermo, she was a very good with excellent English\r\nskills.&nbsp; She also provided a lot of insight into the valley and its\r\npeople, and introduced us to a couple of new fruits at the Pisac market.&nbsp; The\r\ndriver Renato was also very helpful, especially with my daughter who was\r\novercoming a bit of food poisoning.&nbsp; She was not feeling very well but\r\nwent on the <st1:city w:st=\"on\"><st1:place w:st=\"on\">Cuzco</st1:place></st1:city>\r\ntour but slept for most of the rest of tour.&nbsp; Renato would check on her\r\nregularly, ask if she was ok and if she needed anything.&nbsp; In ways he sort\r\nof became our father/grandfather for our time in <st1:place w:st=\"on\"><st1:city w:st=\"on\">Cuzco</st1:city></st1:place>.<o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-size: 8.5pt; font-family: Verdana;\" lang=\"EN-GB\"><br>\r\nI cannot say enough good things about Hotel Torre Dorado.&nbsp; The hotel was\r\nclean, bright, cheery, and very comfortable, but the staff was\r\nEXCEPTIONAL.&nbsp; Peggy and her staff tended to our every need, from laundry\r\nby the kilo (twice) to arranging a late evening pizza dinner in the breakfast\r\narea on our return from <st1:city w:st=\"on\"><st1:place w:st=\"on\">Machu Picchu</st1:place></st1:city>.&nbsp;\r\nThis service is what really sets this hotel apart from every other place we\r\nstayed, and was better than most hotels in the <st1:country-region w:st=\"on\"><st1:place w:st=\"on\">US</st1:place></st1:country-region> as well.&nbsp; Any inconvenience\r\nin not being located immediately downtown (10 minutes by car) is offset by the\r\neasy, quick access of drivers to take you to every part of town (or they will\r\narrange a taxi at a fair expense if the drivers are busy) and the\r\nPEACEFULNESS&nbsp;of the hotel and its </span><span style=\"font-size: 8.5pt; font-family: Verdana;\" lang=\"EN-US\">neighborhood</span><span style=\"font-size: 8.5pt; font-family: Verdana;\" lang=\"EN-GB\">,\r\nwhich lacks the traffic of downtown and the dogs of many other areas.&nbsp; I\r\nwould highly recommend this hotel to travelers to <st1:city w:st=\"on\"><st1:place w:st=\"on\">Cuzco</st1:place></st1:city>.<br>\r\n<br>\r\n<st1:city w:st=\"on\"><st1:place w:st=\"on\">Machu Picchu</st1:place></st1:city> is\r\nlike St. Peter\'s Basilica...it is even far more impressive in person than it is\r\nin pictures.&nbsp; There is no way you cannot come away amazed at the\r\ncomplex.&nbsp; Fabricio was an exceptional guide and coordinator as well.&nbsp;\r\nHe was extremely enthusiastic and friendly, and imparted a high degree of\r\ndetail and stories that other tours (which we observed later that day and the\r\nnext) never discussed, and we saw things that many other tours never saw.&nbsp;\r\nAgain, we felt we had a highly personalized tour and that Fabricio was a\r\ntop-level guide with excellent English skills and a zest in talking about <st1:place w:st=\"on\"><st1:city w:st=\"on\">Machu Picchu</st1:city></st1:place>.<o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-size: 8.5pt; font-family: Verdana;\" lang=\"EN-GB\"><br>\r\nHotel Santuario in Aguas Calientes was a good hotel.&nbsp; We loved the\r\nlocation next to the river (kids had a balcony overlooking the river), and it\r\nwas only a short walk to the town square.&nbsp; The rooms were clean and\r\ncomfortable, and the breakfast was good.&nbsp; The staff was very helpful\r\nkeeping the bags for us and meeting us at the train station upon our departure\r\nto <st1:city w:st=\"on\"><st1:place w:st=\"on\">Cuzco</st1:place></st1:city> and\r\nthen on to Puerto Maldonado.<br>\r\n<br>\r\nWe were met promptly at the airport in Puerto Maldonado and taken to the Lake\r\nSandoval Lodge office to repack for our trip to the jungle.&nbsp; Our guide was\r\nPaul Smutney, who was extremely funny, informative, and knowledgeable of the\r\nanimals, insects, and plants.&nbsp; Our 3 nights there were exceptional.\r\n(Daniel was at the oar, who I believe is a deaf mute, and he was excellent,\r\ncheery and full of life himself).&nbsp; The food was very, very good at all\r\nthree meals, and the bar served very cold beer and good Pisco sours.&nbsp; The\r\nlodge was very comfortable (the kids loved the hammocks), and the views were\r\ngreat.&nbsp; Access to the wildlife in prime times - early morning and evening\r\n- make this an exceptional location to see the jungle, and different sides of\r\nthe lake have different plants, trees, and wildlife themselves.<o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-size: 8.5pt; font-family: Verdana;\" lang=\"EN-GB\"><br>\r\nThe lodge itself is an extremely comfortable way of \"roughing it\" in\r\nthe jungle.&nbsp; I say that only because it is a surprise to find the rooms\r\nwith open-ceilings to the thatch roof, and the ability to hear many noises from\r\nthe adjoining rooms.&nbsp; We adjusted well, as I think most people do, because\r\nthey reduced their personal conversations and noise levels to minimize\r\nintrusions on </span><span style=\"font-size: 8.5pt; font-family: Verdana;\" lang=\"EN-US\">neighbors</span><span style=\"font-size: 8.5pt; font-family: Verdana;\" lang=\"EN-GB\">.&nbsp; It is almost the\r\nsame as being in a tent lodge where the tents are close to each other. I know\r\nwhy the design is the way it is, as morning breezes filled the entire room (the\r\nopen ceiling ventilates all the rooms, especially important in hot weather).<o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-size: 8.5pt; font-family: Verdana;\" lang=\"EN-GB\"><br>\r\nThey did make accommodations to go fishing for 1 1/2 hours.&nbsp; However,\r\nbecause the lake is a protected reserve, we had to fish a small creek feeding\r\ninto the lake.&nbsp; It was fun using line on sticks and hand lines, and my\r\nsons and I enjoyed the experience.<o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-size: 8.5pt; font-family: Verdana;\" lang=\"EN-GB\"><br>\r\nAgain, thank you for helping us to arrange a spectacular trip.&nbsp; Deanna,\r\nyou could not have been any friendlier or more responsive to my many questions\r\nand request.&nbsp; And Abby, thank you for the last touches just prior to our\r\ntrip.<o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-size: 8.5pt; font-family: Verdana;\" lang=\"EN-GB\">&nbsp; <br>\r\nI will highly encourage <st1:country-region w:st=\"on\">Peru</st1:country-region>\r\nas a destination with my friends and clients, and I look forward to coordinating\r\ntrips through <st1:country-region w:st=\"on\"><st1:place w:st=\"on\">Peru</st1:place></st1:country-region>\r\nfor Less.&nbsp; You did an exceptional job of delivering a great vacation for a\r\npretty experienced family of travelers who have seen quite a few places, and we\r\nloved seeing the country, the people, and all the experiences that it\r\noffered.&nbsp;<o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-size: 8.5pt; font-family: Verdana;\" lang=\"EN-GB\"><o:p>&nbsp;</o:p></span></p>\r\n\r\n<b style=\"\"><span style=\"font-size: 8.5pt; font-family: Verdana;\" lang=\"EN-GB\">Kudos to you and all of your staff for delivering on memories that will\r\nlast a lifetime.</span></b>                ','<meta http-equiv=\"Content-Type\" content=\"text/html; charset=utf-8\"><meta name=\"ProgId\" content=\"Word.Document\"><meta name=\"Generator\" content=\"Microsoft Word 11\"><meta name=\"Originator\" content=\"Micro','','','',183,0,0,NULL,NULL,NULL),(383,1,'Dear Peru For Less','<meta http-equiv=\"Content-Type\" content=\"text/html; charset=utf-8\"><meta name=\"ProgId\" content=\"Word.Document\"><meta name=\"Generator\" content=\"Microsoft Word 11\"><meta name=\"Originator\" content=\"Microsoft Word 11\"><link rel=\"File-List\" href=\"file:///C:%5CDOCUME%7E1%5CADMINI%7E1%5CCONFIG%7E1%5CTemp%5Cmsohtml1%5C06%5Cclip_filelist.xml\"><o:smarttagtype namespaceuri=\"urn:schemas-microsoft-com:office:smarttags\" name=\"country-region\" downloadurl=\"http://www.5iantlavalamp.com/\"></o:smarttagtype><o:smarttagtype namespaceuri=\"urn:schemas-microsoft-com:office:smarttags\" name=\"place\" downloadurl=\"http://www.5iantlavalamp.com/\"></o:smarttagtype><o:smarttagtype namespaceuri=\"urn:schemas-microsoft-com:office:smarttags\" name=\"City\" downloadurl=\"http://www.5iamas-microsoft-com:office:smarttags\"></o:smarttagtype><!--[if gte mso 9]><xml>\r\n <w:WordDocument>\r\n  <w:View>Normal</w:View>\r\n  <w:Zoom>0</w:Zoom>\r\n  <w:HyphenationZone>21</w:HyphenationZone>\r\n  <w:PunctuationKerning/>\r\n  <w:ValidateAgainstSchemas/>\r\n  <w:SaveIfXMLInvalid>false</w:SaveIfXMLInvalid>\r\n  <w:IgnoreMixedContent>false</w:IgnoreMixedContent>\r\n  <w:AlwaysShowPlaceholderText>false</w:AlwaysShowPlaceholderText>\r\n  <w:Compatibility>\r\n   <w:BreakWrappedTables/>\r\n   <w:SnapToGridInCell/>\r\n   <w:WrapTextWithPunct/>\r\n   <w:UseAsianBreakRules/>\r\n   <w:DontGrowAutofit/>\r\n  </w:Compatibility>\r\n  <w:BrowserLevel>MicrosoftInternetExplorer4</w:BrowserLevel>\r\n </w:WordDocument>\r\n</xml><![endif]--><!--[if gte mso 9]><xml>\r\n <w:LatentStyles DefLockedState=\"false\" LatentStyleCount=\"156\">\r\n </w:LatentStyles>\r\n</xml><![endif]--><!--[if !mso]><object\r\n classid=\"clsid:38481807-CA0E-42D2-BF39-B33AF135CC4D\" id=ieooui></object>\r\n<style>\r\nst1\\:*{behavior:url(#ieooui) }\r\n</style>\r\n<![endif]--><style>\r\n<!--\r\n /* Font Definitions */\r\n @font-face\r\n	{font-family:Wingdings;\r\n	panose-1:5 0 0 0 0 0 0 0 0 0;\r\n	mso-font-charset:2;\r\n	mso-generic-font-family:auto;\r\n	mso-font-pitch:variable;\r\n	mso-font-signature:0 268435456 0 0 -2147483648 0;}\r\n@font-face\r\n	{font-family:Verdana;\r\n	panose-1:2 11 6 4 3 5 4 4 2 4;\r\n	mso-font-charset:0;\r\n	mso-generic-font-family:swiss;\r\n	mso-font-pitch:variable;\r\n	mso-font-signature:536871559 0 0 0 415 0;}\r\n /* Style Definitions */\r\n p.MsoNormal, li.MsoNormal, div.MsoNormal\r\n	{mso-style-parent:\"\";\r\n	margin:0cm;\r\n	margin-bottom:.0001pt;\r\n	mso-pagination:widow-orphan;\r\n	font-size:12.0pt;\r\n	font-family:\"Times New Roman\";\r\n	mso-fareast-font-family:\"Times New Roman\";}\r\n@page Section1\r\n	{size:612.0pt 792.0pt;\r\n	margin:70.85pt 3.0cm 70.85pt 3.0cm;\r\n	mso-header-margin:36.0pt;\r\n	mso-footer-margin:36.0pt;\r\n	mso-paper-source:0;}\r\ndiv.Section1\r\n	{page:Section1;}\r\n-->\r\n</style><!--[if gte mso 10]>\r\n<style>\r\n /* Style Definitions */\r\n table.MsoNormalTable\r\n	{mso-style-name:\"Tabla normal\";\r\n	mso-tstyle-rowband-size:0;\r\n	mso-tstyle-colband-size:0;\r\n	mso-style-noshow:yes;\r\n	mso-style-parent:\"\";\r\n	mso-padding-alt:0cm 5.4pt 0cm 5.4pt;\r\n	mso-para-margin:0cm;\r\n	mso-para-margin-bottom:.0001pt;\r\n	mso-pagination:widow-orphan;\r\n	font-size:10.0pt;\r\n	font-family:\"Times New Roman\";\r\n	mso-ansi-language:#0400;\r\n	mso-fareast-language:#0400;\r\n	mso-bidi-language:#0400;}\r\n</style>\r\n<![endif]-->\r\n\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><span style=\"font-size: 8.5pt; font-family: Verdana;\" lang=\"EN-GB\">Our trip was&nbsp;GREAT!&nbsp; <st1:country-region w:st=\"on\">Peru</st1:country-region> and <st1:country-region w:st=\"on\"><st1:place w:st=\"on\">Chile</st1:place></st1:country-region> are very different countries\r\nand we had very different but wonderful experiences in both places.<o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><span style=\"font-size: 8.5pt; font-family: Verdana;\" lang=\"EN-GB\">&nbsp;<o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><span style=\"font-size: 8.5pt; font-family: Verdana;\" lang=\"EN-GB\">We were very happy with Peru For Less and all\r\nthat&nbsp;you planned for us.&nbsp; In fact, the day after we returned I was\r\nsharing our itinerary and your information with the family of one of my daughter\'s\r\nfriends.&nbsp; <o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><span style=\"font-size: 8.5pt; font-family: Verdana;\" lang=\"EN-GB\">&nbsp;<o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><span style=\"font-size: 8.5pt; font-family: Verdana;\" lang=\"EN-GB\">We were met at the <st1:city w:st=\"on\">Lima</st1:city>\r\nairport by a young man named Miguel and <span style=\"\">&nbsp;</span>he was the perfect person for our first\r\nimpression of <st1:place w:st=\"on\"><st1:country-region w:st=\"on\">Peru</st1:country-region></st1:place>;\r\nhe was warm and friendly, so charming and smart - we all thought he was great\r\nand he started our trip on such a positive note!&nbsp;&nbsp;Our guide in <st1:city w:st=\"on\"><st1:place w:st=\"on\">Cuzco</st1:place></st1:city>, Mija was\r\nwonderful.&nbsp;&nbsp;She is a very knowledgeable and thoughtful\r\nperson.&nbsp;We are all very impressed with her.&nbsp; Our guide at <st1:city w:st=\"on\"><st1:place w:st=\"on\">Machu Picchu</st1:place></st1:city>, Fabrico was\r\nequally impressive.&nbsp; He too is very knowledgeable and it is clear that he\r\nis proud of his heritage.&nbsp; His tour of <st1:city w:st=\"on\"><st1:place w:st=\"on\">Machu Picchu</st1:place></st1:city> was very informative and\r\nengaging.&nbsp; As you know we had two teenagers and a nine year old in our\r\ngroup - he kept everyone\'s interest the whole time.&nbsp; The teenagers really\r\nappreciated his sense of humor.&nbsp;Both Mija and Fabricio left us with a\r\ndesire to read and learn more about <st1:country-region w:st=\"on\">Peru</st1:country-region>,\r\nthe Incan people and <st1:place w:st=\"on\"><st1:city w:st=\"on\">Machu Picchu</st1:city></st1:place>.<o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><span style=\"font-size: 8.5pt; font-family: Verdana;\" lang=\"EN-GB\"><o:p>&nbsp;</o:p></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><span style=\"font-size: 8.5pt; font-family: Verdana;\" lang=\"EN-GB\">The Arquelogo in <st1:place w:st=\"on\"><st1:city w:st=\"on\">Cuzco</st1:city></st1:place>\r\n- we <b>LOVED</b> this place.&nbsp; It is so charming and beautiful - we loved\r\nthe rooms, the breakfast was great and the restaurant. Divine Comedia was\r\nfantastic.&nbsp; The food was delicious and the prices are very\r\nreasonable.&nbsp;&nbsp;The people that worked in the reception were so sweet\r\nand helpful.<o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><span style=\"font-size: 8.5pt; font-family: Verdana;\" lang=\"EN-GB\"><o:p>&nbsp;</o:p></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><span style=\"font-size: 8.5pt; font-family: Verdana;\" lang=\"EN-GB\">The train was GREAT.&nbsp; We are so glad that you\r\nbooked us on first class - we loved it both ways!&nbsp;<o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><span style=\"font-size: 8.5pt; font-family: Verdana;\" lang=\"EN-GB\"><o:p>&nbsp;</o:p></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><span style=\"font-size: 8.5pt; font-family: Verdana;\" lang=\"EN-GB\">The hotel El Sauce in Ollantaytambo was also\r\nwonderful.&nbsp; The location is great, the rooms are very comfortable, the\r\nbreakfast was&nbsp;good and the people that work there were very nice.<o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><span style=\"font-size: 8.5pt; font-family: Verdana;\" lang=\"EN-GB\"><o:p>&nbsp;</o:p></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><span style=\"font-size: 8.5pt; font-family: Verdana;\" lang=\"EN-GB\">&nbsp;We loved the fact that we were our own private\r\ntour group.&nbsp; All of the transportation was comfortable and the drivers\r\nwere so polite and helpful. </span><span style=\"font-size: 8.5pt; font-family: Verdana;\" lang=\"EN-US\">The shopping at Pisac Markets was\r\nreally the best and we would have liked to have stayed another hour (actually I\r\nam not sure the husbands would agree </span><span style=\"font-size: 8.5pt; font-family: Wingdings;\"><span style=\"\">J</span></span><span style=\"font-size: 8.5pt; font-family: Verdana;\" lang=\"EN-US\">).&nbsp; </span><span style=\"font-size: 8.5pt; font-family: Verdana;\" lang=\"EN-GB\">We\r\ndid appreciate that Mija arranged for the driver to take our purchases back to\r\nthe Arqueologo Hotel for us - that was so helpful.<o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><span style=\"font-size: 8.5pt; font-family: Verdana;\" lang=\"EN-GB\">&nbsp;<o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><span style=\"font-size: 8.5pt; font-family: Verdana;\" lang=\"EN-GB\">We felt that we saw a lot in the short time that we\r\nwere in <st1:country-region w:st=\"on\"><st1:place w:st=\"on\">Peru</st1:place></st1:country-region>.&nbsp;\r\nWe left your country in awe of the rich history and culture.<o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><span style=\"font-size: 8.5pt; font-family: Verdana;\" lang=\"EN-GB\"><o:p>&nbsp;</o:p></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><span style=\"font-size: 8.5pt; font-family: Verdana;\" lang=\"EN-GB\">In <st1:country-region w:st=\"on\">Chile</st1:country-region>&nbsp;we\r\nwere met by Ignacio and&nbsp;also taken to <st1:place w:st=\"on\"><st1:city w:st=\"on\">Vina&nbsp;del Mar</st1:city></st1:place> by him -&nbsp;our\r\nexperience with him was really limited to transportation, but he was&nbsp;very\r\nfriendly and informative.<o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><span style=\"font-size: 8.5pt; font-family: Verdana;\" lang=\"EN-GB\"><o:p>&nbsp;</o:p></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><span style=\"font-size: 8.5pt; font-family: Verdana;\" lang=\"EN-GB\">Thank you for everything Susan.&nbsp; It really was\r\none of the <b>best vacations</b> we have ever had!<o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n\r\n<meta http-equiv=\"Content-Type\" content=\"text/html; charset=utf-8\"><meta name=\"ProgId\" content=\"Word.Document\"><meta name=\"Generator\" content=\"Microsoft Word 11\"><meta name=\"Originator\" content=\"Microsoft Word 11\"><link rel=\"File-List\" href=\"file:///C:%5CDOCUME%7E1%5CADMINI%7E1%5CCONFIG%7E1%5CTemp%5Cmsohtml1%5C03%5Cclip_filelist.xml\"><o:smarttagtype namespaceuri=\"urn:schemas-microsoft-com:office:smarttags\" name=\"country-region\" downloadurl=\"http://www.5iantlavalamp.com/\"></o:smarttagtype><o:smarttagtype namespaceuri=\"urn:schemas-microsoft-com:office:smarttags\" name=\"place\" downloadurl=\"http://www.5iantlavalamp.com/\"></o:smarttagtype><o:smarttagtype namespaceuri=\"urn:schemas-microsoft-com:office:smarttags\" name=\"City\" downloadurl=\"http://www.5iamas-microsoft-com:office:smarttags\"></o:smarttagtype><o:smarttagtype namespaceuri=\"urn:schemas-microsoft-com:office:smarttags\" name=\"PlaceName\" downloadurl=\"http://www.5iantlavalamp.com/\"></o:smarttagtype><o:smarttagtype namespaceuri=\"urn:schemas-microsoft-com:office:smarttags\" name=\"PlaceType\" downloadurl=\"http://www.5iantlavalamp.com/\"></o:smarttagtype><o:smarttagtype namespaceuri=\"urn:schemas-microsoft-com:office:smarttags\" name=\"address\"></o:smarttagtype><o:smarttagtype namespaceuri=\"urn:schemas-microsoft-com:office:smarttags\" name=\"Street\"></o:smarttagtype><!--[if gte mso 9]><xml>\r\n <w:WordDocument>\r\n  <w:View>Normal</w:View>\r\n  <w:Zoom>0</w:Zoom>\r\n  <w:HyphenationZone>21</w:HyphenationZone>\r\n  <w:PunctuationKerning/>\r\n  <w:ValidateAgainstSchemas/>\r\n  <w:SaveIfXMLInvalid>false</w:SaveIfXMLInvalid>\r\n  <w:IgnoreMixedContent>false</w:IgnoreMixedContent>\r\n  <w:AlwaysShowPlaceholderText>false</w:AlwaysShowPlaceholderText>\r\n  <w:Compatibility>\r\n   <w:BreakWrappedTables/>\r\n   <w:SnapToGridInCell/>\r\n   <w:WrapTextWithPunct/>\r\n   <w:UseAsianBreakRules/>\r\n   <w:DontGrowAutofit/>\r\n  </w:Compatibility>\r\n  <w:BrowserLevel>MicrosoftInternetExplorer4</w:BrowserLevel>\r\n </w:WordDocument>\r\n</xml><![endif]--><!--[if gte mso 9]><xml>\r\n <w:LatentStyles DefLockedState=\"false\" LatentStyleCount=\"156\">\r\n </w:LatentStyles>\r\n</xml><![endif]--><!--[if !mso]><object\r\n classid=\"clsid:38481807-CA0E-42D2-BF39-B33AF135CC4D\" id=ieooui></object>\r\n<style>\r\nst1\\:*{behavior:url(#ieooui) }\r\n</style>\r\n<![endif]--><style>\r\n<!--\r\n /* Font Definitions */\r\n @font-face\r\n	{font-family:Verdana;\r\n	panose-1:2 11 6 4 3 5 4 4 2 4;\r\n	mso-font-charset:0;\r\n	mso-generic-font-family:swiss;\r\n	mso-font-pitch:variable;\r\n	mso-font-signature:536871559 0 0 0 415 0;}\r\n /* Style Definitions */\r\n p.MsoNormal, li.MsoNormal, div.MsoNormal\r\n	{mso-style-parent:\"\";\r\n	margin:0cm;\r\n	margin-bottom:.0001pt;\r\n	mso-pagination:widow-orphan;\r\n	font-size:12.0pt;\r\n	font-family:\"Times New Roman\";\r\n	mso-fareast-font-family:\"Times New Roman\";}\r\n@page Section1\r\n	{size:612.0pt 792.0pt;\r\n	margin:70.85pt 3.0cm 70.85pt 3.0cm;\r\n	mso-header-margin:36.0pt;\r\n	mso-footer-margin:36.0pt;\r\n	mso-paper-source:0;}\r\ndiv.Section1\r\n	{page:Section1;}\r\n-->\r\n</style><!--[if gte mso 10]>\r\n<style>\r\n /* Style Definitions */\r\n table.MsoNormalTable\r\n	{mso-style-name:\"Tabla normal\";\r\n	mso-tstyle-rowband-size:0;\r\n	mso-tstyle-colband-size:0;\r\n	mso-style-noshow:yes;\r\n	mso-style-parent:\"\";\r\n	mso-padding-alt:0cm 5.4pt 0cm 5.4pt;\r\n	mso-para-margin:0cm;\r\n	mso-para-margin-bottom:.0001pt;\r\n	mso-pagination:widow-orphan;\r\n	font-size:10.0pt;\r\n	font-family:\"Times New Roman\";\r\n	mso-ansi-language:#0400;\r\n	mso-fareast-language:#0400;\r\n	mso-bidi-language:#0400;}\r\n</style>\r\n<![endif]--><b style=\"\"><span style=\"font-size: 8.5pt; font-family: Verdana;\" lang=\"EN-GB\"></span></b>                ','<meta http-equiv=\"Content-Type\" content=\"text/html; charset=utf-8\"><meta name=\"ProgId\" content=\"Word.Document\"><meta name=\"Generator\" content=\"Microsoft Word 11\"><meta name=\"Originator\" content=\"Micro','','','',182,0,0,NULL,NULL,NULL),(384,1,'Hi Deanna,','<meta http-equiv=\"Content-Type\" content=\"text/html; charset=utf-8\"><meta name=\"ProgId\" content=\"Word.Document\"><meta name=\"Generator\" content=\"Microsoft Word 11\"><meta name=\"Originator\" content=\"Microsoft Word 11\"><link rel=\"File-List\" href=\"file:///C:%5CDOCUME%7E1%5CADMINI%7E1%5CCONFIG%7E1%5CTemp%5Cmsohtml1%5C09%5Cclip_filelist.xml\"><o:smarttagtype namespaceuri=\"urn:schemas-microsoft-com:office:smarttags\" name=\"country-region\" downloadurl=\"http://www.5iantlavalamp.com/\"></o:smarttagtype><o:smarttagtype namespaceuri=\"urn:schemas-microsoft-com:office:smarttags\" name=\"place\" downloadurl=\"http://www.5iantlavalamp.com/\"></o:smarttagtype><o:smarttagtype namespaceuri=\"urn:schemas-microsoft-com:office:smarttags\" name=\"City\" downloadurl=\"http://www.5iamas-microsoft-com:office:smarttags\"></o:smarttagtype><o:smarttagtype namespaceuri=\"urn:schemas-microsoft-com:office:smarttags\" name=\"PlaceName\" downloadurl=\"http://www.5iantlavalamp.com/\"></o:smarttagtype><o:smarttagtype namespaceuri=\"urn:schemas-microsoft-com:office:smarttags\" name=\"PlaceType\" downloadurl=\"http://www.5iantlavalamp.com/\"></o:smarttagtype><!--[if gte mso 9]><xml>\r\n <w:WordDocument>\r\n  <w:View>Normal</w:View>\r\n  <w:Zoom>0</w:Zoom>\r\n  <w:HyphenationZone>21</w:HyphenationZone>\r\n  <w:PunctuationKerning/>\r\n  <w:ValidateAgainstSchemas/>\r\n  <w:SaveIfXMLInvalid>false</w:SaveIfXMLInvalid>\r\n  <w:IgnoreMixedContent>false</w:IgnoreMixedContent>\r\n  <w:AlwaysShowPlaceholderText>false</w:AlwaysShowPlaceholderText>\r\n  <w:Compatibility>\r\n   <w:BreakWrappedTables/>\r\n   <w:SnapToGridInCell/>\r\n   <w:WrapTextWithPunct/>\r\n   <w:UseAsianBreakRules/>\r\n   <w:DontGrowAutofit/>\r\n  </w:Compatibility>\r\n  <w:BrowserLevel>MicrosoftInternetExplorer4</w:BrowserLevel>\r\n </w:WordDocument>\r\n</xml><![endif]--><!--[if gte mso 9]><xml>\r\n <w:LatentStyles DefLockedState=\"false\" LatentStyleCount=\"156\">\r\n </w:LatentStyles>\r\n</xml><![endif]--><!--[if !mso]><object\r\n classid=\"clsid:38481807-CA0E-42D2-BF39-B33AF135CC4D\" id=ieooui></object>\r\n<style>\r\nst1\\:*{behavior:url(#ieooui) }\r\n</style>\r\n<![endif]--><style>\r\n<!--\r\n /* Font Definitions */\r\n @font-face\r\n	{font-family:Verdana;\r\n	panose-1:2 11 6 4 3 5 4 4 2 4;\r\n	mso-font-charset:0;\r\n	mso-generic-font-family:swiss;\r\n	mso-font-pitch:variable;\r\n	mso-font-signature:536871559 0 0 0 415 0;}\r\n /* Style Definitions */\r\n p.MsoNormal, li.MsoNormal, div.MsoNormal\r\n	{mso-style-parent:\"\";\r\n	margin:0cm;\r\n	margin-bottom:.0001pt;\r\n	mso-pagination:widow-orphan;\r\n	font-size:12.0pt;\r\n	font-family:\"Times New Roman\";\r\n	mso-fareast-font-family:\"Times New Roman\";}\r\n@page Section1\r\n	{size:612.0pt 792.0pt;\r\n	margin:70.85pt 3.0cm 70.85pt 3.0cm;\r\n	mso-header-margin:36.0pt;\r\n	mso-footer-margin:36.0pt;\r\n	mso-paper-source:0;}\r\ndiv.Section1\r\n	{page:Section1;}\r\n-->\r\n</style><!--[if gte mso 10]>\r\n<style>\r\n /* Style Definitions */\r\n table.MsoNormalTable\r\n	{mso-style-name:\"Tabla normal\";\r\n	mso-tstyle-rowband-size:0;\r\n	mso-tstyle-colband-size:0;\r\n	mso-style-noshow:yes;\r\n	mso-style-parent:\"\";\r\n	mso-padding-alt:0cm 5.4pt 0cm 5.4pt;\r\n	mso-para-margin:0cm;\r\n	mso-para-margin-bottom:.0001pt;\r\n	mso-pagination:widow-orphan;\r\n	font-size:10.0pt;\r\n	font-family:\"Times New Roman\";\r\n	mso-ansi-language:#0400;\r\n	mso-fareast-language:#0400;\r\n	mso-bidi-language:#0400;}\r\n</style>\r\n<![endif]-->\r\n\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><span style=\"font-size: 8.5pt; font-family: Verdana;\" lang=\"EN-US\">My trip to <st1:city w:st=\"on\">Cuzco</st1:city> and <st1:city w:st=\"on\"><st1:place w:st=\"on\">Machu Picchu</st1:place></st1:city> was\r\nabsolutely superb! I have traveled the world quite a bit and I must say\r\nthat&nbsp;<st1:country-region w:st=\"on\"><st1:place w:st=\"on\">Peru</st1:place></st1:country-region>\r\nhas one of the best organized tourist industries of any country. The attention\r\nto detail was superb. I did not feel I was treated as just another tourist at\r\nany stage.&nbsp;There were absolutely no stuff-ups and everyone and everything\r\nshowed up exactly when and where they were supposed to. My <st1:country-region w:st=\"on\">Peru-for-Less</st1:country-region> rep in <st1:city w:st=\"on\"><st1:place w:st=\"on\">Cuzco</st1:place></st1:city>, Christina (surprisingly, a\r\nSpanish-speaking Romanian), was highly efficient and&nbsp;made the utmost\r\neffort to ensure every part of&nbsp;my itinerary&nbsp;went smoothly. As an\r\nexample, fifteen minutes after arriving in my hotel in Aguas Calientes\r\nafter&nbsp;the grueling three day Salcantay trek, I received a phone call from\r\nher informing me the train&nbsp;ticket for my return journey to <st1:city w:st=\"on\"><st1:place w:st=\"on\">Cuzco</st1:place></st1:city> the following\r\nday&nbsp;was with my guide. It was!<o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><span style=\"font-size: 8.5pt; font-family: Verdana;\" lang=\"EN-US\">&nbsp;<o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><span style=\"font-size: 8.5pt; font-family: Verdana;\" lang=\"EN-US\">My trek guide, Bruno, deserves a special\r\nmention.&nbsp;Courteous and conversational, and highly competent in both\r\nSpanish and English,&nbsp;he alleviated many of the concerns of a non-native\r\nspeaker, acquired tickets and passes with ease, and was highly dependable\r\nthroughout the trek.<o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><span style=\"font-size: 8.5pt; font-family: Verdana;\" lang=\"EN-US\">&nbsp;<o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><span style=\"font-size: 8.5pt; font-family: Verdana;\" lang=\"EN-US\">My hotels (Costa del Sol Ramada in <st1:city w:st=\"on\">Lima</st1:city>,\r\nCasa Andina Private Collection in Cusco and <st1:place w:st=\"on\"><st1:placename w:st=\"on\">Hatuchay</st1:placename> <st1:placetype w:st=\"on\">Tower</st1:placetype></st1:place>\r\nin Aguas Calientes) were all of high, Western&nbsp;standard. I stayed at the\r\nCasa Andina both before and after my trek. The first time I had a ground floor\r\nroom, the second time an upper floor room. The best rooms are on the upper\r\nfloor. The staff at the Casa Andina were excellent and highly professional. I\r\nhad a couple of issues with the toilet and the lockable safe, which were dealt\r\nwith quickly and efficiently. I was not able to take advantage of the\r\ncomplementary dinner and folk show at the Tunupa restaurant in <st1:place w:st=\"on\">Cusco</st1:place> on Day 2, because of a very early start the next\r\nday, so&nbsp;at the conclusion of my trip, I treated myself to&nbsp;a gourmet\r\nlunch there. The menu and wine list are absolutely outstanding! If you like\r\nfood, this restaurant is not to be missed!</span></p><p class=\"MsoNormal\"><br></p><p class=\"MsoNormal\"><meta http-equiv=\"Content-Type\" content=\"text/html; charset=utf-8\"><meta name=\"ProgId\" content=\"Word.Document\"><meta name=\"Generator\" content=\"Microsoft Word 11\"><meta name=\"Originator\" content=\"Microsoft Word 11\"><link rel=\"File-List\" href=\"file:///C:%5CDOCUME%7E1%5CADMINI%7E1%5CCONFIG%7E1%5CTemp%5Cmsohtml1%5C10%5Cclip_filelist.xml\"><!--[if gte mso 9]><xml>\r\n <w:WordDocument>\r\n  <w:View>Normal</w:View>\r\n  <w:Zoom>0</w:Zoom>\r\n  <w:HyphenationZone>21</w:HyphenationZone>\r\n  <w:PunctuationKerning/>\r\n  <w:ValidateAgainstSchemas/>\r\n  <w:SaveIfXMLInvalid>false</w:SaveIfXMLInvalid>\r\n  <w:IgnoreMixedContent>false</w:IgnoreMixedContent>\r\n  <w:AlwaysShowPlaceholderText>false</w:AlwaysShowPlaceholderText>\r\n  <w:Compatibility>\r\n   <w:BreakWrappedTables/>\r\n   <w:SnapToGridInCell/>\r\n   <w:WrapTextWithPunct/>\r\n   <w:UseAsianBreakRules/>\r\n   <w:DontGrowAutofit/>\r\n  </w:Compatibility>\r\n  <w:BrowserLevel>MicrosoftInternetExplorer4</w:BrowserLevel>\r\n </w:WordDocument>\r\n</xml><![endif]--><!--[if gte mso 9]><xml>\r\n <w:LatentStyles DefLockedState=\"false\" LatentStyleCount=\"156\">\r\n </w:LatentStyles>\r\n</xml><![endif]--><style>\r\n<!--\r\n /* Font Definitions */\r\n @font-face\r\n	{font-family:Verdana;\r\n	panose-1:2 11 6 4 3 5 4 4 2 4;\r\n	mso-font-charset:0;\r\n	mso-generic-font-family:swiss;\r\n	mso-font-pitch:variable;\r\n	mso-font-signature:536871559 0 0 0 415 0;}\r\n /* Style Definitions */\r\n p.MsoNormal, li.MsoNormal, div.MsoNormal\r\n	{mso-style-parent:\"\";\r\n	margin:0cm;\r\n	margin-bottom:.0001pt;\r\n	mso-pagination:widow-orphan;\r\n	font-size:12.0pt;\r\n	font-family:\"Times New Roman\";\r\n	mso-fareast-font-family:\"Times New Roman\";}\r\n@page Section1\r\n	{size:612.0pt 792.0pt;\r\n	margin:70.85pt 3.0cm 70.85pt 3.0cm;\r\n	mso-header-margin:36.0pt;\r\n	mso-footer-margin:36.0pt;\r\n	mso-paper-source:0;}\r\ndiv.Section1\r\n	{page:Section1;}\r\n-->\r\n</style><!--[if gte mso 10]>\r\n<style>\r\n /* Style Definitions */\r\n table.MsoNormalTable\r\n	{mso-style-name:\"Tabla normal\";\r\n	mso-tstyle-rowband-size:0;\r\n	mso-tstyle-colband-size:0;\r\n	mso-style-noshow:yes;\r\n	mso-style-parent:\"\";\r\n	mso-padding-alt:0cm 5.4pt 0cm 5.4pt;\r\n	mso-para-margin:0cm;\r\n	mso-para-margin-bottom:.0001pt;\r\n	mso-pagination:widow-orphan;\r\n	font-size:10.0pt;\r\n	font-family:\"Times New Roman\";\r\n	mso-ansi-language:#0400;\r\n	mso-fareast-language:#0400;\r\n	mso-bidi-language:#0400;}\r\n</style>\r\n<![endif]-->\r\n\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><b style=\"\"><span style=\"font-size: 8.5pt; font-family: Verdana;\" lang=\"EN-US\">All in all,\r\na problem free trip of a life time. Many thanks for all your efforts!<o:p></o:p></span></b></p>\r\n\r\n<br><span style=\"font-size: 8.5pt; font-family: Verdana;\" lang=\"EN-US\"><o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n\r\n                ','<meta http-equiv=\"Content-Type\" content=\"text/html; charset=utf-8\"><meta name=\"ProgId\" content=\"Word.Document\"><meta name=\"Generator\" content=\"Microsoft Word 11\"><meta name=\"Originator\" content=\"Micro','','','',181,0,0,NULL,NULL,NULL),(386,1,'Hi Rylee,','<meta http-equiv=\"Content-Type\" content=\"text/html; charset=utf-8\"><meta name=\"ProgId\" content=\"Word.Document\"><meta name=\"Generator\" content=\"Microsoft Word 11\"><meta name=\"Originator\" content=\"Microsoft Word 11\"><link rel=\"File-List\" href=\"file:///C:%5CDOCUME%7E1%5CADMINI%7E1%5CCONFIG%7E1%5CTemp%5Cmsohtml1%5C16%5Cclip_filelist.xml\"><o:smarttagtype namespaceuri=\"urn:schemas-microsoft-com:office:smarttags\" name=\"country-region\" downloadurl=\"http://www.5iantlavalamp.com/\"></o:smarttagtype><o:smarttagtype namespaceuri=\"urn:schemas-microsoft-com:office:smarttags\" name=\"place\" downloadurl=\"http://www.5iantlavalamp.com/\"></o:smarttagtype><o:smarttagtype namespaceuri=\"urn:schemas-microsoft-com:office:smarttags\" name=\"City\" downloadurl=\"http://www.5iamas-microsoft-com:office:smarttags\"></o:smarttagtype><!--[if gte mso 9]><xml>\r\n <w:WordDocument>\r\n  <w:View>Normal</w:View>\r\n  <w:Zoom>0</w:Zoom>\r\n  <w:HyphenationZone>21</w:HyphenationZone>\r\n  <w:PunctuationKerning/>\r\n  <w:ValidateAgainstSchemas/>\r\n  <w:SaveIfXMLInvalid>false</w:SaveIfXMLInvalid>\r\n  <w:IgnoreMixedContent>false</w:IgnoreMixedContent>\r\n  <w:AlwaysShowPlaceholderText>false</w:AlwaysShowPlaceholderText>\r\n  <w:Compatibility>\r\n   <w:BreakWrappedTables/>\r\n   <w:SnapToGridInCell/>\r\n   <w:WrapTextWithPunct/>\r\n   <w:UseAsianBreakRules/>\r\n   <w:DontGrowAutofit/>\r\n  </w:Compatibility>\r\n  <w:BrowserLevel>MicrosoftInternetExplorer4</w:BrowserLevel>\r\n </w:WordDocument>\r\n</xml><![endif]--><!--[if gte mso 9]><xml>\r\n <w:LatentStyles DefLockedState=\"false\" LatentStyleCount=\"156\">\r\n </w:LatentStyles>\r\n</xml><![endif]--><!--[if !mso]><object\r\n classid=\"clsid:38481807-CA0E-42D2-BF39-B33AF135CC4D\" id=ieooui></object>\r\n<style>\r\nst1\\:*{behavior:url(#ieooui) }\r\n</style>\r\n<![endif]--><style>\r\n<!--\r\n /* Font Definitions */\r\n @font-face\r\n	{font-family:Verdana;\r\n	panose-1:2 11 6 4 3 5 4 4 2 4;\r\n	mso-font-charset:0;\r\n	mso-generic-font-family:swiss;\r\n	mso-font-pitch:variable;\r\n	mso-font-signature:536871559 0 0 0 415 0;}\r\n /* Style Definitions */\r\n p.MsoNormal, li.MsoNormal, div.MsoNormal\r\n	{mso-style-parent:\"\";\r\n	margin:0cm;\r\n	margin-bottom:.0001pt;\r\n	mso-pagination:widow-orphan;\r\n	font-size:12.0pt;\r\n	font-family:\"Times New Roman\";\r\n	mso-fareast-font-family:\"Times New Roman\";}\r\n@page Section1\r\n	{size:612.0pt 792.0pt;\r\n	margin:70.85pt 3.0cm 70.85pt 3.0cm;\r\n	mso-header-margin:36.0pt;\r\n	mso-footer-margin:36.0pt;\r\n	mso-paper-source:0;}\r\ndiv.Section1\r\n	{page:Section1;}\r\n-->\r\n</style><!--[if gte mso 10]>\r\n<style>\r\n /* Style Definitions */\r\n table.MsoNormalTable\r\n	{mso-style-name:\"Tabla normal\";\r\n	mso-tstyle-rowband-size:0;\r\n	mso-tstyle-colband-size:0;\r\n	mso-style-noshow:yes;\r\n	mso-style-parent:\"\";\r\n	mso-padding-alt:0cm 5.4pt 0cm 5.4pt;\r\n	mso-para-margin:0cm;\r\n	mso-para-margin-bottom:.0001pt;\r\n	mso-pagination:widow-orphan;\r\n	font-size:10.0pt;\r\n	font-family:\"Times New Roman\";\r\n	mso-ansi-language:#0400;\r\n	mso-fareast-language:#0400;\r\n	mso-bidi-language:#0400;}\r\n</style>\r\n<![endif]-->\r\n\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><span style=\"font-size: 8.5pt; font-family: Verdana;\" lang=\"EN-US\">I\'ve asked the family to send me their comments so I\r\ncan forward a \"family\" testimonial to you.&nbsp; In the meantime, please know\r\nthat we had a fantastic time.&nbsp; <st1:country-region w:st=\"on\"><st1:place w:st=\"on\">Peru</st1:place></st1:country-region> is beautiful and the people\r\nare friendly and helpful.&nbsp; Your staff was extraordinary.&nbsp; The\r\ntransfers went smoothly and without a problem.&nbsp; It was great to be met at\r\nevery airport and hotel.&nbsp; The accommodations were terrific; the Sanctuary\r\nHotel is much closer to <st1:city w:st=\"on\"><st1:place w:st=\"on\">Machu Picchu</st1:place></st1:city>\r\nthan I thought; just a few feet away from the entrance. <st1:city w:st=\"on\"><st1:place w:st=\"on\">Machu Picchu</st1:place></st1:city> was better than I expected; much\r\nlarger and impressive.&nbsp; One highlight was the guides: Alison was great,\r\nBlas was a kick (with his political viewpoint) and Yuri (at Rainforest\r\nExpeditions) was incredible.<o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><span style=\"font-size: 8.5pt; font-family: Verdana;\" lang=\"EN-US\">&nbsp;<o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><span style=\"font-size: 8.5pt; font-family: Verdana;\" lang=\"EN-US\">In all, your team did an outstanding job!!<o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><span style=\"font-size: 8.5pt; font-family: Verdana;\" lang=\"EN-US\">&nbsp;<o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n\r\n                ','<meta http-equiv=\"Content-Type\" content=\"text/html; charset=utf-8\"><meta name=\"ProgId\" content=\"Word.Document\"><meta name=\"Generator\" content=\"Microsoft Word 11\"><meta name=\"Originator\" content=\"Micro','','','',176,0,0,NULL,NULL,NULL),(387,1,'Dear Deanna,','<meta http-equiv=\"Content-Type\" content=\"text/html; charset=utf-8\"><meta name=\"ProgId\" content=\"Word.Document\"><meta name=\"Generator\" content=\"Microsoft Word 11\"><meta name=\"Originator\" content=\"Microsoft Word 11\"><link rel=\"File-List\" href=\"file:///C:%5CDOCUME%7E1%5CADMINI%7E1%5CCONFIG%7E1%5CTemp%5Cmsohtml1%5C20%5Cclip_filelist.xml\"><o:smarttagtype namespaceuri=\"urn:schemas-microsoft-com:office:smarttags\" name=\"country-region\" downloadurl=\"http://www.5iantlavalamp.com/\"></o:smarttagtype><o:smarttagtype namespaceuri=\"urn:schemas-microsoft-com:office:smarttags\" name=\"place\" downloadurl=\"http://www.5iantlavalamp.com/\"></o:smarttagtype><!--[if gte mso 9]><xml>\r\n <w:WordDocument>\r\n  <w:View>Normal</w:View>\r\n  <w:Zoom>0</w:Zoom>\r\n  <w:HyphenationZone>21</w:HyphenationZone>\r\n  <w:PunctuationKerning/>\r\n  <w:ValidateAgainstSchemas/>\r\n  <w:SaveIfXMLInvalid>false</w:SaveIfXMLInvalid>\r\n  <w:IgnoreMixedContent>false</w:IgnoreMixedContent>\r\n  <w:AlwaysShowPlaceholderText>false</w:AlwaysShowPlaceholderText>\r\n  <w:Compatibility>\r\n   <w:BreakWrappedTables/>\r\n   <w:SnapToGridInCell/>\r\n   <w:WrapTextWithPunct/>\r\n   <w:UseAsianBreakRules/>\r\n   <w:DontGrowAutofit/>\r\n  </w:Compatibility>\r\n  <w:BrowserLevel>MicrosoftInternetExplorer4</w:BrowserLevel>\r\n </w:WordDocument>\r\n</xml><![endif]--><!--[if gte mso 9]><xml>\r\n <w:LatentStyles DefLockedState=\"false\" LatentStyleCount=\"156\">\r\n </w:LatentStyles>\r\n</xml><![endif]--><!--[if !mso]><object\r\n classid=\"clsid:38481807-CA0E-42D2-BF39-B33AF135CC4D\" id=ieooui></object>\r\n<style>\r\nst1\\:*{behavior:url(#ieooui) }\r\n</style>\r\n<![endif]--><style>\r\n<!--\r\n /* Font Definitions */\r\n @font-face\r\n	{font-family:Verdana;\r\n	panose-1:2 11 6 4 3 5 4 4 2 4;\r\n	mso-font-charset:0;\r\n	mso-generic-font-family:swiss;\r\n	mso-font-pitch:variable;\r\n	mso-font-signature:536871559 0 0 0 415 0;}\r\n /* Style Definitions */\r\n p.MsoNormal, li.MsoNormal, div.MsoNormal\r\n	{mso-style-parent:\"\";\r\n	margin:0cm;\r\n	margin-bottom:.0001pt;\r\n	mso-pagination:widow-orphan;\r\n	font-size:12.0pt;\r\n	font-family:\"Times New Roman\";\r\n	mso-fareast-font-family:\"Times New Roman\";}\r\n@page Section1\r\n	{size:612.0pt 792.0pt;\r\n	margin:70.85pt 3.0cm 70.85pt 3.0cm;\r\n	mso-header-margin:36.0pt;\r\n	mso-footer-margin:36.0pt;\r\n	mso-paper-source:0;}\r\ndiv.Section1\r\n	{page:Section1;}\r\n-->\r\n</style><!--[if gte mso 10]>\r\n<style>\r\n /* Style Definitions */\r\n table.MsoNormalTable\r\n	{mso-style-name:\"Tabla normal\";\r\n	mso-tstyle-rowband-size:0;\r\n	mso-tstyle-colband-size:0;\r\n	mso-style-noshow:yes;\r\n	mso-style-parent:\"\";\r\n	mso-padding-alt:0cm 5.4pt 0cm 5.4pt;\r\n	mso-para-margin:0cm;\r\n	mso-para-margin-bottom:.0001pt;\r\n	mso-pagination:widow-orphan;\r\n	font-size:10.0pt;\r\n	font-family:\"Times New Roman\";\r\n	mso-ansi-language:#0400;\r\n	mso-fareast-language:#0400;\r\n	mso-bidi-language:#0400;}\r\n</style>\r\n<![endif]-->\r\n\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-size: 8.5pt; font-family: Verdana;\" lang=\"EN-US\">Thanks for\r\nyour message.&nbsp;<st1:country-region w:st=\"on\"><st1:place w:st=\"on\">Peru</st1:place></st1:country-region>\r\nwas just great.&nbsp;It was exactly what we expected and a really unique\r\nexperience.&nbsp; The hotel was lovely and the guides and transfers worked well\r\nso no complaints thanks.<o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-size: 8.5pt; font-family: Verdana;\" lang=\"EN-US\">&nbsp;<o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-size: 8.5pt; font-family: Verdana;\" lang=\"EN-US\">The guide\r\nfor the first day was very informative and enthusiastic. All in all, yes, we\r\nhad a great time and I shall be more than happy to recommend <st1:place w:st=\"on\"><st1:country-region w:st=\"on\">Peru</st1:country-region></st1:place> for Less in the future.&nbsp; <o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><span style=\"font-size: 8.5pt; font-family: Verdana;\" lang=\"EN-US\">&nbsp;<o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><i style=\"\"><span style=\"font-size: 8.5pt; font-family: Verdana;\" lang=\"EN-GB\">Many\r\nthanks,<o:p></o:p></span></i></p>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><i style=\"\"><span style=\"font-size: 8.5pt; font-family: Verdana;\" lang=\"EN-GB\">&nbsp;<o:p></o:p></span></i></p>\r\n\r\n                ','<meta http-equiv=\"Content-Type\" content=\"text/html; charset=utf-8\"><meta name=\"ProgId\" content=\"Word.Document\"><meta name=\"Generator\" content=\"Microsoft Word 11\"><meta name=\"Originator\" content=\"Micro','','','',180,0,0,NULL,NULL,NULL),(388,1,'Dear Peru For Less','<meta http-equiv=\"Content-Type\" content=\"text/html; charset=utf-8\"><meta name=\"ProgId\" content=\"Word.Document\"><meta name=\"Generator\" content=\"Microsoft Word 11\"><meta name=\"Originator\" content=\"Microsoft Word 11\"><link rel=\"File-List\" href=\"file:///C:%5CDOCUME%7E1%5CADMINI%7E1%5CCONFIG%7E1%5CTemp%5Cmsohtml1%5C23%5Cclip_filelist.xml\"><o:smarttagtype namespaceuri=\"urn:schemas-microsoft-com:office:smarttags\" name=\"country-region\" downloadurl=\"http://www.5iantlavalamp.com/\"></o:smarttagtype><o:smarttagtype namespaceuri=\"urn:schemas-microsoft-com:office:smarttags\" name=\"place\" downloadurl=\"http://www.5iantlavalamp.com/\"></o:smarttagtype><o:smarttagtype namespaceuri=\"urn:schemas-microsoft-com:office:smarttags\" name=\"City\" downloadurl=\"http://www.5iamas-microsoft-com:office:smarttags\"></o:smarttagtype><!--[if gte mso 9]><xml>\r\n <w:WordDocument>\r\n  <w:View>Normal</w:View>\r\n  <w:Zoom>0</w:Zoom>\r\n  <w:HyphenationZone>21</w:HyphenationZone>\r\n  <w:PunctuationKerning/>\r\n  <w:ValidateAgainstSchemas/>\r\n  <w:SaveIfXMLInvalid>false</w:SaveIfXMLInvalid>\r\n  <w:IgnoreMixedContent>false</w:IgnoreMixedContent>\r\n  <w:AlwaysShowPlaceholderText>false</w:AlwaysShowPlaceholderText>\r\n  <w:Compatibility>\r\n   <w:BreakWrappedTables/>\r\n   <w:SnapToGridInCell/>\r\n   <w:WrapTextWithPunct/>\r\n   <w:UseAsianBreakRules/>\r\n   <w:DontGrowAutofit/>\r\n  </w:Compatibility>\r\n  <w:BrowserLevel>MicrosoftInternetExplorer4</w:BrowserLevel>\r\n </w:WordDocument>\r\n</xml><![endif]--><!--[if gte mso 9]><xml>\r\n <w:LatentStyles DefLockedState=\"false\" LatentStyleCount=\"156\">\r\n </w:LatentStyles>\r\n</xml><![endif]--><!--[if !mso]><object\r\n classid=\"clsid:38481807-CA0E-42D2-BF39-B33AF135CC4D\" id=ieooui></object>\r\n<style>\r\nst1\\:*{behavior:url(#ieooui) }\r\n</style>\r\n<![endif]--><style>\r\n<!--\r\n /* Font Definitions */\r\n @font-face\r\n	{font-family:Verdana;\r\n	panose-1:2 11 6 4 3 5 4 4 2 4;\r\n	mso-font-charset:0;\r\n	mso-generic-font-family:swiss;\r\n	mso-font-pitch:variable;\r\n	mso-font-signature:536871559 0 0 0 415 0;}\r\n /* Style Definitions */\r\n p.MsoNormal, li.MsoNormal, div.MsoNormal\r\n	{mso-style-parent:\"\";\r\n	margin:0cm;\r\n	margin-bottom:.0001pt;\r\n	mso-pagination:widow-orphan;\r\n	font-size:12.0pt;\r\n	font-family:\"Times New Roman\";\r\n	mso-fareast-font-family:\"Times New Roman\";}\r\n@page Section1\r\n	{size:612.0pt 792.0pt;\r\n	margin:70.85pt 3.0cm 70.85pt 3.0cm;\r\n	mso-header-margin:36.0pt;\r\n	mso-footer-margin:36.0pt;\r\n	mso-paper-source:0;}\r\ndiv.Section1\r\n	{page:Section1;}\r\n-->\r\n</style><!--[if gte mso 10]>\r\n<style>\r\n /* Style Definitions */\r\n table.MsoNormalTable\r\n	{mso-style-name:\"Tabla normal\";\r\n	mso-tstyle-rowband-size:0;\r\n	mso-tstyle-colband-size:0;\r\n	mso-style-noshow:yes;\r\n	mso-style-parent:\"\";\r\n	mso-padding-alt:0cm 5.4pt 0cm 5.4pt;\r\n	mso-para-margin:0cm;\r\n	mso-para-margin-bottom:.0001pt;\r\n	mso-pagination:widow-orphan;\r\n	font-size:10.0pt;\r\n	font-family:\"Times New Roman\";\r\n	mso-ansi-language:#0400;\r\n	mso-fareast-language:#0400;\r\n	mso-bidi-language:#0400;}\r\n</style>\r\n<![endif]-->\r\n\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><span style=\"font-size: 8.5pt; font-family: Verdana;\" lang=\"EN-GB\">The trip to <st1:place w:st=\"on\"><st1:country-region w:st=\"on\">Peru</st1:country-region></st1:place> was amazing.&nbsp; I feel that\r\n<st1:country-region w:st=\"on\"><st1:place w:st=\"on\">Peru</st1:place></st1:country-region>\r\nfor Less took really good care of us.&nbsp; Allison and Fabricio were\r\ngreat!&nbsp; I fell in love with <st1:city w:st=\"on\"><st1:place w:st=\"on\">Cuzco</st1:place></st1:city>.&nbsp;\r\nThe staff at the Arqueologo Hotel made me feel very much at home and they even\r\ntaught me some Spanish :-) I really have to say that the staff at the Rupa Wasi\r\nhotel were also very kind and helpful even though their hotel was not our first\r\nchoice. <o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><span style=\"font-size: 8.5pt; font-family: Verdana;\" lang=\"EN-GB\">&nbsp;<o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><span style=\"font-size: 8.5pt; font-family: Verdana;\" lang=\"EN-GB\">Overall, I would definitely recommend <st1:place w:st=\"on\"><st1:country-region w:st=\"on\">Peru</st1:country-region></st1:place>\r\nfor Less to friends.<o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n\r\n                ','<meta http-equiv=\"Content-Type\" content=\"text/html; charset=utf-8\"><meta name=\"ProgId\" content=\"Word.Document\"><meta name=\"Generator\" content=\"Microsoft Word 11\"><meta name=\"Originator\" content=\"Micro','','','',178,0,0,NULL,NULL,NULL),(389,1,'Hi Juan Pablo, ','<meta http-equiv=\"Content-Type\" content=\"text/html; charset=utf-8\"><meta name=\"ProgId\" content=\"Word.Document\"><meta name=\"Generator\" content=\"Microsoft Word 11\"><meta name=\"Originator\" content=\"Microsoft Word 11\"><link rel=\"File-List\" href=\"file:///C:%5CDOCUME%7E1%5CADMINI%7E1%5CCONFIG%7E1%5CTemp%5Cmsohtml1%5C01%5Cclip_filelist.xml\"><o:smarttagtype namespaceuri=\"urn:schemas-microsoft-com:office:smarttags\" name=\"country-region\" downloadurl=\"http://www.5iantlavalamp.com/\"></o:smarttagtype><o:smarttagtype namespaceuri=\"urn:schemas-microsoft-com:office:smarttags\" name=\"place\" downloadurl=\"http://www.5iantlavalamp.com/\"></o:smarttagtype><!--[if gte mso 9]><xml>\r\n <w:WordDocument>\r\n  <w:View>Normal</w:View>\r\n  <w:Zoom>0</w:Zoom>\r\n  <w:HyphenationZone>21</w:HyphenationZone>\r\n  <w:PunctuationKerning/>\r\n  <w:ValidateAgainstSchemas/>\r\n  <w:SaveIfXMLInvalid>false</w:SaveIfXMLInvalid>\r\n  <w:IgnoreMixedContent>false</w:IgnoreMixedContent>\r\n  <w:AlwaysShowPlaceholderText>false</w:AlwaysShowPlaceholderText>\r\n  <w:Compatibility>\r\n   <w:BreakWrappedTables/>\r\n   <w:SnapToGridInCell/>\r\n   <w:WrapTextWithPunct/>\r\n   <w:UseAsianBreakRules/>\r\n   <w:DontGrowAutofit/>\r\n  </w:Compatibility>\r\n  <w:BrowserLevel>MicrosoftInternetExplorer4</w:BrowserLevel>\r\n </w:WordDocument>\r\n</xml><![endif]--><!--[if gte mso 9]><xml>\r\n <w:LatentStyles DefLockedState=\"false\" LatentStyleCount=\"156\">\r\n </w:LatentStyles>\r\n</xml><![endif]--><!--[if !mso]><object\r\n classid=\"clsid:38481807-CA0E-42D2-BF39-B33AF135CC4D\" id=ieooui></object>\r\n<style>\r\nst1\\:*{behavior:url(#ieooui) }\r\n</style>\r\n<![endif]--><style>\r\n<!--\r\n /* Font Definitions */\r\n @font-face\r\n	{font-family:Verdana;\r\n	panose-1:2 11 6 4 3 5 4 4 2 4;\r\n	mso-font-charset:0;\r\n	mso-generic-font-family:swiss;\r\n	mso-font-pitch:variable;\r\n	mso-font-signature:536871559 0 0 0 415 0;}\r\n /* Style Definitions */\r\n p.MsoNormal, li.MsoNormal, div.MsoNormal\r\n	{mso-style-parent:\"\";\r\n	margin:0cm;\r\n	margin-bottom:.0001pt;\r\n	mso-pagination:widow-orphan;\r\n	font-size:12.0pt;\r\n	font-family:\"Times New Roman\";\r\n	mso-fareast-font-family:\"Times New Roman\";}\r\n@page Section1\r\n	{size:612.0pt 792.0pt;\r\n	margin:70.85pt 3.0cm 70.85pt 3.0cm;\r\n	mso-header-margin:36.0pt;\r\n	mso-footer-margin:36.0pt;\r\n	mso-paper-source:0;}\r\ndiv.Section1\r\n	{page:Section1;}\r\n-->\r\n</style><!--[if gte mso 10]>\r\n<style>\r\n /* Style Definitions */\r\n table.MsoNormalTable\r\n	{mso-style-name:\"Tabla normal\";\r\n	mso-tstyle-rowband-size:0;\r\n	mso-tstyle-colband-size:0;\r\n	mso-style-noshow:yes;\r\n	mso-style-parent:\"\";\r\n	mso-padding-alt:0cm 5.4pt 0cm 5.4pt;\r\n	mso-para-margin:0cm;\r\n	mso-para-margin-bottom:.0001pt;\r\n	mso-pagination:widow-orphan;\r\n	font-size:10.0pt;\r\n	font-family:\"Times New Roman\";\r\n	mso-ansi-language:#0400;\r\n	mso-fareast-language:#0400;\r\n	mso-bidi-language:#0400;}\r\n</style>\r\n<![endif]-->\r\n\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><span style=\"font-size: 8.5pt; font-family: Verdana;\" lang=\"EN-GB\">I am sorry for the delay in my reply.&nbsp; I\r\ndefinitely had some amazing experiences that I will always treasure.&nbsp; The\r\nsites I saw were very beautiful.&nbsp; One of the great things about the\r\nitinerary was that I was able to get ready for the Salkanty Trail by hiking in\r\nthe Amazon (although the hikes were not especially strenuous, it was still good\r\nto get that exercise) and spending a few days in Cuzco to get used to the\r\naltitude.&nbsp; Overall I had a fantastic time in <st1:country-region w:st=\"on\"><st1:place w:st=\"on\">Peru</st1:place></st1:country-region>. <o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n\r\n                ','<meta http-equiv=\"Content-Type\" content=\"text/html; charset=utf-8\"><meta name=\"ProgId\" content=\"Word.Document\"><meta name=\"Generator\" content=\"Microsoft Word 11\"><meta name=\"Originator\" content=\"Micro','','','',174,0,0,NULL,NULL,NULL),(390,1,'Dear Peru For Less','<meta http-equiv=\"Content-Type\" content=\"text/html; charset=utf-8\"><meta name=\"ProgId\" content=\"Word.Document\"><meta name=\"Generator\" content=\"Microsoft Word 11\"><meta name=\"Originator\" content=\"Microsoft Word 11\"><link rel=\"File-List\" href=\"file:///C:%5CDOCUME%7E1%5CADMINI%7E1%5CCONFIG%7E1%5CTemp%5Cmsohtml1%5C04%5Cclip_filelist.xml\"><o:smarttagtype namespaceuri=\"urn:schemas-microsoft-com:office:smarttags\" name=\"place\" downloadurl=\"http://www.5iantlavalamp.com/\"></o:smarttagtype><o:smarttagtype namespaceuri=\"urn:schemas-microsoft-com:office:smarttags\" name=\"City\" downloadurl=\"http://www.5iamas-microsoft-com:office:smarttags\"></o:smarttagtype><o:smarttagtype namespaceuri=\"urn:schemas-microsoft-com:office:smarttags\" name=\"PlaceName\" downloadurl=\"http://www.5iantlavalamp.com/\"></o:smarttagtype><o:smarttagtype namespaceuri=\"urn:schemas-microsoft-com:office:smarttags\" name=\"PlaceType\" downloadurl=\"http://www.5iantlavalamp.com/\"></o:smarttagtype><!--[if gte mso 9]><xml>\r\n <w:WordDocument>\r\n  <w:View>Normal</w:View>\r\n  <w:Zoom>0</w:Zoom>\r\n  <w:HyphenationZone>21</w:HyphenationZone>\r\n  <w:PunctuationKerning/>\r\n  <w:ValidateAgainstSchemas/>\r\n  <w:SaveIfXMLInvalid>false</w:SaveIfXMLInvalid>\r\n  <w:IgnoreMixedContent>false</w:IgnoreMixedContent>\r\n  <w:AlwaysShowPlaceholderText>false</w:AlwaysShowPlaceholderText>\r\n  <w:Compatibility>\r\n   <w:BreakWrappedTables/>\r\n   <w:SnapToGridInCell/>\r\n   <w:WrapTextWithPunct/>\r\n   <w:UseAsianBreakRules/>\r\n   <w:DontGrowAutofit/>\r\n  </w:Compatibility>\r\n  <w:BrowserLevel>MicrosoftInternetExplorer4</w:BrowserLevel>\r\n </w:WordDocument>\r\n</xml><![endif]--><!--[if gte mso 9]><xml>\r\n <w:LatentStyles DefLockedState=\"false\" LatentStyleCount=\"156\">\r\n </w:LatentStyles>\r\n</xml><![endif]--><!--[if !mso]><object\r\n classid=\"clsid:38481807-CA0E-42D2-BF39-B33AF135CC4D\" id=ieooui></object>\r\n<style>\r\nst1\\:*{behavior:url(#ieooui) }\r\n</style>\r\n<![endif]--><style>\r\n<!--\r\n /* Font Definitions */\r\n @font-face\r\n	{font-family:Verdana;\r\n	panose-1:2 11 6 4 3 5 4 4 2 4;\r\n	mso-font-charset:0;\r\n	mso-generic-font-family:swiss;\r\n	mso-font-pitch:variable;\r\n	mso-font-signature:536871559 0 0 0 415 0;}\r\n /* Style Definitions */\r\n p.MsoNormal, li.MsoNormal, div.MsoNormal\r\n	{mso-style-parent:\"\";\r\n	margin:0cm;\r\n	margin-bottom:.0001pt;\r\n	mso-pagination:widow-orphan;\r\n	font-size:12.0pt;\r\n	font-family:\"Times New Roman\";\r\n	mso-fareast-font-family:\"Times New Roman\";}\r\n@page Section1\r\n	{size:612.0pt 792.0pt;\r\n	margin:70.85pt 3.0cm 70.85pt 3.0cm;\r\n	mso-header-margin:36.0pt;\r\n	mso-footer-margin:36.0pt;\r\n	mso-paper-source:0;}\r\ndiv.Section1\r\n	{page:Section1;}\r\n-->\r\n</style><!--[if gte mso 10]>\r\n<style>\r\n /* Style Definitions */\r\n table.MsoNormalTable\r\n	{mso-style-name:\"Tabla normal\";\r\n	mso-tstyle-rowband-size:0;\r\n	mso-tstyle-colband-size:0;\r\n	mso-style-noshow:yes;\r\n	mso-style-parent:\"\";\r\n	mso-padding-alt:0cm 5.4pt 0cm 5.4pt;\r\n	mso-para-margin:0cm;\r\n	mso-para-margin-bottom:.0001pt;\r\n	mso-pagination:widow-orphan;\r\n	font-size:10.0pt;\r\n	font-family:\"Times New Roman\";\r\n	mso-ansi-language:#0400;\r\n	mso-fareast-language:#0400;\r\n	mso-bidi-language:#0400;}\r\n</style>\r\n<![endif]-->\r\n\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><span style=\"font-size: 8.5pt; font-family: Verdana;\" lang=\"EN-GB\">so relaxing yet we were always active doing activities\r\nand adventures. I loved walking through the mud! I also liked the fact there\r\nwas no electricity or hot water, just us and nature. We saw many animal\r\nspecies. <o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><span style=\"font-size: 8.5pt; font-family: Verdana;\" lang=\"EN-GB\">We were both in awe of <st1:city w:st=\"on\"><st1:place w:st=\"on\">Machu Picchu</st1:place></st1:city>. It was just mind blowing. Wandering\r\naround and exploring the Cathedrals and seeing all the gold and guilt was\r\nsomething else. The synergy of Inca and Spanish architecture is just a\r\nspectacular mix. Transfers were always on time and there was always someone\r\nthere to greet us. <o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><span style=\"font-size: 8.5pt; font-family: Verdana;\" lang=\"EN-GB\"><o:p>&nbsp;</o:p></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><span style=\"font-size: 8.5pt; font-family: Verdana;\" lang=\"EN-GB\">Thanks for your help in organising the trip, Chris.\r\nYou explained everything so well and knew what we were after. I have already\r\nrecommend Peru For Less to some of my friends. I would suggest they take a few\r\nextra days and get down to <st1:place w:st=\"on\"><st1:placetype w:st=\"on\">Lake</st1:placetype>\r\n <st1:placename w:st=\"on\">Titikaka</st1:placename></st1:place>; we regret not\r\ngetting down there.<o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n\r\n                ','<meta http-equiv=\"Content-Type\" content=\"text/html; charset=utf-8\"><meta name=\"ProgId\" content=\"Word.Document\"><meta name=\"Generator\" content=\"Microsoft Word 11\"><meta name=\"Originator\" content=\"Micro','','','',172,0,0,NULL,NULL,NULL),(391,1,'Hello Rylee,','<meta http-equiv=\"Content-Type\" content=\"text/html; charset=utf-8\"><meta name=\"ProgId\" content=\"Word.Document\"><meta name=\"Generator\" content=\"Microsoft Word 11\"><meta name=\"Originator\" content=\"Microsoft Word 11\"><link rel=\"File-List\" href=\"file:///C:%5CDOCUME%7E1%5CADMINI%7E1%5CCONFIG%7E1%5CTemp%5Cmsohtml1%5C07%5Cclip_filelist.xml\"><o:smarttagtype namespaceuri=\"urn:schemas-microsoft-com:office:smarttags\" name=\"country-region\" downloadurl=\"http://www.5iantlavalamp.com/\"></o:smarttagtype><o:smarttagtype namespaceuri=\"urn:schemas-microsoft-com:office:smarttags\" name=\"place\" downloadurl=\"http://www.5iantlavalamp.com/\"></o:smarttagtype><o:smarttagtype namespaceuri=\"urn:schemas-microsoft-com:office:smarttags\" name=\"City\" downloadurl=\"http://www.5iamas-microsoft-com:office:smarttags\"></o:smarttagtype><o:smarttagtype namespaceuri=\"urn:schemas-microsoft-com:office:smarttags\" name=\"PlaceName\" downloadurl=\"http://www.5iantlavalamp.com/\"></o:smarttagtype><o:smarttagtype namespaceuri=\"urn:schemas-microsoft-com:office:smarttags\" name=\"PlaceType\" downloadurl=\"http://www.5iantlavalamp.com/\"></o:smarttagtype><!--[if gte mso 9]><xml>\r\n <w:WordDocument>\r\n  <w:View>Normal</w:View>\r\n  <w:Zoom>0</w:Zoom>\r\n  <w:HyphenationZone>21</w:HyphenationZone>\r\n  <w:PunctuationKerning/>\r\n  <w:ValidateAgainstSchemas/>\r\n  <w:SaveIfXMLInvalid>false</w:SaveIfXMLInvalid>\r\n  <w:IgnoreMixedContent>false</w:IgnoreMixedContent>\r\n  <w:AlwaysShowPlaceholderText>false</w:AlwaysShowPlaceholderText>\r\n  <w:Compatibility>\r\n   <w:BreakWrappedTables/>\r\n   <w:SnapToGridInCell/>\r\n   <w:WrapTextWithPunct/>\r\n   <w:UseAsianBreakRules/>\r\n   <w:DontGrowAutofit/>\r\n  </w:Compatibility>\r\n  <w:BrowserLevel>MicrosoftInternetExplorer4</w:BrowserLevel>\r\n </w:WordDocument>\r\n</xml><![endif]--><!--[if gte mso 9]><xml>\r\n <w:LatentStyles DefLockedState=\"false\" LatentStyleCount=\"156\">\r\n </w:LatentStyles>\r\n</xml><![endif]--><!--[if !mso]><object\r\n classid=\"clsid:38481807-CA0E-42D2-BF39-B33AF135CC4D\" id=ieooui></object>\r\n<style>\r\nst1\\:*{behavior:url(#ieooui) }\r\n</style>\r\n<![endif]--><style>\r\n<!--\r\n /* Font Definitions */\r\n @font-face\r\n	{font-family:Verdana;\r\n	panose-1:2 11 6 4 3 5 4 4 2 4;\r\n	mso-font-charset:0;\r\n	mso-generic-font-family:swiss;\r\n	mso-font-pitch:variable;\r\n	mso-font-signature:536871559 0 0 0 415 0;}\r\n /* Style Definitions */\r\n p.MsoNormal, li.MsoNormal, div.MsoNormal\r\n	{mso-style-parent:\"\";\r\n	margin:0cm;\r\n	margin-bottom:.0001pt;\r\n	mso-pagination:widow-orphan;\r\n	font-size:12.0pt;\r\n	font-family:\"Times New Roman\";\r\n	mso-fareast-font-family:\"Times New Roman\";}\r\n@page Section1\r\n	{size:612.0pt 792.0pt;\r\n	margin:70.85pt 3.0cm 70.85pt 3.0cm;\r\n	mso-header-margin:36.0pt;\r\n	mso-footer-margin:36.0pt;\r\n	mso-paper-source:0;}\r\ndiv.Section1\r\n	{page:Section1;}\r\n-->\r\n</style><!--[if gte mso 10]>\r\n<style>\r\n /* Style Definitions */\r\n table.MsoNormalTable\r\n	{mso-style-name:\"Tabla normal\";\r\n	mso-tstyle-rowband-size:0;\r\n	mso-tstyle-colband-size:0;\r\n	mso-style-noshow:yes;\r\n	mso-style-parent:\"\";\r\n	mso-padding-alt:0cm 5.4pt 0cm 5.4pt;\r\n	mso-para-margin:0cm;\r\n	mso-para-margin-bottom:.0001pt;\r\n	mso-pagination:widow-orphan;\r\n	font-size:10.0pt;\r\n	font-family:\"Times New Roman\";\r\n	mso-ansi-language:#0400;\r\n	mso-fareast-language:#0400;\r\n	mso-bidi-language:#0400;}\r\n</style>\r\n<![endif]-->\r\n\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><span style=\"font-size: 8.5pt; font-family: Verdana;\" lang=\"EN-GB\">Now that I am back in the States, I can report to you\r\nthat virtually every aspect of the trip was flawless. Your staff was\r\nexceptional at every location. The hotels were excellent and the country was\r\nbeautiful. I would particularly like to commend Allison in <st1:city w:st=\"on\">Cuzco</st1:city>\r\nand Jimmie, the leader of the <st1:place w:st=\"on\"><st1:placename w:st=\"on\">Sacred</st1:placename>\r\n <st1:placetype w:st=\"on\">Valley</st1:placetype></st1:place> tour. <o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><span style=\"font-size: 8.5pt; font-family: Verdana;\" lang=\"EN-GB\"><o:p>&nbsp;</o:p></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><span style=\"font-size: 8.5pt; font-family: Verdana;\" lang=\"EN-GB\">Machu Pichu was magnificent, as was the Amazon rain forest\r\nand Refugio Amazonas Lodge. Our guide there, Willian Duran, was excellent.\r\nEvery phase of the trip was exceptional, due, in no small part to the proficiency\r\nof your people. They were all excellent! Their language skills were very good\r\nand their knowledge of the culture and history of the places we visited was\r\nalso excellent. As a student of history, I was particularly impressed with the\r\ndetailed analysis given by all of your guides of pre-columbian Peruvian\r\nhistory. I took over 300 photographs, as well as three hours of video which I\r\nwill share with all of my friends. <st1:country-region w:st=\"on\"><st1:place w:st=\"on\">Peru</st1:place></st1:country-region> for Less will receive my\r\nhighest recommendation and I will actively encourage my friends and associates\r\nto patronize your organization. Also, as I am not finished yet with <st1:place w:st=\"on\">Latin America</st1:place>, I look forward to future relations with\r\nyour organization. Thank you for a wonderful experience!<o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n\r\n                ','<meta http-equiv=\"Content-Type\" content=\"text/html; charset=utf-8\"><meta name=\"ProgId\" content=\"Word.Document\"><meta name=\"Generator\" content=\"Microsoft Word 11\"><meta name=\"Originator\" content=\"Micro','','','',170,0,0,NULL,NULL,NULL),(392,1,'Dear Rylee','<meta http-equiv=\"Content-Type\" content=\"text/html; charset=utf-8\"><meta name=\"ProgId\" content=\"Word.Document\"><meta name=\"Generator\" content=\"Microsoft Word 11\"><meta name=\"Originator\" content=\"Microsoft Word 11\"><link rel=\"File-List\" href=\"file:///C:%5CDOCUME%7E1%5CADMINI%7E1%5CCONFIG%7E1%5CTemp%5Cmsohtml1%5C10%5Cclip_filelist.xml\"><o:smarttagtype namespaceuri=\"urn:schemas-microsoft-com:office:smarttags\" name=\"country-region\" downloadurl=\"http://www.5iantlavalamp.com/\"></o:smarttagtype><o:smarttagtype namespaceuri=\"urn:schemas-microsoft-com:office:smarttags\" name=\"place\" downloadurl=\"http://www.5iantlavalamp.com/\"></o:smarttagtype><o:smarttagtype namespaceuri=\"urn:schemas-microsoft-com:office:smarttags\" name=\"City\" downloadurl=\"http://www.5iamas-microsoft-com:office:smarttags\"></o:smarttagtype><o:smarttagtype namespaceuri=\"urn:schemas-microsoft-com:office:smarttags\" name=\"PlaceName\" downloadurl=\"http://www.5iantlavalamp.com/\"></o:smarttagtype><o:smarttagtype namespaceuri=\"urn:schemas-microsoft-com:office:smarttags\" name=\"PlaceType\" downloadurl=\"http://www.5iantlavalamp.com/\"></o:smarttagtype><o:smarttagtype namespaceuri=\"urn:schemas-microsoft-com:office:smarttags\" name=\"State\" downloadurl=\"http://www.5iamas-microsoft-com:office:smarttags\"></o:smarttagtype><!--[if gte mso 9]><xml>\r\n <w:WordDocument>\r\n  <w:View>Normal</w:View>\r\n  <w:Zoom>0</w:Zoom>\r\n  <w:HyphenationZone>21</w:HyphenationZone>\r\n  <w:PunctuationKerning/>\r\n  <w:ValidateAgainstSchemas/>\r\n  <w:SaveIfXMLInvalid>false</w:SaveIfXMLInvalid>\r\n  <w:IgnoreMixedContent>false</w:IgnoreMixedContent>\r\n  <w:AlwaysShowPlaceholderText>false</w:AlwaysShowPlaceholderText>\r\n  <w:Compatibility>\r\n   <w:BreakWrappedTables/>\r\n   <w:SnapToGridInCell/>\r\n   <w:WrapTextWithPunct/>\r\n   <w:UseAsianBreakRules/>\r\n   <w:DontGrowAutofit/>\r\n  </w:Compatibility>\r\n  <w:BrowserLevel>MicrosoftInternetExplorer4</w:BrowserLevel>\r\n </w:WordDocument>\r\n</xml><![endif]--><!--[if gte mso 9]><xml>\r\n <w:LatentStyles DefLockedState=\"false\" LatentStyleCount=\"156\">\r\n </w:LatentStyles>\r\n</xml><![endif]--><!--[if !mso]><object\r\n classid=\"clsid:38481807-CA0E-42D2-BF39-B33AF135CC4D\" id=ieooui></object>\r\n<style>\r\nst1\\:*{behavior:url(#ieooui) }\r\n</style>\r\n<![endif]--><style>\r\n<!--\r\n /* Font Definitions */\r\n @font-face\r\n	{font-family:Verdana;\r\n	panose-1:2 11 6 4 3 5 4 4 2 4;\r\n	mso-font-charset:0;\r\n	mso-generic-font-family:swiss;\r\n	mso-font-pitch:variable;\r\n	mso-font-signature:536871559 0 0 0 415 0;}\r\n /* Style Definitions */\r\n p.MsoNormal, li.MsoNormal, div.MsoNormal\r\n	{mso-style-parent:\"\";\r\n	margin:0cm;\r\n	margin-bottom:.0001pt;\r\n	mso-pagination:widow-orphan;\r\n	font-size:12.0pt;\r\n	font-family:\"Times New Roman\";\r\n	mso-fareast-font-family:\"Times New Roman\";}\r\n@page Section1\r\n	{size:612.0pt 792.0pt;\r\n	margin:70.85pt 3.0cm 70.85pt 3.0cm;\r\n	mso-header-margin:36.0pt;\r\n	mso-footer-margin:36.0pt;\r\n	mso-paper-source:0;}\r\ndiv.Section1\r\n	{page:Section1;}\r\n-->\r\n</style><!--[if gte mso 10]>\r\n<style>\r\n /* Style Definitions */\r\n table.MsoNormalTable\r\n	{mso-style-name:\"Tabla normal\";\r\n	mso-tstyle-rowband-size:0;\r\n	mso-tstyle-colband-size:0;\r\n	mso-style-noshow:yes;\r\n	mso-style-parent:\"\";\r\n	mso-padding-alt:0cm 5.4pt 0cm 5.4pt;\r\n	mso-para-margin:0cm;\r\n	mso-para-margin-bottom:.0001pt;\r\n	mso-pagination:widow-orphan;\r\n	font-size:10.0pt;\r\n	font-family:\"Times New Roman\";\r\n	mso-ansi-language:#0400;\r\n	mso-fareast-language:#0400;\r\n	mso-bidi-language:#0400;}\r\n</style>\r\n<![endif]-->\r\n\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><span style=\"font-size: 8.5pt; font-family: Verdana;\" lang=\"EN-US\">Overall our trip went very well. The sights of <st1:country-region w:st=\"on\">Peru</st1:country-region> are truly impressive and <st1:country-region w:st=\"on\"><st1:place w:st=\"on\">Peru</st1:place></st1:country-region> for Less\r\nwas an excellent vehicle for seeing them.<o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><span style=\"font-size: 8.5pt; font-family: Verdana;\" lang=\"EN-US\"><o:p>&nbsp;</o:p></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><span style=\"font-size: 8.5pt; font-family: Verdana;\" lang=\"EN-US\">The hotels, lunch stops and logistics were all very\r\ngood. Some of the guides were outstanding - Fabricio in <st1:city w:st=\"on\">Machu\r\n Picchu</st1:city>, Juan Carlos in <st1:city w:st=\"on\"><st1:place w:st=\"on\">Cuzco</st1:place></st1:city>,\r\nAngel in Puno and Guillermo in Arequipa/Colca Canyon. They all seemed to have a\r\nreal engagement with their country especially with the native peoples.<o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><span style=\"font-size: 8.5pt; font-family: Verdana;\" lang=\"EN-US\"><o:p>&nbsp;</o:p></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><span style=\"font-size: 8.5pt; font-family: Verdana;\" lang=\"EN-US\">We were a bit worried that we had factored too many\r\nlong-distance bus trips into our planning, but the buses were safe and\r\ncomfortable (especially Cruz del Sur) and if you have the time it is worth the\r\neffort to see <st1:placename w:st=\"on\">Colca</st1:placename> <st1:placetype w:st=\"on\">Canyon</st1:placetype> and <st1:place w:st=\"on\">Lake Titicaca</st1:place><o:p></o:p></span></p><i style=\"\"><span style=\"font-size: 8.5pt; font-family: Verdana;\" lang=\"EN-US\"><st1:city w:st=\"on\"><st1:place w:st=\"on\"></st1:place></st1:city></span></i><i style=\"\"><span style=\"font-size: 8.5pt; font-family: Verdana;\"><o:p></o:p></span></i>\r\n\r\n                ','<meta http-equiv=\"Content-Type\" content=\"text/html; charset=utf-8\"><meta name=\"ProgId\" content=\"Word.Document\"><meta name=\"Generator\" content=\"Microsoft Word 11\"><meta name=\"Originator\" content=\"Micro','','','',168,0,0,NULL,NULL,NULL),(393,1,'Dear Peru For Less','<meta http-equiv=\"Content-Type\" content=\"text/html; charset=utf-8\"><meta name=\"ProgId\" content=\"Word.Document\"><meta name=\"Generator\" content=\"Microsoft Word 11\"><meta name=\"Originator\" content=\"Microsoft Word 11\"><link rel=\"File-List\" href=\"file:///C:%5CDOCUME%7E1%5CADMINI%7E1%5CCONFIG%7E1%5CTemp%5Cmsohtml1%5C13%5Cclip_filelist.xml\"><o:smarttagtype namespaceuri=\"urn:schemas-microsoft-com:office:smarttags\" name=\"country-region\" downloadurl=\"http://www.5iantlavalamp.com/\"></o:smarttagtype><o:smarttagtype namespaceuri=\"urn:schemas-microsoft-com:office:smarttags\" name=\"place\" downloadurl=\"http://www.5iantlavalamp.com/\"></o:smarttagtype><!--[if gte mso 9]><xml>\r\n <w:WordDocument>\r\n  <w:View>Normal</w:View>\r\n  <w:Zoom>0</w:Zoom>\r\n  <w:HyphenationZone>21</w:HyphenationZone>\r\n  <w:PunctuationKerning/>\r\n  <w:ValidateAgainstSchemas/>\r\n  <w:SaveIfXMLInvalid>false</w:SaveIfXMLInvalid>\r\n  <w:IgnoreMixedContent>false</w:IgnoreMixedContent>\r\n  <w:AlwaysShowPlaceholderText>false</w:AlwaysShowPlaceholderText>\r\n  <w:Compatibility>\r\n   <w:BreakWrappedTables/>\r\n   <w:SnapToGridInCell/>\r\n   <w:WrapTextWithPunct/>\r\n   <w:UseAsianBreakRules/>\r\n   <w:DontGrowAutofit/>\r\n  </w:Compatibility>\r\n  <w:BrowserLevel>MicrosoftInternetExplorer4</w:BrowserLevel>\r\n </w:WordDocument>\r\n</xml><![endif]--><!--[if gte mso 9]><xml>\r\n <w:LatentStyles DefLockedState=\"false\" LatentStyleCount=\"156\">\r\n </w:LatentStyles>\r\n</xml><![endif]--><!--[if !mso]><object\r\n classid=\"clsid:38481807-CA0E-42D2-BF39-B33AF135CC4D\" id=ieooui></object>\r\n<style>\r\nst1\\:*{behavior:url(#ieooui) }\r\n</style>\r\n<![endif]--><style>\r\n<!--\r\n /* Font Definitions */\r\n @font-face\r\n	{font-family:Verdana;\r\n	panose-1:2 11 6 4 3 5 4 4 2 4;\r\n	mso-font-charset:0;\r\n	mso-generic-font-family:swiss;\r\n	mso-font-pitch:variable;\r\n	mso-font-signature:536871559 0 0 0 415 0;}\r\n /* Style Definitions */\r\n p.MsoNormal, li.MsoNormal, div.MsoNormal\r\n	{mso-style-parent:\"\";\r\n	margin:0cm;\r\n	margin-bottom:.0001pt;\r\n	mso-pagination:widow-orphan;\r\n	font-size:12.0pt;\r\n	font-family:\"Times New Roman\";\r\n	mso-fareast-font-family:\"Times New Roman\";}\r\n@page Section1\r\n	{size:612.0pt 792.0pt;\r\n	margin:70.85pt 3.0cm 70.85pt 3.0cm;\r\n	mso-header-margin:36.0pt;\r\n	mso-footer-margin:36.0pt;\r\n	mso-paper-source:0;}\r\ndiv.Section1\r\n	{page:Section1;}\r\n-->\r\n</style><!--[if gte mso 10]>\r\n<style>\r\n /* Style Definitions */\r\n table.MsoNormalTable\r\n	{mso-style-name:\"Tabla normal\";\r\n	mso-tstyle-rowband-size:0;\r\n	mso-tstyle-colband-size:0;\r\n	mso-style-noshow:yes;\r\n	mso-style-parent:\"\";\r\n	mso-padding-alt:0cm 5.4pt 0cm 5.4pt;\r\n	mso-para-margin:0cm;\r\n	mso-para-margin-bottom:.0001pt;\r\n	mso-pagination:widow-orphan;\r\n	font-size:10.0pt;\r\n	font-family:\"Times New Roman\";\r\n	mso-ansi-language:#0400;\r\n	mso-fareast-language:#0400;\r\n	mso-bidi-language:#0400;}\r\n</style>\r\n<![endif]-->\r\n\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><span style=\"font-size: 8.5pt; font-family: Verdana;\" lang=\"EN-GB\">During our&nbsp;trip which we were able do and see\r\neverything we had planned for and then some. <o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><span style=\"font-size: 8.5pt; font-family: Verdana;\" lang=\"EN-GB\">All of our private pick ups were on time and all\r\ncommendations were taken care of when we got to the hotel. In fact, all of the\r\nguides asked us what type of food we were into and took us to some of the best\r\nauthentic Peruvian food. <br>\r\n<br>\r\nAlso, every guide was very knowledgeable with <st1:country-region w:st=\"on\"><st1:place w:st=\"on\">Peru</st1:place></st1:country-region>\'s history and culture, which\r\nlet us learn about things that even Lonely Planet failed to cover. The guides\r\nwere also extremely flexible, when my wife and I had a little hard time\r\nadjusting to the high altitude and also the food, they <o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><span style=\"font-size: 8.5pt; font-family: Verdana;\" lang=\"EN-GB\">took us to the local shop for medicine and of course\r\ncoca tea. Giving us time to rest, they dropped us off where our tour had left\r\noff.<o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><span style=\"font-size: 8.5pt; font-family: Verdana;\" lang=\"EN-GB\">&nbsp;<o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><span style=\"font-size: 8.5pt; font-family: Verdana;\" lang=\"EN-GB\">All in all, <st1:country-region w:st=\"on\"><st1:place w:st=\"on\">Peru</st1:place></st1:country-region> for less and their staff did\r\neverything they could to make our trip a memorable one. We will definitely use\r\nyou again when you plan our return trip and will recommend you to all of our\r\nfamily and friends.<o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n\r\n                ','<meta http-equiv=\"Content-Type\" content=\"text/html; charset=utf-8\"><meta name=\"ProgId\" content=\"Word.Document\"><meta name=\"Generator\" content=\"Microsoft Word 11\"><meta name=\"Originator\" content=\"Micro','','','',166,0,0,NULL,NULL,NULL),(394,1,'Hi Deanna,','<meta http-equiv=\"Content-Type\" content=\"text/html; charset=utf-8\"><meta name=\"ProgId\" content=\"Word.Document\"><meta name=\"Generator\" content=\"Microsoft Word 11\"><meta name=\"Originator\" content=\"Microsoft Word 11\"><link rel=\"File-List\" href=\"file:///C:%5CDOCUME%7E1%5CADMINI%7E1%5CCONFIG%7E1%5CTemp%5Cmsohtml1%5C16%5Cclip_filelist.xml\"><o:smarttagtype namespaceuri=\"urn:schemas-microsoft-com:office:smarttags\" name=\"place\" downloadurl=\"http://www.5iantlavalamp.com/\"></o:smarttagtype><o:smarttagtype namespaceuri=\"urn:schemas-microsoft-com:office:smarttags\" name=\"City\" downloadurl=\"http://www.5iamas-microsoft-com:office:smarttags\"></o:smarttagtype><!--[if gte mso 9]><xml>\r\n <w:WordDocument>\r\n  <w:View>Normal</w:View>\r\n  <w:Zoom>0</w:Zoom>\r\n  <w:HyphenationZone>21</w:HyphenationZone>\r\n  <w:PunctuationKerning/>\r\n  <w:ValidateAgainstSchemas/>\r\n  <w:SaveIfXMLInvalid>false</w:SaveIfXMLInvalid>\r\n  <w:IgnoreMixedContent>false</w:IgnoreMixedContent>\r\n  <w:AlwaysShowPlaceholderText>false</w:AlwaysShowPlaceholderText>\r\n  <w:Compatibility>\r\n   <w:BreakWrappedTables/>\r\n   <w:SnapToGridInCell/>\r\n   <w:WrapTextWithPunct/>\r\n   <w:UseAsianBreakRules/>\r\n   <w:DontGrowAutofit/>\r\n  </w:Compatibility>\r\n  <w:BrowserLevel>MicrosoftInternetExplorer4</w:BrowserLevel>\r\n </w:WordDocument>\r\n</xml><![endif]--><!--[if gte mso 9]><xml>\r\n <w:LatentStyles DefLockedState=\"false\" LatentStyleCount=\"156\">\r\n </w:LatentStyles>\r\n</xml><![endif]--><!--[if !mso]><object\r\n classid=\"clsid:38481807-CA0E-42D2-BF39-B33AF135CC4D\" id=ieooui></object>\r\n<style>\r\nst1\\:*{behavior:url(#ieooui) }\r\n</style>\r\n<![endif]--><style>\r\n<!--\r\n /* Font Definitions */\r\n @font-face\r\n	{font-family:Verdana;\r\n	panose-1:2 11 6 4 3 5 4 4 2 4;\r\n	mso-font-charset:0;\r\n	mso-generic-font-family:swiss;\r\n	mso-font-pitch:variable;\r\n	mso-font-signature:536871559 0 0 0 415 0;}\r\n /* Style Definitions */\r\n p.MsoNormal, li.MsoNormal, div.MsoNormal\r\n	{mso-style-parent:\"\";\r\n	margin:0cm;\r\n	margin-bottom:.0001pt;\r\n	mso-pagination:widow-orphan;\r\n	font-size:12.0pt;\r\n	font-family:\"Times New Roman\";\r\n	mso-fareast-font-family:\"Times New Roman\";}\r\n@page Section1\r\n	{size:612.0pt 792.0pt;\r\n	margin:70.85pt 3.0cm 70.85pt 3.0cm;\r\n	mso-header-margin:36.0pt;\r\n	mso-footer-margin:36.0pt;\r\n	mso-paper-source:0;}\r\ndiv.Section1\r\n	{page:Section1;}\r\n-->\r\n</style><!--[if gte mso 10]>\r\n<style>\r\n /* Style Definitions */\r\n table.MsoNormalTable\r\n	{mso-style-name:\"Tabla normal\";\r\n	mso-tstyle-rowband-size:0;\r\n	mso-tstyle-colband-size:0;\r\n	mso-style-noshow:yes;\r\n	mso-style-parent:\"\";\r\n	mso-padding-alt:0cm 5.4pt 0cm 5.4pt;\r\n	mso-para-margin:0cm;\r\n	mso-para-margin-bottom:.0001pt;\r\n	mso-pagination:widow-orphan;\r\n	font-size:10.0pt;\r\n	font-family:\"Times New Roman\";\r\n	mso-ansi-language:#0400;\r\n	mso-fareast-language:#0400;\r\n	mso-bidi-language:#0400;}\r\n</style>\r\n<![endif]--><span style=\"font-size: 8.5pt; font-family: Verdana;\" lang=\"EN-GB\">My\r\ntrip was wonderful, thank you for asking.<br>\r\n&nbsp;<br>\r\nI want to thank you for all your help with the adjustments and changes on our\r\nitinerary.&nbsp; You were a huge help, and&nbsp;my boyfriend and\r\nI&nbsp;thoroughly enjoyed the <st1:city w:st=\"on\">Cuzco</st1:city> and <st1:city w:st=\"on\"><st1:place w:st=\"on\">Machu Picchu</st1:place></st1:city> tours.&nbsp;\r\nOur tour guides were knowledgeable and answered our questions to the best of\r\ntheir abilities.&nbsp;The drivers and tour guides were all pleasant and very\r\ngracious when we gave them tips.<br>\r\n&nbsp;<br>\r\nThe hotel accommodation was terrific.&nbsp;&nbsp;The photos of San Blas canâ??t\r\nbegin to capture the beauty&nbsp;of the place.&nbsp; The photos do not&nbsp;do\r\nthe place justice at all.&nbsp; &nbsp;<br>\r\n&nbsp;<br>\r\nThank you for everything Deanna!&nbsp; Your work and patience with our changing\r\nitinerary is greatly appreciated.<br style=\"\">\r\n<!--[if !supportLineBreakNewLine]--><br style=\"\">\r\n<!--[endif]--></span>                ','<meta http-equiv=\"Content-Type\" content=\"text/html; charset=utf-8\"><meta name=\"ProgId\" content=\"Word.Document\"><meta name=\"Generator\" content=\"Microsoft Word 11\"><meta name=\"Originator\" content=\"Micro','','','',164,0,0,NULL,NULL,NULL),(395,1,'Rylee,','<meta http-equiv=\"Content-Type\" content=\"text/html; charset=utf-8\"><meta name=\"ProgId\" content=\"Word.Document\"><meta name=\"Generator\" content=\"Microsoft Word 11\"><meta name=\"Originator\" content=\"Microsoft Word 11\"><link rel=\"File-List\" href=\"file:///C:%5CDOCUME%7E1%5CADMINI%7E1%5CCONFIG%7E1%5CTemp%5Cmsohtml1%5C19%5Cclip_filelist.xml\"><o:smarttagtype namespaceuri=\"urn:schemas-microsoft-com:office:smarttags\" name=\"place\" downloadurl=\"http://www.5iantlavalamp.com/\"></o:smarttagtype><o:smarttagtype namespaceuri=\"urn:schemas-microsoft-com:office:smarttags\" name=\"City\" downloadurl=\"http://www.5iamas-microsoft-com:office:smarttags\"></o:smarttagtype><!--[if gte mso 9]><xml>\r\n <w:WordDocument>\r\n  <w:View>Normal</w:View>\r\n  <w:Zoom>0</w:Zoom>\r\n  <w:HyphenationZone>21</w:HyphenationZone>\r\n  <w:PunctuationKerning/>\r\n  <w:ValidateAgainstSchemas/>\r\n  <w:SaveIfXMLInvalid>false</w:SaveIfXMLInvalid>\r\n  <w:IgnoreMixedContent>false</w:IgnoreMixedContent>\r\n  <w:AlwaysShowPlaceholderText>false</w:AlwaysShowPlaceholderText>\r\n  <w:Compatibility>\r\n   <w:BreakWrappedTables/>\r\n   <w:SnapToGridInCell/>\r\n   <w:WrapTextWithPunct/>\r\n   <w:UseAsianBreakRules/>\r\n   <w:DontGrowAutofit/>\r\n  </w:Compatibility>\r\n  <w:BrowserLevel>MicrosoftInternetExplorer4</w:BrowserLevel>\r\n </w:WordDocument>\r\n</xml><![endif]--><!--[if gte mso 9]><xml>\r\n <w:LatentStyles DefLockedState=\"false\" LatentStyleCount=\"156\">\r\n </w:LatentStyles>\r\n</xml><![endif]--><!--[if !mso]><object\r\n classid=\"clsid:38481807-CA0E-42D2-BF39-B33AF135CC4D\" id=ieooui></object>\r\n<style>\r\nst1\\:*{behavior:url(#ieooui) }\r\n</style>\r\n<![endif]--><style>\r\n<!--\r\n /* Font Definitions */\r\n @font-face\r\n	{font-family:Verdana;\r\n	panose-1:2 11 6 4 3 5 4 4 2 4;\r\n	mso-font-charset:0;\r\n	mso-generic-font-family:swiss;\r\n	mso-font-pitch:variable;\r\n	mso-font-signature:536871559 0 0 0 415 0;}\r\n /* Style Definitions */\r\n p.MsoNormal, li.MsoNormal, div.MsoNormal\r\n	{mso-style-parent:\"\";\r\n	margin:0cm;\r\n	margin-bottom:.0001pt;\r\n	mso-pagination:widow-orphan;\r\n	font-size:12.0pt;\r\n	font-family:\"Times New Roman\";\r\n	mso-fareast-font-family:\"Times New Roman\";}\r\n@page Section1\r\n	{size:612.0pt 792.0pt;\r\n	margin:70.85pt 3.0cm 70.85pt 3.0cm;\r\n	mso-header-margin:36.0pt;\r\n	mso-footer-margin:36.0pt;\r\n	mso-paper-source:0;}\r\ndiv.Section1\r\n	{page:Section1;}\r\n-->\r\n</style><!--[if gte mso 10]>\r\n<style>\r\n /* Style Definitions */\r\n table.MsoNormalTable\r\n	{mso-style-name:\"Tabla normal\";\r\n	mso-tstyle-rowband-size:0;\r\n	mso-tstyle-colband-size:0;\r\n	mso-style-noshow:yes;\r\n	mso-style-parent:\"\";\r\n	mso-padding-alt:0cm 5.4pt 0cm 5.4pt;\r\n	mso-para-margin:0cm;\r\n	mso-para-margin-bottom:.0001pt;\r\n	mso-pagination:widow-orphan;\r\n	font-size:10.0pt;\r\n	font-family:\"Times New Roman\";\r\n	mso-ansi-language:#0400;\r\n	mso-fareast-language:#0400;\r\n	mso-bidi-language:#0400;}\r\n</style>\r\n<![endif]-->\r\n\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><span style=\"font-size: 8.5pt; font-family: Verdana;\" lang=\"EN-GB\">This trip was great; everything was perfect.<o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><span style=\"font-size: 8.5pt; font-family: Verdana;\" lang=\"EN-GB\">When my son and I arrived to <st1:city w:st=\"on\">Cuzco</st1:city>,\r\n<st1:city w:st=\"on\"><st1:place w:st=\"on\">Tracy</st1:place></st1:city> was\r\nwaiting for us at the airport:&nbsp;she was great.<o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><span style=\"font-size: 8.5pt; font-family: Verdana;\" lang=\"EN-GB\">Maria was&nbsp;our&nbsp;tour guide in <st1:city w:st=\"on\"><st1:place w:st=\"on\">Cuzco</st1:place></st1:city> this is the first time that I have had\r\na guide that knows so much about history, explaining everything in detail.<o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><span style=\"font-size: 8.5pt; font-family: Verdana;\" lang=\"EN-GB\">In Machu Pichu we had Fabrisio he was very good. Casa\r\nAndina in <st1:city w:st=\"on\"><st1:place w:st=\"on\">Machu Picchu</st1:place></st1:city>\r\nis a great place to stay: clean, friendly staff and very comfortable. Although\r\nthe railroad is close to the hotel and you hear the trains, they stop by 9:00\r\npm and start again at 8:00 am, and&nbsp;breakfast was amazing: very good food,\r\nfresh juice and fruit.<o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><span style=\"font-size: 8.5pt; font-family: Verdana;\" lang=\"EN-GB\"><br>\r\nTo all our tour guides - keep up the good work you were wonderful, and Rylee\r\nthank you for scheduling a trip of a lifetime.<o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n\r\n                ','<meta http-equiv=\"Content-Type\" content=\"text/html; charset=utf-8\"><meta name=\"ProgId\" content=\"Word.Document\"><meta name=\"Generator\" content=\"Microsoft Word 11\"><meta name=\"Originator\" content=\"Micro','','','',162,0,0,NULL,NULL,NULL),(396,1,'Hello,','<p>Our&nbsp;trip was incredible! We had such a great time\nand we wanted to thank you Rylee for helping us out with everything. Just to\npoint out some specific people who made this a reality: the kind hearts of you\n(Rylee), Tracy (the young lady who picked us up from the airport), and Fabricio\n(<st1:city w:st=\"on\"><st1:place w:st=\"on\">Machu Picchu</st1:place></st1:city>\nguide). He was so informative I felt like we left with more information that\nanyone. I don\'t have pictures yet but I will send you one when I get one.<o:p></o:p></span></p>\n\n\n<p >In general PFL is a very informative group of people. You\nare reliable in every way and let our dream vacation be stress-free. I felt\nlike we were celebrities the way we were treated with Peru For Less. I came\nabout Peru For Less because another tour company that we were going to use for\nour Machu Picchu\ntrip seemed a bit sketchy, so then I read the testimonials and went with Peru\nFor Less. They are a great company to work with and there are NO unpleasant\nsurprises. Everything that we experienced was breath-taking and as promised.\nAmazing company and I will use Peru For Less again!!!!!!<o:p></o:p></span></p>\n\n\n                ','<meta http-equiv=\"Content-Type\" content=\"text/html; charset=utf-8\"><meta name=\"ProgId\" content=\"Word.Document\"><meta name=\"Generator\" content=\"Microsoft Word 11\"><meta name=\"Originator\" content=\"Micro','','','',160,0,0,NULL,NULL,NULL),(397,1,'Dear Rylee, ','\r\n<p>We had a fantastic time and the whole experience was\r\ntruly amazing. The restaurant in Cuzco\r\nwent well, the dinner was nice and the folk show was really good. Overall we\r\nhad a good time there. </p>\r\n\r\n<p>As for the Galapagos, of course it was wonderful. We\r\nwere really very lucky to have been assigned the best&nbsp;naturalist on board Santa Cruz Marieux,\r\nshe was extremely&nbsp;knowledgeable and very thorough in her knowledge and\r\nexplanations and answers to our questions. We had a great time.</p>\r\n\r\n\r\n<p>Thank you very much for your professional, prompt and\r\nefficient assistance in arranging our trip. </p>\r\n\r\n                ','<meta http-equiv=\"Content-Type\" content=\"text/html; charset=utf-8\"><meta name=\"ProgId\" content=\"Word.Document\"><meta name=\"Generator\" content=\"Microsoft Word 11\"><meta name=\"Originator\" content=\"Micro','','','',158,0,0,NULL,NULL,NULL),(398,1,'Dear Peru For Less','<meta http-equiv=\"Content-Type\" content=\"text/html; charset=utf-8\"><meta name=\"ProgId\" content=\"Word.Document\"><meta name=\"Generator\" content=\"Microsoft Word 11\"><meta name=\"Originator\" content=\"Microsoft Word 11\"><link rel=\"File-List\" href=\"file:///C:%5CDOCUME%7E1%5CADMINI%7E1%5CCONFIG%7E1%5CTemp%5Cmsohtml1%5C03%5Cclip_filelist.xml\"><!--[if gte mso 9]><xml>\r\n <w:WordDocument>\r\n  <w:View>Normal</w:View>\r\n  <w:Zoom>0</w:Zoom>\r\n  <w:HyphenationZone>21</w:HyphenationZone>\r\n  <w:PunctuationKerning/>\r\n  <w:ValidateAgainstSchemas/>\r\n  <w:SaveIfXMLInvalid>false</w:SaveIfXMLInvalid>\r\n  <w:IgnoreMixedContent>false</w:IgnoreMixedContent>\r\n  <w:AlwaysShowPlaceholderText>false</w:AlwaysShowPlaceholderText>\r\n  <w:Compatibility>\r\n   <w:BreakWrappedTables/>\r\n   <w:SnapToGridInCell/>\r\n   <w:WrapTextWithPunct/>\r\n   <w:UseAsianBreakRules/>\r\n   <w:DontGrowAutofit/>\r\n  </w:Compatibility>\r\n  <w:BrowserLevel>MicrosoftInternetExplorer4</w:BrowserLevel>\r\n </w:WordDocument>\r\n</xml><![endif]--><!--[if gte mso 9]><xml>\r\n <w:LatentStyles DefLockedState=\"false\" LatentStyleCount=\"156\">\r\n </w:LatentStyles>\r\n</xml><![endif]--><style>\r\n<!--\r\n /* Font Definitions */\r\n @font-face\r\n	{font-family:Verdana;\r\n	panose-1:2 11 6 4 3 5 4 4 2 4;\r\n	mso-font-charset:0;\r\n	mso-generic-font-family:swiss;\r\n	mso-font-pitch:variable;\r\n	mso-font-signature:536871559 0 0 0 415 0;}\r\n /* Style Definitions */\r\n p.MsoNormal, li.MsoNormal, div.MsoNormal\r\n	{mso-style-parent:\"\";\r\n	margin:0cm;\r\n	margin-bottom:.0001pt;\r\n	mso-pagination:widow-orphan;\r\n	font-size:12.0pt;\r\n	font-family:\"Times New Roman\";\r\n	mso-fareast-font-family:\"Times New Roman\";}\r\n@page Section1\r\n	{size:612.0pt 792.0pt;\r\n	margin:70.85pt 3.0cm 70.85pt 3.0cm;\r\n	mso-header-margin:36.0pt;\r\n	mso-footer-margin:36.0pt;\r\n	mso-paper-source:0;}\r\ndiv.Section1\r\n	{page:Section1;}\r\n-->\r\n</style><!--[if gte mso 10]>\r\n<style>\r\n /* Style Definitions */\r\n table.MsoNormalTable\r\n	{mso-style-name:\"Tabla normal\";\r\n	mso-tstyle-rowband-size:0;\r\n	mso-tstyle-colband-size:0;\r\n	mso-style-noshow:yes;\r\n	mso-style-parent:\"\";\r\n	mso-padding-alt:0cm 5.4pt 0cm 5.4pt;\r\n	mso-para-margin:0cm;\r\n	mso-para-margin-bottom:.0001pt;\r\n	mso-pagination:widow-orphan;\r\n	font-size:10.0pt;\r\n	font-family:\"Times New Roman\";\r\n	mso-ansi-language:#0400;\r\n	mso-fareast-language:#0400;\r\n	mso-bidi-language:#0400;}\r\n</style>\r\n<![endif]-->\r\n\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><span style=\"font-size: 8.5pt; font-family: Verdana;\" lang=\"EN-GB\">Just wanted to let you know we just returned from our\r\nGalapagos vacation, and we had a wonderful time. The accommodations were fine,\r\nthe tours were great, the guides wonderful. All connections were flawless, as\r\nusual.<o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><span style=\"font-size: 8.5pt; font-family: Verdana;\" lang=\"EN-GB\">&nbsp;&nbsp;<o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><span style=\"font-size: 8.5pt; font-family: Verdana;\" lang=\"EN-GB\">We have recommended your services to many people\r\nbecause we have been so happy with our experiences two years in a row now. <o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n\r\n                ','<meta http-equiv=\"Content-Type\" content=\"text/html; charset=utf-8\"><meta name=\"ProgId\" content=\"Word.Document\"><meta name=\"Generator\" content=\"Microsoft Word 11\"><meta name=\"Originator\" content=\"Micro','','','',155,0,0,NULL,NULL,NULL),(399,1,'Dear Peru For Less','<meta http-equiv=\"Content-Type\" content=\"text/html; charset=utf-8\"><meta name=\"ProgId\" content=\"Word.Document\"><meta name=\"Generator\" content=\"Microsoft Word 11\"><meta name=\"Originator\" content=\"Microsoft Word 11\"><link rel=\"File-List\" href=\"file:///C:%5CDOCUME%7E1%5CADMINI%7E1%5CCONFIG%7E1%5CTemp%5Cmsohtml1%5C06%5Cclip_filelist.xml\"><o:smarttagtype namespaceuri=\"urn:schemas-microsoft-com:office:smarttags\" name=\"country-region\" downloadurl=\"http://www.5iantlavalamp.com/\"></o:smarttagtype><o:smarttagtype namespaceuri=\"urn:schemas-microsoft-com:office:smarttags\" name=\"place\" downloadurl=\"http://www.5iantlavalamp.com/\"></o:smarttagtype><!--[if gte mso 9]><xml>\r\n <w:WordDocument>\r\n  <w:View>Normal</w:View>\r\n  <w:Zoom>0</w:Zoom>\r\n  <w:HyphenationZone>21</w:HyphenationZone>\r\n  <w:PunctuationKerning/>\r\n  <w:ValidateAgainstSchemas/>\r\n  <w:SaveIfXMLInvalid>false</w:SaveIfXMLInvalid>\r\n  <w:IgnoreMixedContent>false</w:IgnoreMixedContent>\r\n  <w:AlwaysShowPlaceholderText>false</w:AlwaysShowPlaceholderText>\r\n  <w:Compatibility>\r\n   <w:BreakWrappedTables/>\r\n   <w:SnapToGridInCell/>\r\n   <w:WrapTextWithPunct/>\r\n   <w:UseAsianBreakRules/>\r\n   <w:DontGrowAutofit/>\r\n  </w:Compatibility>\r\n  <w:BrowserLevel>MicrosoftInternetExplorer4</w:BrowserLevel>\r\n </w:WordDocument>\r\n</xml><![endif]--><!--[if gte mso 9]><xml>\r\n <w:LatentStyles DefLockedState=\"false\" LatentStyleCount=\"156\">\r\n </w:LatentStyles>\r\n</xml><![endif]--><!--[if !mso]><object\r\n classid=\"clsid:38481807-CA0E-42D2-BF39-B33AF135CC4D\" id=ieooui></object>\r\n<style>\r\nst1\\:*{behavior:url(#ieooui) }\r\n</style>\r\n<![endif]--><style>\r\n<!--\r\n /* Font Definitions */\r\n @font-face\r\n	{font-family:Verdana;\r\n	panose-1:2 11 6 4 3 5 4 4 2 4;\r\n	mso-font-charset:0;\r\n	mso-generic-font-family:swiss;\r\n	mso-font-pitch:variable;\r\n	mso-font-signature:536871559 0 0 0 415 0;}\r\n /* Style Definitions */\r\n p.MsoNormal, li.MsoNormal, div.MsoNormal\r\n	{mso-style-parent:\"\";\r\n	margin:0cm;\r\n	margin-bottom:.0001pt;\r\n	mso-pagination:widow-orphan;\r\n	font-size:12.0pt;\r\n	font-family:\"Times New Roman\";\r\n	mso-fareast-font-family:\"Times New Roman\";}\r\n@page Section1\r\n	{size:612.0pt 792.0pt;\r\n	margin:70.85pt 3.0cm 70.85pt 3.0cm;\r\n	mso-header-margin:36.0pt;\r\n	mso-footer-margin:36.0pt;\r\n	mso-paper-source:0;}\r\ndiv.Section1\r\n	{page:Section1;}\r\n-->\r\n</style><!--[if gte mso 10]>\r\n<style>\r\n /* Style Definitions */\r\n table.MsoNormalTable\r\n	{mso-style-name:\"Tabla normal\";\r\n	mso-tstyle-rowband-size:0;\r\n	mso-tstyle-colband-size:0;\r\n	mso-style-noshow:yes;\r\n	mso-style-parent:\"\";\r\n	mso-padding-alt:0cm 5.4pt 0cm 5.4pt;\r\n	mso-para-margin:0cm;\r\n	mso-para-margin-bottom:.0001pt;\r\n	mso-pagination:widow-orphan;\r\n	font-size:10.0pt;\r\n	font-family:\"Times New Roman\";\r\n	mso-ansi-language:#0400;\r\n	mso-fareast-language:#0400;\r\n	mso-bidi-language:#0400;}\r\n</style>\r\n<![endif]--><span style=\"font-size: 8.5pt; font-family: Verdana;\" lang=\"EN-GB\">Yes,\r\nIâ??m still in <st1:place w:st=\"on\"><st1:country-region w:st=\"on\">Peru</st1:country-region></st1:place>!\r\nActually at the moment waiting for my bus from Puno to Cuzco, I went to Lake\r\nTiticaca for the weekend =)<br>\r\n<br>\r\nI feel that you did an awesome job, you definitely made everything easy and I\r\nfelt my planning for the trip was pretty smooth sailing. The Inca Trail trek\r\nwas amazing and our guides were the best. They were very helpful and patient,\r\nas well as knowledgeable yet entertaining, we made a great bond with those two.\r\nSo, thank you for all your help and thank you for a wonderful first impression\r\nof <st1:country-region w:st=\"on\"><st1:place w:st=\"on\">Peru</st1:place></st1:country-region>.\r\n<br style=\"\">\r\n<!--[if !supportLineBreakNewLine]--><br style=\"\">\r\n<!--[endif]--></span>                ','<meta http-equiv=\"Content-Type\" content=\"text/html; charset=utf-8\"><meta name=\"ProgId\" content=\"Word.Document\"><meta name=\"Generator\" content=\"Microsoft Word 11\"><meta name=\"Originator\" content=\"Micro','','','',153,0,0,NULL,NULL,NULL),(400,1,'Hi Rylee,','<meta http-equiv=\"Content-Type\" content=\"text/html; charset=utf-8\"><meta name=\"ProgId\" content=\"Word.Document\"><meta name=\"Generator\" content=\"Microsoft Word 11\"><meta name=\"Originator\" content=\"Microsoft Word 11\"><link rel=\"File-List\" href=\"file:///C:%5CDOCUME%7E1%5CADMINI%7E1%5CCONFIG%7E1%5CTemp%5Cmsohtml1%5C09%5Cclip_filelist.xml\"><o:smarttagtype namespaceuri=\"urn:schemas-microsoft-com:office:smarttags\" name=\"place\" downloadurl=\"http://www.5iantlavalamp.com/\"></o:smarttagtype><o:smarttagtype namespaceuri=\"urn:schemas-microsoft-com:office:smarttags\" name=\"City\" downloadurl=\"http://www.5iamas-microsoft-com:office:smarttags\"></o:smarttagtype><!--[if gte mso 9]><xml>\r\n <w:WordDocument>\r\n  <w:View>Normal</w:View>\r\n  <w:Zoom>0</w:Zoom>\r\n  <w:HyphenationZone>21</w:HyphenationZone>\r\n  <w:PunctuationKerning/>\r\n  <w:ValidateAgainstSchemas/>\r\n  <w:SaveIfXMLInvalid>false</w:SaveIfXMLInvalid>\r\n  <w:IgnoreMixedContent>false</w:IgnoreMixedContent>\r\n  <w:AlwaysShowPlaceholderText>false</w:AlwaysShowPlaceholderText>\r\n  <w:Compatibility>\r\n   <w:BreakWrappedTables/>\r\n   <w:SnapToGridInCell/>\r\n   <w:WrapTextWithPunct/>\r\n   <w:UseAsianBreakRules/>\r\n   <w:DontGrowAutofit/>\r\n  </w:Compatibility>\r\n  <w:BrowserLevel>MicrosoftInternetExplorer4</w:BrowserLevel>\r\n </w:WordDocument>\r\n</xml><![endif]--><!--[if gte mso 9]><xml>\r\n <w:LatentStyles DefLockedState=\"false\" LatentStyleCount=\"156\">\r\n </w:LatentStyles>\r\n</xml><![endif]--><!--[if !mso]><object\r\n classid=\"clsid:38481807-CA0E-42D2-BF39-B33AF135CC4D\" id=ieooui></object>\r\n<style>\r\nst1\\:*{behavior:url(#ieooui) }\r\n</style>\r\n<![endif]--><style>\r\n<!--\r\n /* Font Definitions */\r\n @font-face\r\n	{font-family:Verdana;\r\n	panose-1:2 11 6 4 3 5 4 4 2 4;\r\n	mso-font-charset:0;\r\n	mso-generic-font-family:swiss;\r\n	mso-font-pitch:variable;\r\n	mso-font-signature:536871559 0 0 0 415 0;}\r\n /* Style Definitions */\r\n p.MsoNormal, li.MsoNormal, div.MsoNormal\r\n	{mso-style-parent:\"\";\r\n	margin:0cm;\r\n	margin-bottom:.0001pt;\r\n	mso-pagination:widow-orphan;\r\n	font-size:12.0pt;\r\n	font-family:\"Times New Roman\";\r\n	mso-fareast-font-family:\"Times New Roman\";}\r\n@page Section1\r\n	{size:612.0pt 792.0pt;\r\n	margin:70.85pt 3.0cm 70.85pt 3.0cm;\r\n	mso-header-margin:36.0pt;\r\n	mso-footer-margin:36.0pt;\r\n	mso-paper-source:0;}\r\ndiv.Section1\r\n	{page:Section1;}\r\n-->\r\n</style><!--[if gte mso 10]>\r\n<style>\r\n /* Style Definitions */\r\n table.MsoNormalTable\r\n	{mso-style-name:\"Tabla normal\";\r\n	mso-tstyle-rowband-size:0;\r\n	mso-tstyle-colband-size:0;\r\n	mso-style-noshow:yes;\r\n	mso-style-parent:\"\";\r\n	mso-padding-alt:0cm 5.4pt 0cm 5.4pt;\r\n	mso-para-margin:0cm;\r\n	mso-para-margin-bottom:.0001pt;\r\n	mso-pagination:widow-orphan;\r\n	font-size:10.0pt;\r\n	font-family:\"Times New Roman\";\r\n	mso-ansi-language:#0400;\r\n	mso-fareast-language:#0400;\r\n	mso-bidi-language:#0400;}\r\n</style>\r\n<![endif]-->\r\n\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><span style=\"font-size: 8.5pt; font-family: Verdana;\" lang=\"EN-US\">The trip was fantastic.&nbsp; I am completely\r\nsatisfied with everything and you guys came through 100 percent.&nbsp; I have\r\nno complaints and felt like you guys did an awesome job.&nbsp; The free day in <st1:city w:st=\"on\"><st1:place w:st=\"on\">Cuzco</st1:place></st1:city> was filled by going\r\nto the local market and shopping. Thanks for everything, Rylee.</span><span style=\"font-size: 8.5pt; font-family: Verdana;\">&nbsp;&nbsp; <o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n\r\n                ','<meta http-equiv=\"Content-Type\" content=\"text/html; charset=utf-8\"><meta name=\"ProgId\" content=\"Word.Document\"><meta name=\"Generator\" content=\"Microsoft Word 11\"><meta name=\"Originator\" content=\"Micro','','','',151,0,0,NULL,NULL,NULL),(401,1,'Hi, Kristina!','<meta http-equiv=\"Content-Type\" content=\"text/html; charset=utf-8\"><meta name=\"ProgId\" content=\"Word.Document\"><meta name=\"Generator\" content=\"Microsoft Word 11\"><meta name=\"Originator\" content=\"Microsoft Word 11\"><link rel=\"File-List\" href=\"file:///C:%5CDOCUME%7E1%5CADMINI%7E1%5CCONFIG%7E1%5CTemp%5Cmsohtml1%5C12%5Cclip_filelist.xml\"><o:smarttagtype namespaceuri=\"urn:schemas-microsoft-com:office:smarttags\" name=\"place\" downloadurl=\"http://www.5iantlavalamp.com/\"></o:smarttagtype><o:smarttagtype namespaceuri=\"urn:schemas-microsoft-com:office:smarttags\" name=\"PlaceName\" downloadurl=\"http://www.5iantlavalamp.com/\"></o:smarttagtype><o:smarttagtype namespaceuri=\"urn:schemas-