r\n	mso-fareast-language:#0400;\r\n	mso-bidi-language:#0400;}\r\n</style>\r\n<![endif]--><st1:place w:st=\"on\"><st1:city w:st=\"on\"><span style=\"font-size: 8.5pt; font-family: Verdana;\" lang=\"EN-US\">Machu Picchu</span></st1:city></st1:place><span style=\"font-size: 8.5pt; font-family: Verdana;\" lang=\"EN-US\"> was of course awesome\r\nand Fabricio was a great guide with interesting information.</span>                ','<meta http-equiv=\"Content-Type\" content=\"text/html; charset=utf-8\"><meta name=\"ProgId\" content=\"Word.Document\"><meta name=\"Generator\" content=\"Microsoft Word 11\"><meta name=\"Originator\" content=\"Micro','','','',139,0,0,NULL,NULL,NULL),(408,1,'Dear Peru For Less','<meta http-equiv=\"Content-Type\" content=\"text/html; charset=utf-8\"><meta name=\"ProgId\" content=\"Word.Document\"><meta name=\"Generator\" content=\"Microsoft Word 11\"><meta name=\"Originator\" content=\"Microsoft Word 11\"><link rel=\"File-List\" href=\"file:///C:%5CDOCUME%7E1%5CADMINI%7E1%5CCONFIG%7E1%5CTemp%5Cmsohtml1%5C01%5Cclip_filelist.xml\"><o:smarttagtype namespaceuri=\"urn:schemas-microsoft-com:office:smarttags\" name=\"country-region\" downloadurl=\"http://www.5iantlavalamp.com/\"></o:smarttagtype><o:smarttagtype namespaceuri=\"urn:schemas-microsoft-com:office:smarttags\" name=\"place\" downloadurl=\"http://www.5iantlavalamp.com/\"></o:smarttagtype><o:smarttagtype namespaceuri=\"urn:schemas-microsoft-com:office:smarttags\" name=\"City\" downloadurl=\"http://www.5iamas-microsoft-com:office:smarttags\"></o:smarttagtype><!--[if gte mso 9]><xml>\r\n <w:WordDocument>\r\n  <w:View>Normal</w:View>\r\n  <w:Zoom>0</w:Zoom>\r\n  <w:HyphenationZone>21</w:HyphenationZone>\r\n  <w:PunctuationKerning/>\r\n  <w:ValidateAgainstSchemas/>\r\n  <w:SaveIfXMLInvalid>false</w:SaveIfXMLInvalid>\r\n  <w:IgnoreMixedContent>false</w:IgnoreMixedContent>\r\n  <w:AlwaysShowPlaceholderText>false</w:AlwaysShowPlaceholderText>\r\n  <w:Compatibility>\r\n   <w:BreakWrappedTables/>\r\n   <w:SnapToGridInCell/>\r\n   <w:WrapTextWithPunct/>\r\n   <w:UseAsianBreakRules/>\r\n   <w:DontGrowAutofit/>\r\n  </w:Compatibility>\r\n  <w:BrowserLevel>MicrosoftInternetExplorer4</w:BrowserLevel>\r\n </w:WordDocument>\r\n</xml><![endif]--><!--[if gte mso 9]><xml>\r\n <w:LatentStyles DefLockedState=\"false\" LatentStyleCount=\"156\">\r\n </w:LatentStyles>\r\n</xml><![endif]--><!--[if !mso]><object\r\n classid=\"clsid:38481807-CA0E-42D2-BF39-B33AF135CC4D\" id=ieooui></object>\r\n<style>\r\nst1\\:*{behavior:url(#ieooui) }\r\n</style>\r\n<![endif]--><style>\r\n<!--\r\n /* Font Definitions */\r\n @font-face\r\n	{font-family:Verdana;\r\n	panose-1:2 11 6 4 3 5 4 4 2 4;\r\n	mso-font-charset:0;\r\n	mso-generic-font-family:swiss;\r\n	mso-font-pitch:variable;\r\n	mso-font-signature:536871559 0 0 0 415 0;}\r\n /* Style Definitions */\r\n p.MsoNormal, li.MsoNormal, div.MsoNormal\r\n	{mso-style-parent:\"\";\r\n	margin:0cm;\r\n	margin-bottom:.0001pt;\r\n	mso-pagination:widow-orphan;\r\n	font-size:12.0pt;\r\n	font-family:\"Times New Roman\";\r\n	mso-fareast-font-family:\"Times New Roman\";}\r\n@page Section1\r\n	{size:612.0pt 792.0pt;\r\n	margin:70.85pt 3.0cm 70.85pt 3.0cm;\r\n	mso-header-margin:36.0pt;\r\n	mso-footer-margin:36.0pt;\r\n	mso-paper-source:0;}\r\ndiv.Section1\r\n	{page:Section1;}\r\n-->\r\n</style><!--[if gte mso 10]>\r\n<style>\r\n /* Style Definitions */\r\n table.MsoNormalTable\r\n	{mso-style-name:\"Tabla normal\";\r\n	mso-tstyle-rowband-size:0;\r\n	mso-tstyle-colband-size:0;\r\n	mso-style-noshow:yes;\r\n	mso-style-parent:\"\";\r\n	mso-padding-alt:0cm 5.4pt 0cm 5.4pt;\r\n	mso-para-margin:0cm;\r\n	mso-para-margin-bottom:.0001pt;\r\n	mso-pagination:widow-orphan;\r\n	font-size:10.0pt;\r\n	font-family:\"Times New Roman\";\r\n	mso-ansi-language:#0400;\r\n	mso-fareast-language:#0400;\r\n	mso-bidi-language:#0400;}\r\n</style>\r\n<![endif]--><meta http-equiv=\"Content-Type\" content=\"text/html; charset=utf-8\"><meta name=\"ProgId\" content=\"Word.Document\"><meta name=\"Generator\" content=\"Microsoft Word 11\"><meta name=\"Originator\" content=\"Microsoft Word 11\"><link rel=\"File-List\" href=\"file:///C:%5CDOCUME%7E1%5CADMINI%7E1%5CCONFIG%7E1%5CTemp%5Cmsohtml1%5C02%5Cclip_filelist.xml\"><o:smarttagtype namespaceuri=\"urn:schemas-microsoft-com:office:smarttags\" name=\"country-region\" downloadurl=\"http://www.5iantlavalamp.com/\"></o:smarttagtype><o:smarttagtype namespaceuri=\"urn:schemas-microsoft-com:office:smarttags\" name=\"place\" downloadurl=\"http://www.5iantlavalamp.com/\"></o:smarttagtype><o:smarttagtype namespaceuri=\"urn:schemas-microsoft-com:office:smarttags\" name=\"City\" downloadurl=\"http://www.5iamas-microsoft-com:office:smarttags\"></o:smarttagtype><!--[if gte mso 9]><xml>\r\n <w:WordDocument>\r\n  <w:View>Normal</w:View>\r\n  <w:Zoom>0</w:Zoom>\r\n  <w:HyphenationZone>21</w:HyphenationZone>\r\n  <w:PunctuationKerning/>\r\n  <w:ValidateAgainstSchemas/>\r\n  <w:SaveIfXMLInvalid>false</w:SaveIfXMLInvalid>\r\n  <w:IgnoreMixedContent>false</w:IgnoreMixedContent>\r\n  <w:AlwaysShowPlaceholderText>false</w:AlwaysShowPlaceholderText>\r\n  <w:Compatibility>\r\n   <w:BreakWrappedTables/>\r\n   <w:SnapToGridInCell/>\r\n   <w:WrapTextWithPunct/>\r\n   <w:UseAsianBreakRules/>\r\n   <w:DontGrowAutofit/>\r\n  </w:Compatibility>\r\n  <w:BrowserLevel>MicrosoftInternetExplorer4</w:BrowserLevel>\r\n </w:WordDocument>\r\n</xml><![endif]--><!--[if gte mso 9]><xml>\r\n <w:LatentStyles DefLockedState=\"false\" LatentStyleCount=\"156\">\r\n </w:LatentStyles>\r\n</xml><![endif]--><!--[if !mso]><object\r\n classid=\"clsid:38481807-CA0E-42D2-BF39-B33AF135CC4D\" id=ieooui></object>\r\n<style>\r\nst1\\:*{behavior:url(#ieooui) }\r\n</style>\r\n<![endif]--><style>\r\n<!--\r\n /* Font Definitions */\r\n @font-face\r\n	{font-family:Verdana;\r\n	panose-1:2 11 6 4 3 5 4 4 2 4;\r\n	mso-font-charset:0;\r\n	mso-generic-font-family:swiss;\r\n	mso-font-pitch:variable;\r\n	mso-font-signature:536871559 0 0 0 415 0;}\r\n /* Style Definitions */\r\n p.MsoNormal, li.MsoNormal, div.MsoNormal\r\n	{mso-style-parent:\"\";\r\n	margin:0cm;\r\n	margin-bottom:.0001pt;\r\n	mso-pagination:widow-orphan;\r\n	font-size:12.0pt;\r\n	font-family:\"Times New Roman\";\r\n	mso-fareast-font-family:\"Times New Roman\";}\r\n@page Section1\r\n	{size:612.0pt 792.0pt;\r\n	margin:70.85pt 3.0cm 70.85pt 3.0cm;\r\n	mso-header-margin:36.0pt;\r\n	mso-footer-margin:36.0pt;\r\n	mso-paper-source:0;}\r\ndiv.Section1\r\n	{page:Section1;}\r\n-->\r\n</style><!--[if gte mso 10]>\r\n<style>\r\n /* Style Definitions */\r\n table.MsoNormalTable\r\n	{mso-style-name:\"Tabla normal\";\r\n	mso-tstyle-rowband-size:0;\r\n	mso-tstyle-colband-size:0;\r\n	mso-style-noshow:yes;\r\n	mso-style-parent:\"\";\r\n	mso-padding-alt:0cm 5.4pt 0cm 5.4pt;\r\n	mso-para-margin:0cm;\r\n	mso-para-margin-bottom:.0001pt;\r\n	mso-pagination:widow-orphan;\r\n	font-size:10.0pt;\r\n	font-family:\"Times New Roman\";\r\n	mso-ansi-language:#0400;\r\n	mso-fareast-language:#0400;\r\n	mso-bidi-language:#0400;}\r\n</style>\r\n<![endif]-->\r\n\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><span style=\"font-size: 8.5pt; font-family: Verdana;\" lang=\"EN-US\">Overall I had a great time in <st1:country-region w:st=\"on\"><st1:place w:st=\"on\">Peru</st1:place></st1:country-region> both\r\nvisiting with my friends and during my side trip I took with your company. All\r\nof the people affiliated with your company did a fantastic job.&nbsp; The tour\r\nguides were well organized, knowledgeable and spoke English very well. Every\r\nevening there was a message at my hotel confirming my pickup time. I really\r\nliked that. I also appreciated the fact that I had an emergency contact number\r\nin case something happened. I was traveling alone in a strange country and that\r\nwas a great comfort. Not to mention when I left Cuzco, the gal that accompanied\r\nme to the airport walked me to the ticket counter, then proceeded to escort me\r\nto the airport fee counter and then to the security screening area. A very nice\r\ntouch. I felt like a VIP!<o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><span style=\"font-size: 8.5pt; font-family: Verdana;\" lang=\"EN-US\"><o:p>&nbsp;</o:p></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><span style=\"font-size: 8.5pt; font-family: Verdana;\" lang=\"EN-US\">I would like to take this opportunity to point out two\r\nparticular people that I feel stood out.&nbsp; <o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><span style=\"font-size: 8.5pt; font-family: Verdana;\" lang=\"EN-US\"><o:p>&nbsp;</o:p></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><span style=\"font-size: 8.5pt; font-family: Verdana;\" lang=\"EN-US\">The first person is you Chris. You were the first\r\nperson from your agency that I dealt with and you made a great first\r\nimpression. Your knowledge of your product and the fact that we were able to\r\neffectively communicate via email and/or telephone depending on the\r\ncircumstances was important to me. My work schedule can and often changes at a\r\nmoments notice so it is important for people like me to be able to have more\r\nthan one means of communicating. And your knowledge of your company\'s offerings\r\nalso made it easy to deal with you when it came to customizing my trip. <o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><span style=\"font-size: 8.5pt; font-family: Verdana;\" lang=\"EN-US\"><o:p>&nbsp;</o:p></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><span style=\"font-size: 8.5pt; font-family: Verdana;\" lang=\"EN-US\">The second person who really made the trip extra\r\nspecial was Fabricio. <st1:city w:st=\"on\"><st1:place w:st=\"on\">Machu Picchu</st1:place></st1:city>\r\nis a spectacular place all by itself but Fabricio\'s knowledge of the Incas and\r\nthe site in particular enriched the experience all the more.&nbsp; And it was\r\nmore than his knowledge of the site but his enthusiasm and sense of pride that\r\nreally came across. On top of all of that he was very sensitive to the varying\r\nability levels of the group and adjusted his pace accordingly. When it was time\r\nto stop to explain a particular point of interest he made sure that there was\r\nsome shade and whenever possible a place to sit.&nbsp; If your goal is to\r\nexceed your customer\'s expectations you should use him as much as possible for\r\nthe <st1:city w:st=\"on\"><st1:place w:st=\"on\">Machu Picchu</st1:place></st1:city>\r\ntours.&nbsp; And whatever you pay him to conduct those tours, you should double\r\nit. You do not want to lose that guy.<o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><span style=\"font-size: 8.5pt; font-family: Verdana;\" lang=\"EN-US\"><o:p>&nbsp;</o:p></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><span style=\"font-size: 8.5pt; font-family: Verdana;\" lang=\"EN-US\">I was most surprised by <st1:city w:st=\"on\"><st1:place w:st=\"on\">Cuzco</st1:place></st1:city>. I had seen a couple of shows on the\r\nTravel Channel that really only gave it a few minutes and pretty much described\r\nit as a place to stop and adjust to the altitude before continuing on to Machu\r\nPicchu. But it is so much more than that and so much bigger than I expected. I\r\nloved my hotel too.&nbsp; The room was very nice and the location was great. <o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><span style=\"font-size: 8.5pt; font-family: Verdana;\" lang=\"EN-US\"><o:p>&nbsp;</o:p></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><span style=\"font-size: 8.5pt; font-family: Verdana;\" lang=\"EN-US\">My only regret is that I was not aware of how much\r\nhistory is in <st1:place w:st=\"on\"><st1:city w:st=\"on\">Cuzco</st1:city></st1:place>\r\nand not having budgeted enough time to tour more of the sites and museums not\r\nto mention all of the shops and restaurants.<o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><span style=\"font-size: 8.5pt; font-family: Verdana;\" lang=\"EN-US\"><o:p>&nbsp;</o:p></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><span style=\"font-size: 8.5pt; font-family: Verdana;\" lang=\"EN-US\">The time differences really did not have a negative\r\nimpact on the trip, in fact just the opposite. I can appreciate how difficult\r\nit must be to orchestrate these tours especially when dealing with airlines and\r\ntrains. While I didn\'t like the idea of getting up so early to leave <st1:city w:st=\"on\">Lima</st1:city> on the first flight out, once I got to <st1:city w:st=\"on\"><st1:place w:st=\"on\">Cuzco</st1:place></st1:city> I appreciated the\r\ncouple of hours I had to unpack and relax before the afternoon tour started.<o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><span style=\"font-size: 8.5pt; font-family: Verdana;\" lang=\"EN-US\"><o:p>&nbsp;</o:p></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><span style=\"font-size: 8.5pt; font-family: Verdana;\" lang=\"EN-US\">If you are looking for a quote how about this<span style=\"\">:<b> If you can only travel to one place make\r\nit <st1:city w:st=\"on\"><st1:place w:st=\"on\">Machu Picchu</st1:place></st1:city>.\r\n</b></span>There were two couples in my group who have traveled extensively to <st1:country-region w:st=\"on\">Greece</st1:country-region> and <st1:country-region w:st=\"on\">Italy</st1:country-region>\r\nand they both agreed <st1:city w:st=\"on\"><st1:place w:st=\"on\">Machu Picchu</st1:place></st1:city>\r\nbeat them all.<o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><span style=\"font-size: 8.5pt; font-family: Verdana;\" lang=\"EN-US\"><o:p>&nbsp;</o:p></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><span style=\"font-size: 8.5pt; font-family: Verdana;\" lang=\"EN-US\">Overall it was a great experience and I would use you\r\nguys again if I ever return to <st1:place w:st=\"on\">South America</st1:place>.<o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"background: yellow none repeat scroll 0% 0%; font-size: 8.5pt; font-family: Verdana; -moz-background-clip: border; -moz-background-origin: padding; -moz-background-inline-policy: continuous;\" lang=\"EN-US\"><o:p></o:p></span>\r\n\r\n                ','Kenneth <br/>\r\nCathedral City,CA,USA <br/>\r\nCuzco &amp; Machu Picchu\r\n\r\n                ','kenneth-smith.jpg','','',652,0,0,NULL,NULL,NULL),(409,1,'Hi Deanna,','<meta http-equiv=\"Content-Type\" content=\"text/html; charset=utf-8\"><meta name=\"ProgId\" content=\"Word.Document\"><meta name=\"Generator\" content=\"Microsoft Word 11\"><meta name=\"Originator\" content=\"Microsoft Word 11\"><link rel=\"File-List\" href=\"file:///C:%5CDOCUME%7E1%5CADMINI%7E1%5CCONFIG%7E1%5CTemp%5Cmsohtml1%5C09%5Cclip_filelist.xml\"><o:smarttagtype namespaceuri=\"urn:schemas-microsoft-com:office:smarttags\" name=\"country-region\" downloadurl=\"http://www.5iantlavalamp.com/\"></o:smarttagtype><o:smarttagtype namespaceuri=\"urn:schemas-microsoft-com:office:smarttags\" name=\"place\" downloadurl=\"http://www.5iantlavalamp.com/\"></o:smarttagtype><o:smarttagtype namespaceuri=\"urn:schemas-microsoft-com:office:smarttags\" name=\"City\" downloadurl=\"http://www.5iamas-microsoft-com:office:smarttags\"></o:smarttagtype><!--[if gte mso 9]><xml>\r\n <w:WordDocument>\r\n  <w:View>Normal</w:View>\r\n  <w:Zoom>0</w:Zoom>\r\n  <w:HyphenationZone>21</w:HyphenationZone>\r\n  <w:PunctuationKerning/>\r\n  <w:ValidateAgainstSchemas/>\r\n  <w:SaveIfXMLInvalid>false</w:SaveIfXMLInvalid>\r\n  <w:IgnoreMixedContent>false</w:IgnoreMixedContent>\r\n  <w:AlwaysShowPlaceholderText>false</w:AlwaysShowPlaceholderText>\r\n  <w:Compatibility>\r\n   <w:BreakWrappedTables/>\r\n   <w:SnapToGridInCell/>\r\n   <w:WrapTextWithPunct/>\r\n   <w:UseAsianBreakRules/>\r\n   <w:DontGrowAutofit/>\r\n  </w:Compatibility>\r\n  <w:BrowserLevel>MicrosoftInternetExplorer4</w:BrowserLevel>\r\n </w:WordDocument>\r\n</xml><![endif]--><!--[if gte mso 9]><xml>\r\n <w:LatentStyles DefLockedState=\"false\" LatentStyleCount=\"156\">\r\n </w:LatentStyles>\r\n</xml><![endif]--><!--[if !mso]><object\r\n classid=\"clsid:38481807-CA0E-42D2-BF39-B33AF135CC4D\" id=ieooui></object>\r\n<style>\r\nst1\\:*{behavior:url(#ieooui) }\r\n</style>\r\n<![endif]--><style>\r\n<!--\r\n /* Font Definitions */\r\n @font-face\r\n	{font-family:Verdana;\r\n	panose-1:2 11 6 4 3 5 4 4 2 4;\r\n	mso-font-charset:0;\r\n	mso-generic-font-family:swiss;\r\n	mso-font-pitch:variable;\r\n	mso-font-signature:536871559 0 0 0 415 0;}\r\n /* Style Definitions */\r\n p.MsoNormal, li.MsoNormal, div.MsoNormal\r\n	{mso-style-parent:\"\";\r\n	margin:0cm;\r\n	margin-bottom:.0001pt;\r\n	mso-pagination:widow-orphan;\r\n	font-size:12.0pt;\r\n	font-family:\"Times New Roman\";\r\n	mso-fareast-font-family:\"Times New Roman\";}\r\n@page Section1\r\n	{size:612.0pt 792.0pt;\r\n	margin:70.85pt 3.0cm 70.85pt 3.0cm;\r\n	mso-header-margin:36.0pt;\r\n	mso-footer-margin:36.0pt;\r\n	mso-paper-source:0;}\r\ndiv.Section1\r\n	{page:Section1;}\r\n-->\r\n</style><!--[if gte mso 10]>\r\n<style>\r\n /* Style Definitions */\r\n table.MsoNormalTable\r\n	{mso-style-name:\"Tabla normal\";\r\n	mso-tstyle-rowband-size:0;\r\n	mso-tstyle-colband-size:0;\r\n	mso-style-noshow:yes;\r\n	mso-style-parent:\"\";\r\n	mso-padding-alt:0cm 5.4pt 0cm 5.4pt;\r\n	mso-para-margin:0cm;\r\n	mso-para-margin-bottom:.0001pt;\r\n	mso-pagination:widow-orphan;\r\n	font-size:10.0pt;\r\n	font-family:\"Times New Roman\";\r\n	mso-ansi-language:#0400;\r\n	mso-fareast-language:#0400;\r\n	mso-bidi-language:#0400;}\r\n</style>\r\n<![endif]-->\r\n\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><span style=\"font-size: 8.5pt; font-family: Verdana;\" lang=\"EN-US\">We just got back yesterday and everything went very\r\nwell. <br>\r\n<br>\r\nStaying at the Ramada Lima Airport&nbsp;Hotel was a really good idea.&nbsp; It\r\nis across street from baggage claim so perfect when one\'s flights arrive into <st1:city w:st=\"on\"><st1:place w:st=\"on\">Lima</st1:place></st1:city> late, particularly\r\nwith kids in tow.&nbsp; They have a business center for online check-in and\r\nprinting boarding passes in order to save time also.&nbsp; And they store bags\r\nso a great place for using as a \"home base\" for travel within <st1:country-region w:st=\"on\"><st1:place w:st=\"on\">Peru</st1:place></st1:country-region>.<br>\r\n<br>\r\nExplorama Lodge was really well organized. They greeted us at <st1:city w:st=\"on\"><st1:place w:st=\"on\">Iquitos</st1:place></st1:city> airport and gave excellent service at\r\nall times.&nbsp; They actually assign each group a guide who stayed with us the\r\nentire time and helps us plan our&nbsp;daily schedule around our\r\ninterests.&nbsp; Luckily for us, the weather was great.<br>\r\n&nbsp;<br>\r\nThe family we stayed with in <st1:city w:st=\"on\"><st1:place w:st=\"on\">Cuzco</st1:place></st1:city>\r\nwas quite poor and so accommodations were sparse.&nbsp; I\'m not sure I\'d\r\nrecommend it for most tourists but it was what we wanted and worked out.&nbsp;\r\nWe donated stuff to the local school children in Cachiccata which was a huge\r\nsuccess.<br>\r\n&nbsp;<br>\r\nOur guide Jose&nbsp;during the Salkantay Trek was excellent, the food was\r\nplentiful and tasty, support and service was great and they were very well\r\norganized throughout.&nbsp; It was very tough for trekkers but the horses made\r\nit vital for my young boys.&nbsp; (I ended up renting a 2nd horse so each boy\r\nhad their own at all times.&nbsp; I would recommend horses for anyone under 14\r\nand you can trek and ride as you wish, which my boys did.)&nbsp; Day 1 was very\r\ntough and the altitude one cannot really prepare for so everyone was\r\nhurting.&nbsp; But once we got over the pass and began descending on day 2 everyone\r\nrecovered quickly and seemed to enjoy the achievement and diversity of the\r\ntrek.&nbsp; On day 4, I took my boys to the <st1:city w:st=\"on\"><st1:place w:st=\"on\">hot springs</st1:place></st1:city> in Santa Theresa and then met the\r\nremainder of our group at hydroelectric dam rather than trekking that\r\nday.&nbsp; This was smart and the boys loved the hot spring.<br>\r\n&nbsp;<br>\r\n<st1:city w:st=\"on\"><st1:place w:st=\"on\">Machu Picchu</st1:place></st1:city>\r\nwas fantastic and nothing really prepares you for seeing it live.&nbsp; Our\r\nweather was great and having a guide was really important to understanding\r\neverything.&nbsp;The first 400 into MP can climb Huaynapicchu which is scary\r\nlooking and near vertical but the view from the top back toward <st1:city w:st=\"on\"><st1:place w:st=\"on\">Machu Picchu</st1:place></st1:city> is\r\npriceless.<br>\r\n&nbsp;<br>\r\nFinally, Hotel Marqueses in <st1:place w:st=\"on\">Cusco</st1:place> was really\r\ngood for the price and I would highly recommend it for service, proximity to\r\nPlaza de Armas and attractions, breakfast, etc.<br>\r\n&nbsp;<br>\r\nThanks again for everything.&nbsp;<o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><span style=\"font-size: 8.5pt; font-family: Verdana;\" lang=\"EN-US\"><span style=\"\">&nbsp;</span><o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n\r\n                ','Best, <br/>\r\nScott <br/>\r\nPrinceton, NJ, USA <br/>\r\nIquitos, Cuzco, Machu Picchu','scott-smith.jpg','','',651,0,0,NULL,NULL,NULL),(410,1,'Dear Peru For Less','<meta http-equiv=\"Content-Type\" content=\"text/html; charset=utf-8\"><meta name=\"ProgId\" content=\"Word.Document\"><meta name=\"Generator\" content=\"Microsoft Word 11\"><meta name=\"Originator\" content=\"Microsoft Word 11\"><link rel=\"File-List\" href=\"file:///C:%5CDOCUME%7E1%5CADMINI%7E1%5CCONFIG%7E1%5CTemp%5Cmsohtml1%5C13%5Cclip_filelist.xml\"><o:smarttagtype namespaceuri=\"urn:schemas-microsoft-com:office:smarttags\" name=\"country-region\" downloadurl=\"http://www.5iantlavalamp.com/\"></o:smarttagtype><o:smarttagtype namespaceuri=\"urn:schemas-microsoft-com:office:smarttags\" name=\"place\" downloadurl=\"http://www.5iantlavalamp.com/\"></o:smarttagtype><o:smarttagtype namespaceuri=\"urn:schemas-microsoft-com:office:smarttags\" name=\"City\" downloadurl=\"http://www.5iamas-microsoft-com:office:smarttags\"></o:smarttagtype><!--[if gte mso 9]><xml>\r\n <w:WordDocument>\r\n  <w:View>Normal</w:View>\r\n  <w:Zoom>0</w:Zoom>\r\n  <w:HyphenationZone>21</w:HyphenationZone>\r\n  <w:PunctuationKerning/>\r\n  <w:ValidateAgainstSchemas/>\r\n  <w:SaveIfXMLInvalid>false</w:SaveIfXMLInvalid>\r\n  <w:IgnoreMixedContent>false</w:IgnoreMixedContent>\r\n  <w:AlwaysShowPlaceholderText>false</w:AlwaysShowPlaceholderText>\r\n  <w:Compatibility>\r\n   <w:BreakWrappedTables/>\r\n   <w:SnapToGridInCell/>\r\n   <w:WrapTextWithPunct/>\r\n   <w:UseAsianBreakRules/>\r\n   <w:DontGrowAutofit/>\r\n  </w:Compatibility>\r\n  <w:BrowserLevel>MicrosoftInternetExplorer4</w:BrowserLevel>\r\n </w:WordDocument>\r\n</xml><![endif]--><!--[if gte mso 9]><xml>\r\n <w:LatentStyles DefLockedState=\"false\" LatentStyleCount=\"156\">\r\n </w:LatentStyles>\r\n</xml><![endif]--><!--[if !mso]><object\r\n classid=\"clsid:38481807-CA0E-42D2-BF39-B33AF135CC4D\" id=ieooui></object>\r\n<style>\r\nst1\\:*{behavior:url(#ieooui) }\r\n</style>\r\n<![endif]--><style>\r\n<!--\r\n /* Font Definitions */\r\n @font-face\r\n	{font-family:Verdana;\r\n	panose-1:2 11 6 4 3 5 4 4 2 4;\r\n	mso-font-charset:0;\r\n	mso-generic-font-family:swiss;\r\n	mso-font-pitch:variable;\r\n	mso-font-signature:536871559 0 0 0 415 0;}\r\n /* Style Definitions */\r\n p.MsoNormal, li.MsoNormal, div.MsoNormal\r\n	{mso-style-parent:\"\";\r\n	margin:0cm;\r\n	margin-bottom:.0001pt;\r\n	mso-pagination:widow-orphan;\r\n	font-size:12.0pt;\r\n	font-family:\"Times New Roman\";\r\n	mso-fareast-font-family:\"Times New Roman\";}\r\n@page Section1\r\n	{size:612.0pt 792.0pt;\r\n	margin:70.85pt 3.0cm 70.85pt 3.0cm;\r\n	mso-header-margin:36.0pt;\r\n	mso-footer-margin:36.0pt;\r\n	mso-paper-source:0;}\r\ndiv.Section1\r\n	{page:Section1;}\r\n-->\r\n</style><!--[if gte mso 10]>\r\n<style>\r\n /* Style Definitions */\r\n table.MsoNormalTable\r\n	{mso-style-name:\"Tabla normal\";\r\n	mso-tstyle-rowband-size:0;\r\n	mso-tstyle-colband-size:0;\r\n	mso-style-noshow:yes;\r\n	mso-style-parent:\"\";\r\n	mso-padding-alt:0cm 5.4pt 0cm 5.4pt;\r\n	mso-para-margin:0cm;\r\n	mso-para-margin-bottom:.0001pt;\r\n	mso-pagination:widow-orphan;\r\n	font-size:10.0pt;\r\n	font-family:\"Times New Roman\";\r\n	mso-ansi-language:#0400;\r\n	mso-fareast-language:#0400;\r\n	mso-bidi-language:#0400;}\r\n</style>\r\n<![endif]-->\r\n\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><st1:city w:st=\"on\"><st1:place w:st=\"on\"><span style=\"font-size: 8.5pt; font-family: Verdana;\" lang=\"EN-GB\">Cuzco</span></st1:place></st1:city><span style=\"font-size: 8.5pt; font-family: Verdana;\" lang=\"EN-GB\"> on Monday, Tuesday, and Thursday night were\r\nexcellent. The front desk clerk at the Arqueologo Hotel&nbsp;was helpful, very courteous,\r\nand spoke very good English.&nbsp;The location was perfect and very close to\r\nthe town square.&nbsp;The hotel in Aguas Calientes was great. The rooms were\r\nvery clean and the beds were wonderful. The front desk clerk was extremely\r\nhelpful in answering all of our questions. The buffet dinner on Thursday night\r\nwas the best dinner of the entire trip. </span><span style=\"font-size: 8.5pt; font-family: Verdana;\" lang=\"EN-GB\"><o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><span style=\"font-size: 8.5pt; font-family: Verdana;\" lang=\"EN-GB\">&nbsp;&nbsp;<o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><span style=\"font-size: 8.5pt; font-family: Verdana;\" lang=\"EN-GB\">We fell in love with Cathedral\r\nof Cuzco, and its historical significance&nbsp;to&nbsp;the Spanish conquest. All\r\nof the other churches were just as impressive. Sacsayhuaman was an archaeological\r\nsite above and beyond my expectation.<o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><span style=\"font-size: 8.5pt; font-family: Verdana;\" lang=\"EN-GB\"><span style=\"\">&nbsp;</span></span><span style=\"font-size: 8.5pt; font-family: Verdana;\" lang=\"EN-GB\"><o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><span style=\"font-size: 8.5pt; font-family: Verdana;\" lang=\"EN-GB\">The altitude did affect me a\r\nlittle; however there was no sickness or accidents in the Jones clan. Monday\r\nand Tuesday activities prepared us for the ultimate visit: <st1:city w:st=\"on\"><st1:place w:st=\"on\">Machu Picchu</st1:place></st1:city>.&nbsp; It is hard to explain our\r\nexperience at <st1:city w:st=\"on\"><st1:place w:st=\"on\">Machu Picchu</st1:place></st1:city>,\r\nit was more than I had expected. It was the icing on the cake, la cr&eacute;me de la cr&eacute;me,\r\nthe hot tamale, the real enchilada. Mary, our tour guide on Monday and Tuesday,\r\nwas great. She was very informative and knowledgeable of the archaeological\r\nsites. </span><span style=\"font-size: 8.5pt; font-family: Verdana;\" lang=\"EN-GB\"><o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><span style=\"font-size: 8.5pt; font-family: Verdana;\" lang=\"EN-GB\">&nbsp;<o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><span style=\"font-size: 8.5pt; font-family: Verdana;\" lang=\"EN-GB\">Being in sales and marketing\r\nmyself, I am very aware of customer service.&nbsp; Cristina, with her warm\r\npersonality, was a perfect representative for Peru For Less. She took her job\r\nseriously and it showed in her ability to communicate with our group.</span><span style=\"font-size: 8.5pt; font-family: Verdana;\" lang=\"EN-GB\"><o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><span style=\"font-size: 8.5pt; font-family: Verdana;\" lang=\"EN-GB\">Chris, you are the sole\r\nreason I decided to go with Peru For Less. Your attention to detail and your\r\ncommunication skills over the phone and via email made my decision easy. </span><span style=\"font-size: 8.5pt; font-family: Verdana;\" lang=\"EN-GB\"><o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><span style=\"font-size: 8.5pt; font-family: Verdana;\" lang=\"EN-GB\">&nbsp;<o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><span style=\"font-size: 8.5pt; font-family: Verdana;\" lang=\"EN-GB\">I have traveled extensively\r\nthroughout Europe, <st1:country-region w:st=\"on\">Brazil</st1:country-region>, <st1:country-region w:st=\"on\">Mexico</st1:country-region>, <st1:city w:st=\"on\">Southeast Asia</st1:city>,\r\n<st1:country-region w:st=\"on\">Japan</st1:country-region>, and <st1:country-region w:st=\"on\">Korea</st1:country-region> and by far, the <st1:city w:st=\"on\"><st1:place w:st=\"on\">Machu Picchu</st1:place></st1:city> trip was the best trip of my\r\nlong life. It touched all my senses. I will recommend <st1:country-region w:st=\"on\">Peru</st1:country-region> For Less to anyone I meet who wants to go\r\nto <st1:place w:st=\"on\"><st1:city w:st=\"on\">Machu Picchu</st1:city></st1:place>.</span><span style=\"font-size: 8.5pt; font-family: Verdana;\" lang=\"EN-GB\"><o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><span style=\"font-size: 8.5pt; font-family: Verdana;\" lang=\"EN-GB\"><o:p>&nbsp;</o:p></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><span style=\"font-size: 8.5pt; font-family: Verdana;\" lang=\"EN-GB\">Thanks Chris!<o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n\r\n                ','Jim <br/>\r\n\r\nSalt Lake City, Utah, USA <br/>\r\nLima, Cuzco, Sacred Valley, Machu Picchu','jim-jones.jpg','','',650,0,0,NULL,NULL,NULL),(411,1,'Kristina','<meta http-equiv=\"Content-Type\" content=\"text/html; charset=utf-8\"><meta name=\"ProgId\" content=\"Word.Document\"><meta name=\"Generator\" content=\"Microsoft Word 11\"><meta name=\"Originator\" content=\"Microsoft Word 11\"><link rel=\"File-List\" href=\"file:///C:%5CDOCUME%7E1%5CADMINI%7E1%5CCONFIG%7E1%5CTemp%5Cmsohtml1%5C17%5Cclip_filelist.xml\"><o:smarttagtype namespaceuri=\"urn:schemas-microsoft-com:office:smarttags\" name=\"country-region\" downloadurl=\"http://www.5iantlavalamp.com/\"></o:smarttagtype><o:smarttagtype namespaceuri=\"urn:schemas-microsoft-com:office:smarttags\" name=\"place\" downloadurl=\"http://www.5iantlavalamp.com/\"></o:smarttagtype><o:smarttagtype namespaceuri=\"urn:schemas-microsoft-com:office:smarttags\" name=\"City\" downloadurl=\"http://www.5iamas-microsoft-com:office:smarttags\"></o:smarttagtype><o:smarttagtype namespaceuri=\"urn:schemas-microsoft-com:office:smarttags\" name=\"PlaceName\" downloadurl=\"http://www.5iantlavalamp.com/\"></o:smarttagtype><o:smarttagtype namespaceuri=\"urn:schemas-microsoft-com:office:smarttags\" name=\"PlaceType\" downloadurl=\"http://www.5iantlavalamp.com/\"></o:smarttagtype><o:smarttagtype namespaceuri=\"urn:schemas-microsoft-com:office:smarttags\" name=\"PersonName\"></o:smarttagtype><!--[if gte mso 9]><xml>\r\n <w:WordDocument>\r\n  <w:View>Normal</w:View>\r\n  <w:Zoom>0</w:Zoom>\r\n  <w:HyphenationZone>21</w:HyphenationZone>\r\n  <w:PunctuationKerning/>\r\n  <w:ValidateAgainstSchemas/>\r\n  <w:SaveIfXMLInvalid>false</w:SaveIfXMLInvalid>\r\n  <w:IgnoreMixedContent>false</w:IgnoreMixedContent>\r\n  <w:AlwaysShowPlaceholderText>false</w:AlwaysShowPlaceholderText>\r\n  <w:Compatibility>\r\n   <w:BreakWrappedTables/>\r\n   <w:SnapToGridInCell/>\r\n   <w:WrapTextWithPunct/>\r\n   <w:UseAsianBreakRules/>\r\n   <w:DontGrowAutofit/>\r\n  </w:Compatibility>\r\n  <w:BrowserLevel>MicrosoftInternetExplorer4</w:BrowserLevel>\r\n </w:WordDocument>\r\n</xml><![endif]--><!--[if gte mso 9]><xml>\r\n <w:LatentStyles DefLockedState=\"false\" LatentStyleCount=\"156\">\r\n </w:LatentStyles>\r\n</xml><![endif]--><!--[if !mso]><object\r\n classid=\"clsid:38481807-CA0E-42D2-BF39-B33AF135CC4D\" id=ieooui></object>\r\n<style>\r\nst1\\:*{behavior:url(#ieooui) }\r\n</style>\r\n<![endif]--><style>\r\n<!--\r\n /* Font Definitions */\r\n @font-face\r\n	{font-family:Verdana;\r\n	panose-1:2 11 6 4 3 5 4 4 2 4;\r\n	mso-font-charset:0;\r\n	mso-generic-font-family:swiss;\r\n	mso-font-pitch:variable;\r\n	mso-font-signature:536871559 0 0 0 415 0;}\r\n /* Style Definitions */\r\n p.MsoNormal, li.MsoNormal, div.MsoNormal\r\n	{mso-style-parent:\"\";\r\n	margin:0cm;\r\n	margin-bottom:.0001pt;\r\n	mso-pagination:widow-orphan;\r\n	font-size:12.0pt;\r\n	font-family:\"Times New Roman\";\r\n	mso-fareast-font-family:\"Times New Roman\";}\r\n@page Section1\r\n	{size:612.0pt 792.0pt;\r\n	margin:70.85pt 3.0cm 70.85pt 3.0cm;\r\n	mso-header-margin:36.0pt;\r\n	mso-footer-margin:36.0pt;\r\n	mso-paper-source:0;}\r\ndiv.Section1\r\n	{page:Section1;}\r\n-->\r\n</style><!--[if gte mso 10]>\r\n<style>\r\n /* Style Definitions */\r\n table.MsoNormalTable\r\n	{mso-style-name:\"Tabla normal\";\r\n	mso-tstyle-rowband-size:0;\r\n	mso-tstyle-colband-size:0;\r\n	mso-style-noshow:yes;\r\n	mso-style-parent:\"\";\r\n	mso-padding-alt:0cm 5.4pt 0cm 5.4pt;\r\n	mso-para-margin:0cm;\r\n	mso-para-margin-bottom:.0001pt;\r\n	mso-pagination:widow-orphan;\r\n	font-size:10.0pt;\r\n	font-family:\"Times New Roman\";\r\n	mso-ansi-language:#0400;\r\n	mso-fareast-language:#0400;\r\n	mso-bidi-language:#0400;}\r\n</style>\r\n<![endif]-->\r\n\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><span style=\"font-size: 8.5pt; font-family: Verdana;\" lang=\"EN-US\">Thank you so much for a great experience of <st1:country-region w:st=\"on\"><st1:place w:st=\"on\">Peru</st1:place></st1:country-region>!!&nbsp;\r\nEverything was picture perfect!&nbsp; We couldn\'t have asked for a better, more\r\norganized and scheduled vacation!&nbsp; <st1:country-region w:st=\"on\"><st1:place w:st=\"on\">Peru</st1:place></st1:country-region> for Less made the best of our\r\ntrip!<o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><span style=\"font-size: 8.5pt; font-family: Verdana;\" lang=\"EN-US\"><o:p>&nbsp;</o:p></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><span style=\"font-size: 8.5pt; font-family: Verdana;\" lang=\"EN-US\">Pick ups and transfers were scheduled to precision and\r\nPFL re-arranged our itinerary to accommodate the <st1:country-region w:st=\"on\"><st1:place w:st=\"on\">Peru</st1:place></st1:country-region> strikes with no hassle to us\r\nand still managing to fit everything in.<o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><span style=\"font-size: 8.5pt; font-family: Verdana;\" lang=\"EN-US\"><o:p>&nbsp;</o:p></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><span style=\"font-size: 8.5pt; font-family: Verdana;\" lang=\"EN-US\">We loved the Arqueologo Hotel in <st1:city w:st=\"on\"><st1:place w:st=\"on\">Cuzco</st1:place></st1:city>! Hotel staff were very friendly and\r\nhelpful and our local representative (Christina) was very efficient and\r\ninformative.&nbsp; <st1:city w:st=\"on\"><st1:place w:st=\"on\">Cuzco</st1:place></st1:city>\r\nis an amazing and beautiful town and the Inca ruins tour was great. The <st1:place w:st=\"on\"><st1:placename w:st=\"on\">Sacred</st1:placename> <st1:placetype w:st=\"on\">Valley</st1:placetype></st1:place>\r\nand Ollantaytambo were stunning.&nbsp; Then to <st1:city w:st=\"on\"><st1:place w:st=\"on\">Machu Picchu</st1:place></st1:city> - truly awesome!&nbsp; Our tour\r\nguide Fabricio made us capture the true magic of <st1:city w:st=\"on\"><st1:place w:st=\"on\">Machu Picchu</st1:place></st1:city> and the walk up to the sun gate\r\n - Intipunku - was breathtaking, highly recommended!&nbsp; <o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><span style=\"font-size: 8.5pt; font-family: Verdana;\" lang=\"EN-US\"><o:p>&nbsp;</o:p></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><span style=\"font-size: 8.5pt; font-family: Verdana;\" lang=\"EN-US\">Puno on the Andean Explorer train was absolutely worth\r\nit and a great experience.&nbsp; Service was impeccable and the pisco sours\r\nserved at 10am even better! The Casa Andina Tikarani in Puno was lovely as were\r\nthe people of Puno. The Uros floating Islands on Lake Titicaca were fascinating\r\nand the food on <st1:place w:st=\"on\"><st1:placename w:st=\"on\">Taquile</st1:placename>\r\n <st1:placetype w:st=\"on\">Island</st1:placetype></st1:place> fantastic -\r\nbeautiful location.<o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><span style=\"font-size: 8.5pt; font-family: Verdana;\" lang=\"EN-US\"><o:p>&nbsp;</o:p></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><span style=\"font-size: 8.5pt; font-family: Verdana;\" lang=\"EN-US\">Next stop - <st1:city w:st=\"on\">Arequipa</st1:city>\r\nand the <st1:place w:st=\"on\"><st1:placename w:st=\"on\">Colca</st1:placename> <st1:placetype w:st=\"on\">Canyon</st1:placetype></st1:place> - wow!&nbsp; The diversity of <st1:country-region w:st=\"on\"><st1:place w:st=\"on\">Peru</st1:place></st1:country-region> is\r\namazing.&nbsp; The hotel Pozo del Cielo in Chivay was so lovely, especially the\r\nhot water bottles at night.&nbsp; And a special thanks goes to the <st1:personname productid=\"La Gruta Hotel\" w:st=\"on\"><st1:personname productid=\"La Gruta\" w:st=\"on\">La Gruta</st1:personname> Hotel</st1:personname> in <st1:city w:st=\"on\"><st1:place w:st=\"on\">Arequipa</st1:place></st1:city> for allowing us to have the room a\r\nlittle longer when I was ill, everyone was so helpful!<o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><span style=\"font-size: 8.5pt; font-family: Verdana;\" lang=\"EN-US\"><o:p>&nbsp;</o:p></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><span style=\"font-size: 8.5pt; font-family: Verdana;\" lang=\"EN-US\">Loved it all and thanks to PFL we got to see and\r\nexperience the best of <st1:country-region w:st=\"on\"><st1:place w:st=\"on\">Peru</st1:place></st1:country-region>.&nbsp;\r\nScheduled and executed to perfection.&nbsp; We couldn\'t have asked for anything\r\nmore.<o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><span style=\"font-size: 8.5pt; font-family: Verdana;\" lang=\"EN-US\"><o:p>&nbsp;</o:p></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><span style=\"font-size: 8.5pt; font-family: Verdana;\" lang=\"EN-US\">A special thanks to Kristina for going above and\r\nbeyond in organizing the best itinerary and a big thank you to all our reps and\r\ntour guides for a most enjoyable stay in <st1:country-region w:st=\"on\"><st1:place w:st=\"on\">Peru</st1:place></st1:country-region>.<o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><span style=\"font-size: 8.5pt; font-family: Verdana;\" lang=\"EN-US\"><o:p>&nbsp;</o:p></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><span style=\"font-size: 8.5pt; font-family: Verdana;\" lang=\"EN-US\">We would have no hesitation on recommending <st1:country-region w:st=\"on\">Peru</st1:country-region> to future travelers and would definitely use\r\nPFL again for any other <st1:place w:st=\"on\">South America</st1:place> trips\r\nwe\'ll take in the future.<o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n\r\n                ','Linda and Helen<br/>\r\nUK <br/>\r\nCuzco, Machu Picchu, Puno, and Arequipa','budford.jpg','','',649,0,0,NULL,NULL,NULL),(412,1,'Dear Peru For Less','<meta http-equiv=\"Content-Type\" content=\"text/html; charset=utf-8\"><meta name=\"ProgId\" content=\"Word.Document\"><meta name=\"Generator\" content=\"Microsoft Word 11\"><meta name=\"Originator\" content=\"Microsoft Word 11\"><link rel=\"File-List\" href=\"file:///C:%5CDOCUME%7E1%5CADMINI%7E1%5CCONFIG%7E1%5CTemp%5Cmsohtml1%5C21%5Cclip_filelist.xml\"><o:smarttagtype namespaceuri=\"urn:schemas-microsoft-com:office:smarttags\" name=\"country-region\" downloadurl=\"http://www.5iantlavalamp.com/\"></o:smarttagtype><o:smarttagtype namespaceuri=\"urn:schemas-microsoft-com:office:smarttags\" name=\"place\" downloadurl=\"http://www.5iantlavalamp.com/\"></o:smarttagtype><o:smarttagtype namespaceuri=\"urn:schemas-microsoft-com:office:smarttags\" name=\"City\" downloadurl=\"http://www.5iamas-microsoft-com:office:smarttags\"></o:smarttagtype><o:smarttagtype namespaceuri=\"urn:schemas-microsoft-com:office:smarttags\" name=\"PlaceName\" downloadurl=\"http://www.5iantlavalamp.com/\"></o:smarttagtype><o:smarttagtype namespaceuri=\"urn:schemas-microsoft-com:office:smarttags\" name=\"PlaceType\" downloadurl=\"http://www.5iantlavalamp.com/\"></o:smarttagtype><!--[if gte mso 9]><xml>\r\n <w:WordDocument>\r\n  <w:View>Normal</w:View>\r\n  <w:Zoom>0</w:Zoom>\r\n  <w:HyphenationZone>21</w:HyphenationZone>\r\n  <w:PunctuationKerning/>\r\n  <w:ValidateAgainstSchemas/>\r\n  <w:SaveIfXMLInvalid>false</w:SaveIfXMLInvalid>\r\n  <w:IgnoreMixedContent>false</w:IgnoreMixedContent>\r\n  <w:AlwaysShowPlaceholderText>false</w:AlwaysShowPlaceholderText>\r\n  <w:Compatibility>\r\n   <w:BreakWrappedTables/>\r\n   <w:SnapToGridInCell/>\r\n   <w:WrapTextWithPunct/>\r\n   <w:UseAsianBreakRules/>\r\n   <w:DontGrowAutofit/>\r\n  </w:Compatibility>\r\n  <w:BrowserLevel>MicrosoftInternetExplorer4</w:BrowserLevel>\r\n </w:WordDocument>\r\n</xml><![endif]--><!--[if gte mso 9]><xml>\r\n <w:LatentStyles DefLockedState=\"false\" LatentStyleCount=\"156\">\r\n </w:LatentStyles>\r\n</xml><![endif]--><!--[if !mso]><object\r\n classid=\"clsid:38481807-CA0E-42D2-BF39-B33AF135CC4D\" id=ieooui></object>\r\n<style>\r\nst1\\:*{behavior:url(#ieooui) }\r\n</style>\r\n<![endif]--><style>\r\n<!--\r\n /* Font Definitions */\r\n @font-face\r\n	{font-family:Verdana;\r\n	panose-1:2 11 6 4 3 5 4 4 2 4;\r\n	mso-font-charset:0;\r\n	mso-generic-font-family:swiss;\r\n	mso-font-pitch:variable;\r\n	mso-font-signature:536871559 0 0 0 415 0;}\r\n /* Style Definitions */\r\n p.MsoNormal, li.MsoNormal, div.MsoNormal\r\n	{mso-style-parent:\"\";\r\n	margin:0cm;\r\n	margin-bottom:.0001pt;\r\n	mso-pagination:widow-orphan;\r\n	font-size:12.0pt;\r\n	font-family:\"Times New Roman\";\r\n	mso-fareast-font-family:\"Times New Roman\";}\r\n@page Section1\r\n	{size:612.0pt 792.0pt;\r\n	margin:70.85pt 3.0cm 70.85pt 3.0cm;\r\n	mso-header-margin:36.0pt;\r\n	mso-footer-margin:36.0pt;\r\n	mso-paper-source:0;}\r\ndiv.Section1\r\n	{page:Section1;}\r\n-->\r\n</style><!--[if gte mso 10]>\r\n<style>\r\n /* Style Definitions */\r\n table.MsoNormalTable\r\n	{mso-style-name:\"Tabla normal\";\r\n	mso-tstyle-rowband-size:0;\r\n	mso-tstyle-colband-size:0;\r\n	mso-style-noshow:yes;\r\n	mso-style-parent:\"\";\r\n	mso-padding-alt:0cm 5.4pt 0cm 5.4pt;\r\n	mso-para-margin:0cm;\r\n	mso-para-margin-bottom:.0001pt;\r\n	mso-pagination:widow-orphan;\r\n	font-size:10.0pt;\r\n	font-family:\"Times New Roman\";\r\n	mso-ansi-language:#0400;\r\n	mso-fareast-language:#0400;\r\n	mso-bidi-language:#0400;}\r\n</style>\r\n<![endif]-->\r\n\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><span style=\"font-size: 8.5pt; font-family: Verdana;\" lang=\"EN-GB\">First of all, I would like to take this opportunity to\r\nthank you for making all the logistical arrangements for my trip.&nbsp; My\r\nniece was traveling through out South America and I was meeting her in <st1:city w:st=\"on\">Lima</st1:city> for the <st1:country-region w:st=\"on\"><st1:place w:st=\"on\">Peru</st1:place></st1:country-region> trip.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;I am\r\nuse to making my own arrangements but realized that I would have had to spend\r\nhours on different websites to book each and every flight, bus, train, hotel,\r\nand transfer in <st1:city w:st=\"on\">Lima</st1:city>, Cusco, the <st1:place w:st=\"on\"><st1:placename w:st=\"on\">Sacred</st1:placename> <st1:placetype w:st=\"on\">Valley</st1:placetype></st1:place>,\r\nand Puno.&nbsp;&nbsp;Giving the job to you made it so much easier and less\r\nstressful.&nbsp; Rather than booking it all myself, I ended up being a much\r\nhappier traveler!<o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><span style=\"font-size: 8.5pt; font-family: Verdana;\" lang=\"EN-GB\">&nbsp;<o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><span style=\"font-size: 8.5pt; font-family: Verdana;\" lang=\"EN-GB\">As a result of our e-mail conversations, you put\r\ntogether a detailed schedule that fit my travel needs.&nbsp;&nbsp;You were\r\nalways available to answer my questions and gave me good suggestions on hotels\r\nand transportation schedules. &nbsp;You provided excellent customer service\r\nprior to, during, and after the trip.&nbsp; I was extremely impressed with the communication\r\nprocess between you, the <st1:city w:st=\"on\"><st1:place w:st=\"on\">Cuzco</st1:place></st1:city>\r\noffice, tour companies, etc.&nbsp; <o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><span style=\"font-size: 8.5pt; font-family: Verdana;\" lang=\"EN-GB\">&nbsp;<o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><span style=\"font-size: 8.5pt; font-family: Verdana;\" lang=\"EN-GB\">Everything went smoothly, from the time we got picked up\r\nat the airport in <st1:city w:st=\"on\">Cuzco</st1:city> to the time we departed <st1:city w:st=\"on\"><st1:place w:st=\"on\">Lima</st1:place></st1:city> on our last day of\r\nthe trip.&nbsp;&nbsp;I couldn\'t have been happier with the service you\r\nprovided.&nbsp; I am especially appreciative to you for making last minute\r\narrangements when we decided to extend our trip to Puno and <st1:place w:st=\"on\">Lake\r\n Titicaca</st1:place>.<o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><span style=\"font-size: 8.5pt; font-family: Verdana;\" lang=\"EN-GB\">&nbsp;<o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><span style=\"font-size: 8.5pt; font-family: Verdana;\" lang=\"EN-GB\">The hotels you selected for us were outstanding.&nbsp;\r\nThe staff was welcoming and the&nbsp;rooms very comfortable....some of the beds\r\nwere so soft, we felt like we were sleeping on marshmallows!<o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><span style=\"font-size: 8.5pt; font-family: Verdana;\" lang=\"EN-GB\">&nbsp;<o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><span style=\"font-size: 8.5pt; font-family: Verdana;\" lang=\"EN-GB\">A special thanks to Tracy Imbeault for taking care of\r\nus during our time in <st1:city w:st=\"on\"><st1:place w:st=\"on\">Cuzco</st1:place></st1:city>.&nbsp;Our\r\nflight from <st1:city w:st=\"on\"><st1:place w:st=\"on\">Lima</st1:place></st1:city>\r\nwas canceled and we were put on the next flight by the airline.&nbsp; Although <st1:place w:st=\"on\"><st1:city w:st=\"on\">Tracy</st1:city></st1:place> was not aware of the\r\ncancelation,(LAN told her that it was still scheduled to arrive on time),\r\n&nbsp;she was at the airport waiting to take us to the hotel.&nbsp; During our\r\nbriefing, she reviewed our itinerary, gave us our vouchers, helped check us in,\r\nand offered suggestions on activities in Cusco and <st1:city w:st=\"on\"><st1:place w:st=\"on\">Machu Picchu</st1:place></st1:city>.&nbsp; I&nbsp;found her to be\r\nvery knowledgeable....our conversations with <st1:city w:st=\"on\"><st1:place w:st=\"on\">Tracy</st1:place></st1:city> were informative and enjoyable.&nbsp;\r\nShe was both professional and personable.and enthusiastic about her job...a\r\nwonderful representative of <st1:country-region w:st=\"on\"><st1:place w:st=\"on\">Peru</st1:place></st1:country-region>\r\nfor Less.&nbsp; There should be more people like <st1:city w:st=\"on\"><st1:place w:st=\"on\">Tracy</st1:place></st1:city> working in the travel industry!<o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><span style=\"font-size: 8.5pt; font-family: Verdana;\" lang=\"EN-GB\">&nbsp;<o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><span style=\"font-size: 8.5pt; font-family: Verdana;\" lang=\"EN-GB\">I would also like to acknowledge Fabricio Ortiz De\r\nZevallos, our tour guide in <st1:city w:st=\"on\"><st1:place w:st=\"on\">Machu\r\n  Picchu</st1:place></st1:city>.&nbsp; I could tell that he enjoyed what he was\r\ndoing and that he was extremely knowledgeable of history and Inca\r\nculture.&nbsp;He, too, was professional and personable.&nbsp; It was a pleasure\r\nto have him as our guide!<o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><span style=\"font-size: 8.5pt; font-family: Verdana;\" lang=\"EN-GB\">&nbsp;<o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><span style=\"font-size: 8.5pt; font-family: Verdana;\" lang=\"EN-GB\">And although I don\'t remember their names, I am\r\nappreciative&nbsp;to all the drivers who picked us up at airports, bus\r\nstations, hotels, and train stations and transported us to our next stop.&nbsp;\r\nThey were always on time, handled our luggage, and got&nbsp;us safely\r\nto&nbsp;our destinations.&nbsp; <o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><span style=\"font-size: 8.5pt; font-family: Verdana;\" lang=\"EN-GB\">&nbsp;<o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><span style=\"font-size: 8.5pt; font-family: Verdana;\" lang=\"EN-GB\">Again, JP, I can not thank you enough for helping me\r\nplan my trip to <st1:country-region w:st=\"on\"><st1:place w:st=\"on\">Peru</st1:place></st1:country-region>.&nbsp;I\r\nam certain that as a result of my positive experience working with you and the <st1:country-region w:st=\"on\">Peru</st1:country-region> for Less team, that when it comes time to\r\nplan&nbsp;a trip to <st1:country-region w:st=\"on\">Chile</st1:country-region> or\r\n<st1:place w:st=\"on\"><st1:country-region w:st=\"on\">Argentina</st1:country-region></st1:place>,\r\nI will consider using Peru For Less to book all my reservations and logistical\r\narrangements.&nbsp; <o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><span style=\"font-size: 8.5pt; font-family: Verdana;\" lang=\"EN-GB\">&nbsp;<o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><i style=\"\"><span style=\"font-size: 8.5pt; font-family: Verdana;\" lang=\"EN-GB\">With\r\nappreciation,<o:p></o:p></span></i></p>\r\n\r\n                ','Judy <br/>\r\n\r\nWashington, DC <br/>\r\nCusco, Sacred Valley, Machu Picchu, and Puno','frank-judy.jpg','','',648,0,0,NULL,NULL,NULL),(413,1,'Dear Peru For Less','<meta http-equiv=\"Content-Type\" content=\"text/html; charset=utf-8\"><meta name=\"ProgId\" content=\"Word.Document\"><meta name=\"Generator\" content=\"Microsoft Word 11\"><meta name=\"Originator\" content=\"Microsoft Word 11\"><link rel=\"File-List\" href=\"file:///C:%5CDOCUME%7E1%5CADMINI%7E1%5CCONFIG%7E1%5CTemp%5Cmsohtml1%5C07%5Cclip_filelist.xml\"><o:smarttagtype namespaceuri=\"urn:schemas-microsoft-com:office:smarttags\" name=\"place\" downloadurl=\"http://www.5iantlavalamp.com/\"></o:smarttagtype><o:smarttagtype namespaceuri=\"urn:schemas-microsoft-com:office:smarttags\" name=\"City\" downloadurl=\"http://www.5iamas-microsoft-com:office:smarttags\"></o:smarttagtype><!--[if gte mso 9]><xml>\r\n <w:WordDocument>\r\n  <w:View>Normal</w:View>\r\n  <w:Zoom>0</w:Zoom>\r\n  <w:HyphenationZone>21</w:HyphenationZone>\r\n  <w:PunctuationKerning/>\r\n  <w:ValidateAgainstSchemas/>\r\n  <w:SaveIfXMLInvalid>false</w:SaveIfXMLInvalid>\r\n  <w:IgnoreMixedContent>false</w:IgnoreMixedContent>\r\n  <w:AlwaysShowPlaceholderText>false</w:AlwaysShowPlaceholderText>\r\n  <w:Compatibility>\r\n   <w:BreakWrappedTables/>\r\n   <w:SnapToGridInCell/>\r\n   <w:WrapTextWithPunct/>\r\n   <w:UseAsianBreakRules/>\r\n   <w:DontGrowAutofit/>\r\n  </w:Compatibility>\r\n  <w:BrowserLevel>MicrosoftInternetExplorer4</w:BrowserLevel>\r\n </w:WordDocument>\r\n</xml><![endif]--><!--[if gte mso 9]><xml>\r\n <w:LatentStyles DefLockedState=\"false\" LatentStyleCount=\"156\">\r\n </w:LatentStyles>\r\n</xml><![endif]--><!--[if !mso]><object\r\n classid=\"clsid:38481807-CA0E-42D2-BF39-B33AF135CC4D\" id=ieooui></object>\r\n<style>\r\nst1\\:*{behavior:url(#ieooui) }\r\n</style>\r\n<![endif]--><style>\r\n<!--\r\n /* Font Definitions */\r\n @font-face\r\n	{font-family:Verdana;\r\n	panose-1:2 11 6 4 3 5 4 4 2 4;\r\n	mso-font-charset:0;\r\n	mso-generic-font-family:swiss;\r\n	mso-font-pitch:variable;\r\n	mso-font-signature:536871559 0 0 0 415 0;}\r\n /* Style Definitions */\r\n p.MsoNormal, li.MsoNormal, div.MsoNormal\r\n	{mso-style-parent:\"\";\r\n	margin:0cm;\r\n	margin-bottom:.0001pt;\r\n	mso-pagination:widow-orphan;\r\n	font-size:12.0pt;\r\n	font-family:\"Times New Roman\";\r\n	mso-fareast-font-family:\"Times New Roman\";}\r\n@page Section1\r\n	{size:612.0pt 792.0pt;\r\n	margin:70.85pt 3.0cm 70.85pt 3.0cm;\r\n	mso-header-margin:36.0pt;\r\n	mso-footer-margin:36.0pt;\r\n	mso-paper-source:0;}\r\ndiv.Section1\r\n	{page:Section1;}\r\n-->\r\n</style><!--[if gte mso 10]>\r\n<style>\r\n /* Style Definitions */\r\n table.MsoNormalTable\r\n	{mso-style-name:\"Tabla normal\";\r\n	mso-tstyle-rowband-size:0;\r\n	mso-tstyle-colband-size:0;\r\n	mso-style-noshow:yes;\r\n	mso-style-parent:\"\";\r\n	mso-padding-alt:0cm 5.4pt 0cm 5.4pt;\r\n	mso-para-margin:0cm;\r\n	mso-para-margin-bottom:.0001pt;\r\n	mso-pagination:widow-orphan;\r\n	font-size:10.0pt;\r\n	font-family:\"Times New Roman\";\r\n	mso-ansi-language:#0400;\r\n	mso-fareast-language:#0400;\r\n	mso-bidi-language:#0400;}\r\n</style>\r\n<![endif]-->\r\n\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><span style=\"font-size: 8.5pt; font-family: Verdana;\" lang=\"EN-GB\">Yes, we are home safely and had a wonderful time and a\r\nvery memorable trip. Everything went exactly as promised by Peru For Less. All\r\ntransfers and tours were on schedule and all the guides were very good. Peru\r\nfor Less made sure we were informed of everything we needed to know on any\r\ngiven day such as what to take on each excursion. We would use your services\r\nagain and recommend your company to others. <o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><span style=\"font-size: 8.5pt; font-family: Verdana;\" lang=\"EN-GB\"><o:p>&nbsp;</o:p></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><span style=\"font-size: 8.5pt; font-family: Verdana;\" lang=\"EN-GB\">The Casa Andina chain of hotels that you booked us in\r\neverywhere, except at Aguas Calientes, was charming, clean and comfortable and\r\nthe staff was excellent. They were all located near the main square in every\r\ntown we visited which was extremely convenient. <o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><span style=\"font-size: 8.5pt; font-family: Verdana;\" lang=\"EN-GB\"><o:p>&nbsp;</o:p></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><span style=\"font-size: 8.5pt; font-family: Verdana;\" lang=\"EN-GB\">We enjoyed every place we visited, but especially <st1:place w:st=\"on\"><st1:city w:st=\"on\">Arequipa</st1:city></st1:place>. It was an\r\nexcellent place to begin adjusting the altitude before proceeding to Puno and <st1:city w:st=\"on\"><st1:place w:st=\"on\">Cuzco</st1:place></st1:city>. The city has\r\nexceptional charm and prices there are less than other cities. It was the best\r\nplace to add an extra day to our itinerary to relax in the Plaza de Armas, try\r\nqueso helado, see Juanita the ice mummy, feed the pigeons and browse in the\r\nshops. Our trip coincided with the August 15th Founder\'s Day festival and\r\nparade which we enjoyed very much.<o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n\r\n                ','Thanks so much, <br/>\r\n\r\nThe Runyon <br/>\r\nFamily Las Vegas, NV, USA\r\nLima, Arequipa, Puno, Cuzco and Machu Picchu','runyon.jpg','','',647,0,0,NULL,NULL,NULL),(414,1,'Dear Peru For Less','<meta http-equiv=\"Content-Type\" content=\"text/html; charset=utf-8\"><meta name=\"ProgId\" content=\"Word.Document\"><meta name=\"Generator\" content=\"Microsoft Word 11\"><meta name=\"Originator\" content=\"Microsoft Word 11\"><link rel=\"File-List\" href=\"file:///C:%5CDOCUME%7E1%5CADMINI%7E1%5CCONFIG%7E1%5CTemp%5Cmsohtml1%5C01%5Cclip_filelist.xml\"><o:smarttagtype namespaceuri=\"urn:schemas-microsoft-com:office:smarttags\" name=\"country-region\" downloadurl=\"http://www.5iantlavalamp.com/\"></o:smarttagtype><o:smarttagtype namespaceuri=\"urn:schemas-microsoft-com:office:smarttags\" name=\"place\" downloadurl=\"http://www.5iantlavalamp.com/\"></o:smarttagtype><o:smarttagtype namespaceuri=\"urn:schemas-microsoft-com:office:smarttags\" name=\"City\" downloadurl=\"http://www.5iamas-microsoft-com:office:smarttags\"></o:smarttagtype><o:smarttagtype namespaceuri=\"urn:schemas-microsoft-com:office:smarttags\" name=\"metricconverter\"></o:smarttagtype><!--[if gte mso 9]><xml>\r\n <w:WordDocument>\r\n  <w:View>Normal</w:View>\r\n  <w:Zoom>0</w:Zoom>\r\n  <w:HyphenationZone>21</w:HyphenationZone>\r\n  <w:PunctuationKerning/>\r\n  <w:ValidateAgainstSchemas/>\r\n  <w:SaveIfXMLInvalid>false</w:SaveIfXMLInvalid>\r\n  <w:IgnoreMixedContent>false</w:IgnoreMixedContent>\r\n  <w:AlwaysShowPlaceholderText>false</w:AlwaysShowPlaceholderText>\r\n  <w:Compatibility>\r\n   <w:BreakWrappedTables/>\r\n   <w:SnapToGridInCell/>\r\n   <w:WrapTextWithPunct/>\r\n   <w:UseAsianBreakRules/>\r\n   <w:DontGrowAutofit/>\r\n  </w:Compatibility>\r\n  <w:BrowserLevel>MicrosoftInternetExplorer4</w:BrowserLevel>\r\n </w:WordDocument>\r\n</xml><![endif]--><!--[if gte mso 9]><xml>\r\n <w:LatentStyles DefLockedState=\"false\" LatentStyleCount=\"156\">\r\n </w:LatentStyles>\r\n</xml><![endif]--><!--[if !mso]><object\r\n classid=\"clsid:38481807-CA0E-42D2-BF39-B33AF135CC4D\" id=ieooui></object>\r\n<style>\r\nst1\\:*{behavior:url(#ieooui) }\r\n</style>\r\n<![endif]--><style>\r\n<!--\r\n /* Font Definitions */\r\n @font-face\r\n	{font-family:Verdana;\r\n	panose-1:2 11 6 4 3 5 4 4 2 4;\r\n	mso-font-charset:0;\r\n	mso-generic-font-family:swiss;\r\n	mso-font-pitch:variable;\r\n	mso-font-signature:536871559 0 0 0 415 0;}\r\n /* Style Definitions */\r\n p.MsoNormal, li.MsoNormal, div.MsoNormal\r\n	{mso-style-parent:\"\";\r\n	margin:0cm;\r\n	margin-bottom:.0001pt;\r\n	mso-pagination:widow-orphan;\r\n	font-size:12.0pt;\r\n	font-family:\"Times New Roman\";\r\n	mso-fareast-font-family:\"Times New Roman\";}\r\n@page Section1\r\n	{size:612.0pt 792.0pt;\r\n	margin:70.85pt 3.0cm 70.85pt 3.0cm;\r\n	mso-header-margin:36.0pt;\r\n	mso-footer-margin:36.0pt;\r\n	mso-paper-source:0;}\r\ndiv.Section1\r\n	{page:Section1;}\r\n-->\r\n</style><!--[if gte mso 10]>\r\n<style>\r\n /* Style Definitions */\r\n table.MsoNormalTable\r\n	{mso-style-name:\"Tabla normal\";\r\n	mso-tstyle-rowband-size:0;\r\n	mso-tstyle-colband-size:0;\r\n	mso-style-noshow:yes;\r\n	mso-style-parent:\"\";\r\n	mso-padding-alt:0cm 5.4pt 0cm 5.4pt;\r\n	mso-para-margin:0cm;\r\n	mso-para-margin-bottom:.0001pt;\r\n	mso-pagination:widow-orphan;\r\n	font-size:10.0pt;\r\n	font-family:\"Times New Roman\";\r\n	mso-ansi-language:#0400;\r\n	mso-fareast-language:#0400;\r\n	mso-bidi-language:#0400;}\r\n</style>\r\n<![endif]-->\r\n\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><span style=\"font-size: 8.5pt; font-family: Verdana;\" lang=\"EN-GB\">Our trip to <st1:place w:st=\"on\"><st1:country-region w:st=\"on\">Peru</st1:country-region></st1:place> this summer was\r\nfantastic.&nbsp; My husband and I started planning it&nbsp;a few months in\r\nadvance.&nbsp;&nbsp;From the start you were extremely helpful and always\r\navailable to answer any questions that I had.&nbsp; You helped us plan&nbsp;our\r\ntrip to&nbsp;<st1:city w:st=\"on\">Lima</st1:city>, Lake Titicaca, <st1:city w:st=\"on\">Cuzco</st1:city>, and <st1:city w:st=\"on\"><st1:place w:st=\"on\">Machu\r\n  Picchu</st1:place></st1:city>.&nbsp; Your&nbsp;hotel recommendations were\r\nexcellent and you suggested many of the places I had already seen in my Frommer\'s\r\n<st1:country-region w:st=\"on\"><st1:place w:st=\"on\">Peru</st1:place></st1:country-region>\r\nbook, which was great.&nbsp; It was easy to plan and the wonderful thing is\r\nthat we were able to&nbsp;book our own flights and then book the tours and\r\nhotels through you guys.&nbsp; Upon arrival to each city we were greeted by\r\nmany friendly faces who&nbsp;took the time to&nbsp;talk about the cities we\r\nwere in and give us an explanation of what&nbsp;our itinerary would look like\r\nwhile in that particular destination.&nbsp;&nbsp;Tracy (<st1:city w:st=\"on\">Cuzco</st1:city>)&nbsp;and\r\nMiguel (<st1:city w:st=\"on\"><st1:place w:st=\"on\">Lima</st1:place></st1:city>)\r\nwere two of those people.&nbsp; Our guided tours of the the Uros Islands and\r\nTaquile Island by Walter, tour of Machu Picchu by Fabricio, and our tour of\r\nCuzco and&nbsp;nearby ruins by Juan Carlos were fantastic, they exceeded our\r\nexpectations!&nbsp; These tour guides&nbsp;were very knowledgeable and&nbsp;we\r\nlearned a great deal from them.&nbsp;Our trip to <st1:country-region w:st=\"on\"><st1:place w:st=\"on\">Peru</st1:place></st1:country-region> was&nbsp;amazing and my\r\nhusband and I enjoyed every moment.&nbsp;&nbsp;We stayed in Aguas Calientes for\r\nthe night and&nbsp;went&nbsp;to <st1:city w:st=\"on\"><st1:place w:st=\"on\">Machu&nbsp;Picchu</st1:place></st1:city>\r\ntwice.&nbsp; Once&nbsp;on the&nbsp;day we arrived for the guided tour\r\nand&nbsp;then we stayed up there till closing and the second day we woke up at <st1:metricconverter productid=\"4 a\" w:st=\"on\">4 a</st1:metricconverter>.m. to make sure we made it\r\nthere for sunrise.&nbsp; Definitely worth it and I would suggest that everyone\r\nstay the night if they can so that they can see it in a different light the\r\nnext day.&nbsp; We&nbsp;were very pleased with the service provided from start\r\nto finish and we had an amazing trip!<o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n\r\n                ','Thanks for everything, <br/>\r\nVicky <br/>\r\nLima, Cuzco, Machu Picchu and Puno','vicky-gomez.jpg','','',646,0,0,NULL,NULL,NULL),(415,1,'Dear Peru For Less','<meta http-equiv=\"Content-Type\" content=\"text/html; charset=utf-8\"><meta name=\"ProgId\" content=\"Word.Document\"><meta name=\"Generator\" content=\"Microsoft Word 11\"><meta name=\"Originator\" content=\"Microsoft Word 11\"><link rel=\"File-List\" href=\"file:///C:%5CDOCUME%7E1%5CADMINI%7E1%5CCONFIG%7E1%5CTemp%5Cmsohtml1%5C05%5Cclip_filelist.xml\"><o:smarttagtype namespaceuri=\"urn:schemas-microsoft-com:office:smarttags\" name=\"place\" downloadurl=\"http://www.5iantlavalamp.com/\"></o:smarttagtype><o:smarttagtype namespaceuri=\"urn:schemas-microsoft-com:office:smarttags\" name=\"City\" downloadurl=\"http://www.5iamas-microsoft-com:office:smarttags\"></o:smarttagtype><!--[if gte mso 9]><xml>\r\n <w:WordDocument>\r\n  <w:View>Normal</w:View>\r\n  <w:Zoom>0</w:Zoom>\r\n  <w:HyphenationZone>21</w:HyphenationZone>\r\n  <w:PunctuationKerning/>\r\n  <w:ValidateAgainstSchemas/>\r\n  <w:SaveIfXMLInvalid>false</w:SaveIfXMLInvalid>\r\n  <w:IgnoreMixedContent>false</w:IgnoreMixedContent>\r\n  <w:AlwaysShowPlaceholderText>false</w:AlwaysShowPlaceholderText>\r\n  <w:Compatibility>\r\n   <w:BreakWrappedTables/>\r\n   <w:SnapToGridInCell/>\r\n   <w:WrapTextWithPunct/>\r\n   <w:UseAsianBreakRules/>\r\n   <w:DontGrowAutofit/>\r\n  </w:Compatibility>\r\n  <w:BrowserLevel>MicrosoftInternetExplorer4</w:BrowserLevel>\r\n </w:WordDocument>\r\n</xml><![endif]--><!--[if gte mso 9]><xml>\r\n <w:LatentStyles DefLockedState=\"false\" LatentStyleCount=\"156\">\r\n </w:LatentStyles>\r\n</xml><![endif]--><!--[if !mso]><object\r\n classid=\"clsid:38481807-CA0E-42D2-BF39-B33AF135CC4D\" id=ieooui></object>\r\n<style>\r\nst1\\:*{behavior:url(#ieooui) }\r\n</style>\r\n<![endif]--><style>\r\n<!--\r\n /* Font Definitions */\r\n @font-face\r\n	{font-family:Verdana;\r\n	panose-1:2 11 6 4 3 5 4 4 2 4;\r\n	mso-font-charset:0;\r\n	mso-generic-font-family:swiss;\r\n	mso-font-pitch:variable;\r\n	mso-font-signature:536871559 0 0 0 415 0;}\r\n /* Style Definitions */\r\n p.MsoNormal, li.MsoNormal, div.MsoNormal\r\n	{mso-style-parent:\"\";\r\n	margin:0cm;\r\n	margin-bottom:.0001pt;\r\n	mso-pagination:widow-orphan;\r\n	font-size:12.0pt;\r\n	font-family:\"Times New Roman\";\r\n	mso-fareast-font-family:\"Times New Roman\";}\r\n@page Section1\r\n	{size:612.0pt 792.0pt;\r\n	margin:70.85pt 3.0cm 70.85pt 3.0cm;\r\n	mso-header-margin:36.0pt;\r\n	mso-footer-margin:36.0pt;\r\n	mso-paper-source:0;}\r\ndiv.Section1\r\n	{page:Section1;}\r\n-->\r\n</style><!--[if gte mso 10]>\r\n<style>\r\n /* Style Definitions */\r\n table.MsoNormalTable\r\n	{mso-style-name:\"Tabla normal\";\r\n	mso-tstyle-rowband-size:0;\r\n	mso-tstyle-colband-size:0;\r\n	mso-style-noshow:yes;\r\n	mso-style-parent:\"\";\r\n	mso-padding-alt:0cm 5.4pt 0cm 5.4pt;\r\n	mso-para-margin:0cm;\r\n	mso-para-margin-bottom:.0001pt;\r\n	mso-pagination:widow-orphan;\r\n	font-size:10.0pt;\r\n	font-family:\"Times New Roman\";\r\n	mso-ansi-language:#0400;\r\n	mso-fareast-language:#0400;\r\n	mso-bidi-language:#0400;}\r\n</style>\r\n<![endif]-->\r\n\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><span style=\"font-size: 8.5pt; font-family: Verdana;\" lang=\"EN-GB\">I just thought you might like some feedback on our\r\ntrip. Everything went very smoothly and we all had a great time. I would like\r\nto thank you personally Chris for all your hard work and dedication you put\r\ninto organising the trip for all of us to the finest detail. We were a large\r\ngroup (8) ranging in age from 4 to 70 so we appreciated the great service from\r\nall of your staff and tour guides. &nbsp;The hotels and included meals were all\r\nfine. &nbsp;Everyone was very impressed with the local tour guide at Macchu\r\nPiccu (Fabricio). He did a great job and he was especially good with the young\r\nkids. I will be recommending Peru For Less to my friends back home in <st1:place w:st=\"on\"><st1:city w:st=\"on\">Sydney</st1:city></st1:place>. <o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><span style=\"font-size: 8.5pt; font-family: Verdana;\" lang=\"EN-GB\"><o:p>&nbsp;</o:p></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><i style=\"\"><span style=\"font-size: 8.5pt; font-family: Verdana;\" lang=\"EN-GB\"><br><o:p></o:p></span></i></p>\r\n\r\n                ','Thanks again for all of your help, <br/>\r\n\r\nChris <br/>\r\nSydney, New South Wales. Australia<br/>\r\nCuzco &amp; Machu Picchu','conolly.jpg','','',645,0,0,NULL,NULL,NULL),(416,1,'Dear Peru For Less','<meta http-equiv=\"Content-Type\" content=\"text/html; charset=utf-8\"><meta name=\"ProgId\" content=\"Word.Document\"><meta name=\"Generator\" content=\"Microsoft Word 11\"><meta name=\"Originator\" content=\"Microsoft Word 11\"><link rel=\"File-List\" href=\"file:///C:%5CDOCUME%7E1%5CADMINI%7E1%5CCONFIG%7E1%5CTemp%5Cmsohtml1%5C13%5Cclip_filelist.xml\"><o:smarttagtype namespaceuri=\"urn:schemas-microsoft-com:office:smarttags\" name=\"country-region\" downloadurl=\"http://www.5iantlavalamp.com/\"></o:smarttagtype><o:smarttagtype namespaceuri=\"urn:schemas-microsoft-com:office:smarttags\" name=\"place\" downloadurl=\"http://www.5iantlavalamp.com/\"></o:smarttagtype><!--[if gte mso 9]><xml>\r\n <w:WordDocument>\r\n  <w:View>Normal</w:View>\r\n  <w:Zoom>0</w:Zoom>\r\n  <w:HyphenationZone>21</w:HyphenationZone>\r\n  <w:PunctuationKerning/>\r\n  <w:ValidateAgainstSchemas/>\r\n  <w:SaveIfXMLInvalid>false</w:SaveIfXMLInvalid>\r\n  <w:IgnoreMixedContent>false</w:IgnoreMixedContent>\r\n  <w:AlwaysShowPlaceholderText>false</w:AlwaysShowPlaceholderText>\r\n  <w:Compatibility>\r\n   <w:BreakWrappedTables/>\r\n   <w:SnapToGridInCell/>\r\n   <w:WrapTextWithPunct/>\r\n   <w:UseAsianBreakRules/>\r\n   <w:DontGrowAutofit/>\r\n  </w:Compatibility>\r\n  <w:BrowserLevel>MicrosoftInternetExplorer4</w:BrowserLevel>\r\n </w:WordDocument>\r\n</xml><![endif]--><!--[if gte mso 9]><xml>\r\n <w:LatentStyles DefLockedState=\"false\" LatentStyleCount=\"156\">\r\n </w:LatentStyles>\r\n</xml><![endif]--><!--[if !mso]><object\r\n classid=\"clsid:38481807-CA0E-42D2-BF39-B33AF135CC4D\" id=ieooui></object>\r\n<style>\r\nst1\\:*{behavior:url(#ieooui) }\r\n</style>\r\n<![endif]--><style>\r\n<!--\r\n /* Font Definitions */\r\n @font-face\r\n	{font-family:Verdana;\r\n	panose-1:2 11 6 4 3 5 4 4 2 4;\r\n	mso-font-charset:0;\r\n	mso-generic-font-family:swiss;\r\n	mso-font-pitch:variable;\r\n	mso-font-signature:536871559 0 0 0 415 0;}\r\n /* Style Definitions */\r\n p.MsoNormal, li.MsoNormal, div.MsoNormal\r\n	{mso-style-parent:\"\";\r\n	margin:0cm;\r\n	margin-bottom:.0001pt;\r\n	mso-pagination:widow-orphan;\r\n	font-size:12.0pt;\r\n	font-family:\"Times New Roman\";\r\n	mso-fareast-font-family:\"Times New Roman\";}\r\n@page Section1\r\n	{size:612.0pt 792.0pt;\r\n	margin:70.85pt 3.0cm 70.85pt 3.0cm;\r\n	mso-header-margin:36.0pt;\r\n	mso-footer-margin:36.0pt;\r\n	mso-paper-source:0;}\r\ndiv.Section1\r\n	{page:Section1;}\r\n-->\r\n</style><!--[if gte mso 10]>\r\n<style>\r\n /* Style Definitions */\r\n table.MsoNormalTable\r\n	{mso-style-name:\"Tabla normal\";\r\n	mso-tstyle-rowband-size:0;\r\n	mso-tstyle-colband-size:0;\r\n	mso-style-noshow:yes;\r\n	mso-style-parent:\"\";\r\n	mso-padding-alt:0cm 5.4pt 0cm 5.4pt;\r\n	mso-para-margin:0cm;\r\n	mso-para-margin-bottom:.0001pt;\r\n	mso-pagination:widow-orphan;\r\n	font-size:10.0pt;\r\n	font-family:\"Times New Roman\";\r\n	mso-ansi-language:#0400;\r\n	mso-fareast-language:#0400;\r\n	mso-bidi-language:#0400;}\r\n</style>\r\n<![endif]-->\r\n\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><span style=\"font-size: 8.5pt; font-family: Verdana;\" lang=\"EN-GB\">Our trip was perfect and almost flawless! Machu Pichu\r\nwas challenging but we were taken care of so well by Urbano and crew. All of\r\nthe pick ups and transfers were seamless. The hotel in Aguas Caliente was\r\ndelightful; immaculate and the staff were friendly, accommodating and\r\npersonable. I will check to see if Ron has paid the extra $65- if not I will\r\npay pal the amount.<o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><span style=\"font-size: 8.5pt; font-family: Verdana;\" lang=\"EN-GB\">Thank you for all of your hard work, Abby. It was a\r\nforever memorable trip and <st1:place w:st=\"on\"><st1:country-region w:st=\"on\">Peru</st1:country-region></st1:place>\r\nfor Less organization skills made it so easy for us!<o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n\r\n                ','Clarkson, Kirby-Fouse, &amp; Appel Families <br/>\r\nChicago, IL, USA <br/>\r\nLima, Cuzco, Sacred Valley, Inca Trail, Machu Picchu and Puno','kirby-fouse.jpg','','',644,0,0,NULL,NULL,NULL),(417,1,'Dear Peru For Less','<meta http-equiv=\"Content-Type\" content=\"text/html; charset=utf-8\"><meta name=\"ProgId\" content=\"Word.Document\"><meta name=\"Generator\" content=\"Microsoft Word 11\"><meta name=\"Originator\" content=\"Microsoft Word 11\"><link rel=\"File-List\" href=\"file:///C:%5CDOCUME%7E1%5CADMINI%7E1%5CCONFIG%7E1%5CTemp%5Cmsohtml1%5C17%5Cclip_filelist.xml\"><o:smarttagtype namespaceuri=\"urn:schemas-microsoft-com:office:smarttags\" name=\"country-region\" downloadurl=\"http://www.5iantlavalamp.com/\"></o:smarttagtype><o:smarttagtype namespaceuri=\"urn:schemas-microsoft-com:office:smarttags\" name=\"place\" downloadurl=\"http://www.5iantlavalamp.com/\"></o:smarttagtype><!--[if gte mso 9]><xml>\r\n <w:WordDocument>\r\n  <w:View>Normal</w:View>\r\n  <w:Zoom>0</w:Zoom>\r\n  <w:HyphenationZone>21</w:HyphenationZone>\r\n  <w:PunctuationKerning/>\r\n  <w:ValidateAgainstSchemas/>\r\n  <w:SaveIfXMLInvalid>false</w:SaveIfXMLInvalid>\r\n  <w:IgnoreMixedContent>false</w:IgnoreMixedContent>\r\n  <w:AlwaysShowPlaceholderText>false</w:AlwaysShowPlaceholderText>\r\n  <w:Compatibility>\r\n   <w:BreakWrappedTables/>\r\n   <w:SnapToGridInCell/>\r\n   <w:WrapTextWithPunct/>\r\n   <w:UseAsianBreakRules/>\r\n   <w:DontGrowAutofit/>\r\n  </w:Compatibility>\r\n  <w:BrowserLevel>MicrosoftInternetExplorer4</w:BrowserLevel>\r\n </w:WordDocument>\r\n</xml><![endif]--><!--[if gte mso 9]><xml>\r\n <w:LatentStyles DefLockedState=\"false\" LatentStyleCount=\"156\">\r\n </w:LatentStyles>\r\n</xml><![endif]--><!--[if !mso]><object\r\n classid=\"clsid:38481807-CA0E-42D2-BF39-B33AF135CC4D\" id=ieooui></object>\r\n<style>\r\nst1\\:*{behavior:url(#ieooui) }\r\n</style>\r\n<![endif]--><style>\r\n<!--\r\n /* Font Definitions */\r\n @font-face\r\n	{font-family:Verdana;\r\n	panose-1:2 11 6 4 3 5 4 4 2 4;\r\n	mso-font-charset:0;\r\n	mso-generic-font-family:swiss;\r\n	mso-font-pitch:variable;\r\n	mso-font-signature:536871559 0 0 0 415 0;}\r\n /* Style Definitions */\r\n p.MsoNormal, li.MsoNormal, div.MsoNormal\r\n	{mso-style-parent:\"\";\r\n	margin:0cm;\r\n	margin-bottom:.0001pt;\r\n	mso-pagination:widow-orphan;\r\n	font-size:12.0pt;\r\n	font-family:\"Times New Roman\";\r\n	mso-fareast-font-family:\"Times New Roman\";}\r\n@page Section1\r\n	{size:612.0pt 792.0pt;\r\n	margin:70.85pt 3.0cm 70.85pt 3.0cm;\r\n	mso-header-margin:36.0pt;\r\n	mso-footer-margin:36.0pt;\r\n	mso-paper-source:0;}\r\ndiv.Section1\r\n	{page:Section1;}\r\n-->\r\n</style><!--[if gte mso 10]>\r\n<style>\r\n /* Style Definitions */\r\n table.MsoNormalTable\r\n	{mso-style-name:\"Tabla normal\";\r\n	mso-tstyle-rowband-size:0;\r\n	mso-tstyle-colband-size:0;\r\n	mso-style-noshow:yes;\r\n	mso-style-parent:\"\";\r\n	mso-padding-alt:0cm 5.4pt 0cm 5.4pt;\r\n	mso-para-margin:0cm;\r\n	mso-para-margin-bottom:.0001pt;\r\n	mso-pagination:widow-orphan;\r\n	font-size:10.0pt;\r\n	font-family:\"Times New Roman\";\r\n	mso-ansi-language:#0400;\r\n	mso-fareast-language:#0400;\r\n	mso-bidi-language:#0400;}\r\n</style>\r\n<![endif]--><span style=\"font-size: 8.5pt; font-family: Verdana;\" lang=\"EN-GB\">Thank\r\nyou for following up with me.&nbsp; I had a FABULOUS time at Lake Sandoval\r\nLodge in Puerto Maldonado.&nbsp; My tour guide, Paul, was wonderful.&nbsp; He\r\nwas very knowledgeable, friendly, and helpful.&nbsp; The lodge was well kept\r\nup, and very comfortable.&nbsp; They kept us very occupied.&nbsp; The food was\r\nalso very good.<br>\r\n&nbsp;<br>\r\nThanks again for all your help getting me on this trip.&nbsp; I am hooked and\r\nhope to do it again...but for much longer than a weekend.&nbsp; I would love to\r\nsee all of <st1:country-region w:st=\"on\"><st1:place w:st=\"on\">Peru</st1:place></st1:country-region>...it\r\nis so beautiful!<br style=\"\">\r\n<!--[if !supportLineBreakNewLine]--><br style=\"\">\r\n<!--[endif]--></span>                ','Tammy <br/>\r\n\r\nTexas, USA <br/>\r\nPuerto Maldonado','eveland.jpg','','',643,0,0,NULL,NULL,NULL),(418,1,'Hi Rylee,','<meta http-equiv=\"Content-Type\" content=\"text/html; charset=utf-8\"><meta name=\"ProgId\" content=\"Word.Document\"><meta name=\"Generator\" content=\"Microsoft Word 11\"><meta name=\"Originator\" content=\"Microsoft Word 11\"><link rel=\"File-List\" href=\"file:///C:%5CDOCUME%7E1%5CADMINI%7E1%5CCONFIG%7E1%5CTemp%5Cmsohtml1%5C22%5Cclip_filelist.xml\"><o:smarttagtype namespaceuri=\"urn:schemas-microsoft-com:office:smarttags\" name=\"country-region\" downloadurl=\"http://www.5iantlavalamp.com/\"></o:smarttagtype><o:smarttagtype namespaceuri=\"urn:schemas-microsoft-com:office:smarttags\" name=\"place\" downloadurl=\"http://www.5iantlavalamp.com/\"></o:smarttagtype><!--[if gte mso 9]><xml>\r\n <w:WordDocument>\r\n  <w:View>Normal</w:View>\r\n  <w:Zoom>0</w:Zoom>\r\n  <w:HyphenationZone>21</w:HyphenationZone>\r\n  <w:PunctuationKerning/>\r\n  <w:ValidateAgainstSchemas/>\r\n  <w:SaveIfXMLInvalid>false</w:SaveIfXMLInvalid>\r\n  <w:IgnoreMixedContent>false</w:IgnoreMixedContent>\r\n  <w:AlwaysShowPlaceholderText>false</w:AlwaysShowPlaceholderText>\r\n  <w:Compatibility>\r\n   <w:BreakWrappedTables/>\r\n   <w:SnapToGridInCell/>\r\n   <w:WrapTextWithPunct/>\r\n   <w:UseAsianBreakRules/>\r\n   <w:DontGrowAutofit/>\r\n  </w:Compatibility>\r\n  <w:BrowserLevel>MicrosoftInternetExplorer4</w:BrowserLevel>\r\n </w:WordDocument>\r\n</xml><![endif]--><!--[if gte mso 9]><xml>\r\n <w:LatentStyles DefLockedState=\"false\" LatentStyleCount=\"156\">\r\n </w:LatentStyles>\r\n</xml><![endif]--><!--[if !mso]><object\r\n classid=\"clsid:38481807-CA0E-42D2-BF39-B33AF135CC4D\" id=ieooui></object>\r\n<style>\r\nst1\\:*{behavior:url(#ieooui) }\r\n</style>\r\n<![endif]--><style>\r\n<!--\r\n /* Font Definitions */\r\n @font-face\r\n	{font-family:Verdana;\r\n	panose-1:2 11 6 4 3 5 4 4 2 4;\r\n	mso-font-charset:0;\r\n	mso-generic-font-family:swiss;\r\n	mso-font-pitch:variable;\r\n	mso-font-signature:536871559 0 0 0 415 0;}\r\n /* Style Definitions */\r\n p.MsoNormal, li.MsoNormal, div.MsoNormal\r\n	{mso-style-parent:\"\";\r\n	margin:0cm;\r\n	margin-bottom:.0001pt;\r\n	mso-pagination:widow-orphan;\r\n	font-size:12.0pt;\r\n	font-family:\"Times New Roman\";\r\n	mso-fareast-font-family:\"Times New Roman\";}\r\n@page Section1\r\n	{size:612.0pt 792.0pt;\r\n	margin:70.85pt 3.0cm 70.85pt 3.0cm;\r\n	mso-header-margin:36.0pt;\r\n	mso-footer-margin:36.0pt;\r\n	mso-paper-source:0;}\r\ndiv.Section1\r\n	{page:Section1;}\r\n-->\r\n</style><!--[if gte mso 10]>\r\n<style>\r\n /* Style Definitions */\r\n table.MsoNormalTable\r\n	{mso-style-name:\"Tabla normal\";\r\n	mso-tstyle-rowband-size:0;\r\n	mso-tstyle-colband-size:0;\r\n	mso-style-noshow:yes;\r\n	mso-style-parent:\"\";\r\n	mso-padding-alt:0cm 5.4pt 0cm 5.4pt;\r\n	mso-para-margin:0cm;\r\n	mso-para-margin-bottom:.0001pt;\r\n	mso-pagination:widow-orphan;\r\n	font-size:10.0pt;\r\n	font-family:\"Times New Roman\";\r\n	mso-ansi-language:#0400;\r\n	mso-fareast-language:#0400;\r\n	mso-bidi-language:#0400;}\r\n</style>\r\n<![endif]-->\r\n\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-size: 8.5pt; font-family: Verdana;\" lang=\"EN-GB\">anywhere. I\r\nwas very impressed and pleased with your agency.<o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-size: 8.5pt; font-family: Verdana;\" lang=\"EN-GB\">Everyone\r\nwas on time, pleasant to deal with, and worked very hard to make everything go\r\nwell for us. We were escorted to our hotels and the bus stations, and the\r\nagents waited for us if we got in late and stayed with us until we were out of\r\ntown. Our group was especially amazed by the luxury of the Cruz del Sur bus\r\ncompany. Fancier than first class on an airplane! Our hotels were great and\r\nvery unique. It was fun anticipating what the next one would be like. I think\r\nour group all felt like the Uros Floating Islands were the most fascinating\r\nplace we went.<o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-size: 8.5pt; font-family: Verdana;\" lang=\"EN-GB\"><o:p>&nbsp;</o:p></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align: justify;\"><b style=\"\"><span style=\"font-size: 8.5pt; font-family: Verdana;\" lang=\"EN-GB\">I enjoy telling people about our trip and will certainly recommend <st1:place w:st=\"on\"><st1:country-region w:st=\"on\">Peru</st1:country-region></st1:place>\r\nFor Less and you.<o:p></o:p></span></b></p>\r\n\r\n                ','Sincerely, <br/>\r\n\r\nBecki <br/>\r\nLima, Arequipa,\r\nCuzco and Machu Picchu','wallies.jpg','','',642,0,0,NULL,NULL,NULL),(422,1,'Dear Peru For Less','<p>\r\nIt was a magical and adventurous trip more than we ever imagined. Thank you JP and associates for making our dream come true. The trip was well organized from beginning to the end and local\r\ntour guides were friendly, courteous and knowledgeable, especially our Colca Canyon tour guide, Omar, who was very accommodating when I got high altitude sickness. Also the hotel we stayed in Colca Canyon: they let me use their oxygen to help my sickness. Machu Picchu... what can I say...out of this world! What a peaceful, magical place it is! We will be back to Peru soon.     \r\n\r\n</p>','Satsuki and Lloyd <br/>\r\nNorth Hollywood, California <br/>\r\nLima, Nazca, Arequipa, Cuzco Machu Picchu\r\n','satsuki-lloyd.jpg','','',653,0,0,NULL,NULL,NULL),(423,1,'','I found Peru for Less very accommodating in assisting me with booking a last minute add on trip to Peru.  Chris was very knowledgeable and extremely responsive and helpful.  I would not hesitate to use them for my clients again.','Linda  (Your Travel Center) <br/>\r\nSanta Barbera, CA, USA <br/>\r\nCuzco, Sacred Valley and Machu Picchu \r\n\r\n','kavanagh.jpg','','',654,0,0,NULL,NULL,NULL),(424,1,'Deanna,','<p>Our trip was great.  All the transfers and guides worked out wonderfully!</p>','Thank you, <br/>\r\nRon and Jane <br/>\r\nJuniper, FL, USA <br/>\r\nChiclayo and Trujillo\r\n','wiewora.jpg','Ron and Jane Wiewora','',655,0,0,NULL,NULL,NULL),(425,1,'Dear Peru For Less','<p>The trip in itself was a very nice experience.  This was the first time we visited a South American country.  In that perspective, we did a lot of research on the internet, prior to contacting a travel agency, to pin point the main sites we wanted to visit.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>From all the tour packages we reviewed offered by Canadian and US companies, Peru for Less was the one that gave the most flexibility.  The possibility to add days at specific sites in addition to being able to start the trip any day of the year took out the \"boxed in\" feeling of deals from competitors.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>With respect to the rest of the trip, we appreciated the assiduity of the drivers and guides whenever a transfer was in the schedule i.e. between the airport and hotel, etc.  </p>\r\n\r\n<p>Almost all the hotels were nice in their own way. The hotels in Yukay and Arqueologo, in Cuzco, were beautifully set.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>The quality of the guides, for the tours, exceeded our expectations.  They had knowledge and were willing to answer all questions that were asked.  We also appreciated the fact that many tours were one on one and that the rest did not exceed a total of three families (other than Machu Picchu).</p>\r\n\r\n<p>The food in Peru was good.  Fresh papaya, orange and pineapple juice was always on our menu. The variety of meat and fish in the menus of restaurants was also pleasant.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Looking back at all that we saw, all that touched us, the experiences and cultural immersion that occurred, we can say that this was a beautiful and enriching trip.  Peru for Less and its affiliates permitted us to enjoy the trip by being present when needed and offering staff with experience and knowledge.  To that effect, we don`t hesitate to refer your company to colleagues.</p>\r\n','Regards, <br/>\r\n\r\nMartin <br/>\r\nMontreal/Quebec/ Canada <br/>\r\nLima, Ica, Nazca, Arequipa, Cuzco, Puno\r\n','kulczyk.jpg','Martin Kulczyk','',656,0,0,NULL,NULL,NULL),(426,1,'Kristina,','<p>My trip to Peru was wonderful. I could never have planned out what they had for me. I was hesitant at first, but from the beginning, when they picked me up at the airport, and to the end, PFL was always there making sure everything was on schedule and to my liking. I all most felt like they were my parents keeping a watchful eye on me every step of the way. Traveling alone can be somewhat dangerous but I always felt safe in their hands. </p>\r\n<p>\r\nAnd the hotels they booked me in were top caliber at low prices. Tours we\'re great too. PFL is highly recommended. </p>\r\n','Winston <br/>\r\nChicago, Il. USA <br/>\r\nCuzco, Machu Picchu and Inca Trail\r\n','chueng-winston.jpg','Winston Chueng','',657,0,0,NULL,NULL,NULL),(427,1,'Kelly, ','<p>Sorry I didn\'t get back to you right away - it\'s taken a few days to decompress from my whirlwind trip to Peru!  </p>\r\n<p>\r\nI had a wonderful time exploring the ruins of Machu Picchu with my guide Fabrizio (I think that\'s his name!).  The best part about having a private guide was that he was gracious enough to take plenty of photos of me, since I was traveling alone.  \r\n</p>\r\n<p>\r\nThe hotel was phenomenal. I loved soaking in the whirlpool tub, then warming my bones in front of the wood burning fireplace. The staff were attentive and gracious, the breakfast delicious.\r\n</p>\r\n<p>\r\nTracy was right on time to meet me at Maximo Nivel with my travel documents, and I even bumped into her in Cuzco later that night. She\'ll be happy to know that I made it to Machu Picchu, even though I started celebrating my birthday a little early ;). I followed her advice and climbed Putu Cusi my second day in Aguas Calientes - a difficult climb, but a rewarding trip.\r\n</p>\r\n<p>\r\nThanks for coordinating everything on such short notice - I had a blast.\r\n</p>','Sara <br/>\r\nNew Hope, PA USA <br/>\r\nCuzco, Machu Picchu\r\n','dawson-sara.jpg','Sara Dawson','',658,0,0,NULL,NULL,NULL),(428,1,'Dear Peru For Less','<p>We want to thank you for the wonderful attention we received from your group on our recent trip to Peru.  It was so wonderful seeing your people greet us as we stepped off the planes and knew that we would arrive at the right hotels with all our bags in tow.  Everyone was so friendly and so helpful. We could not ask for better service.\r\n</p>\r\n<p>\r\nWe especially appreciated your guides who were so informative and so patient with us when we wanted to stop and take pictures and just catch our breath.\r\n</p>\r\n<p>\r\nAttached is a photo of the 6 of us that shows just how much we enjoyed our trip and how appreciative we are of \"Peru For Less\" for making it a memorable experience.\r\n</p>','Walter, Mary, Otis, Gretchen, Robert, and Rubyetta <br/>\r\nSouthlake, TX USA <br/>\r\nLima, Cuzco, Sacred Valley and Machu Picchu\r\n','braddock-smith.jpg','Walter and Mary Braddock','',659,0,0,NULL,NULL,NULL),(429,1,'','Lynda and I could not be more pleased with Peru for Less and the staff. Peru was much more than we expected and the same could be said for the staff and itinerary provided by Peru for Less.  We were a little concerned using an internet travel site but could not have been happier with the results. All points of destination were met by friendly and informative staff. Advice on side trips, the best places to stay, eat and shop were \"right on\".  \r\n \r\nPeru for Less staff could not be more accommodating. For example, I left my wedding ring at a hotel in Lima and did not realize it until I arrived in Cuzco.  Before I returned home, I was met by Kristina at the airport in Lima with my ring. It was such a relief to have the ring returned to me and she assured that an otherwise fantastic trip did not turn out to be a disaster.\r\n \r\nKristina, Allison and the many drivers that shuttled us from place to place were amazing and made this trip one that will provide lasting memories.\r\n \r\nThank you, Peru for Less.  We are already beginning to look to you for future trips.  \r\n','Paula <br/>\r\nRancho Palos Verdes, California, USA <br/>\r\nLima and Cuzco\r\n','petrotta.jpg','Paula Petrotta','',660,0,0,NULL,NULL,NULL),(430,1,'Riley,','<p>Where to begin? We had an absolutely marvelous trip. Peru is a beautiful country and what could be more awe-inspiring than Machu Picchu? The trip planning was flawless and it was so nice to get a call each night confirming the next day\'s plans. We were greeted on time at the airport and for each tour by one of your staff members. Kristina was a wonderful trip coordinator and we enjoyed all our tour guides and drivers: Blas, Max, Mary, Fabricio and Kristina.  Even when we wanted to add another tour at the last minute, Peru For Less came through.  I will most definitely recommend the company to anyone I know. The price for the tour was the best around and the value was unbeatable. </p><p>\r\nThanks so much for such a wonderful trip.  The memories will last forever.  \r\n</p>','Cindy, Dale, Cleone, Mark, Donna, Ray, Sharon, and Thomas <br/>\r\nRapid City, SD, USA <br/>\r\nCuzco, Sacred Valley, Machu Picchu\r\n','hansen-barck.jpg','Cindy and Dale Hansen','',661,0,0,NULL,NULL,NULL),(431,1,'Dear Peru For Less','<p>Overall, I had an awesome trip! I successfully finished the Salkantay Trek, though I had \r\naltitude sickness the first day and was really sore by the end of the trek. Salkantay is a great alternative route to the Inca trail and has some stunning views of snow capped mountains, \r\nrain forests and the experience of meeting locals in remote villages. \r\n</p>\r\n<p>\r\nGuido our guide and the entire crew at the trek were the best. I would definitely recommend it to all my friends and family. Special thanks to Allison who met me at the Cuzco airport! She helped me with my baggage delay problems and with all the shopping in Cuzco before the trek. The tour guides for Cuzco city tour, Sacred Valley tour were great. \r\n</p>\r\n<p>\r\nI really liked the Hotel in Cuzco, Casa De Campo. It has a great view of Cuzco city! \r\n</p>\r\n<p>\r\nThank you so much for arranging everything and I look forward to visiting Peru again soon! \r\n<p>','Regards, <br/>\r\nMythili <br/>\r\nNew York, New York, USA <br/>\r\nCuzco, Salkantay Trek\r\n\r\n','madhira.jpg','Mythili Madhira','',662,0,0,NULL,NULL,NULL),(432,1,'Dear Rylee','<p>My friends and I want to thank all the Peru for less team for the wonderful trip we had to Peru. Everything was very well planned, always on time to meet us and to take us for all the places we visited. The guides were all very good, always helping us in everything. They were very friendly and doing everything so we could feel well.\r\n</p>\r\n<p>\r\nI especially would like to send our gratitude to Juan Carlos, Mariluz and Tracy in Cuzco, Miguel in Lima, Angel in Machu Picchu and Fino in Puerto Maldonado/posada Amazonas. They were all marvelous.\r\n</p>\r\n<p>\r\nI sent you a photo of us in Machu Picchu and you can see we are all happy. We did the trip we wanted. We have seen the places we wished to visit and everything was organized in such a way that always went very well, without any problems. I will strongly recommend Peru for less to my friends.\r\n</p>\r\n<p>\r\nThank you all for our marvelous vacations.\r\n</p>','Best regards <br/>\r\nMargarida Lima <br/>\r\nLisbon, <br/>\r\nLima, Cuzco, Machu Picchu and Puerto Maldonado\r\n','lima-margarida.jpg','Margarida Lima','',663,0,0,NULL,NULL,NULL),(433,1,'Dear Peru For Less','<p>Wow, what a trip!  We\'re back in the US now from our fabulous trip to Peru. We have lots of great pictures and lots of wonderful memories.  We take trips regularly, but this one to Peru is definitely one of the best on the list.  \r\n </p>\r\n<p>\r\nOur itinerary was well designed with a good amount time seeing the nature, modern, colonial and, of course, ancient Peru.  Lima, with its cosmopolitan and colonial facades was a great starting point.  Miguel was a great Lima city tour guide.  His knowledge about everything Peruvian, and even Latin American was outstanding. We felt very comfortable in Peru from the get-go as Miguel greeted us at the airport.  By the way, the Radisson Decapolis in Miraflores was a top-notch hip hotel. The sushi-fusion bar is classy!\r\n </p>\r\n<p>\r\nDiving into Cuzco\'s history, ancient streets and sidewalks was, of course, one of the highlights of the journey. We adapted smoothly to the high elevation of the city, and started enjoying the city and its surroundings from the first day. The folklore dance program in the evening is a must in order to learn about the different traditions and dances of the area.\r\n </p>\r\n<p>\r\nMachu Piccu goes without saying - is truly one of the wonders of the world. Pictures can\'t describe the awe and majestic views and hiking in the area.  I would say the round trip train to Machu Piccu was also reminiscent of Hiram Bingham\'s exploratory trips to the area, but in the comfort of a full view Vistadome train!\r\n </p>\r\n<p>\r\nOur final leg into Puno and Lake Titicaca, the highest navigable lake in the world, and the floating islands of Uros, were something we had dreamt about for a long time.  Once we set foot on the floating islands, and started interacting and talking to the Indian inhabitants, and even had a conversation inside their house, we suddenly felt like we were taken back hundreds of years!\r\n </p>\r\n<p>\r\nChris, we would like to personally and sincerely thank you for organizing our trip to Peru.  It was well planned, with great efficiency and accuracy.  We felt at ease as soon as we set foot in Lima from our international flight. We specifically appreciate you calling us and checking on us several times during our trip in order to make sure we were doing well, and that everything was taken care of. That is the true meaning of personal customer service, excellent job! We would also like to say hi to everybody at Peru For Less who helped us make this trip a memorable one.\r\n</p>','Regards, <br/>\r\nBijan <br/>\r\nLong Beach, CA <br/>\r\nLima, Cuzco, Machu Picchu, Lake Titicaca \r\n','downletti.jpg','Bijan Dowlati ','',664,0,0,NULL,NULL,NULL),(434,1,'Dear Peru For Less','<p>Let\'s admit that Belgium is pretty far away from Peru and from your U.S. based offices. Furthermore, the only contacts I had with you were per email and a couple of phone calls. Thus, to some extent, I was taking a risk: would your services and advises meet our expectations?\r\nWell, they were even better! We had a really great trip, whether in the Amazonian forest, the Sacred Valley, Cuzco or the Machu Picchu site, and finally the wonderful Galapagos Islands.  During our whole trip, at every place, our transfers were perfectly organized, we were met by pleasant and kind people and we had excellent guides.\r\n</p>\r\n<p>\r\nA special mention of excellence to two people: our guide, Edgar, in the Sacred Valley. This guy was not only a well of science, but had this unique ability of transmitting both his knowledge of the Inca culture and his passion for archeology. And then, the adorable Allison from your office in Cuzco: we were met by her upon our arrival in Cuzco airport, coming from Puerto Maldonado. When we reached our hotel in the Sacred Valley, I realized that I had left my Blackberry on the plane! I called Allison and she told me that she would do everything she could to recuperate it. To make a long story of outstanding services short, a couple of days later, after our visit of Machu Picchu, she accompanied me to the LAN airlines counter where my PDA was handed over to me.\r\n</p>\r\n<p>\r\nWe were a party of five, away for 16 days in South-America: we did not experience anything but enchantment!  My family joins me in congratulating you and your staff for such a high level of professionalism, efficiency and kindness!\r\n</p>','Best regards, <br/>\r\n\r\nBenoit and Monique, with Rapha&euml;l, Frederic and Violaine <br/>\r\nAntwerp, Belgium <br/>\r\nLima, Sacred Valley, Cuzco, Machu Picchu, Puerto Maldonado, Quito, Galapagos\r\n','antwerp.jpg','Benoit and Monique','',665,0,0,NULL,NULL,NULL),(435,1,'Kristina,','<p>In July my husband and I took a trip to Peru. We love traveling the world and almost always plan and journey on our own. This year we searched the internet and found several companies who offered many variations on travel plans through Peru. Why did we choose Latin America For Less? Were there prices competitive? Yes, but equal to many other companies. We chose Latin America For Less, simply because of a first phone conversation with Kristina Rudge. She phoned us back within minutes of our call, and was so helpful and patient that we felt confident we would have the personal assistance we needed. \r\n</p>\r\n<p>\r\nWe were right about Kristina and the rest of the staff at Latin America For Less. Kristina and I organized the trip together via email. She was prompt in her responses, on target with suggestions and above all honest about the trip. She gave us advice, made valid suggestions and sent us paperwork in a most timely fashion.\r\n</p>\r\n<p>\r\nSo we found ourselves with all the paperwork, airline tickets and fully packed suitcases. I wouldn\'t be completely honest if I said we weren\'t nervous about the trip. Would things be as promised? Would we be picked up at each location? This trip included 3 internal flights and several bus and car trips. \r\n</p>\r\n<p>\r\nWe arrived late evening in Lima and waiting for us was a charming young man who had all of our travel documents, accompanied us to our hotel and spent about 45 minutes going through our itinerary and answering questions. This is how it went at every step of our voyage. We were met, escorted, assisted, doted on and had all of our needs met.\r\n</p>\r\n<p>\r\nWas everything perfect? Not completely. My husband suffered from fairly severe altitude sickness. We even had to change some of our plans to accommodate this. The staff at Latin America For Less couldn\'t be more helpful changing arrangements at the last minute.\r\n</p>\r\n<p>\r\nWe can\'t wait to travel again to South America and will, of course, use Latin America For Less. \r\nThis is a really great agency and everyone who we dealt with there was kind, smart and helpful.\r\n</p>','Nancy <br/>\r\nNew Jersey, US <br/>\r\nCuzco, Machu Picchu, Puno, Lake Titicaca and Puerto Maldonado\r\n','rossi-nancy.jpg','Nancy Rossi','',666,0,0,NULL,NULL,NULL),(436,1,'Dear Peru For Less','I had a wonderful trip with many exciting stories to tell!','Thanks,\r\n\r\nMary <br/>\r\nPeachtree City, GA, USA\r\n<br/>Lima, Cuzco, Machu Picchu, Puerto Maldonado\r\n\r\n','','','',142,0,0,NULL,NULL,NULL),(437,1,'Rylee,','<p>          \r\nI just wanted to let you know that we had a wonderful time in Peru. Thank you so much for organizing this last minute excursion for us. You were very helpful as was all the staff in Cuzco. </p>\r\n \r\n<p>We very much enjoyed the trip, the attention was wonderful.</p>\r\n','Ruben <br/>\r\nFrederick, MD, USA\r\n<br/>Cuzco and Machu Picchu\r\n','','','',144,0,0,NULL,NULL,NULL),(438,1,'Dear Peru For Less','Thank you for your-mail. Sorry we could not write you back sooner. We certainly had a wonderful time in Peru. As a matter of fact, we are thinking of visiting Peru again. Thank you again for an amazing trip.','Satsuki <br/>\r\n\r\nNorth Hollywood, California\r\n<br/>Lima, Nazca, Arequipa, Cuzco, Machu Picchu\r\n','','','',146,0,0,NULL,NULL,NULL),(439,1,'Dear Peru For Less','Thank you for everything! I am looking forward to another trip very soon! Tracey was awesome and the trip was well planned!','Mike <br/>\r\nNew York, USA\r\n<br/>Cuzco and Inca Trail to Machu Picchu\r\n','','','',148,0,0,NULL,NULL,NULL),(440,1,'Dear Peru For Less','<p>We had a great trip in Peru! Thanks for coordinating this. Our guide, Edwin, was awesome. I wanted to send him a thank you note but lost his address on the way back to the United States. Can you please either give him my email address or send me his contact info to facilitate this.</p>\r\n\r\nThanks!\r\n<br>','Andy <br/>\r\nOhio, USA\r\n<br/>Salkantay trail\r\n','','','',150,0,0,NULL,NULL,NULL),(441,1,'Dear Peru For Less','<p>Our trip in Peru was amazing! All tours, guides and services were great and on time. Thank you and all the Peru For Less staff for a wonderful experience.</p>\r\n \r\n','Best regards,\r\n \r\nKim <br/>\r\nCalifornia, USA\r\n<br/>Cuzco, Machu Picchu, Puerto Maldonado\r\n','','','',152,0,0,NULL,NULL,NULL),(442,1,'Dear Peru For Less','<p>The trip was awesome as usual. Your company is very professional as well as friendly.</p>\r\n \r\n<p>All I can think about (besides how great this trip was) is planning my next one. I am even considering using Argentina For Less, since I have had so much success with you.</p>\r\n \r\n<p>Thanks again for all your great work!</p>\r\n\r\n','Cindy <br/>\r\nCalifornia, USA\r\n<br/>Arequipa, Puno and Lima\r\n','','','',154,0,0,NULL,NULL,NULL),(443,1,'Hello Rylee,','<p>We absolutely loved our experience and time in Peru! Machu Picchu was beautiful and fascinating. It was such a unique experience and one that will impact me forever. I want to commend the staff that worked with us from Peru For Lessâ?¦ beginning with you, Rylee. You made things come together so well! We have already recommended to others to use Peru For Less when traveling to your beautiful country. </p>\r\n<p>\r\nThank you for putting us in the Hotel Ninos. It was charming and delightful! The staff there were warm and helpful. We loved the history of how the hotel started (if you aren\'t familiar with it, it would be worth learning about because it is a beautiful story). </p>\r\n<p>\r\nI am sure that Jay will want to spend some time giving a testimonial and sharing his insights and experience with you. I wanted you to know how pleased I was and how very appreciative I was of your efforts and those of the staff and guides!\r\n</p>','Many thanks,\r\nSherry <br/>\r\nJackson, Mississippi, USA\r\n<br/>Cuzco and Machu Picchu\r\n','','','',157,0,0,NULL,NULL,NULL),(444,1,'Rylee,','<p>Thank you for your email and checking in. I apologize for the delayed response, but Aimee and I have gone straight back to work and school. We did have a wonderful time in Peru. Thank you for all of your assistance in the planning process. You were great in answering all of our questions quickly. We thoroughly enjoyed our tours and hotels, everything went smooth, and there are really nothing but incredible things to say of Peru. It\'s a beautiful country and we enjoyed every moment. </p>\r\n<p>\r\nThank you for arranging everything for us. </p>\r\n','Ryan <br/>\r\nSan Francisco, CA, USA\r\n<br/>Arequipa, Cuzco, Machu Picchu and Puerto Maldonado\r\n','','','',156,0,0,NULL,NULL,NULL),(445,1,'Hi Rylee, ','<p>Sorry I haven\'t gotten back to you sooner. It was my friend Jennifer who got sick, but thank you for your concern. It was kind of a nightmare for a few days, but everything turned out fine, and now we have quite a story to tell. I will look through my pictures soon. I do have to say that Allison was unbelievable. I don\'t know what Jennifer and I would have done without her there. Is there someone in Cuzco I can write to so that her boss or someone knows how wonderful she is? All of the other tours and services provided were great. Jennifer just must have eaten something that made her ill along the way. We did have a fabulous time and didn\'t let the sickness get us down. Thank you so much for all of your assistance in the planning process. Everything was great. We loved all of our hotels, tours, guides, etc. Please let Allison know how much we appreciated her assistance in Cuzco. She was so wonderful. Thank you again for everything. I will certainly recommend Peru For Less to my friends and family.</p>\r\n<p>\r\n\r\nMany thanks,</p>\r\n','Jenna <br/>\r\nChicago, IL USA\r\n<br/>Cuzco, Inca Trail to Machu Picchu\r\n','','','',159,0,0,NULL,NULL,NULL),(446,1,'Hi Deanna,','<p>I had a really good time in Peru, both in my volunteer part of it and also with traveling with my sisters. The highlight was Macchu Picchu and climbing Huaynapicchu. Overall we were happy with Peru For Less. Winnie and Heidi had two good tour guides in Cuzco and Sacred Valley. We had a good time at Reserva Amazonica besides the crazy cold weather - but the lodging and food and staff there were great! \r\n</p>\r\n<p>\r\nI really appreciate your help and patience, Deanna, with all the pre-trip arrangements! That really made my job in organizing this trip for my sisters easy!\r\n</p>','Thank you.\r\nHolly <br/>\r\nSeattle, WA USA\r\n<br/>Cuzco and Puerto Maldonado\r\n','','','',161,0,0,NULL,NULL,NULL),(447,1,'Dear Peru For Less','<p>Everything went well on the trip.  All your reps were right on time, very knowledgeable and were a pleasure to deal with.  Every plane and train was right on time with no luggage problems.</p>\r\n <p>\r\nPeru is a lovely country and the people are very friendly. We enjoyed every aspect of the trip.\r\nAll the sights were just as we anticipated and more. Good thing we didn\'t wait much longer as the trip is quite strenuous at times for a 65 yr old guy like me. Thought I was in pretty good shape until a few of those up and down tours of ruins in the thin air, but it was never a real problem.  \r\n </p>\r\n<p>\r\nAll the hotels were great. The Pozo Del Cielo in Chivay was probably our favorite. They placed hot water bottles under the bed covers while we were at dinner. The dining and bar areas are great and the setting is just beautiful.\r\n </p>\r\n<p>\r\nThe hotel Andina in Aguas Caliente was interesting to say the least. The new section of town is built along the lower rail road track. The train runs just in front of the hotel entrance, but this was not a problem and the trains did not run at night. Work is in progress on a walkway along the track. I would definitely recommend this hotel. \r\n  </p>\r\n<p>\r\nAll the tours were great with very knowledgeable guides. The second part of the Lake Titicaca excursion to Taquile made for a long day on the boat. I think given the choice we probably would have only done the Uros floating islands which we really enjoyed. \r\n</p>\r\n<p> \r\nOverall we really enjoyed the trip and doing business with you. Maybe someday we\'ll try another country with you.\r\n</p>','Thanks again,\r\nJohn &amp; Linda <br/>\r\nEl Paso, TX, USA\r\n<br/>Lima, Arequipa, Colca Canyon, Cuzco, Machu Picchu, Puno\r\n','','','',163,0,0,NULL,NULL,NULL),(448,1,'Good Morning Rylee,','<p>We had a wonderful time in Peru and found the service provided by Peru for Less to be more than we expected and would be happy to recommend. We were met at all the appropriate locations, provided transportation, given explanations or instructions and had all our questions answered. Flawless. </p>\r\n<p>\r\n  \r\nWe truly enjoyed the experience in Peru and your company were a fabulous help in planning and the trip was a total success. Thank you for all of your patience, feedback and help in organizing our trip. \r\n</p>','Sincerely.\r\n \r\nTodd <br/>\r\nDeltona, FL, USA\r\n<br/>\r\nLima, Cuzco, Machu Picchu, Puerto Maldonado\r\n','','','',165,0,0,NULL,NULL,NULL),(449,1,'Hi Rylee:','<p>I just wanted to drop you a quick email to say thank you for everything. Allison was awesome in Cuzco. Thank you. And, thank you for all of your quick responses and your help in planning this special trip for my son, daughter and I. I know it was last minute, but you were fabulous. Thank you for making it so.</p>','Thanks again,\r\n \r\nRud <br/>\r\nNashville, TN, USA\r\n<br/>Cuzco and Machu Picchu\r\n','','','',167,0,0,NULL,NULL,NULL),(450,1,'Hi Rylee ','<p>Our trip was totally awesome! We had a fantastic time. Thank you so much!</p>\r\n<p>\r\nThe trip was just perfect: everything went like clockwork, the tour guides were brilliant, the lady that met me at the airport from PFL. I canâ??t remember her name right now, but she was very nice and kind and helpful. The hotel was perfect. We were so thrilled.  \r\n</p>\r\n<p>\r\nI understand you also organize trips to Brazil. In the next 8-12 months (once I have saved a little money) I would like to travel to Brazil, specifically Rio and perhaps the Amazon jungle. If you can help with this I will definitely use your guys again; your guidance will be appreciated. \r\n</p>\r\n<p>\r\nAll your help and guidance is so appreciated by me. You answered all my questions and were very supportive and helpful. Thank you. \r\n</p>\r\n<p>\r\nThank you! We had the best vacation and love Peru!\r\n</p>','Angeline <br/>\r\nWeston, FL, USA\r\n<br/>Lima, Cuzco, Machu Picchu\r\n','','','',169,0,0,NULL,NULL,NULL),(451,1,'Hi Rylee!','<p>Machu Picchu was amazing. All our connections went well and the tours were great. It was beautiful and a wonderful experience. It was great having everything taken care of & not having to worry about the little details. All we had to know is where to stand and what time and our representative/guide for the day would pick us up. Everyone was so helpful. Thank you so much for helping us put this together and getting us ready for this.  \r\n </p>\r\n<p>\r\nI\'m already thinking about where to go next and hoping I can work with you or get a referral from you.\r\n</p>','Melody <br/>\r\nNew York, USA\r\n<br/>Cuzco, Inca Trail to Machu Picchu, \r\n','','','',171,0,0,NULL,NULL,NULL),(452,1,'Dear Kristina, ','<p>Sorry it has taken me awhile to get back to you!  So much to do upon arriving home! </p>\r\n<p>\r\nThe trip was fantastic! I enjoyed it thoroughly and Peru For Less was wonderful with guides and escorts there exactly when they were supposed to be.\r\n</p>\r\n<p>\r\nThank you so much for all that you did for us! \r\n\r\n</p>','Sincerely, \r\nJanet  & Rin <br/> \r\nTennessee &amp; Ohio, USA\r\n<br/>Arequipa, Cuzco, Machu Picchu, and Puno- Lake Titicaca\r\n','','','',173,0,0,NULL,NULL,NULL),(453,1,'Deanna,','<p>I\'m tardy in my response but here are a few thoughts:\r\n</p>\r\n<p>Cusco:</p>\r\n<p>\r\nTours: Juan Carlos was great. He provided a different take on the Inca history and it was very interesting. My wife and I are Catholic so some things he said we initially were taken aback but every story has two sides and as we thought about it we were grateful for his take.\r\n</p>\r\n<p>\r\nAguas Calientes and Macchu Pichu:\r\n</p>\r\n<p>\r\nWow. Sumaq was incredible. We paid quite a bit but it was incredible; one of the best hotels on the entire trip. Thank you for a great recommendation.\r\n</p>\r\n<p>\r\nTours: I\'m forgetting our guides name but he was terrific; very energetic and very entertaining. Machu Picchu exceeded every one of our expectations. Unbelievable.\r\n</p>\r\n<p>\r\nPuerto Maldonado:\r\n</p>\r\n<p>\r\nHotel: Inkaterra was great; remote, relaxing, and great service. I have already told friends and family this is a \"must\" on their next vacation.\r\n</p>\r\n<p>\r\nPeru for Less was there every step of the way during our trip. From arranging lodging, tours, and transportation they managed to remove all of the stresses of a vacation. I wouldn\'t hesitate to recommend PFL to friends or family.\r\n</p>\r\n<p>\r\n\r\nDeanna, again, thanks for everything. We had a great time.\r\n</p>','Bob <br/>\r\nWichita, Kansas, USA\r\n<br/>Cuzco, Machu Picchu, Puerto Maldonado\r\n','','','',175,0,0,NULL,NULL,NULL),(454,1,'Dear Kristina,','<p>I apologise for not having got back to you until now. Although I\'ve been back now for almost a month, the memories nevertheless remain as fresh as if it were yesterday and I had a marvellous time, enamoured of Peru.\r\n</p>\r\n<p>\r\nAs for your outfit, I was delighted with the service you provide. I thought it was good value for money and find it difficult to fault. I obviously compared notes with other travellers on the same route and concluded that I had been well served. \r\n</p>\r\n<p>\r\nIn general I particularly appreciated the fact that I could be sure that there was somebody in your office I could contact if need be at any time (which I did, managing thus painlessly to upgrade my hotels in mid-stream) and the fact that without fail somebody, usually charming, would be wherever it was, to pick me up; apart from anything else, this saved me a lot of time and hassle. \r\n</p>\r\n<p>\r\nAll the guides in situ and on the excursion buses were splendid.\r\n</p>\r\n<p>\r\nThe Nazca flight was certainly a highlight, although I personally could have done without the Ica stop - but tastes differ and the distances are huge, so one needs stop somewhere, I suppose.\r\n</p>\r\n<p>\r\nEl Castillo in Arequipa is a real jewel and deserves to be known more. \r\n</p>\r\n<p>\r\nThank you, you seem to be doing a grand job and I would certainly recommend others to use you.\r\n</p>','Yours,\r\nDavid <br/>\r\nUK\r\n<br/>Puerto Maldonado, Cuzco, Machu Picchu, Puno, Arequipa, Nazca, Ica, and Lima + AmantanÃ­ homestay\r\n','','','',177,0,0,NULL,NULL,NULL),(455,1,'Hi Kristina,','<p>Thank you so much for all your help with planning our trip to Peru.  We had a wonderful time!  We really appreciated the fact that you took the time to really plan exactly what we wanted to do and didn\'t try to sell us extra excursions. Our vacation turned out great and all the accommodations were excellent. We would definitely use your company again and recommend it to other people.  All in all we had a great trip and wanted to thank you for your help.  </p>','Christina <br/>\r\nCalifornia, USA\r\n<br/>Lima, Nazca Lines and Cuzco\r\n','','','',179,0,0,NULL,NULL,NULL),(456,1,'Dear Peru For Less','<p>I am writing to let you know that our trip to Peru was excellent. Three of us had a great time and Peru For Less is a great agency. Those who picked us up and took us our tours, hotels and airports were very hospitable, especially the girl from Cuzco who was great. We had an unforgettable experience. Thanks for everything!</p>','Celeste <br/>\r\nNicaragua and Miami, FL, USA\r\n<br/>Lima, Nazca, Cuzco \r\n','','','',185,0,0,NULL,NULL,NULL),(457,1,'Hi Rylee, ','<p>Sorry for the delayed response. We had a fantastic time throughout the trip. All of our pickup and transportations were punctual and very friendly. Machu Picchu was amazing, of course.  Our tour guide, Fabricio, was beyond fantastic. Not only did he give an excellent tour of the site but he took pictures for us during the tour so we would pay attention to him and not spend the whole tour looking for photo ops. He is not only a star of a tour guide but a pretty good photographer as well. Overall the tours and guides were excellent. \r\n</p>\r\n<p>\r\nI would definitely recommend your services to anyone who is planning a trip to South America. On a side note it seems that PeruForLess has a very nice reputation with the companies and hotels you work with in Peru. I heard from several different sources that you guys are a great company.  Keep up the good work.\r\n\r\n</p>','Thank you again for the fabulous trip, \r\nNick <br/>\r\nManorville, NY, USA\r\n<br/>Lima, Ica/Nazca, Arequipa/Colca, Puno/Titicaca, Cuzco/Machu Picchu\r\n','','','',184,0,0,NULL,NULL,NULL),(458,1,'Dear Kelly,','<p>Thank you for your email: I received it just after I had landed!\r\nI was thinking of writing to you just a few minutes before I received it to say a big thank you to you for organizing the trip for me and to all others who I met and who made everything happen so smoothly for me - particularly those last minute requests on Saturday - Sunday! </p>\r\n<p>\r\nI enjoyed every minute of my trip and everything worked like a clock - which is absolutely invaluable as it saved me time and energy! It made me feel that I was taken really good care of during the whole trip. It was really nice meeting Cristina who gave me very good information, was very attentive and caring and helped a lot during my stay in Cuzco. \r\n</p>\r\n<p>\r\nPerhaps the best word for the whole trip would be breathtaking - both figuratively and literally - given the altitude. I really enjoyed all my tours and when I get some rest, I may write a bit more about my impressions and memories. \r\n</p>\r\n<p>\r\nAgain- a very big thank you to you Kelly, and the whole team! I will definitely think of coming back to you if I decide to travel to Peru or other countries in South America and would recommend Peru For Less to my friends.\r\n</p>\r\n<p>\r\nWith best regards,\r\n</p>','Irina <br/>\r\nCantbury, United Kingdom\r\n<br/>Cuzco, Machu Picchu and Puno\r\n','','','',186,0,0,NULL,NULL,NULL),(459,1,'Hi Kristina,','<p>Sorry about the tardy reply. There has been a lot to catch up with.</p>\r\n<p>\r\n \r\nCusco Hotel: Arqueologo was just as we had expected. It was comfortable and situated in a convenient location. The staff was friendly, and the restaurant had good food.\r\nCusco Excursions: Juan Carlos was our guide and he was incredibly well versed and passionate about Cusco, the Incan culture and his religious/spiritual views. We enjoyed all he had to say. He was also very prompt with pickup times.\r\nMachu Pichu Tour: Fabricio was also quite knowledgeable and his energy and enthusiasm made for a good experience..\r\nPuno Hotel: Casa Andina was clean and comfortable as well. Their breakfast was good and the staff was friendly. It was also in a convenient location. \r\n</p>\r\n<p>\r\nLake Titikaka Excursion: The boat ride and tours were enjoyable. The guide was nice.\r\nThe driver and coordinator were always on time or waiting for us at the stated location. \r\nPeru\'s a beautiful country with amazing landscapes, impressive archaeological sanctuaries, and fascinating culture. PeruForLess made the trip quite easy and also helped make for a good experience. \r\nWe elected to take the Vista Dome train to Machu Pichu (great suggestion by the way Kristina!). I\'ll start by saying that the experience was very pleasant. \r\nThanks for all your help Kristina!\r\n</p>','Cheers,\r\n\r\nLydia <br/>\r\nCalifornia, USA, New York\r\n<br/>Cuzco and Puno\r\n','','','',187,0,0,NULL,NULL,NULL),(460,1,'Hi Jennifer,','<p>We just got back from Manu, so I just got your email. Thanks for taking care of this, everything went exactly as planned and we had a wonderful time in Manu and also throughout our entire trip. Tonight is our last night here and we\'re off to Quito tomorrow to continue our trip in Galapagos.\r\n</p>\r\n<p>\r\nWorking with you has really been a pleasure and I look forward to more trips, so perhaps our paths shall cross again. I appreciate all the effort you guys put into making our trip a memorable and seamless one.\r\n</p>\r\n<p>\r\nAll the best,\r\n</p>','Matan and Tracy <br/>\r\nCalifornia, USA\r\n<br/>Lima, Ica, Nazca, Arequipa, Cuzco, Machu Picchu and Manu\r\n','','','',188,0,0,NULL,NULL,NULL),(461,1,'Dear Peru For Less','<p>The trip overall was excellent.  We enjoyed very much all three places we went to: Arequipa/Colca, Cuzco/Sacred Valley/Machu Picchu and Puerto Maldonado.</p>\r\n<p>\r\n\r\nWe highly recommend Alison in Cuzco. The tour guide for the sacred valley tour, I think her name was Isabel, was like a professor and the best guide we had in Peru.  She was so knowledgeable about the Incas and the history of pre-Hispanic America. We enjoyed visiting Ollantaytambo and Chinchero almost as much as Machu Picchu. The whole excursion to Machu Picchu was excellent and we enjoyed our personalized tour.  The Casa Andina San Blas was excellent.  We had a beautiful view of Cuzco from our room, and the service and attention were outstanding.  We would highly recommend this hotel to other travelers.\r\n</p>\r\n<p>\r\nThe whole excursion to Puerto Maldonado and the Amazon was exceptional.  The Refugio Amazonas was one of the most beautiful lodges I have ever stayed in, and the fact that the rooms are open to the jungle made the experience even more wonderful.  The food was excellent and so were the guides.  Our guide Eder took care of us from the moment we arrived at the airport to the moment we left.  We also had a lot of contact with Paula who was also excellent.  I cannot tell you how much I would recommend Rainforest Expeditions.  I think it is one of the best eco-tourism experiences we have had anywhere in the world.\r\n</p>\r\n<p>\r\nOverall, Peru is one of the most beautiful and interesting countries in the world, and we would like to thank Peru for Less for giving us one of the best vacations we have ever had.\r\n</p>\r\n','Rahul and \r\nJuan <br/>\r\nWashington DC, USA\r\n<br/>Cuzco, Arequipa and Puerto Maldonado\r\n','','','',189,0,0,NULL,NULL,NULL),(462,1,'Dear Peru For Less','<p>We had a wonderful time and your company provided all services as sold. We were always on time, had great guides, good hotels, etc. It was all we could ask for during a difficult, but very enjoyable trip. We enjoyed meeting you and having lunch. I can certainly recommend Peru for Less.  Thanks!</p>\r\n\r\n','Gretchen <br/>\r\nSouthlake, TX USA\r\n<br/>Lima, Cuzco, Sacred Valley, Machu Picchu\r\n','','','',190,0,0,NULL,NULL,NULL),(463,1,'Dear Peru For Less','<p>Just wanted to tell you what a great time I had in your beautiful country with my daughter.\r\nI felt that all the guides were very knowledgeable, helpful and courteous. I especially want to congratulate your wonderful employee, Tracy - she most certainly went the extra mile in customer service. My daughter Laurin is on special medication that always needs to be in refrigerator. We had to leave our baggage behind in our hotel and only take a backpack to Macchu Picchu, and were not able to return to Cuzco for 2 days to another different hotel. I told Tracy how anxious I was about leaving my daughter\'s medication behind... After we boarded the bus she went and hand delivered the medication to our next hotel destination. There it was waiting for us upon our arrival already in the hotel refrigerator. What a relief!</p>\r\n<p>\r\n\r\nThank You for having punctual employees. There was always someone waiting at the airports ready to take us to our new destination with all travel arrangements ready. Thank you for organizing and helping to make this trip such a positive experience for me.\r\n</p>','Maria <br/>\r\nCasselbery, FL, USA\r\n<br/>Lima, Cuzco, Inti Raymi, Sacred Valley, Machu Picchu, Puerto Maldonado\r\n','','','',191,0,0,NULL,NULL,NULL),(464,1,'Hi Kristina,','<p>I can\'t say a single bad word about PFL and can say many good ones; I\'ll be happy to write a testimonial. Everything worked perfectly. People were there to meet me when you said they would be; the tour guide to Machu Picchu was fun and informative (and it was lovely to be there later in the afternoon, when many people had departed). I had \"hiccups\" in Peru, but none were associated with PFL (and were probably my fault for not understanding Spanish). I want to thank you particularly for the hotel in Aguas Calientes. My room was on the river side, so I got to be lulled to sleep by the gurgling water.\r\n</p>\r\n<p>\r\nAnd you, my dear, are going to be doing great and fun things - that I know. It has been such a pleasure \"working\" with you and I can\'t tell you how much I enjoyed spending time with you on my birthday. That was so incredibly sweet. If ever you are back in California, you must let me know before, so that perhaps we can meet again. All the best to you Kristina - and many hugs (tell Juan he must give you at least a hundred for me!)\r\n</p>','Kathleen <br/>\r\nCalifornia, USA\r\n<br/>Cuzco, Lima\r\n','','','',192,0,0,NULL,NULL,NULL),(465,1,'Dear Peru For Less','<p>After our fabulous two week trip to Peru, Cecil and I are back at our London office desks and I think it\'s safe to say we\'ve finally recovered from the jetlag!</p>\r\n\r\n<p>But before life runs away with us again we just wanted to send an email to say thank you so much for all your help in making this a holiday of a lifetime! With your expert advice we managed to do everything we wanted to do (and more!), but without having to deal with the stresses you often incur when going to a foreign country. We also really appreciated that you were able to \"un-cancel\" our trip on such short notice.  </p>\r\n<p>\r\nIn general we found the agents very professional. They gave us good advice and were always punctual. We also appreciate the fact that the agents often had to wait long hours for our arrival when the busses were running late. Being able to rely on the agents/agency makes a big difference to the overall experience. We appreciated receiving regular confirmations of pick up times from agents, and having 24 hour emergency numbers available for when things go wrong.</p>\r\n<p>\r\nThe Inca trail was a definite highlight of our trip, and we are so glad that we were able to do it!  Wayki trek played an important role in making the experience so enjoyable. Our guide, Jose Cusi Camero, was superb and the porters were thoughtful, considerate and friendly and the food was delicious - especially considering the conditions in which it was prepared. Their attention to detail made the experience extra special. Jose was very good at sharing his knowledge during our \"history lessons\", was always there to help and made sure that everyone was safe and doing well during the hiking. Everything was done very professionally. </p>\r\n<p>\r\nDuring our trip we often stayed in Casa Andina hotels, and we were very happy with these hotels.  They are always clean, neat and comfortable, provide good breakfasts, free internet and the staff are always very helpful.\r\n</p>\r\n<p>\r\nOur agent in Cusco (Christina (?)) recommended that we include a trip to the Pisac ruins as part of our sacred valley tour. We were very glad that she made this recommendation as we really enjoyed the ruins, and the little walk we had around it and it made the day really worth it!  You should recommend it to other clients as well.\r\n</p>\r\n<p>\r\nWe thought our Colca Canyon tour guide was really good (think his name was Omar Katana); very engaging and enthusiastic.  We really got a sense that he loved the area and nature and he encouraged us to go for walks, rather than just driving to where-ever we needed to be- which made the experience more enjoyable.\r\n</p>\r\n<p>\r\nWe had a fantastic time and thank you again for all your help.\r\n</p>\r\n<p>\r\nLooking forward to speaking to you again when we arrange our trip to Argentina!\r\n</p>','Kind regards,\r\n\r\nJeanne <br/>\r\nParacas/Nazca, Cuzco, Inca Trail to Machu Picchu, Lake Titicaca\r\n','','','',193,0,0,NULL,NULL,NULL),(466,1,'Hi Kelly,','<p>Sorry for taking so long to respond. Ron has been very busy at work so I volunteered to answer your e-mail.</p>\r\n<p>\r\nOur trip was terrific! We had a great time and were extremely happy with the itinerary you arranged for us. Thank you so much for that and of course, we were so impressed that it was all done with less than 72hours before we left. The Peru-for-less contacts in each of the cities were very helpful and friendly (and very eager to please). Except for our small glitch (re: our flight from Arequipa to Lima), everything went off without a hitch.\r\n</p>\r\n<p>\r\nWe loved our trip to Machu Picchu. The Vistadome train ride was lots of fun. The tour of Machu Picchu was great. Alison (your representative in Cuzco) had told me to use insect repellent (which I forgot) and I got thousands (or so it felt like) of itchy bites on my legs. That for me was the only low point of the trip. I am happy to say I am fully recovered :). No one else was bitten.\r\n</p>\r\n<p>\r\nOn the advice of the Machu Picchu guide, we climbed Putucusi the next day. That was tough but lots of fun for the boys (especially the ladders).\r\n</p>\r\n<p>\r\nThe trip to Puno was a pleasant surprise. My younger son and I suffer from motion sickness, so a 9 hour bus ride was not something we were looking forward to but the frequent stops for tours and lunch were great. The floating islands and Lake Titicaca were definitely a highlight. I would certainly recommend the Lake Titicaca tour, it was fascinating.\r\n</p>\r\n<p>\r\nThe Colca Canyon trek was great too. Our young guide was really good and liked hiking with the boys. I think he said that our boys were the only kids he\'s seen on the trek.  It was tough, and hot. The heat probably made it tougher. The walk back up was significantly easier (it was 80% shade). We loved the \"comfortable but basic accommodations\" at the OASIS. The kids thought the mud floors and no lights was just the greatest.\r\n </p>\r\n<p>\r\nThe white water rafting was the favourite part for both boys. The rapids were just thrilling and scary enough to be lots of fun. Safety wise I felt very safe (and rafting makes me nervous).\r\n</p>\r\n<p>\r\nOverall I would give both you and the trip a 10/10 rating. Your help, especially at the last minute, was invaluable.\r\n</p>','Thanks so much,\r\nSusan <br/>\r\nToronto, Canada\r\nCuzco, Machu Picchu, Puno, Arequipa\r\n                ','','','',195,0,0,NULL,NULL,NULL),(467,1,'Hi Kelly, ','<p>We are back and trying to get ready for work after being out for two weeks. The trip was amazing and everything was great and we are very happy we got to meet you. </p>\r\n<p>\r\n \r\nWe were able to climb Wayna Picchu (had to get up at 3:30 AM); the hike and view were amazing. Attached are a few pictures.</p>\r\n<p>\r\n\r\nThank you for organizing everything and for the great memories. \r\n</p>','Thanks and have a great day,  <br/>\r\n\r\nTeodora <br/>\r\nSanta Ana, CA USA <br/>\r\nLima, Cuzco &amp; Machu Picchu\r\n\r\n','iovtcheva.jpg','','',667,0,0,NULL,NULL,NULL),(468,1,'Hi Jennifer,','<p>Peru was awesome. Machu Picchu and Lake Titicaca were magnificent.  </p>\r\n \r\n<p>The Peru For Less guides, drivers and everyone involved with the Peru For Less outfit - including yourself - were fantastic.  They were always on time and extremely knowledgeable and helpful.</p>\r\n \r\n<p>I would recommend everyone to go with Peru for less.</p>\r\n','Warm Regards, <br/>\r\n \r\nPaula <br/>\r\nOhio, USA <br/>\r\nCuzco, Machu Picchu, Puno <br/>\r\nLake Titicaca\r\n','moore-paula.jpg','','',668,0,0,NULL,NULL,NULL),(469,1,'Hi Rylee,','<p>We had a great trip - no complaints at all.  \r\n\r\nEverything worked out smoothly and I\'d highly recommend both the Inca Trail and Peru for Less as a first class travel agency.</p>\r\n<p>\r\nThanks for all your good work and take care,</p>\r\n','Bob <br/>\r\nWeston, CT, USA <br/>\r\nCuzco, Inca trail to Machu Picchu','levi-bob.jpg','','',669,0,0,NULL,NULL,NULL),(470,1,'Dear Kristina, ','<p>Sorry it has taken me a while to get back to you! So much to do upon arriving home! </p>\r\n\r\n<p>The trip was fantastic! I enjoyed it thoroughly and Peru For Less was wonderful with guides and escorts there exactly when they were supposed to be.</p>\r\n<p>\r\n \r\nThank you so much for all that you did for us! \r\n</p>\r\n','Sincerely, <br/>\r\n\r\nRin <br/>\r\nTennessee &amp; Ohio, USA <br/>\r\nSpecial 3: Arequipa, Cuzco, Machu Picchu, Puno\r\n','hansen-rin.jpg','','',670,0,0,NULL,NULL,NULL),(471,1,'Hello Kristina &amp; Sebastian,','<p>Thank you for your note. We had a fabulous trip to Peru and have been busy trying to catch up on work since our return. My apologies for not getting back to you sooner.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>After trying to pull it all together ourselves, we realized that we needed the expertise of a local agency to provide guidance and assist with our internal transportation, accommodations and transfers. Kristina at Peru For Less was simply awesome - very flexible and accommodating in meeting our requests.  We developed an itinerary that maximized our time in Peru but also allowed for some time to ourselves.  Our flights, internal transfers and tours were perfect. After travelling overnight, it was a welcome relief to see the Peru For Less sign and Tracy (our local Cuzco guide) waiting outside the Cuzco Airport. When we arrived at each new location, we were met by our local guide and promptly transferred to our hotel. We truly didn\'t need to worry about a thing - even the weather was great - only 2 afternoons of rain, beyond that very warm, loads of sun and bright blue skies. </p>\r\n\r\n<p>Our accommodations were fantastic. El Picoaga is a lovely colonial hotel in a great location near the Plaza de Armas. We could walk to restaurants and the sights of the city in just 2 minutes.  While visiting Machu Picchu we splurged and stayed at the Inkaterra. We spent so much time at Machu Picchu we did not have enough time to take full advantage of the activities offered by the El Pueblo. The hotel offers nature trails highlighting their extensive orchids and other programs about the area and wildlife that piqued our interest.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>We are fairly independent travelers but chose to have Peru for Less arrange a few tours for us.  While in Cuzco, we enjoyed the tour of the Sacred Valley. Mary was a great guide and we appreciated her recommendation to eat a late lunch so we could beat the crowds at Ollantaytambo. Our group \"clicked\" well and there were lots of laughs and stories shared which added to the overall experience. </p>\r\n\r\n<p>Machu Picchu exceeded all expectations - from the bus ride and its 18 hairpin turns to seeing llamas grazing amongst the ruins. We were fortunate to have a 2 hour private tour with Fabrizio but our time spent exploring on our own was most memorable. On our first day we hiked to the Sun Gate &amp; the Inca Bridge. It started to storm on our way back from the Sun Gate but we were not deterred and decided to go to the bridge -- what a great little hike and we are so happy that we didn\'t let the rain stop us! Based on these short hikes and the amazing views, we decided we just had to hike Waynu Picchu the next day. This option was mentioned by Tracy in Cuzco but it wasn\'t until we reached Machu Picchu that we realized what it entailed. This was by far our best experience during our visit to Peru. It is a tough hike but affords amazing views and you can truly appreciate the expanse of Machu Picchu. We chose to return to the via the trail to the Great Cavern.  The trail down included ladders, cables and steep stone stairways which were fairly challenging but the hike back to Machu Picchu was very challenging! At times we wondered if we\'d make it back in time to catch our return train to Cuzco but we persevered and ended up with plenty of time for showers, pizza and beer before our return trip. We highly recommend all of these hikes if you are in decent physical condition and take lots of water.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Lake Titicaca was a nice surprise. The tourist bus stops every 90 minutes, so the 11 hour trip included site-seeing, shopping and lunch and actually was okay. Our room was cozy and our view of the lake was superb. We decided to forgo the full day tour of the lake for a 1/2 day tour. This gave us a chance to have the afternoon shopping in the Puno market and to enjoy a few beers at the hotel. At the end of the trip, we enjoyed some down time to reflect and relax. While visiting the Uros Islands, our group\'s visit coincided with Miss Peru\'s tour of the island - an added bonus seeing a local celebrity. The Uros islanders were so hospitable and you are left with a great appreciation and respect for their culture and way of life. It is this part of the trip that many of my colleagues, friends and family are most interested in learning about.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>On our last day in Peru, we visited the Sillustani funeral towers with Junior. This was a private tour included as part of our transfer to the airport in Juliaca. Travel days always seem to be \"lost days\" as you end up hanging around airports for transfers and connections. Since our travel required overnight flights, PFL recommended a late day flight from Juliaca to Lima so that we could see this area. What a great recommendation! After we toured the chulpas, Junior took us to a local home where we sample some local food. This was a fantastic way to end our travels and added to our overall visit to the Puno area.  <p>\r\n\r\n<p>All in all a great trip; thank you for all your help!</p>\r\n','Amy <br/>\r\nVermont, USA <br/>\r\nCuzco, Puno <br/>\r\n','perry-amy.jpg','','',671,0,0,NULL,NULL,NULL),(472,1,'Hi Rylee,','<p>Our trip was excellent. Your tours and service was superb. There was a representative to meet us at all our connections even when our plane from the states was 3 hours late arriving at 2:00 AM in Lima. We found the tours well organized and informative. All the guides were pleasant, helpful and knowledgeable about their culture. Our guide, Jose, on the Inca trail was excellent. He knew just what pace to set so that we were not exhausted. In fact groups who had passed us we soon caught up to and left behind at our slow but steady pace. My wife did suffer from altitude sickness and our guide to Coca Canyon was extremely caring and helpful. All our guides showed great pride in sharing their heritage and country with us.  \r\n\r\nAll the accommodations were superb. They met or exceeded our expectations. We were particularly impressed with the Picoaga and Coca Canyon Lodge as they were unique. All the accommodations were modern, clean and comfortable. </p>\r\n\r\n<p>\r\n\r\nOverall the trip was very well organized and professional. The service from the friendly staff of Peru For Less was much appreciated.  I have and will continue to recommend Peru For Less to my friends and family.  </p>\r\n\r\n<p>\r\n\r\nThank you for the well organized and careful planning of our tour of Peru. We hope to return to Peru as there is much more to see and experience in your wonderful country. </p>\r\n','John <br/>\r\nSault Ste. Marie, Ontario <br/>\r\nLima, Ica, Nazca, Arequipa, Puno, Cuzco, Sacred Valley, 2 day Inca Trail to Machu Picchu\r\n','schnablegger.jpg','','',672,0,0,NULL,NULL,NULL),(474,1,'Rylee,','<p>As you requested, we are happy to provide feedback on our trip to you. The trip we had with Peru For Less was fantastic</p>\r\n \r\n<p>We had a great trip and enjoyed all aspects of it. Success for this kind of trip depended on flawless coordination with guides at various locations in different countries, and with coordination of pick-ups at our hotels for tours or connections with flights. Peru For Less executed this perfectly. We always knew where, how and when we would be met; we always knew what was planned for the current day, as well as the next day; and we were kept informed of the type of areas we would be going to.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>\r\n \r\nHotel accommodations were very good. Local tour guides were knowledgeable and attentive to our questions. Land transportation was with modern vehicles and excellent drivers.</p>\r\n \r\n<p>Overall, we were very pleased with the whole trip and would gladly recommend it to anyone wanting to explore this part of the world. We found we were well taken care of, kept informed of activities to the extent that we did not have any concerns at all. All of this was accomplished at a very reasonable price.\r\n</p>','Thank you very much, Peru For Less. <br/>\r\n \r\nEldon and Mary  <br/>\r\nNova Scotia, Canada <br/>\r\nSpecial 8: Rio de Janeiro, Igauzu Falls, Buenos Aires, Lima, Cuzco/Machu Picchu\r\n','eldon-mary-smith.jpg','','',673,0,0,NULL,NULL,NULL),(475,1,'Kelly,','<p>Thank you so much for arranging everything!  We had the smoothest most amazing possible experience on vacation ever. There aren\'t even words to express how wonderful of an experience/adventure that we had, but I\'ll try my best. We got home and looked at each other and both said that that was by far the best vacation that either of us had ever been on. I hope that Peru For Less continues to work with Wayki Trek. This group is amazing. We were hiking along side other groups and I could tell that Wayki Trek not only takes the time to make sure that you\'re every need is met , but they are by far the most professional, knowledgeable, and happy group compared to the other companies.  \r\n</p>\r\n<p>\r\nOur guide Antonio was amazing!  He knew everyone, everywhere.  There were many times that the people from Wayki Trek stood out as being the very best in the area and everyone in our group commented on it continuously. Everyday our guide gave us multiple possible options for the day and we always did the very most that we could possibly do for the day so that we could see as much of Peru as possible.  </p>\r\n<p>\r\n\r\nThe hot springs were nothing like we expected.  We felt like Kings and Queens. There were 3 or 4 large pools and hot spring style showers. Amazing! It was extra but it was well worth the money.  \r\n\r\nWe had such a great experience! I want to see Peru for Less do well. The other couple in our group used a different booking agent and they had quite a few problems and we had none! You guys are awesome and hit a dead ringer for us. Wayki is awesome and provided the very best trekking experience in Peru! Everything was wonderful!  All of the transfers were perfect! It was a life changing experience. I loved every minute of my time in Peru!     </p> \r\n<p>\r\nThank you for the cake.  Chris was quite surprised and enjoyed it very much!  Thank you again for the best trip that we\'ve ever taken!  I\'ve been trying to find other treks comparable to this one and I\'m having a tough time.</p>\r\n<p>\r\nThank you again for everything!  Sorry this is so long, but I have much to say and tell and things to thank you for. I included a few picture of my favorite sites! Let me know if I can help you out at all in the future. I look forward to hopefully booking with you guys again, soon!</p>\r\n','Enjoy the photos! <br/>\r\n\r\nMelissa <br/>\r\nAmherst. NY USA <br/>\r\nCuzco &amp; Salkantay Trek\r\n','baxter-melissa.jpg','','',674,0,0,NULL,NULL,NULL),(476,1,'Matt,','<p>Thanks for the follow up email. My trip was amazing! The Peru For Less team was phenomenal from the planning right down through to the execution of my trip. The tours were small and personal, which was outstanding and gave you a real feel for the country and its people. They were always on time with all pick-ups and transfers and were always available if you had any questions. The personal attention that the trip advisors paid to me was outstanding. It was the trip of a lifetime and I would recommend Peru For Less to anyone thinking about traveling there.\r\nThank you all for the outstanding trip of a lifetime!</p>\r\n<p>\r\nOn a more personal note, I am thinking about taking another trip to South or Central America. I understand you guys handle more then just Peru?\r\nIf so where would you recommended that I should go? Thanks!</p>\r\n','Patrick <br/>\r\nLakewood, Ohio, USA <br/>\r\nLima, Cuzco, Machu Picchu\r\n','naughton.jpg','','',675,0,0,NULL,NULL,NULL),(477,1,'Hello Kelly,','<p>The trip to Puerto Maldonado was really great. I didn\'t expect the lodges to be so \"luxurious\". In my case I would have even been satisfied with a simpler designed location. Everything worked very well. The food was great as well as my guide Vico. I was very lucky to have him as my guide - a biologist who knows every single bird by its call (totally weird!), as well as nearly every plant and all the complicated relations of the jungle. It was a little sad to see that other groups didn\'t have such an experienced guide. Some of the others had to really struggle with their English (or other languages) and they were by far not as educated as Vico was! I was the lucky one.</p>\r\n<p>\r\nAll together it was a great experience that I can recommend to others. I also have attached a few images of my trip.</p>\r\n <p>\r\nThanks for all your efforts. It was awesome!</p>\r\n','Regards from grey and cold Germany, <br/>\r\n \r\nSteffen <br/>\r\nGermany <br/>\r\nPuerto Maldonado\r\n','paetzold.jpg','','',676,0,0,NULL,NULL,NULL),(478,1,'','<p>In Lima we had a great dinner Las Brujas de Cachiche.  It was a great opportunity to meet Rylee - our Peru For Less rep - in person and I would highly recommend using PFL and Rylee in particular if you are traveling in South America.</p>','Baker <br/>\r\nHouston, TX, USA <br/>\r\nLima, Arequipa/Colca Canyon, Cuzco/Machu Picchu and Puerto Maldonado\r\n','baker-houston.jpg','','',677,0,0,NULL,NULL,NULL),(479,1,'Rylee, ','<p>I wanted to take a little more time to thank you for our wonderful trip.  There was never a moment when Peru For Less let us down.   </p>\r\n<p>\r\nDrivers, guides, representatives were prompt, polite, helpful, friendly. Miguel in Lima was so knowledgeable about the religious history -- very interesting. The desk clerk at the Casa Andina always greeted us with his beautiful smile. Johann in Chiclayo took us to some of the most fascinating archaeological sites and museums. I wished for more time there. He took us to a small recently opened restaurant -- which served one of our favorite meals (won\'t forget the sudado).  Had some freshly brewed chicha (corn beer) there. We enjoyed the drive through the sugar cane fields. Convinced him to take us to the local market, where Lucy found some treasures and I enjoyed people-watching and taking photos. Judith in Trujillo went so over and beyond. She invited us in to her home, where all of her family was so warm and hospitable. Trujillo\'s Temple of the Moon was one of the most memorable places. Chan Chan was also beautiful, awesome. Hard to believe they\'ve just begun with all that\'s there to excavate and restore. We also had an amazing meal at a restaurant with a huge buffet there. Judith led us through course after course.  We won\'t forget the ceviche. I am so glad we included the northern desert in our itinerary. Learning about the Moche and Chimu cultures provided such depth and background prior to seeing Machu Picchu.</p>\r\n<p>\r\nThe Amazon may have been my favorite spot. It\'s hard to choose. The Inkaterra was a dream.  I hope I can return there some day. I still dream of what that dense forest sounded like -- a symphony. We also enjoyed \"Applesauce,\" the wild boar who hung around to have his belly rubbed.</p>\r\n<p>\r\nCuzco was a little hard at first.  The altitude was an adjustment.  We were glad we had some off-time to just lounge. The first night though, we dragged ourselves out and heard music on the square -- a brass band, a torch singer, and a musical group. Such fun! The city was like a fairy land at night. We loved our hotel, The Arqueologo. We discovered its cozy bar and ended up being alone in there at times in the evening -- sitting on the comfortable love seats in front of the fire, being served tapas and delicious Peruvian wine. We heard the opera singing waiters and waitresses at the restaurant next door. Maria Elena, our tour guide there, was also a gem. The drive through the Sacred Valley was memorable. We also enjoyed the colorful Pisac Market.</p>\r\n<p>\r\nFrom there we were off to Machu Pichu and of course it was sensational. We loved the Inkaterra Hotel. Had a tour of their lovely orchid garden and saw numerous hummingbirds of all colors and sizes.</p>\r\n<p>\r\nOur final treat was taking that fabulous train to Puno (thank you for your suggestion there, so worth it) and then staying with the family on Amantani Island. Lucy and I were both a bit trepidatious about this, but we had a magical stay. Despite our language differences, we somehow communicated and felt so warmly held by them. We did lots of climbing and saw the sun set on one side of the island and the moon rise on the other. We want to go back. We want to go back to all the places we went. Hopefully we\'ll be able to. Thank you for such great memories. Peru is such a glorious country with such a sense of reverence in its life.  I\'ll send you a couple of pictures.</p>\r\n','Meredith <br/>\r\nAtlanta, GA, USA <br/>\r\nLima, Trujillo/Chiclayo, Puerto Maldonado, Cuzco, Machu Picchu and Puno\r\n','knight-meredith.jpg','','',678,0,0,NULL,NULL,NULL),(483,1,'Rylee,','You were a pleasure to work with â?? you answered our numerous questions and were very accommodating about customizing our trip. All of the accommodations were as described and the staff were very helpful at the hotels.  ','Thanks again,\r\n\r\nTherese <br />\r\nCardiff, CA, USA\r\n<br />\r\nPuno, Cuzco, Sacred Valley, to Machu Picchu\r\n','','','',194,0,0,NULL,NULL,NULL),(484,1,'Hello,','Well I am back in Las Vegas and had a good time in Peru and in Lima.\r\n\r\nThank you to your company. They were on time for everything and very nice to me. Most of all I want to thank you for setting up a nice trip that I will remember forever. You all did a very nice job and when I go back on a vacation, I will contact you for help.\r\n','Thanks again  \r\n\r\nPaul <br />\r\nLas Vegas, NV, USA\r\n<br />Cuzco, Machu Picchu, Puno\r\n','','','',197,0,0,NULL,NULL,NULL),(485,1,'Hi Rylee,','The visit to Peru was a most enlightening experience. For a relatively short trip, the exposure to Peruvian history and Inca Culture was indeed very rewarding and, I might add, rather physically demanding, starting with the approximately 250 steps at the Sacred Valley site and continuing on from there. This is not a complaint, just a report of the activity from the geezer in the group.\r\n\r\nThank you for the very nicely timed arrangements for transportation between all the airport, hotel and tour sites. The local guides, drivers and Peru For Less representatives were all punctual, professional and courteous.  All the members of our little group enjoyed the trip immensely.   Thanks again.\r\n\r\nRegards, \r\n','Donnie <br />\r\nChester, NY, USA\r\n<br />\r\nLima, Cuzco, Machu Picchu, Puno\r\n','','','',199,0,0,NULL,NULL,NULL),(486,1,'Matt,','The trip was fantastic. As far as the logistics went, we couldn\'t have been more pleased.\r\n\r\nAll the guides and representatives were cordial, educated, and very helpful. All tours were run very professionally.\r\n\r\nThanks for helping us coordinate an excellent trip. I will definitely pass you on to anyone I know heading to South America.\r\n ','Doug <br />\r\nVirginia, USA\r\n<br />Puerto Maldonado, Cuzco, Machu Picchu and Puno\r\n','','','',201,0,0,NULL,NULL,NULL),(487,1,'Hello Deanna,','We had a fabulous time on our trip. All of our connections and the travel arrangements throughout Peru were prompt, courteous, and on time. We felt that the sightseeing tours were good.  \r\n\r\nAll in all it was very nice; we really liked Peru and the people. We will keep your agency in mind for future trips and will recommend your agency to anyone wishing to travel to South America. \r\n','Kind Regards,\r\n\r\nVera <br />\r\nColorado, USA\r\n<br />\r\nLima, Cuzco, Machu Picchu, and Puerto Maldonado\r\n','','','',196,0,0,NULL,NULL,NULL),(488,1,'Dear Peru For Less','The trip was great and I have just arrived back into Mia.  All of our relations are set up except for Brazil. We will certainly be using you for our services and our first trip with Brazil For Less is set for January 5th, 2010 for a group of 12. \r\n\r\nI look forward to working with you guys!\r\n\r\n','Aaron <br />\r\nFlorida, USA\r\n<br />\r\nCuzco, Machu Picchu       ','','','',198,0,0,NULL,NULL,NULL),(489,1,'Dear Peru For Less','We just got back from Peru yesterday, as we tagged on a riverboat excursion in the Amazon. Short answer is we were very happy with Peru for Less. We will email you a more detailed answer when we are settled.\r\n\r\n\r\n','Rosalie <br />\r\nCalgary, Canada\r\n<br />\r\nLima, Paracas/Nazca, Arequipa, Cuzco, Machu Picchu        ','','','',200,0,0,NULL,NULL,NULL),(490,1,'Dear Peru For Less','We thoroughly enjoyed our trek to Machu Picchu!\r\n \r\nThank you so much,\r\n\r\n\r\n','Lori <br />\r\nConnecticut, USA\r\n<br />\r\nLima, Cuzco, Inca Trail to Machu Picchu      ','','','',202,0,0,NULL,NULL,NULL),(491,1,'Hello Kristina,','Tomorrow is our flight back home to the U.S.A. Thank you so much for such wonderful time we had in Peru. We just hoped we could have started slow on our elevation. We all became sick, but got over it. As a whole, we had a wonderful experience. Thanks again. We will surely pass the word to all our friends who are interested to travel to Peru. The Peruvians are great people.\r\n\r\n\r\n','Regards, \r\n\r\nTeresita <br />\r\nUSA\r\n<br />\r\nCuzco, Machu Picchu, Lima','','','',203,0,0,NULL,NULL,NULL),(492,1,'Hello Rylee, ','Thanks for the inquiry! It is great to be home and sleep in your own bed and be with the familiar surroundings. Our trip overall was good.\r\nOur stay in Lima was good. Daniel in Lima was a big help since he was fluent in English. The tour guide for our Lima City tour was good.\r\nAllyson in Cuzco was a big help too in providing a lot of information. \r\nCuzco hotel staff was very good - the guy at the register spoke good English and helped us with a lot of info.\r\nOur trip to Machu Picchu was fantastic... beautiful weather... unbelievable scenery... perfect! \r\nThank you for all your help! \r\nRegards, \r\n','Nima <br />\r\nOviedo, FL  (USA)\r\n<br />\r\nLima, Cuzco, Puno\r\n','','','',204,0,0,NULL,NULL,NULL),(493,1,'Hello Kelly!','The trip was great! All transfers went well and all the tours was great too, especially the personal tour of the Sacred Valley.\r\n\r\nThe hotel in Cuzco was really nice and close to the action in Cuzco. It was a great trip, maybe the best part of our world tour!\r\n\r\nThank you for your help, Kelly!\r\n','Mattias <br />\r\nCuzco and Machu Picchu\r\n','','','',205,0,0,NULL,NULL,NULL),(494,1,'To Peru For Less:','\r\nThe Turnerâ??s and Mr. Squillario had a great time on the trip you booked. They said the Peru For Less representatives were great and went above and beyond. I sent them the email you sent a couple of days ago. Hopefully they will respond to it.  Thanks so much for all of your help. You have been great as well. I will be in touch when I have travel to Peru, etc\r\n\r\n','Laurie <br />\r\nGarner World Travel<br />\r\nDalton, GA, USA\r\n<br />\r\nCuzco, Machu Picchu\r\n      ','','','',206,0,0,NULL,NULL,NULL),(495,1,'Rylee,','\r\n\r\nWe recently traveled from Lima to Cuzco and went by train to Machu Picchu. We were very impressed with Peru For Less. Our guides we excellent and Christina managed all the details for us. We enjoyed the hotel and all of the guided tours. Thank you for making us feel welcome and comfortable in you country, Peru.\r\n\r\n','\r\nCarolyn and Henry <br />\r\nDalton, GA, USA\r\n<br />\r\nCuzco, Machu Picchu','','','',207,0,0,NULL,NULL,NULL),(496,1,'Rylee, ','We got back this morning. Our trip far exceeded my already high expectations. Peru for Less didn\'t miss a beat: so professional; went over and above throughout. I want to write more specifics when I have time to reflect. But I planned to thank you as soon as possible. It was a trip of a lifetime and now I want to go back!\r\n\r\nBest to you,\r\n\r\n','Meredith <br />\r\nAtlanta, GA, USA \r\n<br />\r\nLima, Trujillo/Chiclayo, Puerto Maldonado, Cuzco, Machu Picchu and Puno ','','','',208,0,0,NULL,NULL,NULL),(497,1,'Dear Peru For Less','\r\n \r\nWe really enjoyed our trip. We never wanted to be part of a large group traveling together so this worked out great. Guides were so informative and very nice and always kept us updated on our schedule.  It made the trip very easy but also independent. We always felt secure in knowing we had support personnel if needed. We appreciate all the work you did.  If we head to Peru again we would give Peru For Less a call. \r\n \r\nAgain, we had a wonderful time. Thanks for all your help. \r\n \r\n\r\n','Gloria <br />\r\nFlorida, USA\r\n<br />\r\nLima, Cuzco, Machu Picchu   ','','','',209,0,0,NULL,NULL,NULL),(498,1,'Good morning, Rylee!','\r\nI received your e-mail from Tina Willam at Flight Centre and decided to reply to you directly.\r\n\r\nWe were very pleased with all our tours with Peru For Less. All our connections, pick-ups and drop-offs went seamlessly. Thanks for that!\r\n\r\nI\'d like to point out a few of our guides for an extra special thank you. Adrian at Iguazu Falls, Carol in Buenos Aires and especially Mary in Cuzco  - were all amazing. They were knowledgeable, professional and definitely had a love for their city and it showed  - big time. It was also fun to be met by Tracey (from Phoenix) when we arrived in Cuzco.  \r\n\r\nDon and I loved Rio and will probably return at some point; but I think Iguazu Falls and Machu Picchu were definitely the highlights for us. Also, the local people in and around Cuzco were a pleasure.\r\n\r\nWe\'ll definitely recommend Peru For Less to friends and family. I work for an airline, with people obsessed with travel (much like myself) and I\'ve already passed along my kudos about Peru For Less; and of course, about our agent, Tina at Flight Centre in YHZ, without whom none of this would have happened!\r\n\r\nThanks again .. and we\'ll definitely be back.\r\n\r\nRegards,\r\n\r\n\r\n','Jean (and Don) Day<br />\r\nNova Scotia, Canada\r\n<br />\r\nSpecial 8: Rio de Janeiro, Igauzu Falls, Buenos Aires, Lima, Cuzco/Machu Picchu','','','',210,0,0,NULL,NULL,NULL),(499,1,'Jennifer,  ','\r\nChoosing a company for an international trip where you don\'t speak the language can be frightening, but Peru For Less prepared a trip that we will remember for the rest of our lives. Our tour guides, especially for Colca Canyon and the Sacred Valley, were beyond compare. We gained a great deal of knowledge from both guides and appreciated their incredible historical information.  We especially liked the small tour groups which provided a good balance between the planned tour, one-on-one time with our guides and free time to explore. \r\n \r\nAccommodations at all of our four star hotels was fabulous. They were all clean, modern and well appointed. The staff were all polite and eager to make us feel welcomed guests.\r\n \r\nWe also appreciated the way Peru For Less staff kept checking up on us along the way to make sure everything was going well. Our Cuzco representative, Allison, was our very own guardian angel. When we had a situation that caused us to return home earlier than planned, Allison literally took us by the hand, calmed our nerves, aided us in obtaining unscheduled flights and walked us into the airport to make sure that we had all the necessary paperwork for our flight.\r\n \r\nThe staff of Peru For Less made our entire trip fun and worry-free. Thank you for a wonderful trip.  We would recommend your organization without hesitation.\r\n\r\n','\r\nSherry, Terry and Sebert <br />\r\nFlorida, USA\r\n<br />\r\nArequipa, Cuzco, Machu Picchu, Puno','','','',211,0,0,NULL,NULL,NULL),(500,1,'Kristina,  ','\r\nWe had a wonderful time on our adventure in Peru. We enjoyed the diverse schedule of hiking the Inca Trail to wildlife viewing at Lake Sandoval, and spending time in Cuzco and Miraflores. We were at each location for just the right length of time. We greatly appreciate the fact that Peru For Less took care of arranging all of the ground transportation and kept us aware of pickup times the following day.\r\n \r\nI\'d like to thank you personally for doing such a fantastic job of not only coordinating this trip but providing great information and communicating to us so well. We greatly appreciate it!\r\n \r\n','Leslie <br />\r\nWashington, USA\r\n<br />\r\nCuzco, Inca Trail, Machu Picchu, Puerto Maldonado\r\n','','','',212,0,0,NULL,NULL,NULL),(501,1,'Dear Peru For Less','\r\n \r\nYes everything went really smoothly; all the hotels and transfers were right on time. We really loved Refugio and our guide there was a newbie but really a quick learner. We were impressed about the food in the jungle - how do they do it? \r\n\r\nWe loved the new hotel in Aguas Calientes. It was really nicely done. All our guides have been top rate and we lucked out that we got an archaeologist to guide us in Machu Picchu. He was fascinating!\r\n\r\nAll our guides were fabulous. Every one had their own blend and interests.\r\n\r\nThe Vistadome was fun and quite a visual adventure - worth the upgrade!\r\n \r\nAll the staff at each of the hotels were accommodating and willing to please all our needs. \r\n  \r\nThanks for all the work your staff did on our journey. We have already talked up a good review of Peru for less to our family and friends. \r\n \r\nTake care and when can we go back?\r\n\r\n',' Margarita <br />\r\nChicago, IL, USA\r\n<br />\r\nPuerto Maldonado, Cuzco, Arequipa','','','',213,0,0,NULL,NULL,NULL),(502,1,'Hi Rylee and Sebastian,','\r\nOur trip was the best! Loved everything, really it was a just fantastic experience. All of our guides were incredibly knowledgeable and so friendly! Tracy was very helpful and great fun to be around.  Maria Elana and Fabrizio know so much about their respective areas and definitely enriched our visits.  \r\n\r\nRylee, from the moment I spoke with you, you have been nothing but helpful, well informed and responsive. The reason I went with Peru For Less was the ease of planning, the clarity of choices available and the recommendations that you provided. Even when the bookings needed to be altered, you upgraded our change and richly compensated for us as in the hotel changes in Cuzco and in Agua Calientes. We loved our hotels and are very grateful for our dinner and folk show in Cuzco â?? it was really fantastic! Thank you. Our Inkaterra experience was beyond words. Absolutely amazingâ?¦ this was such a perfect way to end our trip. From the incredible excursions to the ease of having an all inclusive program really made for a perfect journey into the jungle!  Elias (our guide) was excellent on all fronts. Thank you for offering this great option on my initial program choices!  \r\n\r\nSebastian, you deserve a gold star.  Thank you for your help while we were stuck in Cuzco. While this unfortunate experience was no fault of PFL, you were easily reached and quick to respond in assisting to come up with a solution. Also a big thank you to you and Rylee for revising our flight plans for the remainder of our trip. This was much appreciated.\r\n\r\nAll in all a great experience and we would highly recommend PFL. \r\n\r\nMany Thanks again!\r\n\r\n','Anne <br />\r\nWilmette, IL, USA\r\n<br />\r\nCuzco, Machu Picchu and Puerto Maldonado','','','',214,0,0,NULL,NULL,NULL),(503,1,'Dear Peru For Less','\r\nThank you so much for following up on our trip. My wife and I had a wonderful time in Peru. We really appreciated you customizing our last minute trip, and dealing with my phone calls and answering all my questions. You did a great job, and we had a lot of fun on all of our tours. Machu Picchu was amazing and it was definitely worth the extra day stay.\r\n\r\nCristina in Cuzco was very friendly and it was a pleasure working with her. She was very informative, and guided us through every step of our journey. She went above and beyond when it came to helping us get to our return flight to Lima. The airline made a last minute change to our reservation and put us on the flight before our original scheduled flight. If it wasn\'t for Cristina running through the airport with us and guiding us to pay the taxes and taking us to security, we would not have made the flight. She did an amazing job! During our whole five day trip we only had a few unexpected problems that we had to deal with. Overall we had an amazing trip, and having the tours and hotels taken care of allowed us to truly enjoy Peru. \r\n\r\n\r\n','Robert <br />\r\nFlorida, USA\r\n<br />Cuzco, Machu Picchu','','','',215,0,0,NULL,NULL,NULL),(504,1,'Hi Rylee,  ','\r\n\r\nThis was an amazing trip and we loved every minute of it. It was very comforting knowing that someone from Peru For Less would be there to greet us every time we got off a plane or train.   You have a great group of people working with you.   \r\n\r\nAs far as our tours, we felt like we hit the jackpot with Carolina, our guide in the jungle and Antonio our guide at Machu Picchu. They both went out of their way to make sure this was an experience of a life time.\r\n\r\nWe really appreciate the time and effort you put into helping us plan this vacation and would be happy to write a testimonial. Polly and I will try to get together next week and see what we can come up with. \r\n\r\nThanks again for all your efforts.\r\n\r\n','Gail <br />\r\nWest Sacramento, CA, USA\r\n<br />\r\nLima, Puerto Maldonado, Cuzco, 2 Day Inca Trail to Machu Picchu','','','',216,0,0,NULL,NULL,NULL),(505,1,'Dear Matt ','\r\nThank you for a fantastic tailor-made holiday to Peru. Firstly, we chose \"Peru For less\" because other companies dictated to us when and where we could go. However, with you it was \"tell us where and when you want to go and we\'ll do the rest\". This was done to a very high standard. Everything went to plan, we were given a very detailed itinerary (who needs a guide book!?) and met by various representatives - always on time, very knowledgeable and pleasant. \r\n\r\nOf course, we loved all the sites - Cuzco, Machu Picchu and Lake Titcaca; they were awesome!  \"Peru For less\" were great when I started feeling unwell on one of the Puno trips, arrangements were made to bring me back to the hotel with speed and efficiency, thank you!\r\n\r\nWe will definitely be using \"Latin America For less\" again and have already recommended you lots of others!\r\n\r\nBest Wishes\r\n\r\n','Disha and family<br />\r\nLondon, UK\r\n<br />\r\nArequipa, Cuzco, Machu Picchu, Puno','','','',217,0,0,NULL,NULL,NULL),(506,1,'Hello Kristina,','\r\n\r\nIt is nice to be back home but our vacation in Peru was wonderful. All the details of the trip were spelled out black and white. Our pick up times were great. We were not left out wondering if someone is going to show up or not. Someone was always there to lead us to the next place, whether it was the hotel, airport, train station or any place mentioned on our trip. Our whole experience was excellent.\r\n\r\nKristina, we really appreciate your patience and understanding. We had so many questions and all were answered by you satisfactorily. You are an excellent travel advisor! We will surely recommend you and your company to all our friends. Thanks again.\r\n\r\n\r\n','Teresita <br />\r\nUSA\r\n<br />\r\nCuzco, Machu Picchu, Lima','','','',218,0,0,NULL,NULL,NULL),(507,1,'Dear Peru For Less','\r\n\r\nAccept my apologies for a delayed testimonial about my Peru trip. I have been crazy busy at work. In any case, here\'s what I have to say about my travel experience to Peruâ?¦\r\n\r\nAwesome! Visiting Machu Pichu was a priceless experience and you made it absolutely enjoyable by organizing every detail of our trip with perfection. I have traveled quite a bit and most definitely this trip was scores a 10/10 for a very well organized and hassle-free as far as travel arrangements are concerned.\r\n\r\nAt the outset I am very appreciative of the fact that you communicated with me even before my trip began and made sure that I had all the details handy. My surprise came in when I actually arrived at Lima and was painlessly transferred to my destination and every person who met us at the airports and transported us to the hotels was just there for us. Every person who met us and detailed us of our daily agenda were very prompt and clear on the plan and gladly answered any questions/concerns we had. It definitely was a luxury to have a well planned trip.\r\n\r\nThe 4 day Inca trail was the highlight of the trip. Even though it was painful :) - it was definitely worth it when we finally arrived at Machu Pichu. Our guide Edgar is a very proud CuzqueÃ±an (rightfully so) and is extremely knowledgeable. I liked his dedication to the trail and the moral support that he gave me all the way through the trail (since I was the slowest in my group, he made sure to stay with me all the way and encouraged me to push harder every time - especially the second day). My heart goes to the 5 porters who carried our camping/food gear with so much ease and were always there at the campsite when we got there with our hot meals/teas. They were the real heroes.\r\n\r\nThe 4th night and 5th day at Aguas Calientes was such a welcome spot after the strenuous hike. \r\n\r\nThe hotels at Cuzco and Aguas Calientes were spotlessly clean and well maintained.\r\n\r\nThe 3 day trip to the Posadas Amazonas Jungle Lodge was one of kind experience. Loved the experience of sleeping in a jungle lodge (although could hardly sleep on first night with all the jungle noises around - but it was worth the experience). The guide Irma was very knowledgeable and we actually managed to spot one of endangered species (sea otters) in the lake. \r\n\r\nI would and have been recommending Peru For Less to all and any one I come across who has an interest of taking up any South American trip.\r\n\r\nThanks Chris, once again. Great job!\r\n\r\nRegards\r\n\r\n','Shanti <br />\r\nMalden, MA, USA<br />\r\nLima, Cuzco, Inca Trail, Machu Picchu, Puerto Maldonado','','','',219,0,0,NULL,NULL,NULL),(508,1,'Hello Rylee,  ','\r\nThank you so much for your email. I was just going to write you but you beat me to it! I wanted to thank you for such a wonderful trip. We had such a great time. Everything was so well organized and it was so nice having people meet us in each location and not have to worry about anything. From the start, you were so sweet and made it so easy to plan exactly what we wanted out of Peru. I really appreciate all of your patience in answering my questions. We loved all of our hotel recommendations and our tours. The staff in Cuzco was also very helpful. I did plan a tour in Lima for our last day, but thank you for your attempts and calling us from home to help us out. \r\n \r\nThank you again, I will try to write more details later, but I just wanted to say, thank you so much Peru For Less!\r\n \r\n\r\n','Chanta <br />\r\nNeptune, NJ, USA\r\n<br />\r\nCuzco, Machu Picchu and Lima','','','',220,0,0,NULL,NULL,NULL),(509,1,'Hi Rylee, ','\r\n\r\nThis trip has been fantastic Rylee!  Thank you.  Sorry to bother you yesterday on your day off! Thank you so much for your assistance in this last minute trip. We had such a great time in Arequipa and are hoping you can book more in the north for us. \r\n\r\nBy the way - we LOVED Posada del Castillo.  It was gorgeous, great views, excellent breakfast, and a really sweet Dutchman owner.  He was really helpful and kind.  It really ended up not mattering that it wasnâ??t in the city center.  It was like a special retreat.\r\n\r\nHave a great rest of your weekend.  Thank you again for going the extra mile for us. \r\n\r\nThanks, \r\n\r\n','Molly <br />\r\nHouston, TX, USA\r\n<br />\r\nArequipa, Colca Canyon ','','','',221,0,0,NULL,NULL,NULL),(510,1,'Dear Peru For Less','\r\nYour travel service was impeccable. Ray and I had a delightful time. All of the guides and people connected with your company were excellent. They were knowledgeable and well informed.\r\n \r\nI can now understand why Machu Picchu is one of the Seven Wonders of the World. It is magnificent. The beauty was pure and unadulterated.\r\n \r\nCuzco reminded me of a cross between France and Spain. This is truly charming city and we especially enjoyed Pisco.\r\n \r\nI would recommend your company and feel comfortable using your services again. I do apologize for the mix up with the credit cards.\r\n \r\nThank you again for the reliable service you provided for us.\r\n \r\nSincerely,\r\n\r\n','Ellen Badgley<br />\r\nSanta Rosa, CA, USA\r\n<br />\r\nLima, Cuzco, Machu Picchu       ','','','',222,0,0,NULL,NULL,NULL),(511,1,'Hi Juan Pablo,','<p>Thanks for inquiring about our trip - which we feel was a once in a life time experience. We loved the intimate experience of the Eden and with only 16 passengers it really felt like family. The crew and guide were also friendly and knowledgeable. The food was fresh and very healthy. We were expecting the highlights to be visiting the islands (which were amazing) but it turned out the highlights were seeing the sea animals up close and personal. The thrill of snorkeling with sea lions, sharks, rays, giant turtles, penguins, and multi-colored fish is hard to describe. We would recommend this experience to anyone who appreciates nature and loves to learn. This was not a relaxing trip - it was an adventure.\r\n</p>\r\n<p>\r\nOur experience in Quito was also very nice. Roberto Peralta was a great guide. \r\n</p>\r\n<p>\r\nWe certainly will think about Peru For Less for our next trip to South America.\r\n</p>\r\nAll the best,\r\n','Kelley  and Barry <br />\r\nNew Glasgow, Canada<br />\r\nQuito, Galapagos\r\n','cavan.jpg','cavan','',679,0,0,NULL,NULL,NULL),(512,1,'Rylee,','<p>Everything was perfect and I can\'t thank you enough for everything you have done for us. You were so patient in answering all my millions of questions and planning a perfect trip. I just wanted to say thank you so much!</p>','Barbara <br />\r\nValley Center, CA USA<br />\r\nCuzco, Inca Trail to Machu Picchu\r\n','rohrer.jpg','rohrer','',680,0,0,NULL,NULL,NULL),(513,1,'Dear Peru For Less','<p>We had a great trip and returned home with lots of pictures and memories from our travel through Peru.  All arrangements with Peru For Less (airport transportation, lodging, tours) worked out well without any complications.  Thank you.  By far the highlight of our trip was exploring Machu Picchu and hiking Wayna Picchu.</p>\r\n <p>\r\nCertainly would recommend Peru For Less to other Peru and South America travelers.  \r\n</p>\r\n<p>\r\nThanks again for all your assistance and making our travels memorable,\r\n </p>\r\n','Michael  &amp; Phillip<br />\r\nWashington, DC and Boston, MA, USA<br />\r\nLima, Cuzco, Machu Picchu\r\n','kremlacek.jpg','','',681,0,0,NULL,NULL,NULL),(514,1,'Dear Peru For Less','<p>We\'d like to say a huge thank you for our truly magnificent holiday. From the moment we arrived until our final flight home we were looked after with the greatest care and attention. All your reps and drivers were always waiting for us, often right outside the doors of airports and stations, with a smile and details of the next stage of our trip. Our tour guides at the various stages were very well informed and good fun. Everything was organized beautifully giving us great piece of mind and the opportunity to really relax and enjoy ourselves. The hotels were spotless and very comfortable. We experienced many wonderful sites and met some lovely Peruvian people. If I had to choose the high spots of our holiday it would have to be Machu Picchu and being able to stay in the park overnight and being the first to watch the sun rising was tremendous and well worth the cost. A bonus was that we were invited to join in the wedding celebrations of a happy couple who had no guests and to share their champagne and wedding cake. Another wonderful surprise came as we returned to Casa Andina Private, Cuzco, for and overnight stop and had been given the luxury suite overlooking the plaza to the front, the best in the hotel. Finally what a surprise to discover our hotel in Lima, Second Home, was the home studio and gallery of the famous Peruvian artist Delfin and what a privilege to meet him and his daughter.\r\n</p>\r\n<p>\r\nWatching the Condors flying in the Colca Canyon was very special and as their immense wings swooped past us we got some great photos. Learning about all the different people, their history and cultures was fascinating. Peru is truly a country of many contrasts and I\'m so glad we visited it whilst it still remains relatively unspoiled by the 21st Century. Can\'t wait to go back and see more. Thank you so much. Hasta la proxima.\r\n</p>\r\n<p>\r\nRegards,\r\n</p>\r\n','Romaine<br />\r\nLima, Arequipa, Cuzco and Machu Picchu, Puno\r\n','romaine-campbell.jpg','','',682,0,0,NULL,NULL,NULL),(515,1,'Rylee,','<p>Martha and I were exhausted from the journey but we still were (and remain) exhilarated by the week we spent in Peru\'s Cuzco and Sacred Valley area with our group of nine family members.</p>\r\n<p>\r\nThe itinerary that we crafted with your help (and patience) was excellent with a good blend of structured activities and free time. I am very glad that we included an initial period of 24 hours of relaxation and accommodation upon our arrival in Cuzco. We needed it partly for the time to adjust to Cuzco\'s altitude and partly to recover from the frenetic pace of activities in Santiago, Chile, for the several preceding days.</p>\r\n<p>\r\nThe time we spent selecting hotels paid off well. The accommodations, food, and staff attention at each one the Casa Andina Private Collection in Cuzco, the Sumaq in Aguas Calientes, and the Pakaritampu in Ollantaytambo were excellent.  (Future Peru For Less travelers may want to know that the Pakaritampu\'s grounds are beautifully maintained and that the hotel buildings are separated from the traffic on the adjoining street by a wall and gate. Some of the Ollantaytambo ruins can be seen from the Pakaritampu\'s garden, and this is aided by a telescope that is set up there.)\r\n</p>\r\n<p>\r\nWhile I don\'t want to sleight the superb service provided by their hotel colleagues (from the front desk to the porters), I want to make special mention of the maitres d\'hotel at the Casa Andina, Emilio, and at the Sumaq, Erick. They and their staffs made us feel both pampered and at-home and they were most helpful in dealing with the special dietary needs of some in our group. In each case, a wide variety and generous amount of food was available for the buffet breakfast; and the Casa Andina had a friendly and efficient chef stationed in the dining room to make eggs to order.  I have to add that the quality of the food preparation and presentation at the Sumaq (where both breakfast and dinner were included in our room rate) was worthy of a dining room in a major city and quite a surprise in the isolated hamlet of Aguas Calientes.</p>\r\n<p>\r\nWe were pleasantly surprised by the provision of a full breakfast (complete with tablecloths) on the early morning train from Cuzco to Machu Picchu. PeruRail provided a box lunch and a fashion show on the mid-day trip from Machu Picchu to Ollantaytambo.\r\n</p>\r\n<p>\r\nPerhaps I should not have waited this long to mention the Peru For Less guides (1) Fabricio at Machu Picchu and (2) David in Cuzco, Ollantaytambo, Pisac and other parts of the Sacred Valley.  The success of this trip and it undoubtedly was a success was dependent upon their knowledge, patience, thoughtful explanations and enthusiasm as well as upon their respective willingness to extend themselves to accommodate my expressed need (picked up by the members of our group) to identify and visit locations that I last had seen 45 years ago!\r\n</p>\r\n<p>\r\nWe were glad to see Christina, the Peru For Less representative in Cuzco, waiting for us outside the terminal as our group was among the last passengers to collect our checked luggage and leave the airport. Christina made sure that we were well-settled at the Casa Andina on the day of our arrival. We are sure that her subsequent behind-the-scenes efforts helped make our week go smoothly. She escorted us to the Cuzco airport at the end of our stay and her presence there was most helpful in assisting my sister Judith in dealing with a boarding pass issue.\r\n</p>\r\n<p>\r\nThank you, Rylee, for the several months of e-mail exchanges that led up to this trip and for helping the Chilean and North American members of our family spend an unforgettable week together in Peru.\r\n</p>','Leo <br />\r\nAlbany, NY, USA<br />\r\nCuzco, Sacred Valley, Machu Picchu<br />\r\n','leo-levy.jpg','leo-levy','',683,0,0,NULL,NULL,NULL),(516,1,'Hello!','The trip was great. Heath River was excellent, as well as the Inca trail. The guides (J. Cusi and Jhandy) as well as the porters were great. \r\n\r\nHad a great time overall. Thanks.','Al and Cheryl <br />\r\nLos Angeles, California, USA<br />\r\nLima, Cuzco, Inca Trail to Machu Picchu, the Amazon\r\n','','','',223,0,0,NULL,NULL,NULL),(517,1,'Rylee,','My wife and I traveled to Cuzco with the Buxton group this week. We had a wonderful experience that we will never forget. Christina and our tour guides could not have been more helpful or informative. Thanks for giving us memories that we will always treasure.','Bob <br />\r\nSimi Valley CA, USA<br />\r\nCuzco/Machu Picchu\r\n','','','',224,0,0,NULL,NULL,NULL),(518,1,'Kelly,','<p>Thanks for all of your help organizing the trip as well as helping me with the luggage situation!  I just returned from the airport where I picked up my delayed bag! </p>\r\n<p>\r\nJust wanted to thank you for everything.  I truly enjoyed my trip to Peru and Machu Picchu, in particular!   </p>\r\n','Thanks again!  \r\n\r\nLinda<br />\r\nLima, Cuzco & Machu Picchu \r\n','','','',225,0,0,NULL,NULL,NULL),(519,1,'Dear Peru For Less','<p>The trip in Peru was great. I had a great time. Peru For Less did an excellent job in customizing my tour and meeting my needs. Everyone in Peru and our tour guides were very friendly, welcoming and knowledgeable. It was my first solo trip out of the country and everything was above excellent. I had lots of fun.  </p>\r\n <p>\r\nThanks Susana and for the rest of the crew,</p>\r\n','Wai <br />\r\nUSA\r\n<br />\r\nLima, Nazca, Cuzco & Mapi\r\n','','','',227,0,0,NULL,NULL,NULL),(520,1,'Dear Peru For Less','Sorry it took so long to respond. The trip went very well. All the guides were wonderful and informative. Our trek with Wyketrek was outstanding. Edwin was a godsend and very patient with his two princesses. Had a great time! I will recommend you to my friends who are coming over in 2011. Thank you very much.','Sandy <br /> \r\nCalifornia, USA\r\n<br />\r\nCuzco & Inca Trail\r\n','','','',226,0,0,NULL,NULL,NULL),(521,1,'Hello Deanna,','<p>Peru was fantastic. Everything went well (seemed to go in our favor) except for the long stay in the Lima airport, but the weather cooperated, pickups were on time and friendly, Machu Picchu was more than we thought, loved the culture and the people. Lake Maldonado was fantastic. </p>\r\n<p>\r\nI rate this trip an A-plus and will travel with you again. I also recommend your site highly.</p>\r\n<p>\r\nThanks for everything,\r\n</p>','Dennis , Vera , Rando <br />\r\nColorado, USA\r\n<br />Lima, Cuzco, Machu Picchu, and Puerto Maldonado\r\n','','','',228,0,0,NULL,NULL,NULL),(522,1,'Hi Kelly, ','<p>Thanks for a putting together such a wonderful trip for my sister Tina and me. I am a resident at Stanford hospital, so getting a one-week vacation is a bonus and going to Peru hassle-free through Peru for Less was awesome. </p>\r\n <p>\r\nOverall, I would say I was very pleased with our itinerary. I loved all the tours in each city, as it was a smaller group so it made it easy to listen to the guide and also the guide was more flexible with the day. For instance, our day into the Sacred Valley, Mary the guide suggested we do the Pisac market in the afternoon instead and see the ruins earlier in the day to avoid the rain - everyone in the group was in agreement since the day before it was raining so hard that we had to miss some of the ruins on account of the weather.\r\n</p>\r\n<p>\r\nThe restaurant recommendations were great. Especially in Cuzco, I went to the Inka Grill and followed the recommendations of the Peru For Less representative Tracy including Incanto which was next to our hotel (their cuy was so yummy!). \r\n </p>\r\n<p>\r\nAlso, thanks for providing information about the airport tax after I asked that in a question about how much cash to bring and to convert to soles. It was helpful to have all this information at hand. I felt prepared for the trip.\r\n </p>\r\n<p>\r\nIn addition, your personal touch prior to our trip was great. I liked our first conversation because you took time to ask me what I was looking for, and kept emailing me promptly. Even when I decided at the last minute that I wanted to do an add-on in my last day in Lima, you made this happen. Overall, the whole trip speaks to the company and their attention to detail and customer service. I did not expect a representative to pick us up from the airport or brief us at each destination individually; I thought there would be other groups of people for this and I was thoroughly happy at the personal touch. In addition to my thanks to you, I would say Daniel Smith (Lima) and Tracy (Cuzco) who were also integral in the experience. \r\n</p>','Thanks,\r\n\r\nJanet<br />\r\nLima, Cuzco and Machu Picchu\r\n','','','',245,0,0,NULL,NULL,NULL),(523,1,'Dear Peru For Less','We were extremely pleased with Peru For Less. At every juncture the representative was there and we were treated extremely well. The only slight hitch happened in Arequipa where the city tour was somehow omitted from our itinerary. This happened to us and another couple. We mentioned this to the rep, and she hastily got a guide and put the tour together. The guide was great. He didn\'t have a van for us and the other couple so he hailed taxies and we went on the city tour. Kudos for quick thinking and quick action. After Peru For Less we went on an Amazon tour with GAP, and they messed things up right from the get-go.\r\n\r\nWe would highly recommend Peru For Less to any of our friends, and will definitely come back to you for future trips of this nature.\r\n\r\nThanks again for a wonderful trip.\r\n','Rosalie & Art <br />\r\nCalgary, Canada\r\n<br />\r\nLima, Paracas/Nazca, Arequipa, Cuzco, Machu Picchu\r\n','','','',244,0,0,NULL,NULL,NULL),(524,1,'Rylee,','<p>I can\'t say enough about the staff at Peru For Less.  I realize we could have gone to Peru for much less but it was worth it to us to not have to worry about anything! Knowing there would be someone to pick us up and get us to the next place was great. </p>\r\n<p>\r\nAllison went above and beyond in helping us at the airport on the last day. She got our boarding passes ahead of time and even waited to make sure we got past the airport tax area. We could have managed but she was wonderful.  \r\nWe had good guides and great drivers!  Driving in Cuzco looks like an art form and all the drivers did a great job.</p>\r\n<p>\r\nOur guides were knowledgeable and very nice. Raymond in Machu Picchu was really good. I have extremely bad knees and that makes me very slow. I told Raymond I would make it but slower than most people. He told us we had him for two hours.  At the two hour mark I told him I knew he had to be somewhere else and he said no problem - he did not have another tour and would actually rather be at Machu Picchu than in town. He was just wonderful to me and helpful as well. We don\'t know what the average wage for a Peruvian is so I hope that we tipped him well. We doubled what Allison recommended for guides. I was very grateful that day that we had a private tour (our paperwork said group) since I was so slow. I saw everything and we had a great day so everything worked out well. I would have felt horrible being slow in a group.\r\n</p>\r\n<p>\r\nEdgar in the Sacred Valley was very knowledgeable but a little more serious than some. Jimmy was great on our Cuzco tour.\r\n </p>\r\n<p>\r\nI was very happy with all the guides and drivers. Everyone we encountered in Peru was nice and helpful, very polite. We were amazed at the cleanliness in Cuzco! We have been to Mexico several times and expected conditions like that so we were pleasantly surprised.  \r\n </p>\r\n<p>\r\nI cannot say enough about how nice it was to not have to worry about how to get somewhere, what time did we need to leave etc. You did it all.\r\n </p>\r\n<p>\r\nWe had a long trip home. Our 3 hour layover in Atlanta turned into 5 due to snow in Denver. So we had to spend an unplanned night on the way home and got home a day late. At least we got home safe and didn\'t have to spend a night in an airport.\r\n </p>\r\n<p>\r\nWe enjoyed the trip and will recommend Peru For Less. \r\n </p>\r\n<p>\r\nThank you for all your help with our questions.\r\n</p>','Debbie<br />\r\nCuzco, Machu Picchu, Sacred Valley\r\n','','','',243,0,0,NULL,NULL,NULL),(525,1,'Rylee,','<p>I can\'t tell you enough how thankful we are to you and the staff at Peru For Less for making this trip so easy and fun for us. You were so accommodating us in the planning process. We were on a tight budget and you were so helpful in rearranging things so they fit our price range. We loved all of your recommended hotels and all of the staff in Cuzco were super helpful. Our guides were also great and the best part of everything is we didn\'t have to do anything but follow our travel program. We loved having everything set and only worrying about what to wear or eat. \r\n </p>\r\n<p>\r\nThank you again for making this trip so easy for us. I will certainly recommend Peru For Less and you to our friends and family. \r\n</p>','Janine and Grez <br />\r\nBoston, MA, USA\r\n<br />\r\nLima, Cuzco, Machu Picchu and Puno\r\n','','','',242,0,0,NULL,NULL,NULL),(526,1,'Hi Kristina,','<p>First let me say that overall our trip was amazing! We truly enjoyed the experience and it\'s a trip memories and friends to last a lifetime! </p>\r\n<p>\r\nCuzco: The hotel was awesome! Our tour guide Kristina was very helpful. We didn\'t have to think; she walked us through everything and made it very easy for us to be in a foreign place. </p>\r\n<p>\r\nTour to sacred valley was great! Our guide was great and we really liked going to the sights and town afterwards. The tour place is heavily involved in community projects and helps local farmers and local people and schools which was really nice. I highly recommend it. He was a lot of fun too.\r\n</p>\r\n<p>\r\nMachu Picchu: We loved our tour guide! He was great! We are so glad we took that tour when we first arrived! Kristina gave us good ideas for the second day in Machu Picchu also. The first day we hiked to the sun gate which was a bit challenging but nice. The second day we waited in line early to be able to climb Waynu Picchu. I highly recommend this. Hotel in Machu Picchu was awesome but unfortunately we got there when it was dark and left in the morning before sun came up so didn\'t get to enjoy it much but it was fabulous. \r\n</p>\r\n<p>\r\nThe Aida Maria and Dario as our tour guide was prob the best experience of our life. We loved the tour, loved Galapagos and met some friends we will have for life. I can go on and on about it. If I were to do it again, I would stay another 2 days in the Galapagos to visit the 2 main islands which the cruise does not go to.\r\n</p>\r\n<p>\r\nI\'ve already recommended you to my mother and two other friends that are interested in going to South America. I will spread the word! Thank you for all your help making our honeymoon the perfect trip!\r\n</p>','Mindy <br /> \r\nNew Jersey, USA\r\n<br />\r\nCuzco, Machu Picchu, Quito & Galapagos Islands\r\n','','','',241,0,0,NULL,NULL,NULL),(527,1,'Hi there!','We had an unforgettable experience! It was really and truly fantastic. Jimmy and his crew were the best. He took very good care of us and was totally enthused to be there! He could answer all our questions and then some! The food was amazing! We were astonished every day by how they produced such fantastic meals with two burners and small tent to work out of! That was great!    We canâ??t say enough. Peru, the people of Peru and Machu Picchu will forever hold special place in my heart.  \r\n\r\nThanks so much,\r\n','Lori <br />\r\nConnecticut, USA\r\n<br />\r\nLima, Cuzco, Inca Trail to Machu Picchu\r\n','','','',240,0,0,NULL,NULL,NULL),(528,1,'Hi Kelly,','<p>Thanks for your note. I am happy to say that we had a wonderful trip to South America!  </p>\r\n <p>\r\nTo answer some of your questions, the transfers and arrangements made by PFL were excellent. I must say it was very nice to have someone waiting for us with a sign bearing my name at the various stops!</p>\r\n<p>\r\n \r\nThe hotels were as expected, very clean with friendly and professional service, and quite adequate. \r\n </p>\r\n<p>\r\nThe Machu Picchu tour was wonderful, and our guide, Fabricio, was excellent. After our tour ended, we spent most of the afternoon walking around the site on our own, and took loads of photos. The following day we explored Aguas Caliente and enjoyed that as well. Generally, all the tour guides were very good.\r\n </P>\r\n<p>\r\nThe Galapagos Journey 1 was excellent in every way. The accommodations were great, the crew was excellent and the guide, Kike, was outstanding. If I had to choose a highlight of the Galapagos trip, I would say it was the tortoises we saw the first day in the Santa Cruz highlands.  But the entire Galapagos experience was wonderful, and I would have been happy to spend a few more days there.\r\n </p>\r\n<p>\r\nIn general, the trip met and even exceeded my expectations. The only change I would make if I were to do it again would be to add a few days of free time in order to relax in between the hectic schedule of tours and travel.  \r\n</p>\r\n<p> \r\nThank you so much for your help in planning this trip, Kelly!  It was definitely a trip to remember!\r\n</p>','                ','','','',239,0,0,NULL,NULL,NULL),(529,1,'Hi Rylee,','<p>Thank you so much for your email. I was actually going to write you today anyway. We are still traveling, but I wanted to thank you for setting up our wonderful trip to Peru. All our transfers and connections were on time. It was so nice to never have to worry about how we were going to get to our hotel. Even in the wee hours of the morning. Our guides were all wonderful and a special thanks to Alison who was great!</p>\r\n<p>\r\nThe hotel Arqueologo was beautiful and they upgraded us to a suite! Machu Picchu was so incredible, better than I could have imagined. I really appreciate all your work in planning our itinerary and answering all my questions - you were so accommodating. I just wanted to say thank you to Peru For Less. We had a terrific time.\r\n</p>','Bob <br />\r\nSevierville, TN, USA\r\n<br />\r\nCuzco and Machu Picchu\r\n','','','',238,0,0,NULL,NULL,NULL),(530,1,'Dear Rylee ','<p>Thank you for your follow up. We were able to find a nice restaurant in Lima and went to the Gold Musuem. Thank you for the suggestion! We had such a fabulous time in Cuzco and Machu Picchu. </p>\r\n<p>\r\nWe had initially contacted Peru For Less to help arrange accommodation and a quick side trip to Machu Picchu as were coming for my brother\'s wedding. Rylee, you were so incredible in planning this trip. I know you worked with my mother as well, but she ended up booking her own services that my brother suggested. I am so happy we booked through Per For Less. Our guides were incredible, our hotels were beautiful and everything was on time and smooth. My mother often mentioned how she regretted not booking with you as well. Her services were not nearly as professional and informative as ours. \r\n</p>\r\n<p>\r\nYou also got back to me quickly and were extremely patient with all of my special requests. Thank you so much. I would like to see if we can set something up to Argentina for the next year sometime. I will be in touch with you about that as well. \r\n</p>\r\n<p>\r\nThank you again to all the staff in Cuzco who made this trip happen with no glitches! I will certainly recommend Peru For Less to all of my friends and family. \r\n</p>','Laura <br />\r\nLeesburg, VA, USA\r\n<br />\r\nCuzco, Machu Picchu\r\n','','','',236,0,0,NULL,NULL,NULL),(531,1,'Dear Matt,','When I came to you so many months ago hoping to plan this once in a lifetime trip I had an idea of what I wanted and the places I wanted to visit. I knew I wanted to visit as much as South America as I could in a month. Throughout the whole planning process you were so great with me and always responded right away and were there whenever I need anything at all! The fact that you could customize everything for me to make sure I got exactly what I wanted was awesome.  Machu Picchu was awesome! The Iguazu Falls were breathtaking! The tour in Rio through Sugarloaf and the Christ the Redeemer statue will stay with me forever!  Being able to experience the beauty and culture of so many different places in one trip was exactly what I was hoping for and it more than exceeded my expectations. The guides, hotels, and everyone I met along the way was so helpful and everyone was always on time and made my experience that much better.  I know if I travel again through South America you will be the first person I come to.  Thanks again for everything as you did a fantastic job!','S.G.\r\nNew Orleans, USA\r\n<br />\r\nLima, Cuzco, Machu Picchu, Santiago, Buenos Aires, Bariloche, Iguazu, Rio de Janeiro\r\n','','','',235,0,0,NULL,NULL,NULL),(532,1,'Hi Kelly, ','We had a wonderful time in Peru. The food, music and sights were incredible. We absolutely loved Machu Picchu and our flight over the Nazca Lines. Peru for less did a great job of getting us from place to place not to mention our excellent guides Mr. Paul in Ica and Leo in Nazca. You did a great job of organizing our side trip and everything went so smoothly. I would have enjoyed meeting you for a drink but we just ran out of time. We hope to return to your beautiful country some time soon.\r\n\r\n\r\nThank you so much,\r\n','Denise <br />\r\nIca, Nazca, Paracas\r\n','','','',234,0,0,NULL,NULL,NULL),(533,1,'Hi Rylee,','<p>We are finally home, and trying to recover from all our sight-seeing mania! The portion of our trip that was covered by Peru For Less was a delight, in that we were met at the airport, transported to our hotel, met there by one of your reps, and everything explained to us.</p>\r\n<p>\r\nEvery time we went somewhere, the guide was excellent. You did an outstanding job of being where you said you would be, and doing what you said you would do. I would not hesitate to recommend your services to someone else coming to Peru.   </p>\r\n<p>\r\nThank you for making that phase of our journey so enjoyable, and easy. Wish I had used you for the rest of it!\r\n</p>\r\n<p>\r\nThanks to all of you,\r\n</p>\r\n','Sue <br />\r\nOdessa, Florida, USA \r\n<br />\r\nCuzco/Machu Picchu\r\n','','','',233,0,0,NULL,NULL,NULL),(534,1,'Hello Jennifer,','<p>We just arrived in Miami. We had a very nice time. We loved Casa San Blas, the service was phenomenal! Cristina was very punctual and explained everything very well. Edwin gave us the city tour. He was very professional and dressed very nice. Sylvia gave us the Sacred Valley tour and she was excellent. We loved her tour. Fabrizio who did the Macchu Picchu was also great: very interesting explanations, simple and to the point.</p>\r\n<p>\r\nThank you for everything!</p>\r\n','Monica <br />\r\nTexas, USA\r\n<br />\r\nCuzco, Machu Picchu\r\n','','','',237,0,0,NULL,NULL,NULL),(535,1,'Rylee,','We just arrived back home and had a wonderful time. What an amazing experience!  Just want to thank you for all your help in making our trip possible. The flights were all on time and everything worked out well. Thanks again and if we ever go back to Peru we will definitely get in touch for your help and guidance. ','Linda <br />\r\nPeru<br />\r\nSeattle, Washington, USA\r\n','','','',232,0,0,NULL,NULL,NULL),(536,1,'Hi Matt,','<P>Thanks so much once again for putting our holiday together. </P>\r\n <p>\r\nMy favorite part of the tour was the Iguazu falls followed closely by Macchu Pichu. All the guides were extremely informative and polite putting up with us and we adored our porters and of course personal chef on the trail. I was very proud of Anna who has never roughed it to this extent before. Was a bit worried though after the 1st day of the trek as she woke up and said she couldn\'t move and that her back hurt (thought she might go home!) but she persevered and finished it.  \r\n </p>\r\n<p>\r\nI think I will have to go back and visit some of the places we missed.</p>\r\n <p>\r\nI am glad you enjoyed your dinner and pressies. You deserved it with all the hard work you put into our trip. So make sure you come to Australia soon and pay us a visit.  \r\n</p>','Cheers\r\n<br />\r\nSydney\r\n<br />\r\nBuenos Aires, Iguazu, Rio de Janeiro, Lima, La Paz, Puno, Cuzco and Machu Picchu (Inca Trail), Buenos Aires\r\n','','','',231,0,0,NULL,NULL,NULL),(537,1,'Dear Kristina and Hayley,','<p>It was an excellent, seamless and well thought-out trip. I am very impressed by the quality of the package put together by Argentina For Less and Peru For Less and how specific requests and interests were easily accommodated e.g. the trip to Racchi to see the temple of viracocha. The tour guide at Cuzco, Mary, was impressive in her knowledge and very engaging particularly since we had some problem with altitude sickness. She patiently brought us to oxygen stations in Cuzco, Ollantaytambo and was considerate in ensuring we had sufficient supplies of water as well as cough medicine when I caught a cold. The driver, Joel, was cheerful and helpful and this made the entire trip very agreeable and enjoyable. We also enjoyed Frank Elias the tour guide at Macchu Picchu, who provided a lot of information about Inca technology and religion and showed us his favourite spot for taking a wonderful photo of Machu Picchu framed by an overhanging rock. The quality of the tour guides, their friendliness, willingness and ability to answer many questions, was excellent. Peru was outstanding. The people are beautiful, the history and culture captivating, even if sad sometimes (the politics at least) and I learnt a lot about the country, which was very satisfying. And I have to say Peruvian pastries rank amongst the top in the world!\r\n </p>\r\n<p>\r\nWe enjoyed Argentina and Chile as well (excellent steak!) and the Cape Horn tour was relaxing and informative. All the travel connections and flights worked well and I would have to say this is one very satisfied customer. I have traveled extensively and widely all over the world and usually do so with minimal input from tour companies but I am certainly glad I came across your website and had expert assistance in planning my travels. This was my first venture to Latin America from Asia; I hope it won\'t be the last. If I visit other Latin American countries in the future, I am glad that I will have a wonderful resource in your company. A good plan grounds a good tour and that is certainly what Argentina for Less and Peru For Less provided through its expertise, ability to accommodate and efficiency. Kudos!\r\n</p>','Dr. Li-ann <br />,\r\n\r\nSingapore\r\n<br />\r\nLima, Cuzco, Buenos Aires, Patagonia cruise\r\n','','','',230,0,0,NULL,NULL,NULL),(538,1,'Hi Kristina,','<p>Everything about our trip was awesome.  We had a great time and you did an amazing job putting it together Kistina.  Your company will come highly recommended. We just wanted to say thanks for doing such a great job organizing our trip. You were nothing but understanding and helpful during the whole process, even when we were probably asking stupid and annoying questions.  We\'re going to have a great time.\r\n</p>\r\n<p>\r\nYou\'re a class act!\r\n</p>','Sincerely,<br />\r\nScott <br />\r\nCanada\r\n<br />Cuzco, Inca Trail, Lima & Mancora\r\n','','','',229,0,0,NULL,NULL,NULL),(539,1,'Hi Kelly,','<p>Thanks for checking up on the trip. Everything was fantastic: from the 2 hotels we stayed at and the food at the Sumaq was outstanding! The customer service and cleanliness was perfect at both hotels. We did a ton of hiking and went to the top of Macchu Picchu Mountain on our first day at the site. We have awesome pictures as well. The whole country is surreal and phenomenal.  Christina with Peru for Less was extremely helpful.  The only drawback was the 9 hour layover in Lima but we got over it and I wish we had another week to tour the Amazon but we had to get back to work. If you want me to put any testimonials anywhere just let me know. Cuzco is wonderful.  \n</p>\n<p>\nThanks,\n</p>\n','Lauren \r\nCuzco & Machu Picchu \r\n','','','',259,0,0,NULL,NULL,NULL),(540,1,'Hi Kelly!  ','<p>We had an amazing trip thanks to your services; transfers and assistance were seamless.  We would like to communicate the highest praise for each Peru for Less representative we encountered:  Tracy and David in Cuzco and Miguel in Lima and of course yourself.  Each representative was kind, knowledgeable, friendly and fun!  When we toured with a group the guides were responsive and flexible with the group\'s desires.  We would like for everyone to know when you travel abroad (any foreign country not just Peru)  the accommodations are not exactly comparable to those we have in the states, however every property we inhabited were clean, neat and functional.  We attribute the enriching experience our family had to the professionalism, responsiveness and thoughtfulness of the Peru for Less staff both stateside and abroad.  \r\nThank you again for a most memorable trip and we are happy to recommend your services without hesitation.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Merry Christmas and God Bless You!  </p>\r\n','Fanchee, John and Willard <br/>\r\nTexas, USA <br/>\r\nLima, Cuzco, &amp; Machu Picchu','whitaker-willard.jpg','','',684,0,0,NULL,NULL,NULL),(541,1,'Hi Kelly,','<p>Our trip to Peru was wonderful! Thanks for all of your help!  </p>\r\n\r\n<p>We absolutely loved every second of the 12 days we spent in Peru!  Thank you for all of the work you did preparing the itinerary and answering all of my many questions!  We did a lot of traveling around the country by planes, trains and buses & everything ran seamlessly.  All of your reps and drivers were not only on time, but were wonderfully friendly, our tour guides were very knowledgeable and a lot of fun and our hotels were great!  Machu Picchu was amazing, as was our guide Fabricio (he even managed to get a free walking stick for a member of our group who injured his leg the day before).  Other highlights include Arequipa and the Colca Canyon, both of which we absolutely loved.  The horseback riding through the countryside in Arequipa with Anibal was so much fun and our tour guide in the Colca Canyon was fantastic (I felt a little sick when we hit 4900 meters above sea level, but our tour guide was prepared with a number of herbs in addition to coca leaves that worked like a charm!)  Our time in Cuzco was also great, and Christina was very helpful & gave us tonnes of great tips about what to do and where to eat! </p>\r\n\r\n<p>Thanks for everything!  </p>\r\n','Jennifer <br/>\r\nOntario, Canada <br/>\r\nArequipa, Puno, Cuzco &amp; Machu Picchu\r\n','higgins-jennifer.jpg','','',685,0,0,NULL,NULL,NULL),(542,1,'Hi Riva,','<p>Thank you Peru For Less for making our first trip to South America, an unforgettable one! Everything was very well organized and followed our itinerary to the tee.\r\nWe would have never been able to visit all the places without your help especially as our Spanish is pretty rudimentary! The agents at every location were knowledgeable and very helpful.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Deanna and Riva helped us plan the perfect trip. Thank you Riva for arranging our final transfer to the airport so we were not spending too much time waiting.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>The guides that you arranged were very passionate about Peru. This enhanced our \"Peruvian\" experience. I would and will recommend you to anyone visiting Peru.\r\nThank you,</p>\r\n','K. <br/>\r\nClawson, MI <br/>\r\nLima, Puerto Maldonado, Cuzco, Machu Picchu, Puno','patel.jpg','','',686,0,0,NULL,NULL,NULL),(546,1,'Hi Rylee,','<p>When I was looking into booking our honeymoon trip to Peru, I was initially skeptical - Peru For Less is definitely cheaper than the alternatives (which is great for two grad students on a limited budget), but would we be sacrificing reliability or quality? However, even before we arrived in Peru, I knew we had made the right choice.<strong> I liked being able to choose every hotel </strong>(I read reviews online so I knew just what to expect, but the PFL options were all well-chosen to begin with), <strong>and Rylee was great about answering my many questions quickly and comprehensively.</strong> We were able to easily mix and match hotels with different numbers of stars (so we could have a little luxury on our honeymoon) as well as add a horseback riding trip.</p>\n\n\n<p>We really enjoyed our trip from start to finish. <strong>From the time we were met at the airport in Lima to our flight out of Cuzco, everything was taken care of.</strong> Even when we had to take a different train back from Machu Picchu that didn\'t go all the way to Cuzco, the PFL rep was there waiting for us at the train station to drive us the rest of the way.</p>\n<p>In general, the hotels were really nice. One exceptional hotel was the Sumaq in Machu Picchu - it was the most expensive, but definitely worth it! We enjoyed the luxury after a day spent hiking around Machu Picchu in the hot sun.</p>\n<p>The tours were also great - the guides were knowledgeable, and we especially enjoyed the stop at the llama/alpaca farm on the trip to Ollantaytambo and the horseback riding on the last day (a great way to see the countryside). And your director\'s restaurant recommendations were spot-on - especially Cicciolina, which could certainly compete with the restaurants here in San Francisco.</p>\n<p>All in all, we came back with many great memories of our honeymoon, and I\'d definitely recommend PFL to anyone traveling to South America.</p>\n<p>Thanks again! </p>\n','Meredith (Berkeley, CA, USA) <br/>\r\nTraveled to: Lima, Cusco, Sacred Valley, Machu Picchu\r\n\r\n','','','\"We came back with many great memories of our honeymoon, and I\'d definitely recommend PFL to anyone traveling to South America.\"',100040,0,0,NULL,'2014-09-10 23:13:20',NULL),(547,1,'Hi Rylee, ','<p>Thank you for your email and the attention to my trip from planning stages through safe return home.  I appreciate yours extra care through my numerous flight plan changes. Sorry!  I was met right at the airport by Allison whose knowledge of the city, the country and my language really paved the way for a great trip.  The transportation was right on time - every time.  The tours recommended took me to some great places I hadn\'t even considered, like Ollantaytambo and Huayna Picchu.  These were great finds.  The purpose of my trip was to see Machu Picchu, and again Peru For Less staff made it great.  Fabricio met me at the train, and gave such a passionate tour of this magical place; I could see it through their eyes.  Other groups who went in on their own were quite literally lost.  I met some other tourists who had been there for hours and didn\'t know what most things were because they had no guide and there are very few signs inside.  Just from what Fabricio told me, I showed them more about Machu Picchu in 40 minutes than they had learned all day.</p>\r\n<p> I\'ll certainly be using your services again!</p>','Jason <br/>\r\nKent, <br/>\r\nCuzco and Machu Picchu\r\n','','','',688,0,0,NULL,NULL,NULL),(548,1,'Hi Jennifer,','<p>We really enjoyed our trip to Peru. Everything went smoothly (the only exception is the 5-hour flight delay from LA to SFO on the way back. Thank God that it was not the way to Peru!).</p>\r\n \r\n<p>I liked Lima and was surprised to see how clean/safe/developed the city wasâ?¦ We had a great time strolling around/doing shopping/eating thereâ?¦ I personally liked the hotel in Lima: clean and quiet. Cusco, a small world heritage town, was also nice. Great place to see/shop/eatâ?¦ I enjoyed the Cusco city and ruins tour and the Sacred Valley tour despite some rain. And the hotel we stayed at in Sacred Valley was too cute as if it was a French cottage.</p>\r\n \r\n<p>To be honest, the trip to Machu Picchu was a bit hectic since we could stay there only several hoursâ?¦ It was magnificent and definitely worth visiting, but it was a shame I did not have time to go to Inca bridge, let alone Huayna Picchu. I wished I could have had one more day to go to those places or even more days to enjoy trekkingâ?¦butâ?¦ it has become an unforgettable experience :)-. Oh, it was fun to see the alpaca fashion show in the train back too! </p>\r\n \r\n<p>As a whole, I truly enjoyed our stay in Peru. Thank you, Jennifer and all the other Peru for Less staff for everything.  As I said, I wished I could have had a few more days in Machu Picchu and probably one more day to Lima. I will definitely want to go back there again sometime in the future.</p>\r\n \r\n<p>Give my big thanks to all the people who made our trip to Peru so memorable.</p>\r\n','Yukari  <br />\r\nLima, Cusco, Machu Picchu\r\n','','','',258,0,0,NULL,NULL,NULL),(549,1,'Hi Rylee,','<p>We had a great trip to Cuzco and Machu Picchu.  Everything went well and we enjoyed the trip very much.  Everyone was very professional and helpful.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Thanks again for good planning and arrangements.</p>\r\n','Vijay<br />\r\nCopley, OH, USA\r\n<br />\r\nCuzco and Machu Picchu\r\n','','','',257,0,0,NULL,NULL,NULL),(550,1,'Hi Riva, ','<p>The trip was really great. We really enjoyed Iguazu and the hotel. A trip to never forget. I also want to say that it was well organized. So thank you and have a great day.</p>\r\n\r\n','Kasper <br />\r\nThe Netherlands\r\n<br />\r\nIguazu Tour\r\n','','','',256,0,0,NULL,NULL,NULL),(551,1,'Hi Rylee!','<p>John and I REALLY enjoyed our South American adventure, and first and foremost want to say a HUGE THANK YOU to you Rylee, for all your time, assistance, patience and guidance. We really appreciate it and feel lucky to have been able to â??findâ? you to help us plan this trip and make it a reality. As you know it did take long time to finally get the right timing, itinerary and costing for us, and I am just so grateful for all that you did â?? you were always so prompt in responding and also providing informative replies. Thank you.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>The hotels that you recommended and managed to book for us were great and also in such convenient locations, allowing us to be able to walk to main areas and sights etc.  The one in Cusco (Archealogo) was definitely my favorite â?¦our room was just beautiful: wooden floors and even the four poster bed, it was just so quaint and delightful.  The hotel in Rio â?? Martinique â?? I must say had such good service, friendly and helpful. The Buenos Aires hotel â?? Las Americas â?? was a superb location, we truly loved Recoleta and could walk easily to various places I had researched and also managed to use the subway.  </p>\r\n\r\n<p>Buenos Aires was one of the places that really surprised us and we just fell in love with it. However each place in our itinerary had its own character and uniqueness and we loved visiting them all.  The tours included in the package which we had were wonderful, with good overview of main sights and allowed us to get a taste of each place.  Obviously it was a very busy and full itinerary but great to be able to see and do so much.  We had added in the two additional â??excursionsâ? of the Dinner Samba Show (Brazil) and also the Dinner Tango Show (Buenos Aires).  The Dinner Tango Show was absolutely top class, we felt like celebrities and the quality of the venue, food and dancing was impeccable. It was a truly fantastic evening.  </p>\r\n\r\n<p>The pickups and transfers in Brazil and Argentina all went smoothly, people were there on time to meet us and also friendly and helpful.  Machu Picchu was glorious â?? even in the rain  - and all the sights and places visited in and around Cusco as well as the Lima tour were fabulous. We really enjoyed it.  New Years eve was lots of fun â?? we spent it in the main square and since we had gone for a truly magnificent dinner the night before at Inka Grill (had to try the Alpaca), we decided on New Years Eve to rather visit several of the places for drinks etc, it was great fun and very festive (very chilly too).</p>\r\n\r\n<p>It was a truly magnificent experience visiting Brazil, Argentina and Peru and most of all we THANK YOU Rylee for arranging it and making it so amazing.  Thanks also to Peru for Less for our t-shirt surprise, they are great.</p>\r\n','Kind and Leanne <br />\r\nGrand Cayman Islands\r\n<br />\r\nRio de Janeiro, Iguazu Falls, Buenos Aires, Lima, Cuzco and Machu Picchu\r\n','','','',255,0,0,NULL,NULL,NULL),(552,1,'Hi Jennifer!','<p>I had a great time in Peru and Ecuador and a smooth ride back home. I had a great time with Jaqui everywhere that we went and I am currently planning another trip to Peru in a few months to see her again. I feel very fortunate for having seen Machu Picchu and the Sacred Valley, given the events have occurred this past week.  Even though we did not have much time in Quito, we did have the opportunity to visit the equatorâ?¦ Standing on that imaginary line was a very unique experience for me. I already knew about the Coriolis Effect and the rotation of fluids in the northern and southern hemispheres, however, I had no idea that a person\'s balance was so bad when standing on that line. That was quite a learning experience.  I enjoyed all the excursions to the islands and the beaches. The (Galapagos) islands are wonderful. This is definitely a place that I would want to visit again one day.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>The entrance tickets for Machu Picchu and the bus tickets for Jacqueline were booked for a foreigner and not for a Peruvian. As a result, the guide that met us at the Aguas Calientes station took Jaqui\'s old bus and entrance tickets and refunded the money, so that the less expensive tickets for a Peruvian national could be bought.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>I really enjoyed my time in Peru and Ecuador. Thank you.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Regards, </p>\r\n','Rad <br />\r\nCanada and Peru\r\n<br />\r\nLima and Peru Special 7: Inspiring Incas &amp; Great Galapagos\r\n','','','',254,0,0,NULL,NULL,NULL),(553,1,'Hi Kelly,','<p>I had a great time on my trip! You were very helpful in planning the trip, thank you.</p>','Thanks!\r\nJP\r\n<br />\r\nLima, Cuzco, Machu Picchu\r\n','','','',253,0,0,NULL,NULL,NULL),(554,1,'Hi Rylee,','<p>Julia and I are safely back in the US.  Thanks again for all of your help with planning and re-planning our trip.  We enjoyed our time in Peru despite the natural disaster and state of emergency! We really enjoyed working with you!  Thanks again for all your advice, assistance, and support!</p>','Rakhee and Julia <br />\r\nPhiladelphia, PA, USA\r\n<br />\r\nCusco\r\n','','','',252,0,0,NULL,NULL,NULL),(555,1,'Dear Peru For Less','<p>To cut a long story short: We have had the trip of our life! What a beautiful country!  From the moment we arrived at the airport in Peru until the day we left, we have been treated as kings (and queens) by your team in Peru. With no exception, all staff members were extremely friendly, very knowledgeable and an extreme pleasure to deal with. </p>\r\n\r\n<p>We were very much aware of the fact that our schedule was loaded with trips and events, but due to the fact that everything was extremely well-organized and perfectly timed, we never felt under pressure to get things done. A tremendous compliment to your guides in Lima, Puerto Maldonado, Cusco, Machu Picchu, Sacred Valley and Puno- it was such a pleasure to see how dedicated and accommodating they all were and how much they all could tell about the places we have been to. I am so glad that you were able to include a trip to the Maras Moray salt mines, as that was certainly one of the most impressive places we have ever been to; my kids must have taken at least 100 pictures that day.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Our stay in the Refugio Amazonas jungle lodge in the rainforest was a blast. It was a great place to stay and our guide Carol was one of the nicest people we have ever met. It was a great experience to learn about all the environmental efforts and activities that take place in this well protected part of the jungle.  Both our kids (17 and 20) enjoyed every second of our stay.\r\nNext to visiting Machu Picchu of course, we consider the train ride from Cusco to Puno as one of the highlights of our trip; we were thrilled that our guide in Cusco was able to arrange the trip in spite of the ongoing railway strikes.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>I could go on for ages, but the bottom-line is that this was one of the best travel experiences we ever had.   Peru for Less had not been able to do a better job. We are impressed by the quality of your service, people and communication. My special thanks to you Aimee! It took a while to get all things in place, but I have never felt a more personal touch than the one you added to our planning experience. We literally had NO negative surprises at all and everything was as good as or even better than we had hoped for.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>There is no doubt that we will utilize Peru For Less for any South America related trips in the future! </p>\r\n\r\n<p>Looking forward to our next trip with Peru For Less! </p>\r\n','Best <br />, \r\nHans, Ellen, Danielle and Martine <br /> \r\nStamford, CT, USA \r\n<br />\r\nPeurto Maldonado, Cuzco, Puno\r\n','','','',251,0,0,NULL,NULL,NULL),(556,1,'Dear Latin America for Less, ','<p>Our trip was spectacular. Kelly (our travel advisor) seemed to be helping us all the time whether it was her day to work or not. She actually took time to meet with us in Miraflores as our ship sailed by Lima on the way to our tour staring point in Buenos Aires two weeks later.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Juana, the representative who first greeted us as the port in Argentina, was an angel.  It was pouring rain when we were to meet her and as we disembarked the ship, she gave us a warm welcome, took over all of our worries, and took our bags and put us in a waiting car.  Then she took care of everything at the hotel and gave us tons of info to help us get started.  She is just outstanding. The next day we went to the Dinner and Tango Show.  The dinner was perhaps the best dinner I have ever had.  This set a very high standard for the rest of our trip. Oh, and Bob was delighted with the ease of having a buffet breakfast every morning.  </p>\r\n\r\n<p>The transfers Kelly arranged were a huge part of the tension free transitions we had between stops and the Peru for Less people were always there waiting patiently for us.  Jana in Buenos Aires, Allison in Cusco and Dan in Lima transitioned us seamlessly and were delightful to work with.  </p>\r\n\r\n<p>Thanks for being great hosts. The Latin America for Less team is awesome. Your updated itineraries were fantastic guides.  You will get great recommendations from us.</p>\r\n<p>Thanks so much.</p>\r\n','Kathy and Bob <br /> \r\nBuenos Aires, Iguazu, Lima, Cuzco, &amp; Machu Picchu\r\n','','','',250,0,0,NULL,NULL,NULL),(557,1,'Dear Peru For Less','<p>We had a WONDERFUL trip.  We were very lucky with the weather and enjoyed Machu Picchu, both sides of Iguazu and Rio.  We were very pleased that a representative was waiting for us each time we arrived at a new location and we were safely delivered to our next destination.  I must say our favorite tour and guide was in Buenos Aires with Victoria. She was fantastic and her love of the city really came through during our day tour. </p>\r\n\r\n<p>Every transfer between airports and hotels and vice versa was flawless.  Each guide made sure we had their contact information and we knew we could call at anytime with any issues.  We were very happy with those who greeted us upon our arrival in Lima and Cusco.  Tracey carefully reviewed our itinerary with us both upon our arrival and when she sent us off to Machu Picchu the next day.  The drivers were very pleasant and the vans were in excellent condition.  Our hotels were very nice and the dining room at our Aguas Calientes served a delicious dinner which was included in our package. Considering Matt and I moved through three countries in about 12 days we had a remarkable time and were very happy with the service we received.  I really do appreciate all of your help with the planning and preparation of all of the activities we wanted to participate in. It was a pleasure working with you.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Thank you again!</p>\r\n','The <br />\r\nSan Diego, CA, USA\r\n<br />\r\nCuzco, Machu Picchu, Buenos Aires, Iguazu, Rio De Janeiro \r\n','','','',249,0,0,NULL,NULL,NULL),(558,1,'Hi Rylee.  ','<p>Everything went great and I would definitely recommend you guys to friends (already have, in fact)â?¦  I appreciate how flexible you guys were when it came to customizing itineraries and also modifying details late in the process. Your biggest nightmare is that you\'re going to sign up with a company that takes your deposit and then does everything they can to charge you even more or not issue refunds when appropriate, but you guys did neither.  I spent as much as I was comfortable spending, and when it became necessary to issue a small refund for a portion we were canceling, you guys did it right away, which was really great.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>I\'m probably going to write a couple of articles instead.  I\'m the CEO of Newsvine and we\'re owned by MSNBC.com so I was planning on writing a piece on Peru and a piece on the Galapagos Islands for Newsvine... travel section.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Cheers and thanks again,</p>','Mike <br />\r\nSeattle, WA, USA\r\n<br />\r\nCuzco, 2 Day Inca Trail to Machu Picchu and Galapagos Islands\r\n','','','',248,0,0,NULL,NULL,NULL),(559,1,'Dear Peru For Less','<p>Our trip was fantastic. Peru is a beautiful country that we truly enjoyed.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>The hotels we chose were all good, but the Inkaterra La Casona in Cusco was one of the best hotel experiences we have ever had. The rooms are beautiful and equipped with every modern amenity from the heated floors, heated towel racks to the staff placing heated bottles in the beds to warm it while you are out enjoying your dinner. The contents of the minibar are included. The staff is fantastic. The restaurant is excellent and the location of the hotel is primeâ?¦ the Inkaterra Machu Picchuâ?¦ offer several complimentary tours around the grounds. Their orchid collection is outstanding. In Lima, the airport hotel was clean and convenient. The JW Marriott in Miraflores was an outstanding value and a very modern hotel with all the modern American conveniences.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>As for our tours and transfers, everything was right on time and as scheduled. Jhanet, the tour guide for the City Tour of Cusco was exceptional and really knew her stuffâ?¦ The dinner and show at Tunapa was very entertaining and the food was good with a large variety to choose from. In Cusco, we did 3 memorable things on our free day: 1) Visited the Jesuit church opposite the cathedral in the Plaza de Armas (fascinating and beautiful); 2) visited the Inka museum and 3) visited the Museum of PreColumbian art. All of these things were very much worthwhile and interesting. We also visited the local market for a perspective on local Cusco life. Our tour planner in Cusco, Tracy, was also very helpful and right on time with her pickups. She made sure we knew everything to do at the airport, hotel and gave us other valuable local information.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>We self booked the Hiram Bingham train to and from Machu Picchu and this was absolutely worth it. This was truly a memorable experience and very first class. The food, the service, the entertainment was second to none. They also provided a very capable guide in Machu Picchu as well as an elaborate tea at the Sanctuary Lodge. On the trip back, it was New Yearâ??s Eve and they certainly did that with panache. Once we boarded the train, we received hats, masks, confetti blasters, feather boas and champagne (Moet et Chandon). The party started immediately. The food was outstanding. They had a jazz band with dancing. The staff was phenomenal as well. We also were able to take the private bus back to the train on our second day at Machu Picchu.</p>\r\n','Sincerely,\r\nRena <br />\r\nFlorida, USA\r\n<br />\r\nLima, Cusco, Machu Picchu\r\n','','','',247,0,0,NULL,NULL,NULL),(560,1,'Hi Rylee,','<p>The trip was fantastic from A to Z. The guides were lovely and so informative. Each place we visited was magic. </p>','Cheers and\r\nCindy <br />\r\nMarin County, CA, USA\r\n<br />\r\nArequipa/Colca Canyon, Cuzco, Puerto Maldonado and Lima\r\n','','','',246,0,0,NULL,NULL,NULL),(561,1,'Kelly','<p>We had a wonderful time during our trip.  You and your colleagues did a terrific job planning our trip with all details covered.  Please convey our thanks to Kaitlin and Allison who we saw in Cuzco.  The hotels were great.  We look forward to working with you on our future plans in South America.  We will also recommend to you others that may be travelling in the region.</p>\r\n \r\n<p>Thanks again.  </p>\r\n','Vishal and Rina <br />\r\nCusco &amp; Machu Picchu\r\n','','','',395,0,0,NULL,NULL,NULL),(562,1,'Hello Peru For Less and especially Rylee!!!','<p><strong>Thank you so much for your consistent hard work and dedication to fulfill our needs,</strong> even when the strike in Cusco did not allow us to go to Sacred Valley, you still managed to change the train tickets for us to come early from Machu Picchu which allowed us to have a tour of the Sacred Valley.</p>\r\n<p>We liked everything: how the trip was scheduled (everything in timing manner), quality of hotels and especially the tour guides. In Lima Giovana Rojas our tour guide for that destination was remarkable, sweet and kind. She was able to answer all our questions and make sure we had fun at the same time!</p>\r\n<p>In Cusco we had Maria as our tour guide and she too was amazing. There wasn\'t a detail that she left out. She also made sure we were comfortable and happy with the stay. For the Sacred Valley, our tour guide made sure we had an easy time making it up the steps and helped us while describing the historic sight.</p>\r\n<p><strong>In Machu Picchu we had an especially nice gentleman named Fabricio. He explained this sacred place in such a matter that we all felt a little bit of magic light up in us.</strong> We also weren\'t feeling well and he made sure to take it slow and helped us in any way we needed, we would especially like in this email to personally thank him for his kindness!</p>\r\n<p>Our Nazca guide, Freddy was also very helpful, he warned us about the hot desert and made sure we had sunscreen and mosquito repellent so we wouldn\'t be harmed. His information was also very insightful.\r\n<p>Lastly, in Puno for Lake Titicaca, we had George as our tour guide. He helped us with things he wasn\'t obligated to do and that really made us feel better. He also did a wonderful job touring.\r\n<p>And <strong>all in all, it couldn\'t have been a better trip.</strong></p>\r\n<p>THANK YOU SOOOOO MUCH PERU FOR LESS!</p>\r\n','The Melen Group Fair Lawn (New Jersey, USA) <br/>\r\nTraveled to: Lima, Nazca, Puno, Cuzco and Machu Picchu\r\n\r\n','','','\"In Machu Picchu..  [our guide] Fabricio.. explained this sacred place in such a matter that we all felt a little bit of magic light up in us.\"',100056,0,0,NULL,'2014-09-10 23:08:24',NULL),(563,1,'Hi Kelly,','<p>Yes! Thank you so much again! Everything worked out so well with the tour, hotels and transportation! You did an awesome job of explaining to me what to expect and the tour guides: Christina, Fabricio, David and the drivers were all wonderful and helpful!</p>\r\n \r\n<p>When I told you how hesitant I was of traveling alone, you gave me assurance and this is actually the best trip I\'ve ever had! (out of the other 30+ something I\'ve taken).</p>\r\n \r\n<p>I did have an awesome time at Machu Picchu, however the highlight of this journey was climbing up to Wayna Picchu! Totally a must for everyone who wants to see the different view of Machu Picchu!</p>\r\n \r\n<p>Again, Kelly, thank you so much for organizing this trip!</p>\r\n \r\n<p>Kind Regards,</p>\r\n','Cherry <br>\r\nChicago, IL<br>\r\nCusco, Machu Picchu\r\n','','','',690,0,0,NULL,NULL,NULL),(564,1,'Rylee,','<p>This was my first time travelling with Peru for less. I found them on the internet so there is always a little trepidation as to what you are going to get. Rylee did a great job individualizing my vacation and offering suggestions before departure. When I got to Peru I found a very professional organization. All the connections worked smoothly and the drivers and guides were very helpful. The hotels we were booked into were excellent. My daughter and I took the 4 day Inca Trail and the guides and porters seemed to take a real pride in their jobs and making the non fit, non campers in our group comfortable.</p>\r\n<p>There was a slight problem at the end with some luggage (not Peru For Less\' fault) but they helped to resolve the issue successfully.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>I am already starting to think about my summer trip to South America and Peru For Less will be the first company I contact.   </p>\r\n','David <br>\r\nUK<br>\r\nCuzco, Inca Trail to Machu Picchu\r\n','','','',691,0,0,NULL,NULL,NULL),(565,1,'Hi Rylee,','<p>What a Grand Adventure we had. And it started with the planning. I gave you a list of too many places to visit and you gave me a sample of possible itineraries that would work within the time we had to spend. Via email we worked together to create a custom vacation specific to my particular requests. </p>\r\n\r\n<p>Throughout the trip we were picked up punctually and where applicable the driver had our flight boarding passes ready and we reached the airports with a comfortable margin of time to comply with air regulations. </p>\r\n\r\n<p>All of our tour guides were so knowledgeable and passionate about their particular geographic area. They didn\'t just spout off facts by rote but spoke with drama and flair. Our guides were: Mariluz in the Colca Canyon area; Pumasanco in the Cusco area; another Mariluz in the Sacred Valley of the Incas; Fabricio in Machu Pichu; Johan in Infierno, Puerto Maldonado (he kept us safe from wasps and other dangers!). </p>\r\n\r\n<p>Caitlin in Cusco was so conscientious and a treat to talk to. And, of course, I called mid-trip asking for 2 more days in Miraflores and you did it in a flash.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>In other words, thank you for putting together a fantastic and memorable trip. Let me know if you need anything else regarding the testimonial.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Cheers,</p>\r\n','Cindy and Graham <br>\r\nSan Rafael, CA<br>\r\nLima, Arequipa, Cuzco/Machu Picchu, Puerto Maldonado\r\n','','','',692,0,0,NULL,NULL,NULL),(566,1,'Jennifer,','<p>From our first contact with Jennifer from Peru For Less we found her to be efficient and professional yet still friendly, informative, enthusiastic and helpful without being \'pushy\' and the advice she gave about the various options was exactly what we needed to know to decide on our itinerary.  </p>\r\n\r\n<p>We had a wonderful stopover with a great tour guide in Lima and a very special night out on New Years Eve - the restaurant Jennifer recommended put on a delicious buffet and an amazing cultural floorshow - and we were delighted to learn some local customs to ensure good luck for the new year!  </p>\r\n\r\n<p>Cusco and Machu Picchu were next and when altitude sickness looked like it would spoil our visit, our trusty Peru For Less tour guide took us to a pharmacy for some magic little pills that gave quick relief enabling us to appreciate and enjoy this truly awe inspiring Inca site.   </p>\r\n\r\n<p>Well done Jennifer and Peru For Less.</p>\r\n','Murray &amp; Vanda <br />\r\nPerth, Western Australia  \r\n<br />\r\nLima, Cusco, Machu Picchu\r\n','','','',392,0,0,NULL,NULL,NULL),(567,1,'Hi Rylee,','<p>My thanks to Rylee and the staff at Peru for Less for putting together a great trip for me in a truly amazing country.  Rylee was invaluable in answering all my questions and putting together a customized trip for me, as well as taking care of all the travel arrangements -- especially deftly arranging a late itinerary change I requested while I was already on the tour.  A representative was always present to pick me up at the airport and get me oriented to the city, and available by phone if I had questions.  I was also quite impressed with the knowledge and passion that the local guides were able to share.  Of course, the vast beauty of Peru speaks for itself.  I would definitely recommend giving Peru For Less a call when you\'re planning a trip there!</p>\r\n\r\n<p>All the best,</p>\r\n\r\n','Brian<br />\r\nSt. Augustine, FL\r\n<br />\r\nCuzco, Inca trail to Machu Picchu, Puno, and Arequipa \r\n','','','',389,0,0,NULL,NULL,NULL),(568,1,'Hi Rylee,','<p>We absolutely loved our trip, Peru was amazing! There is no equivalent to how Peru For Less was able to customise the trip to every little detail to suit our needs! Thanks again for all your help with booking our accommodation and transportation, as the accommodation recommended by Peru for Less is of high standard! \r\nHano and I will always have fond memories of Peru! </p>\r\n\r\n<p>Regards,</p>\r\n','Amanda <br />\r\nTrichardt, South Africa\r\n<br />\r\nLima, Puerto Maldonado, Cuzco (no Machu Picchu) Puno, Arequipa, Nazca, Ica\r\n','','','',386,0,0,NULL,NULL,NULL),(569,1,'Hi Matt, ','<p>If we return to Peru, I definitely will contact you again.  I found  you to be reliable, efficient, courteous and absolutely accurate.  It was a pleasure to deal with you.  We had a nice time in Lima and certainly enjoyed the food, which is internationally well - known.  </p>','Carolyn <br />\r\nFlorida, USA\r\n<br />Lima \r\n','','','',383,0,0,NULL,NULL,NULL),(570,1,'Dear Rylee,  ','<p>We did have a really good time on our trip.  We would certainly use your company again and would not hesitate to recommend you to anyone.  </p>\r\n\r\n<p>Sincerely,  </p>\r\n','Kathy and Hue <br />\r\nSt. Matthews, SC\r\n<br />\r\nLa Paz, Puno, Arequipa, Cuzco/Machu Picchu, Nazca/Ica and Lima\r\n','','','',380,0,0,NULL,NULL,NULL),(571,1,'Hi Sebastian,','<p>We returned from Peru last week, and just wanted to let you know that everything went incredibly smoothly and we loved every day we were there!  Thank you so much for the follow up prior to our trip - particularly with the updates regarding the uncertainties for travel to Machu Picchu.  The short Inca Trail was fantastic, the weather cooperated beautifully, and it seemed to us that the tourist crowd was smaller due to the limited train service, which made visiting M.P. even more wonderful.  </p>\r\n\r\n<p>All aspects of our trip were on time, and completely without hassle.  The arrangements for ground transport and local tours enabled us to see a lot in the short two weeks we were there, and without exception our local guides and representatives were most helpful and professional.  Most especially, I\'d like to mention Wayki Trek operators  in Cusco, Allison and Miguel (Peru for Less representatives in Cusco and Lima), and Luis and the staff at Posadas Amazonas in Puerto Maldonado, who all helped to make our trip delightful, interesting, and completely stress-free.  </p>\r\n\r\n<p>We so enjoyed the people we met in Peru, the food, the incredible sights, and many Pisco Sours.  We will definitely return soon, and look forward to visiting other regions of Peru on our next trip.  We would like to thank you again for all your assistance and attention to the details, and we will recommend Peru for Less without hesitation to any of our friends planning travel to Peru. </p>\r\n\r\n<p>Best Regards,</p>\r\n','Alex &amp; Suzanne  <br>\r\nCuzco, Machu Picchu\r\n','','','',693,0,0,NULL,NULL,NULL),(572,1,'Hi Rylee,','<p>We did have a wonderful trip, thanks mostly to the changes you made.  Our tour guides were all great. The reality tour in Arequipa was one of the highlights of our trip thanks to Miguel.  We also had a great time in Machu Picchu thanks to our informative city guides, especially Edgar.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>All in all, you did a great job and special thanks to Rylee and to Miguel and Edgar, the two most memorable tour guides.</p>\r\n','Vivian and Harold <br /> \r\nLahaina, Hawaii\r\n<br />\r\nLima, Arequipa, Colca, Puno, Cusco, and Machu Picchu\r\n','','','',377,0,0,NULL,NULL,NULL),(573,1,'Jennifer, ','<p>Our trip to Peru passed far too quickly; it was an incredible adventure that we will never forget. I assure you that our trip was more than we expected and absolutely fabulous.  </p>\r\n\r\n<p>I was extremely impressed by how organized it all was as well...drivers always there on time and in correct location, everyone more than friendly and knowledgeable...and also so passionate about Cusco, Peru, and the Inca heritage, reminders about our tours and pickup times via note in our hotel rooms...oh yes and the glorious food!  </p>\r\n\r\n<p>The Galapagos Islands is one of our next planned destinations, so we\'ll be certain to reach out to you when the time comes.</p>\r\n','Leslee and Shane <br />\r\nScottsdale, Arizona\r\n<br />\r\nLima, Cusco, Machu Picchu, Luxury Inca Trail\r\n','','','',375,0,0,NULL,NULL,NULL),(574,1,'Jennifer, ','<p>Thank you for your solicitousness. Except for the rain everything was just great. We really loved everything about Peru. The Hotel Aranwa in the Sacred Valley was simply fabulous. </p>\r\n\r\n<p>We are presently in Bariloche, Argentina, and are looking forward to returning home. </p>\r\n\r\n<p>Thanks again for your follow up on the Peru tour.</p>\r\n\r\n','Remedios <br /> \r\nCalifornia\r\n<br />\r\nCuzco, Machu Picchu, Lima\r\n','','','',372,0,0,NULL,NULL,NULL),(575,1,'Hi Matt,','<p>Thanks for your email.  We had a wonderful time.  Ceiba Tops was perfect.  We loved the Amazon jungle.  Casa Andina in Cusco was excellent, and all the tours were great.  </p>\r\n\r\n<p>Thanks for everything.</p>\r\n','Charlene <br />\r\nIquitos, Cusco, Machu Picchu\r\n','','','',370,0,0,NULL,NULL,NULL),(576,1,'Hi Kristina,','<p>We enjoyed our stay at Amerian Hotel in Iguazu and also enjoyed our trip to the falls. Unfortunately we had heavy rain for the duration of our visit to the Argentinean side of the falls but the weather cleared for our trip to the Brazilian side. </p>\r\n\r\n<p>My husband and I canâ??t stop raving about our trip to Ceiba Tops, it is a must for all travellers to Peru! Everything we did whilst we were there was amazing, down to the food, entertainment and facilities at the lodge. </p>\r\n\r\n<p>hanks again for all of your help organizing our adventures.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Regards,</p>\r\n','Nae Bruce <br />\r\nAustralia\r\n<br />\r\nIguazu Falls &amp; Ceiba Tops\r\n','','','',368,0,0,NULL,NULL,NULL),(577,1,'Hello Kelly,','<p>Overall the trip was great and we will always look back with pleasure. Highlights would be Galapagos and the train ride from Cuzco to Puno. </p>\r\n \r\n<p>Recommended dining was good - we enjoyed Cusco\'s Inka Grill &amp; Chez Maggy and Lima\'s Astrid y Gaston.</p>\r\n  \r\n<p>Overall, very fond memories - thanks for your support.</p>\r\n<p>Kind regards</p>\r\n','Ian &amp; Barbara <br />\r\nLima, Cusco, Machu Picchu, Lake Titicaca, Galapagos Islands\r\n','','','',366,0,0,NULL,NULL,NULL),(578,1,'Hi Kelly,','<p>Overall, things went well. We had a lot of fun. The Inca trail was gruesome, but the end was so worth it. Wayki was great, I loved our tour guide and porters. Most of the transports went smoothly. The tour guides for the city tour and sacred valley were very nice also. We had a lot of fun. It\'s a trip we\'ll never forget.</p>\r\n  \r\n<p>Again, other than that, everything else was enjoyable and went smoothly. </p>\r\n\r\n<p>Thanks, Kelly.</p>','Nancy\r\n<br />\r\nCusco and Inca Trail\r\n','','','',364,0,0,NULL,NULL,NULL),(579,1,'Hi Kelly,','<p>It was a fantastic trip!!  I have no complaints.  Your service in particular was excellent.  Especially with the circumstances surrounding our trip with Machu Picchu closing, the communication back and forth with us was exactly what we needed and expected. </p>\r\n\r\n<p>My favorite part of the trip was the \"country\" road that we took between Cusco and Sacred Valley.  This wouldnâ??t have been included had we followed the normal tourist route.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Thanks for your service,</p>\r\n','Carla <br />\r\n\r\nCusco, Machu Picchu\r\n','','','',362,0,0,NULL,NULL,NULL),(580,1,'Hi Kristina,','<p>My wife Ruthie and I  cannot  tell you how impressed we were with your diligence and we want to thank you enough for all of your hard work! The timeliness of your responses to our many questions and requests could not have been better. Kristina, you were so easy and pleasant to work with, I have already recommended to people that they use Peru for Less and request you.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Our trip to Puno and Lake Titicaca was extremely smooth, everything went according to plan. Ruthie and I were so appreciative of your efforts in helping our daughter\'s friend join us on our trip to Puno, especially with us only giving you 36 hours to work out the logistics. Caitlin in Cusco was very sweet, professional and well organized. The representatives in Puno were punctual, pleasant, eager to please. The same can be said of our trip to Machu Picchu. Our guide, Fabricio, was wonderful. </p>\r\n\r\n<p>Actually, on our return trip from Machu Picchu (Aguas Calientes), our driver was not at the train station in Piscacuchu. Perurail would not let us wait there to see if he would show up and insisted that we board the bus for Ollantaytambo. When we arrived there nobody was there either. Caitlin had given us her cell phone #, and a quick call to her alleviated the problem. Our driver showed up in 20 minutes, so apologetic, we felt bad for him. It was really a minor blip and what could have been a problem was easily handled.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>We are very fortunate and have traveled to many places, far and near. I have preferred to make all of our travel plans ourselves, feeling I could do a better job than any agency. Kristina, you and Peru for Less have made me change my mind! The twists and turns we put you through, changing our minds and what to me seemed to be endless questions for you, all of this was met with courtesy, efficiency and professionalism. We commend you and thank you so much for all that you did to help make those trips so outstanding.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Sincerley,</p>\r\n','Harry &amp; Ruthie <br />\r\nBethlehem, Pa U.S.A.\r\n<br />\r\nPuno and Machu Picchu\r\n','','','',361,0,0,NULL,NULL,NULL),(581,1,'Dear Kristina,','<p>I wanted to let you know that we had a fantastic time in Peru, so much so that we would love to come back!! I\'d like to really thank you for all your help and advice prior to our trip. Neither of us had ever been to South America before and we really felt that that you had our best interests at heart, and we fully appreciated this when we were on the trip, having a really great time! </p>\r\n\r\n<p>All the transfers and trips to different excursions went very smoothly. The hotels we stayed in were lovely. I was especially grateful that Peru For Less offered us the flexibility to tailor our trip as we wanted. We really felt the benefits of just dipping into different groups, which in reality, actually meant we met a wider range of people than we otherwise would have done, which was great! In addition, we also had lots of free time for just the two of us, so this combination of groups and \"free time\" suited us perfectly. </p>\r\n\r\n<p>I would also really recommend Peru For Less for girls traveling together who might be anxious about travelling to South America. There was no point during the trip where we felt vulnerable as two single girls traveling. </p>\r\n\r\n<p>All in all, we couldn\'t have asked for a better trip. Thank you so much for helping us make this the memorable trip that we wanted.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>I have already been recommending you to my friends!!</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Thanks again</p>\r\n','Jasmin <br />\r\nLondon, England\r\n<br />\r\nLima, Arequipa, Puno, Cusco, Puerto Maldonado\r\n','','','',360,0,0,NULL,NULL,NULL),(582,1,'Hi Jennifer,','<p>As a whole, we had a great time. The driver who picked us up from Cusco, Juan Carlos, was very knowledgeable and gave us a nice tour on the way to Ollantaytambo.  Reservations at all hotels were perfect and there were no glitches. The hotels were nice, clean and personnel was friendly.</p>\r\n \r\n<p>Thanks again for everything you did for us.  We will definitely contact you again when we make another trip south.</p>\r\n \r\n<p>Take care,</p>\r\n','Lorna<br />\r\nFort Worth, TEXAS\r\n<br />\r\nLima, Cusco, Machu Picchu\r\n','','','',359,0,0,NULL,NULL,NULL),(583,1,'Dear Peru For Less','<p>We returned from our trip last night, and I would like to thank you for the excellent job you did in arranging our trip. All reservations were in place, the guides were well qualified and pleasant, and we had a fabulous time in beautiful Peru. </p>\r\n \r\n<p>We also appreciate the perfect weather you arranged for us!</p>\r\n \r\n<p>When we take our next trip to South America, we will definitely turn to Peru for Less, and recommend you to all our friends.</p>\r\n','Fran<br />\r\nUSA\r\n<br />\r\nLima, Cusco\r\n','','','',358,0,0,NULL,NULL,NULL),(584,1,'Dear Peru For Less','<p>Our trip to Huacachina was great. Everything went as planned and the hotel was better than we had hoped for. We especially liked the garden with the pool, but also the oasis was wonderful and the place was so calm and relaxing. We enjoyed every minute we stayed there. </p>\r\n\r\n<p>Also, thank you for calling and checking on us.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Best Regards,</p>\r\n\r\n','Kristin<br />\r\nNorway\r\n<br />\r\nIca, Huacachina\r\n','','','',357,0,0,NULL,NULL,NULL),(585,1,'Hi Rylee,','<p>The trip was fantastic...we loved being in Peru and enjoyed the country, people and varied culture across the places we visited. The pick up and drop offs were all on time, professional staff and tour guides.</p>\r\n \r\n<p>Other than that it was a great trip!! Thanks for arranging, it was a real smooth and wonderful experience.</p>\r\n','Aria <br />\r\nNormandy Park WA\r\n<br />\r\nLima, Cuzco, Puno\r\n','','','',356,0,0,NULL,NULL,NULL),(586,1,'Dear Peru For Less','<p>Like our previous tour with Peru For Less, the two city tours of Lima were well executed, very interesting, very informative and fun.  Miguel was a great tour guide. He was knowledgeable, possessed excellent English skills and was fun to be with.  The dinner show at Restaurant Junius was tremendous.  The performers were very talented, music and presentation excellent and the food was great.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Your tours gave us a head start on 10 wonderful days in Lima.  The city exceeded our expectations. The sights were numerous and very interesting. The people of Lima were understanding of our lack of Spanish, helpful, and welcoming. The selection of restaurants was amazing.  We ate at everything from neighbourhood cafes to world class restaurants like Astrid and Gaston.  Dining was varied, delicious and reasonable.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>We will return to South America again (this was our 4th trip) and will be sure to contact Peru For Less.  We will also pass on your contact information to anyone heading south.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Best regards, safe travels and thank you,</p>\r\n','Lorne, Sheila, Robin &amp; Bev<br />\r\nCanada\r\n<br />\r\nLima\r\n','','','',355,0,0,NULL,NULL,NULL),(587,1,'Hi Kelly,','<p>I must tell you that everything went BETTER than excellent.  My husband and I spent 12 days traveling from Lima, to Cuzco, on to Machu Pichu, then to Puno and back again to Lima.  All of our connections were ALWAYS on time...the tours and tour guides were interesting and knowlegable..and fun too!  We stayed in the Andina line of hotels in every city.  Each one was quaint, unique,  spacious and very comfortable. The staff were always friendly and accomodating.</p>\r\n \r\n<p>All in all, the trip was all we had hoped for. Peru for Less did an outstanding job of making sure everything went as smoothly as possible. We were very impressed with the professionalism and the personal service we received from everyone we encountered.  Thank you so much. We are looking forward to booking another trip with you again.</p>\r\n \r\n<p>Best regards,</p>\r\n','Maria <br />\r\nLima, Cusco &amp; Machu Picchu, Lake Titicaca\r\n','','','',354,0,0,NULL,NULL,NULL),(588,1,'Kelly,','<p>Overall everything worked out and the trip was a wonderful once-in-a-lifetime experience. </p>\r\n\r\n<p>We chose 2 star hotels in both Cuzco (Ninos Dos) and Aguas Calientes (Rupa Wasi) and were pleased with both. Ninos was delightful, although a bit out of the way; Rupa Wasi was quaint and comfortable.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>We had Juan Carlos for a tour guide around Cusco and Sacred Valley. He was accommodating, knowledgeable and entertaining. We had Fabricio in Machu Picchu and found him delightful.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>All in all, we would heartily recommend PFL to anyone in booking a trip to Peru.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Thanks for all you did to help make this happen.</p>\r\n','Dan <br />\r\nCusco, Machu Picchu\r\n','','','',353,0,0,NULL,NULL,NULL),(589,1,'Hi Kelly, ','<p>Everything was as promised. I was happy with the Inkatarra and Novotel and the 16 member cruise. I would say excellent. </p>\r\n\r\n<p>Thank you, </p>','Neeraja <br />\r\nCusco, Machu Picchu, Galapagos Islands\r\n','','','',352,0,0,NULL,NULL,NULL),(590,1,'Hi Kelly,','<p>Overall the trip went very well and I was met by PFL personnel promptly at every location. This made it easy especially in remote locations. I would recommend PFL to anyone without hesitation.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>First of all, I really appreciated very prompt efforts by Caitlyn and Emily from your office in Cusco, who looked after our every need. </p>\r\n\r\n<p>I enjoyed Cusco. The guide for the Sacred Valley tour was exceptional. Also, there were others from PFL that I met on several tours and that made the tours very enjoyable with sharing of travel stories, etc. The tour of the Cathedral, the Inca ruins, etc, around Cusco was good as well, and the guide gave us enough time to explore on our own and for photos.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>The dinner and show at the Tunupa Restaurant was very enjoyable. The buffet was excellent and service was courteous. I got a front table which was very nice. </p>\r\n<p>Machu Picchu was simply an exceptional experience and guide there (Jim) was quite good. I had a nice day with good, sunny weather (May 21). I had a super relaxing next day in Agues Calientes. The El MAPI hotel was superb including the staff and I had a lovely lunch by the river. They recommended the Indie Feliz restaurant where I had a terrific dinner at an excellent price.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>For those who want to minimize the hardship, I would recommend to wait until the train track from Cusco to Agues Calientes is completely rebuilt. The bus ride was very uncomfortable with little room for even the small luggage we took. The train service was excellent.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>All in all a very satisfying experience with Peru-for-Less.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Regards,</p>\r\n','Gaurang <br/>\r\nLima, Arequipa, Puno, Cusco\r\n','','','',694,0,0,NULL,NULL,NULL),(591,1,'Kelly:','<p>Let me start by saying \"I wish we were still in Peru!\"</p>\r\n\r\n<p>I gave you the challenge of coordinating an itinerary with a limited amount of time and the entire trip went without incident.  Every flight, every transfer, every taxi, bus and tour was on time and as planned.  Every contact we made from the Hotel Staff to the Tour guides was pleasant, helpful and all aimed to please.  Special kudos to Allison who answered my calls after-hours and always greeted us with a bright smile.  Logistically the trip was flawless....and that\'s hard to do.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>The experience was \"once in a lifetime\" but I hope to do it again, soon.  And, we\'ll be booking through you.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Cusco was a wonderful town with plenty to do...we had to force ourselves to go back to the Hotel and sleep in preparation for the following day.  We could have stayed up late every night.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Aquas Calientes was a pleasant surprise.  I didn\'t expect that kind of charm from a town only accessible by train...wow.  And the hot bathes were a welcome treat after the hike.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>The 2-day Inca Trail was perfect!  We were able to experience the Train and the Hike in our allotted time without feeling \"short-changed\". I am not skilled enough to put into words an adequate description of Machu Picchu.  It must be seen and experienced in person.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Not sure if this was your intent but the physical ability of our group was very well matched. I don\'t know if the experience would be the same if I had to wait for a slower hiker of be the one waited on.  I don\'t remember if you asked an ability question but your pairing of the group was perfect.  Edwin, our guide, was a good balance of knowledge, personality and the ability to gauge our interest for a lecture or if we should move-on.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Thanks for making this a memory of a life-time.\r\nCheers,</p>\r\n','Jesse <br/>\r\nPasadena, CA <br/>\r\nCusco, Machu Picchu, Inca Trail\r\n','','','',695,0,0,NULL,NULL,NULL),(592,1,'Hi Rylee,','<p>I am sorry it took so long to respond, but we have been very busy getting our heads out of the clouds and returning to our lives.  We wanted to let you know that \"Peru for Less\" was absolutely wonderful.  We were very well taken care of by our Travel Guides, I was impressed with their knowledge and pride in their country.  We saw so many things that are so beautiful, that makes their description impossible.  We do appreciate that you did such a good job setting up all the places that we wanted to see in our 11 day vacation, and wanted you to know that if there was a minor problem with time or plans, it was immediately fixed.  We were taken care of by people that enjoyed what they were doing, and they made us feel special.  I know that you asked for a photo, well I am going to send a few (out of 992) that my show how much we ejnoyed the trip.  You will notice the large smiles!! </p>\r\n\r\n<p>Thanks, Rylee!!!\r\nWould I recommend you--Without reservation!</p>\r\n','Tom and Rhonda <br/>\r\nAmarillo, Texas <br/>\r\nLima, Nazca, Cusco, Aguas Caliente, Machu Picchu, Puno, Lake Titicaca, Tiahuanacu and Puma Punka \r\n','','','',696,0,0,NULL,NULL,NULL),(593,1,'Dear Peru For Less','<p>We had such a wonderful time!!!  We really appreciated your willingness to work with us (making sure we had a guide to meet us at Machu Picchu after we changed our train tickets, giving us the dinner/show when you could have very well kept that extra money in our account, making sure that we felt comfortable with everything).  We were extremely happy with the all of the hotels we stayed at and felt safe.  Being able to see Peru and not have to worry about the little details was a dream... thank you so much for everything.  I\'ll make sure to let everyone know how happy we were with Peru For Less :)</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Also, please tell Emily thank you, too.  You both were so great!!!</p>\r\n','The Brus <br/>\r\nLima, Cusco, Puno\r\n','','','',697,0,0,NULL,NULL,NULL),(594,1,'Hi Jennifer,','<p>Our trip was everything we wanted and much more.  It was amazing and we wish we would have had more time to spend in Peru.  The hike was beyond anything we had imagined.  Everyone was so professional and welcoming and friendly and helpful.  We felt very safe and we really appreciated all your \"hand-holding\"... I know that we emailed often to ask every imaginable question and you always got right back to us.   </p>\r\n\r\n<p>We HIGHLY recommend Peru For Less to plan an amazing Peru experience.  From beginning to end, our travel advisor was extremely helpful and knowledgeable.  Our questions were answered right away.  Our itinerary was very well organized, detailed, and explained to us.  When we were to be met by a driver and/or tour guide, they were always on time and very professional and knowledgeable.  We received extremely personal attention and always had a way to contact someone in case of a problem or question.  We even received reminder messages for times of tours and flights.  </p>\r\n\r\n<p>The trek to Machu Picchu was better than we ever imagined.  It was well organized and our guides were wonderful.  I have never eaten so well/healthy on a vacation, either.  I implore you to highly consider planning your trip with this company!</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Fondly,</p>\r\n','Leslee and Shane <br />\r\nScottsdale, Arizona<br>\r\n\r\nLima, Cusco, Machu Picchu, Luxury Inca Trail\r\n','','','',698,0,0,NULL,NULL,NULL),(595,1,'Hi Matt,','<p>Just a note to let you know that we had a wonderful time on our vacation in Peru.  The Ceiba Tops lodge was perfect.  We had our own guide, Basilio, who was an expert on all jungle plants, animals, and culture.  Especially memorable was the visit to the Yagua Indians.  Don\'t think I can say anything about Machu Picchu that hasn\'t already been said by many others - an indescribable, mystical place.  The tours of Cusco, and the Sacred Valley were amazing and we learned so much about Incan history.  </p>\r\n\r\n<p>A special thank you to all our tour guides, especially Fabricio and Mary. Also to Allison from Peru For Less in Cusco who was always available and patiently answered all our many questions.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Finally, a grateful thank you to you, Matt, for your patience in dealing with all our trip changes and preparations, we will certainly recommend Peru for Less to all of our friends.</p>\r\n','Charlene, Carie and Tracy<br />\r\nDenver, Colorado\r\n<br />Lima, Iquitos, Cusco, Machu Picchu\r\n','','','',351,0,0,NULL,NULL,NULL),(596,1,'Hi Rylee,','<p>The trip was excellent! Thank you for all your help with it. I am also going to refer a couple of my friends to you because they are planning a trip as well.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Thanks again!</p>\r\n','Sirisha <br />\r\nSan Diego, CA\r\n<br />\r\nCusco, Inca trail to Machu Picchu\r\n','','','',350,0,0,NULL,NULL,NULL),(597,1,'Hi Rylee,','<p>I hope you are doing well. We are winding down from our trip in Peru and I wanted to send you a quick thank you email. We had a great trip and really appreciate all of your and your colleagues excellent service. </p>\r\n\r\n<p>We were luckily able to see a Harpy Eagle in its nest with a chick at Puerto Maldonado, so for birdwatchers and tourists like us, your tour is fantastic.</po>\r\n\r\n<p>God bless and thank you for the wonderful planning.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Warmest regards, </p>\r\n','Jim and Joann <br />\r\nWinter Haven, FL\r\n<br />\r\nLima, Puerto Maldonado, Cusco, Puno, Arequipa, Nazca, Ica\r\n','','','',349,0,0,NULL,NULL,NULL),(598,1,'Dear Jennifer, ','<p>I am in the airport waiting to return home. The trip was excellent. By far the best service you provide is the personal concierge service - Allison was literally available 24/7.  </p>\r\n\r\n<p>Please let her supervisor know what a wonderful asset she is to your company. She was always available to assist me. Her assistance made the whole trip.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Your company was able to book my trip to Machu Picchu at literally the last minute when American Express said it was impossible!! </p>\r\n\r\n<p>Regards, </p>','Larry <br />\r\nFlorida\r\n<br />\r\nCusco, Machu Picchu\r\n','','','',348,0,0,NULL,NULL,NULL),(599,1,'Dear Peru For Less','<p>Thanks for following up with us. We had a lovely time in Peru. Thank you for all of your help in coordinating with us our adventure-filled itinerary. We loved every city we travelled to, and most of the hotel experiences were exceptionally outstanding. The guide that picked us up from the Lima airport was very friendly and informative. He gave us very helpful advice about day-to-day details that we wouldn\'t have thought of ourselves in order to improve our experience. </p>\r\n\r\n<p>Our Cusco city tour guide was exceptional in her knowledge of Cusco\'s architectural landmarks, historical background, and artistic details. She gladly welcomed all our questions during the tour, and answered them with a solid knowledge base. We incidentally ran into her again at the Machu Picchu train station when our train was delayed, and she sat with us at the station for over an hour telling us very interesting stories in answer to our many questions about the history of Machu Picchu and the Sacred Valley. </p>\r\n\r\n<p>Our Sacred Valley tour guide was equally impressive with his immense knowledge of the Inca culture, similar to Senora Sylvia. He made so many jokes during the tour that really kept our attention and made us want to learn more about the places we were visiting and the history behind them. </p>\r\n\r\n<p>We really enjoyed our plane ride over the Nazca lines, with a very professional pilot and co-pilot. The return bus ride was excellent, with comfortable seats. The driver who picked us up from the Nazca bus station to take us to the hotel was very professional as well and consistently 10 minutes early for every pick up.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Peru itself was amazing, and our experiences there were fantastic. We are telling all our friends about the country and its amazing historical, architectural, and cultural landmarks. We may even return there for another visit someday.  We are very grateful for your hard work in putting together our tour for us, and for your flexibility in coordinating with our intense travel schedule and specific hotel preferences. You did a great job in planning the itinerary in advance with us. We are very grateful to the guides, drivers, and hotel staff that excelled in their hospitality and made us feel so welcome well beyond those in any other country we\'ve visited. </p>\r\n<p>Sincerely,</p>\r\n','Hany and Mary <br />\r\nTorrence, California\r\n<br />\r\nCusco, Machu Picchu, Nazca\r\n','','','',347,0,0,NULL,NULL,NULL),(600,1,'Kelly, ','<p>Thank you for your response. We were okay with not having an extra day at Machu Picchu and we accepted, and understand the fact that the train schedule couldn\'t accommodate us, because of our late booking.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Overall, we are very satisfied with our trip, and experience with PFL!!!</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Thanks,</p>\r\n','Carl <br />\r\nCusco, Machu Picchu \r\n','','','',346,0,0,NULL,NULL,NULL),(601,1,'Hi Kelly,','<p>I\'d be happy to give you a testimonial of the trip, we had an AWESOME time!! \r\nI was not looking forward to spending so much time on a bus in Peru, however, the VIP seats that we were booked on could not have been better.  The bus service was excellent and we did not at all mind travelling on the bus.  I can\'t remember, did I request first class or do you automatically book VIP for you customers?\r\nThe highlight of the trip was definitely the Inca Trail; I have nothing but excellent things to say about Wayki Trek, and specifically our guide Jose.  The guides/porters really made our hike memorable.  Machu Picchu was amazing; however, we enjoyed the hike/scenery/ruins on the trail just as much if not more as Machu Pichu itself.  </p>\r\n \r\n<p>Our favorite destination was probably Cusco, we would have liked to have more time there.  </p>\r\n\r\n<p>As a travel advisor there is nothing else you could\'ve done for us, you were a great help in creating this trip for us.  I also appreciate your time when I had to call you from Puno regarding miscommunication with one of the transfers. </p>\r\n \r\n<p>Thanks a lot for everything, it was nice to arrive and not have any headaches since we were so pressed for time.  I would recommend Peru For Less to anyone!</p>\r\n','Katie <br />\r\nCusco, Inca Trail to Machu Picchu, Puno, Arequipa, Nazca, Ica, Lima\r\n','','','',345,0,0,NULL,NULL,NULL),(602,1,'Dear Kelly and Allison, ','<p>Thanks for arranging a wonderful trip for us in Peru.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>We had a great time especially in Aguas Calientes and at Machu Picchu.\r\nHowever the hotel at Aguas Calientes including the service was excellent.\r\nAllison was very helpful in arranging everything and made the trip enjoyable.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Thank you and best wishes.</p>\r\n','Praveen and Shakun <br />\r\n<br />\r\nCusco, Machu Picchu\r\n','','','',344,0,0,NULL,NULL,NULL),(603,1,'Dear Kristina,','<p>We used Peru as a base for our visit to South America and the Galapagos Islands.  Our entire trip to Peru was completely organized by Peru for Less.  They picked us up from the airport, took us to our airports, and arranged all our tours.  Travelling with two kids, we wanted to make sure we werenâ??t stranded anywhere and Peru for Less made sure we were taken care of the entire trip.  Dealing with Kristina was a pleasure, since she was born and raised in England, and there was no translation issues.  </p>\r\n\r\n<p>When Machu Picchu was rained out, Kristina reached out to us first to give us options before we had a chance to contact her.  While we were in the Galapagos, one of our kids got sick.  We decided that on our return trip to Peru we would tone-down the adventure-side of the trip, and Kristina arranged everything, including first-class accommodations.  We were pleased with the entire time in Peru, and look forward to using Peru for Less again when we can finally visit Machu Picchu and the other amazing sites this wonderful country has to offer. </p>\r\n\r\n<p>Sincerely,</p>\r\n','Duane <br /> \r\nCanada  \r\n<br />\r\nLima \r\n','','','',343,0,0,NULL,NULL,NULL),(604,1,'Dear Jennifer,','<p>Very good trip overall. </p>\r\n\r\n<p>I didn\'t give you much time to set things up, and the washouts from the rain at Machu Picchu did not help when we were there. However, all in all a job well done, thanks for your help and hope to call you again soon for another adventure! </p>\r\n\r\n<p>Thanks again, Cheers, </p>\r\n','Bob Brown\r\nCanada\r\nApril 30-May 7\r\nLima, Cusco, Machu Picchu\r\n','','','',342,0,0,NULL,NULL,NULL),(605,1,'Hi Richard,','<p>Well - where to begin.  We can\'t thank you enough for the wonderful trip.  Everything was perfect.  </p>\r\n\r\n<p>Allison was great - and I just can\'t say enough about Maria Elana and Fabricio (I hope I spelled these names correctly).  You have two really superior guides in these folks - don\'t let them get away from you.  We learned so much - didn\'t know of all the treasures in Cusco!  I think a person really needs a week to do the town correctly - however, thanks to you and your people we saw much more than we imagined we would.</p>\r\n \r\n<p>Thanks again for everything you did to make our trip perfect - and if you ever need references, please have people contact me!</p>','Dick and Sylvia <br />\r\nButte Valley, CA\r\n<br />\r\nCusco, Machu Picchu\r\n','','','',341,0,0,NULL,NULL,NULL),(606,1,'Hi Rylee!','<p>Our trip has been wonderful, we are heading home soon and don\'t want to leave the Peruvian culture yet! Machu Picchu was definitely the highlight of the trip- utterly amazing. The train ride went smoothly.</p><p> Thanks for checking in on us and helping us along the way!<p>','Jillian <br />\r\nGrand Rapids, MI\r\n\r\n','','','',340,0,0,NULL,NULL,NULL),(607,1,'Hello Rylee,','<p>Our trip to Peru was fantastic. We could not be more pleased with Peru for Less. All of your representatives met us as expected, all were on time even when we were delayed and everyone was informative and professional. The hotels were all very nice. We particularly loved Casa Arequipa and Hatchuyay Tower. </p>\r\n\r\n<p>We have already recommended Peru for less to our friends. Oh and thank you for arranging our last minute request for drivers to take us around Lima while waiting for our flight home. </po>\r\n\r\n<p>Thank you again for helping us have such a wonderful experience in Peru.</p>\r\n','Roby <br />\r\nCovington, LA\r\n<br />Lima, Ica, Nazca, Arequipa, Cusco, Machu Picchu\r\n','','','',339,0,0,NULL,NULL,NULL),(608,1,'Hi Kelly,','<p>Thanks for your help in organizing everything. Trip was great and the itinerary worked out well.  Very glad we started with the Amazon as staying in one place for the first couple of days gave us a chance to relax after a lengthy journey to get there. My wife might however argue about how relaxing it was, as she still thinks about the rather large frog she found sitting in the toilet the second night we were there.   </p>\r\n\r\n<p>In hindsight, I was glad to get the hot, humid, and rustic part of the trip out of the way. All the pickups and transfers worked out smoothly and we were overall quite happy with all the guides we had on the trip. </p>\r\n\r\n<p>The private tour of the Sacred Valley was well worth it as having a guide for both the sights as well as insights into modern Peruvian life was most informative.  Highlights of the trip had to be Machu Picchu, Cusco, and the Colca Canyon.  The food was also a big plus for us as we tried out everything from high end places to local Chifa.  </p>\r\n\r\n<p>For your other customers...I thought Huaca Pucllana in Lima was overrated as to food, but made up for it with the great location by the ruins.  Tiendecita Blanca at the top of Kennedy Park was a great place for a nice lunch and actually had one of the better ceviches I had the whole trip.  </p>\r\n\r\n<p>Thanks again for your help,  </p>\r\n','Laurence <br />\r\nAmazon, Cusco, Machu Picchu, Lake Titicaca, Arequipa, Lima\r\n','','','',338,0,0,NULL,NULL,NULL),(609,1,'Dear Peru For Less','<p>You asked us to do a testimonial for our trip way back when - Jan 19th !!!  Well, we are back home, unpacked, mail mostly finished and ready to face \"reality\".  And I am finally getting around to your request.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>We thought you did a spectacular job with everythng - from meeting us at the ship, getting us to the planes, helping us thru the airport procedures, and returning us back to the ship - all was A+++.  Our tour guide in Machu Picchu was very knowledgeable and did not \"short change\" me becasue I was alone, but told me all about the history of the place and the area.  Very fascinating.  Caitlin, in Cusco, was always on time, very helpful, and available for whatever our needs might be.  Machu Picchu was everything and more than I had dreamed.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>We would recommnd you to any and all. Thanks for a job well done. </p>\r\n\r\n<p>Sincerely yours,</p>\r\n','Ernie and Bert <br />\r\nCalifornia\r\n<br />\r\nCusco, Machu Picchu\r\n','','','',337,0,0,NULL,NULL,NULL),(610,1,'Dear RyLee,','<p>Good to hear from you. We had a WONDERFUL time in Peru and found all the connections and contact people to be excellent. We particularly thought that Allison in Cusco was terrific, and Fabricio at Machu Picchu. </p>\r\n\r\n<p>K\'uychi Rumi is an amazing place in Urubamba -- I highly recommend it to your travelers. Ditto for Rumi Punku in Cusco -- a delightful and wonderful hotel. We loved Refugio Amazonas and ESPECIALLY the TRC. </p>\r\n\r\n<p>In every other way, our trip was perfect. Our connections were on time or early, the hotels were excellent, the rainforest trip through Rainforest Expeditions was way beyond our highest expectations. We even saw a jaguar, a rare sighting, on our boat trip up to Tampopata Research Center! Even the weather cooperated - not a drop of rain. </p>\r\n\r\n<p>Every time we needed to communicate with our contacts from Peru for Less, they were right at the end of a phone, ready to solve any problems that came up. We would definitely recommend Peru for Less to other travelers. </p>\r\n\r\n<p>All the best, </p>\r\n\r\n','Dorothy <br />\r\nWallingford, CT\r\n<br />\r\nCusco, Puerto Maldonado\r\n','','','',336,0,0,NULL,NULL,NULL),(611,1,'Kelly,','<p>I am SO SORRY that you have not heard from us. Our trip was fabulous. Tom tells everyone that it was â??the best vacation I ever hadâ?. </p>\r\n\r\n<p>Thanks for everything!</p>\r\n','Faith<br />\r\nLima, Ica, Nazca \r\n','','','',335,0,0,NULL,NULL,NULL),(612,1,'Rylee,','<p>We had a great time. The trip went flawlessly. all the guides and drivers were \r\non time. We had no worries!!!! </p>\r\n\r\n<p>Consequently we are considering another trip with you. </p>\r\n\r\n<p>Thanks, </p>','Linda Holzheimer <br />\r\nGreat Falls, Mt\r\n<br />\r\nArequipa, Puno, Cusco, Machu Picchu\r\n','','','',334,0,0,NULL,NULL,NULL),(613,1,'Dear Rylee,','<p>Teri and I are at the airport in Lima waiting for our return flight home. We want you to know that we had an excellent time. Allison couldn\'t have been more helpful. The experience here at Second Home was quite interesting and the owner gave us a tour of her father\'s private art studio. </p>\r\n\r\n<p>You were so helpful in planning this trip for you and making all the last minute changes, we just had a marvelous time. </p>\r\n\r\n<p>Many thanks for your professional assistance from beginning to end. </p>\r\n\r\n<p>Sincerely,</p>\r\n','Tricia  and Teri <br /> \r\nPalos Verdes Estates, CA\r\n<br />Lima, Cusco, Machu Picchu\r\n','','','',333,0,0,NULL,NULL,NULL),(614,1,'Hello Rylee,','<p>Thank you for organizing such a wonderful trip thus far. We saw the Huaca Pucllana in Lima instead of the NatÂ´l Bank Museum but it was lovely too. Just wanted to say thank you. NASCA was an experience. Unbelievable.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Your country is beautiful. Machu Picchu and the Sacred Valley were wonderful. Your history and Peruvians are all awesome. </p>\r\n\r\n<p>Thanks for hearing me out. </p>\r\n','VIJAY<br />\r\nArcadia, CA\r\n<br />\r\nLima, Nazca, Cusco, Machu Picchu, Sacred Valley\r\n','','','',332,0,0,NULL,NULL,NULL),(615,1,'Hi Rylee,','<p>Just wanted to let you know that Caitlin was true to her word & my bag was waiting for me when we got back to Cusco last night. I now have dilemmas about what to wear during the last 24 hours of our stay in Peru as I now have an abundance of clothes to choose from.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Once again thank you so much for you help with this, and if there is anything I can do by way of some form of written reference/accreditation for you I would be delighted to do so - please let me know - I mean that!!</p>','Nick Parry<br />\r\nLondon, UK\r\n<br />\r\nCusco, Machu Picchu\r\n','','','',331,0,0,NULL,NULL,NULL),(616,1,'Hi Rylee,','<p>It was a fantastic trip and I was very pleased to meet you and Garzo as well.</p>\r\n \r\n<p>I just wanted to let you know we enjoyed every moment of our time in Peru. Your staff was very professional, all of our guides were very knowledgeable, transfers on time. We were lucky to have some much time to work with, we left feeling like we really got to know the country. </p>\r\n','Bernie &amp; Karon<br />\r\nEudlo Qld, Australia\r\n<br />\r\nPuerto Maldonado, Cusco, Machu Picchu, Puno, Arequipa, Colca, Nazca, Paracas, Lima\r\n','','','',330,0,0,NULL,NULL,NULL),(617,1,'Hello Rylee,','<p>Thank you for all of your help and advice for our travels to see Cusco and Machu Picchu. We loved our guides and the prompt pick-up and transfer from the airport in Cusco to our hotel. The Casa Andina hotel staff were very helpful and the hotel was in a great location to visit the Plaza de Armes within seconds. We appreciated your restaurant advice and did enjoy the places that you recommended. All in all our trip was absolutely wonderful. </p>\r\n\r\n<p>We loved Ronnie our guide who took us through the ruins of Ollantaytambo but we ran out of time and only had 20 minutes at the Pisac Market, which was a wonderful market to visit but we had to rush through it. Our guide at Machu Picchu was very nice and very knowledgeable. A two-hour guided tour at Machu Picchu should really be extended to 3-4 hours because there is just so much to see and we loved hearing his stories and wanted more but the tour ended too soon.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Hope this helps!\r\nThanks,</p>\r\n','Sue<br />\r\nManitowoc, WI\r\n<br />\r\nCusco, Machu Picchu\r\n','','','',329,0,0,NULL,NULL,NULL),(618,1,'Hi Kelly,','<p>We were just discussing that we should write an email thanking you for such a wonderful job.  Peru for Less has always come through for us, and we have bizarre requests! I see that we can rely on you for the same efficient, friendly, and professional service.  Thanks Kelly!  Weâ??ll look forward to working with you again soon.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Regards, </p>\r\n','Ed\r\n<br />\r\nCusco, Machu Picchu \r\n','','','',328,0,0,NULL,NULL,NULL),(619,1,'Hi Rylee,','<p>Wanted to let you know that everything went just according to plan and we had a great trip!  Having your reps meet us at each juncture really made it go smoothly. </p>\r\n\r\n<p>In Cusco, Allison was great and answered all our questions.  At Machu Picchu our guide,Guido, was excellent, giving good information and spending extra time with us.  </p>\r\n\r\n<p>Our visit was made even more special by staying at the Sanctuary Lodge.  The Inkaterra Lodge was a wonderful way to end the trip and you were right, we needed three nights not two.  The rainforest is truly something to experience.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Thanks for helping us create just the right trip.</p>\r\n','Pat <br />    \r\nFranklin, TN\r\n<br />\r\nLima, Puerto Maldonado, Cusco and Machu Picchu\r\n','','','',327,0,0,NULL,NULL,NULL),(620,1,'Hi Kelly,','<p>How are you? Hope all\'s well with you. So sorry for the long silence, I was just so busy right after coming back from our wonderful trip. </p>\r\n\r\n<p>I had such a wonderful time enjoying the rich culture of peru in such a short time. It wouldn\'t have been possible without people like you from peru for less to organize our trip. Everything was efficiently handled especially our transfers. Our accommodations were superb at the hotel Albergue, Arquelogo &amp; the Casa Andinas. </p>\r\n\r\n<p>I loved  all the places that we went to-Nazca, The Sacred Valley, Cusco &amp; Machu Picchu which to me was the highlight of that trip. It was mystical.Our guides did make us appreciate more the rich culture that peru has for centuries. I would like to thank Mary Luz & Allison for making us less of a tourist but more of a traveller.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Now i can officially cross off another \"places to see before i die\" on my list.</p>Z\r\n\r\n<p>Again, thank you for helping us.</p>\r\n','Raul<br />\r\nLima, Nazca, Cusco, Machu Picchu \r\n','','','',326,0,0,NULL,NULL,NULL),(621,1,'Dear Peru For Less','<p>Thank you so much for helping us organize our trip to Arequipa, Peru on such a short notice.  The trip was wonderful and we had a great time visiting all the sites that we wanted to see.  We enjoy travelling but having someone like you, taking care of all the details for us, makes it even better.  We would definitely recommend Peru For Less to anyone and everyone planning a trip to this wonderful country. </p>\r\n\r\n<p>Saludos, </p>\r\n','Jesus and Niyi \r\nGlastonbury, CT, USA\r\nArequipa\r\n','','','',325,0,0,NULL,NULL,NULL),(622,1,'Hi Kelly,','<p>In a word, the trip was fantastic. Everything was interesting and overall, we would recommend it to anyone. I enjoyed Machu Picchu the most, while Ann\'s favourite was the jungle. Lake Titikaka was interesting, Taquille Island being by far the best part of that segment. Our guide did a wonderful job describing the Taquille culture during a great lunch high atop a hill, under a canopy, overlooking the lake, and showing us some of the peoples\' customs.</p>\r\n \r\n<p>Machu Picchu was awe inspiring, and I wish we had more time there. Cusco was interesting, being built on the Inca plan, narrow streets, etc. Good food, San Blas was charming, and Marlene, our guide, was terrific. I missed the Sacred Valley (altitude and caught a bug) but Ann and Christina enjoyed it.</p>\r\n \r\n<p>The train to Puno was amazing, although it was a long day. I\'d do that again, nonetheless. </p>\r\n\r\n<p>Refugio worked out very well, especially with our guide Aldo. Knowledgeable, helpful, funny, and our group luckily gelled to add a lot to that segment. Great food even if not too fancy. Saw a lot of interesting stuff like the canopy, Brazil nut trees, the farm across the river, some wildlife, and the vegetation. Even if some animals did not show up, or were not close up, it was unique and one of the best parts of the trip.</p>\r\n \r\n<p>Lima was enjoyable, specifically Miraflores, San Isidro, and Barranco. Great food, especially Astride & Gaston which was superb.</p>\r\n \r\n<p>Hotels were fine, as advertised, not luxurious but very adequate, and the Casa Andina staff were friendly and helpful. Aguas Calientes hotel (Machu Pichu Inn?) was one of the best.</p>\r\n \r\n<p>As far as PFL is concerned, high marks. People were there when they were supposed to be and some were exceptional (Caitlin in Cuzco). We were always looked after, so great job. From start to finish, you did a good job so I would recommend your company to anyone. You personally responded very well to the one small glitch, so thank you for that. </p>\r\n   \r\n<p>Thanks for organizing things so well. </p>\r\n \r\n<p>Regards,</p>\r\n','John <br/>\r\nAmazon, Cusco, Machu Picchu, Puno\r\n','','','',699,0,0,NULL,NULL,NULL),(623,1,'Hi Kelly,','<p>Thank you for your email, we had a lovely time in Peru and we appreciate the service we were given from Peru For Less and especially yourself, who answered all our questions and worries before our trip.</p>\r\n \r\n<p>I will recommend Peru for Less to anyone in England who I hear may want to travel to Peru. In fact, my husband is the editor of a small local magazine, and will put your website in there  for others in Kent to see, as the value for money is far better than anything we could find in the UK.</p>\r\n \r\n<p>Thank you, Kelly, all in all a very enjoyable trip.</p>\r\n \r\n<p>Best Wishes,</p>\r\n','Allison <br>\r\nKent, England<br>\r\nCusco and Machu Picchu\r\n','','','',700,0,0,NULL,NULL,NULL),(624,1,'Riva,','<p>Simply put, that was an amazing trip. We had tons of fun, and enjoyed almost every aspect. Cuzco was beautiful. The staff was great, and we really had a great time with our guide. </p>','Kevin<br>\r\nMound, Minnesota, USA<br>\r\nCusco and Salkantay\r\n','','','',324,0,0,NULL,NULL,NULL),(625,1,'Hi Jennifer! ','<p>The trip was terrific and your arrangements were great. Thank you. Ica was my favorite stop. We went on the sand buggy ride. The city tour was interesting, but the best part was the oasis where our hotel was. Keep up the good work.  </p>\r\n\r\nBest, \r\n','Bill <br/>\r\nFlorida\r\n<br/>\r\nLima, Ica, Nazca\r\n','','','',323,0,0,NULL,NULL,NULL),(626,1,'Hi Kelly,','<p>Thank you for the note. I am well and make it to Buenos Aires fine. </p>\r\n\r\n<p>I think the staff from Peru for Less is excellent.  All the the transfers went well, no issue at all.  </p>\r\n\r\n<p>The Inka Trail was \"Fantastic\"!!! I love the trekking company, I give them the upmost rating!!!  We had the BEST Guide and the BEST Cook.  The cook made us a MANGO icing cake on the 2nd trekking day tea time.  It is unbelievably delicious!!!  We were truly impressed and loved the cook. The guide is so good, the moment we finish the trail, we start to miss all the guides, cook and porters!!!</p>\r\n\r\n<p>For the hotel in Cuzco, all the staff and services are really nice. </p>\r\n\r\n<p>The tour to Uros and Tequile islands was really good, good guide is the key.  He knows all about Lake Titicaca and the people.  Everyone was tipping him at the end of the tour.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>I guess that is a lot from me.  Thanks for all the help.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Regards,</p>\r\n','Fui \r\n<br/>\r\nCusco, the Inca Trail to Machu Picchu, Lake Titicaca, Bolivia\r\n','','','',321,0,0,NULL,NULL,NULL),(627,1,'Hi Staci,','<p>Angela and I had enjoyed our trip that you plan for us.  To begin with, the thoroughness of your scheduling of this trip in a last minute thing, I really appreciated that.  It was really VERY ORGANIZED, the transfers were terrific, always on time to and from the airport. Your agent in Cusco was very helpful too (Allison), she did a very good job, even came to take us to the airport at 5 in the morningJ  We really enjoyed the Machu Pichu guide as well (Angel).</p>\r\n\r\n<p>The hotels we had were very satisfactory; Cusco\'s hotel was excellent (Casa Blas).</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Thanks again, Staci.</p>\r\n','Agnes<br/>\r\nCalifornia, USA  \r\n<br/>\r\nMachu Picchu\r\n','','','',320,0,0,NULL,NULL,NULL),(628,1,'Hi Kelly,','<p>Our trip was great! I enjoyed the Amazon and Machu Picchu the most. </p>\r\n\r\n<p>Transfers & Arrangements all went well except for my pick up in Lima (they forgot so I called the emergency # and didn\'t get to the hotel until after 12:30am). All of our guides were very nice and gave a lot of great information. </p>\r\n\r\n<p>Our favorite hotels were the Sandoval lodge, Arqueologo, and the hotel in Colca Canyon.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>We really liked Cusco - such a neat city! The Amazon was perfect.</p>\r\n','Katie <br/>\r\nLima, the Amazon, Cusco and Machu Picchu, Puno and Arequipa\r\n','','','',319,0,0,NULL,NULL,NULL),(629,1,'Hello Jennifer,','<p>I just wanted to drop you a line and let you know how much we enjoyed our trip to Peru.  It was wonderful.  Every day was filled with a new and exciting adventure.  It was especially helpful knowing that Peru For Less would always be a phone call away if there were any problems.  Our trip went very smoothly and it was great to have someone there waiting for us when we arrived in a new city.  We liked that we were able to see all we wanted to see without having to stick to a certain itinerary set by someone else.  We met many interesting people, including your own employees.  We always felt like we were in good hands and never had any worries as we traveled.  We have told all our friends and family that they need to add Peru to their to do list and to contact Peru For Less to be sure they get the trip they want.  Thanks again for all your help and for providing us with such a great trip.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Sincerely,</p>\r\n','Jim &amp; Suzanne <br/> \r\nCalifornia \r\n<br/>\r\nLima, Puerto Maldonado, Cusco, Machu Picchu, Puno, Arequipa, Nazca, Ica, Paracas\r\n','','','',318,0,0,NULL,NULL,NULL),(630,1,'Hi Kelly,','<p>We had a wonderful time in Lima, Cusco and Machu Picchu! Peru is such a beautiful country. Peru for Less was fantastic as well as Pachamama. The entire trip was very well done and we were so pleased that we used your company. Everything from the hotels, transportation, travel guides and porters were first class. I would highly recommend your company to ANYONE traveling to Peru.</p>\r\n  \r\n<p>Thank you for all of your help!</p>\r\n\r\n','Danielle <br/>\r\n<br/>\r\nLima, Cusco, and the Luxury Inca Trail to Machu Picchu\r\n','','','',317,0,0,NULL,NULL,NULL),(631,1,'Hi Kelly, ','<p>We had a very good time. Both weeks were completed different. Loved Cusco, the Sacred Valley, and Machu Picchu. The hotels were fantastic, especially the Sumaq. </p>\r\n\r\n<p>We upgraded our train tickets ($30) coming home as we wanted an earlier train at 3 pm. It had much nicer seats and service like an airline. I would recommend this level of services on the train to other travelers.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Amazon was great - great guides, crew, and other quests. We had 3 great jungle treks and we met three different tribal villages on the trip. The plant life and animals were interesting and we enjoyed our visits with the local villages.  For those who want to visit the indigenous people of the Amazon I highly recommend bringing donations such as pens and paper for the children. You would not believe how much these items that we take for granted were appreciated.</p>\r\n','Catherine and Sheryl\r\n<br/>\r\nCusco, Machu Picchu, Iquitos\r\n','','','',316,0,0,NULL,NULL,NULL),(632,1,'Hi Rylee,','<p>Thanks for e-mails. As you know, we had the BEST trip. Again-THANKS. We look forward to keeping in touch with you. </p>\r\n\r\n<p>Thanks for taking such good care of us. Ray especially liked being on the \"right\" side of the train-both ways!</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Cheers!   </p>\r\n','G&R<br/>\r\nVancouver, BC\r\n<br/>\r\nLima, Cusco, Machu Picchu\r\n','','','',315,0,0,NULL,NULL,NULL),(633,1,'Rylee,','<p>We had a wonderful trip. I will use you for all our trips to Central and South America. </p>\r\n\r\n<p>Thanks,</p>\r\n','Ravi <br/>\r\nMidland, TX\r\n<br/>\r\nLima, Cusco, Machu Picchu, Puerto Maldonado\r\n','','','',314,0,0,NULL,NULL,NULL),(634,1,'Hello Rylee,','<p>We enjoyed our trip and really appreciate all your help in the planning process. You were great in answering our questions and had some great suggestions for my son\'s birthday in Lima. </p>\r\n\r\n<p>I just wanted to let you know we have an incredible trip. All the guides were wonderful, our hotels were clean and comfortable and all was as planned. Thank you so much, I would definitely recommend Peru For Less and use you in the future for any trips to South America. </p>\r\n \r\n<p>Thanks again!</p>\r\n','Crystal <br/>\r\nIndianapolis, IN\r\n<br/>\r\nLima, Puerto Maldonado, Cusco, Machu Picchu\r\n','','','',313,0,0,NULL,NULL,NULL),(635,1,'Hi, Matt, ','<p>Just got back to Lima last night after a great trip...many thanks for organizing that. Everything went really smoothly, no hickups whatsoever. Really enjoyed the tour...great hotels, fantastic sights. Really great and am looking forward to coming back already, although probably N. Chile and Bolivia will be next...with you guys donig the planning, I hope!! Thanks again. </p>\r\n\r\n<p>Best Regards, </p>\r\n','Brian <br/> \r\nUnited Kingdom\r\n<br/>\r\nLima, Trujillo, Chiclayo, Cusco and Machu Picchu, Puerto Maldonado, Puno, Arequipa and Colca Canyon, Nazca, and Paracas            \r\n	','','','',312,0,0,NULL,NULL,NULL),(636,1,'Rylee,','<p>The rest of our trip was lots of fun. We hope to be able to return to Peru when we can spend a little more time.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Thanks for your help,</p>\r\n','Kathi <br/>\r\nFairbanks, Alaska<br/>\r\nPuerto Maldonado, 2 Day Inca Trail, Machu Picchu\r\n','','','',311,0,0,NULL,NULL,NULL),(637,1,'Dear Peru For Less','<p>My trip to Peru was fabulous and my adventure to Machu Picchu was a highlight. My trip arrangements came off exactly how you described and all Peru for Less folks were super nice, professional, and reliable.  Look forward to booking more excursions! </p>\r\n\r\n<p>Thanks again for your help and expertise, </p>\r\n','Larry <br/>\r\nVermont, USA\r\nMachu Picchu\r\n','','','',310,0,0,NULL,NULL,NULL),(638,1,'Dear Kristina,','<p>We were met by your man on the airport and he immediately took us to hotel Tribeca, which was a fine hotel. The city tour next day was nice, with a good guide. The same about the Dinner and Tango Show: both were great. Hotel Saint George in Iguazu was an excellent hotel.</p>\r\n \r\n<p>Greetings and best wishes,</p>\r\n','Ad  <br/>\r\nHolland<br/>\r\nBuenos Aires and Iguazu Falls\r\n','','','',309,0,0,NULL,NULL,NULL),(639,1,'Hi Kelly, ','<p>We had a WONDERFUL TIME!   We were all SO impressed with Peru for Less. Thank you Kelly for everything you did.  It was an absolutely delightful pleasure to work with you.  </p>','Carolyn<br/>\r\nLima, Ica, Nazca, Arequipa, Cusco, Machu Picchu, Puno\r\n','','','',308,0,0,NULL,NULL,NULL),(640,1,'Hi Rylee,','<p>We are back in San Diego and had to go to work the next day. We had a wonderful time everything went on time and our guides were good.The hike itself was not very difficult gradual slopes good fauna and flora but a lot of steps to climb along the way.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Thank you,</p>\r\n','Girija\r\nLa Mesa, CA\r\nLima, Cusco, 2 Day Inca Trail to Machu Picchu\r\n','','','',307,0,0,NULL,NULL,NULL),(641,1,'Kelly,','<p>We have an excellent experience overall.  Macchu Picchu was definitely the highlight and did not disappoint.  We had great weather there too and not cloudy at the location just in surrounding mountains.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>As for the the specifics, we were very happy to see the guy holding the sign saying MERICLE on it at Lima Airport. It was a relief and helped put us at ease using your company.  The first gentlemen was very nice and appreciated.  The rest of the transfers went well overall.  </p>\r\n \r\n<p>In terms of tours, we enjoyed the Lima tour for two reasons.  One, it covered the key old town areas well enough so we did not feel the need to go there later and it met for the tour bus at a park next to Huaca Pucllana which is from the 7th century AD.  On the last day we walked there and enjoyed a very fine tour (they have English guides) and gained a little insight into the Lima culture along with a small section on some common plants and animals. You also see the surrounding town to provide an interesting juxtoposition. I would recommend this to clients.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>The tour of Cusco was also fine as we covered the Cathedral and its Monastery and another musuem along with Suscayhuaman.  The tour of the Sacred Valley was also interesting and our guide was excellent at Ollaytaytambo.  Ollaytaytambo was spectacular and gave a nice perspective different than Macchu Picchu.  </p>\r\n\r\n<p>All the hotels were good accomadations with the one in Sonesta being our most favorite. It was great each had internet available with the best being at Casa Andina in Cusco.  The service was also friendly and attentive, especially at El Carmel, Casa Andina and Sonesta. Sonesta and Casa Andina had the best breakfasts with pancakes and eggs and bacon available along with breads, cereal, fruit and yogurt. </p>\r\n\r\n<p>Our favorite spot was Macchu Picchu - truly spectacular, including the train ride along the Urubamba River.  After that, we liked Arequipa next most.  We had excellent meals there and the plaza is busy and beautiful.  </p>\r\n\r\n<p>Peru for Less provided us with excellent service and was usually quick to respond when something arose.  </p>\r\n \r\n<p>We will certainly put you at the top of the list for contacts on any future trip to Peru along with trips to Argentina and Brazil.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Blessings and thanks,</p>\r\n','Jim \r\nLima, Cusco, Arequipa\r\n','','','',306,0,0,NULL,NULL,NULL),(642,1,'Hi Rylee, ','<p>Peru for Less truly helped make our trip unforgettable. The service was impeccable and the tour guides were helpful and friendly. We had a wonderful time and would use this company again in a heartbeat. \r\nWe had a fantastic time on our trip. The Peru for Less guides were wonderful and everything went seamlessly. We really appreciate your services and will recommend them to friends. \r\nOnce again, thank you for your help in making this experience so special. </p>\r\n','Emily \r\nWashington, DC\r\nArequipa, Lake Titicaca, Cusco, Machu Picchu\r\n','','','',305,0,0,NULL,NULL,NULL),(643,1,'Matt,','<p>Lorette and I want to thank everyone at Peru For Less for the most memorable and wonderful honeymoon we could possibly imagine. </p>\r\n\r\n<p>Our flight from Atlanta to Lima was more than an hour late. Miguel was there waiting for us, much to our relief. He got us to our hotel, provided and explained all our tickets and documents and patiently answered all our questions despite the late hour. </p>\r\n\r\n<p>The next day we flew to Cuzco where we were met at the airport by Allison, who was cheerful and friendly as well as professional and efficient. She got us to our transportation very quickly and met us shortly afterwards at the hotel to go over our itinerary and answer questions. She also gave us personal recommendations for restaurants which we relied on during the course of the week and we were never disappointed. Maria was our guide for Cuzco and the Sacred Valley and Mr. Renato was our driver. We cannot say enough about the two of them. They were always on time for the tours and more often they were early. Mr. Renato was an excellent driver, his vehicle was spotless and he was courteous and thoughtful. Maria was a jewel. She was so knowledgeable and it was obvious that she was enthusiastic about her role as our tour guide. Both were eager and willing to accommodate when we requested a change in the itinerary, as when we requested to go to the Seminario in Urubamba. When we parted with them at the end of the week, it was as though we were parting with friends. </p>\r\n\r\n<p>Fabrizio was our guide at Machu Picchu. It was obvious that he knew his subject extremely well, and he went out of his way to point out small details and items of interest. Furthermore, he was charming and delightful to be with. </p>\r\n\r\n<p>Justina met us at the train depot at Aquas Calientes. She was so friendly and so helpful. We saw her again at the depot as we were departing and had a lovely conversation. Upon our return to Lima we were met again by Miguel. Also, when I asked about any shops that sold stone and mineral specimens, Miguel went out of his way to find three such stores. </p>\r\n\r\n<p>Finally, we want to personally thank you, Matt. As you well know, we customized our trip to suit ourselves. You worked with us through dozens of emails and numerous phone calls as we tweaked all the details to get it exactly the way we wanted. </p>\r\n\r\n<p>Really and truly, we cannot thank you, and everyone mentioned above, enough for a truly remarkable honeymoon. Gracias!!!</p>\r\n','Bill \r\nCandler, North Carolina\r\nLima, Cusco, Machu Picchu\r\n','','','',304,0,0,NULL,NULL,NULL),(644,1,'Kelly, ','<p>A quick note from me to thank you and your providers for planning a fabulous trip for my son and husband. They returned yesterday quite exhausted, but so happy with all that had happened. The weather was perfect which was a nice touch you must have added.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>The guides were outstanding, the driver was very careful, the hotels were wonderful, and the overall experience breathtaking (literally). Your Peruforless staff were really excellent. They enjoyed the historical knowledge that both Fabrizio and Maria Elena provided for us.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Their favorite hotel was the Sol y Luna which they said was the best hotel they have ever stayed in and they HIGHLY recommend staying there for people the first couple of nights. The sights in that area were fantastic.  Machu Picchu was all they expected and more.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Thanks again for all your help.</p>\r\n',' McNeill \r\nLima, Sacred Valley, Cusco, Machu Picchu\r\n','','','',303,0,0,NULL,NULL,NULL),(645,1,'Rylee,','<p>Joan and I both wanted to express that we had an AMAZING time and owe many thanks to Peru for Less for helping facilitate such an amazing journey for us!  </p>\r\n\r\n<p>The highlight of our trip was the tour guide you set us up with, his name was Edgar, and the fact that we were able to have just the two of us on the hike was more than we could have asked for.  We appreciated that as a big part of what made this experience so special and so much more than just a hike up the Andes mountains.  </p>\r\n\r\n<p>In addition, people were there to pick us up and messages were left for us in a timely fashion that created a security in a place that was foreign to us.  Moreover, the fact that someone walked us into the airport to make sure we got checked in and knew where we had to go to pay the airport tax etc was a huge relief! </p>\r\n\r\n<p>I would highly recommend your company to others traveling to Peru, you can trust I will be sending people your way!</p>\r\n','Carmen\r\nChicago, Illinois\r\nCusco, 2 Day Inca Trail, Machu Picchu\r\n','','','',302,0,0,NULL,NULL,NULL),(646,1,'Hello Kelly,','<p>Here\'s a summary of our trip experiences.  </p>\r\n<p>At the initial stop in Lima the driver and representative that picked us up were great, the transfer was smooth and the coordinator was very helpful. Our first hotel in Lima (El Carmel) was nice, great bathroom, Wi-Fi worked well, the hotel staff was nice and the breakfast was good. At the end of the day we realized how close we were to the park and shopping.  The transfer back to the airport was easy.</p>\r\n<p>In Cuzco the initial flight was great; we had tons of leg room on the plane. Our coordinator was waiting for us at the airport, she was very nice and helpful, and the driver was also very professional. We loved the hotel (Ninos Hotel) right away and really enjoyed staying there very much.</p>\r\n<p>Our first day was a little tough because of the altitude.  We both had hard time breathing, got headaches and sleeping was tough. The guided trip we took was great; buses and guide were very nice.  The guide took us to a wonderful store for buying alpaca clothes where we felt like we had personal shoppers.  We loved being able to negotiate prices.</p>\r\n<p>During the Sacred Valley Tour once again the bus and guide were excellent.  This was likely the best guided tour we took. The valley, markets, food, sights, all of it was just really incredible. Highlights were shopping in the market, seeing the weavers and stopping by the local pub to drink with locals.</p>\r\n<p>Once we got to Aqua Caliente the bag transfer to hotel and getting on the bus to Machu Picchu was very smooth. The bus ride was amazing. We absolutely loved the Machu Picchu site. We had a great lunch and were really impressed in every way.  Weather could not have been more perfect and loved the passport stamp. We then went to our hotel where we found our room to be one of their best.</p>\r\n<p>In Puerto Maldonado once again our transfer to the airport was easy and helpful, both the coordinator and driver were great. Once we arrived the guide was waiting for us and took us to the transfer office.</p>\r\n<p>Our boat ride was really relaxing, exciting and enjoyable.  We loved the lunch of rice, eggs and mushrooms wrapped in the leaf. The checkpoint station was easy and we loved being able to stamp our passport for the Amazon.</p>\r\n<p>The arrival to the Refugio Amazonas lodge while walking was very exciting.  We loved the touch of greeting us with a fruit drink. Our room was great, although it takes some getting used to an open view to the jungle.</p>\r\n<p>Our first night boat trip looking for caimans was a great way to begin. All of the food here was wonderful, including the drinks of pisco sour, hot chocolate and tea. Our guide was very knowledgeable, funny, professional and helpful.  We can\'t compliment him enough. We loved all the guided tours where we saw the diversity in the forest and enjoyed the other group members.  This location seemed to be a key spot for families. The highlights were climbing the canopy tower, learning about the medicinal plant life, touring the farm, paddling in the lake, seeing the large trees and Treina loved her massage.  </p>\r\n<p>All in all we very much enjoyed the trip, </p>\r\n','Eric <br/>\r\nLima, Cuzco, Machu Picchu, The Amazon<br/>\r\n','','','',711,0,0,NULL,NULL,NULL),(647,1,'Dear Jennifer,','<p>We returned safe and sound to Belgium after the fantastic Salkantay hiking trip and the visit to Machu Pichu.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>The Salkantay trip is beautiful and sometimes hard because of the adaptation to the height which is not so easy to deal with especially during the first days. The nights at the beginning were cold which is normal at 4300 m. But this is all quickly forgotten if you see the fantastic nature around you.</p>\r\n<p>When coming down, we entered the rain forests which were also very impressive. At the end, we did a last big effort by climbing the Machu Pichu mountain. From there, the view to the Machu Pichu site was fantastic. Later the guide took us through the Machu Pichu site. No surprise that this is one of the world wonders!\r\n\r\nThe two of us were guided by Fredy and taken care of by the cook Flabio. The organization was very good and there was nothing that went wrong. The food was terrific and we were treated like kings.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>We are very satisfied with the Peru For Less organization and will certainly recommend you. I would also recommend the Salkantay trail, which is unbelievably beautiful, to nature and hiking lovers.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Best regards,</p>\r\n','Lut and Michel <br />\r\nCuzco, Machu Picchu, Salcantay<br/>\r\n','','','',282,0,0,NULL,NULL,NULL),(648,1,'Hello,','<p>We all had a great time in Peru and I wish I was still there!</p>\r\n<p>I enjoyed all of the places that we visited and especially liked Cusco. The Salkantay trek was great with amazing views and a thoroughly enjoyable experience. I am glad I chose to do the trek over getting the train to Machu Picchu. Machu Picchu itself made it all worthwhile, it was spectacular. The transfers were good and made travelling easy. All of the tours were enjoyable and a good value for the money and the tour guides were friendly, helpful and knowledgeable.</p>\r\n<p>The Arqueologo hotel in Cusco was very nice and I would highly recommend this hotel.</p>\r\n<p>I think that Peru for Less does give a good value for the money and uses very good tour companies.</p>\r\n<p>Thank you,</p>\r\n','Alison <br/>\r\nManu, Cuzco, Salcantay Trek to Machu Picchu, Lake Titicaca\r\n','','','',710,0,0,NULL,NULL,NULL),(649,1,'Jennifer,','<p>We had a wonderful time and enjoyed the entire trip.  The Inca trail was extremely challenging and I have to admit, I was not as prepared as I thought. The Galapagos portion of the trip was very relaxing and we were very glad that it came after the Inca trail.  It seems that the order of our adventures was perfect!  Get used to the area in the jungle, then do the killer hike, then relax on the boat;-D\r\nOverall, I would rate the trip wonderful, and all of the people that we met and interacted with were helpful, informative, and pleasant.</p>\r\n<p>Have a wonderful day,</p>\r\n\r\n','Kenne <br/>\r\nCuzco, Machu Picchu, Puerto Maldonado, Lima, Quito, Galapagos, Inca Trail<br/>\r\n','','','',301,0,0,NULL,NULL,NULL),(650,1,'Hi Matt,','<p>We had a great trip!  All the transfers, guides and all the hotels were great.  The Ramada at the Lima airport worked really well.  We had an incredible time at the Explorerâ??s Inn in Puerto Maldonado.  </p>\r\n<p>I think Pakaritampu in Ollantaytambo was our favorite hotel and town.  El Pueblo Inkaterra was great, the grounds remarkable and the food excellent. At Casa Andina San Blas Derrickâ??s and my room were excellent, all that was described about looking out over red tile roofs, etc.  </p>\r\n<p>Machu Picchu was an incredible experience. We had a beautiful, sunny day.</p>\r\n<p>We did not get the name of the woman who took us to the Cusco airport â?? she had been with Peru For Less for only 2 weeks â?? but she was REALLY helpful getting us through the airport in spite of a protest that closed the airport to vehicles.  She was informative on the strike issues and had a great attitude, excellent English and was just a delight to be around.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Thanks again, Matt.</p>\r\n','Marilyn <br/>\r\nSanta Cruz, California<br/>\r\nLima, Puerto Maldonado, Sacred Valley, Cuzco, Machu Picchu<br/>\r\n\r\n','','','',300,0,0,NULL,NULL,NULL),(651,1,'Hi Rylee,','<p>Our trip was very good. We had a positive experience. I know I complicated things in the planning process, but you were always so great in your answers to my questions and your suggestions were also very helpful. The staff along the way was very professional and we enjoyed our guides, tours and hotels. We travel a lot and this was our first trip to South America. Based on our experience with your company, I am sure that we as well as our friends will use your services in the next few years to come.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Thanks for a great experience! </p>\r\n','Vivek <br/>\r\nOrlando, FL<br/>\r\nLima, Puerto Maldonado, Cuzco, Puno and Arequipa\r\n','','','',299,0,0,NULL,NULL,NULL),(652,1,'Hi Kelly, ','<p>The trip was wonderful.  Machu Picchu was amazing but it was only the tip of the iceberg.  Peru has so much to see.  I was amazed by the other Inca temples we visited and I found the Peruvians are soft-spoken and well-mannered.  Thanks for all your help in planning our trip.  I will definitely recommend Peru For Less to my friends and family.</p>','John <br />\r\nLima, Cuzco &amp; Machu Picchu<br />\r\n','','','',298,0,0,NULL,NULL,NULL),(653,1,'Hi Rylee,','<p>Everything went well.  We loved Peru. The guides, the transfers, the sightseeing all were very good and well arranged.  We would have loved to stay longer.  The altitude could be a challenge at times, but aspirins and naps in the buses could overcome that. Naps in buses during the day are sometimes necessary because altitude challenges seemed to affect us even more at night than in the day.  We would wake up at 2:30am and have trouble sleeping for hours.  I hope the guides did not take our naps too personally.</p>\r\n \r\n<p>I really appreciated arriving in new cities and having a Peru For Less arranged driver and/or greeter there for us.  This is particularly good when accompanied by a 70 something year-old or anyone who does not travel much and/or speak the local language.   The hotels were all clean and had lovely grounds.  We felt very relaxed sitting in their courtyards looking at their flowers and birds (really liked the humming birds) and always enjoyed the breakfast buffets.  We tried to buy crafts at a virtually every city and remote outpost stop, often from elderly ladies in full traditional colors and hats. Guides Janet in Cuzco and David in Ollantaytambo were particularly good, but I was happy with all of them \r\nOf course we all loved Cuzco but I was really happy to visit Lake Titicaca and to see what the floating islands and their people are all about.  </p>\r\n \r\n<p>I would certainly recommend Peru For Less to anyone interested in traveling to that wonderful and memorable country.  You and your team in Cuzco did a great job and can be very proud of having put together a complex (hotels, guides, transfers, bus/plane tickets, etc.) itinerary together so well.</p>\r\n \r\n<p>Thank you for all your care in seeing us through this superb experience,</p>\r\n','Paul <br />\r\nLima, Cuzco, Machu Picchu, Puno, Arequipa, Nazca, Paracas\r\n','','','',297,0,0,NULL,NULL,NULL),(654,1,'Dear Peru For Less','<p>You prepared a beautiful trip for us that was well laid out and had resources at every turn.  We have loads of pictures and would love to do a testimonial for you all.  </p>\r\n\r\n<p>I\'m sure with enough time we could outline all the good we noticed along the way. We really enjoyed the trip. We relaxed, learned a lot, and took some exciting adventures. The hotels were all different and perfect for each location.  We especially loved El Alburgue and who couldn\'t be impressed with the Libertador. The 5 stars hotel was the perfect way to end the trip and we were extremely glad we added the extra days in Cusco- amazing city.   </p>\r\n\r\n<p>Thank you again for creating such a well planned, organized but free feeling trip. It fit us perfectly, pregnancy and all!</p>\r\n','Jennifer and Chris <br />\r\nValley Center, CA<br />\r\nLima, Machu Picchu, Cusco<br />\r\n','','','',296,0,0,NULL,NULL,NULL),(655,1,'Hi Kristina','<p>All is well here in Paracas. We had a fantastic time and are continuing to do so.  Thanks for the champagne that was a very nice touch and a wonderful surprise. What a nice way to end our honeymoon!  \r\nThanks for all your organization, everything was as per your itinerary and on time, you certainly have everything worked out very well. </p>\r\n \r\n<p>Regards,</p>\r\n','Carol and Steven  <br />\r\nOntario, Canada<br />\r\nLima, Arequipa, Puno, Cuzco, Puerto Maldonado, Paracas\r\n','','','',295,0,0,NULL,NULL,NULL),(656,1,'Hi Matt,','<p>We had a wonderful time in Peru. It was quite an adventure for us.  I want to thank you for re-arranging the trip at the last minute. I really enjoyed Arequipa and Colca Canyon and I am so glad we added that. All the transfers were flawless.  It is really nice when you are not always thinking about how you are going to get from one place to another. </p>\r\n<p>Thanks,</p>\r\n','Beth <br />\r\nSilver Spring, Maryland<br />\r\nArequipa, Colca Canyon, Cuzco, Machu Picchu\r\n','','','',294,0,0,NULL,NULL,NULL),(657,1,'Hi Matt','<p>We are still in Lima for a few days. Don\'t know if you heard, but Peruvian Airlines sent our luggage to Quitos instead of Cusco. Your folks on the ground stepped in and basically saved me! \r\nDespite three days in the same clothes, the trip was incredible. </p>\r\n','Thompson<br />\r\nLima, Cuzco, Machu Picchu\r\n','','','',293,0,0,NULL,NULL,NULL),(658,1,'Hi,','<p>All went very well. My son and I enjoyed the experience immensely. The group from Wayki Trek was with excellent providers of both hospitality and services. The whole event turned out as a wonderful experience, thanks to the knowledge and experience of the staff of Wayki Trek. The Salcantay Trek was more difficult then I would have ever imagined. However, I am not the one who does a great deal of hiking in the mountains. Matt thanks for your efforts to accommodate my requests during our last day in Lima. You guys are great! Please continue to use Wayki Trek and your list of satisfied customers will continue to grow. </p>','Gonzalez<br />\r\nCuzco, Machu Picchu, Salcantay, Lima\r\n','','','',292,0,0,NULL,NULL,NULL),(659,1,'Staci,','<p>All was great. It was really a no hassle trip.  Allison checked in everyday and made sure I knew where to be the next day.  Ronnie was very passionate about his country which shows in his work. Thanks for a very good time.</p>','Barry <br/>\r\nKentland, IN, USA<br/>\r\nMachu Picchu\r\n','','','',291,0,0,NULL,NULL,NULL),(660,1,'Dear Peru For Less','<p>My recent trip to Peru was absolutely incredible.  I would like to thank you and Peru For Less for helping me put together a comprehensive, customized trip on a very short notice. I really had a fantastic trip - thank you again for helping me make this happen!! </p>','Juliann  <br/>\r\nRI, USA<br/>\r\nLima, Machu Picchu, Cusco, Nazca, Paracas\r\n','','','',290,0,0,NULL,NULL,NULL),(661,1,'Hi Jennifer,','<p>We had a fabulous time and everything went very smoothly!  It was so nice to relax and know that someone would always meet us, explain things to us and keep us organized.</p>\r\n<p>Thanks for all your work in planning our trip.  We have already recommended you to some friends who plan to go next year.</p>\r\n<p>Best,</p>\r\n','Connie  <br />\r\nCusco, Machu Picchu, 2nd Inca Trail\r\n','','','',289,0,0,NULL,NULL,NULL),(662,1,'Matt,','<p>We had a wonderful time.  Everywhere was an adventure.  Your staff was always friendly and helpful. </p>\r\n  \r\n<p>I loved Colca Canyon and we saw many condors.  I enjoyed Titicaca Lake.  We hiked up Machu Pichu mountain and the view was incredible.  The sacred valley was my daughter\'s favorite place.  It was so beautiful.  </p>\r\n \r\n<p>Thanks so much for putting together a terrific itinerary.  You included some great tours and the hotels were nice.  </p>\r\n \r\n<p>I will definitely recommend Peru For Less.  And, I will definitely think of you if I can save enough money for my next trip to Brazil.</p>\r\n \r\n<p>Regards,</p>\r\n','Colette <br />\r\nWailuku, Hawaiii<br />\r\nLima, MP, Cusco, Arequipa, Nazca, Paracas , Puno\r\n','','','',288,0,0,NULL,NULL,NULL),(663,1,'Hello Kelly,','<p>Thanks again for all the help with setting up our trip to Peru.  Everything was so amazing!  Beautiful sites, great guides, and a great adventure. Every representative was absolutely amazing! Everything was two thumbs up.  </p>','Zachary <br />\r\nPuerto Maldonado, Cuzco, Machu Picchu\r\n','','','',287,0,0,NULL,NULL,NULL),(664,1,'Dear Peru For Less','<p>I just wanted to let you know that we had a wonderful trip.  Everything was organized and as expected.  Your company did a great job.  Thank you for reassuring me. </p>\r\n<p>IT WAS WONDERFUL!!!!!  </p>\r\n','Henry and Debra<br />\r\nTX, USA<br />\r\nMachu Picchu, Cusco\r\n','','','',286,0,0,NULL,NULL,NULL),(665,1,'Hi Riva,','<p>Dipan and I had a nice tour in Peru. We wanted to thank Peru For Less for all the arrangements you made for us and all the seamless transactions that we had with you. Your tour guide at all places was helpful and friendly. We had a good experience and we will recommend Peru For Less to our friends and family.</p>\r\n<p>Thank you again for helping us with our tour. </p>\r\n<p>Warm Regards,</p>\r\n','Sunanda <br />\r\nCusco, Machu Picchu\r\n','','','',285,0,0,NULL,NULL,NULL),(666,1,'Dear Jennifer,','<p>WOW! I loved Peru. And a lot of what we experienced was due to your excellent work. Everything went smoothly: from the pickups and transfers to the hotels to the guides on the tours. We felt so relaxed and confident that everything was taken care of for us and all we had to do was enjoy. We loved Second Home, Lilian Delfin is so gracious and meeting Victor Delfin was a high point of our trip. What a unique place to stay. Cuzco and the Sacred Valley and Machu Picchu were spectacular. All our guides were knowledgeable and friendly. And Reserva Amazonica was wonderful. Regrettably, there were no birds on the clay lick but even that was OK. I surely hope we can return someday and if so, we will surely use Peru For Less. You were marvelous. </p>\r\n<p>By the way, my husband, who until recently never wanted to travel, is now thinking about visiting Argentina. So maybe your agency will be able to help us again soon.</p>\r\n<p>Thanks for everything.</p>\r\n','Kathy <br />\r\nCusco, Machu Picchu, Puerto Maldonado, Lima, Ica, Paracas\r\n','','','',284,0,0,NULL,NULL,NULL),(667,1,'Hi, ','<p>I am writing to let you know that I am muy agradecida.  I am hoping the energy of Pachamama lingers with us for days to come.  The trip was a wondrous experience....vistas, histories, affable Peruvians....And, thanks to Peru For Less it became every bit as magical and unforgettable experience as promised by tourist ads.  </p>\r\n\r\n<p>Peru For Less planned a five day tour of Peru with stops in Lima, Cusco and climaxing in Machu Pichu.  On each leg of journey we were met by Peru For Less drivers, escorts and guides who were punctual, professional, knowledgeable and affable.  One certainly develops a sense of confidence in PFL personnel that was waiting in the airport at 2 am for hours later than when we were expected.  I might also add that it is very reassuring to have emergency contact numbers of local PFL personnel; this became especially meaningful when one of us got the dreaded altitude sickness. The paper work was neatly organized. We are very grateful to your attention to details. Thank you also for keeping the tour group small size - the largest group was 8.  </p>\r\n<p>Fabrizio and Juan Carlos are memorable for their charm, knowledge, pride of Inca heritage and theatrical fare.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>We all were very grateful to the efficiency, reliability, professionalism of Peru For Less. We were able to enjoy the beauty and magic of Peru without being stopped by the stress of inefficient trip plans. Yes, we passed this on to the other tourists, especially to the ones that had been let down or deceived by other agencies.  </p>\r\n\r\n<p>We have already recommended PFL to the disgruntled tourists who were let down by their tour guides as well as friends and acquaintances in Florida who have never even thought of traveling to Peru.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Thanks for your good work,  </p>\r\n','Monica <br />\r\nCuzco &amp; Machu Picchu\r\n','','','',322,0,0,NULL,NULL,NULL),(668,1,'Dear Kelly,','<p>Wow, what an incredible 10 days!!!  We have been planning our trip to Peru since last September and hate that is now over.  As you know we had hundreds of questions, all which you answered patiently, always clarifying any of our concerns with your prompt email communications.  </p>\r\n\r\n<p>First let me start that this is the first time that I have used a travel agency from the internet.  I used the Frommer Guide book as a guide and wrote to several agencies about how we wanted to do our trip and estimated costs.  Of all the emails we sent out for information yours was the one that stood out the most.  You assured us that we could plan our trip just the way we wanted and not have to be part of a larger tour group.  Of course we had lots of doubts about the arrangements, the accommodations, and the logistics all which you helped in making our decisions.  </p>\r\n\r\n<p>Here is a breakdown of our trip.  We arrived in Lima late and tired on Friday, June 25. We were immediately greeted by Miguel who took us to the waiting van and on to our first stay at the lovely Bed and Breakfast, Second Home.  We immediately fell in love with this historic home and were very happy with our room with the view of the Pacific Ocean.  The next day we explored the grounds and got a personal tour of Victor Delphin\'s artist studio.  Miguel picked us up as scheduled gave us an informative tour of historic Lima.  We enjoyed his company so much that we invited him to join us for our delicious lunch of Peruvian delicacies and of course our first taste of Pisco Sour.  </p>\r\n\r\n<p>We left for Cuzco on Sunday, on time and on schedule and arrived at Cuzco.  We were once again greeted by a representative from Peru for Less, Emelie, who orientated us to Cuzco, went over our admissions to Machu Picchu, and the travel arrangements to Agua Calientes.  We enjoyed our  free time is Cuzco exploring the Plaza, the San Blas neighborhood, taking a tour of the Temple of the Sun, and  hiring a taxi driver to show us the ruins above the city.  We had no trouble with the altitude and enjoyed our meals at the Inka Grill, Pachapappa, and Cicciolina\'s, all which were first class. We loved our hotel Picoaga and we pleased that we were in the older, colonial section as we had requested. Thanks, Kelly, we were sure that you put in a special request.    Our room was charming with a balcony facing the street and lovely view of the inner courtyard getting to and from our room.  </p>\r\n\r\n<p>We left for Machu Picchu on Tuesday and again were very pleased that our transportation arrived just as promised.  We appreciated the reminders and the communication about our travel plans with the hotel staff.  We enjoyed the leg of our journey in the newly refurbished Backpacker Train. Thanks again for making this change from our original plans.   We arrived at Agua Calientes and was greeted by a representative from Peru for Less who showed us how to get to our hotel and dropped us of at a caf&eacute; to enjoy a leisurely lunch.  Fabricio, our guide, called that evening and we arranged to meet him on Wednesday at 1:30 for our tour of the mountain.  We loved your suggestion of having the full day on the mountain Wednesday.  Wayne and Larry left at 6:30 AM and Cinda and I joined them around 9:30 AM.  We thoroughly enjoyed this incredible sight were glad to have the additional educational insights with Fabricio later that afternoon. It was well worth to the 4,000 mile journey to experience this indescribable place.  The Hatuchay Tower hotel was wonderful with an incredible, accommodating staff.  What a beautiful hotel and we were so surprised about our lovely and delicious gourmet dinner.  It certainly was not typical of our hotel food back in the states.  </p>\r\n\r\n<p>We left for our trip back to Cuzco on Wednesday night and arrived back to the Picoaga hotel even receiving the same room that we had left on Tuesday morning.  On Thursday, once again our transportation was ready to take us to the Cuzco airport for our flight to Puerto Maldonado.  At the airport we were greeted by a representative from our lodge Inkaterra Reserva Amazonica.  We got in the open Safari wagon and were transported to the reception area where we were greeted with cool towels and refreshing drink.  After our boat trip down the Madres the Dios river we thought we had arrived at \"Fantasy Island\" since we were greeted with a ringing bell and the smartly, uniformed staff waiting by the landing. We immediately met our interpreter Wilson who shared with us the many wonderful expeditions that we could participate in during our stay.  We then were ushered into the beautiful main lodge for our first of many delicious meals.  We loved our cute cabin right by the river, (thanks again, Kelly), and our entire experience at this beautiful lodge. The highlight of our stay was doing the canopy walk, seeing the monkeys and the river otters at Lake Sandoval, and connecting with others from all part of the world. </p>\r\n\r\n<p>We hated to leave this beautiful place but we very happy with our hotel Casa Andina Private Collection back in Lima.  Once again your representatives picked us up at the airport and took us back to the airport the next day for our flight back to the states on time and on schedule.    </p>\r\n\r\n<p>We highly recommend our itinerary to other travelers and will recommend you and Peru for Less to any others who want to visit this beautiful country.  Thanks again for making our trip so special and for your patience in answering all of our many questions.  We appreciate you and your great communication in making this one of our very favorite trips. </p>\r\n\r\n<p>Fondly, </p>\r\n','Cristina and Wayne <br />\r\nRoanoke, VA  <br />\r\nLima, Cusco, Machu Picchu, the Amazon\r\n','','','',709,0,0,NULL,NULL,NULL),(669,1,'Kristina,','<p>I want to thank you for organizing such a nice tour of Peru for the 6 of us.  Everything went smoothly and we enjoyed each adventure.  We had some wonderful surprises such as \"Cuzco\" days and \'Farmers\" day at Arequipa, as well as winter solstice at Machu Picchu.   The final day at the Casa Andina private collection in Miraflores topped off a perfect holiday.  </p>\r\n\r\n<p>Peru For Less helped us find an itinerary that suited us personally. They were there to pick us up and transfer us to every bus, train, plane and hotel. They were always on time and very friendly. Our guides were great. They spoke English well and were knowledgeable in their areas.  The trip went off perfectly and we have Peru For Less to thank, especially Kristina who was super to work with and responded promptly to all my emails and helped tweak things so they made all six of us satisfied.  Thank you so much.  I will be recommending Peru For Less to everyone I talk to! Thank you again. </p>\r\n','Ruth  and Kristen <br />\r\nMinnesota, USA <br/>\r\nLima, Puerto Maldonado, Cusco, Puno, Arequipa\r\n','','','',708,0,0,NULL,NULL,NULL),(670,1,'Hi Riley,  ','<p>I had a great trip and was able to see everything that I had hoped. It was quite a bit of traveling to Peru and wish i had stayed a night in Lima to give myself some time to rest before moving on to Arequipa.  But I enjoyed my time there and am glad that I was able to see all the wanted attractions in one trip. I didn\'t have to many problems with the altitude thanks to advice by some of guides.  Also everyone was very friendly. Thanks again for getting all the details of the trip worked out for me. Many thanks.</p>\r\n \r\n','Nick <br/>\r\nArequipa, Colca Canyon, Puno, Cusco, Machu Picchu\r\n','','','',707,0,0,NULL,NULL,NULL),(671,1,'Rylee,','<p>There are no words that can adequately describe the incredible time we had and the spectacular sites we saw and experienced, but I will give it a try. First let me say that I have been recommending Peru For Less to everyone with whom we spoke. It was so easy working with you to plan the itinerary and then the guides and drivers were fantastic. We could not have asked for more. It was so enjoyable because they are so knowledgeable and proud of their history as they should be. Maria, Carlos, and Miguel were outstanding and certainly enhanced everything that we had read on our own.  </p>\r\n \r\n<p>Emily was truly well organized and got us situated very nicely in Cuzco with the hotel, tours and general information. Our drivers, such as Felix, were great and always on time. They certainly handle the road expertly. Felix knew of a great shortcut when we were stuck in traffic.  </p>\r\n \r\n<p>Then hotels and their staff were outstanding.  The breakfasts were more than we could have ever hoped.  </p>\r\n \r\n<p>The people are wonderful - helpful, informative, curious, proud.  One local artisan even gave me an herb, not cocoa, to combat the altitude sickness that affected my husband and my son\'s girlfriend.  His wife told us about her grandmother who was a shaman and showed us photographs.  </p>\r\n \r\n<p>Machu Picchu was breathtaking - everything from the journey there to the actual days spent visiting the site. It was breathtaking and lush and overwhelming.  Two days was not enough.</p>\r\n \r\n<p>In Lima, we enjoyed the city tour with Miguel, but we also explored the pyramid/site that was being restored. I don\'t recall the name. We had a great tour and were able to walk on the actual site and observe the work being done.  </p>\r\n \r\n<p>The food was exceptional everywhere we went. In Aguas Calientes we ate at Indoio Feliz - the kids\' favorite meal.  In Barranco, we happended upon a restaurant that is housed in a family home and the local women prepare the meals.  It is called Songoro Cosango, Ayacucho281, Puente De Los Suspiros - excellent. In Cuzco the kids really liked Jack\'s up the street from the cathedral.</p>\r\n \r\n<p>The surfing experience was fun for my son and his girlfriend. We arranged the day ahead of time with Antonio who owns Penascal in San Bartolo. The kids had a lesson, rented the wet suits and towels and were into water for about two hours. The waves make the California waves seem like gentle ripples.  Needless to say the kids were never able to get up but they had fun.  </p>\r\n \r\n<p>Included in the day was what I consider to be the best meal that I had on our vacation.  Everything is prepared in Antonio\'s home. I had a fish called corvina which I think was Chilean Sea Bass that was freshly caught that morning.  The kids had beef - my son the tenderloin and the girls what looked like a minute steak. We had a vegetable quiche as a starter. The meal included appetizers, rice, beans and dessert - banana in a sweet syrup. My husband opted for a museum day so he missed out on a great meal.  </p>\r\n \r\n<p>If any of your clients are interested in surfing I highly recommend Antonio Tello at Penascal Surf. Great experience all around.</p>\r\n  \r\n<p>I truly enjoyed working with you and plan on using your services when we plan another South American sojourn.</p>\r\n','Hans and Liz Maurer<br />\r\nMilford, CT<br />\r\nJune 24-July 2<br />\r\nLima, Cuzco and Machu Picchu\r\n','','','',283,0,0,NULL,NULL,NULL),(672,1,'Kristina,','<p>From the start, I knew I was in good hands with Peru for Less.  They answered ALL my questions in a timely manner and gave me all the information that I needed prior to my trip.  They were excellent in arranging my flights, hotels and tours.  All we did was show up and everything was taken care of.  The hotels were nice and in good locations and the tour guides were very informative and friendly.  We enjoyed our vacation and will definitely recommend Peru for Less to our family and friends.  Thanks again for the wonderful memories.</p>','Terry   <br/>\r\nFlorida<br/>\r\nLima, Cuzco, 2D Inca Trail\r\n\r\n','','','',706,0,0,NULL,NULL,NULL),(673,1,'Dear Kristina,','<p>Daniel and I wanted to take the time to thank you for an extraordinary trip to Peru.  We were thoroughly impressed with all the care your organization took to look after us while in Peru.  We were always met on time by one of your cordial representatives making our travels and transitions from different cities smoothly.  From your drivers to your guides, the level of professionalism is exemplary.  We felt truly special and pampered.</p>\r\n<p>I want to especially sing the praises of Marlene - our guide in Cuzco and Joel - our driver.  Marlene\'s enthusiasm and knowledge of Peru\'s history and her efforts to ensure we enjoyed our visit was phenomenal.  You have a treasure of a guide in her.  Her passion for Peru is contagious.  Also worth noting is Fabricio who was our guide in Machu Picchu and Miguel in Lima. Both were terrific and professional.</p>\r\n<p>Dan and I felt that we left behind some good friends in Peru - and they were your guides and drivers.</p>\r\n<p>The hotels were fantastic.  We loved Inkaterra Pueblo, El Monasterio and Aranwa in Sacred Valley.</p>\r\n<p>We will definitely recommend you to our friends.  You took good care of us.</p>\r\n<p>All the best,</p>\r\n','Roger <br/>\r\nCalifornia, USA<br/>\r\nLuxury Peru Special 1 and Lima\r\n','','','',704,0,0,NULL,NULL,NULL),(674,1,'Hi Jennifer, ','<p>My husband and I had one of the best trips we\'ve ever taken. Thank you for making all the arrangements; everything worked out great and we were well taken care of by all the guides. All in all, this trip to Peru is something that we\'ll remember forever. </p>\r\n<p>I want to commend all the guides who took us around; they were all very enthusiastic with showing us all the sights and we could see that they all take pride in their country. I want to especially mention our guide Paul in Paracas. My husband had a stomachache on the morning of our Ballestas Islands tour and couldn\'t make it to the tour with me. When I was taken back to the hotel afterwards, without me requesting, Paul asked the hotel if we could delay our checkout for a couple of hours so my husband could get a little more rest in our room. He also took us on a side trip to Ica later that afternoon, which was not planned on our itinerary, and visited a couple of wineries and the sand dunes before taking us toy the Ica bus station to catch the bus that we originally should have taken in Paracas.</p>\r\n<p>On our Sacred Valley tour, we mentioned to our guide Ronny that we wanted to try chica. So he ended up taking us to a chicheria on the way to try some homemade chica, which became a little highlight of our trip!  The guides were flexible and accommodating to our needs and requests. </p>\r\n<p>The view at Machu Picchu is one of the most spectacular we have seen. It definitely lives up to its hype! We felt fortunate that we had the chance to visit this mystical and majestic place. I just wished that we had more time to spend there just to hang out or even do a few more hikes around. </p>\r\n<p>There are many wonderful moments and memories that I couldn\'t list all out here. Thank you again for planning this trip for us. We will definitely recommend your company to anyone who\'s visiting Peru.</p>\r\n','Joycelyn and Steve <br>\r\nNew Jersey, USA<br>\r\nLima, Paracas, Nazca Cusco, Machu Picchu\r\n','','','',703,0,0,NULL,NULL,NULL),(675,1,'Hi Kelly,','<p>The trip was so well organized and went well. The experience was \"once in a lifetime,\" it was hard to leave Peru. We were taken care of by people that enjoyed what they were doing. All the connections worked smoothly and the drivers and guides were very helpful. Thank you for your help with the last minute changes. We enjoyed the people we met, the food and the incredible sights.</p>\r\n<p>We will recommend Peru for Less to any of our friends and we hope to visit other places in South America with your help.</p>\r\n','Chris &amp; Svetlana <br />\r\nLima, Cusco, and Machu Picchu\r\n','','','',702,0,0,NULL,NULL,NULL),(676,1,'Hi Rylee!','<p>Thank you so much for setting up an awesome trip for us! We were able to relax totally because everything had been arranged in advance-there was no worrying about where we were supposed to be or how we would get there. The people we interacted with were such a huge part of making us feel comfortable and welcomed: Our drivers and tour guides were friendly, professional, and very knowledgable and entertaining. Caitlin, in Cusco, was especially helpful, and it was reassuring to know she was just a phone call away should we need anything. Even when our plans changed at the last minute, such as when a workers\' strike shut down the roads our last day in Cusco, Caitlin had backup plans and was able to help us stay on schedule.</p>\r\n<p>While we had an amazing experience in Machu Picchu (and that was mainly the purpose of our trip), our rainforest adventure was really the highlight. Our lodge, Refugio Amazonas, in which we stayed at your suggestion, was perfect for us: It was just rustic enough (not too much like camping, which I appreciated) while still being a little bit posh (I got the best massage of my life there!). We were combined with two other groups of travelers in our tour group, and we all really bonded and got to know and like each other in the few days we had together. Our guide, Aldo, was in part responsible for creating a sense of community, and we can\'t say enough good things about him: Friendly, funny, helpful, really informative, entertaining, he was exactly who we needed to interpret our surroundings and make it a fun and memorable experience. I only wish we had had more time to spend in the rainforest - we did not want to leave!\r\nThis trip was one of the best we\'ve ever taken, and PFL helped make it such a positive, easy experience. I\'m already thinking about other destinations in South America I\'d like to explore, and I would feel more than confident booking with you again. I will recommend Peru For Less to anyone I know who expresses interest in traveling to South America. </p>\r\n<p>Thanks again for everything!</p>\r\n','Wesley  and Beth <br />\r\nSan Jose, CA<br />\r\nLima, Puerto Maldonado, Cusco, Machu Picchu, Aguas Calientes\r\n','','','',281,0,0,NULL,NULL,NULL),(677,1,'Hi Rylee!','<p>My trip was A-MA-ZING!!! The cherry on the top was absolutely, positively going to Machu Picchu!  For years I have seen the pictures and FINALLY, I was able to climb up there myself and take my own pictures!!  \r\nI wanted to give you a huge thanks for arranging everything.  You made it super easy to get around while I was down there and I didn\'t have to think about any logistics.  That was nice.  Caitlin was also very hospitable.  You guys exceeded my expectations by giving door-to-door service.  I was not expecting that!  Again, thanks.  </p>\r\n<p>Thanks again for your service!  </p>\r\n','Bethany  <br/>\r\nHuntington Beach, California, USA<br/>\r\nRio de Janeiro, Iguazu Falls, Buenos Aires, Cusco, Machu Picchu\r\n','','','',705,0,0,NULL,NULL,NULL),(678,1,'Rylee,','<p>We (my husband and I, our son and our parents) just returned from a trip to Peru (July 1-12, 2010). Before planning the trip I looked up the company Peru For Less. I worked with a travel advisor named Rylee McGowan. I started our travel plans in May for our trip in July. I picked through and questioned every item on our itinerary and Rylee patiently answered all the questions without once losing her cool. Whenever I was not sure of a hotel choice she guided me with suggestions but never forced me into committing to one over the other. I even questioned her whether she had taken this trip and she mentioned she did the trip with her father who was in his 60â??s which helped since I was taking this trip with my parents who were in their 70â??s. Also, I wanted to pack in a lot of stuff during our limited time and wanted to go to Lake Titicaca as well. But Riley guided me and made me see that this would not be a good idea. She also suggested that we stay overnight in the Machu Picchu area which was very good advice. </p>\r\n\r\n<p>We do not speak Spanish and it was nice to be met at the airport by a representative and taken to the hotel. All of our domestic transportation was included in the price â?? local tours, train & plane tickets. Our tours in Lima and Cusco were private tours and it was just us. The Puerto Maldonado tour had 3 other people. We were in the jungle and we understood the need for the pairing â?? the literature did mention that groups may be paired up to 10 people.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>For me the best part of the trip was that I could choose the dates I wanted to travel and the places I wanted to go. Also, the little details that were taken care of â?? such as someone meeting us at the airport, taking us to the hotel, giving us a tour, buying the tickets to the local sights as well train and plane tickets. A land slide meant that we had to leave from a different station for Machu Picchu. This was taken care of - I probably could have done it on my own if I was doing this trip without a tour company but it was their headache and not mine and I didn\'t have to worry. Also the private tours were a bonus. In Cusco on Day 1, neither of my parents wanted the tour after we arrived and the guide dropped them off at the hotel and the three of us did the tour on our own. Day 2 of our stay in Cusco one of our parents opted out and this was fine. </p>\r\n\r\n<p>We missed our connection in Atlanta and we called the emergency number and they took down our new flight number and everything was taken care of at their end. </p>\r\n\r\n<p>I recommend this company without hesitation.</p>\r\n','Nagulinie <br/>\r\nManlius, New York, USA<br/>\r\nLima, Cusco, Machu Picchu, and Puerto Maldonado    \r\n','','','',280,0,0,NULL,NULL,NULL),(679,1,'Hi, Riley,','<p>My husband and I wanted to take some of our grandchildren to see the country where he was born and raised.  He found Peru for Less on the internet and decided to contact them. We were pleased to be greeted by Rylee, who was so pleasant that she put us at ease right away. After many emails and phone conversations, we had a plan.  </p>\r\n<p>Our trip went very smoothly, everywhere we went our guide was there to meet us.  The hotels were all very comfortable and our tours were excellent.  This has been the experience of a lifetime for us and our grandchildren.  Thank you Peru for Less!</p>\r\n','Rolando and Betty <br />\r\nHendersonville, Tennessee, USA<br />\r\nLima, Arequipa, Colca Canyon, Puno, Cusco, Machu Picchu\r\n','','','',701,0,0,NULL,NULL,NULL),(680,1,'Kelly,','<p>All in all it was a great trip and I\'d have to give the prize to the guide Paul for going the extra mile to make our visit the best in Ica. You see, we lost our camera and he lent one of his to us...we were also low on cash and had forgotten our pin number so he helped us get to a bank that accepted Visa in order for us to get some cash. We were very thankful how smooth the trip went and no hassle on our part. Thanks again. </p>','Rosaleen <br/>\r\nLima, Cusco, Machu Picchu, Ica, Nazca\r\n','','','',279,0,0,NULL,NULL,NULL),(681,1,'Hello Rylee,','<p>Thank you very much for your hard work and support. I had a very good time and found the experience will stay with me of ever. I will recommend your firm to my friends and have fond memories of the people and places I have met and visited.</p>','John <br/>\r\nKeighley, UK <br/>\r\nCusco, Machu Picchu, Puerto Maldonado, Lima \r\n','','','',278,0,0,NULL,NULL,NULL),(682,1,'Hi Jennifer,','<p>My friend and I had a great time in Peru! Machu Picchu was awesome. </p>\r\n<p>I still cannot believe that I was in Machu Picchu! I will never forget \r\nabout this experience! Both hotels were good, especially the staffs \r\nwere very nice to us. We enjoyed all three tours as well. </p>\r\n<p>All three \r\ntour guides were excellent. We had a great time in Cuzco. Thank you very much.</p>\r\n \r\n<p>Sincerely,</p>\r\n','Erika <br/>\r\nCalifornia <br/>\r\nLima, Cusco, Machu Picchu\r\n','','','',277,0,0,NULL,NULL,NULL),(683,1,'Hi Jennifer, ','<p>Sorry it\'s taken so long for me to get back to you.  Our trip was amazing!!!!  Thank you for all you did to work out all the details.  Everything went very smooth and we had a great time!  The agent in Cusco, Caitlin, was the most amazing help!  She took us to the airport to leave Cusco and we had discovered Steve had left his Iphone at the hotel.  She said not to worry, she would get a cab and go get it.  She did.  She arrived back at the airport before we left. Every detail was worked out perfectly.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Sincerely,</p>\r\n','Betty <br/>\r\nFlorida, USA <br/>\r\nLima, Cusco, Machu Picchu, Galapagos\r\n','','','',276,0,0,NULL,NULL,NULL),(684,1,'Rylee,','<p>We had a great time. We will be talking about Peru for a long time. Cuzco was by far the best city. We enjoyed all of our guides, hotels and tours. Peru was an extremely interesting country, thank you so much for making it happen. We planned very last minute, but your suggestions were all perfect. Our person that meet us at the airport in Cuzco did not have a sign with our name on it so we had to wait until most everyone left and we found each other. Other than that the trip was perfect. I will certainly recommend Peru For Less to all of our friends and family. Thanks for all your help. </p>','Terry <br/>\r\nLa Habra, CA <br/>\r\nLima, Ica, Nazca, Arequipa, Colca Canyon, Cusco, Machu Picchu\r\n','','','',275,0,0,NULL,NULL,NULL),(685,1,'Matt,','<p>We just returned home. It was a great trip. All your service providers we very good. Thanks again.</p>','Hasham <br/>\r\nLima, Cusco, Machu Picchu, Paracas, Nazca, Arequipa, Colca Canyon\r\n','','','',274,0,0,NULL,NULL,NULL),(686,1,'Matt,','<p>Just a quick note to let you know that Wayki Trek/Tours was an amazing operator. Our guide, Edwin, was absolutely incredible. I plan to recommend him to everyone. Please pass on our heartfelt thanks for such a great trek. Trekking with him was my favorite part of our trip and I really hope to return to Peru again soon. </p>\r\n<p>Thanks for your work in organizing the tour. I think everyone was really happy with how it all worked out!</p>\r\n','Camille <br/>\r\nTampa, Florida <br/>\r\nLima, Cusco, Salkantay Trek, Machu Picchu, Iquitos (Ceiba Tops)\r\n','','','',273,0,0,NULL,NULL,NULL),(687,1,'Dear Rylee,','<p>Our trip was really good, especially our time in Machu Picchu. I had a great and unforgettable time on the Huayna Picchu trail and the other surrounding trails. I also enjoyed the entire of my time in Nazca, where we did the flight and some quick visits to the aqueduct site and other places. I really enjoyed the route from Puno to Cusco, for which we had several stops for sightseeing. I wish we had more rides like that.</p>\r\n \r\n<p>Thanks for the help, and since I am planning to do more trips to Latin America, I may contact you again in the future.</p>\r\n','Andreas <br/>\r\nNicosia, Cyprus <br/>\r\nLima, Nazca, Arequipa, Puno, Cusco, Machu Picchu\r\n','','','',272,0,0,NULL,NULL,NULL),(688,1,'Rylee, ','<p>Everything was great, Rylee. It was always reassuring to see the P4L rep at every transition point. Trip of a lifetime, really. I appreciate all your help in the planning and all the guides along the way. I will certainly recommend your services. MAHALO!</p>','Dennis <br/>\r\nWaianae, Hawaii <br/>\r\nLima, Arequipa, Puno, Cusco, Puerto Maldonado\r\n','','','',271,0,0,NULL,NULL,NULL),(689,1,'Hi Rylee,','<p>Everything that you arranged was absolutely great. I wanted to let you know we thoroughly enjoyed Peru and Peru For Less were very helpful all the way. You were always there to answer questions and were very helpful in the planning process, it all paid off! The guides and tours were great, and we loved our Cuzco hotel. We could not have been happier with every part of the trip. Thank you so much!</p>','Kathy <br/>\r\nSan Jose, CA <br/>\r\nLima, Cusco, Machu Picchu\r\n','','','',270,0,0,NULL,NULL,NULL),(690,1,'Riva,','<p>We had a fabulous time in Argentina. Gustavo our city tour guide was wonderful. The tango/dinner show was unforgettable. We were amazed on how passionate the people are about football (World cup). We were there during the Argentina game. We also stayed in a trendy area (Arenales) close to Santa Fe and enjoyed the window shopping. We were also lucky to get tickets to Teatro Colon and watched a ballet show. It was great.</p>',' Maria <br/>\r\nFlorida, USA <br/>\r\nBuenos Aires\r\n','','','',269,0,0,NULL,NULL,NULL),(691,1,'Dear Jennifer,','<p>I thought the itinerary you arranged was excellent.  No doubt it would not have been possible for us to take care of all those details. The San Blas Botique was immaculately clean and in a great location. And boy did we appreciate being able to leave our luggage in the room when we went to Machu Picchu! </p>','Annie <br/>\r\nColorado, USA <br/>\r\nCusco and Machu Picchu\r\n','','','',268,0,0,NULL,NULL,NULL),(692,1,'Hello Kelly,','<p>This was my second trip arranged by Latin America for Less, and I will certainly plan to use your services again. Sharon and I had a wonderful experience. Your planning and guidance before the trip were excellent. Since we had signed up for one of your advertised escorted tours that never filled, we thought you might cancelâ??or for a reduced price, change it to one of your more typical arranged but not escorted trips. We were quite surprised and pleased to have such a personalized visit. </p>\r\n<p>Caitlin, the office manager in Cuzco, was particularly attentive and helpful. Her competence was truly amazing and we really enjoyed her company. The hotels were superb, the restaurants where our meals were arranged were delightful and the food was delicious. It goes without saying that Cuzco and Machu Picchu are as spectacular as we anticipated, and the local guides and excellent drivers provided us with good tours. In Lima, we found the Largo Collection of Incan Art to be a highlight, and Miguelâ??s knowledge of history made him an excellent guide for that venue. Another highlight in Lima was the visit to Los Ficus Hacienda where we were delighted by the Peruvian Paso Horse Show and an excellent lunch on the veranda from their beautiful organic garden. </p>\r\n<p>We thank you and all the Latin America for Less staff for a positively memorable trip.</p>\r\n','Barbara <br/>\r\nEscorted Peru Tour: Lima, Cusco, and Machu Picchu \r\n','','','',267,0,0,NULL,NULL,NULL),(693,1,'Hi, Kelly','<p>Both Viv and I had a great time on the trip (her first to South America). The hotel in Cuzco was nice. All of the transfers and tours went off without any problems. I\'ll make sure to mention Peru For Less to anyone else I know who plans to go there.</p>\r\n<p>Regards,</p>\r\n','Brian <br/>\r\nCusco and Machu Picchu\r\n','','','',266,0,0,NULL,NULL,NULL),(694,1,'Hi Rylee,','<p>We had a great time.   Peru For Less is the best.   It was very comforting having someone meet us at each of the stops to get us where we needed to go.  We loved the guides.   Their tours were informative and funny.  It couldn\'t have gone better.   The only thing that would have been helpful is perhaps a little more guidance on tips. You\'ve definitely earned more business!</p>','Gary <br/>\r\nHuntsville, Utah, USA <br/>\r\nLima, Nazca, Cusco, Puno\r\n\r\n','','','',265,0,0,NULL,NULL,NULL),(695,1,'Hi Matt,','<p>We had a great time- thanks! Our trip to Machu Picchu was great. The guides were fantastic-  very personable and knowledgeable. Overall, a stellar trip.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Thanks!</p>\r\n','Dave <br/>\r\nLima, Cusco, and Machu Picchu\r\n','','','',264,0,0,NULL,NULL,NULL),(696,1,'Jennifer, ','<p>First I want to thank you for the trip arrangements you made for us over the last few months. The accommodations were very good, as were the flights, the transfers, and the guides. We enjoyed the whole trip. If one has to select, the highlights of the visit were obviously Machu Picchu and the Sacred Valley. Also the Tambopata Research Center. The buffet dinner and show at the Tunupa Restaurant was very enjoyable. Our favorite hotel was Colca Lodge. If we were planning the trip again we would have scheduled two nights there. Based on our experiences we would have no reservations in recommending PFL as the travel agent, and Peru as a beautiful and diversified country to visit.</p>\r\n<p>Best regards,</p>\r\n','Norman <br/>\r\nLima, Cusco, Machu Picchu, Arequipa, Colca Canyon, Puerto Maldonado\r\n','','','',263,0,0,NULL,NULL,NULL),(697,1,'Hi Rylee, ','<p>We were very impressed with all of our coordinators, guides and drivers; the trip went very smoothly, and everyone was so knowledgeable and friendly. Thank you for setting it all up!</p>\r\n<p>The trip was great. The Galapagos expedition was fabulous, as were Cusco and Machu Picchu. Thanks again for all of your help!</p>\r\n','Debbie <br/>\r\nCanton, Georgia, USA <br/>\r\nLima, Cusco, Quito, Galapagos Islands\r\n','','','',262,0,0,NULL,NULL,NULL),(698,1,'Hi Rylee, ','<p>Machu Picchu was a great experience. I will go to your site and thank you for everything, it has been a pleasure working with you and your company as well. I would highly recommend it to anyone who wants to use your services and will be in touch in my future travels to South America.</p>','Shubha <br/>\r\nManvel, Texas, USA\r\n','','','',261,0,0,NULL,NULL,NULL),(699,1,'Hi Jennifer,','<p>Jennifer, we loved our trip to Peru. In the jungle, we had an awesome guide Juan. We highly recommend him. The other guides and drivers were also good. Everyone we dealt with was very helpful and worked around the snafus that come up with travel and tours. </p>\r\n\r\n<p>Thanks again for your help and emails. </p>\r\n','Jamie <br/>\r\nLima, Cusco, Machu Picchu, Manu\r\n','','','',260,0,0,NULL,NULL,NULL),(700,1,'Hi Kelly, ','<p>The trip was wonderful.  Machu Picchu was amazing, but it was only the tip of the iceberg.  Peru has so much to see.  I was amazed by the other Inca temples we visited and I found the Peruvians to be soft-spoken and well-mannered.  Thanks for all your help in planning our tour.  I will definitely recommend Peru For less to my friends and family.  </p>','John <br />\r\nLima, Cuzco &amp; Machu Picchu\r\n','','','',394,0,0,NULL,NULL,NULL),(701,1,'Dera Rylee,','<p>The trip was great! Thanks for your follow-up and the hotel picks. They were just what we were looking for. Having someone there to help us get around was so important, and we really appreciated that someone from Peru for Less was always there. The folks were super friendly.\r\nI\'m glad we booked through you.  </p>\r\n\r\n<p>The staff in Lima and Cuzco were all very helpful, and always went above and beyond to accommodate and help us out with any questions/recommendations. This definitely lent to the charm of Peru!  I\'ve already recommended your company to a few friends.</p>\r\n','Sharon and Mae <br />\r\nEdison, NJ<br />\r\nLima, Cuzco and Machu Picchu\r\n','','','',391,0,0,NULL,NULL,NULL),(702,1,'Dear Elizabeth,','<p>Thank you and Caitlyn for all the organization you provided for our trip. Also Caitlyn was incredible how she quickly knew what to do as we arrived with Sofia\'s health in a terrible condition. Without hesitation she took us to the emergency clinic where they provide excellent attention to my daughter\'s health needs. Caitlyn consistently checked to see how we were doing. </p>\r\n\r\n<p>The organization and quality service to Machu Picchu was excellent. </p>\r\n\r\n<p>My daughter and Caitlyn are still communicating in Cuzco. She even helped her find a better living situation. Sofia ended up selecting somewhere else to live, but Caitlyn was so supportive. </p>\r\n\r\n<p>Thank you, Elizabeth. I hope our paths cross again. </p>\r\n','Josie <br />\r\nSan Francisco, CA<br />\r\nMachu Picchu\r\n','','','',388,0,0,NULL,NULL,NULL),(703,1,'Dear Kelly,','<p>We had a lovely trip, and all the hotels and transfers were perfect. We were very impressed with the guide, Silvia, from Klein Tours in Quito. She was very professional and helpful. </p>\r\n \r\n<p>You couldnÂ´t have done any better for us, all was perfect. Also thanks for organizing the Mitad del Mundo - the Equator line in Quito.Wwe really enjoyed it and wouldnÂ´t have liked to have missed it.</p>\r\n \r\n<p>I also loved my Peru For Less T-Shirt and proudly wear it a lot, I was lucky that the size was perfect!</p>\r\n \r\n<p>Thanks for everything.</p>\r\n','Karen <br />\r\nLima, La Paz, Cuzco &AMP; Machu Picchu + Quito, Galapagos\r\n','','','',385,0,0,NULL,NULL,NULL),(704,1,'Hello Rylee,','<p>We were very happy with the services provided by Peru For Less, the hotels selected and the knowledge of the guides.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Special thanks to Susana, the person that met us on our arrival and departure. She was very helpful explaining us the trip and extremely nice. Also to Rylee, who was wonderful in the planning process and so helpful in answering our questions. Your restaurant recommendations were also wonderful. </p>\r\n \r\n<p>We would certainly recommend Peru For Less to other people.</p>\r\n','David <br />\r\nMadrid, Spain<br />\r\nCuzco and Machu Picchu\r\n','','','',382,0,0,NULL,NULL,NULL),(705,1,'Hi Rylee,','<p>We really enjoyed our trip.  All of your staff along the way was very friendly and helpful, and we loved our hotels.  We really enjoyed our tour guide through the Sacred Valley.  I will certainly recommend your services to my friends and family. Thanks again for all of your assistance, it was lovely working with you.</p>','Alfred<br />\r\nAustin, Texas<br />\r\nCuzco, Machu Picchu, and Iquitos\r\n','','','',379,0,0,NULL,NULL,NULL),(706,1,'Rylee,','<p>We just got home from our wonderful trip to Peru.  Very different from anywhere we have ever been.  It was so good to see my daughter who has been there for a year with the Peace Corps.  The Peru for Less services were wonderful.  We really enjoyed Jimmy, Mary and Suzanna.  Everyone was prompt in the pick-ups and held their signs high.  They were very knowledgeable and a pleasure to be with during the tours.  Thanks for everything, you were very helpful and I will certainly recommend your services</p>','Christine  <br />\r\nStony Brook, NY<br />\r\nCuzco &amp; Machu Picchu\r\n','','','',376,0,0,NULL,NULL,NULL),(707,1,'Hi Kristina,','<p>We had a blast! Wayki Trek makes the BEST food and their porters are sweet people. They helped my girlfriend with her pack on several occasions when she was sick and even brought food out to us while we were all exhausted on day two. Jose Condor was a GREAT guide.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>The tours themselves were all great and we all learned a ton about Incan and Peruvian culture. Everyone was on time and where they needed to be. </p>\r\n\r\n<p>We were in great hands with Peru For Less. In eight days we had an amazing adventure through the Andes - and deep inside ancient Incan culture - while enjoying fantastic food the entire way.\"</p>\r\n','Rob <br />\r\nMassachusetts<br />\r\nCuzco &amp; Inca Trail\r\n','','','',374,0,0,NULL,NULL,NULL),(708,1,'Hi Rylee, ','<p>All went well - hotels, buses and tours were very good and on time. Thanks for arranging everything. You were fabulous in the planning process and I appreciate you arranging this for me.. Thanks again for all of your assistance. </p>','John <br />\r\nParish<br />\r\nAkron, OH<br />\r\nCuzco and Machu Picchu\r\n','','','',371,0,0,NULL,NULL,NULL),(709,1,'Dear Riva,','<p>Everything was fantastic! We will definitely write about our experience on TripAdvisor.com.  </p>','Chad <br />\r\nBaltimore, NC<br />\r\nLima, Puerto Maldonado, Cuzco, Machu Picchu, Arequipa\r\n','','','',369,0,0,NULL,NULL,NULL),(710,1,'Dear Kristina,','<p>We had a brilliant holiday in Peru. I just wish that we could have stayed a little longer!</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Susanna gave us a brilliant introduction to Cusco and Machu Picchu. She also gave us some suggestions for Miraflores and Barranco in Lima. </p>\r\n\r\n<p>I didn\'t remember the name of the bloke that met us in Lima and conducted the tour of the centre of Lima. He was brilliant and we had a really good personal tour of the main square and a monastery.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>The trip was really well organised and we were very well looked after.</p>\r\n','James <br />\r\nUK<br />\r\nLima, Cuzco\r\n','','','',367,0,0,NULL,NULL,NULL),(711,1,'Dear Staci,','<p>We had a wonderful time at the Inotawa Lodge,Carlos was a very good guide.  We managed to see quite a bit of wildlife, and it was great that they were able to provide vegetarian food for me  The bungalows were very spacious and it was lovely laying in bed listening to the sounds of the rainforest. On the whole, an unforgettable experience. Many thanks for your help in arranging the trip.</p>','Kathy <br />\r\nSan Francisco<br />\r\nPuerto Maldonado            \r\n','','','',365,0,0,NULL,NULL,NULL),(712,1,'Hi Kelly,','<p>The trip was absolutely fantastic. Thank you very much.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Suzanna was great and very helpful. She met us, took care of all the logistics, gave us the rundown. It is very nice to get off the plane, after 15 hours, in a foreign land, and have someone meet you, speak your language, and take care of all the \"settling in\". </p>\r\n\r\n<p>The Sacred Valley tour was interesting, and the guide (Guillermo) was good. He did a good job of showing us the sites and differentiating between known facts and various theories. On the way back we visited a small village with a beautiful church - that was quite a treat!</p>\r\n\r\n<p>The trek was very good. The head guide (Edwin) was great. Friendly, knowledgeable, good English, fun to be with. We really enjoyed his company, and the trek had gorgeous views. The cooks (Solio and Aurelio - I think Solio was the main cook) were absolutely unbelievable. The food was fantastic and beyond anything one can reasonably expect in the back-country. Really, really impressive!</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Machu-Pichu itself was obviously great. Very beautiful. Very imposing. Completely defying description.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Overall, fantastic organization. Everything worked out as expected. Great vacation - thank you!</p>\r\n','Alik  <br />\r\nPuno, Cuzco, Machu Picchu, Salcantay Trek\r\n','','','',363,0,0,NULL,NULL,NULL),(713,1,'Hi Danielle,','<p>I wanted to visit Macchu Picchu Peru for a long time since I retired, and Peru For Less made that happen very easily, economically, efficiently and nicely. The planning, scheduling and booking are all done very professionally from the start.</p>\r\n \r\n<p>The stay-over in Lima was short but necessary to get over the jetlag, and Lima is good city to spend a couple of days. There\'s lot of shopping at reasonable prices. The trip to Cusco was very smooth, and the accommodation exceeded my expectations. I will definitely visit Cusco and stay there again for longer time. There is a lot to see and do in Cusco and the food is very cheap and delicious.</p>\r\n \r\n<p>Machu Picchu is amazing and trip of a life time. I highly recommended staying in Aguas Calientes for an extra night;`the ruins need a couple of days to explore. The visit to Machu Picchu is too short but worth every minute of your time. So I would recommend adding an extra day to the trip, especially if you are a photographer.</p>\r\n \r\n<p>Danielle took care of everything for us and there were no surprises. Thank you once again and I can\'t wait to do another South America Trip and let you plan for us again!</p>\r\n','Shirley  and Mark <br />\r\nOntario, Canada<br />\r\nLima, Machu Picchu, Cusco<br />\r\n','','','',713,0,0,NULL,NULL,NULL),(714,1,'Hi Riva,','<p>The trip was fantastic! Machu Picchu was absolutely amazing. </p>\r\n\r\n<p>We found the arrangements and contacts at PFL were very well-organized. Each of our transfers were smooth and on-time. Our guide at Machu Picchu (Fabrisio) was excellent- very knowledgeable and personable. We stayed at the Inti Inn in Aguas Calientes and the accommodations were very comfortable.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Though I did not get to meet her, my brother found Caitlin to be very helpful. She had great tips on what to see and do in the Cuzco area. It was also really great to have someone \"see us off\" - I\'m sorry I didn\'t get the woman\'s name who escorted us to the airport.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>I especially appreciated PFL\'s flexibility and willingness to work with my independent travel arrangements for my medical mission. The clinical aspect of the trip allowed me to meet local people and provide care to a very impoverished population while the part of my trip organized by PFL allowed me to appreciate the cultural and archeological attractions of the country.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Thanks so much for your assistance in making our trip to Peru a very memorable one.</p>\r\n','Kate <br />\r\nBaltimore, MD<br />\r\nMachu Picchu/Cuzco\r\n','','','',714,0,0,NULL,NULL,NULL),(715,1,'Rylee;','<p>We had a fabulous time!  We highly recommend your company (and YOU!) and are already thinking about a trip to Argentina for our next adventure!  </p>\r\n  \r\n<p>We had lunch the first day at Cebecheria La Mar-terrific! Our hotel in Cuzco was darling with GREAT  location. Had dinner at Chi Cha, owned by Astrid y Gaston. The hotel in Aguas Calientes was great!  A gourmet dinner was included as well as a welcome drink...what a nice surprise! Our tour in Machu Picchu was great!A great recommendation while in Lima is to have dinner at Huaca Pullcana-we sat outside right next to the ruins and then had a tour.  It was amazing.  That was the first night.  Then on the last day we didn\'t have time for a museum, but we visited two sites:  Huallamarca and Huaca Julliana-the first one has a small museum. The second one has indigenous plants and animals and is huge...and free. It was great being next to Kennedy Park and the artisan markets.  We had Pisco Sours at a great hole in the wall spot, Pepe\'s, next to the hotel.  </p>\r\n \r\n<p>You were wonderful to work with and we LOVED Peru! I will be sending many family and friends to you!</p>\r\n','Ellen <br />\r\nSouthern Pines, NC,<br />\r\nLima, Cuzco and Machu Picchu\r\n','','','',715,0,0,NULL,NULL,NULL),(716,1,'Hi Kristina, ','<p>Everything on the trip functioned like a clockwork. The hotels and tours were great. Thank you for your suggestions; they were all \'on target\'. We very much enjoyed the Inka Trail and Machu Picchu was a Wonder. The trip lived up to every expectation, which is always high praise as we all set unrealistic expectations. Thanks again to you and everyone at Peru For Less for everything.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Now that we\'re home and have had a few days to reflect I wanted to share with you, and hopefully you\'ll share with everyone who had a hand in making our trip as wonderful as it was, the heartfelt \"thank you\'s\" we wish to share. It\'s rare that a trip doesn\'t suffer some unforeseen blip or some change of plan. In our case, on this trip, with Peru-for-Less and Wayki Trek\'s help, this trip not only was perfect in execution but met ALL of our expectations.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>To start, we were fortunate to have worked with Kristina Rudge in the planning of this little family adventure. We are a family of 6 with 4 daughters (the youngest 9) and this was the biggest trip, by far, we\'d ever  taken. Kristina helped us flesh out the details of the trip. Her personal experience with Peru was invaluable in helping us plan and her patience (diplomatically guiding us from the unreasonable to the reasonable) was appreciated. In the end we relied on a number of her suggestions and are thankful for it.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>The essence of our trip was the Inka Trail (4 day trek) and Machu Picchu. We added day trips in Cuzco and a tour of the Sacred Valley for 2 days while we acclimated to the elevation.  Susanna met us in Cuzco and walked us through our itinerary. Since she lives in Cuzco she proved to be a wealth of information for us (restaurants, do\'s/don\'t\'s, etc.) and the girls loved her.  Rony was our guide for both our day trip in Cuzco and the tour of the Sacred Valley. A bright, knowledgeable guy whose English was excellent, he took a shine to our 9 year old. In 2 days the girls received a history lesson that outstripped anything they could have received in a classroom (us, too).</p>\r\n\r\n<p>And then it was time for our trek. We met our guide, Fredy, the evening before and were on our way early the next morning. There\'s no way we can sum up in a short note all of our great experiences in those 4 days. Fredy was wonderful. If you\'re fortunate to have him as your guide you are in great hands. A wealth of historical, cultural, botanical, and geologic knowledge is contained in a personable and patient personality (remember he had 4 girls to help shepherd). The food was great. Our cook, Elias, was able to do things on a trail stove that many restaurants are not able to do. And as for Wayki Trek and our porters, all I can say is thank you. I commend Peru-for-Less for partnering with a local trekking organization that is entirely indigenous owned. I think the pride they take in making their company successful matters in the service they provide. </p>\r\n\r\n<p>The climax of our trip, Machu Picchu, is truly a Wonder of the World and in the planning we arranged for a 2nd day (after arriving from the trek) there. We highly recommend that. The day you arrive after being on the trail for 4 days is magical as the Sun has not yet arisen on your first view of Machu Picchu coming through the Sun Gate. But you are tired and after several hours there, a break is needed. For us, going down to Aguas Calientes for R &amp; R allowed us to recharge and return to Machu Picchu on day 2 with fresh eyes. While we didn\'t experience the hot springs in Aguas Calientes, we did have some great food.</p>\r\n\r\n\r\n<p>As for the rest, well, our biggest concern with 4 daughters with us, was the transitions and transfers. These were managed perfectly. Thank you.  We would (and will) recommend Peru-for-Less to everyone. </p>\r\n','Matt <br />\r\nVermont<br />\r\nLima, Cuzco, Inca Trail<br />\r\n','','','',718,0,0,NULL,NULL,NULL),(717,1,'Dear Kristina,','<p>We had a wonderful time in Peru.  Every aspect of the trip was above our expectations.  Not to mention the breathtaking scenery and the amazing accomplishments of the Incas. We are grateful to you and your company for a well organized trip.  Thank you to you and your team for making it a most memorable trip.  We had 3 guided tours and the guides were knowledgeable and had excellent command of the English language.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>I was particularly impressed by your planning of our trip, giving us a few days at each place. This allowed us to get acclimated and have a little time to look around. We also got some pointers from the guides early on the trip about how to minimize the altitude impact.  </p>\r\n\r\n<p>Our hike from km 104 to Macchu Picchu took place on my wife\'s 69th birthday.  We were a little apprehensive whether we would be able to hike from 6000 feet up to 9000 or so in a few hours.  Especially when we saw that at the start there were no other hikers who were more than half our age. I admit it was a tough hike but we did it. Our guide Freddy turned out to be a good photographer as well as an excellent guide.  All the persons associated with your company were polite, helpful, and caring.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>So thank you again for organizing an unforgettable trip.  We are happy to recommend your company to our friends who expressed interest in going to Peru.</p>\r\n','Stephen  <br />\r\nCalifornia<br />\r\nLima, Cuzco, 2D Inca Trail\r\n','','','',719,0,0,NULL,NULL,NULL),(718,1,'Hello Riva:','<p>We had a great time. Brazil is beautiful.  We enjoyed our time in Rio de Janeiro as we visited Corcovado and Sugar Loaf.  That was just breathtaking to see. Bahia was also nice with the various native costumes, colorful buildings, and interesting history of the various churches.  What can I say about Iguazu? The falls was just spectacular.  It was great seeing it from both the Brazilian side and the Argentina side. Devils Throat, on the Argentina side, was one of the most amazing sights I have ever seen.  Our hotels were good, all the tour guides were wonderful people, and all our connecting flights in Brazil were right on time. We had no problems.  </p>\r\n \r\n<p>We Thank You Riva and Brazil For Less for all the arrangements you made.  Everything you promised was fulfilled.  We look forward to our next trip to South America. Thanks a million! </p>\r\n','Neville &amp; Beverly <br />\r\nRoosevelt, New York<br />\r\n Rio, Salvador, Iguazu\r\n','','','',717,0,0,NULL,NULL,NULL),(719,1,'Dear Peru For Less, ','<p>We had a fabulous trip to Ecuador and Peru.  The Galapagos Islands and Machu Picchu were definitely the highlights.  Amazing!!!  Thanks for coordinating the trip.  We were met every time when we were supposed to and all of our tours went according to plan.  Even when we missed our connection due to airport closure, your office stepped up to the plate and rearranged our activities for the next day.  </p>\r\n<p>Thanks for a wonderful trip.</p>\r\n','Joan <br />\r\nReston, VA<br />\r\nQuito, Galapagos, Cusco, Machu Picchu and Lake Titicaca<br/>\r\n','','','',720,0,0,NULL,NULL,NULL),(720,1,'Dear Peru For Less, ','<p>Trip was a wondrous experience....vistas, histories, affable Peruvians....And, thanks to Peru For Less the trip became every bit as magical and unforgettable as promised.  </p>\r\n\r\n<p>Peru For Less planned a 5-day tour of Peru with stops in Lima, Cusco and climaxing in Machu Picchu.  On each leg of journey we were met by Peru For Less chauffeurs, escorts, and guides who were punctual, professional, knowledgeable and affable.  One certainly develops a sense of confidence in Peru For Less personnel that was waiting in the airport at 2 am- hours later than when we were expected.  I might also add that it is very reassuring to have emergency contact numbers of local Peru For Less personnel. This became specially meaningful when one of us got the dreaded mountain sickness. Thank you for keeping the tour group size small as the largest group was 8. </p>\r\n<p>We have already recommended Peru For Less to disgruntled tourists who were let down by their tour guides as well as friends and acquaintances in Florida who have never even thought of traveling to Peru.</p>\r\n','Monica <br />\r\nCusco and Machu Picchu <br />\r\n','','','',716,0,0,NULL,NULL,NULL),(721,1,'Dear Peru For Less, ','<p>My personal experience with Peru For Less was incredible.  I was traveling alone and the company provided excellent accommodations for me the entire trip.  My adventure was absolutely enhanced because of the staff that I came into contact with.  I greatly appreciated their service and I am undoubtedly going to use Peru For Less again.   </p>','Gonzalez, Jaysen <br />\r\nFlorida<br/>\r\nCusco, Machu Picchu, Inca Trail<br />\r\n','','','',721,0,0,NULL,NULL,NULL),(722,1,'Hi Matt,','<p>All was well organized. The Cusco and Valley tour were great with knowledgeable guides who were proud of their heritage. Dad and I enjoyed the hike into Machu Picchu. The rainy season came early and a poncho is not enough to fend off the driving rain. We stayed wet most of the hike. The trail dining experience was fabulous and welcome after the grueling day.</p>\r\n<p>I will look forward to another of your adventures in the future.</p>\r\n','Emmett and Ray <br />\r\nHouston Texas<br />\r\nLima, Cusco, Machu Picchu,  Inca Trail<br />\r\n','','','',723,0,0,NULL,NULL,NULL),(723,1,'Hi Kelly, ','<p>Our trek of the Inka Trail to Machu Picchu was the best. Your careful and comprehensive planning made the entire experience go smoothly and greatly exceeded our expectations. The transfers were easy and right on time. The tours from Cusco were great and gave us an insight into all that awaited us in Machu Picchu. </p>\r\n\r\n<p>Wayki Trek was an excellent company to use for the trek.  The porters were terrific. Each day we enjoyed sumptuous meals and comfortable camping provided with care and consideration.  Our guide was courteous, knowledgeable and lots of fun. He kept us on a comfortable pace with plenty of stops along the way for resting or explanation of the ruin sites. We had a long tour of Machu Picchu which was unhurried and exciting. Jose took obvious pride in bringing the varied sites to life for us with his considerable knowledge of both history and myth.  </p>\r\n\r\n<p>Our sincere thanks to you, Peru For Less, and Wayki Trek for providing such a wonderful adventure. We will recommend Peru For Less to our friends and hope to return for another trek in the future.  \r\nAll our best wishes</p>\r\n','Kris, Judi and Fred <br />\r\nCusco<br />\r\n','','','',726,0,0,NULL,NULL,NULL),(724,1,'Hi Rylee,','<p>We had a fantastic time, everything ran smoothly and we are now new salespeople for Peru, Peru For Less and you. Everything went smooth and I canâ??t thank you enough for all of your assistance, tips and patience with me. </p>\r\n\r\n<p>Thank you for all your support we had a great time.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Best wishes</p>\r\n','Andy <br/>\r\nGodalming, Surrey, UK<br/>\r\nPuerto Maldonado, Cusco, 2 Day Inca Trail, Lake Titicaca, Arequipa and Colca Canyon<br/>\r\n','','','',373,0,0,NULL,NULL,NULL),(725,1,'Hi Riva,','<p>Our trip was just wonderful. Our tours were fun, all the drivers and guides were on time and friendly, and the hotels were very nice. We especially liked the hotel in Cusco. To top it all off the weather was just great the whole time! Hiking the Inka Trail was a fantastic experience, and the guide there was good too. It was an adventure of a lifetime. </p>\r\n\r\n<p>We would definitely recommend Peru For Less to our friends, and who knows, maybe someday we will be in touch again for another adventure.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Thanks,</p>\r\n','Carol & Lee <br />\r\nColorado, USA<br />\r\nMachu Picchu and Cusco<br />\r\n','','','',404,0,0,NULL,NULL,NULL),(726,1,'Dear Rylee, ','<p>From beginning to end, Peru For Less was an easy and great travel agency to work with. The trip was great and everyone we met through Peru For Less was great to work with, prompt and friendly. The hotel selections available were fabulous and lived up to their expectations.  The personal touches like a list of restaurants recommended in various cities were also very nice.  Thanks to you guys, it was incredibly easy to get around Peru even though I speak zero actual Spanish. </p>\r\n \r\n<p>Thanks again!</p>\r\n','Mitka <br />\r\nAlexandria, VA<br />\r\nLima, Paracas, Nazca, Arequipa, Cusco and Machu Picchu<br />\r\n','','','',378,0,0,NULL,NULL,NULL),(727,1,'Dear Peru For Less, ','<p>My wife and I began planning our honeymoon to Peru in early 2010.  We were looking to customize a trip for our own interests with flexibility, but we also wanted to minimize the headaches of trying to get around completely on our own in South America over great distances.  </p>\n\n<p>We considered a few in-country agencies to start, but we decided to go with Peru For Less given their good reviews and frankly their being based in the US for peace of mind. We emailed Riva Bacquet, their representative based in Lima, dozens of times to customize a trip to Lima, Puerto Maldonado, Cusco, Urubamba Valley, Machu Picchu, Puno, Colca Canyon, and Arequipa.  Riva is superb.  She patiently responded with itinerary options for various scenarios that we considered... All the while offering what turned out to be exceptionally good advice on our trip.  All communication was prompt, friendly, and professional via email and phone.  </p>\n\n<p>But the real test was being there. We went with mid-range 3-star accommodations for what we think was an unbeatable price. All accommodations exceeded our expectations for the costs.  All were centrally located, clean and safe.  All connections were flawless for the most part and pick-up drivers were prompt and courteous.  The bottom line: we minimized the hassle of figuring out connections and accommodations, and maximized our time in each location.  In most cases, excursions were pre-planned though we\'d custom built in time to explore on our own with Riva\'s help.  </p>\n\n<p>The guides that Peru For Less arranged were all superior. In some cases, we had private tours (at no extra cost as far as we could tell) that were fantastic.  I honestly can\'t imagine covering as much ground in such a short time (yet it truly being quality time) without these folks and their expertly planned excursions, particularly in Peru where the distances to hot spots are relatively great.  Renting a car or busing on your own didn\'t seem like an option as in other parts of the world unless you had weeks upon weeks to get around Peru.  </p>\n\n<p>I ended up taking 6,200 photos in two weeks...we absolutely had the time of our lives marveling at the wonders of Peru.  And they are completely accessible in Peru via phone.  On one connection, we decided to make a time change and called the 24-hour number, and they said no problem and hooked us up.  Just one hiccup, we got to Arequipa and for some reason our reservation at the hotel was canceled.  Turns out they\'d upgraded us to a fancier hotel.  Some hiccup, eh?  I highly recommend Peru For Less and Riva Bacquet in particular.  </p>\n\n<p>The Peru For Less representative that met us in Cusco, Caitlyn, was world class.  We didn\'t have any trouble ourselves with losing luggage, but it\'s inevitable.  When we arrived in Cusco, Caitlyn met us at the airport.  We needed to wait a few minutes for her to retrieve another client\'s luggage and it was comforting to us to know that Peru For Less had folks on the ground chasing down such things for travelers.  She came with us to the hotel and gathered us around the lobby table to assure we had all tickets, transfer documents, itineraries, etc. for our adventures.  </p>\n\n<p>One last staff comment. We didn\'t realize that Miguel was an employee.  He gave a fantastic tour of Lima that was one of our favorites.  Well, it took us a few weeks since our return from Peru to write up a good review for these well-deserving folks, but they truly bent over backwards to assure we had a great honeymoon.  The next time we travel to Latin American, you can bet we\'ll use them.  </p>\n\n<p>Hands down A+ travel service. Well done, Peru For Less. Thank you, Riva!</p>\n','Lloyd<br />\r\nBaltimore, NC<br />\r\nLima, Puerto Maldonado, Cusco, Mapi, Arequipa<br />\r\n','','','',381,0,0,NULL,NULL,NULL),(728,1,'Hi Matt,','<p>We are home and had a great trip.  The Peru For Less-style of travel support suited us to a \"t\" and we\'d happily recommend you to our friends.  </p>\r\n<p>Again, thanks for the great support.</p>\r\n<p>Regards,</p>\r\n','Dave <br />\r\nShoreline, Washington<br />\r\nLima, Huaraz, Cusco, Machu Picchu, Puno<br />\r\n','','','',384,0,0,NULL,NULL,NULL),(729,1,'Hi Danielle,','<p>Our trip was great. Peru For Less and especially Nick were awesome. We had some minor setbacks like lost luggage into Cusco and getting sick on hike, but Nick was wonderful and rescheduled all our tours, hotels, and transportations. I was very impressed that Peru For Less made themselves available for any needs that were required. I will definitely book with you guys again and recommend you to family and friends. I\'m planning to go to Egypt next spring, and too bad you guys don\'t have tours there. I would have loved to go through you again. </p>\r\n<p>Once again, thank you for everything.</p>\r\n','Chi <br />\r\nSan Diego, CA<br />\r\nCusco, Machu Picchu, Inca Trail<br />\r\n','','','',387,0,0,NULL,NULL,NULL),(730,1,'Estimada Kristina,','<p>El transporte que reservamos por \"Peru For Less\" estaba muy bien, todo al tiempo previsto y con ayuda en la frontera, estamos muy contentos de su servicio.</p>\r\n<p>Muchos saludos desde Belgica</p>\r\n<p>Anita</p>\r\n','Anita <br>\r\nBelgium<br>\r\nCopacabana, Puno and Cusco<br>\r\n','','','',390,0,0,NULL,NULL,NULL),(731,1,'Hi Kaitlin,','<p>It was great! Great rafting, great guide, and great setting.\r\nThanks a lot</p>\r\n','Tommaso <br>\r\nMogliano Veneto, Italy<br>\r\nSacred Valley River Rafting<br>\r\n','','','',393,0,0,NULL,NULL,NULL),(732,1,'Hi Jennifer,','<p>The trip was fantastic. Everything went off without a hitch. All of our drivers and guides met us on time and helped us with all of our transfers. </p>\r\n \r\n<p>I\'m very happy that we went with Peru For Less. Having that extra assurance that everything was taken care of was worth the extra money spent.</p>\r\n \r\n<p>Overall the experience was really nice and worry-free!</p>\r\n<p>Thank you</p>\r\n','Andrea and Julie <br>\r\nCusco, Lima, Galapagos<br>\r\n','','','',397,0,0,NULL,NULL,NULL),(733,1,'Hey Jennifer!','<p>I just wanted to thank you for all of your help in accommodating us during the strike last week and providing great services. Sonia, our Machu Picchu tour guide was great as well as the drivers who picked us up from our Cusco hostel and from the Cusco airport after our stay in Aguas Calientes. </p>\r\n\r\n<p>The Andina Luxury was a beautiful hotel so thanks for arranging that for us as well. Overall, we lucked out booking our Machu Picchu experience with your company! I think my parents are planning a Machu Picchu trip next summer so I will be sure to contact you to help plan their trip as well, as my friends and I were very pleased working with you and Caitlin.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Thanks again!</p>\r\n','Meera <br />\r\nChicago, Illinois<br />\r\nMachu Picchu<br />\r\n','','','',399,0,0,NULL,NULL,NULL),(734,1,'Dear Peru For Less, ','<p>We were in great hands with Peru For Less. In eight days we had an amazing adventure through the Andes - and deep inside ancient Incan culture - while enjoying fantastic food all the way.</p>','Rob <br/>\r\nMassachusetts<br/>\r\nCusco &amp; Inca Trail<br/>\r\n','','','',722,0,0,NULL,NULL,NULL),(735,1,'Dear Peru For Less,','<p>Thanks again for a wonderful experience. Lia and I got the experiences we were looking for and it has made us curious about other tours you could perhaps arrange for us in the future. This was our first \'guided\' tour, but the PFL team assembled a very nice trip for us! </p>','Lia and Cherik <br />\r\nArequipa, Cusco, Puno<br />\r\n','','','',727,0,0,NULL,NULL,NULL),(736,1,'Hello Kristina,','<p>Thanks for all your help in arranging our recent trip to Peru, all of the organization of our holiday was extremely straightforward, no complications.</p>\r\n \r\n<p>We knew that the schedule would be hectic for us, as we wanted to go to as many places as possible, namely, Lima, Ica, Nazca, Arequipa, Colca Canyon, Puno (Lake Titicaca), Cusco, and Machu Picchu.  All of the transfers to and from airports and coach stations went smoothly, we were always given times to be picked and everyone was on time, so that gave us peace of mind.  Our hotels were all very clean and comfortable with friendly helpful staff, and we couldn\'t fault any of the food.  Found Peru to be a fascinating and interesting country, with diverse landscapes, from the coast to high Andes, we found all of the guides extremely knowledgeable and genuinely interested in promoting their country.  We did suffer from the altitude going to Colca Canyon, but guide and driver very supportive and understanding.  </p>\r\n \r\n<p>Overall we had a fantastic trip, we did not have one overall highlight, but obviously Machu Picchu and travelling through the Sacred Valley and discovering the Inca history was fascinating, but seeing 15-20 condors flying low over us at Colca Canyon was quite spectacular.</p>\r\n','Heather &amp; Neil <br />\r\nUK<br />\r\nLima, Ica, Nazca, Arequipa, Colca Canyon, Puno, Lake Titicaca, Cusco, Machu Picchu<br />\r\n','','','',724,0,0,NULL,NULL,NULL),(737,1,'Hi Rylee,','<p>We are back from a trip of a lifetime. Thank you so much for all your help. The hotels and arrangements were all wonderful. I would highly recommend all of the hotels where we stayed. The representatives who met us at each stop were superb--friendly, knowledgeable, helpful, on time. Just for your information, the only problem we had was with our reservation from Lima to Puno. Apparently, the reservation number matched a flight for 12 noon rather than 2:30. The airline was great, and got our flight changed, but thank goodness there was room on the flight. </p>\r\n<p>The train rides were highlights, both the vistas and the service. What a difference from air travel today. Definitely the way to go in Peru if you have the time. </p>\r\n<p>I cannot begin to tell you how spectacular the Inca Trail was. We were so right that if you have the physical stamina, this is the way to see Machu Picchu. The trail was incredibly beautiful, and the ruins along the way prepare you for Machu Picchu in a way that riding the bus could never do. Wayki was terrific. Edwin, our guide, was the best. He took care of us \"chicas\" every minute. He said it was his first all female trip, and he and all the porters treated us like queens. We were wakened to tea and hot water to wash in our tents, and went to sleep by having them check to make sure we were all carefully zipped in our tents. Every meal was special; how they do that on a two burner stove, I will never know. Edwin, was knowledgeable of the trail and through excellent planning and timing, kept us away from the crowds, both on the trail and in the campsites. I fell and sprained my ankle and scrapped my knee on the lst morning of the trail, and he expertly took care of both. We felt we were in very good hands the entire trip.</p>\r\n<p>There is one problem on the trail that I know you are in no way responsible for, but we want to pass on in the event you can have some leverage with the park or with the trail tour companies. The toilet facilities are totally inadequate for the number of persons on the trail using them. They get very dirty very fast, at times we gagged, just getting near them. Consequently, many (most) people don\'t even use them, choosing to use the woods along the trail or near the campsites. This means there is toilet paper all around the campsites and all along the trail in every potentially beautiful grotto. Often the smell along the trail is nauseous.  I know we and I assume most campers would gladly pay more for the use of more and cleaner toilets along the trail. In the states, campers must have separate toilet tents with portable toilets in most parks. Any solution would be better than the unsanitary conditions at present. This marred what should have been a pristine hiking experience.</p>\r\n<p>Finally, one last note. We discussed one evening what we think is an unfortunate name for your company. \"Peru For Less\" suggests low cost, but does nothing to suggest the quality of your services. Frankly, if I had not had a recommendation from a friend, I would not have gone with you, as the name suggests cost as the primary factor. Let me say, I am an experienced traveler, and you and your company are top-notch. I cannot see that one detail was spared. You planned the trip exactly as we wanted, let us choose the accommodations, allowing us to be on our own, yet taking the hassle out of transfers and reservations. We had terrific representatives at each stop that we could call if we needed more information (and we did). Maybe you need a tag line something along the lines of \"the best doesn\'t have to cost more\". That is what we got, absolutely the best at a very reasonable price.</p>\r\n','Dina  (Williamson group)<br />\r\nGalveston, TX<br />\r\nLima, Puno, Cusco, Inca Trail to Machu PIcchu<br />\r\n','','','',725,0,0,NULL,NULL,NULL),(738,1,'Hi Rylee,','<p>We had the most memorable and awesome experience in Peru. Thanks to your impeccable arrangement, we enjoyed the whole trip without a hitch. In fact the timings were so perfect, we could not believe the coordination you have between the drivers, tour guides. We chose some pricey hotels, but the experience was worth it. The people were warm and friendly and we felt instant connection. We will recommend your company without reservation. We are looking forward to more of South American tours.</p>','Avinash and Vandana <br />\r\nClaremont, CA<br />\r\nLima, Cusco, Machu Picchu<br />\r\n','','','',733,0,0,NULL,NULL,NULL),(739,1,'Hi Rylee,','<p>Thank you for an excellently organized trip to Peru and Bolivia. The Ceiba Treetops Expolorama Lodge was a very good and comfortable base to explore the Amazon and a couple of her near-by tributaries. </p>\r\n \r\n<p>All in all, the itinerary was followed closely and punctually and all local tour guides were very professional and informative.</p>\r\n','Ned  <br />\r\nCalgary, Alberta, Canada<br />\r\nIquitos, Lima, Paracas, Nazca, La Paz<br />\r\n','','','',729,0,0,NULL,NULL,NULL),(740,1,'Aloha Kelly,','<p>We had such a magical experience!!!</p>\r\n \r\n<p>We are so impressed with the service that we received during our recent trip to Peru.  We were greeted at each location by one of your representatives who were always very informative about our itinerary and made great recommendations.</p>\r\n \r\n<p>Our tours were fantastic!  We loved our guides who all seemed to have a very spiritual connection to \"Pachamama\" and shared with us much of the history and legends at each location.      </p>\r\n \r\n<p>The white water rafting and the horseback ride to Moras and Moray were awesome.  We were especially impressed with the wonderful local-style meals that were included in each of those tours.  Lunching with our guides and drivers gave us an opportunity to learn more about how the local people live, their customs and beliefs.  We also had some \"chicha\" which was quite tasty. </p>\r\n \r\n<p>The train ride to Puno was a great experience.  There was always something happening to keep you entertained.  Plus, we thoroughly enjoyed our visit to the Uros Islands and the Isle of Tequile.   </p>\r\n \r\n<p>What can I say about Machu Picchu ... WOW.  Pictures cannot capture the beauty and energy of Machu Picchu.  We had planned to hike Huayna Picchu on our second day; however, our guide suggested that we hike Mountania Machu Picchu instead.  We are so glad that we did.  The hike was a very challenging and extremely rewarding experience.  The views were spectacular.</p>\r\n \r\n<p>Thank you Kelly and Peru4Less!  We had such a wonderful time that we are going to do it again...this time on the Inca Trail.  Talk to you soon!</p>\r\n','Dixie <br />\r\nLima, Cusco, Machu Picchu, Lake Titicaca<br />\r\n','','','',728,0,0,NULL,NULL,NULL),(741,1,'Hi Rylee, ','<p>We are back! I am sorry that I couldn\'t respond earlier but our 20-day Peru holiday was an epic adventure of a lifetime and it has taken this long for us to recover and resume our normal lives. </p>\r\n\r\n<p>Our trip was fantastic and we found Peru to be an absolutely amazing country of so much natural beauty. I have organised many excursions for our group of intrepid travellers for many years and I must say that Peru For Less is one of the best and most professional companies I have dealt with. From the start, you were always fast with your emails and have the patience of a saint dealing with my never ending questions and concerns. We were well taken care of during our trip by your numerous greeters and drivers at each and every port all of whom were very friendly and helpful. </p>\r\n\r\n<p>Once again Rylee, we would like to say thank you for helping us arrange a trip of a lifetime. It will certainly stay in our memories for many years to come. Without hesitation, we would recommend you and PFL to everyone. </p>\r\n','Winnie <br />\r\nKuala Lumpur, Malaysia<br />\r\nLima, Paracas, Nazca, Arequipa, Colca Canyon, Lake Titicaca, Cusco, Sacred Valley, Choquequirao, Machu Picchu<br />\r\n','','','',730,0,0,NULL,NULL,NULL),(742,1,'Hi Rylee!!','<p>I\'m so sorry it took me such a long while to reply back, but I was not going to skip an opportunity to thank you for your great help and amazing planning!! Peru was absolutely beautiful to visit!! I have been back home for a few months, and I still wish I could rewind time and live it all again!</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Cusco was a beauty to discover! The guides were very well versed and the services were above any expectations. My sister and my friends loved the experience so much they can\'t believe it was over that quickly! Thank you so much for making the arrangements for her birthday cake during the Inca Trail! She will remember that one forever!! Machu Picchu was a jewel! Despite the heavy/light rain we encountered, the experience was simply unbelievable! Seeing the panorama, learning the history, discovering the Inca culture, sweating our way up the Inca Train, no words can describe the emotions you go through during those 4 incredible days!! A great place to refill energy and live a great experience!!</p>\r\n\r\n<p>I would not have had it any different and you made it all possible!! We were indeed lucky escaping the storm! We heard about it when we arrived in Puno; we were so sad to hear they had to evacuate people... but at least the bad weather is over though!! I am still dreaming of this trip, every aspect of it was an unforgettable life experience!! Peru For Less made my first trip to South America very memorable!!</p>\r\n\r\n<p>I look forward another hike again soon!! I have attached two pictures: a picture with Jose (Waiki Trek guide), myself, David, Sofia, and Gisele at the top of Warmiwanuska (4215masl) and one with the entire crew of waiki trek.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Thanks again for everything you\'ve done!!</p>\r\n','Stephania <br />\r\nLaval, Quebec Canada<br />\r\nCusco, Inca Trail to Machu Picchu and Lake Titicaca<br />\r\n','','','',712,0,0,NULL,NULL,NULL),(743,1,'Dear Riva,','<p>Everything went just perfect and I had a really wonderful time. I learned so many things and I couldn\'t get enough of walking around in Cusco and also at Machu Picchu. On my free day at Machu Picchu, I went to the butterfly garden which is a lovely place with a very nice guide but which is still recovering from the floods earlier this year, and to the botanical garden. The guide there was very sweet and knew two types of orchids: \"orchids no flower\" and \"orchid flower\". He knew actually much more than as I found out - so it\'s worth asking some questions. The park with the water fall and river at the end of the hike was really nice and peaceful and just what I needed to have some quite time in Nature. The museum is certainly worth a visit and the small caf&eacute; at the bridge is a nice place to have a little rest and a really strong coffee.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>The hotels were both very nice, especially the one is Cusco, and the people were all so very friendly and kind. The train ride was great too, with nice music and good food.</p>\r\n','Sigrid <br />\r\nPhilippines<br />\r\nCusco, Machu Picchu<br />\r\n','','','',734,0,0,NULL,NULL,NULL),(744,1,'Dear Peru For Less,','<p>We indeed had a wonderful time. Everything went according to plan without a hitch. The PFL staff was on hand every step of the way with transportation and guidance. They were always on time and very courteous. PFL services are indeed most impressive.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Trip to Nazca was long but buses were very comfortable. Nazca lines flight was impressive and accommodation was great. We very much enjoyed Cusco and Machu Picchu. The overnight stay at Machu Picchu was worth the cost.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Galapagos trip also went without any problem. Very efficient and courteous staff. We would like to thank you for your efforts.</p>\r\n','Masud <br />\r\nArizona<br />\r\nLima, Cusco, Machu Picchu, Quito, Galapagos<br />\r\n','','','',731,0,0,NULL,NULL,NULL),(745,1,'Dear Danielle,','<p>With a plethora of travel websites/companies on the Internet, it was a bit daunting for us to find a suitable travel agency. We\'re so pleased that we chose Peru For Less. During our one-week vacation, we had an unforgettable time in and around Cusco and Machu Picchu. Peru For Less delivered on all the things you expect from a travel agency: professionalism, promptness, coordination, friendliness, flexibility, reasonable pricing, smooth booking process, fascinating tours and knowledgeable, well-spoken English-speaking tour guides. In fact, for all our future South America travels we would definitely contact you again and we would definitely recommend your company to others. </p>','Michelle and Ryan <br />\r\nEncino, CA<br />\r\nCusco, Machu Picchu, Sacred Valley<br />\r\n','','','',732,0,0,NULL,NULL,NULL),(746,1,'Danielle,','<p>Thank you for helping us with booking a hotel in Aguas Calientes.  Our adventure in Machu Picchu was unforgettable.  The scenery was breathtaking, and the ruins were fantastic.  </p>\r\n\r\n<p>We loved Peru, the people and everything we saw.</p>\r\n','Margie<br />\r\nLake Oswego, OR<br />\r\nAguas Calientes<br />\r\n','','','',396,0,0,NULL,NULL,NULL),(747,1,'Dear Peru For Less,','<p>We just returned from an AMAZING time in Peru that was organized by Peru For Less!  Our entire trip was customized based on the specific schedule and itinerary that we wanted.  The representatives at PFL were quick to respond to my many questions and patiently worked through multiple iterations of our itinerary.  When we arrived in Cusco, everything went very smoothly -- we didn\'t have to worry about any of the logistics.  We could focus all of our time and energy on enjoying the wonderful sights!  The hotels were very clean and centrally located.  The representative who met us at the Cusco airport was very cheery and gave us great restaurant recommendations.  </p>\r\n<p>We received pretty much door to door service the whole time we were there, which exceeded our expectations.  We loved this trip and would definitely recommend Peru For Less.</p>','Lisa and Jon <br />\r\nChicago, IL<br />\r\nCusco, Machu Picchu, Sacred Valley<br />\r\n','','','',398,0,0,NULL,NULL,NULL),(748,1,'Dear Rylee,','<p>We want to thank you and all those from Peru For Less who helped make our Peru trip so memorable, convenient and affordable.  Your advice and recommendations and those of JP regarding planning the trip were invaluable.   The PFL representatives who met us at each stage to welcome us and brief us on the itinerary were extremely courteous and helpful with any questions we had.  The transitions from airport to hotel to train or bus or boat were handled efficiently and safely.  We still wonder at how our capable drivers navigated those narrow Cusco streets. </p>\r\n\r\n<p>Perhaps most of all, we appreciated the local guides.  They were all very knowledgeable and enhanced our experiences greatly.  Jose Luis at Refugio Amazonas never failed to find and identify fascinating flora and fauna for us to see, including caimans, capybaras, monkeys and birds as diverse as a horned screamer, parrots and the oropendulas who constantly swooped in and out of their nests suspended from palms close to the jungle lodge, and even a tarantula teased out of its in-ground nest.  Darwin at Machu Picchu, a guide at the ruins for some 30 years, is also an author of books about Machu Picchu.  He was proud and passionate when telling us â??pilgrimsâ? about the Inca civilization and its amazing astronomical and engineering accomplishments.   Maria Elena gave us many new insights as she guided us through colonial Cusco and nearby archaeological sites, and through the Sacred Valley. </p>\r\n\r\n<p>We were satisfied with the accommodations, and especially charmed by the romantic, though rustic, lodge at Refugio Amazonas.  We very much enjoyed the scenic train trip to Aguas Calientes and, after our tour of Machu Picchu, welcomed the comfort of the Casa Andina Luxury hotel.   In Cusco, we found the staff at Ninos II hotel very friendly and looked forward each morning to breakfast, served by a young beneficiary of the nonprofit founded to support local orphans with hotel profits.  She is an inspiring, real-life success story.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>We heartily recommend Peru For Less and a similar itinerary to others.  Thanks for everything.</p>\r\n','Frank  and Elaine <br />\r\nGrass Valley, CA<br />\r\nLima, Puerto Maldonado, Cusco, Machu Picchu<br />\r\n','','','',400,0,0,NULL,NULL,NULL),(749,1,'Hi Matt,','<p>Wow!  What a trip!</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Firstly, I would like to tell you that in all instances, our guides were incredible!  They were knowledgeable and very passionate about their country and its history.  </p>\r\n\r\n<p>After the first couple of glitches, everything else went very, very smoothly.  It was not the guideÂ´s fault that he was unable to find us when we first arrived, it was not clear to us that the cafÃ© was back in the airport â?? he was actually waiting for us, we just missed each other.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Thank you for providing our lunch at the Sanctuary.  After seeing the La Puebla Inkaterra, we all agreed that we were happy to stay there, rather than at the Sanctuary, as the experience at La Puebla was fantastic!  Our trip down from Machu Picchu was on the Hiram Bingham, arranged (I think by magic) through Caitlin, what a great experience that was!</p>\r\n\r\n<p>All in all, we arrived home safely, exhausted but very happy. </p>\r\n','Dorothy <br />\r\nCanada<br />\r\nLima, Ica, Nazca, Arequipa, Puno, Cusco, Mapi <br />\r\n','','','',401,0,0,NULL,NULL,NULL),(750,1,'Matt,','<p>Appreciate all you did in setting up a fantastic trip customized for us and on such short notice.  Everything pretty much went like clockwork.  Margaret and I had a great time.  We really enjoyed our trip.  It was a great feeling to know we were not alone if something happened.  </p>','Mike <br />\r\nChicago, IL<br />\r\nLima, Cusco, Mapi, Puno<br />\r\n','','','',402,0,0,NULL,NULL,NULL),(751,1,'Dear Jennifer, ','<p>I may have had the best trip of my life. You really got us as far as the balance between playing and tour. We felt like princesses. Everything was so well organized. Each person was on time and really knew their stuff. Our guides and drivers were so great. The land was amazing. The people were beautiful. My favorite moments, our Shaman, Lucus and the story of how we got our interpreter, hiking to the top of Machu Picchu, riding the horse to the top of the mountain with our private tent and being served lunch, the market place, the history, the fun, the different food (no guinea pig), feeling taken care of, slowing my body down for a much-needed break.</p>','Carla <br />\r\nCalifornia<br />\r\nLima, Cusco, Sacred Valley, Machu Picchu<br />\r\n','','','',403,0,0,NULL,NULL,NULL),(752,1,'Jennifer,','<p>I wanted to thank you for all your efforts to organize our trip. We had a great time. \r\nThe hotels were excellent. We were also positively surprised by the punctuality of all pickups and transfers. </p>\r\n\r\n<p>Your tour guide Darwin at Machu Picchu was outstanding! He was finally what we expected and tuned the visit into an unforgotten experience. </p>\r\n','Kerstin <br />\r\nTexas<br />\r\nCusco &amp; Machu Picchu<br />\r\n','','','',405,0,0,NULL,NULL,NULL),(753,1,'Hi Kim,','<p>I had a great time in Peru, the trip could not have been any better. All our guides were very helpful and knowledgeable, whether it was in the Jungle, Lake Titicaca or Machu Picchu; and the weather cooperated too. I was very impressed with Peru For Less. The guides were always were they were supposed to be. </p>\r\n<p>I would definitely recommend Peru For Less to my family and friends.</p>\r\n','Thompson  (Baughman group)<br />\r\nLima, Puerto Maldonado, Cusco, Machu Picchu, Lake Titicaca<br />\r\n','','','',406,0,0,NULL,NULL,NULL),(754,1,'Hi Kelly,','<p>Our trip was fantastic.  All of your services were excellent and all of the guides and hotels were better than we expected.</p>\r\n \r\n<p>We were met promptly at every airport and picked up from our hotel right on time, every time.</p>\r\n \r\n<p>The highlight of the trip for us was Easter Island....I always wanted to go there and it was fantastic.</p>\r\n \r\n<p>Thanks so much for all of your help.  </p>\r\n','Jim <br />\r\nCusco, Machu Picchu, Santiago, Easter Island<br />\r\n','','','',407,0,0,NULL,NULL,NULL),(755,1,'Hi Kristen.','<p>The hotel was so nice especially the staff. The tours were wonderful and well arranged. The Glacier was very beautiful. And yes! Exactly as you told me, it doesn\'t require any special physical ability :) I totally enjoyed this Glacier trip.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Thanks for everything; I will definitely keep you in mind for the future travel.</p>\r\n','Pianporn <br />\r\n','','','',408,0,0,NULL,NULL,NULL),(756,1,'Hi Rylee,','<p>Peru For Less really made the difference for us: the assistance with transfers, the knowledge of our guides, In fact, cannot imagine having done the trip without your support. Thanks for a quality product and top-notch service. Look forward to another trip with Peru For Less.</p>\r\n\r\n','Heather <br />\r\nLima<br />\r\nChiclayo &amp; Trujillo<br />\r\n','','','',409,0,0,NULL,NULL,NULL),(757,1,'Dear Peru For Less,','<p>We had a wonderful trip.  All connections and tours were good.  The guide in Quito from Klein tours (Ramon) was excellent.  The Galapagos tour on Coral II was great.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Thanks for all of your help in planning our last minute trip. We loved Ecuador!</p>\r\n','John <br />\r\nMidland, MI<br />\r\nQuito and the Galapagos<br />\r\n','','','',410,0,0,NULL,NULL,NULL),(758,1,'Hi Kristina,','<p>All in all we had a fantastic trip, thanks so very much.  </p>','Don <br />\r\nCalifornia<br />\r\nGalapagos, Lima, Cusco, Machu Picchu<br />\r\n','','','',411,0,0,NULL,NULL,NULL),(759,1,'Riva,','<p>We are home and our trip was awesome. Thanks again for everything on such short notice. Agua Calientas was so beautiful and our hotel was so nice too.</p>','Susanne <br />\r\nMinnesota<br />\r\nCusco, Mapi<br />\r\n','','','',412,0,0,NULL,NULL,NULL),(760,1,'Dear Peru For Less,','<p>I first heard about Peru for Less from my dentist.  I immediately went online to see if I could find any bad reviews of Peru for Less.  After doing intense internet research on non-Peru for Less affiliated sites, I came back empty.  </p>\n\n<p>After sending an inquiry email, I got an almost immediate response back from Jennifer.  I couldn\'t believe how quickly she responded to all my emails (~30) including the ones I sent on the weekend.  It really helped to know that if I had any questions or concerns I could easily ask and know I would get a response back.  Peru for Less made arrangements for our 15 day trip including 5 plane flights and 5 tours.  Everything went as planned.  If it was on our itinerary, it happened.  </p>\n\n<p>We traveled with the hopes of seeing lots of different species and boy did we.  We took over 3,000 pictures and enjoyed every moment of our trip.  The highlight of our trip was definitely the Galapagos.  We loved all the snorkeling and hiking.  </p>\n','Nicole and Sarah <br />\r\nQuito, Galapagos, Lima, Manu, Cusco, Machu Picchu \r\n','','','',735,0,0,NULL,NULL,NULL),(761,1,'Dear Rylee,','<p>I did want you to know that my sister and I had an absolutely wonderful time up north!  The guides were very knowledgeable, and I was quite impressed with how comfortable the bus trip was.  I want to thank you personally for handling all our arrangements so smoothly.  In fact, when my family comes to visit in December 2011, Iâ??d like to work with you again on a trip to Arequipa!  </p>','Heather <br />\r\nLima, Peru<br />\r\nTrujillo, Chiclayo\r\n','','','',412,0,0,NULL,NULL,NULL),(762,1,'Hi Jennifer,','<p>It was absolutely great. Nothing to complain at all.</p>\r\n<p>Thanks,</p>\r\n','Dong  <br />\r\nCusco, Machu Picchu <br />\r\n','','','',412,0,0,NULL,NULL,NULL),(763,1,'Dear Peru For Less,','<p>My grandsons and I had a great time with your company. Nancy made our visit to Tiauanaku wonderful. It was my second time with your company in La Paz and I would certainly recommend it to anyone.</p>\r\n<p>Thanks, </p>\r\n','John <br />\r\nPennsylvania<br />\r\nLa Paz, Bolivia<br />\r\n','','','',412,0,0,NULL,NULL,NULL),(764,1,'Hi Staci,','<p>We\'ve returned home from our trip and are pleased to report that we had a wonderful time!  We particularly enjoyed the Sacred Valley and found the Quechua people to be very welcoming and sincere.\r\nOur experience with PFL and Klein was very positive â?? everyone was very professional, the customer service was excellent and the itinerary was executed well.\r\nThanks and best regards,</p>\r\n','Norman <br />\r\nUS and Canada<br />\r\nLima, Cusco, Sacred Valley, Machu Picchu, Quito and Galapagos            \r\n','','','',412,0,0,NULL,NULL,NULL),(765,1,'Kelly,','<p>The trip was fabulous! All the connections worked out well - a little anxiety the first one or two times - but after that I was confident we would connect with each of the many local contacts! They were wonderful and very punctual.  It\'s clear to me Peru For Less is well organized and concerned for the welfare of its customers. I appreciated all of your collective attention.</p>\r\n \r\n<p>My only confusion was the uncertainty of when to tip and to who and how much!  There were transport drivers, tour guides, porters not to mention doormen who were enthusiastic to help us out - some received a tip from us, and some did not - and only once did I get accosted from a \"porter\" that I should give him a tip, but my sense was that he was not part of Peru For Less personnel; more likely a free agent just trying to make a buck.</p>\r\n \r\n<p>All the sights were wonderful and awe inspiring - Cusco as the \"hometown\" of the rising Inca civilization was very impressive; and Lake Titicaca with the Floating Islands as well as Brown Paradise Island with its verticalness (it felt like 2,000 irregular steps up - lunch - and then a different set of 2,000 steps down!).  There were the Nazca Lines that have been there for such a long time and the set of islands with so many species of birds and sea lions - wow!</p>\r\n \r\n<p>Thank you so much, and I have already sung your praises to so many others I have talked with since we\'ve been back.  I hope you hear from some of these folks in Connecticut about coming down to see your country.</p>\r\n \r\n<p>Thank you again and again.  Happy holidays!</p>\r\n','Peter and Mary <br/>\r\nConnecticut, USA<br/>\r\nLima, Chiclayo, Trujillo, Paracas, Nazca, Arequipa, Colca Canyon, PuÃ±o, Cusco, Sacred Valley &amp; Machu Picchu<br/>\r\n','','','',413,0,0,NULL,NULL,NULL),(766,1,'Dear Kelly,','<p>Please forgive us for the extreme delay in our response.  We are not as punctual and organized as all of you at Peru For Less!  You asked how our trip through Peru went and if we enjoyed ourselves... I cannot express to you how incredible the entire experience was for us!  We completely customized our trip and spent 10 days covering as much ground as we possibly could. Peru For Less made every single detail seamless.  We made one mistake in Ica (missed our bus stop) but your people on the ground had us back on track in less than five minutes.</p>\r\n  \r\n<p>While in Peru we travelled by air, bus, train and van. We stayed in a different location almost every night! We loved it!  We were particularly impressed with how comfortable the buses were, and the promptness and politeness of every driver and guide along the way.  The hotels were lovely (we chose the 3 star option) and the staff all very helpful. </p>\r\n\r\n<p>The food was beyond good, we never had a bad meal.  One morning in Arequipa we had an early morning transfer to the airport.  The good people at Casa Arequipa packed us some sandwiches to take along, hours before breakfast was available.  They didn\'t charge us a penny for them!  And the guides- I don\'t know where to start-- they were awesome!  We felt that every tour we went on we had the best guides possible.  We loved them all, but have to say that our tour of the Sacred Valley with Edgar, and Machu Picchu with Fabricio wouldn\'t have been the same with anyone else.  Our time in Peru will be in my heart forever. No doubt Peru has some of the world\'s most breathtaking sights to behold, but we needed help getting there. I thank you for making this journey possible for us.  We experienced many things that blew our minds and filled our hearts.  This will not be the last you hear from us. Thank you!!</p>\r\n \r\n<p>Sincerely,</p>\r\n','Amanda  and David <br />\r\nUSA<br />\r\nLima, Ica, Nazca, Arequipa, Colca Canyon, Cusco &amo; Machu Picchu <br />\r\n','','','',413,0,0,NULL,NULL,NULL),(767,1,'Hi Matt, ','<p>We are safely back! We want to thank you and your company for all the hard work you put into our trip to make it a pleasurable experience. I have to admit we were very wary in the beginning sending money to a company we did not know and had found on the Internet.</p>\r\n \r\n<p>All the arranged places we were to be met - happened. All the transfers -happened. The hotels were as detailed and were up to the standard we expected. The drivers, staff and anyone else we dealt with at Peru For Less were exemplary. Our one hic-cup of missing a connection was handled quickly and professionally plus the refund check for this unfortunate episode was waiting for us when we returned to Los Angeles last evening. </p>\r\n \r\n<p>In short we would certainly use your services again and highly recommend your company.</p>\r\n \r\n<p>Thank you again,</p>\r\n','Richard and Christine <br />\r\nUSA<br />\r\nLima, Nazca, Cusco &amp; Machu Picchu <br />\r\n','','','',413,0,0,NULL,NULL,NULL),(768,1,'Hi Jennie,','<p>Our trip to Peru was great!  Your very fine people met us when we arrived, explained the itinerary in detail, answered all our questions, took us where we needed to go, and made sure we were taken care of.  The hotel accommodations were superb (we want to stay in the same place in Cusco when we return next time), and the guides could not have been better.  I would recommend Peru For Less to anyone for a flawless, never-to-be-forgotten experience.  The only thing I would change the next time we make this trip (and we will) would be to spend more time in Ollantaytambo, possibly spending the night there to break up the train ride to Machu Picchu.  Other than that, I wouldn\'t change a thing.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Thanks again for an unforgettable experience,</p>\r\n','Kirk and Linda  <br />\r\nUSA<br />\r\nCusco, Sacred Valley &amp; Machu Picchu <br />\r\n','','','',413,0,0,NULL,NULL,NULL),(769,1,'Hi Rylee, ','<p>Our trip was fantastic. You were excellent in the planning process, responded to all of our millions of questions and were there the whole way through the trip to make sure all was alright. Thanks. Our trip was top notch which was truly your superb work and we have been a high maintenance group. </p>\r\n\r\n<p>I plan on sending you more details when the time is better, but I wanted to let you know how much we appreciated your help in the organization and safety of our trip. I will be recommending Peru For Less to all of my friends and family.</p>\r\n','Lark <br />\r\nCalagary, Alberta, Canada<br />\r\nLima, Puerto Maldonado, Cusco, Inca Trail, Machu Picchu, Puno, Lake Titicaca, Arequipa &amp; Colca Canyon <br />\r\n','','','',413,0,0,NULL,NULL,NULL),(770,1,'Hi Riva,','<p>The trip was excellent. My brother and I enjoyed our vacation. Peru is a beautiful and diverse country.</p>\r\n \r\n<p>All transfers and tours were seamless. I never had to wait for a pick-up or transfer. Despite a 3rd party handling our voyage in Puno, they were also very professional and were dependable for all pickups.</p>\r\n \r\n<p>Wiki Tour for the Inca Trail is excellent. It turned out to be a private tour for us which allowed us to hike at our own pace. They were excellent.  </p>\r\n\r\n<p>The Amazon was nice and Refugio Amazones is a beautiful lodge. Posadas Amazones may be preferred since it is a little shorter boat ride, although the accommodations are probably not as nice. The food was excellent there.</p>\r\n \r\n<p>Accommodations in Cuzco and Puno were as expected for moderate level hotel. The breakfast at Casa Andina in Cuzco is excellent. My only suggestion is that on our late arrival to Peru, it probably would have been easier to stay in a hotel near the airport rather than Miraflores, since we had an early morning flight.</p>\r\n \r\n<p>All in all, the trip was fantastic. </p>\r\n \r\n<p>Thanks,</p>\r\n','Pat <br />\r\nSan Diego, California, USA<br />\r\nLima, Puerto Maldonado, Cusco, Inca Trail, Machu Picchu &amp; PuÃ±o <br />\r\n','','','',413,0,0,NULL,NULL,NULL),(771,1,'Hi!','<p>Thank you, I had a great time in Peru! I loved every moment of it, and ended up taking close to 800 pictures! All the accommodations where great, better than I could have expected because it was so last minute.\r\nAntonio was a WONDERFUL guide I will definitely be referring him and your company to others I know. Please forward my email to Antonio I would love to send him some of the pictures I took.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Thank you so much for helping put it all together for me, it was a great experience that I hope to do again soon.</p>\r\n','Dianne <br />\r\nPeru<br />\r\nInca Trail <br />\r\n','','','',413,0,0,NULL,NULL,NULL),(772,1,'Hi Rylee,','<p>Peru was amazing, I want to move there. And after staying at the Marriott,   I don\'t know how I can stay anywhere else now.  You were incredible in the planning process and I will definitely be booking with you for every trip to South America. I will go to Peru every year. </p>\r\n\r\n<p>I was searching online for travel/tour companies in Peru and thatâ??s how I learned about Peru For Less.  I liked the website and also I was able to read about the agents which made me more comfortable in reaching out to Rylee.  Coming from the US, I also liked that Peru for Less has offices in Peru and the US.  </p>\r\n\r\n<p>This was my second time using Peru For Less and both times they were great. Iâ??m a very strict and detailed person and all the travel arrangements were handled quickly and accurately.  Even last year when our flight was delayed coming home to the US, I simply called the 24/7 number and was able to change my pick up time and get more sleep.  Also, every time I e-mailed Rylee, she got back to me right away which is very important to me. I always felt like I was her only client. I would recommend this company for all your travel needs</p>\r\n','Omar <br />\r\nChicago, Il, USA<br />\r\nLima &amp; Trujillo<br />\r\n','','','',413,0,0,NULL,NULL,NULL),(773,1,'Hi Kelly,','<p>You beat me to the punch as I was planning to send you an email to thank you so much for all your help! Everything about the trip you organized went so well and was designed as if you knew us! After our previous unsuccessful attempts to organize the trip with other agencies we were understandably anxious and distrustful about what we would encounter when we got to Peru. </p>\r\n\r\n<p>We needn\'t have worried because it was all handled perfectly. At every stop our guide or transport was waiting for us and told us what to expect. They were all courteous, knowledgeable and professional. The hotels were perfect for our tastes. Our bus seats were a pleasant surprise as we hadn\'t recalled asking for the VIP seats that allowed us to stretch out more comfortably on the overnight ride (we may have talked about this but I don\'t recall doing so) and our guide helped us change our time of departure on the return to Lima which was very helpful. Everything went like clockwork and we are so grateful. You turned our experience from dread to delight! Thank you for everything!</p>\r\n \r\n<p>PS: We also appreciate the help in providing a testimonial which we most certainly will do. You\'ve earned it! And when we ever travel to Peru or any other country in South America, you\'ll be the first number we\'ll call. </p>\r\n','Donna and Roger <br />\r\nPuno, Arequipa, Colca Canyon &amp; Nazca <br />\r\n','','','',736,0,0,NULL,NULL,NULL),(774,1,'Dear Matt,','<p>My visit to Cusco and Machu Picchu was a very magical experience and one that I will cherish always. From designing the trip to arrival and departure, the team at Peru For Less were very professional and kind. The guides for the City Tour, Inca Trial Hike and visit to Machu Picchu were so knowledgeable of the history and proud of their heritage. The staff at Casa Andina, San Blas and El Santuario was lovely and made sure I had a comfortable and enjoyable stay. </p>\r\n\r\n<p>The two days I spent traveling via the Vista Dome train and hiking the last portion of the Inca Trial to arrive at the Sun Gate of Machu Picchu were absolutely magical!  Along the trail we arrived at Winaywayna (Forever Young), the last urban center before reaching the Sun Gate and the sacred city of Machu Picchu. This site was simply stunning and made the pending arrival at Inti Punku (Sun Gate) even more exciting.  I had a very special experience as we arrived at the Sun Gate late in the day to enjoy a completely clear view of the citadel area. The light rain, cool air and quietness provided for such a delightful introduction to the city. I am so thankful and feel very fortunate to have had such an experience. I recommend the 2 Day Hike plan to anyone interested in enhancing their experience at Machu Picchu however may not be interested in the 4 Day Hike.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>I recommend Peru For Less to all my friends and anyone else interested in visiting Cusco and Machu Picchu. I hope to return to Peru and expand my horizons by visiting other magical areas of the country. Please extend my gratitude to all involved in making my visit such a lovely experience!</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Much&iacute;simas gracias a todos!</p>\r\n','Michelle <br />\r\nSan Diego, California, USA<br />\r\nCusco, Inca Trail &amp; Machu Picchu <br />\r\n','','','',738,0,0,NULL,NULL,NULL),(775,1,'Hi Matt,','<p>We can\'t thank you enough for helping to create such a memorable experience for us in Peru.<strong> From the moment we arrived to our departure from Cusco, Peru for Less took care of us.</strong> Everyone was extremely friendly, helpful and truly excited about our visit. I have no idea how they keep that enthusiasm up for each person that visits this great country, but they did and it was awesome. We arrived in Lima at 10 p.m. and were immediately greeted by a friendly face and informative person to guide us to our hotel. All of the lodging picked by Peru for Less was wonderful. We were pleasantly surprised at each spot. Also, each hotel we stayed in was really ideal to each location.</p>\r\n<p>We went on many tours and each was lead by extremely knowledgeable tour guides who again, had a wonderful passion for their country. <strong>In the Amazon, Explorama Lodge was awesome. We felt that we were in the rain forest but with a group of excited explorers. We hung out on the hammocks, went for a few hikes, watched the sunset over the Amazon, went fishing for piranhas and saw countless creepy but interesting bugs!! </strong>This was by far, the best food we had during the trip. We liked how everyone staying at the lodge got together for breakfast, lunch and dinner. It was a great opportunity to meet others traveling. The staff there was also exceptional. Many had worked for the company since its creation and truly cared about showcasing the rainforest. The thing I liked most about the Explorama company is that they are deeply committed to preserving the rainforest.</p>\r\n<p>Cusco was such a pleasant surprise. The town was great to stay in, full of things to do, shopping, great restaurants, etc. The bed and breakfast we stayed in, Casa San Blas, was great. The service was wonderful. After we got back from Aguas Calientes, they had warmers in our beds so we could relax after our days at Machu Picchu. They also had a very good breakfast.</p>\r\n<p>In Aguas Calientes, we had a good hotel with an awesome view of the Urubamba River. Aguas Calientes was a small, easy to get around in town. For dinner, we found a place called tree tops and hands down, it was awesome! Go there for dinner when you are here! We highly recommend it! And while in Aguas Calientes, we went to Machu Picchu, which was absolutely breathtaking. <strong>Our guide, Darwin, was awesome.</strong> I\'m pretty sure he said he had written many books about Machu Picchu.</p>\r\n<p><strong>When we got to the end of our trip, we were so amazed at how smoothly everything went and it was all thanks to Peru for Less.</strong> They really have excellent local vendors that made the trip amazing. Also, prior to the trip, Matt was helpful in nailing down our schedule and helping us to experience as much as possible in the time we had. All of our communication was done via email and his response turnaround was great. I don\'t think we went more than a day without an answer to any question.</p>\r\n','Emiliy and Geoff (Minneapolis, Minnesota, USA)<br/>\r\nTraveled to: Lima, Iquitos, Cusco & Machu Picchu \r\n','','','\"From the moment we arrived to our departure from Cusco, Peru For Less took care of us.\"',100055,0,0,NULL,'2014-09-10 23:08:24',NULL),(776,1,'Kristina,','<p>We are currently in Cusco.  Machu Picchu was very interesting and it was worth the trouble. I want to thank you and your staff for your wonderful attention and details. I have recommended Peru For Less to others.</p>\r\n \r\n<p>Please tell Suzanne from Cusco that the Inca restaurant in Aguas Calientes was wonderful.  Great food and fantasticatmosphere. We didn\'t want to leave.</p>\r\n \r\n<p>Thanks again, </p>\r\n','Jan and Patrick <br/> \r\nUSA<br/>\r\nLima, Cusco &amp; Machu Picchu \r\n','','','',414,0,0,NULL,NULL,NULL),(777,1,'Dear Staci,','<p>Thanks so much for your responses to our questions.  It has been great working with you to finalize all the details for this trip.  We really appreciate your thorough and timely responses throughout the process.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Best regards,</p>\r\n','Payal <br/>\r\nLima, Cuzco, Machu Picchu, Puerto Maldonado\r\n','','','',414,0,0,NULL,NULL,NULL),(778,1,'Hi Riva,','<p>We just wanted to thank you for all your help with our trip. Here we are at Iguazu Falls which is truly a world wonder. Waking up and seeing them from the Sheraton was something special. Another highlight of our trip was of course Machu Picchu. Thank you for booking us in to El Mapi Hotel. We were very happy with the Matrimonial deluxe suite and the staff was exceptional. Your team of guides was fantastic especially in Peru, Fernando, Fabio, Jimmy & Carmen in Buenos Aires. I have recommended your company to friends and we would have no hesitation in using your company again.</p>','Lynn &amp; Tim <br/>\r\nSydney, Australia<br/>\r\n#8 World Wonders\r\n','','','',740,0,0,NULL,NULL,NULL),(779,1,'Dear Kelly,','<p>Thanks a lot for making our first trip to South America a success. It was tiring once we got back home. But we enjoyed the whole experience very much. Dinner & Tango night in Buenos Aires was great. All the guides and drivers were very good. I must add that Nemicio in La Paz was outstanding. The Iguazu Falls and Machu Picchu were definitely the highlights. The train trip was enjoyable too. Of all the hotels, we really liked the location in Machu Picchu. On the way back to Cusco, we changed the train to an earlier train and were a bit disappointed that even after paying US $ 13.00 each extra, the train had fewer facilities.</p>\r\n \r\n<p>ll in all, we had a memorable journey.</p>\r\n \r\n<p>Thanks a lot to you & your team.</p>\r\n \r\n<p>Regards,</p>\r\n','Kithsiri <br/>\r\nRio, Iguazu Falls, Buenos Aires, Santiago de Chile, Lima, Cuzco, Machu Picchu, Lake Titicac & La Paz\r\n','','','',414,0,0,NULL,NULL,NULL),(780,1,'Thank you Rylee!','<p>We had a great time in Peru!  Everything was simply perfect, well organized, from beginning to end.  Our tour guides were excellent. Macchu Picchu was amazing! We learned, and experienced a great deal! Thank you for being so efficient, and helping us plan such a memorable experience.  I look forward to booking another tour with Latin America for Less. </p>','Melissa <br/>\r\nWest Orange, NJ<br/>\r\nLima, Cuzco &amp; Machu Picchu\r\n','','','',739,0,0,NULL,NULL,NULL),(781,1,'Hi Rylee,','<p>I had a great trip and I am thankful that you did such a wonderful job putting it together for me. As someone traveling alone, and someone who was traveling to Peru for the first time, I was a little concerned about how all the details of the trip would play out. To my delight, the trip was a very polished experience with only one major issue caused by myself. I accidentally left my camera in a taxi in Puno. On my bus ride from Puno to Cusco my tour guide was nice enough to call the travel agency for me. They found my camera and arranged for it to be brough to Cusco on the bus the next day. I was so thrilled when I received it and I am eternally grateful to get my memories back! Thanks again for the wonderful trip and I wish you the best.</p>\r\n \r\n<p>Sincerely,</p>\r\n','Craig <br/>\r\nCharlottesville, VA<br/>\r\nLima, Arequipa, Colca Canyon, Lake Titicaca, Cuzco, &amp; Machu Picchu \r\n','','','',414,0,0,NULL,NULL,NULL),(782,1,'Hi Kristina,','<p>Our trip was wonderful! Initially I had some doubts about arranging the trip through a tour company as I was afraid it would be too rigidly structured and that we would simply be packed onto a bus with 50 other foreigners and shipped from one sight to another with a limited time to explore. My doubts were unfounded - the experience we had was amazing!</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Caitlyn\'s friendly face was a sight for travel-weary eyes when we arrived in Cusco. She was punctual, informed and briefed us on our itinerary thoroughly, answering all of our questions and giving us some great tips on places to eat and things to see. Our hotel in Cusco, Casa Andina San Blas was GREAT! The accommodations were central, comfortable and left little for want. The staff there was fantastic as well: they spoke English but encouraged my rusty Spanish with patience and good humor.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>The trip to Aguas Calientes went smoothly and we enjoyed the train ride immensely! Our accommodations at Inti Inn were very comfortable and the staff there was delightful as well. Our guide for Macchu Picchu, Fabricio, was very well-informed, kept a great pace, and communicated an exciting passion for the site.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Our travel to Puerto Maldonado and the Selva beyond was also great! The boat ride to Refugio Amazonas was such an exciting way to enter the jungle. Refugio Amazonas was like an oasis in the jungle, and when we arrived we were greeted by friendly smiles, icy-cold towels for our faces and sweet lemonade. The accommodations were tranquil and our jungle itinerary was packed with adventure. Our guide, Johan, was knowledgeable and tireless. He had a wonderful sense of people and made everyone feel included. The food at Refugio was also delicious, produced largely from the local geography.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Our accommodations in Lima at Hotel Allpa were stellar. There was some sort of mix up and we ended up with a lovely suite! What a happy error and great way to be pampered at the end of our stay.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>All in all, our trip to Peru was unmarred by any travel mishaps and we were able to really enjoy ourselves without worries about any of the arrangements thanks to the folks at Peru For Less. I would strongly recommend Peru For Less to anyone planning to travel to Latin America. They are very friendly, professional and knowledgeable. Now I only wish there was a European counterpart!</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Thanks again Kristina for all your quick, tidy work. We really did have a blast! </p>\r\n\r\n<p>Many thanks,</p>\r\n','Sarah <br/>\r\nSan Francisco, USA<br/>\r\nLima, Cusco &amp; Puerto Maldonado \r\n','','','',738,0,0,NULL,NULL,NULL),(783,1,'Riva,','<p>I wanted to thank you so much for all you did for me while I was in Peru. I knew right from the beginning I was in the hands of professionals and that I was going to get so much out of this trip. Please know that I noticed every time you went above and beyond your job. Thanks again to you and everyone.</p>','Barbara <br/>\r\nMD, USA<br/>\r\nLima &amp; Cusco \r\n','','','',414,0,0,NULL,NULL,NULL),(784,1,'hi peruforless,','<p>We had a fabulous trip and I would recommend your services to others traveling to Peru. That being said, here\'s some feedback for you.</p>\r\n \r\n<p>All of the transfers worked wonderfully. We had a delayed flight from Puerto Maldonado -- about three hours. Julio was still waiting for us when we arrived. Unfortunately we basically missed the city tour with a guide. However, Julio, the driver, took us through the central area so we could get a peak and then took us to Miraflores for dinner. After a quick dinner we joined another pickup on the way back to the airport. Julio patched this arrangement together for us. It was interesting since he didn\'t speak English and my Spanish is barely passable. I butcher the language but generally get my question or point across. I can\'t say enough about Julio accommodating us.  He was outstanding.</p>\r\n \r\n<p>All the hotels were very nice with wonderful breakfasts. I would highly recommend them.</p>\r\n \r\n<p>Suzana in Cusco was really helpful. She recommended a number of sights and restaurants. We ate following her recommendations and were never disappointed. She was great. The day tours in Cusco were nice and I think Rony did a nice job. </p>\r\n \r\n<p>The Inca Trail company did a wonderful job. As you may know, we had one member of our group that wasn\'t capable of walking the entire trail. Jose adjusted the trip for her so she could hike the first day, return with one porter, and then meet us at Machu Picchu. It worked really well for all involved. We had requested a guide with birding knowledge. Jose knew some birds, but a little more birding experience on his part would have been nice. On the day we went over the pass (day two) we didn\'t have lunch until we got to camp at about 4:00. There was a snack on the trail but it was a long day. I told this to Suzana too. Otherwise, the hike was great. Jose and all the porters were exceptionally friendly. The food was delicious. The overall service was wonderful. It may be that we had a warm spell. If had to pack over again, I would have brought shorts to hike in and more short-sleeve T-shirts. I had too much warm gear.</p>\r\n  \r\n<p>The Posada Amazonas in Puerto Maldonado was really nice.   We weren\'t quite prepared for the lack of electricity.  I\'m not sure if you could have given us more info up front or we were so focused on packing for the Inca Trail that we didn\'t think it through well. Oscar, our guide, was an excellent birder. He knew the calls, had an iPod to draw them in and was exactly what wanted. When we met him at the airport he asked if we had a spotting scope. We didn\'t bring one because we were led to believe that he would have one. In the end it didn\'t matter too much since a majority of the birds were at close quarters where a scope doesn\'t help. All the people there were friendly, and the food was wonderful. This place was perfect for birding and to see something more in Peru. We\'re very glad you suggested it.</p>\r\n \r\n<p>The overall trip was wonderful and we only had minor issues.  Again, I would recommend your service to anyone planning a trip to Peru.</p>\r\n \r\n<p>Thanks,</p>\r\n','Hampton <br/>\r\nVA, USA<br/>\r\nLima, Cusco, Inca Trail, Machu Picchu & Puerto Maldonado \r\n','','','',414,0,0,NULL,NULL,NULL),(785,1,'Hi Kristina,','<p>The trip was outstanding. Everybody in the group truly enjoyed themselves. It was an exhausting adventure but well worth it. I think the altitude in Puno hit us and myself particularly, pretty hard. But we had a great time none the less. All of our transfers, except Puno, worked out extremely well. Suzan was great and she had a fantastic personality. She made all of us feel extremely welcome when we reached Cusco and she gave us very helpful information on restaurants, markets, etc to visit while in Cusco. I loved Cusco. </p>\r\n\r\n<p>Fabricio also did an outstanding job during our private tour of Machu Picchu. Brian and I were able to spend some time going through Machu Picchu, after we visited the Sun Gate, prior to our tour. Fabricio pointed out so many wonderful details and provided great history that we didnâ??t, and never would have picked up on our own while going through the ruins. Lauralee, Deb, and Ted were able to go out on Lake Titicaca for the overnighter. They said they really enjoyed it and were happy they did it. The rest of us managed to make it to Uros despite being ill. It was a great experience all around. Everyone in the group was happy that Peru For Less was involved. It freed us up to simply enjoy our trip, confident that the details were taken care of for us. </p>\r\n\r\n<p>Thank you for all of your help in setting  up this trip Kristina. You were very enjoyable to work with and you made our Peru experience considerably better than it otherwise would have been. Thank you very much!</p>\r\n','Steven <br/>\r\nPA, USA<br/>\r\nMachu Picchu & Lake Titicaca\r\n','','','',414,0,0,NULL,NULL,NULL),(786,1,'Dear Kelly,','<p>We had a WONDERFUL time. Your charming Peru For Less representative in Cuzco met us and served us coca tea immediately on arrival at the hotel (for the altitude), briefed us on our itinerary, and got us set up comfortably in the hotel. We were totally enthralled with Machu Picchu and the raft trip was great; both greatly exceeded expectations. </p>\r\n\r\n<p>It was great having your representative meet us very early in the morning, have our tickets for the return flight ready for us,  escort us all the way to security, and bid us a genuinely fond farewell. It was a great positive surprise to find that the tour in Lima was private and the guide was very knowledgeable.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>I can\'t say enough for the tour guides at Machu Picchu and on the raft trip.  The Machu Picchu guide was exceptionally considerate. He insisted frequently from the very start that we go slowly, that he lend me a hand on the steps and rough places and he even insisted on carrying my large heavy purse. He was very knowledgeable answering all of our many questions; I would highly recommend him to any future visitors. The raft trip guide was also very experienced, managing to negotiate us through what were for me frightening but exciting rapids; Jessica was probably of some help in the rowing, but I doubt that I was. </p>\r\n\r\n<p>Thanks again for all you did to make our trip so wonderful and for being so gracious and patient with all my questions. </p>\r\n','Jane <br/>\r\nMO, USA<br/>\r\nLima, Cusco, and Machu Picchu\r\n','','','',414,0,0,NULL,NULL,NULL),(787,1,'hi Peruforless,','<p>At the end of October 2010, we decided to take advantage of a free week in December between family events in New York City, to travel to Machu Picchu. After we looked into the possible itinerary, we knew that we needed a professional and experienced travel company that could make this trip a reality given our limitation of time.  During an internet search of travel companies in Peru, I discovered Peru For Less. They advertised a 4-day tour, which, on the last day, included a trip to Machu Picchu.  When we read the itinerary proposed b Peru For Less, it seemed that someone in the company had designed the trip especially for us.  Obviously, Peru For Less has had many one-week customers, eager to see as much as possible in a short time.</p>\r\n \r\n<p>We dealt with Kelly Chrystal who was assigned to us and who, from our very first e-mail correspondence, seemed like a perfect fit.  Kelly saw to every detail of our trip and even made suggestions on how best to prepare for it.  When we told her we were vegetarians, Kelly immediately e-mailed us a list of what turned out to be wonderful vegetarian restaurants in Cusco, which was our home base.  Each restaurant we tried was better than the next.  Kelly also sent us reminders and updates throughout our planning stages and by the time we made our final payment (also done very easily through PayPal), we felt that our every need was attended to.  A tribute to Kelly and to Peru For Less is that we never made one phone call to check up on or to change our itinerary.  </p>\r\n \r\n<p>When we got to Peru, we were met at the airport by another Peru For Less representative, Suzannah, who immediately made us feel welcome.  Our luggage did not make it from Lima to Cusco on the day we arrived, but thanks to Suzannah\'s follow-up, our suitcases were delivered to our room at Casa Andina Catedral Hotel the next morning. Hint: we always travel with at least one change of clothes in our carry-ons.</p>\r\n \r\n<p>Our guides, selected by Peru For Less were all English-speakers and very knowledgeable about their country.  We fell in love with Cusco and with Incan history.  Every minute of our 4 days was filled and everything ran like clockwork.  Since we are rather seasoned travelers, we know how much work goes into planning and carrying out an itinerary that is adhered to, minute by minute.  At no time, however, did we feel rushed or under pressure.  The guides were all willing to stop to expand on the history, culture or importance of a particular place if we requested that they do so.  Every guide was willing to stop to let us take photographs and at least 2 of the guides actually helped us get the best pictures we could, given the light and the subject.</p>\r\n \r\n<p>The trip to Agua Calientes and Machu Picchu was memorable and we were amazed at how wonderful the train ride was; we both agreed that the train trip was worth the price of the entire trip.</p>\r\n \r\n<p>We cannot praise Peru For Less enough and Kelly Chrystal in particular for enabling us to enjoy a short but unforgettable vacation.  We wholeheartedly recommend Peru For Less. </p>\r\n','Marcia and Jim <br/>\r\nNY, USA\r\nCusco &amp; Machu Picchu \r\n','','','',414,0,0,NULL,NULL,NULL),(788,1,'Dear Peruforless,','<p>We really, really enjoyed our trip! Your staff in Peru was great - always on time, and helpful. We really enjoyed the experience. This was the first time we used a travel agency and plan to use one for all our future international travels. The Inca trail was amazing. The food and services were above our expectations. I would suggest using that agency in the future.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>The only thing we\'d change is to spend some time in Lima (cutting out the day at the base of Machu Picchu). </p>\r\n\r\n<p>All the hotels were good. The one in Puno was acceptable but noisy (Eco Inn). </p>\r\n\r\n<p>We hope to use your service in the future to see other parts of South America. </p>\r\n\r\n<p>Thanks!</p>\r\n','Scott <br/>\r\nUSA<br/>\r\nCusco, Inca Trail, Machu Picchu, Puno, Lake Titicaca &amp; Paracas\r\n','','','',414,0,0,NULL,NULL,NULL),(789,1,'Dear Kelly,','<p>I have returned from my South American holiday in one piece and with some wonderful memories. It was an amazing holiday. Having now recovered from Christmas, I would like to thank you and Peru For Less for all the work and effort you put in to make my South American adventure such a memorable experience.  </p>\r\n\r\n<p>My travel itinerary was quite extensive and involved a significant amount of planning to gather together all the travel, hotel and tour arrangements.  Not only did you help and assist at the planning stage you were also extremely helpful during the trip when a few things started to go wrong with my plans due to circumstances outside of your remit.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Again I would like to thank you for all the effort you put into the itinerary and for answering the endless questions I have asked.  My friend Marcelle thinks you are wonderful after she emailed you while I was away.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>In the end, I had a wonderful holiday and I would like to thank you personally and also the competent team at Peru for Less.  </p>\r\n\r\n<p>Kind regards,</p>\r\n','Chris <br/>\r\nUSA<br/>\r\nRio de Janeiro, Puerto Iguazu, Buenos Aires &amp; Cusco \r\n','','','',414,0,0,NULL,NULL,NULL),(790,1,'Hi Staci,','<p>Thanks for your email.  We had a great time and everything was very smooth, except for a delay from Lima to Cusco.  We had a great time and really enjoyed all of the hotels and guides.</p>','Ben  & Debbie  <br/>\r\nPA, USA\r\nLima, Cusco &amp; Machu Picchu \r\n','','','',414,0,0,NULL,NULL,NULL),(791,1,'Hi Kelly,','<p>Thanks for checking. We had an absolutely wonderful trip. We really appreciated your help. We were superbly happy and satisfied with the plan that you had arranged. Hotels were great, and food was excellent. Our guides were excellent, they were on time, very cordial, fluent in English, and very knowledgeable. We are really happy about our trip. I would love to refer my friends to you anytime for any trips.</p>\r\n \r\n<p>Thanks again.</p>\r\n','Ishrat <br/>\r\nLima, Cusco &amp; Machu Picchu \r\n','','','',414,0,0,NULL,NULL,NULL),(792,1,'Hi Kelly,','<p>Overall, it was a really great trip. The tours, hotels, and guides were greatâ??especially on my birthday. I highly recommend Sayri as a spiritual guide for Machu Picchuâ??that was THE highlight of the whole trip. </p>\r\n\r\n<p>All of the transfers worked smoothly up until Lima, when it started to get a little unclear and I had to call the emergency line to find out when I would be picked up the following day for tours and transfers to the airport, confirmation of flights, tickets, etc. In Puno, the transfers picked back up again and were clear for the most part straight through to the end of the trip in Santiago. </p>\r\n\r\n<p>In Cuzco, I have to really give it to the woman who handled my itinerary. She laid it out for me beautifully, walked me through each day, told me when to be ready, when to use the tickets she gave me and when she would supply paper tickets vs. electronic, etc. Very thorough. If that had happened again in Lima and someone had walked me through the rest of the Peru portion, it would have been a flawless experience. Not the end of the world though and again, I absolutely loved the content of the tours, the guides, etc. Awesome trip to Peru!</p>\r\n\r\n<p>As far as Chile, the only real annoyance was day 2 in Santiago when I had a full-day tour of Valparaiso and the wineryâ?¦30 person bus was a total nightmare, and the guide really only spoke Spanish. Really not great. Otherwise, Santiago and Easter Island were fantastic. </p>\r\n\r\n<p>I would love to work with you guys again. Happy New Year!</p>\r\n','Rebecca <br/>\r\nUSA\r\nLima, Cusco, Machu Picchu, Lake Titicaca, Ica, Nazca, Santiago, Valparaiso &amp; Easter Island \r\n','','','',414,0,0,NULL,NULL,NULL),(793,1,'Hi Rylee,','<p>I just got back to Hong Kong and back at work. You were fantastic in helping us arrange this trip. It was well planned and accommodated all our needs. Furthermore, your prompt and diligent attention helped make the trip easy and enjoyable. All of our tours and hotels were fantastic. I would highly recommend Peru For Less to all my friends. </p>\r\n\r\n<p>Happy New Year!</p>\r\n','Meng and Robert <br/>\r\nHong Kong, China\r\nIquitos, Cusco, Inca Trail, Machu Picchu &amp; Lima\r\n','','','',414,0,0,NULL,NULL,NULL),(794,1,'Hi Kelly,','<p>I\'ve already recommended your agency to several people. I was a bit leery because I found you on the internet and knew nothing about you guys. We did not get top level hotels and they were all fabulous. The pickups and attentiveness were really wonderful to experience. We lost our baggage and everyone made an effort to help us out. If not for your agency\'s help I don\'t believe we would have got them until we\'d been there for a week! The food was terrific in Peru. </p>\r\n\r\n<p>There is nothing anyone could have doneto make it better! Thanks again for all your high quality efforts. My son and I had a terrific time!</p>\r\n','Rhoda <br/>\r\nPittsburg, USA\r\nArequipa, Cusco &amp; Machu Picchu \r\n','','','',414,0,0,NULL,NULL,NULL),(795,1,'Dear Rylee, ','<p>I can\'t thank you enough for a wonderful holiday. I was so impressed with the organization of your company - always on time, no issues or problems etc. You were truly amazing getting everything set up so quickly. </p>\r\n\r\n<p>Thank you so much, Rylee for making this journey spectacular! I missed all the storms, and the weather held up. I was so afraid that something would go wrong and I would miss the mountain!</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Warm regards,</p>\r\n','Kathy \r\nUSA\r\nLima &amp; Cusco \r\n','','','',414,0,0,NULL,NULL,NULL),(796,1,'Matt,','<p>We found Peru For Less by searching on the web for travel companies that did a lot of business in Peru.  Well, we did our homework on Peru For Less and on the sites we wanted to see in Peru and couldnâ??t be happier with both of our choices!</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Our travels took us to Cusco, the Sacred Valley, Machu Picchu, the floating islands in Lake Titicaca and Lima.  Peru For Less arranged for guides at each of these locations and we were extremely impressed with the knowledge, language skills and friendliness of each of them.  You also did an excellent job helping us select hotels and arrange for all transfers.  Not one guide was late.  They had all the necessary tickets and boarding passes and also helped coordinate the next leg of our trip.  </p>\r\n\r\n<p>We wanted to thank you and the entire Peru For Less team for their seamless coordination of our family vacation.  From your city representatives meeting us in the airport when we arrived to the guides and drivers at each of our destinations, your team did not miss a beat.  Peru For Less worked with us on putting together a personalized itinerary that worked perfectly for our family. </p>\r\n\r\n<p>Please share our thanks to your team and we would highly recommend Peru For Less to any travelers looking for a great travel agency in Peru.</p>\r\n','The \r\nMilwaukee, WI, USA\r\nLima, Cusco, Machu Picchu &amp; PuÃ±o\r\n','','','',414,0,0,NULL,NULL,NULL),(797,1,'Hi Kelly,','<p>Overall, it was a really great trip. The tours, hotels, and guides were greatâ??especially on my birthday. I highly recommend Sayri as a spiritual guide for Machu Picchuâ??that was THE highlight of the whole trip. </p>\r\n\r\n<p>All of the transfers worked smoothly up until Lima, when it started to get a little unclear and I had to call the emergency line to find out when I would be picked up the following day for tours and transfers to the airport, confirmation of flights, tickets, etc. In Puno, the transfers picked back up again and were clear for the most part straight through to the end of the trip in Santiago. </p>\r\n\r\n<p>In Cuzco, I have to really give it to the woman who handled my itinerary. She laid it out for me beautifully, walked me through each day, told me when to be ready, when to use the tickets she gave me and when she would supply paper tickets vs. electronic, etc. Very thorough. If that had happened again in Lima and someone had walked me through the rest of the Peru portion, it would have been a flawless experience. Not the end of the world though and again, I absolutely loved the content of the tours, the guides, etc. Awesome trip to Peru!</p>\r\n\r\n<p>As far as Chile, the only real annoyance was day 2 in Santiago when I had a full-day tour of Valparaiso and the wineryâ?¦30 person bus was a total nightmare, and the guide really only spoke Spanish. Really not great. Otherwise, Santiago and Easter Island were fantastic. </p>\r\n\r\n<p>I would love to work with you guys again. Happy New Year!</p>\r\n','Rebecca <br/>\r\nUSA\r\nLima, Cusco, Machu Picchu, Lake Titicaca, Ica, Nazca, Santiago, Valparaiso & Easter Island \r\n','','','',414,0,0,NULL,NULL,NULL),(798,1,'Hi Rylee, ','<p>I had a fantastic trip.  I am still traveling on business now and I will be sure to write you more of a glowing testimonial, but for now all I can say is THANK YOU. You really hassled to get the confirmations in order for me to get my visa information all together. You were quick to respond to all of my emails and all the hotel recommendations were fabulous. The guides were very informative and I never felt unsafe traveling on my own. </p>\r\n\r\n<p>Thank you again for all of your help in planning a terrific vacation. I have already recommended you to all my friends. </p>\r\n','Jenny <br />China\r\nSao Paulo, Lima, Nazca, Paracas, Arequipa, Colca Canyon, Lake Titicaca, Cusco, Macu Picchu & Puerto Maldonado \r\n','','','',415,0,0,NULL,NULL,NULL),(799,1,'Dear Kelly, ','<p>We are nearing the end of the part of our trip organized by you and it is therefore the proper moment for an evaluation. You will have realized by now that we represent an upper market segment of your customer base, possibly spoiled but certainly experienced. On that basis we give you an absolute ten for your organization, flexibility and choice of Hotels. </p>\r\n\r\n<p>All absolutely perfect, although you may drop the adjective â??For Less\" in our case. The way you adjusted to our sudden change of plans was, unexpectedly, perfect. Apart from the genuine compliments, and certainly our recommendations to our circle of friends to contact you for their travel plans in this part of the world, I have a small, positive criticism. </p>\r\n\r\n<p>I realize that you booked us on the luxury train ride from Cusco to Aqua Caliente and that the return trip on that tourist train was scheduled for most tourists at 16.00 hours. However as we had time on our hands, returning only the following day, you should have informed us of the various possibilities. I realize that other trains serve less service and we did have tremendous fun in the one carriage train with the fashion show. I realize that it may be somewhat difficult to anticipate every ones personal preferences but a more elaborate lay-out of the possibilities would have helped us, although at the end everything turned out perfect, which was the comment I started with.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>With kind regards </p>\r\n','Brundt and Lily  \r\nUSA\r\nCusco, Machu Picchu &amp; Lima\r\n','','','',415,0,0,NULL,NULL,NULL),(800,1,'Hi Kristina','<p>We had a wonderful time in Peru, from Paracas to Ollantaytambo, Machu Picchu,  Cusco and Lima.  The drivers and guides were always on time, helpful and friendly.  I even got to improve my Spanish with Paul in Paracas, Jaime in Cusco and Julio in Lima.  And Caitlin and Christina in your Cusco and Agua Calientes offices were great as well.  </p>\r\n\r\n<p>The hotels we picked out together were wonderful. La Hacienda in Paracas was so relaxing as a starting place to unwind and the Parikatumbo in Ollantaytambo was beautiful with magnificent gardens and its setting surrounded by the mountains.  This is the first trip that we have not planned and done ourselves, and I have to admit that the relaxation of knowing that everything was planned for us was a luxury.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Thanks again for your responsiveness in the planning process and your staff\'s availability while we were in Peru. </p>\r\n','Joan and Stephen \r\nUSA\r\nLima, Paracas, Cusco, Sacred Valley &amp; Machu Picchu \r\n','','','',415,0,0,NULL,NULL,NULL),(801,1,'Hello Matt,','<p>Our trip to Peru was great. All of the services provided by Peru for Less including travel, guides, accommodations, etc. were excellent. We were pleasantly surprised everyday by what we experienced. Peru is a beautiful place to visit.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Thank you for the great service,</p>\r\n','Chuck \r\nLima, Cusco &amp; Machu Picchu \r\n','','','',415,0,0,NULL,NULL,NULL),(802,1,'Dear Riva,','<p>We were extremely pleased with the tour package Peru for Less, and specifically Riva, put together for us.  The travel schedule was detailed, printed so we could understand it, and was our companion every day at both breakfast and dinner.  Never having visited Peru or South America, we did not know quite what to expect; but felt very comfortable traveling around the country, and in good hands with our drivers and guides.  </p>\r\n\r\n<p>The three highlights of the trip for us were a visit to Machu Picchu, which took our breath away with its grandeur; a visit to a 3 generation family of weavers for an Alpaca wool spinning, dying and weaving demonstration; and the short boat tour to the Ballestas Islands, loaded with birds and wildlife.  We loved the cuisine, the Pisco sours, the expertise of our guides who knew virtually everything about their subjects; and above all, the welcoming people of Peru.</p>\r\n','Rick & Ann \r\nSaratoga, CA\r\nCusco, Paracas &amp; Huacachina \r\n','','','',415,0,0,NULL,NULL,NULL),(803,1,'Dear Peru For Less,','<p>Our trip to Peru was done without a lot of planning. We wavered a lot between a few different destinations and finally settled on Peru. As such we were rather apprehensive on how good the trip was going to be...</p>\r\n\r\n<p>But, it turned out to be a fantastic trip, one of the best vacations we took in a long time. </p>\r\n\r\n<p>Highlights of the trip - hands down - Cusco, Sacred Valley, Machu Picchu and the train ride to Puno.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Signing up with you Peru For Less was the BEST DECISION we made... They even customized one of their packages to suit the timelines we had and our tastes and interest... They ensured that there was someone to welcome us and ease us into each section of the trip. The drivers and guides were fabulous and very knowledgeable... We just had to make sure that we were ready when they came to pick us up. It was that hands off. </p>\r\n\r\n<p>They offer a few different price tiers and hotel types for you to choose from and provide you with a lot of information right from the planning stage - Jennie - You are the best !!!. The tour company is made up of people with a genuine love for travel and other cultures and this makes them really really good at what they do.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>We usually try to do things on our own (at least that is what we did on all our previous vacations). But, this experience has made us re-think that.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>I\'d recommend a trip to Peru to anyone and everyone and if you are going to Peru, I\'d recommend Peru For Less in a heartbeat.</p>\r\n','Shyam & Abitha \r\nCusco, Sacred Valley, Machu Picchu, Puno &amp; Lima\r\n','','','',415,0,0,NULL,NULL,NULL),(804,1,'Dear Kelly,','<p>We have returned to Beijing safely last night, and enjoyed our trip to Peru and Chile very much.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>All of our tours and transfers have worked out well as expected. The only complaint is that either tour guide or driver did not know how to get to Hotel La Casona at Vina Matetic. As a result, we did not reach hotel till 9:30 p.m. on Feb. 3.\r\nWe were very impressed by the tour guide at Machu Picchu, and both Alwin and James at Santiago.\r\nKind regards,</p>\r\n','Gordon \r\nBeijing, China\r\nCusco, Machu Picchu, Santiago & San Pedro de Atacama\r\n','','','',415,0,0,NULL,NULL,NULL),(805,1,'Hi Silvana,','<p>Our time spent in Cusco and the Scared Valley/Machu Picchu was wonderful.  That area of Peru is beautiful.  When we came back to Lima for the last week we took a bus to Pisco and Paracas area.  That was an eye opener.  Such devastation from the earthquake in Pisco and Chincha, unbelieveable.  We stayed at Hacienda Bahia in Paracas and that was wonderful.  </p>\r\n \r\n<p>The services you provided for me were very good.  The flights worked out well for us.  Our changes we made flying earlier to Cusco, we were able to make at a Star Peru office in Puerto Maldonado, so that was easy.  I guess if I had known about the services your company provides I would have used you assistance more, but we had most of the trip booked by the time I had you book my flights. Next time.  </p>\r\n<p>Chau,</p>\r\n','Joni \r\nAlberta, Canada\r\nLima, Puerto Maldonado, Cusco\r\n','','','',415,0,0,NULL,NULL,NULL),(806,1,'Dear Staci,','<p>Well, our overall impression is very good! We are impressed with the good organization, the documentation is superb, times are met, and everybody is very polite. Especially we like our wonderful instructor, Arnold, who shows very good knowledge, speaks fluent English and is clear, nice, and acts with courtesy and wisdom. </p>\r\n\r\n<p>One thing bothers us, however. The level of the hotel is not the level that we are used to. Although the hotel is located very good and is structured very nice overall, and has a pool and a garden and the hosts are polite, we received a room that does not meet our expectations whatsoever. First of all, toilet and bathroom are in a bad condition, the bed is narrow and rocking, there is no heating, lamps are broken and maintenance is poor. </p>\r\n\r\n<p>In addition, one thing that bothers us is that in the same hotel there other rooms which are at a higher level, newer and better. It is true that we did not seek a luxurious hotel because we wanted to save, yet for $ 350 per day one would have expected better conditions, at least one would expect a comfortable place to sleep. A narrow and rocking bed is certainly not acceptable to us.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>We already wanted to update you but we didn\'t have internet until now. The great news is that from that moment on everything was really perfect. We had great two days in Colca Canyon and despite the rain yesterday afternoon we saw a lot and enjoyed everything the area as well as our guide Elisabeth and the really good driver. </p>\r\n\r\n<p>Our hotel in Puno looks perfect as we just arrived. </p>\r\n\r\n<p>Best regards,</p>\r\n','Danny &amp; Elinor \r\nIsrael\r\nArequipa, Puno &amp; Lake Titicaca, Cusco &amp; Machu Picchu \r\n','','','',415,0,0,NULL,NULL,NULL),(807,1,'Dear Peru For Less,','<p>Peru: it was the experience of a lifetime.  After our stay in Miraflores and exploring Lima, our journey began to see Peru in its most awesome form.  </p>\r\n\r\n<p>First, I must say that having Peru For Less organize our travel was the best thing we did as on arrival at the airports there was always a contact there to let us know what was happening, whether it was by car or plane the same process was followed.  Also the pick-ups were clockwork, always on time.  The hotels were spot-on with great breakfasts and lots to choose from on the dinner menu, although you don\'t want to order soup and a main course, it\'s just too much!</p>\r\n  \r\n<p>Upon arrival in Puno, we were greeted by our guide who was with us the entire time we were there.  He made suggestions to keep the altitude problem to a minimum, lots of coca tea, which I continuously drank. It may have helped but I didn\'t notice!  However, we took the two hour boat ride to Isla Taquile and enjoyed our tour there.  While on the island, the sun came out and the scenery was magnificent. The hike to the top was a little challenging but everyone got there.  We had a wonderful lunch and heard a bit about the history which was quite interesting.  We then went to Isla Uros where we saw the reed islands and the boats were Kon Tiki - style, made of reeds. It was quite a day.  </p>\r\n\r\n<p>We got to Cusco two days later and our representative was waiting for us at the airport.  Edgar, what an amazing gentleman, teaches history and architecture, and our two days with him was a lesson on Peru and its history, totally enjoyable.  Cusco is a wonderful city and the cathedral in particular was impressive. Having our private guide made it so much more interesting.  The next day, we left Cusco for the Sacred Valley and the scenery was phenomenal, but that\'s everywhere in Peru.  We visited the Pisac market and the Ollantaytambo fortress and got another history lesson on how the Incas managed to move the rocks up the mountains to assemble them with such accuracy.  </p>\r\n\r\n<p>Our last full day finally took us to Machu Picchu.  Even the train ride to Aguas Calientes was quite enthralling with the river at its highest.  Machu Picchu is, to say the least, an amazing place. It leaves one in awe of the magnitude of the Incas and how they managed nature. We should take some lessons from them.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>We had one incident after our Machu Picchu trip, when the train was very late getting us back to Ollantaytambo, and when we arrived, no one was there to take us back to our hotel. But we called our main contact and she organized a pick up for us at 11 o\'clock at night. As I said, there was always someone we could call on for assistance.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Thanks Peru For Less, it was a wonderful adventure.</p>\r\n','Derek &amp; Yvonne <br />\r\nToronto, Canada<br/>\r\nPuno, Cusco, Sacred Valley &amp; Machu Picchu <br/>\r\n','','','',741,0,0,NULL,NULL,NULL),(808,1,'Jennie,','<p>Our trip to Peru was fantastic. We had a marvelous time and did not want to come home. What a beautiful country with friendly people and a unique culture. All our tour guides were tremendous and our drivers were all punctual. We felt spoiled. Our hotels were all great and some were fabulous. If we were to return we would book into Las Casitas del Colca and Sol y Luna for 4 or 5 days.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>We also appreciated how quickly you took care of the airline mishap with Star Peru. We don\'t hold you responsible as we met other people who had similar bookings with Star Peru and they were not informed and had to make last minute arrangements. </p>\r\n\r\n<p>The changes were actually positive. Although our tour of Lake Titicaca was shortened it was better, in that with only Henry and us, the visit to Taquile and Uros Island were much more intimate. The trip on the Andean Explorer was marvelous. We loved it and would recommend it to anyone. What a great way to travel.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Thank-you,</p>\r\n','Bob &amp; Barb <br/>\r\nUSA<br/>\r\nLima, Paracas, Nazca, Arequipa, Colca Canyon, Lake Titicaca, Cucso, Sacred Valley &amp; Machu Picchu \r\n','','','',742,0,0,NULL,NULL,NULL),(809,1,'Hi Kelly,','<p>We had 12 great days traveling in Peru, due to perfect organization by Peru For Less.  Our travel advisor Kelly arranged 9 different hotels; transportation by plane, bus, train and car to the various locations and some tours in various locales.  We were always met promptly by friendly and informative agents at each destination.  </p>\r\n\r\n<p>We were able to make two earlier plane flights during our travels and in each city our local guides promptly notified the company to make sure we were met at the right time in the next city.  Kelly even called us during our travels to check in on us.  We liked the hotels, all the travel arrangements and the very nice people who took care of us at each destination.  There were absolutely no problems thanks to their expertise.  Because of this experience, we want to return to South America and look forward to working with them again.   </p>\r\n','Dexter and Shelley <br/>\r\nTuscaloosa, Alabama<br/>\r\nParacas, Nazca, Arequipa, Colca Canyon, Puno, Lake Titicaca, Cusco, Sacred Valley, Machu Picchu &amp; Lima\r\n','','','',743,0,0,NULL,NULL,NULL),(810,1,'Dear Rylee,','<p>I would be pleased to recommend the PFL team to anyone needing travel services.  The execution was flawless.  Each concern I had before leaving was addressed promptly and in a friendly manner as well as questions I had during the tour.  Each team member was in place as promised and had excellent information to share.  I shopped agencies thoroughly before choosing and was happy with my choice.  </p>\r\n\r\n<p>Thank you   </p>\r\n','Cheri <br/>\r\nSullivan, MO<br/>\r\nCusco, Sacred Valley &amp; Machu Picchu \r\n','','','',744,0,0,NULL,NULL,NULL),(811,1,'Dear Rylee,','<p>We enjoyed our trip and our arrangements went without a hitch. Your staff in Cusco was especially helpful monitoring our flight schedule and noting a last minute change which was well communicated to us. Changes in our trip to Machu Picchu included a special trip to our hotel. All of the guides and drivers did an excellent job. The hotel in Cusco was very nice and your staff also made some excellent recommendations for lunch and dinner.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>The hotel in Buenos Aires was also fine, the tango show and the tour guides were good. The hotels in the other locations were also very good and the tour guides in all of the locations were exceptional. Those who met us at the airport were timely and helpful. Our tour guide to Valparaiso, Jose, deserves special mention.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>We will certainly recommend Peru For Less to our friends</p>\r\n','Judy &amp; Gary <br/>\r\nMadison, Wisconsin<br/>\r\nCusco, 2D Inca Trail, Machu Picchu, Rio de Janeiro, Iguazu, Buenos Aires, Puerto Madryn, Ushuaia, Bariloche &amp; Santiago<br/>\r\n','','','',415,0,0,NULL,NULL,NULL),(812,1,'Hi Jennifer,','<p>Hard to believe we have been back from our trip over a week ago now....time sure does fly.  I just wanted to let you know how much I enjoyed it and to thank you for all you did to arrange such a great vacation!  Everything went according to plan and it was wonderful to not have to worry about anything.</p>\r\n \r\n<p>We all really enjoyed Vicky, our tour guide in Quito.  She was great!  Right from the beginning when she was waiting for Craig and me at the airport she took wonderful care of us.  She got us checked in at the hotel and arranged to pick us up for our tours. Each day she was on time and was very patient with our group.  I think sometimes it must have been a bit like \"herding cats\" to keep us all together and moving!  And I know we must have exceeded the timing of the tours, but she was always very patient with us.  We were fortunate to take our tour of the city center on Monday when there was the changing of the guards and she positioned us perfectly to get the best view and take the best photos.  In fact, throughout our time with her she became our photographer and took tons of photos of us in front of all the vistas, so we can prove we really were there!!  Since we were there to have a spanish immersion experience she spoke only Spanish to us and did it slowly enough so we were all able to follow her.  She gave clear descriptions of what we were seeing and had a great knowledge of the area.  But, she did not talk TOO much....that can be as bad as saying too little!!  We were so glad to have her along when we needed to fly from Quito to the Galapagos, that would have been a confusing dash through the airport on our own but she got it all arranged for us so it was very easy.  And here\'s an example of how wonderful she was, she went and visited John (he broke his ankle) in the hospital several times and was able to give us an update when we came back from the Galapagos.  Oh, that\'s right, she made a point of finding us in the airport because she knew we were going to waiting for our flights back to the US and told us about John and gave us chocolates.....what a sweet person!</p>\r\n \r\n<p>The two drivers were excellent (Enrique and Javier) and drove very safely.   We spent more time with Javier so got to know him better but they both were very friendly and helpful.  Javier led us on a wonderful hike up the volcano and he was very careful and encouraging with us on that hike (we were all huffing and puffing!)  We were breathless but had a lot of fun!</p>\r\n \r\n<p>The Hotel Mercure was excellent!!  Somehow we got suites so my rooms were wonderful!!  The breakfast buffet was delicious every morning.. I miss the chocolate croissants!  It was also nice to have the opportunity to try some Ecuadorian specialties each morning.  The staff of the hotel and restaurant were very helpful, polite and always available.  I felt very safe and very well taken care of.  It was also nice that the hotel had computers we could use.  Definitely a great place to stay and a very inexpensive taxi ride to the district with all the restaurants.  </p>\r\n \r\n<p>Our Galapagos tour was also wonderful.  Except for us and our luggage getting absolutely drenched while taking the shuttle boat to Santa Cruz everything with all of our connections worked out great!  The Guantanamera was a good ship and our guide, Marvy, had a lot of energy and gave us a lot of fun tours.  He also spoke both in English and Spanish.  The food on the boat was delicious and they kept us well fed. After the two-room suite at the Hotel Mercure the cabins were of course quite small, but the bathroom and shower were surprisingly spacious.  And since we didn\'t spend much time in the cabins it wasn\'t important. I was glad our cabins were on the main deck, especially the last night when my motion sickness patch seemed to lose its effectiveness!  (I\'ve decided it was a 56 hour patch not a 72 hour patch!!)  The boat had a nice amount of space for relaxing compared with some boats we saw.  It was really nice to have only 14 people on the boat and on our tours.  I will say I was very glad we were not cruising around when the Tsunami was on the way!</p>\r\n \r\n<p>So, again, we had a great time!  Thanks so much for all your work setting up such a fun trip.  This is the third trip I\'ve taken with Peru For Less and they have all been great.</p>\r\n','Marcella <br />\r\nUSA<br/>\r\nQuito, Otavalo, Cotopaxi &amp; Galapagos Islands \r\n','','','',415,0,0,NULL,NULL,NULL),(813,1,'Hi Silvana,','<p>My husband and I prefer independent travel to group tours, but a trip to Cusco & Machu Picchu seemed too much for us to do by ourselves. Peru For Less was the perfect answer to our needs. With the help of their competent and friendly travel advisor, Silvana, we planned a 4-night trip that was like independent travel, but with \'hand holding\'.  </p>\r\n\r\n<p>Peru For Less arranged our flight from Lima to Cusco. We were met in Cusco by a representative who took us to our hotel, explained the details of our stay, recommended restaurants (Cicciolina was great) and gave us all the tickets we needed. She made reminder phone calls for our pickup times. Our tour guides were knowledgeable and professional. We loved our hotels: Hotel Casa San Blas in Cusco and Andina Luxury in Aguas Calientes. Ask for a room by the river. The river was loud, but it was exciting to be near the rushing water in March. </p>\r\n\r\n<p>We had no problems, and Silvana accommodated our request for the exact hotels we wanted (rather than waiting to find out the hotel after paying for the trip). I just wish I had decided to spend an extra day or two in Cusco, as we didnâ??t have enough time to explore there. I\'m happy to recommend Peru For Less.</p>\r\n','Elaine <br />\r\nPennsylvania, USA<br/>\r\nCusco &amp; Machu Picchu \r\n','','','',415,0,0,NULL,NULL,NULL),(814,1,'Dear Peru For Less,','<p>I organized a trip to Machu Picchu within a few days thanks to Peru For Less. Despite the complications caused by my inability to confirm my schedule until the last minute and my request to stay at the Sanctuary Lodge instead of the usual hotels, Jennie at Peru For Less managed to arrange the entire trip for me within one morning. </p>\r\n\r\n<p>She was fantastic - efficient and full of good advice which she patiently provided through a series of over 20 emails. The pick up at the Cusco airport was great and so were all the tours. The send off at the airport by Suzanne was the ribbon on the whole package as she stayed behind until I had checked my luggage in so as to advise me about the things I could do at the airport while waiting for the flight. </p>\r\n\r\n<p>While travel in Peru can be complicated by the weather, PeruRail, and the lack of detailed information, relying on the efficient and experienced employees of Peru For Less helps to minimize the potential inconveniences. </p>\r\n','Michael <br />\r\nSingapore<br />\r\nCusco, Sacred Valley &amp; Machu Picchu \r\n','','','',415,0,0,NULL,NULL,NULL),(815,1,'Hi Matt! ','<p>The trip was very good!!!! </p>\r\n\r\n<p>Your people were real pros. From Susanna (who met us at the Cusco airport, and recommended the best places for dining), to Raul (awesome guy, who took us to Ollantaytambo and Chinchero) and Fabricio who took us to Machu Picchu, all were very friendly and knowledgeable. Unfortunately, I missed the first day\'s tour of Cusco because of a bad case of altitude sickness. However, the staff at Casa San Blas Boutique Hotel was so helpful and accommodating, and I was able to get the needed meds. I was up and about the next day and was able to join Raul\'s tour.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>I am particularly happy about the fact that Raul took us to Chinchero to this family of weavers where we learned about the process of weaving. They showed us how they get the alpaca wool cleaned with this grated root that acts like a detergent, the dyeing process using natural materials, and how the wool is spun and woven. I loved that it was educational instead of just taking us to the market to buy the sweaters and rugs.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Then there was Fabricio, who took us up to Machu Picchu. He was very gracious when someone unreasonably complained that the bus did not immediately depart when they got on it. Fabricio was very calm and pleasant and told them that the bus leaves every 15 minutes, and that we only had to wait for 5 more minutes. He also made sure they got a call to respond to their concerns. </p>\r\n\r\n<p>I chickened out of climbing Huayna Picchu (my knees were starting to hurt after Ollantaytambo and Machu Picchu), but the trip was no less wonderful for that.  </p>\r\n\r\n<p>At Aguas Calientes, accommodations at Casa Andina were equally comfortable. </p>\r\n\r\n<p>Thank you for everything, and please send my thanks to Nick as well. Both of you responded to my emails promptly and thoroughly, so that I felt no qualms at all before coming on this trip.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>I would definitely recommend Peru For Less to my friends. In fact, I already did!</p>\r\n','Diana <br/>\r\nUSA<br/>\r\nCusco &amp; Machu Picchu \r\n','','','',415,0,0,NULL,NULL,NULL),(816,1,'Hi Kelly,','<p>We are now at home.  We loved the trip. Yes, we were disappointed that we did not get to see the Nazca lines, but that could not be helped. The gastronomic tour with Carlos was a huge success. We got to see a few other parts of Lima, in addition to tasting many new fruits and foods, etc.</p>\r\n  \r\n<p>All of the drivers and guides and people we spoke with via phone from Peru For Less were wonderful. We found everyone knowledgeable and helpful.</p>\r\n \r\n<p>The Aranwa hotels were really great, and we really liked Casa Andina Private Collection in Lima.  </p>\r\n\r\n<p>In the future, we hope to plan a trip to Argentina, or Costa Rica, or Panama.  We will certainly use your services again when we travel in Latin America.</p> \r\n<p>Thanks again. </p>\r\n','Jane  &amp; Anthony <br/>\r\nUSA<br/>\r\nLima, Cusco, Sacred Valley, Machu Picchu, Puno &amp; Lake Titicaca, Paracas &amp; Nazca \r\n','','','',415,0,0,NULL,NULL,NULL),(817,1,'Hannah,','<p>It was an excellent trip, we loved it and can only recommend it to anyone else. We had lots of fun and all was very well organized. The food was way above our expectations and so was the overall service and the guide. We were both really happy with the trip. Macchu Picchu is obviously breathtaking. </p>\r\n\r\n<p>Thanks very much for handling the logistics,</p>\r\n\r\nBest regards,\r\n','Johannes <br/>\r\nCalifornia, USA<br/>\r\nInca Trail \r\n','','','',415,0,0,NULL,NULL,NULL),(818,1,'Dear Mari,','<p>Thank you so much for making the arrangements for my trip. I totally enjoyed my vacation in Cusco, Machu Picchu and Lima. The Peruvian people were very friendly, food was great, places were magnificent and I got some great pictures. I strongly hope I can come to Peru again. Thank you again for your assistance.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>There was a smooth flow right from the time I landed in Lima till the drop off back to Lima on the last day. Everything went great except a small delay in airline, which no one can control.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Peru For Less for Exceptionally great!</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Thank You Mari,</p>\r\n','Jag <br />\r\nUSA<br/>\r\nLima, Cusco &amp; Inca Trail </br>\r\n','','','',755,0,0,NULL,NULL,NULL),(819,1,'Kristina,','<p>Our trip to Ecuador and Peru was fantastic. All the planning and arrangements you made for us were just perfect. The schedule was full but not too busy. We never felt rushed and really enjoyed seeing so much. Starting in the Galapagos was great and really got us relaxed and settled in. The wildlife is spectacular. The Odyssey was quite the ship and the service impeccable. Our guide Tatiana was extremely knowledgeable and fun to be with. Every day we looked forward to a new adventure.  </p>\r\n\r\n<p>Moving on to Cusco and Machu Picchu was quite the transition. You go from understanding Darwin and his thoughts to the vortex of an incredible civilization. The Incas were indeed very accomplished and exploring the ruins was fascinating. Our guide David is an expert and really gave us a deep insight into their history. The Andean Explorer to Puno was beautiful.  Passing through La Raya is like a time warp with all the shepherds tending to their flocks of alpaca. Once again the service was just impeccable. Lake Titicaca was another great segment of the trip. The floating islands were incredible. We will never forget Rosa and her family. Taking a ride on a grass reed catamaran is a must.   </p>\r\n\r\n<p>All the transfers, guides, and service were top notch. It is a strong testament to you and your team in providing a great service to travelers like me who enjoy having everything planned out. It was always reassuring to see someone with a sign with our name on it and then whisking us away to our hotel as soon as we arrived. Making sure we maximized our time was important and we would not have been able to do it as well without you.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>I will certainly recommend your service to my friends. I will also be using your services in the future as I plan other adventures in South America.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>All the best,</p>\r\n','Phil and Kate <br />\r\nCalifornia, USA<br />\r\nGalapagos, Cusco &amp; Machu Picchu \r\n','','','',756,0,0,NULL,NULL,NULL),(820,1,'Hi Matt and everyone at Peru For Less,','<p>Our visit to Lima, Cusco and Machu Picchu was just fantastic. A magical experience and one that we will cherish always. First let me say a warm thank you to all the team at Peru For Less who helped me design a wonderful 8 days in Peru. The upfront planning via email was very thorough (thank you Matt) and everything went pretty much according to plan.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>In Cusco were met by Suzanne. Her enthusiasm and passion for Peru was wonderful and she filled us in on what to expect next while driving to the Casa Andina hotel in Cusco town. I have to comment on how great the hotel was and the kindness of the staff there especially Juan Carlos who helped us with our luggage. We then took a tour of the City with Carlos a well versed historian who showed us all the sites including the Sacred Valley.  </p>\r\n \r\n<p>Next we met Edgar our Inca Trail guru, a gift of energy and enthusiasm who was so warm, professional and informative. The Inca trail hike and visit to Machu Picchu were even more meaningful as a result of his knowledgeable of the history and Incan traditions. Additionally the staff and especially porters from \"Wayki Trek\" treated us like family.</p>\r\n \r\n<p>Finally we made it to Macchu Picchu. One word, \'breathtaking\'\', describes the scene. The clouds that had hovered over us in the early morning gradually parted revealing the beautiful site and the ancient ruins were crystal clear. After arriving at Macchu Picchu we were able to take our time and stroll though the ruins.</p>\r\n \r\n<p>Finally we were on our way down to Aguas Calientes. Thank you to all the staff at El Mapi hotel: wonderful location and great service, rooms and meals. I cannot say enough about that.  We even made it to the hot springs for a dip in the warm pool and took some great photos of the Urubamba river.</p>\r\n<p>R\r\nSo to anyone who wants to travel to Macchu Picchu, choose \'Peru For Less\'. We had a wonderful experience and saw all the key sites including Winaywayna (Forever Young), the last urban center before reaching the Sun Gate (Inti Punku). I recommend Peru For Less to all my friends and anyone else interested in visiting Cusco and Machu Picchu. I hope to return to Peru (Lake Titicaca and Amazon) and also visit Ecuador and Bolivia at the same time and would have no hesitation in planning the trip with Peru For Less. </p>\r\n\r\n<p>Matt please extend our gratitude to all involved in making our visit such a lovely experience including, Edgar, Suzanne, all the staff at the hotels and most importantly our guides from Waki Trek too many to mention.  </p>\r\n \r\n<p>Gracias a todos!</p>\r\n','Ita &amp; Dave <br/>\r\nToronto, Canada<br/>\r\nLima, Cusco, 4D Inca Trail &amp; Machu Picchu\r\n','','','',757,0,0,NULL,NULL,NULL),(821,1,'Hi Riva,','<p>We just wanted to thank you for such a wonderfully arranged trip for our recent honeymoon. We couldn\'t have imagined that our trip to Lima, Cusco, the Sacred Valley, Machu Picchu via the abbreviated Inca Trail, and Lake Titicaca could have been any better. Everything went incredibly smoothly, from transfers at airports and train stations to the tours themselves. All of our guides were friendly, professional, proficiently bilingual, and very knowledgeable. Every aspect of the trip was nearly perfect, and we can\'t wait to return to Peru. Typically we travel without the use of a service or agent, but the ease and fluidity of this vacation has converted us. We greatly appreciate all of your help in organizing the trip and your professionalism and responsiveness throughout the process. We look forward to working with you and Peru For Less in the future.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Sincerely,</p>\r\n','Katie and Ben <br />\r\nMaryland, USA<br />\r\nLima, Cusco, Machu Picchu, 2D Inca Trail &amp; Lake Titicaca\r\n','','','',758,0,0,NULL,NULL,NULL),(822,1,'Dear Peru For Less,','<p>The time that I worked with you was great.  I felt confident that I was working with a good company and in your hands, taken care of.  Even the issue of changing my ticket payment from one credit card to another after the fact, went smoothly and without a hitch or a worry.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Thank you for taking such excellent ongoing care of me and for keeping in touch which makes me feel like a valued client.  The entire part of the journey that you prepared for me, from Lima to Cusco return, was perfectly organized. \r\nThank you very much.</p>\r\n','Debra <br/>\r\nOntario, Canada<br/>\r\nFlights Lima - Cusco<br/>\r\n','','','',415,0,0,NULL,NULL,NULL),(823,1,'Silvana,','<p>Our trip was wonderful. All of the transfers worked very well and everyone was punctual. I wanted to give a special commendation for the young man who met us at the airport upon arrival in Lima. The bus station was closed. He worked with his supervisor and he received permission to take my wife and I out to dinner. The Ballestas Islands tour was wonderful - it was just enough for us, not too long of a day. I want to thank you for making all of the arrangements.  You work for a great company and we would definitely use your services again.</p>\r\n \r\n<p>Regards,</p>\r\n','Tom and Patricia <br />\r\nTexas, USA<br />\r\nParacas, Lima\r\n','','','',415,0,0,NULL,NULL,NULL),(824,1,'Dear Aleks,','<p>We did have a wonderful trip to Peru. We loved each part of our trip and often speak very positively about our trip and Peru For Less too.</p>\r\n \r\n<p>I appreciated being able to tailor our trip to our schedule and desires. We felt that all the people we worked with from your office and all over Peru were professional and very helpful. Most everything went off without a hitch and it was so great to get off a bus, train or plane and have someone with a sign there with our name on it. We loved or tours and for the most part our tour guides were very informative and attentive to our needs. Some of the guides were exceptional- David, who took us to the Salt Mines, was one. We learned a lot about the beautiful country of Peru from them and came to appreciate its history and people through their guidance. </p>\r\n \r\n<p>An \"A+\" goes to Susana, the friendly gal in Cusco who explained everything on our rather complicated itinerary very thoroughly so that we really understood what, where and how to do everything. </p>\r\n\r\n<p>All in all, we were very pleased with our trip and have confidence in recommending Peru For Less to our friends and family. There were a couple of problems, but since we had the Peru for Less phone number, we were able to get them figured out, and that was great.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Thanks for all you did.</p>\r\n','Lucy Heyming<br />\r\nUSA<br />\r\nFebruary 10th - February 23rd 2011<br />\r\nLima, Paracas, Nazca, Cusco, Sacred Valley, Machu Picchu, Puno &amp; Lake Titicaca\r\n','','','',415,0,0,NULL,NULL,NULL),(825,1,'Hello Rylee, ','<p>I just wanted to let you know we are having a fabulous time in Peru. We are pleased with all our guides and hotels.  You really pulled this together. I wish we had used you for the whole trip. Thank you for all you did and are doing for us. I have already recommended you to 5 fellow travelers and will be sure to spread the word once I get home. </p>\r\n\r\n<p>Thanks you again!</p>\r\n','Sallie and Carolyn <br />\r\nOklahoma, USA<br />\r\nArequipa, Colca Canyon, Puno, Lake Titicaca, Cusco, Sacred Valley &amp; Machu Picchu \r\n','','','',415,0,0,NULL,NULL,NULL),(826,1,'Hi Rylee,','<p>My trip was outstanding. Everyone on your team was truly fantastic and I would wholeheartedly recommend your company to anyone. </p>','Shaun<br />\r\nNew Jersey, USA<br />\r\nCusco, Inca Trail &amp; Machu Picchu\r\n','','','',415,0,0,NULL,NULL,NULL),(827,1,'Hi Rylee, ','<p>Thank you very much for organizing our trip.  Our guides were all excellent: prompt, friendly and helpful, and we enjoyed our hotels very much. </p>\r\n\r\n<p>Peru surpassed my expectations in many, many ways, and Machu Picchu was simply the most beautiful place I have ever seen. </p>\r\n\r\n<p>I would also have enjoyed tours of the architectural and gold museums in Lima, but my friends were not interested. But those are ideas for the future, and I definitely would love to return.  I am still in a daze from all the amazing Inca architecture and the beauty of the Andes.  I can see why people like to walk the Inca Trail to make the most of the mountains. </p>\r\n\r\n<p>I think Sandra told you that we were extremely lucky with the weather, especially on our day at Machu Picchu.  It was raining in the morning, but when we arrived it turned into a perfect day. </p>\r\n\r\n<p>Thank you for a wonderful holiday! </p>\r\n','Richard <br />\r\nGrenada<br />\r\nLima, Cusco &amp; Machu Picchu \r\n','','','',415,0,0,NULL,NULL,NULL),(828,1,'Hello Rylee,','<p>Thanks, we had a wonderful trip to Peru. We did have a fabulous time and we really appreciate all of your help in the planning process. You were great. </p>\r\n\r\n<p>My only criticism is that we were only able to spend 2 hours in Machu Picchu. The whole purpose of our trip was to visit Machu Picchu, which was magical, and more than lived up to my expectations. </p>\r\n\r\n<p>We spoke to Suzanna your representative in Cusco and she agreed with this, mentioning that when she received our schedule she thought it was tight.  </p>\r\n\r\n<p>The hotels were good, especially the delightful Casa San Blas in Cusco. The Carmel Hotel in Lima is centrally located in a nice area of Miraflores, convenient for shopping and restaurants.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>All your representatives and the hotel staff were very helpful and friendly.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Many thanks for organizing my â??Bucket Listâ? trip, it was an amazing experience.</p>\r\n','Georgina<br />\r\nGrenada<br />\r\nLima, Cusco &amp; Machu Picchu \r\n','','','',415,0,0,NULL,NULL,NULL),(829,1,'Hi Rylee,','<p>We are back home and settling in again.  What an experience we have had!  Peru, and Machu Picchu, was a wonderful ending to it all. We had a great time, and all the hotels and arrangements were great. I was happy with the 3-star hotels, they were all nice and the hot water bottle in the bed in Cusco was a really nice touch.</p>\r\n \r\n<p>We have a wonderful guide in Cusco for 2 tours, Carlos. Our guide at Machu Picchu was also great, but I can\'t remember his name. We were glad we had a private tour there and the rain stopped and the sun shone for our entire visit. Even a double rainbow!</p>\r\n \r\n<p>You did a superb job planning this trip for us. Thanks again for your help,</p>\r\n','Linda <br />\r\nCoquitlam, Canada<br />\r\nLima, Cusco, Machu Picchu, Puno &amp; Lake Titicaca\r\n','','','',415,0,0,NULL,NULL,NULL),(830,1,'Hi Kelly,','<p>The trip was amazing! You could not have done anything to make it better. Everything was taken care of. All the guides were great, the hotel was lovely and the transfers were comfortable and on time.</p>\r\n \r\n<p>Thank you for all your help!</p>\r\n','Ashley<br />\r\nUSA<br />\r\nCusco, Inca Trail &amp; Machu Picchu\r\n','','','',415,0,0,NULL,NULL,NULL),(831,1,'Dear Peru For Less,','<p>I\'m sorry I did not respond to your last email but we get pretty busy after vacations. We loved everything about it. I put a comment in the tripadvisor thread you sent in your last email recommending you guys for anybody planning on visiting Peru. As for our trip it was AWESOME. Everything was taken care of, the hotels were great, the guides knowledgeable and friendly, and the drivers were very punctual. We will definitely have Latin America For Less in our minds when we decide to go to any other country in your portfolio. </p>\r\n \r\n<p>Thank you very much. </p>\r\n','Edgar<br />\r\nUSA<br />\r\nLima, Cusco &amp; Machu Picchu\r\n','','','',415,0,0,NULL,NULL,NULL),(832,1,'Dear Matt,','<p>You would recall planning our South American trip for us, with your correspondences mainly with and through Doreen. I would wish to thank you for the well organized and perfectly carried out program you created for us. Everything went smoothly, and your team of people were so helpful and knew how to make our visit most pleasant. Everywhere upon our arrival and departure and at each hotel pick-up, they were there on time. At no time at all were we ever made to feel lost. It went like clock-work.  </p>\r\n \r\n<p>We offer our thanks and congratulations for your wonderful organization. </p>\r\n\r\n<p>Kindest regards,</p>\r\n','Dick <br />\r\nSingapore<br />\r\nRio de Janeiro, Iguazu Falls, El Calafate, Buenos Aires, Cusco & Machu Picchu\r\n','','','',415,0,0,NULL,NULL,NULL),(833,1,'Hi Kelly,','<p>We really liked that we were welcomed and briefed by a representative from Peru For Less, Caitlin, as soon as we arrived to the airport. I would just suggest that you specify to your client that they will be waiting for them right outside of the airport because we were looking for someone by the baggage claim.  Once we saw Caitlin and her driver, she was very courteous and informative.</p>\r\n \r\n<p>We enjoyed the tour of the city of Cusco and the guide was very good. We enjoyed the Sacred Valley tour alot.  The guide was pleasant and informed.  The transport bus was also very clean and very comfortable. We really enjoyed the Machu Picchu tour.  It was the highlight of our trip.  The guide was very good and professional, even though it was a difficult trip up the steps and we had slight rain.</p>\r\n \r\n<p>Overall, I have nothing but praise for all of the tours and service.  I will recommend Peru for Less to all of my friends.</p>\r\n \r\n<p>Thanks,</p>\r\n','Natasha <br />\r\nUSA<br />\r\nCusco &amp; Machu Picchu \r\n','','','',415,0,0,NULL,NULL,NULL),(834,1,'Mari,','<p>I had such a great time in Peru that in all honesty, I thought of staying for a few extra days. Thank you for everything.  It was so easy and everything (minus the hiccup yesterday) went off without a hitch and just knowing the details were taken care of meant I had more time to enjoy every moment.  It was an amazing trip and I\'m so happy I did it. I\'ve traveled before by myself, but this was by far the best time I\'ve had.  </p>\r\n \r\n<p>And on a personal note, I can\'t tell you enough how sweet it was that you showed up to meet me last night.  The T-shirt is great and the chocolates...well, they are delicious! Really, I was beyond touched that it meant that much to you to make sure I was okay.  Given all our communication has been via email and somewhat anonymous it would be easy for most to shoot me an email back and apologize. What you did though was really special. </p>\r\n \r\n<p>Thank you again.  It was a perfect trip.  </p>\r\n','Erin <br />\r\nWashington DS, USA<br />\r\nLima, Cusco, 2-day Inca Trail &amp; Machu Picchu \r\n','','','',415,0,0,NULL,NULL,NULL),(835,1,'Hi Staci,  ','<p>I had a great and very memorable visit to Peru!  Seeing Lima, Cusco, Aguas Calientes, and Machu Picchu first-hand was an amazing experience. Thank you so much for making all of the coordination and arrangements for my lodging, flights, and transfers. The Peru For Less tour guides were very knowledgeable, professional, and friendly, which helped to make my first trip to Peru more enjoyable. I hope to return to Peru some day to see and experience more of the country, and will definitely consider Peru For Less when planning that trip.    </p>','John <br />\r\nUSA<br />\r\nCusco &amp; Machu Picchu \r\n','','','',415,0,0,NULL,NULL,NULL),(836,1,'Hi, ','<p>The trip went excellent. The itinerary was well-planned and what I was most impressed with how timely and efficiently everything was executed. The guides and drivers were always on time and well equipped with informed. Being a woman traveller, I felt safe the entire time. Thanks so much for all of your help in organizing the trip. I will look you up in the future for all of my trips. </p>','Dave <br />\r\nUSA<br />\r\nLima, Arequipa &amp; Colca Canyon, Puno, Amazon, Cusco &amp; Machu Picchu \r\n','','','',415,0,0,NULL,NULL,NULL),(837,1,'Dear Matt ,','<p>Our 2-day Inca Trail trek and Machu Picchu were incredible!  All your plans went perfectly. We were well briefed at our hotel, our guide was fantastic and I would definitely recommend Peru For Less. The only thing that went wrong was beyond your control- our train home was delayed by 4 hours due to a landslide. The bus then had to take a detour due to another landslide on the road but we were met at the  station on our return and delivered safely back to our hotel. </p>\r\n\r\n<p>Thanks for everything! </p>\r\n','Rachel &amp; Gavin <br />\r\nUSA<br />\r\n2D Inca Trail Trek &amp; Machu Picchu \r\n','','','',415,0,0,NULL,NULL,NULL),(838,1,'Hi Kristina, ','<p>The trip to Peru was very nice, thank you. My family enjoyed the excursions and the guides did an excellent job. The Delphin II was excellent as well and we all enjoyed the food they served.</p>','Sean <br />\r\nCalifornia, USA<br />\r\nAmazon Cruise \r\n','','','',415,0,0,NULL,NULL,NULL),(839,1,'Dear Kristina','<p>I cannot tell you how much I enjoyed Peru. Machu Picchu touched something in me. Our guide Fabricio was absolutely fantastic and really made the introduction to this magical place something extraordinary. Please convey this to him if you have an opportunity.  </p>\r\n\r\n<p>All in all the arrangements were exceptional. I was very nervous doing everything online as I usually work with an agent in Cape Town, but I cannot even begin to tell you how smoothly it all went.  Our hotels, pickups and tours were all perfectly on time and there was not one glitch in any of your arrangements. I would recommend your service to anyone - it is excellent.  </p>\r\n\r\n<p>I am planning to come back to Peru to do the Inca trail and I am also seriously considering a visit to Chile. In both instances I will not even consider using anybody else to make my arrangements. The trust I have in you is complete. I do not say this lightly as I travel a fair amount and I have never had such a hassle-free experience.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>The very best regards to you and your team and a very, very big thank you.  </p>\r\n','Tanya <br />\r\nSouth Africa<br />\r\nLima, Cusco &amp; Machu Picchu\r\n','','','',415,0,0,NULL,NULL,NULL),(840,1,'Hello Rylee, ','<p>We had a wonderful trip to Peru and have you to thank for making it happen. We gave you two days to pull this together during Easter and you came through with flying colors. We loved the Tambopata Research Center in Puerto Maldonado. We saw so many types of birds and wildlife, the kids loved it. Machu Picchu was spectacular and it was nice to stay in the Sacred Valley. All of our guides were great and all of your staff were so helpful. </p>\r\n\r\n<p>Thank you so much. I will be sure to recommend to all of my friends and family.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>All the best!</p>\r\n','James <br />\r\nNewport, Australia<br />\r\nLima, Puerto Maldonado, Lake Titicaca, Cusco &amp; Machu Picchu \r\n','','','',415,0,0,NULL,NULL,NULL),(841,1,'Hi Rylee,','<p>Our trip was fantastic! All your arrangements were perfect and the guides were excellent. We had a fantastic time and canâ??t thank you enough. Even with our delayed flight arrangements, you were able to rearrange our tours and everything went without a hitch. We were lucky to have missed the Puno strike and were thankful to have seen the lake. </p>\r\n\r\n<p>The Aranwa hotel in Cusco was OUTSTANDING. Many thanks for arranging this. We loved Hatun Inti in Machu Picchu as well. THANK YOU so much for all of your assistance in planning the trip, your recommendations, and your check-ups while traveling. </p>\r\n','John (Ohio, USA)<br />\r\nTraveled to: Lima, Arequipa, Colca Canyon, Puno, Cusco, Machu Picchu<br />\r\n','','','',416,0,0,NULL,NULL,NULL),(842,1,'Dear Rylee,','<p>Shirley and I had lunch together yesterday and re-lived our wonderful trip to Peru. Each segment was a perfect gem. Physically, the trip it was grueling for us, but we would not have changed it - except perhaps to have included a few more days here and there along the way for down time. Thanks you for all you did to make our trip so wonderful!</p>','Carolyn (Philippines)<br />\r\nTraveled to: Lima, Nazca, Arequipa, Cusco, Machu Picchu<br />\r\n','','','',416,0,0,NULL,NULL,NULL),(843,1,'Hi Kelly,','<p>We\'ve had wonderful time and could not be happier with our tour guides. They were very accommodating of our needs and informative as well. It really seems like we had a great overview of each city we visited, and I would highly recommend these tour guides to anyone visiting Peru! You were also very helpful as well, and we very much appreciate the follow-ups and checking in to make sure our tours were up to par.  It is hard to find good tour guides while in a foreign country and we were very happy with our finds with your company! </p>','Hailey (New York, USA)<br />\r\nTraveled to: Lima, Cusco, Sacred Valley\r\n','','','',416,0,0,NULL,NULL,NULL),(844,1,'Dear Jennie,','<p>I researched several weeks to find a good travel agent to help me and my daughter plan two April weeks in Peru.  Peru For Less was one of three I contacted, and the one I chose. And, the choice turned out to be a great one. In the past, I have planned and made all of my own arrangements when traveling overseas.  This time, I didnâ??t have the time due to job requirements. Plus, I had never traveled in South America so I was a novice, and I am at the point where I would like to have a few more conveniences.  </p>\r\n\r\n<p>I used Peru For Less to provide overall planning, based on my preferences, which included a lot of unstructured time in a home base, plus a few structured small-sized tours (Machu Picchu, Jungle Eco Tour, Lake Titicaca) and a lot of coordinated transfers. My contact (Jennie) worked with me and arranged a final tour portfolio on a very fast and efficient basis. The tours were excellent and the right size, the transfers were always on time, and the agency checked in with me on a regular basis through a representative based in Cusco, where I was home-based with my daughter. One day, on short notice, we decided we wanted to tour a Cusco planetarium and learn about southern hemisphere constellations. Our local rep. made a private tour happen. We had an astronomers and a high power telescope all to ourselves. I enjoyed the trip, and plan to return to South America again.  And when I do, I plan to contact \"Peru For Less\" for assistance. </p>\r\n','Jana and Lizzie (Nebraska, USA)<br/>\r\nTraveled to: Cusco, Machu Picchu, Lake Titicaca, Puerto Maldonado\r\n','','','',416,0,0,NULL,NULL,NULL),(845,1,'Hi Kelly, ','<p>Thanks for everything! The hotel in Arequipa was fine, the staff was excellent, and the food was great.  The train from Puno was an amazing journey! Your representatives in Cusco were excellent. </p>','Anna &amp; James (Vancouver, Canada)<br />\r\nTraveled to: Lima, Paracas, Nazca, Arequipa, Puno, Lake Titicaca, Cusco, Machu Picchu, Puerto Maldonado\r\n','','','',416,0,0,NULL,NULL,NULL),(846,1,'Hi Matt,','<p>Thanks for arranging our trip. Overall, we were satisfied with the level of service we received.</p>\r\n<p>The guides were friendly, knowledgeable, and their English was good. Otherwise, we had a great time without issues with flights or pickups. Machu Picchu and IguazÃº falls were amazing and we were able to enjoy our trip very much.</p>\r\n','Amy (USA)<br />\r\nTraveled to: Lima, Cusco, Machu Picchu (Peru), Buenos Aires, IguazÃº Falls (Argentina)<br />\r\n','','','',416,0,0,NULL,NULL,NULL),(847,1,'Hi Kelly,','<p>Our trip across the border was a real adventure and over 12 exhausting hours in all. The drivers and escorts on both sides were excellent, but unfortunately there was a communication breakdown between them, and we waited 2 hours at different border crossings. Because of this delay, the border town was unattended and we had to take extra time getting entry stamps. However, we are very grateful for all your work arranging this, as there did not seem to be an easy way into Bolivia. Everything else has run like clockwork and was really professional.</p>','Anne (USA)<br />\r\nTraveled to: Cusco, Machu Picchu, Puno (Peru) &amp; La Paz (Bolivia)<br />\r\n','','','',416,0,0,NULL,NULL,NULL),(848,1,'Dear Rylee,','<p>We had a couple mishaps, but for the most part everything went smoothly. I certainly would recommend the hotel in Cusco, San Blas, as it was excellent. You were excellent as well and I would like to thank you especially for arranging the trip. We couldn\'t have made it work without you. </p>','Amoy (Toronto, Canada)<br/>\r\nTraveled to: Lima, Cusco, Machu Picchu<br/>\r\n','','','',416,0,0,NULL,NULL,NULL),(849,1,'Hello Aleksandar,','<p>The trip was very nice, thank you. The service you provided was very good and reliable. The minor transportation issue we had was resolved quickly and easily. Thank you for a great trip.</p>','Cory (Arizona, USA)<br />\r\nTraveled to: Lima\r\n','','','',416,0,0,NULL,NULL,NULL),(850,1,'Hi Kristina,','<p>I couldn\'t have been happier with the services we received from Peru for Less. Our rep, Kristina Rudge, was fantastic! She was always accessible, always responded quickly and thoroughly to any of my emails, and made me feel confident in dealing with a company with whom we had never worked with before. She researched additional options for our group as we were deciding on the exact itinerary and provided me with comprehensive information so that we could make the best choice. The tour was very well priced and we were able to tailor it to our groupâ??s needs, down to making requests for specific restaurants that were not on the standard itinerary. I would highly recommend Peru for Less, and if you\'re lucky enough to work with Kristina, you won\'t be disappointed!</p>\r\n\r\n<p>I\'ve emailed other members from our group and they had a fantastic time and had nothing but praise to offer. Here are a few direct comments:</p>\r\n\r\n<p>\"For my part, this trip was near perfect!  I had reasonably high expectations, but the reality vastly exceeded them. Peru itself was truly wonderful. But the arrangements made by Peru For Less were really great. Great hotels. Great food. Great guides. Great itinerary. Everything was so well thought out.\"</p>\r\n\r\n<p>\"It truly seemed to be the perfect experience. We never travel with a group of people so this was different for us, but it could not have been better. The organization of all the arrangements, travel, accommodations, food, and especially the tour guides made for a very special experience.\"</p> \r\n','Sharon (Programs Coordinator for Center for Global Education trip from New England, USA)<br />\r\nTraveled to: Sacred Valley, Machu Picchu, Cusco, Lima<br />\r\n','','','',416,0,0,NULL,NULL,NULL),(851,1,'Dear Silvana,','<p>The trip was great.  Every one of the coordinators, drivers, hotel personal, and tour guides, was on time and very knowledgeable. They made everyone comfortable and took care of any needs. I was very happy with this trip. Your staff, guides, etc. are the best I have been with compared to any other trip. Thank you so much!</p>','Ron (Massachusetts, USA)<br />\r\nDates traveled: May 12-16, 2011<br />\r\nTraveled to: Cusco &amp; Machu Picchu<br />\r\n','','','',416,0,0,NULL,NULL,NULL),(852,1,'Hi Rylee','<p>Just wanted to thank you & Peru For Less for arranging our amazing trip to Peru. We saw so much: landscapes, nature, people, animals, and history. You were wonderful to work with, always prompt, answering all my questions, and giving good suggestions as well as always being so pleasant and personable. You even upgraded our hotel without extra cost after hearing about some concerns regarding the hotel we had been booked into. </p>\r\n\r\n<p>My husband & I have never gone through an Agency before, but it made our trip much easier and less stressful. The trip was hard work but more than worth it. The drivers and guides were always there to meet us or to take us to our various forms of transportation including vans, buses, airplanes, trains, and boats. They had our tickets ready. You arranged for our luggage to be sent ahead so we did not have to worry about it at Machu Picchu. Our guides were amazing - we ended up with several private tours which were the best. I have to single out Beatriz, our guide in Arequipa and the Colca Canyon and our driver Edgardo Rodriguez for their excellent work and friendly service.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>We found the people of Peru to be friendly, kind, and helpful. You allowed us to individualized our trip and coordinated our friend meeting up with us for the last week in the Sacred Valley and Cuzco. We saw a great deal in a relatively short time and have come back wanting to learn more about Peru and its history.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Thanks again for the trip of a lifetime and we would not hesitate to recommend Peru For Less to anyone wanting to travel in Peru.. </p>\r\n','Patsy  & Jesse  (Toronto, Canada)<br />\r\nTraveled to: Lima, Paracas, Nazca, Arequipa, Colca Canyon, Puno, Lake Titicaca, Sacred Valley, Aguas Calientes, Machu Picchu, Cusco         \r\n','','','',416,0,0,NULL,NULL,NULL),(853,1,'Dear Rylee,','<p>We had a lovely honeymoon and I only wish we could have stayed longer. Back to real world here. I am downloading our photos and will send you a couple once I have more time and post my comments on trip advisor as well. Peru For Less worked out perfectly, I am so glad I found you. You planned the perfect vacation for us. All of our guides were great, and all of your hotel recommendations were spot on. Thanks again for all of your help and for taking the time to answer my billion questions. I\'ll be in touch with more praise shortly.</p>','Kristen (Ontario, Canada)<br/>\r\nTraveled to: Lima, Cusco, Machu Picchu, Arequipa, Colca Canyon, Puno\r\n','','','',416,0,0,NULL,NULL,NULL),(854,1,'Hey Rylee,','<p>The trip was great, and seeing Machu Picchu after a good days hike was spectacular. The ten days there were not enough but we had so much fun. Thank you for all your help. </p>\r\n<p>The hotels were even better than we expected as were the people we dealt with and met. The Peru For less people were nice and courteous and the guides were great. It was a fantastic trip. </p>\r\n','Michael and Rachel (USA)<br/>\r\nTraveled to: Lima, Cusco, Inca Trail to Machu Picchu, Amazon (Puerto Maldonado) \r\n','','','',416,0,0,NULL,NULL,NULL),(855,1,'Hi Stacey,','<p>We thoroughly enjoyed every minute of our trip but Colca Canyon was one of the definite highlights. The tour we did round Arequipa with our lovely guide, Beatrice, was super and gave us a wonderful insight into the history and the beauty of the area. It also allowed us to explore on our own with a much better understanding and an idea where to go to buy the best Alpaca!</p>\r\n\r\n<p>The trip to Colca canyon with Roberto was absolutely superb. Roberto made it so much more special. His knowledge and ability to paint a picture of life for the locals along with how life was in the pre and post Inca times was truly remarkable and it not only gave us an appreciation of the Colca valley, but we took that knowledge with us on the rest of our holiday and I am sure it helped us to have a deeper and more meaningful understanding of all the places and people we met thereafter.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>It was great fun having the young folk on our bus from Kumaku and that also added another dimension to our time in Colca. Roberto was wonderful when one of the girls got sick and showed his experience in dealing with that as well as ensuring everyone else had a good time. Everyone got amazing photos of the condors and we all had lots of fun and laughter both on the way up and the way back. I wanted to take Roberto with us on the rest of our trip!</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Thank you for your professionalism in organizing our bus trips and our tour, we felt very confident that you had it all under control and it was lovely to have a contact person to reassure us when we needed it. If we ever have the opportunity to travel back to South America we will certainly contact your organization again.</p>\r\n','Gill (USA)<br />\r\nTraveled to: Arequipa &amp; Colca Canyon \r\n','','','',416,0,0,NULL,NULL,NULL),(856,1,'Dear Jennie,','<p>Peru For Less was highly recommended by a co-worker and we were not disappointed. Everything was fantastic! Friends since college, with a lot of travel under our belts, our adventures in Peru exceeded our expectations.  </p>\r\n\r\n<p>Jennie was great to work with and made planning the trip a breeze. She patiently worked with us over several weeks to customize our trip to fit our timeframe and interests. Suzanna met us at the Cusco airport with a huge smile, told us what to expect, who would be our tour guide for each leg of our trip, what time to be where and, most importantly, how to get the most out of our trip to Peru and enjoy the beautiful countryside, culture and wonderful people. Everything was delivered as promised. Even a 7-hour train delay due to a mudslide - where plans became very iffy - was taken care of. The local Peru For Less team in Aguas Calientes found us in a crowd, took us to their offices and kept us comfortable and informed about constantly changing updates. </p>\r\n\r\n<p>Every guide that we met was warm, knowledgeable, very proud of their culture and committed to making our time in Peru the best it could be. Our accommodations at the Aranwa Hotel were amazing.  We have not stopped talking about our trip and cannot wait to go back to Peru with our families. Peru For Less will be our first call in planning the next trip.  </p>\r\n','Jane &amp; Pattie (Boston, USA)<br />\r\nTraveled to: Lima, Cusco, Sacred Valley, Machu Picchu \r\n','','','',416,0,0,NULL,NULL,NULL),(857,1,'Dear Jennie,','<p>Our trip was absolutely fantastic!  I cannot say enough about your employees.  Everything was done so professionally, pleasantly and nothing was a surprise - except for the landslide and train delays but even then we were taken care of by Peru For Less.</p>\r\n \r\n<p>Thank you for all that you did to make our trip so easy, memorable and beyond our expectations. I am talking with my brother and at least one of my sisters about making the trip. Of course, their trip has to include me!</p>\r\n','Tricia (Maryland, USA)<br />\r\nTraveled to: Lima, Cusco, Machu Picchu \r\n','','','',416,0,0,NULL,NULL,NULL),(858,1,'Dear Peru For Less, ','<p>I just finished my trip to Machu Picchu, Cusco and the Sacred Valley where I had Peru For Less do all the arranging and I could not have been more pleased. I did not do a budget trip. I did five star hotels, private van/driver and private (excellent) guides every day, and I thought the cost very reasonable. It compared very favorably to much lower level tours. They even arranged for a photographer guide for the entire day at Machu Picchu as a complimentary upgrade.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Peru For Less is the only time I have used a travel service for South America, but it was great when we were stuck on the tracks because of the landslide and no communication on, that I knew someone was rearranging on the other end. When we arrived in Ollantaytambo after our four-hour delay, our driver was waiting (and carried our bags the interminable gravel path walk back to the town as the road was shut down) and our afternoon and the next day had been reorganized so that we didn\'t miss anything. Caitlyn, who is a fabulous on site Peru For Less representative in Cusco, was great and called a couple times during the stay to make sure everything was working the way we expected. The attention was just right - not in your face, but always there when something happened or you needed something. </p>\r\n\r\n<p>So, I had a great experience with Peru For Less. I can\'t say anything about the others, but I was very pleased with my experience.</p>\r\n','Patricia (New York, USA)<br />\r\nTraveled to: Cusco, Sacred Valley, Machu Picchu, Lima \r\n','','','',416,0,0,NULL,NULL,NULL),(859,1,'Dear Kristina,','<p>My wife and I had a fabulous time hiking the Inca Trail. We found our guide, cook, and porters from Wayki Trek to be wonderful, friendly, and patient. In fact, we would argue that they were the best group on the trail. Our meals were better than the food in Cusco (and these were cooked with on a camping stove with food carried along the trail). Our guide shared his culture, love for Incan history and society, and his amazing knowledge of botanic with us along the trek. The hike itself was magical and Machu Picchu was breathtaking. </P>\r\n\r\n<p>We had a rough start due to flight issues, but the staff at Peru For Less quickly and efficiently helped to re-arrange our schedule so that we did what was most important. They coordinated our Inca Trail vacation so that it was exactly what we had wanted. </p>\r\n\r\n<p>Thank you again for all you help.  </p>\r\n\r\n','Chris (Ohio, USA)<br />\r\nTraveled to: Cusco, Inca Trail, Machu Picchu','','','',416,0,0,NULL,NULL,NULL),(860,1,'Hi Jennifer,','<p>Emily and I had a terrific time in Peru overall. The programs as arranged were generally of excellent quality, and gave us superb insights into both the Highlands/Inca culture and the Amazon area. Thanks for setting up for us such a strong itinerary. All three hotels (Monasterio, Inkaterra El Pueblo, and Inkaterra Reserva Amazonica) were great.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>All the best to you, and thanks again for a terrific travel experience.</p>\r\n','David & Emily (California, USA)<br />\r\nTraveled to: Lima, Cusco, Machu Picchu, Puerto Maldonado\r\n','','','',416,0,0,NULL,NULL,NULL),(861,1,'Dear Peru For Less, ','<p>At some point when you are planning a big trip that is several months in the making, you can\'t help but wonder if it will all come together as you hoped.Luckily, my trip to Peru lived up to everything I was hoping for and then a whole lot more!</p>\n\n<p>Kelly at Peru For Less put together a tour package specific to the dates we had in Cusco and walked us through every step -- helping us get the most bang for our time and money.</p>\n\n<p>Arriving in Cusco, we were given a complete run down on what to expect from our various tours and also given a good deal of helpful suggestions of places to see in town and how to deal with the first day or two of life at 11,000 feet!</p>\n\n<p>Our tour groups were small (the largest group was 8 guests) and the guides were wonderful. Transportation to the Sacred Valley and the train ride to Machu Picchu went off without a hitch. In fact, everything ran smoothly from start to finish. </p>\n\n<p>To anyone looking for a solid tour company that really will make you feel confident in booking a trip with them, I cannot recommend Peru For Less enough. They will take care of you (and told us over and over that if anything did go wrong, they would be available 24/7 to fix it).</p>\n','Jim (USA)<br />\r\nTraveled to: Cusco &amp; Machu Picchu \r\n','','','',416,0,0,NULL,NULL,NULL),(862,1,'Hi Kelly,','<p>Yes, we are back and as hectic as it was, it was a brilliant holiday and my husband and I enjoyed so much! To see Machu Picchu was a dream of mine for a very long time and I am truly glad I got you as our travel advisor so thank you for all the advice and help you have given me throughout. </p>\r\n\r\n<p>There were however some glitches during our holiday and some significant blunders. All in all Kelly, we did have a brilliant holiday and 1500 odd pictures to prove and show it too!!!!!!! :-)) So thank you for all your help and suggestions throughout helping us to enjoy our PERU!!! :-)) </p>\r\n\r\n<p>Best regards,</p>\r\n','Dilini (USA)<br />\r\nTraveled to:  Lima, Arequipa & Colca Canyon, Puno, Lake Titicaca, Cusco, Machu Picchu \r\n','','','',416,0,0,NULL,NULL,NULL),(863,1,'Hi Kelly,','<p>I had a wonderful time in Peru! The tour guides starting from the girl who picked me up at the airport (I forgot her name), to the tour guides in both the Cusco city Tour and Sacred Valley tour, as well as Wayki Trek were terrific.  They went beyond the call of duty. The hotel accommodations were just right.  Â¡I liked the Inca Trail Trek very much...although I did detest the rain on the 3rd day when it came. So many sights to see.</p>\r\n  \r\n<p>More Power to You and Your Organization!</p>\r\n','Christina (USA)<br/>\r\nTraveled to: Cusco & Machu Picchu \r\n','','','',416,0,0,NULL,NULL,NULL),(864,1,'Hi Rylee,','<p>Thanks for arranging the trip and the change in schedule. We had a wonderful time in the Galapagos. It totally exceeded ones expectation. The ship, staff and service were impeccable. The food and meals were healthy and flavorful. We saw a lot of wonderful animals, birds and creatures on the islands and it was really relaxing for us to be there and experience so many wonderful things.</p>\r\n \r\n<p>The guides and the pickup and drop offs in Quito all went fine. They were always pleasant and wonderful to deal with.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>This is my second trip booked through you and I will certainly be booking more. </p> \r\n<p>Thanks again,</p>\r\n','Aria (Washington State, USA)<br />\r\nTraveled to: Quito & Galapagos (Ecuador)\r\n','','','',416,0,0,NULL,NULL,NULL),(865,1,'Hi Mari,','<p>We just got back this weekend and are having fun enjoying our pictures and distributing souvenirs. The trip went great! It was really a dream come true for us. Peru For Less did a great job and we won\'t hesitate to work with you again, as well as recommend your services.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Some feedback on the highlights of our trip:</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Lima - Sandra, our city guide, was great.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Cuzco - everything in Cuzco was truly amazing. I want to single out Susana, who picked us up at the airport, because she really made us feel welcome and gave us a wealth of information that was beyond anything expected. If you can, please let her know that we ate at 3 of the restaurants that she recommended and loved it! Fabricio, our Machu Picchu guide, was a character (just like Susana had promised) and made our tour unforgettable.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>All our hotels were great but El Mapi completely surpassed our expectations and offered an unexpected dinner that was delicious.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>The Andean Explorer from Cusco to Puno was one of the highlights of our trip and we\'ll recommend it to everybody. We absolutely loved the floating islands of Uros on Lake Titicaca.</p>\r\n','Marta (USA &amp; Portugal)<br />\r\nTraveled to: Lima, Cusco, Machu Picchu, Puno, Lake Titicaca\r\n','','','',416,0,0,NULL,NULL,NULL),(866,1,'Hi Kelly,','<p>We had an absolutely amazing time. We need a vacation from our vacation. Every day was filled with beautiful sights and sounds. The transfers all worked out great - I especially loved being met at the airports by someone who had a sign with our name on it.  </p>\r\n\r\n<p>The trekking company (Wayki Trek) was beyond excellent. The porters and guides made our trip so pleasant - very knowledgeable and considerate. After hiking all day, we were met with a cold fruit drink and all we had to do was relax and enjoy. The food was unique and tasteful. Our group was small (only 7 of us) which was especially appealing since the larger groups that passed us seemed to be rather loud. Our guides never rushed us and we were able to go at our own pace.  IT WAS SO MUCH FUN!  </p>\r\n\r\n<p>Posada Amazonas was quite interesting. The only suggestion I would make would be to make sure people know that they will need to sign up in advance for the activities offered by Posada Amazonas. The guides were also very knowledgeable and had much enthusiasm.  </p>\r\n\r\n<p>The hotels were a welcome relief after being outside trekking.  Hot showers and full breakfasts in each place. Everyone accommodated our wishes.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Thanks for all your hard work.  </p>\r\n','Cindy &amp; Bill (USA)<br />\r\nTraveled to: Cusco, Inca Trail, Machu Picchu, Amazon (Puerto Maldonado)\r\n','','','',416,0,0,NULL,NULL,NULL),(867,1,'Dear Matt, ','<p>Job well done. The trip you planned was absolutely spectacular. Hotel Aranwa in Cusco was incredible with fantastic personnel. The hotel Sumaq in Aguas Calientes was even better. </p>\r\n\r\n<p>My wife and I had the best time thanks to your tailored trip. Every detail of the written trip was on time. Our tour guides at Cusco and Machu Picchu (David and Fabricio) were unbelievable.The trip up to Machu Picchu was a dream come true. Photos do not do justice. </p>\r\n\r\n<p>People of Peru are kind, hospitable and go out of their way to please tourists. We met so many great Peruvian people. We are so glad first trip to South America started in Peru. Now start working on Patagonia trip winter of next year! </p>\r\n\r\n<p>Thank you and Peru For Less for making my trip a memorable one. I will recommend this trip to family and friends. </p>\r\n','Farhood (New Jersey, USA)<br />\r\nTraveled to: Cusco & Machu Picchu \r\n','','','',416,0,0,NULL,NULL,NULL),(868,1,'Hi Staci,','<p>The Cusco &amp; Machu Picchu tour you booked for our group was EXCELLENT! Everything was as planned and there weren\'t any problems. Your Peru staff did an excellent job of guiding us and ensuring we were well taken care of. Thanks for making it a memorable experience. As Rajesh mentioned in his email, we did Wayna Picchu. That was awesome! Excellent view of Machu Picchu. </p>','Shawn (USA)<br />\r\nTraveled to Cusco & Machu Picchu\r\n','','','',416,0,0,NULL,NULL,NULL),(869,1,'Hi Riva,','<p>It was an absolutely fantastic trip from beginning to end. The logistics of all the transfers were all exactly on time and all the hotels were just lovely. The guides were fantastic and the Hiram Bingham was a thrill.  We had a wonderful time and we will never forget the beautiful Sacred Valley and Machu Picchu. Thank you for helping us organizing this wonderful trip.</p>','Sally &amp; Nancy (Texas, USA)<br />\r\nTraveled to: Lima, Cusco, Machu Picchu\r\n','','','',416,0,0,NULL,NULL,NULL),(870,1,'Dear Peru For Less, ','<p>Everything was terrific. No worries with the transfers. The drivers were on time and polite. All tour guides and handoffs were excellent. We were both satisfied.  </p>','Cheryl (Texas, USA)<br />\r\nTraveled to: Cusco, Machu Picchu, Arequipa\r\n','','','',416,0,0,NULL,NULL,NULL);
INSERT INTO `testimonies` VALUES (871,1,'Hi Silvana,','<p>You did an awesome job!! Thank you. Whatever you planned for us went extremely well. I am so glad we went with you as our travel advisor.</p>\r\n \r\n<p>All the tour guides were awesome, friendly and knowledgeable. We enjoyed our trip thoroughly. The only snag was Cusco, the high altitude did not agree with me and also the choice of hotel was not good at all (my fault - I should have listened to you).</p>\r\n \r\n<p>The Iguazu Falls are engrained in our memory. We will go back God willing. </p>\r\n','Nikki (Toronto, Canada)<br />\r\nTraveled to: Lima, Cusco, Machu Picchu (Peru) &amp; Iguazu Falls (Argentina)\r\n','','','',416,0,0,NULL,NULL,NULL),(872,1,'Dear Rylee,','<p>Our trip was fantastic. Hotels, weather, and logistics were flawless. We all loved Peru and would love to return one day soon. Itâ??s quite a beautiful country. Thanks for your assistance in planning everything. I will recommend you and Peru For Less to all of my friends and family.</p>','Stuart (North Carolina, USA)<br />\r\nTraveled to: Lima, Cusco, Machu Picchu \r\n','','','',416,0,0,NULL,NULL,NULL),(873,1,'Dear Rylee,','<p>Thank you so much. We had a great time.  It was great to see our friends and see such a beautiful country, Peru. I cannot thank you enough for all of your assistance. I will definitely recommend you to anyone that I know is planning to travel to Peru. I will let you know when we plan to visit Peru again.</p>','Melissa (Ohio, USA)<br />\r\nTraveled to: Cusco & Machu Picchu\r\n','','','',759,0,0,NULL,NULL,NULL),(874,1,'Hi Peru For Less,','<p>My trip was amazing and will be one of the highlights of my life. My exceptions were exceeded at every turn by your professional, prompt and detailed response to your questions. In fact, it was such a wonderful experience that I go out of my way to tell friends about how wonderful Peru is and recommend your company as a possible tour vendor. I may have a friend travelling to Peru later this year and have recommended you to her.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>I had an excellent experience with the tours, food, organization, and the overall planning was wonderful. Your guides were knowledgeable, bilingual and quite willing to go with the flow! I\'ve now fallen in love with Peru\'s people, food and land. Take care!</p>\r\n','Christopher (Jamaica)<br />\r\nTraveled to: Lima, Cusco, Sacred Valley, Machu Picchu \r\n','','','',760,0,0,NULL,NULL,NULL),(875,1,'Dear Matt,','<p>We had an absolutely terrific time in Peru!  We were met at every point along the way and never had to worry about a thing. The service and support firmly exceeded our expectations!  When our hotel was changed at the last minute in Lima, we received a complete explanation that it was due to noise and construction adjacent to the existing hotel.  </p>\r\n \r\n<p>The beauty and experience of Peru was greatly enhanced by the escorts. The Inca Trail was the highlight of our trip, and Willy Jones with Wayki treks was phenomenal. We couldn\'t have asked for a better experience.  Thanks for your detailed attention, quick responses, and timely updates to make our vacation a truly unforgettable one.  Thanks,</p>\r\n','Jason and Julie (Washington DC, USA)<br />\r\nTraveled to: Lima, Cusco, Machu Picchu, Inca Trail\r\n','','','',761,0,0,NULL,NULL,NULL),(876,1,'Buenos Dias Matt, ','<p>For a solo-female traveler, I couldn\'t have felt more safe and well-looked after every step of the way. I did not have to worry about any transfers or pick-up... Every single one was on-time (and waited for me when I was late) and courteous. In total, Peru For Less, you made my trip! I have already started to think about what other trips to South America I hope to plan with your assistance, as I met quite a few other travelers who were on a complete \"South American\" experience with your company.</p>','Susie (Vancouver, Canada)<br />\r\nTraveled to: Lima, Cusco, Machu Picchu\r\n','','','',762,0,0,NULL,NULL,NULL),(877,1,'Dear Jenny,','<p>Saying the trip was amazing does not do it justice. I looked into other travel packages and trip offers and am extremely confident that by choosing Peru For Less that the right choice was made. Everything worked like clockwork. We get off a plane, train, or bus and there was someone from Peru For Less waiting for us. All of the contacts were helpful, and answered all of our questions. The food in Peru was so good; I think I ate 4 times a day and loved it all. I thank you so much for all your assistance in planning this trip and I have had nothing but good things to say about my travel experience. I know you also do all of Latin America; but if you operate in other countries as well, I would like to know about those for future trips and will be excited to use you again. Thanks so much!</p>','Jimmy (Tennessee, USA)<br />\r\nTraveled to: Nazca, Cusco, Sacred Valley, Machu Picchu\r\n','','','',763,0,0,NULL,NULL,NULL),(878,1,'Dear Peru For Less,','<p>All went well for us on our Cusco/Machu Picchu trip. Actually, it was quite perfect. Kyle asked me to marry him at Machu Picchu! We woke up super early to climb up Waynu Picchu and he asked me on the top of that mountain. It was too perfect. And really it was thanks for the great trip planning and pre-trip advice that we received from our travel advisors (Hannah Groff and YOU!).  So, thank-you, thank-you, thank-you! I would highly recommend Peru for less. You all are flexible and willing to work with what the client wants and needs! Thanks for a great trip.</p>','Allison (USA)<br />\r\nTraveled to: Cusco &amp; Machu Picchu\r\n','','','',764,0,0,NULL,NULL,NULL),(879,1,'Hi Kelly,','<p>I\'m a little slow in keeping my promise, but better late than never I hope. We just got back from our 4 months winter journey in California, Arizona and Nevada and so on. Once again thank you for building memories for life for all of us. </p>','Fred (USA)<br />\r\nTraveled to: Cusco & Machu Picchu  \r\n','','','',765,0,0,NULL,NULL,NULL),(880,1,'Hi Silvana,','<p>I want to thank you and Peru For Less for a fantastic trip to Machu Picchu and Cusco. After quite a bit of research with the \"big\" companies as well as some of the smaller companies I decided to go with Peru For Less and I definitely do not regret my decision. This was the second of 5 legs of my trip and because Silvana was so helpful with my package I decided to ask her to help with the remainder of my trip. She was by far able to get me the best prices, but even better than that she was able to work with my dates and provide me with quality guides, accommodation and transport for the entire trip. The personal messages left at the hotel and by email to follow up and make sure everything was running smoothly, as well as the personal itinerary were all a nice touch!  </p>\r\n\r\n<p>Before I had even completed my vacation I had recommended Silvana and Peru For Less/Latin America For Less to two friends and I will not hesitate to recommend or use them again. Thank you for helping to make a memorable trip!</p>\r\n','Marcos (Ontario, Canada)<br />\r\nTraveled to: Cusco & Machu Picchu\r\n','','','',766,0,0,NULL,NULL,NULL),(881,1,'Dear Riva,','<p>Our plans for our trip to South America were very ambitious and there was very little time to organize the itinerary, but you made it all happen! We were pleased to have had such an enjoyable and memorable time, particularly in Peru.</p>\r\n \r\n<p>Our guides were friendly and knowledgeable, and we really enjoyed the flexibility of our private tours. Equally pleasant, and very caring, were our agency representatives and transfer people. One of our memorable moments was when the two of us were met at the Aguas Calientes train station by a welcoming party of four, including the bellboy from the hotel! The hotel rooms were all clean and comfortable, and the hotels were well located.</p>\r\n \r\n<p>Thank you so much for pulling this trip together for us at virtually the last minute. I really appreciated your professionalism and attentiveness to our needs. I would definitely recommend Peru For Less/Latin America For Less for travel to South America.</p>\r\n','Tracey (Canada)<br/>\r\nTraveled to: Rio de Janeiro, Iguazu Falls, Puerto Madryn, Buenos Aires, Santiago, Lima, Cusco, Machu Picchu \r\n','','','',767,0,0,NULL,NULL,NULL),(882,1,'Dear Matt,','<p>Here is my report of the glorious trip you had planned for my party and me in South America. <strong>I have to admit that, before the trip began, I had experienced some apprehension, wondering if everything planned would be carried out as promised or... would we encounter one difficulty after another?</strong> I wasn\'t very certain so I could not assure my friends that things would be all right! <strong>Now that I\'m back, I can say for sure that one can definitely depend on Latin America For Less!</strong></p>\n<p>Your itinerary specially tailored for us really did work like clockwork from the moment we met our first tour representative in Rio de Janeiro all the way to our last destination before we flew to Sao Paulo from Lima! Thank you so much for offering us such professional advice and service! Everyone involved was friendly, punctual and efficient. The moment we exited at an airport, there was always someone waiting to greet us and bring us to our hotel. When it came time for us to leave a place for the airport, the same service was given. <strong>We were never left stranded, wondering who would meet us, as your representatives were always there before us! Truly, I am so glad I sought your advice before making my trip to South America!</strong></p>\n<p>The hotels you had booked for us were also good! Some were quaint and homely while others were more modern. Whatever kind of hotel we were in there was always a nice, clean bed to sleep in and a TV to catch up with the latest news. </p>\n<p>An incident I would like to make mention of is the one that you had earlier written to Dick (Nee Khuen) about; the lost camera. You had followed up on this issue and made enquiries with Peru Rail regarding its retrieval. Thank you so much for doing your part in helping us locating the camera. It was indeed a big blow to Dick and Nah Nee to have lost it. Imagine all the beautiful and precious photos they have taken going into \'thin air\' at the end of their trip. That could have \'marred\' their otherwise wonderful trip to some extent.</p>\n<p>Among all the great sights we had covered, I must say that the Perito Moreno Glacier was most outstanding. We had the opportunity to come pretty close to that huge river of ice thanks to the ride in the catamaran that was included in our tour. I have attached two photos of our memorable tour and you can see for yourself the wonderful places we had visited which made all that travel to South America worthwhile.</p>\n<p><strong>Once again, it has been my privilege and pleasure to have corresponded with you on the planning of this \'once in a lifetime\' trip</strong> and I am most grateful for all the help and advice you have given to all our queries. <strong>I will strongly recommend you and your team at Latin America For Less to all my friends who wish to embark on such a trip in the future.</strong> In fact, ever since my return, my sister (she was the one who had told me to write to Latin America For Less after she had accidentally discovered your website while surfing the net), has been receiving feedback from me as she intends to make a similar trip to Argentina with her friends, sometime in the future. Furthermore, Nah Nee\'s brother will be visiting South America in a few months and I am sure he will be seeking advice from Nah Nee regarding the planning of his trip. We intend to recommend you and your company, so be on the lookout for more Singaporeans writing to you for travel advice and making you their Trip Advisor!!</p>\n<p>Here\'s wishing you all the best for the future!</p>\n','Doreen (Singapore)<br/>\r\nTraveled to: Rio de Janeiro, IguazÃº Falls, Buenos Aires, El Calafate, Cusco, Machu Picchu\r\n\r\n','','','\"I can say for sure that one can definitely depend on Latin America For Less!\"',100058,0,0,NULL,'2014-09-10 23:13:26',NULL),(883,1,'Hi Mari, ','<p>Our travels to South America were amazing!  Everything went smoothly and we are back in town safely. Thank you very much.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>The Iguazu falls were incredible and no wonder the falls are now contenders for the new seven natural wonders of the world.  Machu Picchu was amazing as well and we enjoyed the experience very much.</p>\r\n','Noriko (US &amp; Japan)<br />\r\nTraveled to: Buenos Aires, Iguazu Falls, Cusco &amp; Machu Picchu\r\n','','','',769,0,0,NULL,NULL,NULL),(884,1,'Dear Peru For Less,','<p>My friends and I had started planning a trip to Peru since the beginning of 2011. We contacted various tour operators for quotes and comparison. What caught our attention was the reasonably less cost Peru For Less quoted (comparing to other quotes) and the responsiveness of our contact Riva Bacquet at PFL. Through the 4 months of trip planning we have sent numerous emails with questions, requests for change of itinerary and locations, etc. Not even once did I personally felt ignored. As a matter of fact, Riva demonstrated great professionalism and patience through it all. </p>\r\n\r\n<p>Once we got in Peru, we were impressed with the services provided to us each step of the way. Additionally, the hotels booked for us were clean, nice, and convenient. Each tour group arranged for us was led by friendly, polite, and knowledgeable tour guides. Each of the tour group we were in were small in number of people, which made it a lot easier to get to know each person in the group and the tour guide better. We felt a connection to them all. </p>\r\n\r\n<p>We chose to do the 2 day Inca Trail to Machu Picchu. The tour operator Peru For Less used was Wayki Trek. Our guide was Jose Cusi Camero. We highly recommend Jose for any Machu Picchu trekking adventure to anyone who is considering it. </p>\r\n\r\n<p>All in all, thank you Riva, for the amazing tour package you prepared for us and for the high quality services you have provided. This is no doubt in my mind what made our trip to Peru that much more memorable. I would highly recommend Riva, Peru For Less, and Jose to anyone who is planning a trip to Peru. </p>\r\n','Ling (Texas, USA)<br />\r\nTraveled to: Cusco & Machu Picchu \r\n','','','',770,0,0,NULL,NULL,NULL),(885,1,'Hi Staci,','<p>Our trip was excellent. At all the locations, we were met by the Peru For Less representatives on time and were briefed precisely about our agenda. After arriving to Cusco, the Peru For Less representative (Caitlin) was warm and welcoming and the tour guide was quite detailed. We really enjoyed her narratives on the Incan history. After the tour of Cusco, we were driven to the train station to go to Agua Calientes, where we planned our next day. We took the early morning first bus ride to Machu Picchu and then a hike to Huayna Picchu. The hike, though tiring, rewards one with an amazing panoramic view of the ruins and made us feel as if we have conquered a tough peak.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>The tour of the ruins was interesting, but we were so beat up by the hike that later we simply decided to take it easy, relax and stroll around Aguas Calientes. After returning to Cusco late in the evening, we spent the night at Casa San Blas, a neat and comfortable hotel in the historical downtown of Cusco. I liked the touristy streets and squares at Cusco and the atmosphere was quite refreshing. </p>\r\n\r\n<p>We were dropped off at the Cusco airport by Caitlin in the morning on time and I was definitely wishing we had more time to spend around Cusco. But for what it\'s worth, for a quick trip, it was an amazing experience, thanks to the meticulous organization by PFL.</p>\r\n','Raj (USA)<br />\r\nTraveled to: Cusco & Machu Picchu \r\n','','','',771,0,0,NULL,NULL,NULL),(886,1,'Hi Kelly, ','<p>I appreciate all your help in planning a fantastic tripâ??it was beyond amazing. This was the first big trip/adventure like this that Iâ??ve ever undertaken. I think you guys were a big reason for the success. Being able to email Peru For Less and receive quick and detailed responses was helpful and removed a lot of stress. Also, the folks that picked up us were great. They were always on time; easy to identify, and very focused on our satisfaction. Our guide on the trail was Antonio and we were connected to Waki Trek. Both the guide and the porters were great, making us feel very welcomed and providing a great education/experience.</p>\r\n \r\n<p>My only suggestion is that I would really recommend you push people to go to Paracas and see the Islands and the Reserve. What a great way to see Peru!  I know you offered this as a tour option, but I kind of stumbled into going there, and it would be great if Peru For Less highlighted this destination as a package deal. Thanks again!</p>\r\n','Bob (United States)<br />\r\nTraveled to: Paracas, Nazca Lines, 4-day Inca Trail to Machu Picchu\r\n','','','',416,0,0,NULL,NULL,NULL),(887,1,'Dear Jennie,','<p>On a scale of ten with 10 being tops, my clients ranked their trip with Peru For Less as an 11 or better! Congratulations! Everything was wonderful.</p>','Janâ?? Agent (Florida)<br />\r\nTraveled to: Cusco, Sacred Valley, Machu Picchu, Lima\r\n','','','',416,0,0,NULL,NULL,NULL),(888,1,'Dear Spencer,','<p>The tours, guides, restaurants, and hotels were wonderful and far beyond what we had hoped for. Spencer (out of Lima) helped us every step of the way and even substituted a great alternative trip when there were strikes and protests in one area. The English-speaking guides were informative, helpful, kind, and met us at every stop. We have traveled a lot and with many different agencies. I just wish that Peru For Less had a branch in every country! Many thanks to Spencer (in Lima), Kathleen (in Cusco) and to all of your staff! (This testimonial is also posted on TripAdvisor.)</p>','Mary (Pennsylvania, USA)<br />\r\nTraveled to: Arequipa, Sacred Valley, Cusco\r\n','','','',416,0,0,NULL,NULL,NULL),(889,1,'Dear Matt,','<p>In November 2010 I started to search for a tour operator in South America, as we planned to take a 3-week journey in Peru. I found the homepage for Peru For Less. The professional outlook and content made such a serious and strong impression on me that I decided to contact PFL. Very soon after, I received an answer from Matt Greenberg. He became my travel advisor and was very helpful. Many e-mails crossed the Atlantic until we finalized a program which fulfilled all our wishes. Matt always answered our requests promptly and professionally. To build up trust, it was important for me to know that Peru For Less is part of the American Society of Travel Agents (ASTA) and other organizations. </p>\r\n\r\n<p>On our tour in Peru, we were impressed with the services provided to us all the time. The hotels booked for us were very nice, clean, and convenient. All the tours we booked were very well organized and led by friendly, polite, and knowledgeable tour guides. The groups were small, which made it easy to get to know to each person. </p>\r\n\r\n<p>During our South America vacation, we visited Sao Paulo, Lima, the Nazca Lines, Arequipa, the Colca Canyon (one of the highlights there was the Hotel Casa Andina Private), Puno, Cusco, the 2-day Inca Trail to Machu Picchu, and a few days in the Amazon rainforest. A highlight was the train trip from Puno to Cusco. The journey gave us an interesting view into the life of Peruvian villagers and allowed us to admire the beautiful Andean scenery. </p>\r\n\r\n<p>All in all, thank you Matt, for the amazing tour package you prepared for us and for the high quality of service you provided for us. I would highly recommend Peru For Less for anyone who is planning a trip to Peru.</p>\r\n','Heinz and Dagmar (Principality of Liechtenstein)<br />\r\nTraveled to: Sao Paulo (Brazil), Lima, Paracas, Nazca Lines, Arequipa, Colca Canyon, Cusco, 2-day Inca Trail to Machu Picchu, Puerto Maldonado (','','','',416,0,0,NULL,NULL,NULL),(890,1,'Dear Rylee,','<p>The itinerary for this Peru trip was superb and we all enjoyed it very much, as it allowed us to experience a diverse culture and the beautiful scenery of the Amazon rainforest and Machu Picchu.  </p>\r\n \r\n<p>We were very happy with all the activities arranged by The Rainforest Expeditionsâ?? tour guides Ivan and Yuri. The setting and accommodation at the Refugio Amazonas was very unique and a pleasant experience for all of us. Ivan and Yuri are truly excellent tour guides with good information and knowledge as well as humor. All of us enjoyed this part of the trip very much!</p>\r\n \r\n<p>We are very thankful to you for spending so much time and effort to give us a very well planned itinerary and accommodation arrangements. I\'ll be very happy to refer my friends to contact you for their Peru trip!   </p>\r\n','Hai-Dee (New York)<br />\r\nTraveled to: Lima, Puerto Maldonado (Amazon), Cusco, Sacred Valley, Machu Picchu\r\n','','','',416,0,0,NULL,NULL,NULL),(891,1,'Dear Jennie,','<p>My boyfriend and I were looking to book an adventure-filled vacation to Peru. Luckily, we found Peru For Less, which helped us with exactly what we wanted! The company has fabulous trip advisors, ours being Jennie Duong. She was extremely helpful, informative, and I loved how she constantly stayed in close contact with us while planning the trip. She made sure to cater to every need and want and help us to understand what would be best for our trip too!</p>\r\n \r\n<p>Because of the great, in-depth planning we did with Peru For Less, we ended with an amazing, memorable vacation! Lima was beautiful and our hotel accommodations were perfect. Our domestic flights could not have run more smoothly. And we were always met at the airport and picked up from our hotel, as well as consulted before our big hike and white water rafting adventure with advisors from the company who were on time and professional. It took the worry out of the vacation.</p>\r\n \r\n<p>Our hike was phenomenal: the 4-day trek to Machu Picchu. We had a great experience, a truly rewarding one. Cusco was amazing as well. The city has so much culture and history and we enjoyed our time there immensely. The white water rafting was fun as well, but I would not recommend it during the dry season, as there were not too many rapids. If you are looking for something more thrilling, do it during the rainy season, or find rapids at a higher level. But, even with calmer waters, it was a great first experience.</p>\r\n \r\n<p>All in all, this vacation challenged us, and certainly was adventure-filled, which provided us with memories to last a lifetime. We appreciated all the company did for us and honestly would recommend Peru For Less to anyone looking to book a trip to South America. We had a phenomenal experience, I am already thinking of when I can head back and see what other vacations can be planned!</p>\r\n','Maria (United States)<br />\r\nTraveled to: Lima, Cusco, 4-day Inca Trail to Machu Picchu\r\n','','','',416,0,0,NULL,NULL,NULL),(892,1,'Hi Jennie,','<p>My trip was impeccably managed by Peru For Less. You were incredibly responsive and flexible in order to accommodate my fast changing needs, even right up to the time of departure. On arrival, everything was arranged with full guidance and my itinerary waiting for me. I was particularly delighted that Peru For Less worked with an indigenously-owned local companyâ??and this was reflected in the warmth of the service I received throughout the trek. A variety of lovely hot food, an informative guide, and a friendly team made the hike itself a wonderful experience. And watching the morning sun hit Machu Picchu at the end was the experience of a lifetime. Thank you Peru For Less! </p>','Gareth (London, UK)<br />\r\nTraveled to: Inca Trail to Machu Picchu\r\n','','','',416,0,0,NULL,NULL,NULL),(893,1,'Dear Matt,','<p>The tour and transfers were well organized and we were very impressed with Peru For Less. The tour guides were very passionate about their country and culture. Machu Picchu was breathtaking and so was the Scared Valley tour. It was also impressive that you sorted out our accommodation so quickly, especially during peak season. Thank you for your excellent service.</p>','Qissara <br />\r\nTraveled to: Lima, Cusco, Machu Picchu\r\n','','','',416,0,0,NULL,NULL,NULL),(894,1,'Hi Staci,','<p>Our trip was great. Rainforest Expeditions is very professional and very thorough. The scenery, wildlife, and vegetation were just incredible to see. The guides are very well trained, very knowledgeable, and worked hard to ensure that we got to see as much as possible and learn as much as we wanted to learn. The lodge exceeded my expectationsâ??clean, well run, and a private bathroom in each room. The food was exceptional. Staff were friendly and professional. Tours ran promptly, according to the time schedule, so we knew what to expect.  </p>\r\n\r\n<p>Fino, our guide, went out of his way to ensure we saw as much as we possibly could. A bonus was that, because our flight was in the afternoon and we got back to Puerto Maldonado in the morning, they arranged for us to have our own private guide (Paola) and driver on the last day. Paola showed us around Puerto Maldonado and gave us a great deal of information about the history of the area, its economics, politics, etc. What a bonus!</p>\r\n\r\n<p>I would highly recommend Rainforest Expeditions to anyone, and in particular, Posada Amazonas is an incredible place to visit. Thanks for your help in arranging this, Staci.</p>\r\n','Shannon (USA)<br />\r\nTraveled to: Puerto Maldonado (Amazon)\r\n','','','',416,0,0,NULL,NULL,NULL),(895,1,'Hi Aleks,','<p>We would just like to thank you for your wonderful service and recommendations. The trip was no doubt one of the best I have ever taken myself. Peru was absolutely breathtaking...and we definitely enjoyed it to the fullest thanks to all the arrangements and planning that you, and Peru For Less, fulfilled on our behalf. You completely understood and addressed our requirements. The hotels you booked for us were exactly what we were looking for, the pick-ups and transfers made our lives hassle-free, the tours were professional and informative, and Ollantaytambo was a wonderful recommendationâ??we would never have thought of staying longer in this town and it ended up being one of the highlights of the entire trip Thanks again Aleks!</p>','Madelaine & Ghada (Canada)<br />\r\nTraveled to: Lima, Cusco, Sacred Valley, Machu Picchu, Puno, Arequipa\r\n','','','',416,0,0,NULL,NULL,NULL),(896,1,'Hola Matt,','<p>We had a wonderful trip! We absolutely loved Peru. The hotels were amazing. The staff at Aranwa Boutique Hotel were so friendly and very professional. We found them to be very sincere and gracious. In Aguas Calientes, the Inca Terra Hotel had such a wonderful, lush tropical setting, on the river, and is beautifully designed. We had a fire in the fireplace and enjoyed an outstanding dinner in the beautiful dining room with windows everywhere. Magnificent. </p>\r\n\r\n<p>Machu Picchu was totally awesome. The guides were all very friendly, knowledgeable, educated, and very interesting individuals. As hikers and outdoor lovers, we had much in common with them. They were always at the gate ready to greet us; very punctual and reliable.</p>\r\n','Marty (California, USA)<br />\r\nTraveled to: Rio, Iguazu, Buenos Aires, Cusco, Machu Picchu\r\n','','','',416,0,0,NULL,NULL,NULL),(897,1,'Hi Rylee, ','<p>I just wanted to say thank you for everything you did in organizing our trip. We loved Cusco and Machu Picchu and of course Puerto Maldonado was a highlight. We had such a great time and didnâ??t want it to come to an end. This was a trip for me and my other sisters, and we couldnâ??t have done it on our own. Thank you for making this trip possible. I will be sure to pass your email on to friends and family interested in South America travel. </p>','Eva (Florida, USA)<br/>\r\nTraveled to: Lima, Arequipa, Colca Canyon, Cusco, Machu Picchu, Puerto Maldonado\r\n','','','',416,0,0,NULL,NULL,NULL),(898,1,'Hi Rylee,','<p>We are back home, after the most wonderful holidayâ??all due to your efficiency, helpfulness and friendliness!  Thank you for making our holiday such a success.  </p>','Joan(South Africa)<br />\r\nTraveled to: Sao Paolo, Iguazu Falls, Lima, Cusco, Machu Picchu, Buenos Aires\r\n','','','',416,0,0,NULL,NULL,NULL),(899,1,'Hello Rylee,','<p>Just a quick note to let you know the trip went very well and I was pleased with my accommodations, the coordination between transfers, and the informative tours and guides. I was also pleased with the hotel and the room in Lima. My accommodations in Ollantaytambo were fabulous and I would definitively stay there again and the hotel in Cusco was great with a lot of character, a very well appointed room and convenient location close to everything. Overall my experience was wonderful and I\'m looking forward to further explorations of South America. Thanks again for your assistance!</p>','Jule (Ontario, Canada)<br />\r\nTraveled to: Lima, Paracas, Nazca, Arequipa, Colca Canyon, Lake Titicaca, Cusco, Sacred Valley, Machu Picchu\r\n','','','',416,0,0,NULL,NULL,NULL),(900,1,'Hi Rylee,','<p>The trip was amazing â?? thanks! We found Peru a very interesting country and were very pleased with all of our tours and guides. Thank you for making all the arrangements. We had some issues in Iquitos at Explorama: We missed out on the last day there as our flights were cancelled.  However, I understand things happen and you donâ??t have control over the airlines. </p>\r\n<p>I will gladly recommend Peru For Less to anyone wishing to travel to Peru. Also, during our trip, we met other extremely satisfied Peru For Less clients who all sang your praises. Thanks so much for arranging this for us!  </p>\r\n','Nadja (South Africa)<br />\r\nTraveled to: Lima, Nazca, Cusco, Machu Picchu, Iquitos\r\n','','','',416,0,0,NULL,NULL,NULL),(901,1,'Hi Rylee,','<p>We had a wonderful trip overall, despite the change in plan due to a strike in Puno. Everything worked the way it should. All the tours are worth seeing and well organized. The services were very good and punctual. All personnel were pleasant, well trained, and helpful. We got a very informative orientation by Suzanne upon arriving in Cusco. She gave us some really helpful tips regarding restaurants, shopping, and getting around in Cusco. All hotels were very nice overall, well located, and the staff at the hotels were all very pleasant and helpful.  </p>\r\n\r\n<p>Overall, we were very happy with the trip and had a wonderful time. We would definitely use Peru For Less again in the future and would recommend your services to friends and other people. Thanks again for your assistance.</p>\r\n','Jane (Texas, USA)<br />\r\nTraveled to: Lima, Arequipa, Colca Canyon, Cusco, Machu Picchu\r\n','','','',416,0,0,NULL,NULL,NULL),(902,1,'Hi Mari,','<p>I\'ve traveled to several countries in the past and have used a wide range of travel agencies/tour operators, but every single time I either walked away feeling cheated or simply let down. But Peru For Less-in general and you in particular-has changed that outlook of mine forever. The professional way in which you handled all the arrangements and the level of detail which you went into blew my mind. </p>\r\n \r\n<p>Machu Picchu was of course amazing, but just as amazing was the immaculate way you organized the whole trip for us. This was the first trip I took in years during which I was completely at ease, knowing full well that the arrangements for the next day would be in place and you would come through for me every time. I was also very impressed by the fact that you never cut any corners trying to save a few bucks. Rather, quite a few arrangements you made for us were above and beyond what we expected.</p>\r\n \r\n<p>I\'d especially like to thank you for your help when we needed to change our train tickets at the last minute. I\'m sure another company might have also done that, but the personal touch that you put in by calling me in Peru and making sure everything was fine was like icing on the cake for us.</p>\r\n \r\n<p>I\'ll definitely recommend a trip to Machu Picchu to all my friends. But I\'ll also tell them that if they wanted to have a truly memorable experience, then they\'ll have to get in touch with you! Thanks again, Mari!</p>\r\n','Abhinav (India and USA)<br />\r\nTraveled to: Cusco, Sacred Valley, Machu Picchu, Inca Trail\r\n','','','',772,0,0,NULL,NULL,NULL),(903,1,'Dear Kristina,','<p>I cannot tell you how much I enjoyed Peru.  Machu Picchu touched something inside me. Our guide Fabricio was absolutely fantastic and really made the introduction to this magical place something extraordinary. </p>\r\n\r\n<p>All in all the arrangements were exceptional. I was very nervous doing everything online as I usually work with an agent in Cape Town, but I cannot even begin to tell you how smoothly it all went.  Our hotels, pickups, and tours were all perfectly on time and there was not one glitch in any of your arrangements. I would recommend your service to anyone-it is excellent.  </p>\r\n\r\n<p>I am planning to come back to Peru to do the Inca trail and I am also seriously considering a visit to Chile. In both instances, I will not even consider using anybody else to make my arrangements.  The trust I have in you is complete :-).  I do not say this lightly, as I travel a fair amount and I have never had such a hassle free experience. The very best regards to you and your team and a very, very big thank you.  </p>\r\n','Tanya (South Africa)<br />\r\nTraveled to: Cusco, Machu Picchu, Lima\r\n','','','',773,0,0,NULL,NULL,NULL),(904,1,'Hi Jennifer, ','<p>Thank you so much for your assistance with my amazing experience in South America. For as flexible, cost efficient, and simple as it was to organize, everything exceeded my expectations and ran flawlessly.</p>\r\n \r\n<p>Iguazu was spectacular. The hotel was beautiful and relaxing, exactly what I needed after hiking around Buenos Aires for a week! Peru (Cuzco, Sacred Valley, Machu Picchu, and Lima) was the highlight of the six weeks I had in South America.  Colorful, delicious, breathtaking-I wish I had more time there! Machu Picchu is a very special place, something everyone should experience.  As a single traveler, I enjoyed having different tours to join because it enabled me to meet lots of people every day. </p>\r\n\r\n<p>Muchas gracias para todos, mis viajes estuvan muy excellente! I will definitely be contacting you in the future for my return.</p>\r\n','Cayley (Alberta, Canada)<br />\r\nTraveled to: Lima, Cusco, Machu Picchu, Iguazu \r\n','','','',774,0,0,NULL,NULL,NULL),(905,1,'Dear Rylee,','<p>Thanks to highly recommended PFL, we had a fabulous time!  Representatives and drivers were there to meet us on time; the hotels were great; the tours were punctual and had friendly and extremely well informed guides. Prepaid bus, train, and plane reservations made travel smooth with additional help from transfer drivers. We had great fun meeting up with other PFL travelers! I usually arrange my own travel plans, but I could not have done Peru without your excellent preparation and team to guide us all the way-all within our required budget! </p>','Rita (Washington, USA)<br />\r\nTraveled to: Lima, Nazca, Arequipa, Colca Canyon, Cusco, Machu Picchu\r\n','','','',774,0,0,NULL,NULL,NULL),(906,1,'Dear Silvana Zavala,','<p>Greetings and best wishes to you! The four of us enjoyed our trip very much. At every city we visited we were welcomed by your English-speaking guides and representatives. We never once were worried about the arrangements. The hotels were really good and all your guides and staff members were excellent. All the arrangements were fantastic. I personally look forward to another pleasant trip with Peru For Less. </p>\r\n\r\n<p>Our travel agency here said they had never seen such great guidance and correspondence as they did from your company. They said that in the future for any Peru inquiries from their clients, they will get in touch with Peru For Less. I congratulate you for all you did and appreciate your efficiency. God be with you.</p>\r\n','Ramabraham (India)<br />\r\nTraveled to: Lima, Cusco, Sacred Valley, Machu Picchu\r\n','','','',775,0,0,NULL,NULL,NULL),(907,1,'Hi Staci,','<p>We had so much fun in Peru and we are now back in New York. We were sad when we woke up and we realized we were not in Cusco anymore. Thank you for the seamless travel arrangements you provided for us-all the tours were on time, if not early, and all the guides were good and passionate (we were surprised to know that Fabricio is a descendant of one of the last Incas!). It was truly an amazing experience. Until the next time, hopefully Chile and Ecuador!</p>','Coreena (New York, USA)<br />\r\nTraveled to: Lima, Cusco, Machu Picchu\r\n','','','',776,0,0,NULL,NULL,NULL),(908,1,'Dear Jennifer,','<p>We just wanted to thank Peru For Less for putting together our recent trip to Peru. Everything was seamless, all of the drivers were right on time (if not early), and the tour guides were so knowledgeable. We missed our connection to Cusco, and within minutes of calling the office in Peru, they had alerted our airport transfer, and made arrangements to take us directly to our first tour and drop our luggage off at the hotel. And when we wanted to arrange a tour of Lima three days before we were set to arrive there, Peru For Less made it happen again. Thanks again! Our trip would not have been the same without you.</p>','Andrew and Brooke (New York, USA) <br/>\r\nTraveled to: Lima, Cusco, Machu Picchu, Puerto Maldonado\r\n','','','',777,0,0,NULL,NULL,NULL),(909,1,'Hi Silvana,','<p>The itinerary you planned for me was perfect. From pick-up at the airport to drop-off at the airport, everything went smoothly. The drivers in Lima and Cusco were courteous, prompt, and safe. The guide in Cusco was charming, knowledgeable, and willing to adjust to my pace. Thank you.</p>','Max. (New York, USA)<br/>\r\nTraveled to: Lima, Cusco, Machu Picchu','','','',778,0,0,NULL,NULL,NULL),(910,1,'Dear Mari-Ellena, ','<p>My trip to Cusco and Machu Picchu was awesome, an experience I will never forget. During my 9 day trip each day was as good if not better than the previous day. I had no idea how to plan my trip, but Jennifer and Mari-Ellena of Peru For Less set everything up for me and, thanks to them, this trip ranks in the top five things I will remember the rest of my life.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>I stayed at the Casa del Sol Hotel in Cusco where I was briefed on what to expect during my stay in Peru, including my tours and Inca Trail hike. The hotel staff were highly professional, friendly, and answered any questions I had. I would recommend this hotel to anyone. I would also recommend the city and Sacred Valley tours to anyone going to Peru. A must see! The tour guides are highly motivated and believe in the culture and are detail orientated from start to finish.</p>\r\n \r\n<p>The third night I met Edgar, my Inca Trail guide. Edgar was phenomenal. He explained what to expect over the next 4 days, what I needed to take, and what to expect on the trek. Edgar is a unique individual, and when we parted ways I felt like he was truly a friend, not just an acquaintance. I will remember him as a highlight of the tour.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>We finally made it to Machu Picchu - and, as one would say, it was \"truly breathtaking.\" Not a cloud in the sky and the closer you got to the ruins, the more awe inspiring it looked. Edgar explained every detail as we strolled through the ruins. Not once during the whole 4 days did he try to rush me in anyway, he instilled confidence in me so I had no doubt I could finish the trek. Also, the porters and cooks were fabulous. The soups and rice pudding were the best I\'ve ever eaten in my life.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>The only thing that could have made my trip a little better would have been if I would have learned a little Spanish but, then again, it did not detract from my experience.  Please pass on my gratitude to Edgar, the hotel staff, Jennifer, Mari-Ellena, and everyone who helped set up my trek. I recommend this tour from Peru For Less to everyone. What an experience!</p>\r\n','Peter (Oregon, USA)<br />\r\nTraveled to: Lima, Cusco, 4-day Inca Trail, Machu Picchu            \r\n','','','',779,0,0,NULL,NULL,NULL),(911,1,'Hello Kelly,','<p>I can\'t thank you enough for helping make my dream trip a reality! Peru was everything I had imagined, and more. Every aspect of the trip that you had planned for us went smoothly.  </p>\r\n\r\n<p>The drivers were on time, and very courteous. The tour guides were wonderful, especially, David. He went the extra mile to explain things to us in detail, and to answer my never ending questions. All of the hotels that you sent us to were wonderful - excellent choices. The locations were great, and the staff was friendly and helpful. </p>\r\n\r\n<p>Your suggestion to take the Maras and Moray tour was right on, that was a wonderful tour. I\'m also so happy you had us stay in the Sacred Valley and extra day. Ollantaytambo was fascinating, and well worth spending extra time there. Also thanks to your suggestions, we had some wonderful meals in Lima. Cala was an excellent recommendation for dinner. The seafood was awesome. Next time I plan a trip to Latin America, you\'ll be the first person I call! Many thanks!</p>\r\n','Carol (United States)<br />\r\nTraveled to: Lima, Cusco, Sacred Valley, Machu Picchu\r\n','','','',100000,0,0,NULL,'2014-09-10 22:55:12',NULL),(912,1,'Hi Kristina,','<p>We had a great time on our honeymoon! Everything was spectacular, and we were both really pleased that we booked through Peru For Less. We met a few people that were on their own and having to take taxis or walk places, who had run into some problems. It was great peace of mind knowing that we were always going to be picked up. We only had one morning with an issue, where our transport to the hotel was late, but everyone was very on top of things, and alternate transport was arranged and we made it to the airport in time to catch our flight. </p>\r\n\r\n<p>We loved the fact that we were able to tailor the trip to what we were looking for, the flexibility was great. The dunebuggy & sandboard excursion that we added on was probably the most fun we had on the whole trip! The quality of hotels was beyond what we were expecting, and all of the staff were courteous and helpful. Two weeks was definitely not enough time, we would love to go back, and Peru For Less would definitely be the first place we\'d check for our next trip.</p>\r\n','Rebecca & Jason (Ontario, Canada)<br/>\r\nTraveled to: Lima, Paracas, Nazca, Arequipa, Colca Canyon, Cusco,  Machu Picchu\r\n','','','',417,0,0,NULL,NULL,NULL),(913,1,'Dear Jennie,','<p>We had a GREAT TIME! I\'d like to thank you for all the efforts you made to make our trip a successful one. WE LOVED IT. </p>','Rosy (Florida, USA)<br/>\r\nTraveled to:  Lima, Cusco, Sacred Valley, Machu Picchu\r\n','','','',417,0,0,NULL,NULL,NULL),(914,1,'Hi Silvana,','<p>We loved Peru and especially the time spent in Machu Picchu. Susanna, in Cusco, was really helpful, friendly, and nice.  We really appreciated the time she spent explaining to us our itinerary.  All the drivers and guides were very courteous and prompt. Thanks for your wonderful help with our trip to Peru! </p>','Cawin and Vance (California, USA)<br/>\r\nTraveled to: Lima, Cusco\r\n','','','',417,0,0,NULL,NULL,NULL),(915,1,'Dear Rylee,','<p>When we first had the idea to visit places in South America, we found it very difficult to find someone who could put together an itinerary to include what we wanted to do and see in the time frame we had to travel, which was one month. It started to look like we wouldn\'t be able to go and we would have to rethink our dream honeymoon......but then we found Rylee at Latin America For less and with just a brief synopsis of what we hoped to achieve, she came back with a fantastic itinerary. However, we were still a little off on budget and times so again we went back to Rylee who was able to work with what we had and didn\'t mind at all changing things around to suit us. </p>\r\n\r\n<p>Everything was taken care of for us so we could just arrive from Ireland and start our honeymoon without trying to organize things from scratch. Airport transfers, hotels, city tours, special excursions, and internal flights were all taken care of; all we had to do was go and enjoy the samba of Rio, the steak and wine of Buenos Aires, the beauty of Iguazu, the wonder of Machu Picchu, and the wildlife of the Galapagos. </p>\r\n','Iseult (Dublin, Ireland)<br/>\r\nTraveled to: Rio de Janiero, Buzios, Iguazu, Buenos Aires, Lima, Cusco, Machu Picchu, Quito, the Galapagos \r\n','','','',417,0,0,NULL,NULL,NULL),(916,1,'Hi Rylee, ','<p>Our trip was great!!!  I\'m SO glad we traveled with you. The hotels were great, the tour guides were wonderful (we especially loved Carlos), and it was so nice to have PFL folks meet us everywhere we went. It really did make for worry-free traveling (sickness aside!). I have recommended PFL (or LAFL) to anyone who thinks they might be traveling in that region. Any chance you also work in Costa Rica?  We may be attending a wedding there next spring. . . Thanks again, so much, for all of your help.  We truly had a wonderful trip. </p>','Laura (Ohio, USA)<br/>\r\nTraveled to: Cusco, Machu Picchu\r\n','','','',417,0,0,NULL,NULL,NULL),(917,1,'Hello Rylee,','<p>My husband I had a blast in Peru! It was much more than we were expecting! The Peruvian people were very kind. The food was out of this world. The history and sights never failed to impress. All of the services provided by Peru For less were dependable, reliable, and timely. All our guides had extensive knowledge; we enjoyed learning from each of them. We had no transportation or communication problems at anytime during our travels. We went all over Peru, including Lima, Cusco, Machu Picchu, Puno, Isla Suasi, Arequipa, and Nazca. And we are planning to go back to visit the jungle and Paracas! When the time comes, we most certainly will travel with Peru For less again.  Thank you for an exceptional travel experience! </p>','Lisa (New Mexico, USA)<br/>\r\nTraveled to: Lima, Cusco, Puno Isla Suasi, Arequipa, Colca Canyon, Nazca\r\n','','','',417,0,0,NULL,NULL,NULL),(918,1,'Dear Kelly, ','<p>Thank you very much for all the services you provided on our trip to Iquitos, Peru. Everything went smoothly and was well organized by your local agent. The tour guide was excellent, very kind and helpful. The Saiba Top Resort was also very nice with a good hospitality staff. Our group enjoyed the trip very much and hopes to go back again. Again, I want to thank you for the great trip you organized. </p>','Chattrin (Thailand)<br/>\r\nTraveled to: Iquitos\r\n','','','',417,0,0,NULL,NULL,NULL),(919,1,'Dear Jennie, ','<p>The Inca Trail hike to Machu Picchu was better than I could have envisioned. It was not an easy hike, but it was fun pushing myself and the views were more than worth it. I had no idea the views were so beautiful! I would recommend this trip to anyone. The Wayki Trek group we went with was amazing. The food was delicious, there was plenty of water, they had warm tea/coffee waiting for us in the morning, and they even had warm water for us to wash our face, etc., at the end of each night, which made us so comfortable. Antonio, our guide, spoke excellent English, had tons of knowledge about the culture/Machu Picchu/etc., and was so friendly. When we wanted to hike Huyana Picchu, he told us he\'s not sure it can happen (since people wait in line first thing in the morning and we wouldn\'t be there that early) but he would try. Well he made it work and we were able to hike it! We couldn\'t have been happier with the service and the trek! </p>','Elizabeth (California, USA)<br/>\r\nTraveled to: Inca Trail to Machu Picchu\r\n','','','',417,0,0,NULL,NULL,NULL),(920,1,'Hi Kelly Chrystal','<p>Angela and I want to congratulate you for an excellently planned trip, every detail of which was brilliantly executed. Everybody we met and every place we went to could not be better. We enjoyed every moment of our stay in Peru, not only because it is a beautiful country with lovely, smiling people, but also because we had nothing to worry about. Everything had been taken care of in the best possible way. We even were happy to miss our flight back home (due to fog), as this gave us the opportunity to spend an extra day in Lima, which proved to be a wonderful experience.   </p>\r\n\r\n<p>If one asks us of the one thing that we will never forget, it has to be the fact that everybody we met was genuinely nice, friendly, and helpful. They all enjoyed what they were doing and made us feel welcome and â??â??at home.â??â?? </p>\r\n\r\n<p>We can\'t be thankful enough to Dario of Peru For Less, the young man at the airport in Cusco, who did so much, in a calm and friendly way, to help us when we were stuck there because of the fog and running out of time to catch our flight from Lima to Paris. The same goes for the staff of â??iPeruâ? at the airport. </p>\r\n\r\n<p>Peru is a place we want to go back to and PERU FOR LESS will certainly be the agent we will use again. It will also be the one weâ??ll recommend to friends and relatives. </p>\r\n','Thanks and regards,<br/>\r\n\r\nAngela &amp; Nikos <br/>\r\nTraveled to: Lima, Amazon, Cusco, Machu Picchu\r\n','','','',417,0,0,NULL,NULL,NULL),(921,1,'Hi Kelly H,','<p>We had a wonderful trip even with all the rain! Thank you for your help and planning.  It was wonderful to know that we could always depend on you and Peru For Less! Every transfer, bus ride, train ride, tour, etc. went smoothly and safely! The hotels were wonderful, although we had our favorites.  </p>\r\n\r\n<p>We had a great experience and Brianne plans on coming back. We would recommend Peru For Less and you specifically for anyoneâ??s travel needs! You all were able to handle the flexibility of late planes, closed airports, etc. Thank you for having someone meet me in the middle of the night in Lima when my plane was so late. That was a scary experience for me as an inexperienced traveler and English only speaker!  </p>\r\n\r\n<p>In Cusco, we visited the Chocolate Factory just off the square.  That was a neat experience for chocolate lovers. I can\'t say how much we appreciated you for all your planning for a smooth and safe trip, the wonderful experience, informative guides, excellent food, and the trip of a lifetime!     </p>\r\n','Janet (Colorado, USA)<br/>\r\nTraveled to: Lima, Arequipa, Puno, Cusco, Puerto Maldonado \r\n','','','',417,0,0,NULL,NULL,NULL),(922,1,'Dear Kristina,','<p>Thank you so much for a seamless and well organized adventure in Peru! I had done some research on my own, and knew the places I wanted to visit, and Peru for Less put together the best itinerary. I was very impressed with the hotels that were provided, and would happily recommend them to anyone as well as your planning services. We loved Colca Lodge, Casa San Blas, El Albergue, and the Machu Picchu Pueblo hotels the most.  </p>\r\n \r\n<p>The rep who met us in Cusco was particularly great, as she walked us through the next couple of days which were a little challenging logistically. At the last minute, we inadvertently realized we did not have our train tickets to Machu Picchu. I was able to call and got assistance immediately. The tickets were emailed to our hotel, and all was well. Your company is very easy to reach and very responsive! Also the rep in Cusco spent a lot of time making sure we understood what was happening (what to bring, etc.) before we set off for our train trip from the Sacred Valley. Another big plus was that we often had small or even private guide situations. I really wasnâ??t expecting this, and it was great. All of the guides were extremely knowledgeable and personable. After our tour in Arequipa, we felt like we had made a new friend with our guide. We even hugged her goodbye with tears in our eyes.  </p>   \r\n \r\n<p>This trip has sparked a love for learning even more about Incan history and culture. It was a wonderful 25 year anniversary trip, and I am grateful for the assistance/guidance I had from Peru For Less. Thanks for the wonderful memories! </p>\r\n','Kathy (Missouri, USA)<br/>\r\nTraveled to: Arequipa, Puno, Cusco, Sacred Valley, Machu Picchu\r\n','','','',417,0,0,NULL,NULL,NULL),(923,1,'Dear Silvana,','<p>Silvana, the trip was amazing! You planned a great combination of sights for us to seeâ?¦ Cusco was beautiful, the views that we saw were incredible. It was nice to have the opportunity to choose what we wanted to eat and the convenience of the hotel in relation to the main square made it easy to experience everything around there. It was nice to really experience the culture there because even though the town accommodates tourists a lot, it was right in the middle of locals that were genuinely friendly and helpful. The staff at the hotel went out of their way to make us feel comfortable and the woman that initially met us was really willing to help us out. You did an excellent job and I will be happy to refer you to friends! </p>','Elizabeth <br/>\r\nTraveled to: Lima, Cusco, Machu Picchu, Puerto Maldonado\r\n','','','',417,0,0,NULL,NULL,NULL),(924,1,'Dear Staci,','<p>Thank you so much for everything you did to arrange this trip! We had a truly wonderful time!  Everything you set up worked perfectlyâ??all of the flights/tours/pickups, etc. Some of the hotels were really fantastic too â?? the girls loved Ceiba Tops and the jungle, and we all really enjoy the Casa Andina in Cusco (where they gave us huge, beautiful rooms and the service was fantastic) and Inkaterra in Machu Picchu. I would absolutely recommend Peru for Less! Thanks again! </p>','Susan (USA)<br/>\r\nTraveled to: Lima, Iquitos, Cusco, Machu Picchu\r\n','','','',417,0,0,NULL,NULL,NULL),(925,1,'Hi Rylee, ','<p>We really enjoyed our trip to Peru. It was an amazing vacation. I personally was very pleased with Peru For Less. It was very convenient to have your representatives waiting to escort us from one destination to the next. And our guides were very knowledgeable and a pleasure to tour with. And our accommodations were also quite comfortable, even in the rainforest, where we expected conditions to be rather primitive. On the whole, I was extremely pleased with the way the trip was put together. Thank you so much for working with us in such a short timeframe. </p>','Sheryl (Tennessee, USA)<br/>\r\nTraveled to: Lima, Arequipa, Colca Canyon, Cusco, Machu Picchu, Puerto Maldonado\r\n','','','',417,0,0,NULL,NULL,NULL),(926,1,'Hi Rylee,','<p>Everything worked like clockwork. Someone met us at every connection. The hotels were very nice especially the Hotel San Blas in Cusco. It was very charming. We loved Peru and thought you did a fantastic job planning everything. The highlight was the Amazon. I really did not know what to expect, but it turned out to be the best part of the trip. I had a wonderful trip, and I look forward to working with you again on my next trip to South  America. </p>','Bryan and Elizabeth (Arizona, USA)<br/>\r\nTraveled to: Lima, Arequipa, Puno, Cusco, Machu Picchu, Puerto Maldonado\r\n','','','',417,0,0,NULL,NULL,NULL),(927,1,'Hi Jennie,','<p>Your service was excellent. I truly appreciate all of your help from the beginning to the end during my trip in PERU. Based on our conversations and e-mails, I think that you are an excellent travel adviser. There was never a moment where I felt that you weren\'t responding to me in a timely matter or giving me false or misleading information.  </p>\r\n\r\n<p>Overall, the front end experience with you was great! I know many times I had so many questions for you to answer. I felt bad at times asking so many questions but I guess I am one of those types that wants to know things ahead if time. I truly appreciate your patience and help with everything.  Your representative Brenna was very helpful also. Keep up the good work. </p>\r\n','Choulong (Illinois, USA)<br/>\r\nTraveled to: Cusco, Sacred Valley\r\n','','','',417,0,0,NULL,NULL,NULL),(928,1,'Hi Rylee, ','<p>We had a great trip in Peru thanks to your careful planning. I know we spent months putting together this itinerary and I am glad we did. All of your help and ideas paid off. We loved the Casa Andina in the Sacred Valley. We enjoyed seeing the stars in the planetarium and thought all the staff was superb. Machu Picchu, of course, was impressive and the highlight of the trip. </p>\r\n<p>Everything was splendid. Thank you so much for all of your assistance. </p>\r\n','Heather and Larry Engle (New York, USA)<br/>\r\nTraveled to: Arequipa, Colca Canyon, Puno, Cusco, Sacred Valley, Machu Picchu\r\n','','','',417,0,0,NULL,NULL,NULL),(929,1,'Hi Jennie','<p>Our trip was fabulous and we were very impressed with Peru For Less.  We fell in love with the country and many of the people.  Both Ali and I said we would like to return one day. Our favorite places/activities were: the Inca trail to Machu Picchu, Cusco, the Paracas and Nazca trip, and the Andean Explorer ride. We would not hesitate to recommend Peru For Less to someone else</p>','Sam and Ali (Australia)<br/>\r\nTraveled to: Lima, Paracas, Nazca Lines, Puno, Cusco, Inca Trail to Machu Picchu\r\n','','','',417,0,0,NULL,NULL,NULL),(930,1,'Hi Kelly,','<p>Overall, the trip was excellent.  Peru is an amazing country, and we were able to see some of its best facets. The smaller group sizes on the Inca Trail and Amazon excursions made for a very enjoyable experience. The high quality of rafting in the Sacred Valley, city tours (Lima and Cuzco), and train ride from Aqua Calientes made for some great memories. Almost all of the transfers went smoothly, and the accommodations exceeded expectations. Having most of the travel taxes paid in advance was very convenient. The next day activity updates and briefings in the evening were also very helpful. All in all, things went really smoothly, and I appreciate how much planning you put into our program. It was very relaxing to focus our efforts on enjoying Peru, and not on the travel details. </p>','Jeremiah <br/>\r\nTraveled to: Lima, Cusco, Inca Trail to Machu Picchu, Puerto Maldonado, Lake Titicaca\r\n','','','',417,0,0,NULL,NULL,NULL),(931,1,'Hi Rylee','<p>Thank you so much! The trip was wonderful! Everything was perfectly planned; we were met at each stop of the trip by someone who took us around. Our guides were all excellent, friendly, and knowledgeable (especially Fabricio at Machu Picchu). The hotels were all clean and professional. We particularly liked our hotel in Aguas Calientes, which was very helpful and accommodating. There was nothing you could have done to be more helpful -- you were extremely courteous, quick to respond, knowledgeable, and offered us a nice variety of options. Thank you so much for all of your help planning this trip. It was amazing. </p>','Joe (Pennsylvania, USA)<br/>\r\nTraveled to: Cusco, Machu Picchu\r\n','','','',417,0,0,NULL,NULL,NULL),(932,1,'Dear Riva,','<p>Our trip to Peru, Machu Picchu, surrounding areas, and the Amazon River area was exciting and extremely enjoyable.  Peru For Less did a great job of making all the arrangements, plane connections, hotels, guides, etc...  Their guides were very knowledgeable, met us at every step, spoke good English, etc...  Our destination manager Riva Bacquet did a great job and was highly information and had good suggestions. I would highly recommend their services. </p>','Bill (New Mexico, USA)<br/>\r\nTraveled to: Lima, Machu Picchu, Cuzco, Puerto Maldonado\r\n','','','',417,0,0,NULL,NULL,NULL),(933,1,'Hi Kelly,','<p>We were really happy with our trip and want you to know that the support you provided before hand was invaluable - given our lack of understanding of customs and our lack of Spanish. </p>\r\n\r\n<p>The highlights for us were the beautiful cities of Arequipa and Cusco; the fabulous setting and accommodation on Lake Titicaca; Machu Picchu (where we were able to access tickets to revisit on our second day by going to the local ticket office when we arrived); and then all topped off with a great trip to the Amazon (the resort was fantastic and the canopy walk was a great bonus.) </p>\r\n','Peter (Australia)<br/>\r\nTraveled to: Arequipa, Colca Canyon, Puno, Cusco, Machu Picchu, Iquitos\r\n','','','',417,0,0,NULL,NULL,NULL),(934,1,'Hello Rylee, ','<p>We had a wonderful trip to Peru. We loved all the guides and found them quite helpful as well as the staff around Peru. You were fabulous to work with! You planned this trip with three days notice and we really enjoyed it. I will certainly recommend you to my friends and family. </p>','Hyon (Florida, USA)<br/>\r\nTraveled to: Lima, Cusco, Machu Picchu, Puno\r\n','','','',417,0,0,NULL,NULL,NULL),(935,1,'Hi Rylee,','<p>Once more you put together a great trip. This was one of the best ones. Not many vacations when you can swim with sea lions in the morning and walk with giant tortoises in the afternoon. All the transfers went on schedule. The guy who worked with us in Quito was especially helpful considering the short durations of our transfers.  Another great and memorable trip. </p>','David (Texas, USA)<br/>\r\nTraveled to: Quito, Galapagos Islands (Ecuador)\r\n','','','',417,0,0,NULL,NULL,NULL),(936,1,'Hi Silvana,','<p>Just wanted to let you know we had such a fantastic time in Peru and we love love, love, your country! I will truly recommend you to my friends in the UK as well as back home in Indonesia. Thank you and I do hope to come back one day. </p>','Irma (United Kingdom)<br/>\r\nTraveled to: Lima, Cusco\r\n','','','',417,0,0,NULL,NULL,NULL),(937,1,'Dear Kelly,','<p>Thanks for the opportunity for feedback on our recent trip to Peru. Cusco and Machu Picchu were wonderful and certainly exceeded our expectations! Peru For Less certainly produced a fabulous experience for us four. </p>','Mike <br/>\r\nTraveled to: Lima, Cusco, Machu Picchu\r\n','','','',417,0,0,NULL,NULL,NULL),(938,1,'Hi Kristina,','<p>Our trip through Argentina and Peru was truly a trip of a lifetime. I appreciated your patience and guidance over the nearly two years it took for me to sort out what would be fun for Sue as her retirement celebration. </p>\r\n\r\n<p>All the arrangements were perfect - there was always a person waiting to greet us at the airport and a car or van to take us to each event on our itinerary. The six hotels you arranged for us during our two week trip were everything we asked for and more. </p>\r\n\r\n<p>The sites around Buenos Aires, Iguazu Falls, Cusco, Machu Picchu, and Lima were breathtaking. Everyone gave us great suggestions and \"insider\'s tips\" so we quickly got the lay of the land and could enjoy things the \"locals\" prefer.  It was great to see some of the sites when the crowds were light or even non-existent. Thank you for all your help. </p>\r\n','Rich and Sue (Illinois, USA) <br/>\r\nTraveled to: Buenos Aires, Iguazu, Lima, Cusco, Machu Picchu\r\n','','','',100001,0,0,NULL,'2014-09-10 22:55:12',NULL),(939,1,'Dear Staci,','<p>When we made our South American travel arrangements with you we had little doubt that we would enjoy our time there. This turned out to be corrected, as there were so many wonderful experiences on our itinerary. </p>\r\n\r\n<p>Our main concern was whether the logistics would work out as planned: being met off flights; punctual pick-ups for travel connections and tours; hotels that were expecting us and so on. To be able to depend on the plan was very important for our peace-of-mind as planning from New Zealand seemed so far away. And it turned out just fine. For instance, our flight from Santiago to Quito landed four hours later than scheduled. We were concerned that out our courier would not be there, but we were most pleasantly surprised to find our courier still waiting for us.   </p>\r\n\r\n<p>That was service at its best, and all the other connections worked like clockwork as well. Also worthy of mention is the quality of the guides that were organised for us. The standard was high and in most cases exceptional in their knowledge, communication ability, humor, and general friendliness. The standard of transport was generally very good - we have never been in so many Mercedes vehicles in such a short time period, even if they were mini-coaches. </p>\r\n\r\n<p>Any time that there was a change in plans you notified us immediately, both via e-mail and via a phone call to our hotel. We felt free to contact you any time and knew that our questions would be answered immediately. </p>\r\n\r\n<p>Our appreciation to all the guides, drivers, and hotel staff you organised throughout our holiday, and our thanks to you and Peru For Less for providing such a wonderful service. We would be happy to recommend you to anyone considering a holiday in South America. </p>\r\n','Paul and Sue (Wellington, New Zealand)<br/>\r\nTraveled to: Santiago, Quito, Lima, Paracas, Nazca, Arequipa, Colca Canyon, Puno, Cusco, Sacred Valley, Machu Picchu, Puerto Maldonado\r\n','','','',100002,0,0,NULL,'2014-09-10 22:55:11',NULL),(940,1,'Hi Rylee,','<p>Our trip was fantastic! We really appreciate the professional manner in which Peru For Less handled ALL arrangements for our visit to Peru. What a wonderful experience!</p>\n<p><strong>Although all of us had traveled extensively and always without using a travel service, we felt Peru might be a special challenge due to the languages and topography. We did not want to waste our time finding our way around such a varied and difficult landscape. So we selected Peru For Less to handle all arrangements and we are truly grateful!</strong> You ALWAYS provided expert guides...Juliaca, Lake Titicaca, Cusco, the Sacred Valley, Machu Picchu, Lima...we were met on time everywhere and escorted to our hotels or taken directly on a tour.</p>\n<p>Your personnel were always there on time, knew exactly what they were doing, helped us with travel, restaurants, and every accommodation. The Aranwa hotel in Cusco was OUTSTANDING. Many thanks for arranging this. We loved Hatun Inti in Machu Picchu as well.<strong> THANK YOU so much for all of your assistance in planning the trip, your recommendations, and your check-ups while traveling.</strong></p>\n<p><strong>We could not have asked for more personal or professional service.</strong> Plus, two of us had to delay our departure to Peru for four days due to illness, and the free travel insurance Peru For Less offered through iTravelInsured completely reimbursed us for all expenses (almost $1,000) related to our delayed departure.</p>\n<p><strong>Rylee, your personal assistance in accommodating the desires of six travelers was exceptional.</strong> We all thank you for making our trip so memorable.</p>\n','John (Ohio, USA)<br/>\r\nTraveled to: Lima, Arequipa, Colca Canyon, Puno, Cusco, Machu Picchu\r\n','','','\"We selected Peru For Less to handle all arrangements and we are truly grateful!\"',100053,0,0,NULL,'2014-09-10 23:08:25',NULL),(941,1,'Hi Kelly,','<p>We arrived in Cusco early in the morning we were met by our Peru For Less representative. She was very friendly and took us to our hotel. We had a bit of a rest before we were collected in the afternoon to see the sights around Cusco. Once again the representatives were prompt. The driver and guide were very friendly, and the guide was also informative and funny. We loved the Cathedral and Saqsaywaman. </p>\r\n\r\n<p>The next morning we had to be up bright and early to go to Machu Picchu. Train ride there was stunning. We were served a snack in style. When we got to the town at the bottom of Machu Picchu the guide was there to collect us and show us the way to the busses. Machu Picchu is one of the most stunning places I have ever been to. I can\'t imagine how long it took them to get all those rocks on top of one another, but the fact that they did it is amazing. </p>\r\n\r\n<p>I would recommend Peru For Less to all my friends. The service we recieved was excellent and everything went like clockwork. Thanks to Kelly for arranging the package to our needs and for all your advice and help. </p>\r\n','Linda du Toit Family<br/>\r\nTraveled to: Cusco, Machu Picchu\r\n','','','',100003,0,0,NULL,'2014-09-10 22:55:11',NULL),(942,1,'Hi Kelly,','<p>We had an amazing time in Peru, thanks to Peru For Less. We spent 10 days in Peru and each destination was just incredible and the people were so friendly.  The trip was very well planned and coordinated. In addition, we really enjoyed the hotel accommodations in all the cities, the guided tours were a lot of fun, and the tour guides were very knowledgeable.  Kelly, our travel advisor, was very helpful and answered all our questions before and during the trip. I would definitely recommend Latin America For Less to any of my friends.  Thank you for arranging an experience of a lifetime. </p>','Amit and Meghana (New Jersey, USA)<br/>\r\nTraveled to: Lima, Cusco, Sacred Valley, Machu Picchu, Puno, Lake Titicaca, Colca Canyon, Arequipa\r\n','','','',100004,0,0,NULL,'2014-09-10 22:55:11',NULL),(943,1,'Hi Matt,','<p>We had a great trip! The one day Inca Trail hike was fabulous-loved our guide Edwin! I wished we would\'ve had more time to spend in the Galapagos-because we only did the short cruise we didn\'t get to see all of the animals we\'d like to have seen. Overall we had excellent guides and excellent accommodations. I was very impressed with the people-everyone was so nice and the cities were so clean, especially Cusco.  Thanks so much for all your help putting the trip together!  </p>','Carolyn and Ken (Texas, USA)<br/>\r\nTraveled to: Lima, Cusco, Machu Picchu (Peru), Quito, Galapagos Islands, Guayaquil (Ecuador)\r\n','','','',100005,0,0,NULL,'2014-09-10 22:55:11',NULL),(944,1,'Hi Kelly C, ','<p>The trip was fantastic. Machu Picchu: What a place! It was much larger than I thought it would be. I was in awe when I first arrived there. Our tour guide Maria of the other various sites was fantastic. She is so knowledgeable of the history of the Incas. I was very much impressed with her. Fabricio, our guide at Machu Picchu, is also well informed. The hotel staff at Casa San Blas Boutique Hotel are all very professional and polite. I enjoyed every minute of my stay there. I enjoyed the various festivals that were taking place during my stay and the food was fantastic. Peru is a very beautiful country with beautiful, friendly people. I wish I could have stayed for at least another week.  Thank you so much. It was an experience that I will never forget.  </p>','Thomas (USA)<br/>\r\nTraveled to: Cusco and Machu Picchu\r\n','','','',100006,0,0,NULL,'2014-09-10 22:55:11',NULL),(945,1,'Dear Silvana,','<p>We wanted to thank you for the experience of lifetime that we had in Peru. It was a great pleasure to work with you and we feel lucky meeting you in person. To those looking for a travel agency to book a trip to Latin America with, we would like to say: Look no more, and ask for Silvana!</p>\r\n<p><strong>From day one she was able to understand our requirements and offer the right package for us (we did a custom tour selecting dates and itinerary).</strong> All of the hotels that Silvana suggested were excellent. <strong>The logistics of the trip went without a glitch, and it was nice to ponder Incan history rather than trying to figure out where to get a taxi at 6 AM.</strong></p>\r\n<p>Silvana called and emailed us during the trip, making sure things were running smoothly. She answered all ad-hoc questions that we had. There are some risks even in a perfectly planned trip, and things that are out of anybody\'s control. Silvana stepped in and saved our trip, and all we remember now is her kindness and the magical experience she managed to create for us.</p>\r\n<p><strong>We compared notes on other travel agencies with people that we met during our Peru vacation, and concluded that we had the best experience and the most transparency while working with our agency.</strong> We recommend Peru For Less and Silvana to everybody how is interested in traveling to Latin America.</p>\r\n','Irina and Vladimir (New Jersey, USA)<br/>\r\nTraveled to: Lima, Cusco, 4-day Inca Trail to Machu Picchu, Puerto Maldonado, Paracas\r\n','','','\"Silvana stepped in and saved our trip, and all we remember now is her kindness and the magical experience she managed to create for us.\"',100046,0,0,NULL,'2014-09-10 22:55:09',NULL),(946,1,'Hello Staci,','<p>Thank you so much for all of your help with our trip to Peru. This was the first time my mom has ever left the United States and I wanted to make it special-and with your help I was able to.  From the very beginning you were prompt in answering all of my questions and concerns with no hesitation, even changing our itinerary up to 9 times until it was perfect! We were so impressed that a Peruvian representative was promptly there to greet us at every stop. Despite the unfortunate strikes that occurred in Puno while we were there, we were contacted immediately and re-routed with ease. I couldn\'t ask for more! I look forward to booking an upcoming to trip to Brazil with you in the coming years.  Muchisimas Gracias! </p>','Janel (California, USA)<br/>\r\nTraveled to: Lima, Nazca, Arequipa, Colca Canyon, Cusco, Sacred Valley, Machu Picchu\r\n','','','',100007,0,0,NULL,'2014-09-10 22:55:11',NULL),(947,1,'Hi Silvana,','<p>I just wanted to say thanks for making all the arrangements for our Peru vacation! We had a wonderful time, and everything went smoothly during the course of the 16 days! All of our guides were excellent, and we have lasting memories of our 5-day Salkantay hike to Machu Picchu! </p>','Patrick (California, USA)<br/>\r\nTraveled to: Lima, Puno, Cusco, Salkantay trek, Puerto Maldonado\r\n','','','',100008,0,0,NULL,'2014-09-10 22:55:11',NULL),(948,1,'Dear Staci,','<p>We could not have been happier with our trip to Peru. EVERYTHING was amazing. Everything happened exactly as planned without a hitch. Miguel in Lima...David in Cusco...Fabricio at Machu Picchu...and Jose on our horseback trip....they were all AMAZING. And where would we have been without Kathleen in Cusco??? There was not one person, either a Peru For Less employee or a guide contracted by them, that was not totally there for us and our experience. Even the hotel staff were of the utmost caliber. All we can say is that our entire experience was top notch. We came home wondering if we had really just experienced all that, or if it was a dream. Very smooth! Kudos to all at Peru For Less, and know that we will be recommending your agency every chance we get. Thanks again to all and know that this was a trip of a lifetime thanks to you.  </p>','David and Sarah (Arizona, USA)<br/>\r\nTraveled to: Lima, Cusco, Machu Picchu\r\n','','','',100009,0,0,NULL,'2014-09-10 22:55:11',NULL),(949,1,'Hi Matt,','<p>We had a fantastic trip in Peru! Bill and I were impressed with our tour guides. David in the Sacred Valley, Fabricio in Machu Picchu and Marianne in Cusco were wonderful historians and really made the trip special for us! Peru For Less did a fabulous job orchestrating our customized vacation. </p>\r\n\r\n<p>Observing other large tour groups being herded into specific eating establishments and receiving limited menus made us really appreciate the individualized nature of our experience. We loved having the freedom to choose our own restaurants and the free days where we could venture into the local markets. Bill was able to eat at San Pedro market in Cusco, just as Anthony Bourdain on his show No Reservations! The guides were accommodating in letting me stop and take typical pictures of the locals, and explaining traditions and customs.  We now know who is selling Chicha by the color of the flags out front. The transportation from one location to the next was seamless, worry free, and comfortable. </p>\r\n','Bill & Mary (USA)<br/>\r\nTraveled to: Lima, Cusco, Sacred Valley, Machu Picchu\r\n','','','',100010,0,0,NULL,'2014-09-10 22:55:11',NULL),(950,1,'Hi Silvana,','<p>Pat and I would like to thank you for your wonderful hospitality yesterday. We really enjoyed meeting you in person finally and having the fun time of telling you about our awesome trip that you arranged for us. It will be a trip that we will never forget that is for sure. We had such a fabulous time seeing your incredible country and meeting such interesting and wonderful people. We just want you to know how much we appreciated your caring, kindness, and guidance with preparing us for this trip and making it such an incredible experience! Please come and visit us in the USA -- me mean it when we say mi casa su casa! </p>','Mary Gay and Pat (California, USA)<br/>\r\nTraveled to: Lima, Paracas, Nazca, Arequipa, Puno, Lake Titicaca, Cusco, Machu Picchu, Puerto Maldonado \r\n','','','',100011,0,0,NULL,'2014-09-10 22:55:11',NULL),(951,1,'Hi Silvana,','<p>Thank you so much for the amazing trip to Peru you organized for my husband and me. I admire your professionalism while helping us with accommodation and transport and ensuring the best guides in the different places. We spent the most wonderful, interesting, relaxing, and trouble-free vacation ever. This was the trip of my dreams; I never thought it would come true! Machu Picchu was incredible. </p>\r\n<p>Thank you also for your patience and fast responses during the 3 months preparation for the trip. </p>\r\n<p>I happened to have a birthday in Arequipa and you made it really special by this wonderful surprise we found when entered the hotel room there. I was touched to tears. Now I know I have a friend in Peru and please don\'t forget you have 2 Bulgarian friends. </p>\r\n<p>I already recommended you and Peru For Less to my daughter and son-in-law who are interested in a trip to Machu Picchu. </p>\r\n','Evelina (Sofia, Bulgaria)<br/>\r\nTraveled to: Lime, Arequipa, Colca Canyon, Puno, Cusco\r\n','','','',100012,0,0,NULL,'2014-09-10 22:55:11',NULL),(952,1,'Dear Rylee,  ','<p>I wanted to thank you and Peru For Less for your help and professional assistance with our trip.  We had a wonderful time in Peru. Each and every guide and driver met us at our destinations without a flaw. The jungle was fantastic. Luis was our guide and he was fabulous and he shared his love and knowledge of the jungle with us. I can understand why he would not want to leave the Amazon for more urban areas. </p>\r\n<p>From there we flew to Cusco and a driver picked us up to transport us to Sacred Valley. He and his wife stopped at various places to show us the highlights of this area. We even learned how to make chicha. The ruins at Ollantaytambo and Machu Picchu were inspirational and the scenery spectacular. Our guides there, Ronnie and Fabricio, were very knowledgeable and very proud of their heritage. They helped us to understand the culture of the Inca people and how they lived. </p>\r\n<p>In the train to Puno we felt like royalty, riding through towns and beautiful scenery. As you recommended, this was the best mode of transport from Cusco to Puno. Lake Titicaca was beautiful. Michael was our guide there and he helped us to understand what it is like to live on the Uros Islands and the Isla of Tequille. The families on Uros welcomed us into their homes and were very proud and happy to show us their island. The traditions at Taquile were amazing. </p>\r\n<p>Erica helped us through the Andes and Colca Canyon. She too was very proud of her country and very knowledgeable of the area and the people and animals that inhabit it. Arequipa was a beautiful city. Our guide for the tour was fantastic. From Arequipa we went to the coast. The Nazca Lines were fantastic. We were then transported to Paracas. The scenery at Paracas and at Laguna de Huacacina were absolutely beautiful.  Our guide Paul was most considerate and willing to do rearrange tour times to make it convenient for us.  </p>\r\n<p>Our trip was fantastic and while we originally thought that 3 weeks would be way too long, we found ourselves wanting to stay longer. Each destination in Peru was unique and varied from the other areas; however, they all had one thing in common: the Peruvian people were so friendly and proud of their country and they welcomed us and thanked us for coming to visit. </p>\r\n<p>Thank you again for helping us to live our dream.  </p>\r\n','Nita and Marc<br/>\r\nTraveled to: Lima, Iquitos, Sacred Valley, Machu Picchu, Cusco, Puno, Arequipa, Colca Canyon, Nazca, Paracas\r\n','','','',100013,0,0,NULL,'2014-09-10 22:55:11',NULL),(953,1,'Dear Peru For Less,','<p>I was working with Kelly Hurst from Peru For Less, and I found her services to be very professional and helpful. I booked a flight from Lima to Arequipa, another flight from Cusco to Lima, and a tourist bus from Puno to Cusco. Everything worked out very well. At one point I was concerned about whether the bus was booked and Kelly confirmed that it was and there no problem. Everything worked perfectly and I would recommend these services highly. </p>','Christie (British Columbia, Canada)<br/>\r\nTraveled to: Lima, Cusco, Puno\r\n','','','',100014,0,0,NULL,'2014-09-10 22:55:11',NULL),(954,1,'Hi Mari,','<p>Our trip to Peru was a memorable adventure. The hotels, city tours, and the Inca Trek were all fabulous. Thank you for working with us to meet all our needs while we were in Peru. The itinerary you prepared was perfect for us. </p>\r\n<p>We researched several companies before we left and spoke to many fellow travelers along the way.  Peru For Less was the perfect choice.  The price was at least 1/3 less than most companies and the personal service was top notch. </p>\r\n<p>We\'ve already recommended your company to our friends and family. We will certainly contact you next time we plan to travel to South America. Thank you again for everything. </p>\r\n','Cara and Ian (Washington DC, USA)<br/>\r\nTraveled to: Inca Trail to Machu Picchu, Cusco, Lima\r\n','','','',100015,0,0,NULL,'2014-09-10 22:55:11',NULL),(955,1,'Dear Kelly,','<p>Thanks for putting everything together for me on this trip, your tireless work and consistent emails greatly helped me put this trip together. As a single traveler, I wanted to have everything organized before my trip and your advice about what to do in Peru was great. The customer service, included travel insurance, and great tour guides are all added incentives and what make Peru For Less a great provider for American travelers. I truly believe you are in another category when you compare your services to local Peruvian tour providers (which I saw for myself in Peru). Thanks again for all the great advice, the great price, and your customer service. All the best!</p>','Jonathan (Australia and USA)<br/>\r\nTraveled to: Lima, Cusco, Machu Picchu\r\n','','','',100016,0,0,NULL,'2014-09-10 22:55:11',NULL),(956,1,'Hey Jennie,','<p>Peru For Less hooked us up with all the tools and plans to have an unforgettable experience. I didn\'t really know what to expect having never gone through an agency before when traveling, but after a couple months of email consultations, I was able to come up with an awesome itinerary at a reasonable rate. Our advisor made some valuable suggestions and, with a little of my own research, we developed the plan together. I especially liked how the website was organized for choosing hotels.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>As for the trip itself, there were so many memories to love. We started in Cusco, where I advise anyone to spend a couple days to acclimate if they\'re going to do the Inca Trail.  Our greeter at the Cusco airport was lovely and she really made us feel welcome. Not only did she answer almost every question we had, but she pointed us in the right direction for the questions she couldn\'t answer herself. I also recommend staying at Hotel Aranwa in Cusco if you want affordable luxury for a couple nights.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>We were hooked up with Wayki Trek for the hike to Machu Picchu and they were beyond all expectations! Our guide was magnificent, our group was small (only 4 of us in total), and we were all so impressed with the porters and cooks. Of course the trail was unbelievable, and not nearly as difficult as I expected. </p>\r\n\r\n<p>We then went to Puno and toured Lake Titicaca, which was fascinating, especially the floating islands of Uros. The main part of Bolivia that I highly recommend is the Salt Flats of Uyuni. It\'s like being on another planet. We spent two days driving on and around the flats in a four runner with a guide and a driver. We couldn\'t complete the third day of the tour to the Laguna Colorada because of bad weather, but the agency and local tour group worked out a flawless change of plans and even gave us a refund.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>All in all, we were very impressed and always felt like there was someone looking out for us on the trip. All the drivers and guides were on time and very helpful. Only very minor issues came about which were mostly not the fault of Peru For Less. We kept in email contact with them throughout the trip as needed, and I couldn\'t recommend them more if you\'re planning a trip to Peru or Bolivia. Take the time to develop your itinerary carefully and you\'ll be very pleased with the experience!</p>\r\n','(New Orleans, USA)<br/>\r\nTraveled to: Lima, Cusco, Inca Trail/Machu Picchu, Sacred Valley, Puno, La Paz, Uyuni/Salt Flats\r\n','','','',100017,0,0,NULL,'2014-09-10 22:55:10',NULL),(957,1,'Hi Kelly,','<p>I thought it was a great trip. Not a relaxing trip, but we knew that when we squeezed so much stuff in. And then rearranged everything last minute! We could never have done so much in so little time without your help. And you made the process very easy for us by being so receptive to our suggestions and needs, and responding so quickly. All the PFL folks in Peru were on-time, personable and knowledgeable which really made things nice. The detailed itinerary made it very easy to plan things out. And the flexibility that was shown was amazing. </p>\r\n\r\n<p>The Ballestas Islands were way more interesting than I expected. We loved the sand dunes. I think we were the oldest group out there, but we went for the sandboarding (on our stomachs). Also, the Nazca Lines is definitely a worthwhile thing to do. </p>\r\n\r\n<p> Another pleasant surprise was the Lake Titicaca tour - it was way too long on the lake, but we were blown away by the floating islands (I didn\'t have high hopes for them given everything that I have read) and Tequile is absolutely fascinating. </p>\r\n\r\n<p>Thanks for everything. I don\'t know when we\'ll be back in Peru again, but you\'ll be our first call!</p>\r\n','Susan and Dan (pictured far right, along with travel mates Cathi, Chris, and Bill)<br/>\r\nTraveled to: Ica, Paracas, Cusco, Machu Picchu, Puno\r\n','','','',100018,0,0,NULL,'2014-09-10 22:55:10',NULL),(959,1,'Dear Jennie,','<p>The trip to Machu Picchu was really one to remember. My time spent at the top will always have a place in my heart and soul. </p>\r\n  \r\n<p>Overall, I was happy with Latin America For Less and the way they helped me through some difficult situations. Special thanks to Fabricio, my tour guide at Machu Picchu. It was my understanding that my tour guide would have my tickets when I arrived to the top. I soon found out that I had my ticket all along, and it was left in my bag at the hotel. Fabricio was on the ball and made numerous phone calls (with his 3 cell phones) to coordinate getting my ticket up to me. He went above and beyond to make my big day happen, and on top of that he was a very informative tour guide. </p>\r\n\r\n<p>Also, I would like to give special thanks to Antonio \"Banderas.\" He was the driver that picked me up from the airport in Cusco. Because my flight was delayed, he had special orders from your colleague to make sure I made my train \"anyway he possibly could.\" This resulted in the wildest drive of my life through the mountains and small towns. I would nominate him to be a professional race car driver any day. Despite the hurdles, every obstacle seemed minuscule once I made it to the ruins, gazing over the majestic city that seemed to stop time...it was worth every penny!</p>\r\n','Steve (Florida, USA)<br/>\r\nTraveled to: Machu Picchu, Cusco\r\n','','','',100019,0,0,NULL,'2014-09-10 22:55:10',NULL),(960,1,'Dear Mari-Ellena,','<p>After a very long day, we are finally home. It was an unforgettable trip for us. I had done some research regarding operators for Peru.  After reading some very positive comments about your agency, I basically convinced my family to use Peru For Less. We hesitated to pay on-line, were concerned about the reliability of your company and mostly, were concerned we may arrive at Lima and find ourselves victims of an internet scam. I am glad to say, that overall, your company (and you specifically) surpassed our expectations.  </p>\r\n<p>I want to thank you for a superb job in being responsive to our complaints and issues and for being professional at all times and working to solve and bridge our misunderstanding; I truly appreciated it. You can count on me recommending your agency to my friends.  Again, thank you so much for ensuring these past days were unforgettable to us. Until the next trip, all the best.</p>\r\n','Claudia (Canada)<br/>\r\nTraveled to: Lima, Nazca, Cusco, Machu Picchu \r\n','','','',100020,0,0,NULL,'2014-09-10 22:55:10',NULL),(961,1,'Hi Rylee,','<p>What a fabulous vacation and what a wonderful experience to have been able to travel to Peru and Ecuador. Our trip went on without a glitch! Our drivers were wonderful, the tour guides all fabulous! The hotels were perfect. We loved every city we visited. We really loved Cusco, what a charming little city. Our hotel there, Quinoa, couldn\'t have been better. The staff there really made us feel at home. We enjoyed all of the hotels! They were just perfect. We couldn\'t believe the prices in Cusco; shopping for me was fabulous! The people were so wonderful and sweet, calling me \"senorita\" and \"amiga\". The food was great. I did not try cuy in Ecuador, but the rest of the gang did. I did not try the worms in Ecuador either, but the guys did! I couldn\'t put that squishy thing in my mouth! But I did do the best at the blowgun in the rainforest! Beat the pants off the guys! Go figure! We enjoyed La Casa del Suizo, but the drinks were not included and the sodas were very expensive! We met a wonderful Ecuadorian family there and they have invited Alec to go back next summer to their home, even do a year of school there with them if he wanted. I don\'t think I would send him for that long at his age now but we could definitely visit them next summer and have even discussed bringing their daughter back to the US with us for a few weeks. We\'ll see what happens... </p>\n \n<p>We couldn\'t have asked for a better vacation or accommodations. I just can\'t thank you enough for all of your hard work! We had a fabulous time thanks to your knowledge and expertise in putting together our perfect vacation! I will gladly write positive reviews for Peru For Less! I will recommend you to everyone I know who is interested in traveling to South America! </p>\n','Vicki<br/>\r\nTraveled to: Peru and Ecuador, Lima, Cusco, Machu Picchu, and Quito and the Ecuador Amazon\r\n','','','',418,0,0,NULL,NULL,NULL),(962,1,'Dear Rylee,','<p>I had a great trip and it was well choreographed as far as all the pick-ups and places to see! All of the drivers and contacts were very nice and I was happy with all of the hotels that I stayed in. They were all centrally located and I was able to get around very well on my own. I was very relieved to feel safe at all of the places and had a really great trip! </p>\r\n\r\n<p>The number 1 highlight for me was the Huayna Picchu hike. I did it on my own and I was really glad to have been alone on that hike; I really felt that it was a test of what I could do and I felt such a great accomplishment. The second best thing was the Paracas Islands boat tour. That was very beautiful and magical. I loved obviously Machu Picchu, but the hike really made it for me. </p>\r\n\r\n<p>I am really glad that I went on this trip and would recommend your services to others.  Thank you so much, and happy travels!!!  </p>\r\n','Lizz (California, USA)<br/>\r\nTraveled to: Nazca, Cusco, Machu Picchu\r\n','','','',418,0,0,NULL,NULL,NULL),(963,1,'Hi Mari-Ellena,','<p>Eric and I had a PHENOMENAL time in Peru, especially Machu Picchu and the Amazon. It was such a once-in-a-lifetime trip and we loved every minute of it. Our friends and family are eagerly waiting to see the pictures we took (about 900 pictures). </p>\r\n\r\n<p>Eric and I met many other travelers from the States as well around the world, and I conversed in Spanish, which I learned 20 years ago in high school and college. The people are very polite and itâ??s such a different culture. We were very happy with the arrangements you and Peru For Less did for us. It was nice to be â??stress freeâ? and not worrying how to get from one place to another or buying tickets to the attractions, and you guys confirmed everything for us either through the hotel we were staying in Cusco or one of your representatives met us. All the drivers were great and the tours guides were excellent and very knowledgeable about their country and city. You can tell they are very proud of their country and culture.  </p>\r\n\r\n<p>Machu Picchu - breath taking and no words can describe how magnificent it is. We were just in awe.  Climbing Wayna Picchu was worth the extra money and the climb itself. It took Eric and I a couple of hours to climb up the  mountain and back down, but the view from the top looking onto Machu Picchu was again, breathtaking and we were quite speechless. I canâ??t believe the Incas built all that.  </p>\r\n\r\n<p>Again, thank you so much for everything you did for us. I know we had a lot of questions and last minute changes for you, but you answered all our questions promptly and assured us everything was taken care for us. We will definitely recommend to friends and family PFL or LAFL, and of course we would definitely use you guys again for our next adventure (Iâ??m thinking Costa Rica!).  Overall, Eric and I are extremely pleased with PFL and we will definitely post comments on your website as well as Trip Advisor of the wonderful services we received and the awesome vacation we had! </p>\r\n','Angie &amp; Eric (Massachusetts, USA)<br/>\r\nTraveled to: Lima, Cusco, Machu Picchu, Puerto Maldonado\r\n','','','',418,0,0,NULL,NULL,NULL),(964,1,'Dear Matt,','<p>We had a wonderful time during our vacations in Latin America. The vacation program that you prepared for us was great and we enjoy every minute of it. All taxi pickup, hotels, and tours were carefully coordinated and worked as planned. Noel and I would like to thank you for making this experience a memorable one. You certainly raised the bar for us with respect to planned vacations and we remain hopeful that we will be able to do other wonderful trips with you guys in the near future. </p>','Luis &amp; Noel<br/>\r\nTraveled to: Brazil, Argentina, and Peru (Rio de Janeiro, Iguazu, Buenos Aires, Cusco, Machu Picchu, Lima)\r\n','','','',418,0,0,NULL,NULL,NULL),(965,1,'Dear Rylee,','<p>The trip was fantastic!  The Peru For Less people that met us in Lima and Cusco were great, and your subcontractors were really good too, especially Giardino.  We were always met on time by professional people, and they were very easy to find. </p>\r\n<p>The Allpa hotel in Lima was perfect and in a good location. We are glad we stayed in Miraflores. The private city tour was really good. We thought Refugio Amazonas was great â?? it was perfect for the kids, and they accommodated my vegetarian daughter with wonderful meals. The Casa Andina San Blas in Cusco was one of our favorite hotels on the trip, with great staff and a quiet location. We grew tired of the main plaza area, but loved the San Blas district.  </p>\r\n<p>Our Cusco tour guide, David, gave a great half day tour of the city and surroundings, and a fantastic full day tour of the Sacred Valley. I am really glad we spent a night in Aguas Calientes, because it allowed us plenty of time to enjoy all of Machu Picchu over 2 days and do several nice hikes. We loved the whole Colca Canyon excursion. We like the Casina Andina Classic hotel in Arequipa, especially the terrace on the 4th floor with views of the city and volcanoes.  </p>\r\n<p>Thanks for your help in arranging this spectacular trip. Peru For Less was a great experience. I could really relax and enjoy the trip, knowing that everything was included, and we did not have to deal with purchasing any admission or transportation tickets. Your service enabled us to travel independently in a foreign county where we donâ??t speak the language. </p>\r\n','David (Florida, USA)<br/>\r\nTraveled to: Lima, Arequipa, Colca Canyon, Puno, Cusco, Machu Picchu, Puerto Maldonado \r\n','','','',418,0,0,NULL,NULL,NULL),(966,1,'Dear Rylee,','<p>We had an amazing time. Everything went smoothly and all of our tour guides were amazing. I really liked the smaller groups because it allowed for more one-on-one time. My favorite hotel was the Casa Andina in the Sacred Valley; it was beautiful and the food was amazing. I would recommend your agency for future trips. Thanks for all your help! </p>','<p>We had an amazing time. Everything went smoothly and all of our tour guides were amazing. I really liked the smaller groups because it allowed for more one-on-one time. My favorite hotel was the Ca','','','',418,0,0,NULL,NULL,NULL),(967,1,'Dear Kelly,','<p>We are home.  Please know that despite the challenges we faced getting here that our vacation was EXTRAORDINARY!!!!! The Cusco hotel, Suenos del Inka, was wonderful! The location was perfect and the people friendly and extremely helpful. We loved the first class service on the train. Breakfast at Gringo Bills was cooked to order; eggs along with the usual fruit, bread and meats. We were at Gringo Bills for only a short time but it worked out well for what we needed. All in all, the package was just exactly what we wanted and we were glad that we were not \"on a tour.\"  We saw plenty of them and they were way too regimented for us. </p>','Richard<br/>\r\nTraveled to: Cusco, Machu Picchu\r\n','','','',418,0,0,NULL,NULL,NULL),(968,1,'Dear Jennie,','<p>The trip was wonderful, and the service we received from everyone involved with Latin America/Peru For Less was absolutely great.  </p>\r\n \r\n<p>Our itinerary was detailed and easy to follow, and all our connections were made smoothly. All our drivers were right on time, and everyone associated with Peru For Less was professional, friendly, and helpful.  We had only one small problem the whole time. The day we were scheduled to travel from Cusco back to Lima, Debbie felt too sick to travel. Our contact, Dario, was very helpful in changing our pickup time so we could take a later flight, which worked out fine. </p>\r\n \r\n<p>Visiting Machu Picchu was awe-inspiring, and the experience was made even more interesting by being there the week of the 100-year celebration.  We participated in the day-long celebration in Cusco while we were there. The tours of Cusco and the Sacred Valley that you arranged were both fun and educational. We loved the unique Casa San Blas in Cusco, and our room at the Andina Luxury Hotel in Aguas Calientes, although a little chilly, had a balcony over a rushing creek. Spectacular. </p>\r\n \r\n<p>This was our first trip to a South American country, and we weren\'t sure what to expect, but everyone was so helpful that we felt quite at home and comfortable. We can\'t wait to return. We can enthusiastically recommend Latin America For Less. Thanks so much for all your help, Jennie, in arranging our best-ever trip. </p>\r\n','Debbie and Dave (New York, USA)<br/>\r\nTraveled to: Lima, Cusco, Sacred Valley, Machu Picchu\r\n','','','',418,0,0,NULL,NULL,NULL),(969,1,'Dear Matt,','<p>Trip was great man! The team was awesome, very accommodating.  Really friendly, on time, and informative. The tours were good, not too long, just enough information.  The group sizes were perfect too. Until next time, nothing but love. </p>','Julian<br/>\r\nTraveled to: Cusco, Machu Picchu\r\n','','','',418,0,0,NULL,NULL,NULL),(970,1,'Hello Matt,','<p>We just returned from our trip.  After visiting Peru we also visited Galapagos Islands. The experience with Peru For Less was excellent. All the tour guides, transportation, drivers, and hotels were wonderful and our trip progressed very smoothly. We absolutely loved all the hotels - great locations, luxury accommodation, very good food, excellent service. We also loved the restaurant in Sacred Valley for lunch that our guide recommended.  </p>\r\n  \r\n<p>Thank you for all your help.  I enjoyed working with you and from the beginning you listened to our needs for a customized itinerary.  We also appreciated your ability to manage and organize the trip in the short period of time.  We had a great experience. </p>\r\n','Renata<br/>\r\nTraveled to: Cusco, Sacred Valley, Machu Picchu\r\n','','','',418,0,0,NULL,NULL,NULL),(971,1,'Dear Staci,','<p>On behalf of my wife and myself, I would like to thank you and the staff at Latin America For Less for the amazing vacations to Peru. Our transport was always there, even though our flight was 4 hours late once. They served us right every step of the way. The guides were nice and knowledge full, everything was perfect. </p>','Gabe (Virginia, USA)<br/>\r\nTraveled to: Cusco, Sacred Valley, Machu Picchu, Lima \r\n','','','',418,0,0,NULL,NULL,NULL),(972,1,'Hi Silvana','<p>Our trip to Peru was most enjoyable. I am very pleased that we went to Arequipa and the Colca Canyon. Arequipa was a beautiful city. Our hotels throughout our stay were lovely and unexpected. Overall all transfers went well and the tour guides were so proud of their country that their enthusiasm was contagious. Thank you for your help in making our trip wonderful. </p>','Allison and Gina (Canada)<br/>\r\nTraveled to: Arequipa and Colca Canyon\r\n','','','',418,0,0,NULL,NULL,NULL),(973,1,'Hi Kelly, ','<p>Our trip to Peru was great! It was 2 weeks of bliss. Our pick-ups were always on time and everyone made sure we were where we needed to be. The Casa Andina Hotels are excellent. The staff at each hotel was very friendly and helpful, the hotels were clean and comfortable, providing everything we needed. The trek on the Inca Trail was awesome! Wayki Trek was fantastic. I really liked the way the whole trip was handled. I will certainly book with you folks if I travel anywhere else in Latin America. Right now I am thinking about an Argentina/Antarctica trip. Thanks again for a great vacation. </p>','Billie<br/>\r\nTraveled to: Lima, Nazca, Cusco, 4-day Inca Trail trek to Machu Picchu, Lake Titicaca\r\n','','','',418,0,0,NULL,NULL,NULL),(974,1,'Hi Kelly,','<p>I wanted to thank you for organizing our wonderful tour in Peru. We were very pleased with our Discover Peru trip, which surpassed our expectations. Everything went very smoothly, there was always someone waiting for us in the bus station/airport. And what a luxury it was to have your own private guide in most of the destinations we visited! It was also very nice when you called to our hotel room in Puno when I was suffering from gastroenteritis. Not knowing a word of Spanish wasn\'t a problem when there was always someone to take care of you and all the practical stuff - we could just concentrate on enjoying all the wonderful destinations. </p>\r\n\r\n<p>It was great being able to customize the tour according to our interests and also to pick up the hotels - which were of very good standard in general. </p>\r\n\r\n<p>One of the highlights of our trip was the two-day Inca Trail, where we had our own private guide, who was exceptionally knowledgeable and friendly. There weren\'t many other people on the path, even in July, so we were able to enjoy the hike in peace and quiet appreciating the beautiful nature with orchids and other flowers - and rewarding ourselves with the view of Macchu Picchu at the end. </p>\r\n\r\n<p>We also enjoyed Paracas very much, our hotel Hacienda Bahia was like an oasis of tranquility in spectacular desert settings. The Ballestas Islands were very impressing and picturesque, and flying over the Nazca lines an unforgettable experience. </p>\r\n\r\n<p>I would also recommend visiting Arequipa to everyone, it was much more peaceful and non-touristic compared to Cusco with some very interesting sights such as the Santa Catalina monastery. And with great local food! In Casa Arequipa bed and breakfast we got very individual and attentive service of five-class standard. </p>\r\n\r\n<p>Of course our visit to the Amazonas and Puerto Maldonado was one of the highlights as well. We enjoyed staying at the Inkaterra, where we got very spoilt with good service - and saw a lot of wildlife, too, such as different species of monkeys. </p>\r\n\r\n<p>I would certainly recommend travelling with Peru For Less for anyone considering travelling to Peru! </p>\r\n','Krista (Finland)<br/>\r\nTraveled to: Lima, Paracas, Nazca, Arequipa, Colca Canyon, Puno, Cusco, Sacred Valley,2-day Inca Trail Trek to Machu Picchu, Puerto Maldonado\r\n','','','',418,0,0,NULL,NULL,NULL),(975,1,'Dear Kelly,','<p>We had an amazing experience, it really was a holiday of a lifetime. The organization was perfect and all the transfers and tours were on time. To be honest, it exceeded my expectations. Thank you very much for organizing it; it was pleasure to deal with you. </p>','Vera<br/>\r\nTraveled to: Rio de Janeiro, Iguazu, Buenos Aires, Cusco, Sacred Valley, Machu Picchu, Puno\r\n','','','',418,0,0,NULL,NULL,NULL),(976,1,'Dear Staci,','<p>My trip was absolutely perfect! I thoroughly enjoyed seeing the amazing sights of Peru and found the services of Peru For Less to be outstanding! Each segment of the trip was well-planned and well-coordinated, and I saw so much of Peru in such a short time, I\'m still amazed that I managed to \"see it all.\" I have to look at all my incredible pictures just to prove it to myself that I saw and did so much. Staci was an absolute pleasure to work with and I highly recommend using Peru for Less. </p>\r\n \r\n<p>Thanks again for all the work you did on my behalf. I loved my trip and am having fun reliving it again and again as I show my pictures and tell my stories! </p>\r\n','Maureen <br/>\r\nTraveled to: Arequipa, Colca Canyon, Puno, Cusco, Machu Picchu\r\n','','','',418,0,0,NULL,NULL,NULL),(977,1,'Dear Staci,','<p>I went on an impromptu vacation to Peru with less than a week to plan, but made it happen with the help of Latin America For Less! My travel consultant, Staci, was very responsive and accommodating to my needs. I booked an adventure vacation to experience the culture and life of Incan descendants living in the Andes Mountains and to do some backpacking along the Lares Trail to Machu Picchu. </p>\r\n\r\n<p>I flew into Lima and took a flight into Cusco. Upon arrival, I had one day to acclimate, which I spent at the spa the entire day before beginning my trek. I joined a group of other like-minded foreigners who shared this same idea of a vacation, a local guide, two cowboys that walked alongside mules carrying our equipment, and two chefs who cooked our meals off of the land. </p>\r\n\r\n<p>It was a grueling 3 days and 2 nights on the trek, covering approximately 20 miles and reaching altitudes of 15,000 feet above sea level. We saw lots of llama-herding children (think scenes from the book, The Alchemist); defied altitude sickness and food poisoning; endured freezing nights and scorching mornings; ate trout from the river and farm-fresh lamb; avoided baby Anacondas and large tarantulas; and climbed the most beautiful mountains. After this challenging trek, I reached Machu Picchu unscathed and have to say that reaching the finale of my trip was well worth the journey. The history of Machu Picchu is thoroughly amazing and the friendships that were formed among the locals and with the other travelers on this trip are unforgettable. Thanks again, Staci. I enjoyed planning my trip with you! </p>\r\n','Frances (California, USA)<br/>\r\nTraveled to: Cusco, Machu Picchu, Lars Trek\r\n','','','',418,0,0,NULL,NULL,NULL),(978,1,'Hi Riva,','<p>I just got back from my incredible trip and just wanted to thank you and the hard working people of Peru For Less so much for making it the trip of a lifetime. I had such an incredible experience and it has forever changed my life. Everything was perfect. The hotels were beautiful, the tours were amazing, and the people could not have been nicer. Thank you from the very bottom of my heart. I will give you and Peru for Less glowing reviews and will absolutely use your services again in the future and recommend you to everyone I know. </p>','Alex (California, USA)<br/>\r\nTraveled to: Lima, Cusco, Sacred Valley, Machu Picchu\r\n','','','',418,0,0,NULL,NULL,NULL),(979,1,'Hi Matt,','<p>You did a superb job of putting together a flawless trip in a minimal amount of time. Many people plan their trips for months before they depart, and ideally that is how I like to travel. But when the opportunity presented itself, I had to jump on it. My expectations were low, given the fact that we were still putting the finishing touches on the trip 3 days before departure. This trip flowed so smoothly, you would have thought we had tweaked it for months. Thank you so much for your attention to the little details that made my trip one to cherish for a lifetime. Matt, I will be happy to recommend you to any of my friends looking to go on a special trip to Peru, It was a pleasure to work with you. </p>','Ellen<br/>\r\nTraveled to: Lima, Cusco, Quito, Galapagos\r\n','','','',100021,0,0,NULL,'2014-09-10 22:55:10',NULL),(980,1,'Hi Matt,','<p>Your logistics worked perfectly on the field. You have been a great help and I sincerely thank you for it.\r\nThe hotels were lovely. I particularly liked Sonesta Posada del Inca in Arequipa - a charming place, strategically positioned, kind and discrete staff, beautiful terraces, lovely view. I wish we could have spent more time in Arequipa. \r\nOur second hotel was the Colca Canyon Lodge where we had a nice and cozy apartment with 2 bedrooms, a spacious sitting room, small terrace, and a perfect view over the valley. The Colca Valley is a mythical, mystical place. Definitely one of the places I would like to visit again. </p>\r\n\r\n<p>In Cusco, the charming streets reminded me of our Mediterranean streets along the Croatian coastline, while the crooked little houses of the San Blas quarter looked like those in Sarajevo\'s Turkish quarter. I found the Casa San Blas Boutique hotel sweet and comfortable with a lovely view over the city and a gentle and kind staff. I particularly liked the moving and confusion in the narrow Cuesta de San Blas when a car stopped to pick up hotel guests, with lot of honking and yelling. We walked up to San Blas square and there was an artistic fair. I bought some watercolor paintings in the local art shop; everybody is crazy about them over here. </p>\r\n\r\n<p>If I would have to pick one guide I liked the best (and all of them were very good indeed) it would probably be Luis, the one that was with us on our journey from Arequipa to Canyon de Colca. His big smile, wit, gestures, the information he provided and the energy he put in it were amazing. Jorje, the driver, discrete and helpful, would also be among my favorites. </p>\r\n','Darja<br/>\r\nTraveled to: Arequipa, Colca Canyon, Puno, Cusco, Machu Picchu\r\n','','','',100022,0,0,NULL,'2014-09-10 22:55:10',NULL),(981,1,'Dear Kelly, ','<p>Thanks to Peru For Less, my daughter and I enjoyed a fabulous trip to Peru. Our Peru For Less contact was always ready and available to help us fine-tune our itinerary; and it worked so well!! </p>\r\n\r\n<p>We were always met on arrivals and given the necessary transfers, tickets, and information we needed for the next leg of the trip.The hotels booked for us were fabulous. The service was very gracious, and the amenities were better than could have been imagined. We truly left every hotel wishing we could have stayed longer! Our tour guides were delightful and extremely knowledgeable. We felt marvelously educated at the end of each tour, as well as a bit sad at saying good-bye to new friends. </p>\r\n\r\n<p>The trains to and from Machu Picchu were a special treat. An unforgettable part of the trip. Everything we expected from the trip was surpassed. We felt that all plans were superbly organized for us; yet, most importantly, we felt very independent and free to explore and enjoy Peru on our own. </p>\r\n','Suzanne and Violeta <br/>\r\nTraveled to Lima, Cusco, Sacred Valley, Machu Picchu\r\n','','','',100023,0,0,NULL,'2014-09-10 22:55:10',NULL),(982,1,'Dear Staci,','<p>My husband and I had a wonderful 2 week trip to Peru in April 2011.  We were initially going to plan our trip on our own but realized quickly it would be a little difficult! When looking around on the web, we came across some tour companies that could help us with our planning.  We chose Peru For Less because we got the best prices and fastest responses from our advisor Staci. She was so helpful with our planning. The best part about going with a tour/travel company is the support you get while you are on your vacation. We had some bumps in the road at the beginning of our vacation and Peru For Less took care of all of it for us! We were so thankful we had them to help us! </p>  \r\n\r\n<p>We planned 3 different areas to visit while we were in Peru. First, we went to Iquitos, Peru, to get our Amazon River experience.  We booked a 3 day trip with Amazon Explorama Lodges. We had a wonderful time in the Amazon and our guide Lucio was great! We stayed 1 night at ACT\'s Field Station and 1 night at ExploNapo Lodge. We went on the canopy walkway, went fishing on the Amazon, went looking for wildlife, and visited a Shaman. It was a wonderful experience! See below for a picture of us on the Canopy Walkway looking out for miles at the Amazon Rainforest! It was so peaceful and beautiful!   </p>\r\n\r\n<p>We then flew to Cusco and spent a few days up in the mountains! We took the train to see Machu Picchu. We did a 2-day hike to Machu Picchu with Wayki Trek. We had such a great experience on this hike. We didn\'t have enough time in our itinerary to do the 4-day hike so we decided to do the 2-day hike. We got off the train at KM 104 and started hiking through the Andes. We had an awesome guide, Antonio, who made our experience even better! We would highly recommend doing the 2-day hike to Machu Picchu if you can\'t or don\'t want to do the 4 day Inca Trail hike. You still get to experience seeing Machu Picchu for the first time through the Sun Gate just like the Incas did! It was amazing! We then got to spend the next day exploring Machu Picchu! We also spent one night in Ollantaytambo. We stayed at El Albergue Bed & Breakfast right in the train station. We enjoyed our day exploring Ollantaytambo and the bed and breakfast was a beautiful little place! We highly recommend staying here if you are staying in Ollantaytambo.  </p>\r\n\r\n<p>The third and last part of our trip was to visit Puno and experience Lake Titicaca. We took a tour bus from Cusco to Puno and got to see a lot of towns, ruins, and history. Once we arrived to Puno, we enjoyed the city in the evening. The next day we booked a Lake Titicaca home stay on Amantani Island.  We started our day visiting the Floating Islands then took a boat to Amantani Island. We also had a wonderful tour guide, Joni, who was with us the entire two days! He grew up on Amantani Island and we had the pleasure of staying with his family once we arrived to the Island. We had home-cooked meals with his family and felt their way of living. We were going to hike up to the top of the Island to watch the sunset but unfortunately I started getting a terrible headache and was bedridden all night long. His family was so supportive and went out of their way to find me oxygen and medicine to make me feel better! I also got to try some home remedies like drinking Coca Tea and placing tea leaves on my forehead to help relieve the headache! They went scurrying all over the island to find ways to help me feel better and for that I will be forever grateful! It could have been altitude sickness or just a severe headache, but either way, they were wonderful to me! Being sick on an island with a hospital that was closed for the night was quite the experience! Being a nurse myself didn\'t help the situation either! I knew what I needed and couldn\'t get it! How frustrating! The next day after feeling 100% better, we went to Taquille Island and had lunch then rode back on the boat to Puno. We spent another night in Puno and then headed back to Lima to end our trip!  </p>\r\n\r\n<p>We would highly recommend Peru For Less. At each new journey there was a Peru For Less representative there to greet us and put our minds at ease with answering any questions we had and giving us the needed forms/tickets.  Thank you, Peru For Less, for making our Peru adventure amazing!  A special thanks to Staci for spending so much time helping us plan our trip. She wrote up 8 itineraries for us because we couldn\'t make up our minds on what we wanted to do within our budget! She was so helpful! What an experience! Thank you!  </p>\r\n','Jesse and Lori (Minnesota, USA)<br/>\r\nTraveled to: Lima, Iquitos, Cusco, Machu Picchu, Puno\r\n','','','',100024,0,0,NULL,'2014-09-10 22:55:10',NULL),(983,1,'Hi Aleks, ','<p>I definitely wanted to take the time to thank you and PFL for putting together such a fabulous vacation for us this last spring.<strong> I appreciate all the time you took to answer questions and prepare us for the trip. Everything was beautiful, as one would expect from a trip to Peru:</strong> all the hotels were charming and immaculate, the tour guides were knowledgeable and friendly, and the<strong> PFL representatives did a fantastic job of taking care of us and making us feel welcomed and comfortable on our first trip abroad.</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>I especially wanted to express thanks to the representatives who took care of us in Lima and Cusco. Jose did a wonderful job introducing us to the city and to the country, and he was even there to see us off at 3 AM at the end of our trip, which I was not expecting. <strong>When our flight out of Lima to Cusco was delayed, our rep in Cusco quickly juggled our tour times for us so that we did not end up missing out on anything. She had it all taken care of by the time we landed and was able to give us our modified itinerary immediately, which was a great relief to our minds.</strong> She also gave us excellent advice on what to see and do and where to eat around Machu Picchu and Cusco.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Of course you would expect that all the sightseeing in Peru would be incredible, and it was, but it was a real bonus to have Peru For Less there to take care of the details so that we could spend our time focusing on enjoying ourselves and just living in each moment.<strong> I would definitely recommend PFL to anyone I know for travel to Peru</strong>, and I will use the company again should I get the chance to come back to South America as I would like to do.</p>\r\n','Terri & Jonathan (USA)<br/>\r\nTraveled to: Lima, Cusco, Sacred Valley, Machu Picchu, Puno\r\n','','','\"It was a real bonus to have Peru For Less there to take care of the details so that we could spend our time focusing on enjoying ourselves and just living in each moment.\"',100037,0,0,NULL,'2014-09-10 23:08:30',NULL),(984,1,'Hi Aleks,','<p>We had a wonderful time in Peru. I am extremely happy with the Peru For Less service. Feel free to use my name for reference. Thanks! </p>','Khandker (USA)<br/>\r\nTraveled to: Lima, Cusco, Machu Picchu\r\n','','','',100025,0,0,NULL,'2014-09-10 22:55:10',NULL),(985,1,'Dear Silvana,','<p>Though we travel 5-6 weeks every summer (we are teachers), we have never traveled with a tour company before. We were initially a bit overwhelmed by booking and visiting the Amazon and Machu Picchu. Peru For Less was incredibly accommodating and created a tour specific to our requests. We had private tours for the majority of the trip and felt like we had chosen the best group to go with. Some groups had 10+ people, we were just 2!</p>\r\n<p>We stayed in the Amazon with Amazon Rainforest Excursions at the Posada Amazonas for 1 night and at Refugio for 2 nights. We saw monkeys, 40+ species of birds, caimans, etc. Our guide, William, was knowledgeable, friendly, and experienced. We preferred Posada Amazonas because there was more abundant wildlife and the lodge was a little more relaxed. Refugio was great also but a bit louder and more for groups with children. The food was incredible; I am a vegetarian and felt taken care of at every meal. </p>\r\n<p>Our stay in Cusco was well planned. We went around with Jose who was friendly and knew his way around the city sites and the Sacred Valley. I was really happy to have seen some of the other ruins before Machu Picchu. Kathleen recommended great restaurants and helped us acclimate into Cusco. </p>\r\n<p>We cannot thank you enough for such a wonderful trip. PFL was personal and professional and worked with extraordinary individuals and excellent accommodations to provide us with a carefree and well considered trip. Our contact with you personally helped us to make the decision to book with PFL and later reinforced that we had picked the right company. </p>\r\n','Siobhan &amp; Brendan<br/>\r\nTraveled to: Cusco, Machu Picchu, Puerto Maldonado\r\n','','','',100026,0,0,NULL,'2014-09-10 22:55:10',NULL),(986,1,'Hi Rylee,','<p>It was a great trip. Everything worked like clock-work with reminders as to what we had to do, pick-ups, exchanges to airport and hotel â?? flawless and everyone was exceeding pleasant and efficient â?? thanks to your planning and PFL resources. </p>\r\n\r\n<p>Thanks for hanging in there all those months, for listening to my requirements, and putting together a flawless experience. Our interaction with every Peru For Less employee/contractor was exceptional. </p>\r\n','Marge &amp; Doug (Tokyo, Japan)<br/>\r\nTraveled to: Lima, Cusco, Machu Picchu & Amazon (Puerto Maldonado)\r\n','','','',418,0,0,NULL,NULL,NULL),(987,1,'Hi Kelly,','<p>Thank you so much for making my trip to Peru a great success. Both the planning and the execution were excellent, the hotel choice was perfect and all your guides, drivers and other staff are absolutely wonderful. </p>\r\n\r\n<p>I would also like to thank you personally for spending so much time helping me plan my layover in Lima and making a reservation at a world famous restaurant for me, even though officially it was not part of your job. Since it was a Saturday, it crossed my mind to invite you to join me for lunch at Astrid y Gaston, but then I thought you would probably find it a bit strange...Anyway, I\'m so glad you were in charge of my trip, I would not hesitate to recommend Peru for Less to anyone who\'s planning to visit Peru and I will advice them to ask for you. </p>\r\n\r\n<p>All the best, </p>\r\n','Karima (Tokyo, Japan)<br/>\r\nTraveled to: Cusco, Sacred Valley & Machu Picchu\r\n','','','',418,0,0,NULL,NULL,NULL),(988,1,'Hi Spencer, ','<p>I thought you provided excellent service throughout the entire process! Starting from when I was just looking at flights all the way through all the Peruvian airlines changes. I was very impressed at how prompt you were with searches and correspondence in response to my questions or with flight time changes. I was very happy we booked through you and I would recommend you to friends and family who were looking to travel in Peru in the future. </p>\r\n\r\n<p>Thanks again for all your help! </p>\r\n','Carrie (USA)<br/>\r\nFlight booking only\r\n','','','',418,0,0,NULL,NULL,NULL),(989,1,'Hi Kelly,','<p>First, I think your company is amazing. The attention to detail that you put into our itinerary was absolutely perfect! We were always on time for every tour, picked up by the most pleasant and professional tour guides and drivers, warmly greeted by all of the hotels and their employees. We enjoyed every moment of our time in Peru. The country is amazing and the people are incredibly friendly and helpful. The contrast from desert to jungle is spectacular; it made me feel like I was in two different countries at times. </p>\r\n\r\n<p>Second, you did an incredible job with our trip.  I don\'t know how you knew to cover every detail but, I truly felt safe and secure in every leg of our journey because it was so well planned by you.  </p>\r\n\r\n<p>The most spectacular parts of the trip was the Ballestas Islands and of course Machu Picchu. The islands were absolutely beautiful. Mary kept saying that she felt like she was in a National Geographic movie. And, we saved the best for last. Machu Picchu was the perfect way to end our trip!  It was everything I expected and more. The trip started out great and ended with a bang! It was very educational as well. We learned so much about the people and the customs of the Peruvians and Incas. It was truly an amazing journey that I will never forget. </p>\r\n\r\n<p>I would recommend you and your company to anyone that plans to visit Peru or South America. You were always professional, helpful, and extremely accommodating with all of our requests. You are great at what you do and we appreciate every moment you spent making our vacation something we will always remember and treasure. </p>\r\n\r\n<p>Thanks Kelly, it would not have been the dream vacation without your help. </p>\r\n\r\n<p>Check out Rhondaâ??s review on TripAdvisor. </p>\r\n','Rhonda (Louisiana, USA)<br/>\r\nTraveled to: Lima, Cusco &amp; Machu Picchu\r\n','','','',418,0,0,NULL,NULL,NULL),(990,1,'Hi Rylee,','<p>This trip was hands down one of the most amazing adventures I have ever been on! It surpassed my expectations. </p>\r\n\r\n<p>The organization was great, people were there to meet us when they were supposed to be there, all of the guides were professional and very knowledgeable and went out of their way to make us feel comfortable. The hotels where we stayed were lovely, clean, and comfortable. Staff at all of the hotels was very accommodating and welcoming. </p>\r\n\r\n<p>Special mention goes to Jose Antonio of Wayki Trek; he was fantastic and his passion and knowledge of Inca and Peruvian history was terrific. Along the trek we had many â??history lessonsâ? and I now have a full appreciation for the history of the Inca people. The cook we had on the trek was amazing; I never imagined we would have the quality of food that was prepared for us. It was always well presented and delicious! Imagine having a 3-course meal on the trail!!  The hard work of the porters needs mention the loads they carried and the attention to us was super!! I particularly liked having tea served in my tent before I was even up! The soles of one of my boots starting coming off (imagine) and one of the porters sewed it back on for me. Little things like this added to the whole enjoyment of the trip. </p>\r\n\r\n<p>It was really nice being with such a small group, there was only 4 of us and it certainly allowed for getting to know each other and we had the good fortune of being with a wonderful couple from the UK. </p>\r\n\r\n<p>The jungle portion was equally wonderful; my first exposure to a jungle ecosystem and I found it all very interesting and educational. The lodge was terrific and very comfortable. On my last night there I had a wonderful massage and facial!!! </p>\r\n\r\n<p>Rylee, I wish to thank you very much for helping us organize this trip and making it such a success!!!!  I have absolutely no problem in referring Peru For Less to anyone who may be interested in going to Peru. </p>\r\n\r\nThank you,\r\n','Janette (Ontario, Canada)<br/>\r\nTraveled to: Lima, Cusco, Inca Trail to Machu Picchu & Amazon (Puerto Maldonado)\r\n','','','',418,0,0,NULL,NULL,NULL),(991,1,'Hi Matt,','<p>Let me thank you and the whole team for a trip of a lifetime. From the minute I arrived to Lima to the minute I left, things were simply great and perfect. Your whole team is amazing, I want you to make sure that the management will thank and congratulate every person I got in contact with in this trip for a well done job. </p>\r\n \r\n<p>Hotels were good, transportation was perfect , train ride was AMAZING, everyone was friendly and very helpful, and all the tour guides went the extra mile to make me happy </p>\r\n \r\n<p>MATT thanks a lot for your guidelines and patience in organizing this trip and I am sure you are on the good list for a lot of people. </p>\r\n\r\nBest regards,\r\n','Majdi (USA)<br/>\r\nTraveled to: Lima, Cusco, Machu Picchu &amp; Puno\r\n','','','',418,0,0,NULL,NULL,NULL),(992,1,'Hi Matt,','<p>I thought you were excellent to deal with, you gave me solutions to problems and came up with suggestions to ensure I had all aspects of the trip organized. </p>\r\n \r\n<p>You were a delight to deal with. Thanks for making the trip work so well! </p>\r\n \r\nRegards,\r\n','Peter (USA)<br/>\r\nTraveled to: Lima, Cusco, Machu Picchu & Sacred Valley\r\n','','','',418,0,0,NULL,NULL,NULL),(993,1,'Hi Aleks,','<p>You did a great job organizing our trip. My mom really enjoyed the whole itinerary. I think for her, she was happiest to see Machu Picchu as it was a childhood dream of hers to visit. But a close second for her was the Iguazu Falls. The hotel that you chose for us in Iguazu was probably our favorite so nice work on that one, but again the hotel in Paracas, La Hacienda, was equally amazing especially being right on the beach. </p>\r\n\r\n<p>My dad said the falls were the most impressive part of the trip for him. I think he would have enjoyed Machu Picchu more if he weren\'t afraid of heights. I think his second favorite was the Nazca lines. </p>\r\n\r\n<p>As for the local contacts and tour guides, all were professional and helpful so no complaints there. </p>\r\n','Tim (Australia)<br/>\r\nTraveled to: Buenos Aires, Colonia, Iguazu, Lima, Paracas, Nazca, Arequipa, Cusco & Machu Picchu\r\n','','','',418,0,0,NULL,NULL,NULL),(994,1,'Hi Dana,','<p>We are home and we enjoyed our trip. The return flights were full of stand bys due to overbooking. Nevertheless, we made it back and did enjoy the trip. Thanks for arranging the flight for Dennis. </p>','Rene (Colorado, USA)<br/>\r\nTraveled to: Lima &amp; Arequipa\r\n','','','',418,0,0,NULL,NULL,NULL),(995,1,'Hi Matt,','<p>The trip was fantastic!  Everything went smoothly, the hotels were great, etc.Thank you for organizing and I look forward to using your company again. </p>','Marjorie (New York, USA)<br/>\r\nTraveled to: Lima, Arequipa & Colca Canyon, Cusco & Machu Picchu, Puno & Lake Titicaca\r\n','','','',418,0,0,NULL,NULL,NULL),(996,1,'Hi Aleks,','<p>I cannot tell you how great it has been. The Inca trail was hard for me....not too hard, but being the oldest by a couple decades in our group, I was a bit behind- not bad though, and the others were nice, and the guide and porters were great! It was so beautiful. It was worth every sore muscle! A one of a kind experience for sure, and a great way to celebrate my graduation! </p>\r\n\r\n<p>Everyone has been helpful and kind. I love Peru and only wish I knew Spanish instead of some French- but getting along was fine. It was not bad being on my own, meeting lots of good people. Many thanks for all your time and effort. It has been wonderful! </p>\r\n\r\n<p>Check out Sueâ??s review on TripAdvisor. </p>\r\n','Sue (USA)<br/>\r\nTraveled to: Lima, Arequipa & Colca Canyon, Cusco & Inca Trail to Machu Picchu\r\n','','','',418,0,0,NULL,NULL,NULL),(997,1,'Hi Rylee!','<p>My trip was awesome! Thank you so much for your help. I really enjoyed all the hotels, transportation arrangement as well as my long but comfortable bus ride to Cusco. I felt really comfortable with the drivers who picked me up as well as the friendly and helpful staff I met at the hotels, especially since I was traveling solo. My favorite hotel stay was at Casa San Blas, great hotel and great location! Thank you for suggesting it. I look forward to using Peru For Less in the future for my next adventure! Thank you again! </p>','Jennie (California)<br/>\r\nTraveled to: Lima, Cusco &amp; Machu Picchu \r\n','','','',418,0,0,NULL,NULL,NULL),(998,1,'Dear Kristina,','<p>I\'ve been meaning to contact you for the longest time to tell you our trip was fantastic. Thank you so much for all of your suggestions. My daughterâ??s favorite was the hike at Macchu Picchu, while I had a stomach bug and barely made it. We also both loved Cusco and would like to return someday. </p>\r\n\r\n<p>The tours we took were fabulous, as were all the guides.  We were glad we did Maras & Moray, it was a very interesting afternoon.  At Pisac, we happened upon a sun celebration and at Macchu Picchu we had sun one day and mist/fog the next - it was interesting to see it both ways. The Cusco tour was great and the people we met that day we saw for the rest of our trip here and there. The Nazca lines were a dream come true, though the circling plane had me a little woozy at the end. </p>\r\n\r\n<p>All in all we loved it - it\'s a beautiful country, everyone we met was nice and we would love to return and see different places. If I know anyone going to Peru or South America, I will send them to you. </p>\r\n\r\nRegards,\r\n','Holly (New York, USA)<br/>\r\nTraveled to: Lima, Paracas, Cusco & Machu Picchu\r\n','','','',418,0,0,NULL,NULL,NULL),(999,1,'Dear Kelly,','<p>We loved Peru and can honestly say Peru For less is a fantastic company. The hotels were great, the weather great, the people, etc. </p>\r\n\r\n<p>I think everything was just perfect and it was nice not having to worry about where we were going to stay and how we were going to get there. You did a fantastic job and I know Susan feels the same way. </p>\r\n\r\n<p>Again, thanks to you and to everyone else who helped make this an awesome experience. </p>\r\n','Liz (USA)<br/>\r\nTraveled to: Lima, Paracas &amp; Nazca, Arequipa &amp; Colca Canyon, Puno & Lake Titicaca, Cusco & Machu Picchu, Amazon \r\n','','','',418,0,0,NULL,NULL,NULL),(1000,1,'Hi Silvana,','<p>I cannot say enough positive things about my trip. I was nervous to travel alone but every person I encountered made me feel relaxed and really made my trip great. I loved staying at Casa San Blas; the hotel is close to the main plaza in Cusco and it made it easy to get to a lot of great restaurants in the area. The Hiram Bingham train to Machu Picchu was amazing and definitely worth the added expense. </p>\r\n \r\n<p>Thank you for all of your help. I would definitely use your agency again in the future. </p>\r\n','Nicole (USA)<br/>\r\nTraveled to: Lima, Cusco & Machu Picchu\r\n','','','',418,0,0,NULL,NULL,NULL),(1001,1,'Hi Kelly!  ','<p>Our trip was fantastic. The hotel was great - we actually were upgraded at both check-ins and everyone there was so pleasant. The hike was strenuous but definitely worth it. We had a few days of rain on the hike and at Machu Picchu, but not much that could have been done about that. I wish we had been able to spend more time in Peru and especially Cusco, but we hope to come back one day!\r\nThank you so much for all your help along the way from planning out our trip to answering all of our questions.  </p>\r\n','Kelly & Adam (USA)<br/>\r\nTraveled to : Cusco & Inca Trail to Machu Picchu\r\n','','','',418,0,0,NULL,NULL,NULL),(1002,1,'Hi Staci,','<p>Both my uncle and I had a great trip. We were very pleased with how it turned out in terms of accommodation, food, travel, etc. Our guide was friendly, helpful, and always on time. The whole experience was really memorable. </p>\r\n\r\n<p>I would like to thank you for helping me plan this trip. I know we went through several itineraries between the planning for Peru and Ecuador. You have been extremely pleasant to work with. </p>\r\n','Divya (USA)<br/>\r\nTraveled to: Quito, Napo, Banos\r\n','','','',418,0,0,NULL,NULL,NULL),(1003,1,'Hello Kristina ','<p>The trip and the weather were great. We were very happy with what you arranged.  I had some issues with the altitude but adjusted.  I liked our guides for the most part. </p>\r\n \r\n<p>Regarding the Sanctuary, I am glad we chose that option. I enjoyed the setting, and the hotel itself. The staff was very accommodating.  </p>\r\n \r\n<p>As to Peru For Less, I have told my friends that if they consider going to Peru they should use your travel organization.  I was quite happy with your service and attention. </p>\r\n \r\nThanks again.\r\n','Mike (Wisconsin, USA)<br/>\r\nTraveled to : Cusco & Machu Picchu\r\n','','','',418,0,0,NULL,NULL,NULL),(1004,1,'Hi Silvana,','<p>Wes, we had a great trip to Peru overall. All the transfers did work very well, all the guides were great, and the representative who outlined our Cusco-Machu Picchu trip was great. Machu Picchu was indeed terrific! </p>\r\n\r\n<p>Thanks for arranging our trip. Peru is amazing. </p>\r\n','Vivien & Miquel (Arkansas, USA)<br/>\r\nTraveled to: Lima, Cusco, Machu Picchu & Amazon\r\n','','','',418,0,0,NULL,NULL,NULL),(1005,1,'Dear Bernard,','<p>I wanted to express sincere gratitude concerning my recent trip arranged through your agency. I could not have been more pleased with your representative Kristina. She was able to set up the perfect trip for me and met all my needs and expectations while visiting. Quite honestly, it wasnâ??t an easy booking because I changed my mind several times and it just was not a problem for her. Her organizational skills were key here. </p>\r\n\r\n<p>I still feel badly about putting her through all my changes in the itinerary, but then perfection does sometimes take more than the ordinary to achieve. She is a true professional and I will book with her again when I come back to experience more of your country. </p>\r\n \r\n<p>This was my 40th country to visit outside of the United States. So many of the places I visited in your country were truly awing experiences, to say the least. Machu Picchu, The Nazca lines, Lake Titicaca, Cusco, and Iquitos. Staying in the Amazon jungle was the highlight of my trip. Catching that first piranha, armor catfish, and a snakefish were all dreams come true for me. </p>\r\n\r\n<p>I just want everyone to know that your agency has to be #1 among delivering the best services for the money people spend to enjoy themselves while traveling. </p>\r\n \r\n<p>As my grandchildren would say, Peru For Less â??ROCKSâ?! </p>\r\n','Joan (Indiana, USA)<br/>\r\nTraveled to: Lima, Ica, Puno & Lake Titicaca, Cusco & Machu Picchu, Amazon (Iquitos)\r\n','','','',418,0,0,NULL,NULL,NULL),(1006,1,'Hi Mari,','<p>We had a fantastic time. It was so worth waiting for. Overall, the accommodations were awesome!! Much better than we expected. We particularly liked Ceiba Tops and Reservas Amazonas, Casa Arequipa (that was so sweet and the staff amazing!!!), and Casa San Blas in Cusco, which was lovely and had a fantastic location. All in all, the majority of the accommodations were so lovely that I could comfortably say you did a great job!! </p>\r\n\r\n<p>I do want to thank you profusely for your flexibility. Due to the schedule noted above, we were exhausted when we got to Puno and just needed to \"get off the treadmill\" for a bit. Too much early rising and tours. One call to our guide and he chopped the Titicaca trip to an abbreviated, half day, later pick up, without question. It was just what we needed!!! Our batteries were recharged and we were ready to go again. </p>\r\n\r\n<p>This was an incredibly memorable and enjoyable trip, and I would recommend you guys to anyone profusely!!! Thank you so much for all you did all along. You guys are the best!!! </p>\r\n\r\n<p>Check out Karenâ??s review on TripAdvisor. </p>\r\n','Karen (California, USA)<br/>\r\nTraveled to: Lima, Iquitos, Arequipa & Colca Canyon, Puno & Lake Titicaca, Cusco & Machu Picchu, Puerto Maldonado (Amazon)\r\n','','','',418,0,0,NULL,NULL,NULL),(1007,1,'Hi Mari,','<p>Thank you Peru For Less for a wonderful trip! Since I travel with my daughter, safety is a big issue for me, and we couldn\'t feel safer knowing that everything had been taken care of to the last detail, including timely schedules, hotel location, excellent transportation, and a friendly guide on every place to explain and suggest places to visit and/or eat. Really, you just have to relax and enjoy!  </p>\r\n\r\n<p>Check out Liliaâ??s review on TripAdvisor. </p>\r\n','Lilia (Mexico)<br/>\r\nTraveled to: Puerto Maldonado, Cusco & Machu Picchu\r\n','','','',418,0,0,NULL,NULL,NULL),(1008,1,'Hi Rylee,','<p>The trip to Peru was amazing!! I really enjoyed the Lares Trek and Machu Picchu. My favorite part of the Lares Trek was camping in the small villages along the mountainside and being able to observe the everyday life in the village. The coolest thing by far was reaching the 15,000 feet peak on day 2! I enjoyed the scenery and the views along the way too. Our guide, Bryan, was great. He was very knowledgeable about Inca history, traditions and culture. Our cook and horseman were great too. The food was really tasty and I was happy to see how well the cook was able to accommodate my vegetarian diet. They even made us a cake on the last day, which was really nice.</p>\r\n \r\n<p>Machu Picchu was unbelievable! I am glad we arrived early before it got crowded. Bryan did a great job of giving us a tour and letting us explore. Most importantly, we were able to meet up with our friends on the Inca Trail as planned.</p>\r\n \r\n<p>Thank you so much for helping us plan our trip to Peru and making it an unforgettable experience!! I will be sure to share my positive experience with Peru for Less on Trip Advisor.</p>\r\n \r\nThank you Rylee!\r\n','Millie (USA)<br/>\r\nTraveled to: Lares trek & Inca Trail to Machu Picchu\r\n','','','',418,0,0,NULL,NULL,NULL),(1009,1,'Hi Matt,','<p>We are home, safe and happy (and tired). The short answer is we were thrilled with Peru For Less and amazed at how every connection went like clockwork. On our last day for the drive from our hotel to the Cusco airport, the representative was ON TIME, but because so many had been early (as were we), it actually felt as if she were late! </p>\r\n \r\n<p>All in all, if and when we want to return to Latin America for a vacation, we would start with Latin America for Less to see if you cover our intended destination. </p>\r\n \r\n<p>So, thank you, thank you, thank you.  Muchass gracias for an unforgettable Peru trip. </p>\r\n','Sarah (USA)<br/>\r\nTraveled to: Arequipa, Colca Canyon, Puno, Cusco & Machu Picchu\r\n','','','',418,0,0,NULL,NULL,NULL),(1010,1,'Hi Jennie,','<p>Peru For Less has delivered a truly unique experience for me as per my requests. The service and attention to detail was faultless. </p>\r\n\r\n<p>The fact I was given free travel insurance and that the cost of the newly introduced ticket to Huayna Picchu plus an unexplained conversion charge was absorbed by the company makes it even more remarkable. I have already recommended the company to other travelers I met and would not hesitate to do so again. Their prices are also very competitive compared to the same trip booked from the UK. </p>\r\n','Linda (West Sussex, UK)<br/>\r\nTraveled to: Lima, Cusco, Machu Picchu, Puno, Colca Canyon, Arequipa, Nazca & Paracas\r\n','','','',418,0,0,NULL,NULL,NULL),(1011,1,'Hello Kelly,','<p>Just a quick note to say thank you for the wonderful vacation/adventure. The entire trip went flawlessly and I felt it was the dream vacation right off the National Geographic channel that I had always hoped to take. I was absolutely delighted with how smooth everything went with regard to the itinerary and truly enjoyed all the \"highlights\" of Peru. The schedule was packed full and kept me continually intrigued throughout the entire journey. </p>\r\n\r\n<p>Thank you again and all the best, </p>\r\n','Orest (USA)<br/>\r\nTraveled to: Lima, Paracas, Arequipa, Colca Canyon, Puno, Cusco, Sacred Valley, Machu Picchu & Puerto Maldonado\r\n','','','',418,0,0,NULL,NULL,NULL),(1012,1,'Hi Mari,','<p>Our recent trip to Peru would definitely not have been as great without Peru For Less (PFL). Arriving in a city and not knowing the lay of the land, not knowing where your hotel is or how to get there can be really frustrating. But with Peru For Less, we were met on time, every time, by a local host and our driver who made the transitions incredibly smooth. Besides, it\'s pretty neat to get off the plane and have someone holding a welcome sign with your name on it. </p>\r\n\r\n<p>They also provide knowledgeable and interesting guides who shared not only copious information but also the spirit of their homeland. Our agent, Mari-Ellena was great. Anytime we needed to alter our itinerary or ask a question, Peru For Less was just a quick phone call away at any time. They are all fun people to work with. We loved our trip and are grateful for Peru For Less expert assistance. </p>\r\n\r\n<p>Check out Hollyâ??s review on TripAdvisor. </p>\r\n','Holly (California, USA)<br/>\r\nTraveled to: Lima, Arequipa, Puno, Cusco, Machu Picchu & Puerto Maldonado\r\n','','','',418,0,0,NULL,NULL,NULL),(1013,1,'Hi Mari,','<p>Machu Picchu is an experience that I never thought I would actually have. It took my breath away and brought tears to my eyes. And that\'s not from the climbing either!!! It\'s so awesome. </p>\r\n\r\n<p>Our 17-day Peru adventure would have been very perplexing if it were not for the expert planning of Peru For Less. Our lodging, transportation, transfers, guides, drivers, and all matters were handled seamlessly by Peru ForLess. I have no idea how we could have done it without them. You determine your trip, type of hotel, itinerary, abilities, etc, and they do the hard part of booking and scheduling. And the cost seems to be very reasonable too. </p>\r\n\r\n<p>In Aguas Calientes, we stayed at the Andina Luxury Hotel overlooking the Urabamba River. The rushing river was a spectacular counterpoint to the meditative stillness of Machu Pittchu. Definitely request a river room. Peru For Less had already done this for us. </p>\r\n\r\n<p>I agree with another reviewer that Machu Picchu is a lovely place to end your vacation. Anything else pales by comparison. As far as other places, we really enjoyed Cusco. </p>\r\n\r\n<p>Check out Candiceâ??s review on TripAdvisor. </p>\r\n','Candice (California, USA)<br/>\r\nTraveled to: Lima, Arequipa, Puno, Cusco, Machu Picchu & Puerto Maldonado\r\n','','','',418,0,0,NULL,NULL,NULL),(1014,1,'Hi Jennie,','<p>I was very happy about 99% of the trip. Everything worked VERY well with hotels, rendez-vous, connections, travel, tickets, etc. I am actually amazed that it worked as well as it did, considering all the different people involved. Timing was perfect with all the parts of our trip and the guides were very good, ALL the ones we had. </p>\r\n\r\n<p>I will recommend you to other travelers for sure. Hotels were of nice standard as well by the way. </p>\r\n\r\n<p>All the best and maybe we\'ll connect again sometime, because I\'ll definitely come back. </p>\r\n','Joakim (New York, USA)<br/>\r\nTraveled to : Lima, Cusco, Sacred Valley & Machu Picchu\r\n','','','',418,0,0,NULL,NULL,NULL),(1015,1,'Hi Staci, ','<p>We had a great time.  All the guides were great and always on time.  No major hiccups with the flights either.  We never had a problem with any part of the organized tours.  </p>\r\n\r\n<p>The hotels were clean and actually more than we expected. We had a great time, saw a lot and met a lot of nice people.  </p>\r\n\r\n<p>Thanks for all your hard work. We have already recommended people to your site. </p>\r\n','Alvina (USA)<br/>\r\nTraveled to: Lima, Arequipa, Colca Caynon, Cusco, Machu Picchu & Puerto Maldonado\r\n','','','',418,0,0,NULL,NULL,NULL),(1016,1,'Dear Aleks, ','<p>1) Thank you, Aleks, for all of your help in organizing the trip. Your flexibility and sometimes the last minute re-scheduling were terrific and much appreciated.  For example, Edgar was a gift!  We had most interesting discussions all day long!  The climb to Huayna Picchu will stay forever in our memory and it may not have happened without the last moment tickets which you sent to us! </p>\r\n\r\n<p>2)  All the guides we had were very knowledgeable and extremely enthusiastic. They made our experience very personal, we never felt forgotten in a group. The largest group we had had only seven people (with three of us included).  </p>\r\n\r\n<p>3)  Food was good everywhere we went. Your recommendation, Tanto, put us on a good path. We ate a lot, Peruvian specialties whenever possible, but we actually lost weight (due to lots of walking and lots of Quinoa, a very healthy grain). Not bad. </p>\r\n\r\n<p>4)  All hotels were terrific (with rivers of coca tea), clean and quiet. Michael was particularly happy with the Casa de San Blas in Cusco. His other impressions of the last week are still unknown to us but in general he was - just like us - very positively impressed with the entire trip. The Colca lodge, with hot springs, was a pleasant surprise for us. It has the atmosphere of a ski lodge with the smell of wood burning fireplaces, but - of course, there is no snow. We truly enjoyed the hot springs till late in the night.  </p>\r\n\r\n<p>5)  We were lucky with the weather, and we saw almost all what was planned and then some.  Unfortunately we did not see condors, but we saw some impressive hawks and eagles. The rain forest was full of life, and the programs for visitors had a rich agenda - with bird watching starting at 5 am, and evening walks after dinner, with a flush light. Beautiful.  </p>\r\n\r\n<p>6)  In general we feel stronger and better after the trip than we felt prior to the trip. So much for high altitude and rigorous climbing! It was all good exercise.  </p>\r\n\r\n<p>Thank you, Aleks, for this marvelous experience! You did great!  </p>\r\n\r\n<p>Check out Vlastaâ??s review on TripAdvisor. </p>\r\n','Vlasta (Illinois, USA)<br/>\r\nTraveled to: Cusco, Lima, Arequipa & Puerto Maldonado (Amazon)\r\n','','','',418,0,0,NULL,NULL,NULL),(1017,1,'Hi Jennie, ','<p>We enjoyed our trip very much and were impressed with the way it was structured by your company. All of our transfers were friendly and on time and made getting around very easy. My favorite part, and I think I speak for everyone, was definitely the Inca Trail. It was difficult but exactly what we were hoping for. The views were breathtaking and we were the only hikers in our group which made for a much more personalized experience. Evan and I really enjoyed Cuzco. Our hotel (San Blas) was very nice and the city was just a fun time day or night. We enjoyed just about everything and plan to return some day. </p>','Bryan (New Jersey, USA)<br/>\r\nTraveled to: Cusco, Inca Trail, Puerto Maldonado, Puno, Colca Canyon, Arequipa & Paracas\r\n','','','',418,0,0,NULL,NULL,NULL),(1018,1,'Hi Silvana,','<p>I just want to thank you for the amazing trip! We had so much fun!!! Everything was great, the food, the lodge, the activities, the guide, etc. </p>\r\n\r\n<p>We will remember our vacation at the Refugio aAazonas lodge. By the way thank you for the book on Peru! We saw lots of animals too (monkeys, snake, capybaras, caimans, macaws, parrots, hoatzin and I could go on and on). We even swam in the Tambopata River with the guide. I enjoyed the boat ride. </p>\r\n\r\n<p>I came home with great memories! Peru is a wonderful country with lots of things to see! Thank you so much for the great experience, everything went well. </p>\r\n \r\n<p>Sincerely, </p>\r\n','JaÃ«le (Canada)\r\nTraveled to: Puerto Maldonado (Amazon)\r\n','','','',418,0,0,NULL,NULL,NULL),(1019,1,'Hi Matt,','<p>The trip was amazing. Of course, the altitude sickness did get to me but it wasn\'t anything major. All the pick-ups and tours went as planned. The hotel was very clean and the staff very friendly. The itinerary was clear and easy to follow. Machu Picchu was the highlight but unfortunately I got sick from something I ate however I still made the best of it. </p>','Carmen (USA)<br/>\r\nTraveled to : Cusco, Sacred Valley & Machu Picchu\r\n','','','',418,0,0,NULL,NULL,NULL),(1020,1,'Hello Rylee,','<p>I just wanted to let you know we arrived safe and sound back in Canada after our 17-day adventure in Peru. My, what a magnificent country! We were truly amazed by all that we saw and did during our vacation. Everything went smooth as silk. </p>\r\n\r\n<p>We loved all our guides who always made us feel safe and well looked after. They were very informative,spoke english well and always made sure we were comfortable when tackling any adventure we were taking on. They also went out of their way to take us to a bank or markets or a certain restaurant to try the local food. </p>\r\n\r\n<p>We were always impressed with every hotel that we stayed at. All were unique in their own way and all with great locations. My favourite was in Ollantaytambo. I just loved our place there and loved the Sacred Valley. As far as Machu Picchu is concerned, nothing can prepare you for the true greatness and wonder of this place. It truly brought me to tears. Pictures just cannot do it justice nor can they evoke the spirituality felt when walking amongst the ruins. This is truly I think the worldâ??s greatest wonder. </p>\r\n\r\n<p>We have been very fortunate to have visited Peru and have seen a lot of the great wonders it has to offer and there is so much more! We thank you for looking after us and giving us a lifetime of wonderful memories. We would highly recommend Peru For Less to anyone planning a trip to this magnificent part of the world!             </p>                                             \r\n','Andrew and Deborah (Ontario, Canada)<br/>\r\nTraveled to: Lima, Paracas, Nazca, Arequipa, Colca, Puno, Cusco, Sacred Valley & Machu Picchu\r\n','','','',418,0,0,NULL,NULL,NULL),(1185,1,'Dear Silvana and Latin America For Less,','<p>Our trip to Peru was fabulous! Everyone we worked with were true professionals. They promptly answered questions and gave us \'the straight answer\'. The hotels selected by Latin America For Less were excellent! Everyone we encountered was friendly, courteous, and service-oriented. We never worried about getting from Point A to Point B since your firm took care of all our transportation needs.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>We both learned so much on the trip from the tours that were arranged and got to have many new experiences. Peru is a beautiful country that should be on everyone\'s must-see list. Equally impressive is the rich culture and history exemplified around every corner. Cusco, The Sacred Valley, and of course Machu Picchu were highlights along with the excellent Peruvian/Andean cuisine.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>We won\'t hesitate to use your services again the next time we plan to visit South America.</p>\r\n','David (IL, USA)<br/>\r\nTraveled to: Cusco, Sacred Valley, & Machu Picchu\r\n\r\n','','','',100027,0,0,NULL,'2014-09-10 22:55:10',NULL),(1186,1,'Hi Silvana,','<p>We made it safely home with great memories of an unforgettable Peru holiday.  We were both extremely happy with all the transfers and the assistance from Peru For Less which went beyond our expectations (especially the call to the hotel on Friday to ask if I needed any assistance). </p>\r\n\r\n<p>All of the hotels exceeded my expectations and were fabulous.  I think the biggest blessings were Colca Lodge and the wonderful hot springs and the Sol de Oro was a great treat after the Amazon.  I was especially grateful to have had the late check out.  But all the hotels were beautiful. </p>\r\n\r\n<p>The biggest highlights were the people we met along the way which added to an incredible experience. </p>\r\n\r\n<p>We were very impressed with Giardino - Beatrice met us in Arequipa and did the tour right away rather than coming back for us later.  This gave us time afterwards to go for a nice lunch and then to explore Santa Catalina.  For the Colca Canyon tour, Erika was a lot of fun and our driver Julio had a great sense of humor. </p>\r\n\r\n<p>In Cusco, Jordan gave us a lot of good advice, including some advice on shopping for Michelle\'s teenage sons (and her sons are thrilled with the pants she brought back for them). </p>\r\n\r\n<p>Peru for Less was great.  Our transfer drivers were always kind enough to stop somewhere so we could get water for our rooms which helped a lot. </p>\r\n\r\n<p>I would/will recommend your company, and you, to anyone considering South America as a holiday destination. </p>\r\n\r\n<p>Again, thank you for helping to make a dream come true for us.  We had a great time together and with all the people we met. </p>\r\n\r\n<p>Best regards,</p>\r\n','Annette (Grand Cayman) Traveled to: Lima, Paracas & Nazca, Arequipa & Colca Canyon, Cusco & Machu Picchu, Puno, & Amazon','','','',100028,0,0,NULL,'2014-09-10 22:55:10',NULL),(1187,1,'Hi Kelly,','<p>My friend and I enjoyed a great, stress-free tour of the Incan heartland of Cusco, Sacred Valley and Machu Picchu. The arrangements for transfers, hotels and tours were seamless and we were greeted at each site. </p>\r\n \r\n<p>The restaurant and bar suggestion we got in Cusco was very useful. Our guides were very knowledgeable, explaining the culture, history and engineering behind everything we saw.</p>\r\n \r\n<p>Thank you for organizing our tour to fit the small amount of time we had, on a very short notice too. We will definitely recommend Peru For Less to our friends who are considering heading to South America in the future.</p>\r\n','Collin & Pieter (Toronto & Ontario, Canada)<br/>\r\nTraveled to: Cusco, Sacred Valley & Machu Picchu\r\n','','','',100029,0,0,NULL,'2014-09-10 22:55:10',NULL),(1188,1,'Hi Kelly:','<p>Our Peru trip was absolutely fantastic.  And you guys took a lot of stress out of planning the trip for us.  We really had a memorable time in Cusco, on the Inca Trail, in sacred valley and of course, at Machu Picchu. </p>\r\n\r\n<p>Peru for Less\'s contact in Cusco, Hannah, was very sweet.  It helped to have English speaking guides everywhere.  Especially Jose, our Inca Trail and Machu Picchu guide, was extremely helpful and considerate.  Our visit to the sacred valley towns of PÃ­sac and Ollantaytambo were excellent.  Casa Andina Private Collection and Andean Wings were very clean, comfortable and unique hotels in Cusco.  I can recommend those places to anyone.  </p>\r\n','Sharad Maheshwari (Yorktown, VA)<br/>\r\nTraveled to: Cusco, 2-day Inca Trail to Machu Picchu\r\n','','','',100030,0,0,NULL,'2014-09-10 22:55:10',NULL),(1247,1,'Dear Peru for Less,','<p>Our trip was wonderful - we did not want to leave. Our biggest regret \r\nwas not planning more time! We could have stayed on the beaches of Rio \r\nlonger and we fell in love with the smiling faces and hospitality in \r\nPeru. Machu Picchu was incredible and fulfilled a dream of \r\nours. You were amazing and we can\'t thank you enough for your \r\nservices.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Everything went along without a hitch; the whole process was smooth \r\nfrom start to finish. We also appreciated all of your restaurant \r\nrecommendations and travel guides. We had a great time sampling them!</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Thank you, thank you thank you!</p>','Sincerely,\r\nArie and Barbara Austin','','','',420,0,0,NULL,NULL,NULL),(1248,1,'Hi Matt,','<p>We are back at home now and settled back into regular life once again after our wonderful trip to Peru.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Our trip with Peru for Less was excellent. We had a couple of hiccups but nothing serious and one big disappointment which had nothing to do with your company.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Your detailed schedule that you prepared for us was amazing and we so appreciated knowing that no matter where we went there was someone to pick us up and take us safely to our next destination.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>The Casa Andina Private Collection hotel in Miraflores is outstanding and we highly recommend it as a place to stay. Also, the Casa Andina in the Sacred Valley was another very special and outstanding hotel.  The gal who met us in Cusco, Katti, was extremely pleasant \r\nand thorough going through our tour package and answering all our questions. Our guide for the Sacred Valley, Jose, was charming and funny and we very much enjoyed our day with him seeing Pisac and Ollantaytambo. Fabricio in Machu Picchu was passionate and knowledgeable which made for a wonderful morning with him.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>We would have no hesitation in recommending Peru for Less to anyone we know wanting to travel to Peru.  Your attention to detail and the precision with which everything happened was amazing. At no time were we looking around for someone to greet us, everyone was always there on time or early. It was a pleasure to deal with you during the planning stage and all in all it was a wonderful adventure in Peru.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Many thanks to you and your entire team for an amazing trip to Peru!!</p>','Blair and Susan Kerr\r\n','','','',420,0,0,NULL,NULL,NULL),(1249,1,'Bonjour Adrienne,','<p>I felt very anxious to travel alone but the whole trip preparation you made with a lot of professionalism and you exceeded my expectations with the additional booking of flights from Sao Paolo. You were really pro-active and quick answering my emails. </p>\r\n<p>Once actually there, there was no disappointment: the quality of service booked for hotel and tours was excellent.</p>\r\n  \r\n<p>Andean Wonders Hotel had amazing staff, above all when I started to feel mountain sickness. They took really good care \r\nof me which is really important when you are travelling alone.  </p>\r\n<p>The Casa Andina Sacred Valley has an amazing location, and I had a good room. </p>\r\n  \r\n<p>The Vistadome train on the way back from Machu Picchu was a lot of fun with entertainment and a fashion show in the carriage. They also provided a nice cheese plate served on a white napkin. Top service in first class!</p>\r\n  \r\n<p>Bravo and keep on doing a good job!</p>\r\n','Carole Lutaud','','','',420,0,0,NULL,NULL,NULL),(1250,1,'Hi Kristina,','<p>Our trip was awesome.  We experienced a lot - met a lot of nice \r\npeople, saw a lot of interesting things, had a lot of fun... </p>\r\n\r\n<p>With respect to our amenities and getting from one place to the next, for the most part, things worked out well. The Inca Trail company Wayki was excellent. Roy, our guide, was always friendly and made sure we had everything we needed. The meals they provided us were delicious, better that I was expecting. All the porters did an incredible job hauling our stuff from one campsite to the next. They pack all the stuff up after we start trekking and pass us on the trail.. lol...</p>\r\n\r\n<p>The Titicaca tour was my favorite tour. It allowed us to interact with the locals and our tour guide provided us with information on how the locals live and survive, which I found interesting. </p>\r\n\r\n<p>Thanks again, Kristina, for all the work you did arranging this trip for us. Speaking for myself and hopefully for Alice, it was a lot of fun.</p>\r\n','Dave Berm','','','',420,0,0,NULL,NULL,NULL);
/*!40000 ALTER TABLE `testimonies` ENABLE KEYS */;
